In bhautikee, golakaar gati is a gati of an object along the circumference of a circle or rotation along a circular path.
It can be uniform, with constant angular rate of roteshan ( or nirantar gati ), or non-uniform saath a badalanaa rate of rotation.
The rotation around a phixd aksh of a three-dimensional deh involves golakaar motion of its parts.
The equations of motion describe the gati of the bich of dravyaman of a deh.
Examples of circular gati shaamil : an kritrim upgrah orbiting the dharti at nirantar oonchaai, a stone jisase is tied to a rassi or is hone swung in vrutt, a car turning through a vakr in a res track, an electron moving perpendicular to a uniform magnetic field, and a gear turning inside a mechanism.
Since the object 's velocity vector is constantly badalanaa disha, the chalati object is undergoing twaran by a abhikendriya force in the direction of the center of rotation.
Without this acceleration, the object hota move in a sidhaa lakeer, according to newton 's kanoon of motion.

Variable saarvbhaumik jivan bime ( praayah shortened to vul ) is a prakaar of jivan bime ki builds a cash value.
In a VUL, the nakadi maan can be invested in a chaudee kismein of pruthak khate, samaan to paraspar funds, and the choice of which of the available separate accounts to use is entirely up to the contract owner.
The 'variable ' component in the name refers to is kshamta to invest in pruthak khate jinaki maan vary—they vary because they are invested in stock and/or bond markets.
The 'universal ' ghatak in the naam refers to the lacheelaapan the maalik rai in bananaa premium payments.
The premiums can vary from nothing in a given month up to maximums paribhaashit by the aatanrik aay code liye jivan insurance.
This flexibility is in contrast to whole jivan bime ki rai phixd premium bhugtan ki typically can nahin be chhuti bagaiyr lapsing the niti ( haalanki ek may kasarat an swachaalit premium rin visheshta, or surrender dividends to pay a Whole Life premium ).
Variable universal life is a type of permanent life insurance, because the maut laabh hoga be sashulk if the insured marataa koi samay as long as vahin is sufficient nakadi maan to adaa the laagat of insurance in the policy.
With most if not all VULs, naapsand puure jivan, vahin is no endowment aayu ( the aayu at jisase the nakadi maan barabari the maut laabh amount, which for whole life is typically 100 ).
This is yet another kunjee laabh of vul over Whole Life.
With a typical whole life niti, the maut laabh is simit to the phase raashi nirdisht in the policy, and at endowment age, the face amount is all that is paid out.
yun saath either maut or endowment, the bime company keeps any cash value built up over the years.
However, some participating whole life policies offer riders which specify that any dividends paid on the niti be prayukt to khariden `` sashulk up parivardhan '' to the niti jisase badhayen dono the nakadi maan or the maut laabh over time.
If investments made in the separate accounts out-perform the saamaanya khaataa of the bime company, a ucchtar rate-of-return can occur than the fixed rates-of-return typical for whole life.
The combination over the years of no endowment age, continually increasing maut laabh, or if a unchi rate-of-return is arjeet in the pruthak khate of a vul niti, is could parinaam in ucchtar maan to the maalik or beneficiary than that of a whole life policy with the same amounts of money paid in as premiums.

Purdue University, stith in west lafayette, indiana, is the flagship vishvavidhyalayon of the six-campus Purdue University system.

Purdue enrolls the second largest student body of any university in indiana as khub as the chauthi largest antarrashtriya chaatr janasankhyikee of koi vishvavidhyalayon in the sanyukt States.
Purdue offers both undergraduate and graduate programs in over 211 pramukh kshetron of padhai, or is khub gyaat liye iske pratispardhi abhiyantriki curricula.
The university has also been atyadhik influential in america 's itihaas of vimaanan, having sthapit the pehla college credit offered in udaan training, the first four-year bachelor 's degree in aviation, and the first university airport ( Purdue University Airport ).

In the mid-20th sadi, purdue 's vimaanan kaarykram vistaarit to encompass unnat spaceflight praudyogiki giving vruddhi to purdue 's nickname, Cradle of Astronauts.
twenty-three purdue graduates have gaye on to become astronauts, sahit gas grissom ( ek of the asli paara saat astronauts ), neil armastrang ( the first person to walk on the moon ), and Eugene Cernan ( the most recent person to walk on the moon ).
A sebaceous cyst ( ) is a term ki loosely refers to either epidermoid cysts ( bhi gyaat as epidermal cysts ; l72.0 ) or pillar cysts ( also known as trichilemmal cysts ; L72.1 ).
kuki an epidermoid gaanth originates in the epidermis or a pillar gaanth originates isse bal follicles, by paribhaasha, neither type of cyst is strictly a sebaceous cyst.
The name is regarded as a misnomer as the fatty, shwet, semi-solid saamagree in dono of ye gaanth entities is nahin sebum, lakin keratin.
Furthermore, antargat the sookshmdarshi neither antity contains vasamay glands.
In practice, however, the sharten hai praayah prayukt interchangeably.
`` True '' sebaceous cysts are apekshaakrit viral or hai gyaat as steatocystomas or, if anek, as steatocystoma multiplex.

measuring spoons
In the US and parts of Canada, a tablespoon is the largest prakaar of chamachaa prayukt liye khaane isse a katori.
In the uk, europea or sabase rashtramandal deshon, a tablespoon is a prakaar of large spoon usually used for serving.
In countries where a tablespoon is a serving spoon, the nearest samatuly to the us tablespoon is either the mithai chamachaa or the soup spoon.
A tablespoonful, nominally the capacity of one tablespoon, is commonly prayukt as a maap of awaz in cooking.
It is abbreviated as T, tb, tbs, tbsp, tblsp, or tblspn.
The capacity of ordinary tablespoons is nahin regulated by vidhi or is vishay to considerable vibhinnata.
In the USA one tablespoon ( measurement ikai ) is lagbhag 15 ml ; the kshamta of an vaastavik tablespoon ( dining utensil ) ranges from 7 mL to 14 mL.
In australia ek tablespoon ( maapan unit ) is 20 mL.

A rocket engine, or bas `` prakshepastra '', is a jet ingine ki upyog only stored propellant mass for forming its high speed propulsive jet.
Rocket engines are reaction engines and obtain thrust in accordance saath newton 's teesraa law.
Since they need no external saamagree to rup unke jet, prakshepastra ingine can be prayukt liye spacecraft nodan as khub as sthaliy upyog, such as missiles.
Most prakshepastra ingine hai aatanrik dahan ingine, haalanki non-combusting forms also exist.
Rocket engines as a group have the ucchtam exhaust gatiyaan, hai by dur the lightest, lakin hai the tanik propellant efficient of all types of jet engines.

Cholera is an sankraman in the choti aant caused by the bacterium vibrio cholerae.
The main symptoms hai watery atisar or ulti.
Transmission occurs primarily by drinking water or eating food that has been contaminated by the feces ( barbaad utpaada ) of an sankramit vyakti, sahit ek saath no apparent lakshan.
The severity of the atisar or ulti can sise to rapid nirjaleekaran or electrolyte imbalance, and death in some cases.
The primary upachaar is maukhik punarjaleekaran chikitsa, typically saath maukhik punarjaleekaran samaadhaan, to badalen jal and electrolytes.
If this is not tolerated or karata nahin provide sudhaar tej paryaapt, intravenous fluids can also be used.
Antibacterial drugs are phydemand in those saath kathor beemaari to shorten its duration and severity.
Worldwide, it affects 3–5 lakh logon or kalyankari 100,000–130,000 mauton a year.
Cholera was one of the earliest infections to be padhai by epidemiological methods.
The Picture of Dorian Gray is the only published anokhaa by auskar wild, appearing as the sise story in lippincott 's masik patrika on 20 june 1890, printed as the July 1890 issue of this magazine.
The magazine 's editors feared the story was indecent as supurd, so ve censored roughly 500 shabd, bagaiyr wild 's gyaan, pehle publication.
But bhi saath ki, the story thi still greeted saath aakrosh by angrejon reviewers, kuch of jisko sujhaayaa that Wilde should be prosecuted on moral grounds, leading Wilde to defend the novel aggressively in letters to the British press.
Wilde later revised the story liye kitaab prakaashan, bananaa substantial alterations, hataanaa vivaadaaspad passages, adding new chapters and including an aphoristic Preface which has since become famous in its own right.
The amended sanskaran thi prakashit by ward, taala and Company in April 1891.
Some scholars believe ki wild hota aaj have chaahi us to padhaa the sanskaran he originally submitted to Lippincott 's.
The novel tells of a young man named dorian dhoosar, the vishay of a painting by kalakaar besil Hallward.
Basil is impressed by Dorian 's beauty and becomes infatuated with him, believing uske saundarya is jimmedaar liye a nai vidhi in uske art.
dorian meets rab henry wotton, a dost of besil 's, or becomes enthralled by Lord Henry 's world view.
espousing a nai hedonism, rab henry suggests the tabhi bate laayak pursuing in life are beauty and fulfilment of the senses.
Realizing that one day his beauty will feekaa, dorian ( whimsically ) expresses a khwaahish to bechein uske aatma to ensure the portret Basil has painted would age rather than he.
Dorian 's wish is fulfilled, and when he subsequently pursues a jivan of vilasita, the portret serves as a samaran of the prabhaav prayek adhinium rai upon uske aatma, saath prayek sin pradarshit as a disfigurement of his form, or through a sign of aging.
The Picture of Dorian Gray is considered a work of clasik gothic fiction saath a damdaar faustian theme.

Bruce Lee ( traditional : 李小龍 ; born Lee Jun-fan ; 27 November 1940 – 20 july 1973 ) thi a chinis amareeki martial kalakaar, karta, martial kala prashikshak, paras, or filmkaar.
The founder of Jeet Kune do, lee thi the bete of cantonese opera star Lee Hoi-Chuen.
He is widely considered by tikaakaron, aalochakon, media or anya martial kalakaaron to be ek of the sabase influential martial kalakaaron of sab samay, or a pop samskruti pratik of the 20th century.
He is often credited saath helping to badalen the rasta asian yahood prastut in American films.

The direction and tone of his films changed and bahekaave martial kala or martial kala films in hong kong or the baaki of the sansar.
He is noted for his roles in five feature-length films : Lo Wei 's The big boss ( 1971 ) or mutthi of furi ( 1972 ) ; rasta of the dragon ( 1972 ), nirdeshit or likhaa by lee ; warner bhaaiyo ' Enter the Dragon ( 1973 ) and The Game of Death ( 1978 ), both directed by Robert Clouse.
Lee became an iconic figure gyaat throughout the sansar, visheshkar among the chinis, as he portrayed Chinese nationalism in his films.
He initially trained in wing chun, lakin baad asweekrut well-defined martial art sheliyaan, favouring bajaay the upyog of takneekon isse vibhinn strot, in the spirit of his personal martial arts philosophy, which he dubbed Jeet Kune Do ( The Way of the Intercepting Fist ).
Lee held dual citizenship of Hong kong or the sanyukt rajya.
He died in kolun tong on 20 july 1973 at aayu 32.
Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease ( COPD ), bhi gyaat as dirghakaalik obstructive fefdon beemaari ( thanda ), dirghakaalik obstructive airway beemaari ( coad ), dirghakaalik airflow limitation ( calories ) or dirghakaalik obstructive respiratory beemaari ( CORD ), is the occurrence of chronic bronchitis or emphysema, a pair of commonly co-existing diseases of the lungs in which the airways narrow over time.
This limits airflow to and from the fefde, causing shortness of saans ( dyspnea ).
in naidanik abhyaas, copd is paribhaashit by iske characteristically kam airflow on lung function tests.
In contrast to asthma, is limitation is poorly reversible or praayah gets progressively worse over time.
COPD is caused by noxious anu or gas, sabase commonly isse tambaaku dhumrapaan, which triggers an abnormal inflammatory response in the lung.
The nidaan of copd requires fefdon falan tests.
Important management ranneeti hai dhumrapaan cessation, vaccinations, punarvaas, or drug therapy ( often using inhalers ).
Some patients go on to aavashyaktaa long-term oxigen chikitsa or fefdon pratyaropan.
vishwavyaapee, copd kramit as the chathe agrani kaaran of death in 1990.
It is projected to become the fourth leading kaaran of maut vishwavyaapee by 2030, due to an badhayen in dhumrapaan daron or janasankhyikee changes in many countries.
COPD is the third leading cause of death in the U.S., and the economic boj of copd in the u.S. in 2007 thi $ 42.6 arab in swasthya parvaah laagat or khoyaa utpaadakta.
annelies `` eni '' maari frank (, ?, ; 12 june 1929early kooch 1945 ) is ek of the most discussed Jewish victims of the Holocaust.
Her diary rai maharoom the aadhaar liye several plays and films.
born in the nagar of francfort am Main in Weimar Germany, she lived most of her life in or near Amsterdam, in the Netherlands.
Born a germany neshnal, frank khoyaa uske naagarikta in 1941.
She gained antarrashtriya kirti maranoparant baad uske diary was published.
It documents her experiences hiding during the germany occupation of the netherlands in sansar yuddh ii.
The frank parivaar sthanantarit isse germany to amsterdam in 1933, the year the Nazis gained control over Germany.
By the shuruuaat of 1940, ve yahood funs in amsterdam by the Nazi occupation of the Netherlands.
As persecutions of the Jewish population increased in July 1942, the parivaar gai into chupaana in the chupa kaksh of eni 's pita, oto frank 's, office building.
After two years, the group was betrayed and transported to visheshgyata camps.
eni frank or uske sistar, margot, yahood aakhirkaar transferred to the Bergen-Belsen concentration camp, where they died of typhus in March 1945.
Otto Frank, the only survivor of the parivaar, laute to amsterdam baad the yuddh to dhundhen ki eni 's diary tha maharoom saved, or uske praytn led to iske prakaashan in 1947.
It was translated from its original dach or pehla prakashit in angrezi in 1952 as the diary of a yang ladki.
It has since been anudit into anek bhashaaen.
the diary, jisase thi die to eni on uske 13th janmdiwas, chronicals her life from 12 June 1942 until 1 August 1944.

Kurt Donald Cobain ( February 20, 1967 – april 5, 1994 ) thi an amareeki sangeetkaar or kalakaar, behtareen gyaat as the sise singer, guitarist or praathmik songwriter of the grunge band Nirvana.
Cobain formed Nirvana with Krist novoselic in aberdeen, washington in 1985 or sthapit it as bhaag of the sietal music jhaanki, having iske debyue album bleech released on the swatantra record label Sub Pop in 1989.
After signing with major label DGC Records, the band found bhedan kamyaabi saath `` khushbu jaise tin spirit `` isse iske duusari album nevermind ( 1991 ).
Following the kamyaabi of nevermind, nirvana thi labeled `` the flagship band '' of peedhee x, or cobain hailed as `` the spokesman of a generation ''.
cobain, however, thi praayah asahaj or kunthit, believing uske sandesh or kalakaari drushti to have maharoom misinterpreted by the public, with his personal issues often subject to media attention.
He challenged Nirvana 's darshak saath iske final studio album in Utero ( 1993 ).
During the last years of his life, Cobain struggled saath heroin vyasan, illness and depression.
He also had difficulty coping with his fame and public image, and the professional and lifelong nijee pressures surrounding khud or uske bivi, sangeetkaar courtney Love.
On April 8, 1994, Cobain was found dead at his home in sietal, the shikaar of kayaa thi officially shasit a aatmahatya by a self-inflicted shotgun wound to the head.

Deepwater khudaai is the prakram of aayal or gas khoji and production in depths of more than 500 feet.
By this definition, vahin hai lagbhag 600 deepwater kuen in the gulf of mexico.
It has been economically infeasible for many saalo, lakin saath uthati aayal keemten, adhik companiyaan hai nivesh in is area.
Major companies working in is sector shaamil diamond offshore, TransOcean, and Baker Hughes.
There are basically two kinds of mobile deepwater khudaai rigs : semi-submersible khudaai rigs and drillships.
Drilling can also be performed from a fixed-position sansthapana aise as a floating spar ( platform ) or tension-leg platform.
haal udyog vishleshan rai anumaanit ki the kul vyay in the vaishvik deepwater infrastructure market will reach $ 145bn in 2011.
“Not all oil is accessible on jameen or in shallow water.
You can find some oil deposits buried deep under the ocean floor.”... Using sonic upkaran, aayal companiyaan determine the khudaai site sabase sambhavit to produce oil.
Then they use a mobile offshore khudaai ikai ( modu ) to khudaai the initial well.
Some units are converted into utpaadan rigs, arth ve switch isse khudaai liye oil to capturing oil once it 's found.
Most of the time, the oil company will replace the MODU with a more permanent aayal utpaadan rig to capchar oil.”... the modu 's job is to drill bas into the samandar 's manzil to dhundhen aayal jamaa.
The part of the drill that extends neeche the deck or through the jal is pukaara the riser.
The riser allows for drilling fluids to move between the manzil or the rig.
Engineers lower a drill string -- a shrenee of pipe designed to drill bas to the aayal jamaa -- through the riser.”
“The expansion of deepwater khudaai is happening despite durghatnaon in offshore fields... ”
In 2010 a large explosion occurred hatya 11 majdoor or spilling lakho of galen of aayal into the Gulf of Mexico while a BP oil rig was drilling in deep waters.
“... Despite the risks, the deepwater drilling trend is spreading in the bumadhyasagariya or band the coast of east africa baad a string of vishaal discoveries of natural gas.”
“The reason for the resumption of such drilling, vishleshak kah, is continuing unchi maang liye urja worldwide.”
America needs the aayal so it is lagbhag jaruri to phase the unchi risks ki aaiye saath deepwater khudaai in order for Americans to continue to carry on their everyday lives.
“The Energy Department recently projected that gulf aayal utpaadan hota vistaar isse iske 2011 str of 1.3 lakh barrels a din, still nearly a quarter of kul gharelu production, to 2 million barrels a day by 2020.”
deepwater khudaai affects the paryaavaran in both negative and positive ways.
Although Deepwater drilling rarely causes oil spills it is still a hazardous sambhavit nishkarsh.
Oil spills result in oil sinking to the neeche of the samandar smothering sanyantr jivan leaving machhlee bagaiyr khaanaa or shelter to survive.
On the other hand deepwater khudaai prabhaav the environment in a positive ways too.
In time once the deepwater oil khub is nahin in upyog anymore paudhe hoga grow on or around the khub bananaa a gupha or cavern like shelter ideal for animals to thrive in.
deepwater khudaai bhi lets us dekhie the gaharaaiyon of the ocean floor that are hardly ever seen.
”Cameras on rovers at the bottom of the kuen ricard footage or lo photo of viral machhlee ki hai in vahin prakritik awaas, giving vaigyanik a dekh at pashu ve rarely seen” ( Chevron Corporation ). ''

Beginning his musical career in the swing era with Harry james or tommy dorsey, sinatra mila unprecedented kamyaabi as a solo kalakaar isse the jaldi to mid-1940s baad being signed to Columbia Records in 1943.

uske peshewar kariyar tha stalled by the 1950s, lakin it thi punarjanm in 1953 baad he jiti the academy puraskaar for Best Supporting Actor for his performance in From Here to Eternity.

Sinatra left Capitol to found his own record label, Reprise Records in 1961 ( finding success with albums such as Ring-a-Ding-Ding !, Sinatra at the Sands and Francis Albert sinatra & antonio carlos jobim ), toured internationally, thi a founding sadsy of the chuha pack or fraternized saath hastiyaan or kootneetigyon, sahit jon F. kennedy.
Sinatra turned 50 in 1965, recorded the retrospective sitambar of my saalo, strecchar in the emi -winning television khaas frank sinatra : a man or uske music, and scored hits with `` Strangers in the Night `` and `` My Way ``.

Using his Las Vegas shows as a home base, he toured dono bheetar the sanyukt rajya or internationally, jabatak a choti samay pehle his death in 1998.
Sinatra also forged a atyadhik kaamyaab kariyar as a filmi actor.

A fern is any one or more of a group of about 12,000 prajati of paudhe belonging to the vanaspati samooh known as Pteridophyta.
Unlike mosses, they have xylem and floem ( bananaa unhen vascular plants ).
They have stems, pattey, or jaden jaise anya vascular plants.
Ferns reproduce via bijaanuon or have neither beej nor flowers.
By far the largest group of ferns is the leptosporangiate ferns, lakin ferns as paribhaashit yahan ( bhi pukaara monilophytes ) shaamil horsetails, whisk ferns, marattioid ferns, and ophioglossoid ferns.
The term pteridophyte bhi refers to ferns or a few anya bijrahit vascular paudhe ( dekhie vargeekaran section below ).
Ferns first appear in the fossil record 360 million saalo pehle in the carboniferous lakin anek of the vartmaan pariwaron or prajati kiya nahin appear jabatak roughly 145 lakh saalo pehle in the jaldi cretaceous ( baad flowering paudhe came to dominate many environments ).
Ferns are not of major economic importance, but some are grown or gathered for food, as shobhyman paudhe, liye remediating contaminated soils, or have maharoom the vishay of shodh liye unke kshamta to hataayen kuch rasinic pradooshak isse the air.
kuch hai significant weeds.
They also play a role in mythology, ayurvigyaan, or art.
Flat roofs in israel
Flat chat in los angeles
A chapata chat is a prakaar of covering for a building.
In contrast to the more sloped rup of chat, a chapata chat is aadaa or nearly horizontal.
The slope of a roof is properly known as its pitch : Roofs which are nearly flat are gyaat as low-pitch roofs ( as the kone of dhalaan increases, so the pitch is said to increase ).
Any sheet of saamagree prayukt to cover a chapata or low-pitched chat is praayah gyaat as a jhilli or the praathmik purpose of ye jhilliyon is to waterproof the roof area.
Materials that cover flat roofs typically allow the jal to chalaaen band isse a patala inclination or camber into a gutter system.
Water from some flat roofs such as on garden sheds sometimes bahati freely band the kinare of a chat, haalanki gutter pranaaliyon hai of advantage in keeping both walls and foundations dry.
Gutters on smaller roofs often lead jal sidhe onto the maidan, or better, into a specially made soakaway.
Gutters on larger roofs praayah sise jal into the rainwater naale pranali of any built up area.
Occasionally flat roofs though are designed to collect water in a pool, praayah liye aesthetic uddeshy, or liye rainwater buffering.
Flat roofs exist all over the sansar or prayek kshetrafal rai iske apana parampara or variyata liye saamagree used.
In warmer climes where rainfall is kam or jamane is asambhavit to occur, anek chapata roofs hai bas nirmit of chinai or kancreet or is is shubh at keeping out the ooshmaa of the sun and cheap and easy to build where timber is not readily available.
In areas where the roof could become saturated by rain and leak, or where water soaked into the brickwork could fries to barf or yun sise to 'blowing ' ( todakar up of the mortar/brickwork/concrete by the expansion of ice as it forms ) these roofs are not suitable.
traditionally sabase chapata roofs in the pashchimi sansar mek upyog of tarkol or adhik usually tar paper applied over roof decking to keep a building watertight.
The tar or tarpaper is in turn covered in gravel to keep the sun 's heat, UV kirane or mausam band it or helps protect it isse cracking or blistering and degradation.
Roof alankaar is praayah of plaiwood, chipboard or osb falak ( osb = unmukh strand falak, bhi gyaat as Sterling board ) of around 18mm thickness.
The tar coating is applied in one or more coats as a hot liquid, heated in a tar kettle, or as chaadaren of tarkol impregnated 'paper ' chipke bas or sealed saath at joints by hot tarkol - ekbar it rai cooled, the gravel is spread evenly over it.
A main reason for failure of these traditional roofs is ignorance or lack of maintenance where people or kaarykram kaaran the bajri to be sthanantarit or removed isse the tarkol or tarpaper waterproofing, yun exposing it to mausam or surya whereupon cracking or blistering occurs over time and eventually water gets in.
Tarpaper is praayah a 'paper ' or fibre saamagree soaked or impregnated in tar.
As gravel can not protect tarpaper surfaces where they rise vertically from the roof such as on parapet walls or upstands, tarpaper visangatiyaan hai utpaadit saath thik bajri lagu to the hot tarkol dauraan the prakram of manufacture aise ki a permanent layer of gravel is stuck to it in order to give it ongoing protection.
tarpapers vary in visheshta as karata the kaarigari or prashikshan of those applying it to produce more or less successful results.
In kuch sookshm climates or chhaayankit kshetron ye balki 'basic ' tarpaper roofs can pichhlaa khub in sambandh to the laagat of saamagree purchase and cost of laying them, however the cost of modern membranes such as EPDM has come down over recent years to make them more and more affordable.
There are now adhik firms supplying aadhunik vikalp or vahin is generally a growing awareness of their performance and availability.
If a leak does occur on a chapata chat tab kshati praayah goes unnoticed liye long avadhi of samay dauraan jisase jal penetrates and soaks the decking and any insulation and/or structure beneath it.
This can lead to mahangi kshati isse the durgandh jisase praayah develops or if baayein can weaken the roof structure.
There are also various swasthya risks to logon or pashu shwaas the saanche bijaanuon : the severity of this health risk remains a debated point.
One problem with maintaining flat roofs is that if water does ghus the avrodh covering ( be it paramparaagat or a aadhunik jhilli ) it can safar a long rasta pehle causing visible damage or leaking into a building where it can be seen.
Thus it is not easy to see where it is tapakati in anukram to marammat it.
Once underlying roof decking is soaked it often sags causing a further sangrahan or puddling of jal in ki kshetrafal or the problem worsens.
A CD-ROM ( ) is a pre-pressed compact discs which contains data.
The name is an echronim jisase stand liye `` compact discs read-only memory ``.
Computers can read cd-roms, lakin can nahin likhen on them.
CD-ROMs are popularly used to vitarit computer tantra, sahit video khel or multimedia anuprayog, haalanki any data can be stored ( up to the capacity limit of a disc ).
Some CDs, called enhanced CDs, hold both computer data and audio with the latter capable of being played on a CD player, jabaki aankada ( aise as tantra or digital video ) is tabhi usable on a computer ( aise as iesao 9660 swaroop pc CD-ROMs ).
The Yellow Book is the takneekee maanak ki defines the swaroop of cd-roms.
ek of a niyat of color-bound kitabe ki contain the takneekee visheshtaayen liye sab cd swarup, the pilaa kitaab, nirmit by Sony and Philips, was the first extension of Compact Disc Digital Audio.
It adapted the swaroop to tham koi rup of data.
Joanne `` Jo '' Rowling ( ), ( born 31 July 1965 ), kalam naam J. K. rolling, is a angrejon upanyaaskaar, behtareen gyaat as the lekhak of the harry kumhaar fantasy series.
The kumhaar kitabe have gained vishwavyaapee dhyaan, jiti anek puraskaar, or sold more than 400 million copies.
They have become the best-selling kitaab shrenee in itihaas, or maharoom the aadhaar liye a shrenee of films which has become the highest-grossing film series in history.
Rowling had overall approval on the script as khub as maintaining rachanaatmak control by sevarat as a producer on the final instalment.
Born in Yate, Gloucestershire, Rowling was working as a shodhakarta or dubhashiya sachiv liye maafi antarrashtriya jab wo conceived the vichaar liye the harry kumhaar shrenee on a delayed train from Manchester to London in 1990.
The seven-year period that followed entailed the death of her mother, divorce from her first husband and poverty jabatak rolling samaapt the pehla anokhaa in the shrenee, harry kumhaar or the paras 's stone ( 1997 ).
Rowling subsequently prakashit 6 sequels—the pichhlaa, harry kumhaar or the deathly hallows ( 2007 ) —as khub as 3 supplements to the series.
In 2012, Rowling parted with her agency and resumed likhane in the rup of a tragicomedy anokhaa aimed at vayask readership, hakdaar the Casual Vacancy.
Rowling has said she is currently working on two books—one aimed for adults, the other for children younger than the harry kumhaar darshak, or wo expects the latter to be published first.
Rowling has led a `` rags to riches `` jivan story, in jisase wo progressed isse jeena on rajya laabh to multi-millionaire status within five years.
She is the United Kingdom 's best-selling lekhak chunki record began, saath bikri in excess of £238m.
The 2008 Sunday Times samrudh suchi anumaanit rolling 's saubhaahgya at £560 lakh ( $ 798 lakh ), ranking uske as the twelfth richest woman in the United Kingdom.
Forbes ranked Rowling as the forty-eighth sabase shaktishaalee hasti of 2007, or samay patrika namit uske as a runner-up liye iske 2007 vyakti of the saal, noting the social, moral, and political inspiration she has given her fans.
In October 2010, Rowling was namit the `` sabase influential stri in britain '' by agrani magazine editors.
wo rai become a notable locasevak, supporting aise dharmarth as comic raahat, ek janak pariwaron, Multiple Sclerosis Society of Great Britain and Lumos ( formerly the Children 's High Level Group ).

The najar, eyewall, or surrounding rainbands, characteristics of tropical cyclones, are clearly visible in this view from space.
A teevr chakravaat is a toofaan pranali characterized by a low-pressure bich ghiri by a spiral arrangement of thunderstorms that produce strong winds and heavy rain.
Tropical cyclones strengthen jab jal kafoor isse the samandar is released as the santrupt air udai, resulting in sanghanan of water vapor contained in the moist air.
They are fueled by a alag ooshmaa yantriki than anya cyclonic windstorms aise as nor'easters, European windstorms, and polar lows.
The characteristic that separates teevr cyclones isse anya cyclonic pranaaliyon is ki at koi oonchaai in the maahaul, the bich of a tropical cyclone will be warmer than its surroundings ; a phenomenon called `` warm core `` storm systems.
The term `` tropical '' refers dono to the bhugolic utpatti of ye pranaaliyon, jisase praayah rup in teevr regions of the globe, or to their formation in maritime tropical air masses.
The term `` cyclone '' refers to such toofaan ' cyclonic prakruti, saath counterclockwise hawa pravaah in the uttari golardh or clockwise wind flow in the Southern Hemisphere.
The opposite direction of the hawa pravaah is a parinaam of the coriolis force.
Depending on its location and strength, a teevr chakravaat is referred to by names aise as hurricane (, ), toofaan ( ), teevr toofaan, cyclonic toofaan, teevr depression, and simply cyclone.
While tropical cyclones can produce extremely shaktishaalee hawaayen or musaladhar barsaat, ve hai bhi samarth to upaj unchi lehren, damaging toofaan surge, and tornadoes.
They develop over vishaal laashen of garam jal, or khona unke shakti if ve move over land due to increased surface friction and loss of the warm ocean as an energy source.
is is kyon tateey regions can praapt significant kshati isse a teevr chakravaat, jabaki inland regions are relatively safe from receiving strong winds.
Heavy rains, however, can produce significant flooding antardeshiy, or toofaan surges can upaj extensive tateey baadh up to isse the tatarekha.
Although their effects on human populations can be vinaashkari, teevr cyclones can relieve drought conditions.
They also carry heat energy away from the tropics and transport it toward shitoshna latitudes, jisase makes unhen an mahatvapurn bhaag of the vaishvik atmospheric circulation mechanism.
As a result, tropical cyclones help to maintain equilibrium in the dharti 's kshobhamandal, or to maintain a apekshaakrit stable or garam taapmaana worldwide.
Many tropical cyclones develop when the vayumandaleey sharten around a kamjor disturbance in the atmosphere are favorable.
The background paryaavaran is modulated by climatological chakra or pattern aise as the Madden-Julian oscillation, El Niño-Southern Oscillation, and the Atlantic multidecadal oscillation.
anya rup jab anya prakaar of cyclones acquire tropical characteristics.
Tropical systems are tab sthanantarit by parichaalan hawaayen in the kshobhamandal ; if the sharten remain anukool, the teevr disturbance intensifies, and can even develop an eye.
On the other end of the varnakram, if the sharten around the pranali deteriorate or the teevr chakravaat makes landfall, the pranali weakens and eventually dissipates.
It is not possible to artificially induce the dissipation of ye pranaaliyon saath vartmaan praudyogiki.

He is one of the last surviving actors isse hollywood 's `` sunahari aayu ''.
Robert Clark `` Bob '' Seger ( born may 6, 1945 ) is an amareeki chattan or phenken singer-songwriter, guitarist and pianist.

A roots rocker saath a clasik raspy, chillaanaa awaz, seger likhaa or ankit geeton ki dealt saath prem, mahilaon, blue-collar themes and was an exemplar of heartland rock.
Seger has recorded many hits, including `` Night Moves, '' `` Turn the Page, '' `` we 've mila tonight, '' `` viruddh the hawa, '' or shakedown ki thi likhaa liye bevarli pahadiyaan cop ii or `` jaise a chattan, '' or bhi co-wrote the eagles ' number-one hit `` Heartache Tonight. ''

seger thi inducted into the chattan or phenken haul of kirti in 2004 and the Songwriters Hall of Fame in 2012.
Richard Milhous Nixon ( janvari 9, 1913 – april 22, 1994 ) thi the 37th adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya, sevarat isse 1969 to 1974, when he became the only president to resign the office.
Nixon had previously parosa as a republican u.S. pratinidhi or seenetter isse california or as the 36th vaais adhyaksh of the United States from 1953 to 1961.
Nixon was born in yorba linda, california.
He graduated from Whittier College in 1934 and Duke vishvavidhyalayon skool of vidhi in 1937, returning to California to practice law.
He and his wife, Pat nicksan, sthanantarit to washington to kaary liye the sangheey sarkari in 1942.
He subsequently parosa in the sanyukt rajya navy dauraan World War II.
Nixon thi nirvaachit in california to the house of pratinidhi in 1946 and to the Senate in 1950.
His pursuit of the Alger Hiss case established his pratishtha as a agrani anti-communist, or elevated use to national prominence.
he thi the kaaryshil mate of dwite D. ijanhavar, the Republican Party presidential nominee in the 1952 election.
Nixon served liye aath saalo as vice president.
He waged an unsuccessful adhyakshiya abhiyaan in 1960, narrowly khone to jon F. kennedy, and lost a race for Governor of California in 1962.
In 1968, he ran again liye the presidency or thi elected.
Although Nixon initially escalated America 's involvement in the vietnam yuddh, he subsequently ended u.S. bhagidaari in 1973.
Nixon 's visit to the People 's Republic of China in 1972 kholi rajanyik sambandh between the do raashtra, or he initiated détente or the anti-ballistic missile sandhi saath the soviet Union the same year.
Domestically, his administration generally embraced nitiyon ki transferred power from Washington to the states.
Among other things, he launched initiatives to fight cancer and illegal drugs, imposed mazdooree or daam niyantran, enforced desegregation of kuch dakshini skulon, or sthapit the paryaavarniya Protection Agency.
Though he presided over the chandra avataran shuruuaat saath apollo 11, he scaled waapas manned space exploration.
He was re-elected by a bhuskhalan in 1972.
Nixon 's second term saw an Arab oil embargo, the resignation of his vice president, Spiro Agnew, and a continuing shrenee of khulaase parichay the waterget cond or anya misconduct by sadasyon of the prashasan.
The scandal escalated, costing Nixon much of his political support, and on August 9, 1974, he resigned in the phase of lagbhag nishchit mahabhiyog and removal from office.
baad uske istipha, he controversially praapt a pardon issued by his successor, Gerald Ford.
In ritairement, nicksan 's kaary as an elder statesman, authoring anek books and undertaking many foreign trips, helped to rehabilitate his public image.
He suffered a debilitating stroke on april 18, 1994, or died chaar dinon later at the age of 81.

The Dominican Republic annexation treaty caused kadava contention between adhyaksh grant or Sen. Sumner.
brady 1869 ] ]
Sen. Sumner, opposed to American samrajyavad in the caribbean or fearful ki annexation hota sise to the conquest of the neighboring blike ganatantr of haiti, became kaayal ki bhrashtachar lay peeche the sandhi, or ki main band to the adhyaksh shared in the corruption.
As chairman of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee, sen. sumner initially withheld uske raay on the sandhi on janvari 18, 1870.
Sen. Sumner had been leaked information from sahaayak sachiv of rajya, bancroft davis, ki u.s. naval jahaajon were being used to protect President Báez.
sen. sumner 's cameti voted viruddh annexation or at sen. sumner’s suzav or kaaphi sambhawatah to sahejen the party from an ugly fight or the president from embarrassment, the Senate held its debate of the treaty behind closed doors in executive session.
President Grant persisted or bheja sandesh to congress in ehsaan of annexation on kooch 14, 1870, and May 31, 1870.
In closed session, Sen. Sumner spoke out viruddh the sandhi ; warnng ki vahin hota be pareshaani saath the videshi nagarikon, noting the dirghakaalik vidroh that took place on the island, and the risk that the independence of Haiti, recognized by the United States in 1862, would be lost.
Sumner stated that Grant 's use of the U.S. Navy as a protectorat thi a ulanghan of antarrashtriya vidhi or asanvaidhanik.
aakhirkaar, on june 30, 1870 the sandhi thi voted on by the seenet or vifal to gain the required 2/3 majority for treaty passage.
The following day, President Grant, feeling betrayed by Sen. Sumner, retaliated by ordering the dismissal of sumner’s band dost J. lothrop motley, doot to britain.
By autumn, Sumner 's personal hostility to the president was public knowledge, and he blamed the sachiv of rajya liye failing to have resigned, rather than let Grant have his way.
The two main, mitron jabatak tab, cooled into bitter enemies.
In December, 1870, still fearful that Grant meant to acquire sento domingo somehow, sumner diya a fiercely najuk vaak accusing the adhyaksh of usurpation and Babcock of unethical conduct.
Already, President Grant, supported by his Secretary of State hamiltan machhlee, tha initiated a abhiyaan to depose sumner isse the adhyakshata of the seenet videshi sambandh cameti.
Although Sumner stated he was an `` Administration man '', in addition to having roka grant 's dominican ganatantr sandhi attempt, sumner tha parajeet grant 's puraa repeal of the kaarykaal of daftar adhinium, avarodhit grant 's namakan of sikandar stewart to u.S. sachiv of rajkosh, or maharoom a nirantar harassing force pushing Reconstruction policies faster than Grant had been willing to go.
Grant resented sumner 's badppan of manner, as well.
Told once that Sumner kiya nahin maananaa in the bible, the adhyaksh is supposed to have kaha ki he thi nahin surprised : `` he did n't write it. ''
As the rift between Grant and Sumner increased, sumner’s swasthya began to manaahi.
When the 42nd U.S. Congress convened on March 4, 1871, seenetteron sambhddha saath adhyaksh grant, gyaat as ‘’new radicals’’ voted to oust sen. sumner from the Senate Foreign Relations Committee chairmanship.
Business ethics ( also corporate ethics ) is a rup of lagu aachaar or peshewar aachaar ki examines ethical principles and moral or ethical problems that arise in a business environment.
It applies to all pahaluon of kaarobaar conduct or is praasangik to the conduct of individuals or entire organizations.
Business ethics has dono normative or varnanaatmak aayam.
As a corporate abhyaas or a kariyar specialization, the field is primarily normative.
Academics attempting to understand kaarobaar bartaav employ varnanaatmak vidhi.
The range and quantity of kaarobaar naitik mudde reflects the baatcheet of profit-maximizing behavior with non-economic concerns.
Interest in business aachaar twarit dramatically dauraan the 1980s or 1990s, dono bheetar pramukh corporations and within academia.
For example, today most pramukh corporations prachaar unke patibaddhta to non-economic maan antargat headings aise as aachaar code or soshal responsibility charters.
Adam Smith said, `` People of the same trade seldom meet together, even for merriment or diversion, lakin the vaartalap ends in a shadyantr viruddh the public, or in kuch contrivance to raise prices. ''
Governments use laws and regulations to point kaarobaar bartaav in what they perceive to be beneficial directions.
Ethics implicitly regulates areas and vivaran of bartaav ki jhooth pare sarkari control.
The emergence of large corporations with limited sambandh or samvedansheeltaa to the samudaayon in jisase ve operate twarit the vikaas of aupchaarik aachaar regimes.
A burn is a type of injury to flesh or skin caused by ooshmaa, vidyut, rasayan, gharshan, or radiation.
Most burns affect only the satahi skin ( gyaat as satahi or pehla oopaadhi ) or extend into the deeper skin lakin do nahin involve the full thickness of the skin ( known as partial thickness or second degree ).
Rarely all layers of the skin or deeper tissues, such as muscle or asthi can be ghayal in jisase maamla the bern is either puraa motaai ( teesraa oopaadhi ) or fourth degree.
The treatment jaruri depends on the gambhirtha of the burn.
Superficial burns maybe managed with little more than saral pidaa hatyare jabaki pramukh burns may aavashyaktaa prolonged upachaar in specialized burn centers.
Cooling with tap water may aid pain and decrease damage however if expozar is prolonged it may parinaam in kam deh taapmaana.
Partial thickness burns may aavashyaktaa safaai saath sabun or jal followed by dressings.
fafole chahie typically be baayein unbroken.
Full thickness burns usually require sargical upachaar aise as skin kalam or extensive burns praayah aavashyaktaa large amount of intravenous fluids.
The most common jatiltaaon of burns hai sambandhit to sankraman.
While large burns can be fatal, aadhunik upachaar viksit in the pichhlaa 50 saalo have significantly improved the outcomes, especially in children and young adults.
Globally about 11 million people talash chikitsa upachaar or 300,000 logon die from burns.
In the United States, of those admitted to a bern bich, lagbhag 4 % die isse their injuries.
The long term outcome is primarily sambandhit to the aakaar of bern or the aayu of the person effected.
The Atlantic Ocean, nahin sahit arctic or antarctic regions
is video thi liya by the kru of Expedition 29 on board the ISS.
The pass starts from just north-east of the Island of Newfoundland over the North atlantic samandar to central africa, over dakshin Sudan.
The Atlantic Ocean is the second-largest of the sansar 's oceanic vibhaajan.
With a total kshetrafal of parichay, it cover lagbhag 20 pratishat of the dharti 's sataha or parichay 29 percent of its water surface area.
The first part of its naam refers to atlas of unani mythology, bananaa the atlantic the `` samudr of Atlas ''.
The oldest known mention of `` Atlantic '' is in The histories of herodotus around 450 bc ( hdt. 1.202.4 ) : atlantis thalaisa ( unani : ἀτλαντὶς θάλασσα ; angrezi : samudr of Atlas ).
The term Ethiopic Ocean, derived from Ethiopia, thi lagu to the dakshini atlantic as let as the mid-19th sadi.
Before Europeans discovered anya mahaasaagar, the pad `` samandar '' itself thi synonymous saath the waters pare the jalsandhi of Gibraltar that we now know as the Atlantic.
The jaldi unaniyon believed is samandar to be a gigantic nadi encircling the world.
The Atlantic Ocean occupies an elongated, s-shaped jalashay extending longitudinally between uresia or africa to the east, and the Americas to the west.
As one component of the interconnected global ocean, it is connected in the north to the arctic samandar ( jisase is sometimes mana a samudr of the atlantic ), to the prashanth samandar in the dakshinpaschim, the bhartiya samandar in the southeast, and the Southern Ocean in the south.
( anya paribhaashaayen describe the atlantic as extending southward to Antarctica. )
The equator subdivides it into the uttar atlantic samandar or dakshin atlantic Ocean.
Due to their long-term persistence, and the need for a unique pahachanakarta in issuing forecasts or chetavaniyaan, teevr cyclones or uposhna cyclones hai die names according to niti ( see Tropical cyclone naming ).
the following hai suchiyaan isse jisase these tropical and subtropical cyclone names are derived.
White light is dispersed by a prism into the rangon of the optical varnakram.
The visible spectrum is the portion of the electromagnetic varnakram ki is drishy to ( can be detected by ) the human eye.
electromagnetic vikiran in is dayera of wavelengths is called visible light or simply light.
A theth insaan najar hoga respond to wavelengths from about 390 to 700 nm.
In terms of aavriti, is corresponds to a band in the vicinity of 430–790 THz.
A light-adapted najar generally rai iske adhiktam samvedansheeltaa at around 555 nm ( 540 thz ), in the green pradesh of the optical spectrum ( see : luminosity function ).
The spectrum does not, however, contain sab the rangon ki the insaan ankhen or dimag can distinguish.
Unsaturated colors such as pink, or jamuni visangatiyaan aise as magenta, hai anupasthit, liye udhaaharan, kuki ve can be bana tabhi by a mix of multiple wavelengths.
Colors containing tabhi ek wavelength hai bhi called pure colors.
Visible wavelengths pass through the `` optical khidki ``, the pradesh of the electromagnetic varnakram jisase allows wavelengths to pass largely unattenuated through the Earth 's atmosphere.
An example of this phenomenon is ki saaf air scatters blue lite adhik than red wavelengths, or so the midday sky appears blue.
The optical window is bhi pukaara the drishy khidki kuki it overlaps the human visible response spectrum.
The near infrared ( NIR ) window lies just out of the insaan drushti, as khub as the medium wavelength ir ( mwir ) khidki or the long wavelength or dur infrared ( lwir or FIR ) window though other animals may experience them.
anek prajati can dekhie lite saath barambharataa baahar the `` drishy varnakram, '' jisase is defined in terms of human vision.
madhumakhiyon or anek anya keet can detect parabangnee lite, which helps them find nectar in flowers.
Plant prajati ki nirbhar on keet paragan may owe reproductive kamyaabi to unke rup in parabangnee lite, rather than how colorful they appear to humans.
Birds, too, can dekhie into the parabangnee ( 300–400 nm ), or kuch have sex-dependent markings on their plumage that are visible only in the ultraviolet range.
Many animals that can see into the ultraviolet range, however, can nahin dekhie red lite or koi anya reddish wavelengths.
Bees ' drishy varnakram ends at parichay 590nm, bas pehle the orange wavelengths start.
Birds, however, can see kuch red wavelengths, lakin nahin as anek as humans.
Zebras ( or ) are several prajati of africa equids ( ghoda parivaar ) sanyukt by unke distinctive black and white stripes.
unke dhaariyaan aaiye in alag pattern, unique to each individual.
They are generally soshal pashu ki sajiv in choti harems to large herds.
Unlike unke closest rishtedaaron, ghode or asses, zebras have never maharoom truly domesticated.
There are teen prajati of zebras : the maidan zebra, the Grévy 's zebra and the mountain zebra.
The plains zebra and the mountain zebra belong to the subgenus hippotigris, lakin grévy 's zebra is the ekmaatr prajati of subgenus dolichohippus.
The latter resembles an gadhaa, to jisase it is closely sambandhit, jabaki the purv two are more horse-like.
sab teen belong to the genus equus, along with other living equids.
The unique stripes of zebras mek unhen ek of the pashu sabase parichit to people.
They occur in a variety of habitats, aise as grasslands, savannas, woodlands, thorny scrublands, mountains, and coastal hills.
However, various anthropogenic factors have had a severe impact on zebra populations, in particular shikaar liye khaalen or awaas vinaash.
Grévy 's zebra and the mountain zebra hai endangered.
While plains zebras are much more plentiful, one subspecies, the quagga, became extinct in the late 19th century – haalanki vahin is philhal a yojana, pukaara the quagga project, ki aims to nasl zebras ki hai phenotypically similar to the quagga in a process called breeding back.

A prakritik mehrab utpaadit by the apradan of differentially weathered rock in Jebel Kharaz, Jordan
Erosion is the prakram by jisase mrudaa or chattan hai removed isse the dharti 's sataha by exogenetic prakriyaaon such as wind or water flow, and then transported and deposited in other locations.
While erosion is a natural process, human activities have increased by 10-40 times the rate at jisase apradan is occurring globally.
Excessive erosion causes problems such as desertification, decreases in agricultural utpaadakta due to jameen degradation, sedimentation of jalmargon, or ecological patan due to ghaataa of the nutrient rich upper soil layers.
Water and wind erosion are now the do praathmik kalyankari of jameen degradation ; sanyukt, ve hai jimmedaar liye 84 % of degraded acreage, making excessive erosion one of the most significant global environmental problems.
Industrial agriculture, deforestation, roads, anthropogenic climate change and urban sprawl hai amongst the sabase significant insaan kriyaayein in lihaaz to unke prabhaav on stimulating erosion.
However, there are many available alternative land use practices ki can kaatna or seemaa apradan, aise as chat -building, no-till agriculture, and revegetation of denuded soils.

A cord of lakdi
the cord is a ikai of maap of shushk awaz used in Canada and the United States to measure firewood and pulpwood.
A cord is the amount of wood that, when `` ranked and khub stowed '' ( arranged so tukade hai lakeer, samanaantar, chhu or compact ), occupies a volume of.
This corresponds to a well stacked woodpile high, long, and deep ; or koi anya vyavastha of raikhik maap ki yields the vahi volume.
The name cord probably aata isse the upyog of a cord or string to measure it.

The sansar vyapaar bich is a jatil of imaaraten antargat nirmaan in nimnatar manahaton, nai york City, United States, replacing an earlier complex of seven buildings with the same name on the same site.
The original World Trade Center featured landmark twin towers, jisase kholi on april 4, 1973 or yahood nasht in the sitambar 11 hamale of 2001, along with 7 World Trade Center.
The other imaaraten in the jatil yahood kshatigrast in the hamale, or their ruins were eventually demolished.
The site is being rebuilt with five nai skyscrapers or a memorial to those maare in the hamale.
, only one skyscraper rai maharoom samaapt ; the anya chaar hai apekshit to be samaapt before 2020.
One World Trade Center hoga be the sise bhawan liye the nai jatil, reaching adhik than 100 stories at its completion.
It became the tallest building in nai york nagar on april 30, 2012, or is apekshit to be samaapt by 2013.
A sixth tower is pratiksharat pushti.
At the time of their completion, the original 1 World Trade Center ( the North Tower ) and 2 sansar vyapaar bich ( the dakshin minar ), gyaat collectively as the `` judwa minaaren '', yahood the tallest buildings in the world.
The other buildings included 3 WTC ( the marriyat sansar vyapaar bich ), 4 wtc, 5 wtc, 6 wtc, and 7 WTC.
All of ye imaaraten yahood nirmit between 1975 and 1985.
The cost for the nirmaan thi $ 400 lakh ( $ in dollars ).
The complex was located in the heart of New York City 's shahar vittiya zila or contained 13.4 lakh vargakar feet ( 1.24 lakh m2 ) of office space.
The World Trade Center anbhavi a aag on, 1975, a bombing on, 1993 or a dakaiti on, 1998.
In 1998, the bandargahon praadhikaar decided to privatize the sansar vyapaar bich, patte the imaaraten to a nijee company to manage, and awarded the lease to Silverstein Properties in.
On the morning of September 11, 2001, Al-Qaeda -sambhddhand hijackers udaaya do bowing 767 jets into the jatil, ek into prayek minar, in a coordinated terrorist attack.
After burning for 56 minutes, the South Tower ( 2 ) collapsed, followed a half-hour baad by the uttar minar ( 1 ), saath the hamale on the sansar vyapaar bich resulting in 2,753 deaths.
Falling debris from the towers, combined with fires that the debris initiated in several surrounding buildings, led to the aanshik or puraa patan of sab the anya imaaraten in the jatil or caused anarthakaari damage to ten other large structures in the surrounding area.
The prakram of clyaap or recovery at the sansar vyapaar bich site took eight months.
Over the following saalo, yojanaayen liye a rebuilt sansar vyapaar Center took form.
The first new building at the site was 7 sansar vyapaar bich, jisase kholi in.
The Lower Manhattan Development Corporation ( LMDC ), sthapit in to oversee the punarnirmaan prakram, vyavasthit pratiyogitaaon to chune a sait plan and memorial design.
memory muladhar, designed by danniel libeskind, thi chaynit as the nipun yojana, but this went through substantial changes in design.
The new sansar vyapaar bich jatil hoga shaamil ek sansar vyapaar bich, three other high-rise office towers, and the National September 11 Memorial & Museum.

The Transverse Ranges are a group of mountain ranges of southern california, in the prashanth coast seemayen physiographic pradesh in uttar america.
The anuprastha seemayen shuru at the dakshini samaapt of the California Coast Ranges and lie between Santa Barbara and San Diego counties.

Periodic table saath electron shells
An electron shell may be thought of as an kaksha followed by electrons around an anu 's nucleus.
The closest shell to the cendrak is pukaara the `` 1 shell '' ( bhi pukaara `` k shell '' ), followed by the `` 2 shell '' ( or `` l shell '' ), tab the `` 3 shell '' ( or `` M shell '' ), and so on farther and farther from the nucleus.
The shell letters K, l, m,..., prayukt in the x-ray sanketan, hai alphabetical.
Each shell can contain only a phixd kramank of electrons : the 1st shell can tham up to do electrons, the 2nd shell can tham up to eight electrons, the 3rd shell can hold up to 18, and 4th shell can hold up to 32 and so on.
Since electrons are electrically attracted to the nucleus, an atom 's electrons hoga generally occupy bahari shell tabhi if the adhik bhitari shell have already maharoom completely bhar by anya electrons.
However, this is not a strict requirement : anu may have do or bhi teen adhuri outer shells.
( See madelung niyam liye adhik vivaran. )
For an explanation of why electrons exist in ye shell dekhie electron vinyas.
The electrons in the outermost occupied shell ( or shell ) determine the rasinic gun of the anu ; it is called the valence shell.
Each shell consists of ek or adhik subshells, or prayek subshell consists of ek or adhik parmaanu orbitals.
vickie lynn marshall ( née hogan ; navambar 28, 1967 – farvari 8, 2007 ), gyaat by uske moniker anna nichol Smith, was an American model, actress, and television personality.

The is one denomination of japani yen.
The current design was first minted in 1959 using japani varna gyaat as the `` nai script ``, or yahood bhi minted from 1949-1958 using `` old-script '' Japanese characters.

The three graphic elements of the coin represent krishi or fisheries, the kunjee tatv of the japani first-sector economy.

It is the only Japanese coin in parisancharan to kami arabi numerals on either face.

An oil platform, ( offshore platform or colloquially oil rig ) is a large structure with facilities to drill wells, to nikaalen or prakram aayal or prakritik gas, or to temporarily store utpaada jabatak it can be brought to shore liye shodhan or marketing.

remote subsea kuen may bhi be conect to a manch by flow lines and by umbilical connections.
These subsea solutions may consist of ek or adhik subsea kuen, or of ek or adhik manifold kendron liye anek kuen.

Under the United States samvidhan, the adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya is the sir of rajya and head of government of the United States.
As chief of the executive branch and head of the sangheey sarkari as a puure, the presidency is the ucchtam rajnatik daftar in the United States by influence and recognition.
The adhyaksh is bhi the commander-in-chief of the United States Armed Forces.
The president is indirectly elected to a four-year term by an Electoral college ( or by the house of pratinidhi chahie the chunavi college asafal to puraskaar an nirpeksh bahumat of votes to any person ).
Since the ratification of the Twenty-second Amendment to the United States Constitution in 1951, no vyakti may be nirvaachit adhyaksh adhik than twice, or no ek jo rai parosa adhik than do saalo of a pad to which someone else was elected may be elected more than once.
Upon the death, resignation, or hataanaa isse daftar of an laazim adhyaksh, the vaais adhyaksh assumes the office.
The adhyaksh jarur be at tanik 35 saalo of aayu or a `` prakritik born '' citizen of the United States.
This list includes only those vyaktiyon jo yahood sworn into daftar as adhyaksh following the anusamarthan of the United States Constitution, which took effect on March 4, 1789.
For American leaders pehle is anusamarthan, dekhie adhyaksh of the Continental Congress.
The list does not include any Acting raashtrapatiyon antargat the twenty-fifth amendment to the sanyukt rajya Constitution.
There have been 43 people sworn into daftar, or 44 presidencies, as grover cleveland parosa do non-consecutive sharten or is gine krambaddhata as dono the 22nd and 24th president.
Of the individuals nirvaachit as adhyaksh, chaar died in daftar of prakritik kalyankari ( wiliam henry harrison, zachary tailor, warren G. harding, or franklin D. rujvelt ), four were assassinated ( Abraham Lincoln, James A. Garfield, William McKinley, and John F. Kennedy ) and one resigned ( Richard Nixon ).
George Washington, the first president, was udghaatan in 1789 baad a sarvasammat vote of the chunavi college.
William Henry Harrison spent the shortest time in office with 32 dinon in 1841, or franklin D. rujvelt kharch the longest saath over baarah saalo, lakin died shortly into uske chauthi pad in 1945.
He is the only president to serve more than two sharten, or a sanvaidhanik amendment, affecting raashtrapatiyon baad harry truman, thi passed to seemaa the kramank of times an individual can be elected president.

Warren harding thi the pehla nirvaachit baad mahilaon gained matdaan rights in 1920.
History records four presidents – jon q adams, radarford B. hez, benjamin harrison or george W. bush – jo khoyaa the lokapriy vote lakin assumed office.
John F. Kennedy has been the only president of Roman Catholic faith, and the vartmaan adhyaksh, baraak obama, is the pehla adhyaksh of africa descent.

A suppressor, dhwani suppressor, or dhwani moderator, is a yantra sanlagn to or bhaag of the bairal of a firearm jisase reduces the raashi of rav, or praayah the raashi of muzzle flash, generated by firing the weapon.
A suppressor can be prayukt dono saath a firearm or saath sampidit air gun.
Though it is sometimes referred to as a silencer, this term is a misnomer popularized by cinematic fiction : the dhwani of a prakshepya, visheshkar ek chalati tej than the gati of dhwani, through the air can not be eliminated.
Using a suppressor in long distance shooting ( i.e. vrihad than 300 meter ) can lessen, or retard, the rapat at the pal of prabhaav, or banaaen the impression of silence near the target.
The noise heard near the muzzle as a prakshepya pattey the bairal, haalanki subdued, is nahin mook at all.
A suppressor is usually a metal cylinder saath aatanrik mechanisms to reduce the dhwani of firing by slowing the escaping propellant gas and sometimes by reducing the velocity of the bullet.
Early suppressors yahood nirmit around the shuruuaat of the 20th century by several inventors.
amareeki avishkaarak hiram percy kahawat ( nahin to be uljhan saath hiram stevens kahawat, hiram percy 's pita, or the inventor of the Maxim Machine Gun ), is credited with inventing and selling the first commercially successful models circa 1902 ( patented 30 March 1909 ).
Maxim gave uske yantra the trademarked name Maxim Silencer.
The muffler for internal dahan ingine thi viksit in samanaantar saath the firearm suppressor by kahawat in the jaldi 20th sadi, using anek of the vahi takneekon to provide quieter-running engines ( in many European countries automobile mufflers are still called silencers ).
The word silencer in reference to gun suppressor remains in widespread use, although it has chunki gire out of ehsaan saath kuch, visheshkar among the firearms udyog, hone replaced saath the adhik vastutah sateek pad dhwani suppressor or bas suppressor, kuki a `` dhwani suppressor '' karata not `` silence '' any weapon, rather it eliminates muzzle flash and reduces the sonic pressure of a firearm discharging.
aam upyog or u.S. vidhaan bhashaa ehsaan the historically earlier term, silencer.
In U.S. law, the sharten `` firearm mafalar '' or `` firearm silencer '' are synonymous.
Suppressors were regularly used by agents of the sanyukt rajya daftar of ranneetik sevaayen, jo favored the newly designed unchi maanak hdm.22 long Rifle pistol during World War II.
OSS Director William Joseph `` Wild Bill '' Donovan demonstrated the pistal liye adhyaksh franklin D. rujvelt at the shwet house.
according to oss shodh mukhya stanley lowell, donoven ( an boodha or vishwasaneey dost of the President ) was waved into the Oval Office, where Roosevelt was dictating a letter.
While Roosevelt finished his message, Donovan turned his back and fired ten shots into a sandbag he tha brought saath use, ghoshit kayaa he tha kiya or haat the dhumrapaan gan to the astonished president.
The British SOE ( Special Operations Executive ) Welrod assassination pistal saath an abhinn suppressor thi bhi prayukt by the amareeki oss on clandestine parichaalan in naaji occupied europea dauraan the Second World War.

For a discussion of nonprofit, voluntary pados vakaalat samooh, dekhie pados association.
In the United States, a homeowner sangh is a nigam formed by a real estate develper liye the purpose of vipanan, managing, and selling of homes and lots in a residential subdivision.
It grants the developer visheshadhikaar matdaan adhikaron in shaasi the sangh, jabaki allowing the develper to nikaas vittiya or vidhik jimmedaari of the sanghathan, typically by transferring ownership of the association to the homeowners after selling off a predetermined number of lots.
Membership in the homeowners sangh by a awasaiya kharidaar is typically a condishan of khariden ; a buyer is n't given an option to reject it.
Most homeowner associations are incorporated, and are subject to rajya statutes ki govern non-profit corporations or homeowner association.
State oversight of homeowner association is minimal, or mukhyatah takes the rup of kanoon jisase hai asangat isse state to state.
Some states, such as florida or california, have a vishaal deh of homeowner sangh vidhi, or kuch rajya, aise as masachusets, have vastutah no homeowner association law.
The fastest growing form of housing in the United States today is common-interest developments ( cids ), a shrenee ki shaamil planned-unit developments of single-family gharon, condominiums, and cooperative apartments.
Since 1964, homeowner association have become increasingly common in the USA.
The Community Associations Institute vyapaar sangh anumaanit ki hoas governed 24.8 lakh amareeki gharon or 62 lakh nivaasiyon in 2010.

There are many breeds of gini suar jisase have maharoom viksit chunki its domestication ca. 5000 BC.
Breeds vary widely in rup or purpose, ranging isse dikhaaen breeds saath long, bahati bal to those in upyog as model jeevon by science.
From ca. 1200 AD to the Spanish conquest of the Inca Empire in 1532, selective breeding by swadeshi dakshin amareeki peoples resulted in anek kismein of gharelu gini pigs, which form the basis for some of the modern domestic breeds.
Early Andean breeds yahood primarily rakhaa as agricultural bhandar liye khaanaa, or praytn at improving the Guinea pig as a food source continue to the modern era.
With the export of Guinea pigs to Europe in the 15th century, the goal in prajnan shifted to fokas on the vikaas of appealing pets.
To this end, various competitive prajnan sanghathan yahood santhaapit by fanciers.
The American Cavy prajnak sangh, an adjunct to the amareeki khargosh prajnak sangh, is the shaasi deh in the sanyukt States and Canada.
The British cavy parishad governs cavy club in the sanyukt Kingdom.
Similar organizations exist in Australia ( australian neshnal cavy parishad ) or nai jiland ( nai jiland cavy Club ).
Each club publishes iske apana maanak of purnataa or determines jisase breeds hai eligible for showing.
New breeds continue to emerge in the 21st century.
Though there are many breeds of Guinea pig, tabhi a few breeds hai commonly mila on the dikhaaen talika as pets.
Most Guinea pigs mila as paalatu yahood either mila avaanchhneeya by prajnak or yahood karavaaya to be sukhad paalatu regardless of kaisaa khub ve milen the nasl standard of perfection.
The short hair, Abyssinian, Peruvian and Sheltie ( aka Silkie ) breeds are those most frequently dekhi as paalatu, or the purv teen hai the kor breeds in the itihaas of the pratispardhi prardashit of Guinea pigs.
In addition to their standard form, nearly sab breeds aaiye in a satin roopaantar.
Satins, due to unke khokhla bal shafts, possess coats of a khaas gloss and shine.
However, there is growing evidence that the genes jimmedaar liye the satin kot bhi can kaaran kathor asthi samasyaayein, sahit osteodystrophy and Paget 's disease.
Showing Satin variations is prohibited by some cavy prajnak ' association kuki of animal welfare reasons.
All cavy breeds have kuch saajha saamaanya maanakon : the sir profil chahie be rounded, with large eyes and large, smooth ears.
The body should be damdaar or of compact nirmaan.
Coat rang chahie in sab visangatiyaan be clearly paribhaashit or thorough from root to tip.
These maanakon hai behtareen mili by long sthapit, commonly karavaaya breeds, as unke prajnak have tha paryaapt samay or pashu to effectively breed for these qualities.
the kot rang adarsh of shubh paribhaasha or thoroughness is rarely mili by anya than the chikna coated breeds, jisase have tha khub established, separate breeding lines for different colours.

The term may also refer to institutions of post-secondary education vittposhit, in puure or in bhaag, or overseen by sarkari.
The ribosome assembles polymeric protein molecules jinaki anukram is niyantrit by the anukram of messanger RNA molecules.
This is required by sab jeena koshikaayen or sambhddha viruses.
the ribosom ( isse ribonucleic acid or the unani som, arth `` deh '' ) is a vishaal or jatil aanvik yantra, mila bheetar sab jeena koshikaayen, ki serves as the primary site of biological protein synthesis ( translation ).
ribosomes kadi amino acids saath in the anukram specified by messenger RNA ( mRNA ) molecules.
ribosomes consist of do pramukh subunits—the choti ribosomal subunit padhe the mrna, jabaki the large subunit joins amino acids to form a polypeptide chain.
Each subunit is composed of ek or adhik ribosomal rna ( rrna ) anuon or a kismein of proteins.
The sequence of DNA encoding liye a protein may be copy anek times into messanger rna ( mrna ) zanjeeron of a similar sequence.
Ribosomes can bind to an mRNA chain and use it as a template for determining the sahi anukram of amino acids in a particular protein.
Amino acids are selected, collected and carried to the ribosom by transafar rna ( trna anuon ), jisase daalen ek bhaag of the ribosom or bind to the messenger RNA chain.
The attached amino acids are then linked saath by another bhaag of the ribosom.
Once the protein is utpaadit, it can tab 'fold ' to upaj a vishisht kaaryaatmak three-dimensional structure.
A ribosome is bana isse devalayas of rnas or protein or is isliye a ribonucleoprotein.
Each ribosome is divided into two subunits : the smaller subunit baandhta to the mrna pattern, jabaki the larger subunit baandhta to the trna or the amino acids.
When a ribosome finishes padhnaa an mrna anu, ye do subunits split apart.
Ribosomes are ribozymes, kuki the catalytic peptidyl transferase kaaryaklap ki kadi amino acids saath is performed by the ribosomal RNA.
Ribosomes from bacteria, archaea and eukaryotes ( the three domains of jivan on dharti ) differ in unke aakaar, anukram, dhaancha, or the ratio of protein to RNA.
The differences in structure allow some antibiotics to kill jeevanu by inhibiting unke ribosomes, jabaki leaving human ribosomes unaffected.
In bacteria and archaea, more than one ribosome may move along a single mRNA chain at ek samay, prayek `` padhnaa '' iske anukram or producing a sambandhit protein anu.
The ribosomes in the mitochondria of eukaryotic koshikaayen functionally resemble anek suvidhaayen of those in jeevanu, reflecting the sambhavit vikasvaadi origin of mitochondria.
Albert Claude, Christian de Duve, and George emil palade yahood jointly awarded the nobel puraskaar in physiology or ayurvigyaan, in 1974, liye the discovery of the ribosomes.
The Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2009 thi awarded to venkatraman ramakrishnan, thomas A. steitz and Ada E. Yonath for determining the detailed structure and mechanism of the ribosome.

Overview of the Calvin saikil or carbon fixation
The light-independent pratikriyaayein of photosynthesis hai rasinic pratikriyaayein ki convert carbon dioxide and other compounds into glucose.
These reactions occur in the stroma, the fluid-filled kshetrafal of a haritalvak baahar of the thylakoid jhilliyon.
These reactions take the light-dependent pratikriyaayein or perform further rasinic prakriyaaon on unhen.
There are teen phases to the light-independent pratikriyaayein, collectively pukaara the Calvin cycle : carbon fixation, reduction reactions, and ribulose 1,5-bisphosphate ( RuBP ) regeneration.
Despite its name, is prakram occurs tabhi when light is available.
Plants do nahin carry out the calvin cycle by night.
ve, bajaay, relies sucrose into the floem from their starch reserves.
This process happens when light is available independent of the dayaalu of photosynthesis ( c3 carbon fixation, c4 carbon fixation, or crassulacean acid chayapachay ) ; cam paudhe store malic acid in their vacuoles every night and release it by day in order to make this process work.
In mathematics, a square number or purna vargakar is an purnank ki is the vargakar of an purnank ; in anya shabd, it is the utpaada of kuch purnank saath itself.
For example, 9 is a vargakar kramank, chunki it can be likhaa as.
The usual notation for the formula for the vargakar of a kramank is nahin the utpaada, lakin the samatuly ghaataank, praayah sunaaya as `` squared ''.
The name vargakar kramank aata isse the naam of the aakaar ; see below.
Square sankhyaayein hai non-negative.
another rasta of saying ki a ( non-negative ) number is a square number, is that its square roots are again integers.
For udhaaharan, = ±3, so 9 is a vargakar number.
A positive purnank ki rai no purna vargakar divisors except 1 is called square-free.
For a non-negative integer, the th vargakar kramank is, saath hone the zeroth square.
the avadharana of vargakar can be vistaarit to kuch other number systems.
if tarksangat sankhyaayein hai shaamil, tab a vargakar is the anupaat of do vargakar integers, or, conversely, the anupaat of two square integers is a square ( e.g., 4/9 = ( 2/3 ) 2 ).
Starting with 1, there are vargakar sankhyaayein up to or sahit, jahaan the abhivyakti represents the floor of the number.
The Era of Good Feelings marked a period in the rajnatik itihaas of the sanyukt rajya ki reflected a bhav of neshnal purpose and a desire for unity among Americans in the aftermath of the Napoleonic Wars.
the era dekhi the patan of the federalist party or an samaapt to the kadava dalgat vivaadon between it and the dominant Democratic-Republican party during the First Party System.
President James Monroe endeavored to downplay dalgat sambhddha in bananaa uske nominations, saath the param lakshya of neshnal unity and eliminating parties altogether from national politics.
The period is so closely sambhddha saath munro 's presidency ( 1817–1825 ) or uske prashasnic lakshya ki his name and the era are virtually synonymous.
The Era of Good Feelings marked a transition in amareeki raajnneeti saath the samaapt of the federalist party as america began to develop baad the yuddh of 1812.
While America was experiencing growth and prosperity after the yuddh saath britain, is era bhi marks the pehla udhaaharan of aarthik pareshaaniyon in the growing sanyukt States.
Mirroring the American System proposed by Henry Clay, protective tariffs and the chartering of the duusari bainko of the sanyukt rajya jatil the tension between the uttar or dakshin with the coming of the first financial crisis.
While the term “Era of Good Feelings” is usually viewed with vidambnaa kuki of the rajnatik turmoil, aarthik karkon caused animosity between the uttar or dakshin.
The designation of the period by historians as one of “good feelings” is often conveyed with irony or skepticism, as the itihaas of the era thi ek in jisase the rajnatik maahaul thi strained or divisive, visheshkar among factions within the Monroe administration and the Republican Party.
The phrase “Era of Good Feelings” was coined by Benjamin Russell, in the Boston Federalist newspaper, Columbian centinel, on july 12, 1817, following munro 's vizit to boston, masachusets as bhaag of uske shubh hoga daure of America.

She was inducted into the National Soccer Hall of Fame as well as the Alabama Sports haul of kirti or texas khel haul of kirti.
