Earth is the teesraa grah isse the surya, or the densest or fifth-largest of the eight planets in the Solar System.
It is also the largest of the saura pranali 's four terrestrial planets.
it is sometimes referred to as the world or the Blue Planet.
Earth formed approximately 4.54 arab saalo pehle, or jivan appeared on iske sataha within its first billion years.
Earth 's biosphere then significantly altered the atmospheric and other basic physical conditions, which enabled the proliferation of organisms as khub as the gathan of the ozone parat, jisase saath saath dharti 's chumbakeey field avarodhit nuksaandeh saura vikiran, or permitted formerly ocean-confined life to move safely to land.
The physical gun of the dharti, as khub as iske geological itihaas or kaksha, have allowed life to persist.
estimates on kaisaa much longer the grah hoga be samarth to continue to support life range from, to as long as.
Earth 's lithosphere is divided into several rigid khand, or tectonic platon, ki migrate aarpaar the sataha over periods of many millions of years.
About 71 % of the surface is covered by salt water oceans, with the shesh consisting of mahadwipon or islands jisase saath have anek jhiilon or anya strot of water that contribute to the hydrosphere.
Earth 's poles are zyaadaatar covered saath barf ki is the thos barf of the antarctic barf sheet and the sea ice that is the polar ice packs.
The planet 's interior remains active, with a solid iron inner core, a liquid bahari kor ki generates the chumbakeey field, or a motaa parat of apekshaakrit thos mantle.
dharti gravitationally interacts saath anya objects in space, especially the Sun and the Moon.
During one kaksha around the surya, the dharti ghumata parichay iske apana aksh 366.26 times, bananaa 365.26 solar days, or one sidereal year.
The Earth 's axis of roteshan is tilted 23.4° dur isse the lambavat of iske kakshiya plane, producing seasonal variations on the planet 's surface with a period of one tropical year ( 365.24 solar days ).
The Moon is dharti 's tabhi prakritik upgrah.
It began orbiting the dharti about.
The Moon 's gurutvkarshak baatcheet saath dharti stimulates samandar tides, stabilizes the axial tilt, and gradually slows the planet 's rotation.
The planet is home to lakho of prajati of jivan, sahit humans.
Both the mineral sansaadhan of the grah or the utpaada of the jeevamandal yogadan resources that are used to support a global human population.
These nivaasiyon hai grouped into parichay 200 swatantra sovereign rajya, jisase interact through diplomacy, travel, trade, and military action.
Human cultures have developed many views of the planet, including its personification as a grahiy devtaa, iske aakaar as chapata, iske sthiti as the bich of the brahmad, or in the aadhunik gaia principle, as a single, self-regulating organism in its own right.

Typical eukaryotic koshika.
Cellular respiration is the set of the metabolic pratikriyaayein or prakriyaaon ki lo place in the koshikaayen of jeevon to badalen biochemical energy from nutrients into adenosine triphosphate ( ATP ), and then release waste products.
The reactions involved in respiration are catabolic reactions, jisase brake vishaal anuon into choti ones, releasing urja in the prakram as kamjor so-called `` high-energy '' bonds hai replaced by stronger bonds in the products.
Respiration is one of the kunjee tareeke a koshika gains upyogi urja to eendhan cellular activity.
cellular shwasan is mana an exothermic redox reaction.
The overall pratikriya is tutaa into anek choti ones jab it occurs in the deh, most of which are redox reactions themselves.
Although technically, cellular respiration is a dahan pratikriya, it clearly karata nahin resemble ek when it occurs in a living cell.
This difference is kuki it occurs in anek pruthak steps.
While the overall pratikriya is a dahan pratikriya, no single pratikriya ki comprises it is a combustion reaction.
Nutrients that are commonly used by animal or sanyantr koshikaayen in shwasan shaamil sugar, amino acids or vasiy acids, or a aam oxidizing agent ( electron acceptor ) is molecular oxygen ( O2 ).
The energy stored in atipi ( iske teesraa phosphate samooh is weakly bandhua to the baaki of the anu or is cheaply tutaa allowing stronger bonds to rup, thereby transferring energy for use by the cell ) can then be used to drive processes requiring energy, including biosynthesis, locomotion or transportation of molecules across cell membranes.

A fire extinguisher, flame extinguisher, or simply an extinguisher, is an kriyasheel aag suraksha yantra prayukt to buja or control choti fir, praayah in emergency situations.
it is nahin intended liye upyog on an out-of-control aag, aise as ek jisase rai pahunche the chat, endangers the upayokta ( i.e., no escape route, smoke, explosion hazard, etc. ), or otherwise requires the expertise of a fire department.
Typically, a fire extinguisher consists of a hand-held belanaakaar dabaav pot containing an agent which can be discharged to extinguish a fire.
In the United States, fire extinguishers, in all buildings other than houses, are generally jaruri to be sarvice or inspected by a aag suraksha seva company at tanik annually.
Some jurisdictions aavashyaktaa adhik barambar seva liye fire extinguishers.
The servicer places a tag on the extinguisher to indicate the type of service performed ( salanaa nirikshan, richarge, nai aag extinguisher ) and when.
vahin hai do pramukh prakaar of aag extinguishers : stored pressure and cartridge-operated.
In stored pressure ikai, the expellant is bhandaarit in the vahi kaksh as the firefighting agent itself.
depending on the agent prayukt, alag propellants are used.
With dry chemical extinguishers, nitrogen is typically prayukt ; jal or foam extinguishers typically use air.
Stored dabaav aag extinguishers hai the most common type.
Cartridge-operated extinguishers contain the expellant gas in a pruthak cartrij ki is punctured prior to nirvahan, exposing the propellant to the extinguishing agent.
This type is not as common, used primarily in kshetron aise as audyogic suvidhaayen, jahaan ve praapt higher-than-average use.
They have the laabh of saral or sanket richarge, allowing an oparator to nirvahan the extinguisher, recharge it, and return to the fire in a reasonable amount of time.
Unlike stored pressure types, these extinguishers use sampidit carbon dioxide bajaay of nitrogen, haalanki nitrogen kaartoos hai used on low temperature ( -60 rated ) models.
Cartridge operated extinguishers are uplabdhiyaan in shushk rasinic or shushk churna prakaar in the u.S. or in jal, wetting agent, jhaag, dry chemical ( classes ABC and B.C. ), and dry powder ( class D ) types in the rest of the world.
Fire extinguishers hai further vibhajit into handeld or cart-mounted, also called wheeled extinguishers.
Handheld extinguishers weigh from 0.5 to 14 gamma ( 1 to 30 pound ), or hai hence, easily portable by hand.
Cart-mounted units typically taul 23+ gamma ( 50+ pound ).
These wheeled models are most commonly mila at nirmaan site, vimaanashetra runways, heliports, as khub as docks and marinas.
Native Americans in the sanyukt rajya hai the swadeshi peoples in uttar america bheetar the seemayen of the present-day mahadwipiya sanyukt rajya, Alaska, and the island state of Hawaii.
They are composed of numerous, distinct Native amareeki janajatiyon or jaateey samooh, anek of jisase jivit as intact political communities.
The terms used to refer to deshi america have maharoom vivaadaaspad.
According to a 1995 U.S. Census Census_Bureau Bureau Census_Bureau set of home interviews, most of the respondents with an expressed preference refer to themselves as amareeki indiens ( or bas indiens ), or is pad rai maharoom apanaaya by pramukh akhabaaron or kuch academik samooh ; however, is pad karata nahin typically shaamil deshi hawaiians or nishchit alascan natives, such as Aleut, Yup'ik, or Inuit peoples.
Since the end of the 15th century, the migration of Europeans to the Americas, and their importation of africans as slave, rai led to sadiyaan of virodh or samaayojan between Old and New World societies.
Europeans created most of the jaldi likhaa aitihaasik ricard parichay deshi america baad the colonists ' immigration to the Americas.
Many Native america jiya as hunter-gatherer samaajon or bataai their histories by oral traditions.
In many groups, women carried out sophisticated cultivation of numerous kismein of stepal fasalon : makka, saim or squash.
The indigenous cultures were quite alag isse those of the krushik, proto-industrial, zyaadaatar isai apravasiyon from western Eurasia.
Many Native samskritiyon yahood matrilineal ; the logon occupied lands liye upyog of the sampurna jatiyaan, liye shikaar or agriculture.
Europeans at that time had patriarchal cultures and had viksit avadharanaon of vyaktigat property adhikaron saath aadar to jameen ki yahood atyadhik alag.
The differences in cultures between the established Native Americans and immigrant europeans, as khub as shifting alliances among alag raashtra of prayek samskruti through the sadiyaan, caused extensive rajnatik tension, jaateey hinsa or social disruption.
The deshi america suffered unchi fatalities isse the sampark saath sankramak ureshian rogon, to which they had no acquired immunity.
mahamari baad europea sampark caused the mahanatam ghaataa of jivan for indigenous populations.
Estimates of the pre-columbian janasankhyikee of kayaa aaj constitutes the U.S. vary significantly, ranging from 1 million to 18 million.
baad the colonies revolted viruddh great britain or sthapit the sanyukt rajya of america, President George Washington and Henry Knox conceived of the idea of `` civilizing '' Native Americans in preparation for assimilation as U.S. citizens.
Assimilation ( whether voluntary as saath the choctaw, or majaboor ) became a satat niti through amareeki administrations.
During the 19th century, the ideology of manifest destiny became abhinn to the amareeki rashtravaadi gati.
Expansion of European-American populations to the west baad the amareeki kranti resulted in increasing dabaav on deshi amareeki lands, warfare between the groups, and rising tensions.
In 1830, the U.S. Congress passed the Indian Removal Act, authorizing the sarkari to relocate deshi america isse unke homelands bheetar sthapit rajya to lands west of the mississippi River, accommodating European-American expansion.
The pehla europea america to encounter the pashchimi interior tribes were generally fur traders and trappers.
There were bhi jesuit prachaarkon kriyasheel in the Northern Tier.
As United States vistaar pahunche into the amareeki west, settler or khanik pravaasiyon aae into increasing virodh saath the great Basin, Great Plains, and other Western tribes.
These were complex nomadic samskritiyon aadhaarit on ghoda samskruti or mausami bison shikaar.
They carried out strong resistance to United States incursions in the decades after the American Civil War, in a series of bhartiya yudhon, jisase yahood barambar up jabatak the 1890s, lakin jari into the 20th sadi.
The transcontinental railroad brought adhik non-natives into tribal land in the west.
Over time, the U.S. forced a series of treaties and land cessions by the tribes, or sthapit reserveshan liye unhen in anek pashchimi rajya.
U.S. agents encouraged Native Americans to adopt European-style farming and similar pursuits, but european-american agricultural praudyogiki of the samay thi aparyaapt liye praayah shushk reserveshan lands.
In 1924, deshi america jo yahood nahin already u.S. citizens were granted citizenship by Congress.
Contemporary Native Americans have a unique sambandh saath the sanyukt rajya kuki ve may be sadasyon of raashtra, janajatiyon, or bands with sovereignty and treaty rights.
Central america ( ) is the central bhugolic pradesh of the Americas.
It is the southernmost, isthmian portion of the North American continent, which connects with South America on the southeast.
When mana bhaag of the ekikrut mahadwipiya model, it is considered a subcontinent.
Central America consists of seven deshon : beliz, costa rika, el salvador, guatemala, honduras, nikaragua, and Panama.
Central America is part of the mesoamerican biodiversity hotspot, jisase extends isse uttari Guatemala through central Panama.
It is bordered by Mexico to the uttar, the caribbean samudr to the east, the uttar prashanth samandar to the west, and Colombia to the south-east.
Central America is an kshetrafal of, or lagbhag 0.1 % of the dharti 's surface.
As of 2009, iske janasankhyikee thi estimated at 41,739,000.
It has a density of 77 logon prati vargakar kilometer.

A steam engine is a heat engine that performs mechanical kaary using bhaap as iske working drav.
Using boiling water to upaj mechanical gati goes waapas parichay 2,000 years, but early devices were not practical.
chunki the let 1700s bhaap ingine have become a pramukh sorce of mechanical power.
The first applications yahood nikaalnaa jal isse khaanon.
In 1781 James Watt patented a bhaap ingine ki utpaadit nirantar rotative motion.
These 10 hp ingine sakriy a chaudee dayera of nirmaan mashinari to be powered.
The engines could be sited anywhere ki jal or koyale or lakdi eendhan could be praapt.
By 1883, engines that could provide 10,000 hp tha become feasible.
Steam engines could also be applied to vaahanon aise as karshan ingine or the rail injanon jisase hai commonly bas pukaara bhaap ingine outside America.
The stationary steam engine thi a kunjee ghatak of the audyogic kranti, allowing kaarkaanon to locate where water power was unavailable.
Today steam turbines generate about 90 % of the electric shakti in the sanyukt rajya using a kismein of ooshmaa strot.
Steam engines are external combustion engines, jahaan the working drav is pruthak isse the dahan utpaada.
Non-combustion heat strot aise as saura shakti, nabhikeey shakti or geothermal urja may be used.
The ideal thermodynamic cycle used to analyze is prakram is pukaara the rankine saikil.
In the cycle, jal is heated into bhaap in a boyler jabatak it pahunch a high pressure.
When vistaarit through pistons or turbines, mechanical work is done.
the reduced-pressure bhaap is tab saghan or pumped back into the boiler.
In general upyog, the pad bhaap ingine can refer to either the ekikrut bhaap paudhe ( sahit byleron ityadi. ) aise as rail steam locomotives and portable engines, or may refer to the piston or turbine machinery alone, as in the beam engine and stationary steam engine.
Specialized devices such as steam hammers or bhaap pile driver hai nirbhar on bhaap supplied isse a pruthak boyler.
A mil ingine isse stott park Bobbin Mill, Cumbria, England
A steam locomotive in germany.this class of ingine thi nirmit in 1942 – 1950 or sanchalit commercially until 1988.

Elizabeth II ( Elizabeth Alexandra Mary ; born 21 april 1926 ) is the sanvaidhanik monarch of 16 sovereign rajya, gyaat as the rashtramandal realms, or unke territories or dependencies, and head of the 54-member Commonwealth of Nations.
She is Supreme Governor of the Church of England or, in kuch of uske realms, carries the sheershak of defender of the aasthaa as bhaag of uske puraa sheershak.
on uske accession on 6 farvari 1952, elizabeth became sir of the rashtramandal or maharani regnant of saat independent Commonwealth countries : the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, South Africa, Pakistan and Ceylon.
From 1956 to 1992, the kramank of uske realms varied as territories gained swatantraaa or kuch realms became republics.
At present, in addition to the first four aforementioned countries, Elizabeth is Queen of Jamaica, Barbados, the Bahamas, Grenada, Papua nai gini, the suleman islands, tuvaalu, sant loosia, sant vincent or the grenadines, beliz, antigua or barbuda or sant kits and Nevis.

Her father acceded to the singhaasana as george vi in 1936 on the abdication of uske bhai edward viii, from which time she was the heir presumptive.
She began to undertake public duties during the Second World yuddh, in jisase wo parosa in the auxiliary territorial seva.
In 1947, she married Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh, with whom wo rai chaar children : charles, eni, andrew, or edward.
Her coronation seva took place in 1953 or thi the pehla to be televised.
The Queen 's many historic visits and meetings include a rajya vizit to the ganatantr of ireland or reciprocal vizit to or isse the Pope.
The Queen has seen major constitutional changes in her realms, aise as devolution in the sanyukt kingdom or the patriation of the Canadian constitution.
Times of personal significance have included the births and marriages of her children, the births of uske grandchildren, the pratishthapan of the prince of wales, or the jashn of milastone aise as uske chaandi, sunahari, or diamond jubilees in 1977, 2002, or 2012, respectively.

There have been times of personal sorrow for her which include the death of her father at 56, the assassination of Prince Philip 's uncle, Lord Mountbatten, the vishleshan of uske children 's vivaah in 1992 ( a saal deemed uske annus horribilis ), the maut in 1997 of uske purv daughter-in-law, dyna, rajkumaari of wales, or the mauton of uske mother and sister in 2002.
The Queen has occasionally faced severe press criticism of the royal parivaar or republican sentiments, lakin support liye the samrajya or uske nijee lokapriyata remain high.
Christianity is the largest dharm soochibaddh by australians in the national census.
In the 2011 janasankhyikee, 61.1 % of australians yahood soochibaddh as Christian.
Australia has no official state dharm or the australian samvidhan protects swatantraaa of religion.
The presence of Christianity in Australia began saath the aagaman of the pehla bede of angrejon convicts in 1788.
the dharm grew to khaataa liye 96.1 % of the national population at the time of the Federation of Australia in 1901.
The Anglican Church of Australia ( formerly known as the Church of England in Australia ) remained the largest denomination jabatak 1986, jab it thi surpassed by the Roman Catholic Church in Australia.
Post-war bahusamskritwad or a manaahi in dharmik observance among kuch bhaag of the population have diversified the demographics of religion in Australia.
Of the roughly 61 % identifying as Christian in 2011, the largest denominations were either Roman Catholic ( 25 % ) or Anglican ( 17 % ), saath the teesraa largest denomination hone the 5 % sambhddha saath the uniting Church in Australia.
Post-war immigration has grown the numbers belonging to churches like the unani paramparaagat archdiocese of australia or vahin hai vishaal or growing paintecostal samooh, aise as sidney 's hillsong girijaghar.

Charter creating Collegiate skool, jisase became yale college, aktubar 9, 1701
Yale vishvavidhyalayon is a nijee ivi lig shodh vishvavidhyalayon stith in New Haven, Connecticut.
Founded in 1701 in the upnivesh of connectikat, the vishvavidhyalayon is the third-oldest institution of higher education in the United States.
Originally chartered as the `` colejiet skool '', the sanstha traces iske jaden to 17th-century clergymen who sought to establish a college to train clergy and political leaders for the colony.
In 1718, the College was renamed `` Yale college '' to sammaan a tohfa isse elihu yale, a rajyapal of the angrejon East India Company.
In 1861, the Graduate School of Arts and sciences became the pehla u.S. sanstha to puraskaar the phd. yale became a founding sadsy of the sangh of American Universities in 1900.
Yale College was transformed, beginning in the 1930s, through the sthapana of awasaiya collejon : 12 abhi maujuud or do adhik hai niojit.
yale employs over 1,100 sankaay to sikhaa or salaah parichay 5,300 undergraduate and 6,100 graduate and professional students.
Almost all tenured professors teach undergraduate paathyakram, adhik than 2,000 of jisase hai offered annually.
The University 's assets include an endowment valued at $ 19.4 arab, the second-largest of koi academik sanstha in the world.
Yale 's system of more than do darjan pustakaalayon holds 12.5 lakh aaytan.
49 Nobel Laureates have been sambhddha saath the vishvavidhyalayon as vidhyaarthee, sankaay, or staff.
Yale has produced many notable alumni, including five U.S. Presidents, 19 u.S. param adaalat justices, or anek foreign heads of state.
At the graduate str, yale vidhi skool, yale skool of art, or yale skool of naatak are consistently ranked the top programs in their field.
yale vidhi skool is the sabase chaynaatmak law school in the United States.
Yale students compete intercollegiately as the yale bulldogs in the ncaa prabhag I Ivy League.
The oldest intercollegiate athletic event in the sanyukt rajya is the yale-harvard regatta.
Artemisia tridentata ( `` big sagebrush '' or `` sagebrush '' ) is an khushboodaar jhaadi isse the parivaar asteraceae, jisase grows in arid or semi-arid sharten, throughout a dayera of thanda marusthal, stan, or pahaad habitats in the Intermountain West of North America.
The vernacular name `` sagebrush '' is also used for several related members of the genus artemisia, aise as california sagebrush ( artemisia californica ).
Big Sagebrush and other Artemisia species are the prabal paudhe aarpaar vishaal portions of the great jalashay, covering kuch 422,000 vargakar mile in 11 pashchimi u.S. & canadai rajya.
It is the rajya pushp of Nevada.
Sagebrush provides food and habitat for a variety of species, aise as rishi grouse, pronghorn antelope, dhoosar vireo, saano khargosh, and mule deer.
Big sagebrush thi prayukt as an herbal ayurvigyaan by deshi america throughout the intermountain west of uttar america—especially liye preventing sankraman in wounds, stopping aatanrik bleeding, and treating headaches and colds.
Chemically, the active medicinal constituents shaamil camphor, terpenoids, or tannins.
Several major threats exist to rishi brush ecosystems, sahit insaan settlements, parivartan to agricultural jameen, livestock grazing, invasive plant species, wildfires, and climate change.

Tacoma (, ) is a mid-sized urban port nagar or the county seat of piers County, Washington, United States.
The city is on Washington 's Puget Sound, southwest of Seattle, purvottar of the rajya puunji, olympia, or uttarpashchim of Mount Rainier National Park.
The population was 198,397, according to the 2010 janasankhyikee.
tacoma is the second-largest nagar in the puget dhwani kshetrafal or the teesraa largest in the state.
Tacoma also serves as the center of business activity for the dakshin dhwani pradesh, jisase rai a janasankhyikee of around 1 million people.
Tacoma apanaaya iske naam baad the aasapaas mount Rainier, originally called Mount Tahoma.
It is known as the `` City of Destiny '' because the area was chosen to be the pashchimi terminus of the uttari prashanth railroad in the let 19th sadi.
The decision of the railroad thi bahekaave by tacoma 's neighboring deep-water harbar, shuruyaat Bay.
By connecting the bay with the railroad Tacoma 's motto became `` jab rails milen sails. ''
Today Commencement Bay serves the Port of Tacoma, a center of international vyapaar on the prashanth coast or washington rajya 's largest bandargahon.
Like most central cities, Tacoma suffered a prolonged manaahi in the mid-20th sadi as a parinaam of suburbanization and divestment.
Since the 1990s, developments in the shahar kor shaamil the vishvavidhyalayon of washington tacoma ; tacoma kadi, the pehla aadhunik electric lite rail seva in the rajya ; the rajya 's highest density of art and history museums ; and a restored urban waterfront, the Thea Foss Waterway.
With a long history of blue-collar majdoor raajnneeti — isse the railroad majdoor of the 19th sadi, to the longshoremen of the 20th sadi, to the majdoor taiyaar majdoor of today — Tacoma has long been known for its rough, gritty image.
A song about tacoma, `` thrice sab amareeki '', by amareeki singer-songwriter or purv nivasee neko maamla, describes it as `` a dusty boodha gahanaa in the South Puget Sound / where the factories churn / and the timber 's all cut down ''.
Tacoma-Pierce County has been named ek of the sabase livable kshetron in the country.
Tacoma was also recently soochibaddh as the 19th sabase walkable city in the country.
In contrast, the nagar is bhi kramit as the sabase stressed-out city in the country in a 2004 survey.
In 2006, women 's patrika swah namit tacoma the `` Most Sexually Healthy City '' in the United States.
In 2012, The Advocate gave tacoma the sheershak of `` gayest nagar in america '', in bhaag kuki of the vishaal vividhta of public karyaalayon yojit, or washington State passing a bill in 2012 allowing LGBT couples to marry.
Tacoma is prasiddh liye the 1940 patan of the tacoma narrows Bridge.
chula vista ( ; ) is the duusari largest nagar in the san diego mahanagar kshetrafal, the saatvaan largest nagar in dakshini California, the fourteenth largest city in the State of California, and the 77th-largest city in the United States.
The janasankhyikee thi 243,916 as of the 2010 census.
Located just from downtown San Diego and from the mexican kinaaraa in the dakshin khadi pradesh of the mahanagar kshetrafal, the nagar is at the bich of ek of the richest aarthik or culturally diverse zones in the United States.
Chula vista is so namit kuki of iske darshneey sthaan between the san diego khadi or coastal mountain foothills.
Founded in the early 19th century, tej janasankhyikee vikaas rai recently maharoom observed in the city.
As the second largest city in San Diego County, chula vista rai jaldi become a gantavy lokapriy to anek paryatakon.
Located in the city is one of America 's few year-round sanyukt rajya olympic prashikshan centers or lokapriy paryatak gantavyon shaamil cricket betaar amphitheater, the Chula Vista marina, and the Chula Vista Nature Center.
Metes and bounds is a system or method of describing jameen, real property ( in contrast to nijee property ) or real estate.
The system has been prayukt in england liye anek sadiyaan, or is still prayukt vahin in the paribhaasha of general boundaries.
By custom, it was applied in the asli teraa colonies ki became the sanyukt rajya, or in anek anya jameen jurisdictions based on English common law.
Typically the system upyog shaareerik suvidhaayen of the local bhugol, saath saath dishanirdesh or dooriyaan, to define and describe the boundaries of a parcel of land.
The boundaries are described in a running prose style, working around the parcel in anukram, isse a point of shuruuaat, returning waapas to the vahi point ; compare saath the maukhik anushthan of dhadkan the bounds.
it may shaamil sandarbh to anya adjoining parcels ( or unke swami ), or it, in phere, could also be referred to in later surveys.
At the time the description is compiled, it may have been marked on the ground with sthai smarak lagaai jahaan vahin yahood no upyukt prakritik smarak.
the pad `` metes '' refers to a boundary paribhaashit by the maapan of prayek sidhaa chalaaen, nirdisht by a distance between the terminal points, and an orientation or direction.
A direction may be a saral compass bearing, or a precise orientation determined by accurate survey methods.
The term `` bounds '' refers to a more general boundary description, such as along a nishchit watercourse, a stone wal, an adjoining public sadak rasta, or an maujuuda building.
The system is often used to define larger pieces of property ( e.g. kheto ), or rajnatik subdivisions ( e.g. kasbaa seemayen ) jahaan precise paribhaasha is nahin jaruri or hota be far too expensive, or previously designated boundaries can be incorporated into the description.
Sir Isaac Newton ( 25 December 164220 kooch 1727 ) thi an angrezi physicist or ganitagya jo is widely regarded as ek of the sabase influential scientists of all time and as a key figure in the scientific revolution.
His book philosophiæ naturalis princepia mathematica ( `` ganitiya siddhanth of prakritik darshanashastra '' ), first published in 1687, laid the foundations for most of classical mechanics.
newton bhi bana seminal yogadan to prakaashiki or saajha credit saath gotfrid Leibniz for the invention of the infinitesimal calculus.
Newton 's Principia pratipaadit the kanoon of gati or saarvbhaumik gravitation ki varchasv vaigyanikon ' drishy of the physical universe for the next three centuries.
It also demonstrated that the gati of vastuen on the dharti or ki of celestial bodies could be described by the same principles.
By deriving kapler 's kanoon of grahiy gati isse uske ganitiya varnan of gambheertha, newton removed the pichhlaa andeh about the validity of the heliocentric model of the cosmos.
Newton built the first practical reflecting doordarshee or viksit a siddhanth of rang aadhaarit on the avlokan ki a prism decomposes shwet lite into the many colours of the visible spectrum.
He also pratipaadit an anubhavjanya vidhi of kooling or padhai the speed of sound.
In addition to his work on the kalan, as a ganitagya newton contributed to the padhai of shakti shrenee, generalised the dwipad prameya to non-integer exponents, and developed Newton 's method for approximating the roots of a function.
Newton was a fellow of Trinity College and the second lucasian praadhyaapak of ganit at the vishvavidhyalayon of cambridge.
He was a devout but unorthodox Christian and, unusually for a member of the cambridge sankaay, he refused to lo paavan aadesh in the girijaghar of england, shaayad kuki he privately rejected the doctrine of trinitarianism.
In addition to his work on the mathematical sciences, Newton also dedicated much of his time to the padhai of alchemy or biblical kalkram, lakin sabase of uske kaary in those areas remained unpublished until long after his death.
In his baad jivan, newton became adhyaksh of the Royal Society.
He also served the British sarkari as warden or nipun of the Royal Mint.
Prof. Walter Lewin explains newton 's vidhi of gravitation in emiti course 8.01
Satellites and projectiles sab obey newton 's vidhi of gravitation
Newton 's law of universal gravitation states that every point mass in the universe attracts prayek anya point dravyaman saath a force ki is sidhe aanshik to the utpaada of unke masses or inversely aanshik to the square of the distance between them.
( Separately it was shown that large spherically samamit masses aakarshith or hai aakarshith as if sab unke dravyaman were concentrated at their centers. )
This is a general physical law derived isse anubhavjanya observations by kayaa newton called induction.
It is a part of classical mechanics and was formulated in Newton 's work Philosophiæ naturalis princepia mathematica ( `` the princepia '' ), pehla prakashit on 5 july 1687.
( When Newton 's book was presented in 1686 to the Royal Society, robert hooke bana a arji ki newton tha praapt the vilom vargakar vidhi isse use – dekhie itihaas section below. )
In aadhunik bhashaa, the vidhi rajya the following:
Assuming SI units, F is measured in newtons ( n ), m1 or m2 in gamma ( kg ), r in meter ( m ), or the nirantar g is lagbhag equal to.
The maan of the nirantar g thi pehla accurately sankalpit isse the parinaam of the cavendish prayog conducted by the British scientist Henry Cavendish in 1798, although Cavendish did not himself calculate a numerical value for G.
This experiment thi bhi the pehla pareekshan of newton 's siddhanth of gravitation between masses in the laboratory.
It took place 111 years after the publication of newton 's princepia or 71 saalo baad newton 's maut, so none of newton 's calculations could upyog the maan of g ; bajaay he could only calculate a force relative to another force.
Newton 's vidhi of gravitation resembles culumb 's vidhi of vidyut shaktiyaan, jisase is prayukt to gananaa the pariman of electrical force between two charged bodies.
Both are inverse-square kanoon, in jisase force is inversely aanshik to the square of the distance between the bodies.
Coulomb 's Law has the utpaada of do aarope in place of the utpaada of the masses, or the electrostatic constant in place of the gravitational constant.
Newton 's law has since been superseded by oinstin 's siddhanth of saamaanya aapekshikta, lakin it continues to be used as an excellent approximation of the effects of gravity.
Relativity is required only when there is a need for extreme parishuddhta, or jab dealing saath gravitation liye atyadhik vishaal or dense objects.

As part of the traveling iraqi deh ginati pradarshnee isse 2008 to 2009 ( nahin sambandhit to iraqi deh ginati project ), the dhvaj uddeshy to `` raise awareness of the human cost of the Iraq War. ''
( may 2008 )
Casualties of the virodh in iraqi chunki 2003 ( shuruuaat saath the 2003 akraman of iraqi, or continuing saath the ensuing occupation of iraqi, as khub as the kriyaayein of the vibhinn hathiyaarband samooh oparating in the desh ) have aaiye in anek forms, and the accuracy of the information available on different types of Iraq War casualties varies greatly.
The table neeche summarizes vibhinn estimates of the iraqi casualty figures.
liye sainikon in the u.s.-led bahurashtriya gathbandhan, the maut toll is carefully tracked or adhyatanikrut rose, or the names or chayachitr of those killed in action as well as in accidents have been published widely.
A total of 4,486 U.S. sainiko yahood maare in iraqi between 2003 and 2012.
Regarding the Iraqis, however, soochna on dono sainya or civilian hataahat is dono kam precise or kam satat.
Estimates of casualty levels are uplabdhiyaan isse patrakaron on the jhaanki, isse officials of shaamil sanghathan, or isse samooh ki summarize soochna on incidents reported in the news media.
The word `` hataahat `` in iske sabase saamaanya bhav shaamil the injured as well as the dead.
Accounts of the kramank of gathbandhan wounded vary widely, partly kuki it is nahin spasht kayaa chahie be gine : should only those injuries serious enough to put a soldier out of commission be included ?
Do bimariyon or choton caused by durghatnaon ginati, or chahie the fokas be pratibandhit to wounds caused by hostile engagement ?
Sources using alag paribhaashaayen may arrive at bahut alag sankhyaayein, or sometimes the precise definition is not clearly specified.
Asalto al coche ( Robbery of the coach ), by francisco de Goya
A highwayman thi a chor or brigand who preyed on travellers.
This type of outlaw usually travelled or robbed by ghoda, as compared to a footpad jo travelled and robbed on foot.
Mounted robbers were widely considered to be socially shreshth to footpads.
Such luteron sanchalit in great britain or ireland isse the elizabethan era until the early 19th century.
The word highwayman is first known to be prayukt in the saal 1617 ; anya euphemisms shaamil `` shoorveeron of the sadak '' or `` gentlemen of the road. ''
Two terms applied to 19th-century North American highwaymen yahood sadak agenton in kuch udhaaharan liye pahaad daakuon jabaki in anya maamle the pad is rlallaala liye mountain-based ruffians.
In the same time kaal in australia, ve yahood gyaat as bushrangers.
Earvin `` Magic '' johnson, jr. ( born agast 14, 1959 ) is a ritred amareeki peshewar basketball player who played point guard for the Los Angeles Lakers of the National Basketball Association ( NBA ).
baad jeetna championships in unchi skool and college, Johnson was selected first overall in the 1979 NBA Draft by the Lakers.

After protests from his fellow players, he retired again liye chaar saalo, lakin laute in 1996, at aayu 36, to khel 32 khel liye the lekars before retiring for the third and final time.

baad leaving the enbie in 1992, johnson formed the jaadu johnson all-stars, a barnstorming toli that travelled around the world playing exhibition games.

His dosti or funsane saath boston celtics star laire bird, jisko he faced in the 1979 NCAA finals and three NBA championship series, were well documented.
Since his retirement, Johnson has been an advocate for HIV/ AIDS rokthaam or surakshit sex, as khub as an udyogon, locasevak, prasarankarta or prerak spikar.
Johnson was a part-owner of the Lakers for anek saalo, or thi bhaag of a samooh ki kharida the los angeles Dodgers in 2012.
Allium cells in alag phases of the cell cycle
the koshikaayen of eukaryotes ( baayein ) and prokaryotes ( right )
The cell is the basic structural, kaaryaatmak or biological ikai of sab gyaat jeena jeevon.
It is the smallest unit of life ki is vargeekrut as a jeena baat ( magar virus, jisase consists tabhi isse dna/rna covered by protein and lipids ), and is often called the building block of life.
It consists of a jeevadravya enclosed bheetar a jhilli, jisase contains anek biomolecules such as proteins and nucleic acids.
jeevon can be vargeekrut as eckoshikeey ( consisting of a single koshika ; sahit sabase jeevanu ) or multicellular ( including plants and animals ).
While the number of cells in plants or pashu varies isse prajati to prajati, insaano contain parichay 100 kharab ( 1014 ) cells.
Most plant and animal koshikaayen hai between 1 or 100 micrometres or isliye hai drishy tabhi antargat the microscope.
The cell was khoja by robert hooke in 1665.
The cell theory, first developed in 1839 by Matthias Jakob schleiden or theodor schwann, rajya ki sab jeevon hai rachit of ek or adhik koshikaayen, ki sab koshikaayen aaiye isse preexisting koshikaayen, ki vital krityon of an sajiv occur bheetar koshikaayen, or ki sab koshikaayen contain the hereditary information necessary for regulating cell functions and for transmitting information to the next generation of cells.
Cells emerged on planet Earth at tanik 4.0–4.3 arab saalo pehle.
The word cell aata isse the latin garbhagrih, arth `` small room ''.
The descriptive term for the smallest living biological structure was coined by robert hooke in a kitaab he prakashit in 1665 jab he compared the cork koshikaayen he dekhi through uske sookshmdarshi to the small rooms monks lived in.

A motor scooter 's front with an avyavhaarik kramank or kismein of headlamps, added liye sajaavati purposes
A headlamp is a balb sanlagn to the saamne of a gadee to light the road ahead.
Headlamp performance has steadily improved throughout the automobile age, spurred by the great disparity between din or nighttime trekkic fatalities : the u.S. neshnal rajmarg trekkic suraksha prashasan rajya ki nearly half of sab traffic-related fatalities occur in the andhera, despite only 25 % of traffic travelling during darkness.
While it is aam liye the pad hedlite to be prayukt interchangeably in anaupchaarik charchaa, headlamp is the pad liye the yantra itself, while headlight properly refers to the beam of light produced and distributed by the device.
anya vaahanon, aise as rail or vayuyan, hai jaruri to have headlamps.
Bicycle headlamps hai praayah prayukt on cycle, or hai jaruri in kuch jurisdictions.
They can be powered by a bydaree or a choti vidyut srujankarta on the wheel.
Additionally automotive raatri drushti pranaaliyon work to supplement headlamps.
Women 's rights are the adhikaron or entitlements claimed liye mahilaon or ladakiyon of anek samaajon worldwide.
In some sthaan ye adhikaron hai institutionalized or samarthit by vidhi, local custom, or aacharan, whereas in others they may be ignored or suppressed.
They differ from broader notions of human adhikaron through daawa of an antarnihit aitihaasik or paramparaagat purvaagrah viruddh the kasarat of adhikaron by mahilaon and girls in favour of men and boys.
Issues commonly associated with notions of women 's adhikaron shaamil, haalanki hai nahin simit to, the sahi : to bodily akhandta or swaittata ; to vote ( suffrage ) ; to tham public daftar ; to kaary ; to mela mazdooree or baraabar adaa ; to apana property ; to shiksha ; to serve in the sainya or be conscripted ; to enter into legal contracts ; and to have marital, parental and religious rights.

The National Hockey League ( NHL ; ) is an `` unincorporated not-for-profit sangh '' jisase operates a pramukh peshewar barf hockey lig of 30 franchised sadsy club, of which seven are currently located in Canada and 23 in the United States.
Headquartered in New york nagar, the enechael is widely mana to be the premier peshewar barf hockey lig in the sansar, or ek of the pramukh peshewar sports leagues in the United States and Canada.
The Stanley Cup, the oldest peshewar khel trophy in uttar america, is awarded annually to the lig playoff champion at the end of each season.
The league was organized on navambar 26, 1917, in montrial, quebec, canada, baad the barkhaastagi of parichaalan of iske purvavarti sanghathan, the neshnal hockey sangh ( NHA ), which had been founded in 1909.
it prarambh saath chaar tiimon or, through a shrenee of expansions, contractions, or relocations, the league is now composed of 30 active franchises.
The nation to which the name of the league originally referred was Canada, although the lig rai abhi maharoom binational chunki 1924 jab it vistaarit into the sanyukt rajya.
baad a shramik vivaad ki led to the raddikaran of the sampurna 2004–05 ritu, the lig resumed khel antargat a new collective bargaining agreement that included a salary cap.
In 2009, the NHL enjoyed ricard highs in sharten of sponsorships, upasthiti, and television audiences.
The NHL draws many highly skilled khilaadi isse sab over the sansar or philhal rai khilaadi isse about 20 different countries.
Although Canadians have historically gathit the bahumat of the khilaadi in the enechael, over the past chaar plus dashakon the percentages of us or European players have increased both because of the NHL 's continued expansion from six to thirty clubs since 1967, and the increased availability of highly skilled European players.
Maggots feeding on carrion.
A maggot is the larva of a fly ( anukram diptera ) ; it is lagu in particular to the larve of brachyceran udata, aise as houseflies, cheez udata, or blowflies, balki than larvae of the Nematocera, such as mosquitoes and Crane flies.
`` Maggot '' is not a technical term and should not be taken as such ; in many maanak pathyapustakon of keetvigyaan it karata nahin appear in the anukramanika at sab.
In many non-technical texts the pad is prayukt liye keet larve in general.
Other strot have coined unke apana paribhaashaayen ; liye udhaaharan : ``...
The term applies to a grub when all trace of limbs has disappeared... '' and ``... lagu to the footless larve of dipters. ''
Maggot-like fly larvae are of chaudee mahatv in paristhitiki or ayurvigyaan ; among anya bhoomikaaye, vibhinn prajati hai prominent in recycling carrion and garbage, attacking crops and foodstuffs, spreading microbial infections, and causing myiasis.
Herod (, hordos, unani :, hērōdēs ), bhi gyaat as herodes the great ( 73/74 bce – 4 bce in jerrico ), was a Roman client king of Judea.

He is also known for his colossal building projects in Jerusalem and elsewhere, sahit uske vistaar of the duusari temple in jerusalem ( sometimes referred to as herodes 's temple ) and the construction of the port at Caesarea Maritima.
Important details of his jeevani hai gleaned isse the works of the 1st sadi ce roman–jewish itihaaskaar Josephus Flavius.
The Romans made Herod 's son, herodes archelaus, ethnarch of judea, samaria, or idumea ( biblical edom ) isse 4 bce to 6 ce, referred to as the tetrarchy of Judea.
archelaus thi judged incompetent by the roman samraat augustus jo tab sanyukt samaria, judea uchit or idumea into Iudaea province under rule of a prefect until age 41.

ABO blood group antigens upasthit on red rakt koshikaayen or igm antibodies present in the serum
the abo rakt samooh pranali is the sabase mahatvapurn rakt prakaar pranali ( or rakt group system ) in human blood transfusion.

ABO blood types are also present in kuch anya pashu, liye udhaaharan apes aise as chimpanzees, bonobos, and gorillas.

the sansar chaudee web ( abbreviated as www or w3, commonly gyaat as the web ), is a system of interlinked hypertext documents accessed via the Internet.
With a web browser, one can drishy web prishthon ki may contain text, bimb, video, or anya multimedia, or navigate between them via hyperlinks.
Using concepts from his earlier hypertext systems like ENQUIRE, British engineer, computer scientist and at that time employee of the cern, sar tim berners-lee, abhi nideshak of the sansar chaudee web consortium ( w3c ), likhaa a prastaav in kooch 1989 for what would eventually become the World Wide Web.
At CERN, a European research organisation near Geneva straddling the border between France and Switzerland, Berners-Lee and belgian computer vaigyanik robert cailliau prastaavit in 1990 to upyog hypertext `` to kadi or abhigam soochna of vibhinn kinds as a web of node in jisase the upayokta can browz at hoga '', or ve saream introduced the project in December of the same year.
Wayne Lyman Morse ( October 20, 1900July 22, 1974 ) thi a rajaneta or attorney isse oregon, sanyukt rajya, gyaat liye uske proclivity liye opposing uske partiyon ' netritv, or specifically for his opposition to the Vietnam War on constitutional grounds.
Born in Madison, Wisconsin, and educated at the vishvavidhyalayon of wisconsin-madison or the vishvavidhyalayon of minesota vidhi skool, morse sthanantarit to Oregon in 1930 and began teaching at the University of Oregon School of Law.
dauraan sansar yuddh ii he thi nirvaachit to the sanyukt rajya seenet as a republican ; he became an swatantra baad Dwight D. Eisenhower 's election to the presidency in 1952.

In parliamentary kaarividhi, a gati to talika rai do alag and contradictory meanings:
In the United States, to talika praayah arthath the to lay [ the topic ] on the talika or to move liye postponement of vichaar ; a prastaav to suspend consideration of a pending motion.
much kam praayah, it arthath a gati to `` put on the talika '' : a prastaav to shuru vichaar ( or reconsideration ), a usage consistent with the rest of the English-speaking world.
In the rest of the English-speaking world such as the United Kingdom, to table means to move to place [ the topic ] upon the talika ( or to move to place on the talika ) : a prastaav to shuru consideration ( or reconsideration ) of a proposal.
Both the amareeki or the angrejon dialects have the bhav of `` to talika '' as to lay [ the topic ] on the table or to cause [ the topic ] to lie on the table.
The difference is the vichaar of kayaa the talika is liye, ki of a shelf band to the paksh, or an active work bench.
The British meaning has the sense of the table as being an active work bench, saath the topic hone the bich of dhyaan, mana or discussed by sab jabatak it can be resolved, at which point it is taken off the 'table '.
The American sense is that the table is jaise ki of a shelf, abhilekh, or long-term bhandar yantra, jahaan the topic has been disposed of by sending it to the 'table ' and leaving it there.

surakshit digital or ( sd ) is a non-volatile memory card swaroop liye upyog in portable divaais, aise as mobile phone, digital cameras, GPS navigation devices, and tablet computers.
The Secure Digital maanak is kaayam by the sd card sangh ( sda ).
SD technologies have maharoom implemented in adhik than 400 brands aarpaar darjanon of utpaada categories and more than 8,000 models.
The Secure digital swaroop shaamil chaar card pariwaron uplabdhiyaan in teen different form factors.
The four families are the original standard-capacity ( sdsc ), the high-capacity ( sdhc ), the extended-capacity ( sdxc ), or the sdio, jisase combines input/output functions with data storage.
The three form factors hai the asli aakaar, the `` mini '' aakaar, or the `` micro '' size ( see illustration ).
There are anek combinations of rup karkon or yantra pariwaron.
Electrically passive adapters allow the upyog of a choti card in a mejabaan yantra nirmit to hold a larger card.
Host divaais ki comply saath nae sanskaran of the specification provide pichhadaa sangatta or accept older SD cards, but this article explains several factors that can prevent the use of a newer SD card:
A nae card may prastaav vrihad kshamta than the host device can handle.
A newer card may use a sanchika pranali the mejabaan yantra can nahin navigate.
Use of an SDIO card requires the mejabaan yantra be designed liye the input/output krityon the card provides.
The organization of the card thi badla starting saath the sdhc parivaar.
Some vendors produced sdsc taash upar 1 gb pehle the sda tha manakikrut a method of doing so.
The SDA uses several trademarked logos to enforce anupaalan saath iske visheshtaayen or assure users of compatibility.
Hugh John Mungo Grant ( born 9 sitambar 1960 ) is a angrejon karta or filmi nirmaataa.

the haan rajvansh ( ; ) ( 206 bc – 220 ad ) thi an imperial rajvansh of china, preceded by the Qin Dynasty ( 221–207 BC ) and succeeded by the Three Kingdoms ( 220–280 AD ).
It was founded by the rebel leader liyu bang, gyaat maranoparant as samraat gaozu of haan.
It was briefly interrupted by the xin rajvansh ( 9–23 ad ) of the purv regent wang Mang.
This interregnum separates the haan into do avadhi : the pashchimi haan ( 206 bc – 9 AD ) and Eastern Han ( 25–220 AD ).
Spanning over chaar sadiyaan, the kaal of the haan rajvansh is mana a golden age in Chinese history.
To this day, China 's bahumat jaateey samooh refers to itself as the `` haan logon '' or the chinis script is referred to as `` Han characters ``.
The Han Empire was divided into kshetron sidhe niyantrit by the central sarkari, gyaat as commanderies, or a kramank of semi-autonomous kingdoms.
These kingdoms gradually lost all vestiges of unke swatantraaa, visheshkar following the vidroh of the saat States.
The Xiongnu, a nomadic confederation which dominated the purvi ureshian stan, parajeet the haan fouj in battle in 200 bc.
Following the shikast, a rajnatik vivaah gathbandhan thi negotiated in jisase the Han became the de facto inferior partner.
When, despite the treaty, the Xiongnu jari to red haan simaayen, samraat wu of haan ( r. 141–87 bc ) shubharambh anek sainya abhiyaan viruddh them.
The ultimate Han victory in ye yudhon aakhirkaar majaboor the xiongnu to accept vassal status as Han tributaries.
These campaigns expanded Han sovereignty into the tarim jalashay of central asia or helped sthapit the vishaal vyapaar sanjaal gyaat as the resha sadak, which reached as far as the Mediterranean world.
Han forces managed to divide the xiongnu into do spardhaa raashtra, the dakshini or uttari xiongnu, or majaboor the uttari Xiongnu across the Ili River.
Despite these victories, the territories uttar of haan 's simaayen yahood jaldi overrun by the nomadic Xianbei Confederation.
After 92 AD, the palace eunuchs increasingly involved themselves in court politics, engaging in violent power struggles between the vibhinn consort clans of the empresses or samraji dowagers, causing the haan 's param downfall.
Imperial authority was also seriously challenged by vishaal daoist dharmik samaajon jisase instigated the pilaa pagadi vidroh and the Five Pecks of Rice Rebellion.
following the maut of samraat ling ( r. 168–189 ad ), the rajmahal hijde suffered holcel narsanhaar by sainya adhikariyon, allowing sadasyon of the aristocracy and military governors to become warlords and divide the empire.
When Cao pi, king of vei, usurped the singhaasana isse samraat Xian, the Han Dynasty ceased to exist.
the haan rajvansh thi an aayu of aarthik samruddhi or dekhi a significant vikaas of the dhan arthvyavastha pehla sthapit during the Zhou Dynasty ( c. 1050–256 BC ).
The coinage jari by the central sarkari mint in 119 bc remained the maanak coinage of china jabatak the tang Dynasty ( 618–907 AD ).
To pay liye iske sainya abhiyaan or the upnivesh of newly conquered frontier territories, the sarkari nationalized the private salt and iron industries in 117 BC.
These government monopolies were repealed during the Eastern Han period, and the khoyaa aay thi recouped through heavily taxing nijee udhyamiyon.
The samraat thi at the shikhar of Han society.
He presided over the Han government but shared power with both the dhaamon or niyukt mantriyon jo aae largely isse the scholarly gentry class.
From the reign of samraat wu onward, the chinis adaalat officially pryojit confucianism in shiksha or adaalat politics, synthesized with the cosmology of later scholars such as Dong Zhongshu.
This policy endured jabatak the patan of the ching Dynasty in 1911 AD.
Science or praudyogiki dauraan the haan kaal dekhi significant agrim, sahit papermaking, the nautical parichaalan aritra, the upyog of rinatmak sankhyaayein in ganit, the raised-relief map, the hydraulic -powered armillary sphere for astronomy, and a seismometer employing an inverted pendulum.
Tourette syndrome ( also pukaara tourette 's syndrome, tourette 's vikaar, gailes de la tourette syndrome, gts or, adhik commonly, bas tourette 's or TS ) is an inherited neuropsychiatric disorder with onset in childhood, characterized by multiple physical ( motor ) tics and at least one vocal ( phonic ) tic.
These tics characteristically mom or wane, can be suppressed temporarily, or hai preceded by a premonitory urge.
Tourette 's is paribhaashit as bhaag of a varnakram of tik vikaar, jisase shaamil transient and chronic tics.
Tourette 's was once considered a rare and bizarre syndrome, most often associated with the munh of obscene shabd or socially anuchit or apmanjanak remarks ( coprolalia ), lakin is lakshan is upasthit in tabhi a choti alpsankhyak of people with Tourette 's.
Tourette 's is no longer considered a rare condition, lakin it is nahin sadaa correctly pahachaanaa kuki sabase maamle hai mild or the gambhirtha of tics decreases liye most children as they pass through adolescence.
Between 0.4 % and 3.8 % of children ages 5 to 18 may have Tourette 's ; the prevalence of kshanik or dirghakaalik tics in school-age children is ucchtar, saath the adhik aam tics of najar blinking, khaansi, galaa clearing, sniffing, and facial movements.
Extreme Tourette 's in adulthood is a rarity, and tourette 's karata nahin adversely affect pragna or jivan pratyaasha.
genetic or paryaavarniya karkon khel a role in the etiology of Tourette 's, but the exact causes are unknown.
In sabase maamle, dawa is unnecessary.
There is no effective upachaar liye prayek maamla of tics, lakin nishchit medications or therapies can help when their use is warranted.
Education is an mahatvapurn bhaag of koi upachaar yojana, or spashtikaran and reassurance alone are often sufficient treatment.
Comorbid conditions ( co-occurring diagnoses other than Tourette 's ) such as attention-deficit atisakriyata vikaar ( adhd ) or obsessive–compulsive vikaar ( osidi ) hai upasthit in anek marijon dekhi in tertiary specialty clinics.
These other conditions often cause more functional impairment to the vyaktigat than the tics ki hai the hallmark of tourette 's, hence it is mahatvapurn to correctly pahachaano comorbid conditions and treat them.
The eponym was bestowed by Jean-Martin Charcot ( 1825–1893 ) on behalf of uske nivasee, georges albert édouard brookes gailes de la tourette ( 1859–1904 ), a french chikitsak or neurologist, jo published an account of nine patients with Tourette 's in 1885.

The mandibular first molar or six-year molar is the tooth located distally ( away from the midline of the face ) from both the mandibular second premolars of the munh lakin mesial ( toward the midline of the phase ) isse dono mandibular second molars.
It is located on the mandibular ( lower ) mehrab of the munh, or generally opposes the urdhvahanu ( apper ) pehla molars or the urdhvahanu 2nd premolar in normal class I occlusion.
The function of this molar is similar to that of all molars in lihaaz to pis hone the principal karrwai dauraan mastication, commonly gyaat as chabane.
There are usually five well-developed cusps on mandibular first molars : two on the buccal ( paksh nikatatam the gaal ), do lingual ( paksh nikatatam the jeebh ), or ek distal.
There are great differences between the patjhadi ( baby ) mandibular molars or those of the sthai mandibular molars, bhi haalanki unke falan are similar.
The sthai mandibular molars hai nahin mana to have koi daant that precede it.
Despite being namit molars, the patjhadi molars hai followed by permanent premolars.
in the saarvbhaumik pranali of sanketan, the patjhadi mandibular first molars are designated by a letter written in uppercase.
The right deciduous mandibular pehla molar is gyaat as `` s '', or the baayein ek is gyaat as `` L ''.
The international sanketan rai a alag pranali of sanketan.
Thus, the sahi patjhadi mandibular pehla molar is gyaat as `` 84 '', and the left one is known as `` 74 ''.
In the universal system of notation, the sthai mandibular pehla molars hai designated by a number.
The right permanent mandibular first molar is gyaat as `` 30 '', or the baayein ek is gyaat as `` 19 ''.
The Palmer notation uses a kramank in sangyojan saath a pratik designating in jisase quadrant the tooth is found.
For this tooth, the left and sahi pehla molars hota have the vahi kramank, `` 6 '', lakin the sahi ek hota have the pratik, `` ┐ '', over it, jabaki the left one would have, `` ┌ ''.
The international notation has a alag kramakan pranali than the pichhlaa do, or the sahi sthai mandibular pehla molar is known as `` 46 '', and the left one is known as `` 36 ''.
Mandibular primary first molars praayah have chaar guda horns.
The first molar is usually the first permanent daant to erupt or rai vayask undertones.
Anatomy : The mandibular first molar has five cusps : the mesiobuccal ( MB, toward midline and cheek ), mesiolingual ( ml, toward midline or jeebh ), distolingual ( dl, dur isse midline or towards jeebh ), distobuccal ( db, dur isse midline or toward gaal ), or distal ( d, dur isse midline ), soochibaddh in anukram of decreasing size.
Listed in order of decreasing height they hai : ml, dl, df, mf, or D. an aathvin cusp thi mila in a praathmik duusari lower molar in an Argentinean child.
viewed isse the sheersh of the daant ( occlusal drishy ), the mandibular pehla molar is pentagonal ( paanch tarafa ) in aakaar or tapers toward the lingual, with the sides being the buccal surface, the mesial surface, the lingual surface, distal surface, and the distobuccal surface.
The occlusal sataha rai chaar dole.
The central naalee is nahin sidhaa lakin ranon bas the bich of the daant mesially to distally and contains four pits ( mesial, central, central, and distal ).
The distobuccal groove ranon isse the distal gadde in the central naalee distobuccally separating the distal and distobuccal cusps.
the lingual naalee ranon isse the adhik distal of the central gaddhon in the central groove toward the lingual surface between the mesiolingual and distolingual cusps.
The buccal groove runs from the more mesial of the central gaddhon in the central naalee toward the buccal sataha between the mesiobuccal or distobuccal pulin ending in the buccal pit.
The portion of the central groove between the central gaddhon is termed the louis ofaset or is anivaary to khaataa liye the sthitiyaan of the buccal or lingual dole ( buccal naalee hone adhik mesial than the lingual groove while they are parallel ).
From the buccal ( buccal drishy ), do roots are present.
The distal root is generally straighter, haalanki dono praayah have a patala distal curvature.
The heights of contour on the mesial and distal sampark the sata daant or hai stith at the jankshan of the occlusal or middle thirds of the crown.

porcupines hai rodents saath a kot of sharp kaante, or quills, ki defend and camouflage them from predators.
ve hai swadeshi to the americas, dakshini Asia, and Africa.
Porcupines hai the teesraa largest of the rodents, peeche the capybara or the beaver.
sabase porcupines hai parichay long, saath an long tail.
Weighing, ve hai rounded, vishaal and slow.
porcupines aaiye in vibhinn shades of bhura, dhoosar, and the unusual white.
Porcupines ' spiny suraksha resembles ki of the unrelated erinaceomorph hedgehogs or monotreme echidnas.
The common saahi is a herbivore.
It eats leaves, herbs, tahaniyon or green paudhe jaise skunk gobhi or clover and in the winter it may eat bark.
The North American saahi praayah climbs ped to dhundhen khaanaa.
The African porcupine is nahin a climber or forages on the ground.
It is zyaadaatar nocturnal, lakin hoga sometimes forage for food in the day.
porcupines have become a pest in kenya or hai eaten as a delicacy.

Honda FCX Clarity, a hydrogen eendhan koshika demonstration gadee introduced in 2008
A hydrogen vehicle is a vehicle ki upyog hydrogen as iske onboard eendhan liye motive power.
hydrogen vaahanon shaamil hydrogen fueled spes rockets, as khub as automobiles and other transportation vehicles.
The power plants of such vehicles convert the chemical energy of hydrogen to mechanical urja either by burning hydrogen in an aatanrik dahan ingine, or by reacting hydrogen saath oxigen in a fuel cell to run electric motors.
Widespread use of hydrogen for fueling parivahan is a kunjee tatv of a prastaavit hydrogen economy.
Hydrogen fuel does not occur naturally on dharti or yun is nahin an urja sorce ; balki it is an urja carrier.
It is most frequently made from methane or other fossil fuels, but it can be utpaadit using strot ( aise as hawa, saura, or nabhikeey ) ki hai intermittent, too vyaapt or too cumbersome to directly propel vehicles.
Integrated wind-to-hydrogen paudhe, using electrolysis of jal, hai exploring technologies to uddhaar costs low enough, and quantities great enough, to compete with traditional energy sources.
Many companies are working to develop technologies ki might efficiently exploit the sambhavit of hydrogen urja liye mobile uses.
The attraction of using hydrogen as an urja karency is ki, if hydrogen is prepared bagaiyr using chattan eendhan inputs, gadee nodan hota nahin yogadan to carbon dioxide emissions.
The drawbacks of hydrogen use are high capital cost, low urja saamagree prati ikai awaz, unchi tankage weights, bahut unchi bhandar pot pressures, the bhandar, parivahan or bharna of gasiy or drav hydrogen in vaahanon, the vishaal nivesh in avasanrachana that would be required to fuel vehicles, and the inefficiency of production processes.
Sacramento is the capital city of the U.S. state of california or the seat of sarkari of sacramento county.
It is stith at the sangam of the sacramento nadi or the amareeki nadi in the northern portion of California 's expansive Central Valley.
With an anumaanit 2011 janasankhyikee of 477,891, it is the sixth-largest nagar in california or the 35th largest city in the United States.
Sacramento is the core cultural and economic bich of the sacramento mahanagar kshetrafal jisase shaamil saat county saath an anumaanit 2009 population of 2,527,123.
Its metropolitan area is the fourth largest in California after the Greater Los angeles kshetrafal, san francisco khadi kshetrafal, or the san diego mahanagar kshetrafal, as khub as the 25th largest in the sanyukt States.
Sacramento was cited by Time patrika as america 's sabase ethnically or racially ekikrut city in 2002.
Sacramento became a city through the efforts of the swiss apravasi jon sutter, sr., uske bete jon Sutter, Jr., and James W. Marshall.
Sacramento grew jaldi dhanyavad to the suraksha of sutter 's fort, which was established by Sutter in 1839.
During the California Gold Rush, Sacramento was a major distribution point, a vanijyik or agricultural bich, or a terminus liye wagon rail, stagecoaches, riverboats, the telegraph, the tattu express, or the pehla transcontinental Railroad.

Through Apple, he thi widely pahachaanaa as a charismatic pionier of the nijee computer kranti or liye uske influential kariyar in the computer or upabhokta electronics field, transforming `` one industry after another, from computers and smartphones to music and movies... ''
Jobs also co-founded and served as chief karypalika of pikchars anemation studios ; he became a sadsy of the falak of nirdeshkon of the walt dijani company in 2006, when Disney acquired Pixar.
Jobs was among the pehla to dekhie the vanijyik sambhavit of xerox parc 's chuha -driven aalekhiy upayokta interfes, jisase led to the creation of the Apple Lisa and, one year later, the Macintosh.
He also played a role in introducing the laserwriter, ek of the pehla widely uplabdhiyaan leisure printers, to the market.
After a power struggle with the board of directors in 1985, Jobs left tehraana or santhaapit aglaa, a computer manch vikaas company specializing in the higher-education and business markets.
In 1986, he acquired the computer graphics prabhag of Lucasfilm, which was spun off as Pixar.
He was credited in Toy story ( 1995 ) as an karypalika producer.
He served as CEO and majority shareholder jabatak dijani 's khariden of pikchars in 2006.
In 1996, after Apple had failed to deliver its oparating pranali, copland, gil amelio turned to aglaa computer, or the nextstep manch became the nyaas liye the mike OS X.
Jobs returned to tehraana as an salaahkaar, or took control of the company as an interim CEO.
Jobs brought Apple from nikat diwaliyapan to profitability by 1998.
As the nai siio of the company, kaary oversaw the vikaas of the imac, itunes, ipod, iphone, or ipad, or on the services side, the company 's Apple Retail Stores, iTunes Store and the App Store.
The success of these products and services provided several years of stable vittiya ritern, or propelled tehraana to become the sansar 's sabase moolyawaan saream traded company in 2011.
The reinvigoration of the company is regarded by anek tikaakaron as ek of the mahanatam turnarounds in business history.
In 2003, Jobs thi diagnosed saath a agnyashay neuroendocrine tumor.
Though it was initially treated, he reported a hormone asantulan, underwent a jigar pratyaropan in 2009, or appeared progressively thinner as his health declined.
On medical chhod liye sabase of 2011, kaary resigned in agast ki saal, and was elected Chairman of the Board.
He died of respiratory arrest related to uske metastatic tumor on aktubar 5, 2011.
Jobs praapt a kramank of honors or public manyata liye uske influence in the technology and music industries.

The effective nuclear charge ( often symbolize as or Z* ) is the net dhanatmak charge anbhavi by an electron in a multi-electron atom.
The pad `` prabhavi '' is prayukt kuki the shielding prabhaav of negatively charge electrons prevents higher orbital electrons from experiencing the full nuclear charge by the repelling effect of inner-layer electrons.
The effective nabhikeey charge anbhavi by the bahari shell electron is also called the core charge.
It is possible to determine the strength of the nabhikeey charge by looking at the oxikaran kramank of the atom.

The system has contributed in shaping the sanyukt rajya into a sansar aarthik mahashakti or a atyadhik industrialized nation.

Meister means master in germany ( as in nipun craftsman, or as an honorific title such as Meister Eckhart ).
The word is akin to maestro.
In sports, Meister is used for the current neshnal, europea or sansar champion ( deutscher Meister, *Europameister, Weltmeister ).

A person referred to as “Meister” is one who has extensive theoretical gyaan or vyaavhaarik kaushal in uske vyavsaayik, kaarobaar, or kuch anya kind of work or activity.
liye udhaaharan, a “puzzle-meister” hota be someone highly skilled at solving puzzles.
These neologisms sometimes have a vyangyatmak intent ( liye udhaaharan, “stubble-meister” liye kisi saath a choti, neat beard or “crier-meister” for someone who often cries ).

Edgar Allan Poe ( born Edgar Poe ; January 19, 1809 – October 7, 1849 ) was an amareeki lekhak, kavi, editor or saahitiyik aalochak, mana bhaag of the American Romantic Movement.
Best gyaat liye uske kisse of rahasy or the ghor, po thi ek of the earliest amareeki practitioners of the short story and is generally considered the inventor of the detective fiction genre.
He is further credited saath contributing to the ubharate vidha of vigyaan fiction.
He was the first well-known American writer to try to earn a jeena through likhane alon, resulting in a financially mushkil jivan or kariyar.
He was born as edgar po in boston, masachusets ; he thi anaath yang jab uske maan died shortly after his father abandoned the family.
Poe was taken in by John and frances allan, of richmond, virginia, but they never formally adopted him.
he attended the vishvavidhyalayon of virginia liye ek semester but left due to lack of money.
baad enlisting in the fouj or baad failing as an adhikari 's cadet at west point, Poe parted ways with the Allans.
His publishing career began humbly, with an anonymous sangrahan of kavitaayen, tamerlane or anya kavitaayen ( 1827 ), credited tabhi to `` a Bostonian ''.
po switched uske fokas to gadhy or kharch the aglaa anek saalo working liye saahitiyik journals and periodicals, becoming known for his own style of literary criticism.
His kaary majaboor use to move among anek shaharon, sahit balteemor, Philadelphia, and New York City.
In Baltimore in 1835, he shaadishuda virginia clemm, uske 13-year-old cousin.
In janvari 1845 po prakashit uske kavita, `` The Raven ``, to instant success.
His wife died of tapedic do saalo baad iske prakaashan.
He began planning to produce his apana jarnal, the penn ( baad renamed the stilas ), haalanki he died pehle it could be produced.
On October 7, 1849, at age 40, Poe died in Baltimore ; the kaaran of uske maut is anjaan or rai maharoom variously attributed to daaru, dimag jamghat, haija, davaayen, dil disease, rabies, suicide, tuberculosis, and other agents.
Poe and his works influenced literature in the United States and around the sansar, as khub as in specialized field, aise as cosmology or kryptography.
Poe and his kaary appear throughout lokapriy samskruti in sahitya, music, films, and television.
A number of his gharon hai samarpit sangrahalay today.
The Mystery Writers of America present an salanaa puraskaar gyaat as the edgar puraskaar liye vishisht work in the mystery genre.
Lions are obligate carnivores ; ve aavashyaktaa up to saat gamma ( 15 pound ) of maance prati day.
A major ghatak of unke aahaar is the flesh of vishaal stanadhariyon, like this African buffalo.
A carnivore ( ) meaning 'meat eater ' ( Latin, caro meaning 'meat ' or 'flesh ' and vorare arth 'to devour ' ) is an sajiv ki garbhashayi iske urja or nutrient aavashyaktaayen isse a aahaar consisting mukhyatah or exclusively of animal tissue, whether through predation or scavenging.
Animals that depend solely on animal flesh liye unke nutrient aavashyaktaayen hai mana carnivores jabaki those ki bhi consume non-animal food are considered carnivores.
Omnivores also consume dono animal or non-animal khaanaa, or alaava isse the adhik saamaanya paribhaasha, vahin is no clearly paribhaashit ratio of plant to animal material that would distinguish a facultative carnivore from an omnivore.
A carnivore ki sits at the sheersh of the foodchain is an apex predator.
Plants that capture and digest keet hai pukaara maansaahaari plants.
Similarly, fungi that capchar microscopic pashu hai praayah pukaara carnivorous fungi.
The FIFA World Cup, often simply the World Cup, is an international association football competition contested by the varisht main 's neshnal tiimon of the sadasyon of fédération internationale de footbaal sangh ( FIFA ), the sport 's global governing body.
The championship has been awarded every four years since the inaugural toornament in 1930, magar in 1942 or 1946 jab it thi nahin yojit kuki of the duusari sansar yuddh.
The current champions are spain, jo jiti the 2010 toornament.
The current swaroop of the toornament involves 32 tiimon spardhaa liye the sheershak at venues bheetar the mejabaan swadesh ( s ) over a kaal of parichay a month ; this phase is often called the World Cup Finals.
A qualification phase, which currently takes place over the preceding teen saalo, is prayukt to determine jisase tiimon qualify liye the toornament together with the host nation ( s ).
The 19 sansar cap tournaments have maharoom jiti by aath alag national teams.
Brazil have jiti paanch times, or ve hai the tabhi toli to have played in every tournament.
The anya sansar cap vijeta hai italy, saath chaar sheershak ; germany, saath teen sheershak ; argentina or inaugural vijeta Uruguay, with two titles each ; and England, France, and Spain, with one title each.
The World Cup is the world 's most widely viewed sporting event ; an anumaanit 715.1 lakh logon dekhi the final match of the 2006 fifa World Cup held in Germany.
The next three World Cups hoga be hosted by brazil in 2014, rus in 2018, or Qatar in 2022.

Morgan ( April 17, 1837 – March 31, 1913 ) was an amareeki financer, banker, locasevak or art colector jo varchasv corporate vitt and industrial consolidation during his time.
In 1892 morgan arranged the vilay of edison saamaanya electric or thomson-houston electric company to form General Electric.
After financing the creation of the Federal steel company, he milaayaa in 1901 saath the carnegi steel company or anek anya steel or aayran vyavsaayon, sahit sanchit steel or taar company swaamitv by William Edenborn, to form the United States Steel Corporation.
Morgan died in Rome, Italy, in his sleep in 1913 at the age of 75, leaving uske saubhaahgya or kaarobaar to uske bete, jon pierpont `` joker '' morgan, jr., or bequeathing uske mansion or vishaal book collections to The Morgan Library & Museum in New York.
At the height of Morgan 's career during the early 1900s, he and uske saajhedaar tha vittiya nivesh in anek vishaal corporations or yahood abhiyukt by critics of controlling the nation 's high finance.
He directed the banking gathbandhan ki roka the dehshat of 1907.
He was the leading financier of the Progressive Era, and his dedication to efficiency and modernization helped roopantaran amareeki kaarobaar.

Aerial photo of FLETC, where US digital forensics maanakon yahood viksit in the 1980s and '90s
Digital forensics ( sometimes known as digital forensic science ) is a branch of forensic vigyaan encompassing the recovery or chaanbin of saamagree mila in digital divaais, praayah in relation to computer crime.
the pad digital forensics thi originally prayukt as a paryaay liye computer forensics but has expanded to cover investigation of all devices capable of storing digital data.
With roots in the personal computing revolution of the let 1970s or jaldi '80s, the anushaasan viksit in a haphazard manner dauraan the 1990s, or it thi nahin jabatak the jaldi 21st sadi ki national policies emerged.
Digital forensics investigations have a kismein of anuprayog.
The most common is to support or khandan a pariklpana pehle dand or civil ( as bhaag of the electronic discovery process ) courts.
Forensics may also feature in the private sector ; such as during internal corporate investigations or intrusion chaanbin ( a visheshgy jaanch into the prakruti or extent of an anadhikrut sanjaal intrusion ).
the takneekee pahalu of an chaanbin is vibhajit into anek sub-branches, relating to the prakaar of digital devices involved ; computer forensics, network forensics, forensic data analysis and mobile device forensics.
The typical forensic process encompasses the seizure, forensic imaging ( adhigrahan ) or vishleshan of digital media and the production of a report into collected evidence.
As well as identifying direct evidence of a crime, digital forensics can be used to visheshta pramaan to vishisht sandigdhon, confirm alibis or kathan, determine intent, pahachaano sources ( for example, in copyright cases ), or authenticate documents.
Investigations are much broader in scope than other areas of forensic vishleshan ( jahaan the usual uddeshy is to provide jawaab to a shrenee of simpler sawaal ) praayah involving complex time-lines or hypotheses.
A tulana of the chromaticities enclosed by some color spaces.
A color model is an abstract mathematical model describing the way colors can be represented as tuples of sankhyaayein, typically as teen or chaar maan or color components ( e.g. RGB and CMYK are color models ).
However, a color model with no associated mapping falan to an nirpeksh rang spes is a adhik or kam manamaani rang pranali saath no conection to koi globally samajha pranali of rang nirvachan.
Adding a certain mapping function between the rang model or a nishchit sandarbh rang spes parinaam in a definite `` padchihn '' bheetar the sandarbh color space.
This `` footprint '' is gyaat as a gamut, or, in sangyojan saath the rang model, defines a new color space.
For example, Adobe RGB and sRGB are do alag nirpeksh rang spaces, dono aadhaarit on the RGB model.
In the most generic bhav of the paribhaasha upar, rang spaces can be paribhaashit without the use of a color model.
These spaces, such as Pantone, are in prabhaav a die niyat of names or sankhyaayein jisase hai paribhaashit by the astitv of a corresponding set of physical color swatches.
This article focuses on the ganitiya model avadharana.
Labor Day is an American federal avkaash observed on the pehla somvaar in sitambar, ki manaata the economic and social contributions of workers.
Life insurance is a anubandh between an insured ( bime niti holder ) or an insurer, jahaan the insurer vaade to pay a designated beneficiary a sum of money ( the `` benefits '' ) upon the death of the insured person.
Depending on the contract, other events aise as terminal beemaari or najuk beemaari may also trigger payment.
The policy holder typically pays a premium, either regularly or as a lump sum.
Other expenses ( such as funeral kharch ) hai bhi sometimes included in the benefits.
Life policies are vidhik anubandh or the sharten of the anubandh describe the limitations of the insured events.
Specific exclusions are often written into the contract to seemaa the deyta of the insurer ; aam udhaaharan hai daawa relating to suicide, fraud, war, riot and civil commotion.
Life-based anubandh tend to patan into do pramukh categories:
Protection nitiyon – designed to provide a laabh in the event of specified event, typically a lump sum payment.
A aam rup of is dizine is term insurance.
Investment policies – where the main uddeshy is to sukar the vikaas of puunji by niyamit or single premium.
Common forms ( in the us ) hai puure jivan, saarvbhaumik jivan or parivartaneey jivan nitiyon.

the exbox 360 is the duusari video khel consol viksit by or produced for Microsoft and the successor to the Xbox.
The Xbox 360 competes saath soni 's plastesan 3 or nintendo 's Wii as part of the seventh generation of video game consoles.

The consol bechi out completely upon relies in sab regions except in Japan.
Several major features of the Xbox 360 are its integrated Xbox Live service that allows players to compete online ; download arcade khel, khel demos, trailers, tv shows, music or filmon ; or iske khidkiyaan media bich multimedia samarthy.
The Xbox Live also offers abhigam to vibhinn ( praayah region-specific ) third-party media streaming applications.
At their E3 prastutikaran on june 14, 2010, microsoft ghoshit a redesigned exbox 360 that would ship on the same day.
The redesigned console is slimmer than the previous Xbox 360 model or suvidhaayen ekikrut 802.11 b/g/n wi-fi, toslink s/pdif optical audio output, paanch USB 2.0 ports ( compared to the three from older versions ) and a special AUX port.
Older models of the exbox 360 have chunki maharoom discontinued.
The first new console to be released features a 250 GB hard drive, while a baad, kam mahangi sku suvidhaayen 4 gb aatanrik storage.
