A backpack ( also called rucksack, knapsack, packsack, pack ) is, in its simplest rup, a cloth bori carried on ek 's waapas or secured saath do straps that go over the shoulders, but there can be exceptions.
Lightweight types of backpacks hai sometimes worn on tabhi ek kandhe strap.
Backpacks hai praayah pasandida to handbag liye carrying baari loads or carrying koi sort of upkaran, because of the limited capacity to carry heavy weights for long periods of time in the hands.
Large backpacks, used to carry loads over 10 kg ( 22 pound ), praayah offload the largest bhaag ( up to parichay 90 % ) of unke vazan onto padded hip belt, leaving the kandhe straps mainly for stabilising the load.
This improves the potential to carry heavy loads, as the hips are stronger than the shoulders, and also increases chapaltaa or santulan, chunki the lod yatraayen nearer the wearer 's own center of mass.
In ancient times, the backpack thi prayukt as a arthath to carry the shikari 's larger khel or anya prakaar of prey and as a way of easier transport for other materials.
In the cases of larger hunts, the hunters hota dismember unke shikaar or vitarit the tukade of the animal around, prayek ek packing the meat into many wrappings and then into bags which they placed on to their backs.
The bag itself was made up of different animal hide and skin ( depending on kayaa sorts of pashu yahood in the kshetrafal ) or sewn saath by the aanton of said animals, which were woven together tightly to make a sturdy thread-like material.
mexico ( ; ; ), officially the sanyukt mexican rajya ( ), is a federal constitutional republic in North America.
It is bordered on the uttar by the sanyukt rajya ; on the dakshin or west by the prashanth samandar ; on the southeast by guatemala, Belize, and the Caribbean Sea ; and on the east by the Gulf of Mexico.
Covering almost two million square kilometres ( over 760,000 sq mi ), Mexico is the paanchvaan largest desh in the americas by kul kshetrafal or the 13th largest swatantra swadesh in the world.
With an estimated janasankhyikee of over 113 lakh, it is the sansar 's eleventh sabase populous desh or the most populous Spanish-speaking country.
Mexico is a federation comprising thirty-one states or a sangheey zila, the puunji city.
In pre-Columbian Mexico many cultures matured into advanced civilizations aise as the olmec, the toltec, the teotihuacan, the zapotec, the maaya or the azetek pehle pehla sampark saath europeans.
In 1521, Spain conquered and colonized the territory isse iske aadhaar in méxico-tenochtitlan, jisase thi administered as the viceroyalty of New Spain.
This territory hota aakhirkaar become mexico following manyata of the colony 's independence in 1821.
The post-independence period was characterized by economic asthirataa, the mexican-american yuddh or territorial cession to the sanyukt rajya, a civil war, two empires and a domestic dictatorship.
the latter led to the mexican kranti in 1910, jisase culminated saath the promulgation of the 1917 samvidhan and the emergence of the country 's current political system.
Elections held in July 2000 chihnit the pehla samay ki an vipaksh party jiti the presidency isse the sansthagat Revolutionary Party.
chunki 2006 the desh rai maharoom in the midst of a drug yuddh which has caused 60,000 deaths.
Mexico has one of the sansar 's largest economies, or is mana both a regional power and middle power.
In addition, Mexico was the first Latin American member of the sanghathan liye aarthik co-operation or vikaas oecd ( chunki 1994 ), or mana an upper-middle aay desh by the sansar Bank.
Mexico is mana a newly industrialized desh and an emerging power.
It has the fourteenth largest nammaatr jidipi or the eleventh largest jidipi by purchasing power parity.
The economy is strongly linked to those of iske uttar amareeki free vyapaar anubandh ( nafta ) saajhedaar, visheshkar the United States of America.
Mexico ranks sixth in the world and first in the Americas by kramank of unesco sansar viraasat site saath 31, or in 2007 thi the dasavaan sabase visited desh in the sansar saath 21.4 million international arrivals per year.
Babe Ruth holds the emelbi kariyar slugging pratishat record (.690 ).
In baseball statistics, slugging pratishat ( abbreviated slg ) is a lokapriy maap of the power of a hitter.
It is calculated as kul bases vibhajit by at bats :
where AB is the number of at-bats for a given player, or 1b, 2b, 3b, or hr hai the kramank of singles, yugal, tiguna, or ghar ranon, kramshah.
Walks are specifically excluded isse is gananaa.
For example, in 1920, beb ruth nibhaai uske pehla ritu liye the nai york yankis.
In 458 at bats, Ruth had 172 hits, comprising 73 singles, 36 yugal, 9 tiguna, or 54 ghar ranon, jisase brings the kul aadhaar ginati to ( 73 × 1 ) + ( 36 × 2 ) + ( 9 × 3 ) + ( 54 × 4 ) = 388.
His total number of bases ( 388 ) divided by his kul at-bats ( 458 ) is.847, uske slugging percentage for the season.
The aglaa saal he slugged.846, or ye record gai akhand jabatak 2001, jab bairi bonds hasil 411 bases in 476 at-bats, bringing his slugging percentage to.863, unmatched since.
is a role-playing video game developed and published by Square ( now Square Enix ) liye the super nintendo entertainment System in 1995.

A slightly enhanced Chrono trigar thi released liye the nintendo ds on navambar 25, 2008, in uttar america or japani, or gai on bikri in australia on February 3, 2009 and in Europe on February 6, 2009.

Hyperthermia is elevated deh taapmaana due to vifal thermoregulation ki occurs jab a deh produces or absorbs more heat than it dissipates.
Extreme temperature elevation tab becomes a chikitsa apaat requiring taatkaalik upachaar to prevent disability or death.
The most common causes shaamil ooshmaa stroke or pratikul pratikriyaayein to drugs.
The former is an acute temperature unnayan caused by expozar to excessive ooshmaa, or sangyojan of ooshmaa or ardrata, ki overwhelms the heat-regulating mechanisms.
The latter is a relatively rare side effect of anek davaayen, visheshkar those ki affect the central nervous system.
Malignant atitaap is a viral complication of kuch prakaar of general anesthesia.
Hyperthermia can also be deliberately induced using drugs or medical devices and may be prayukt in the upachaar of kuch kinds of karkat or anya sharten, sabase commonly in conjunction with radiotherapy.
atitaap differs isse fever in ki the deh 's taapmaana set point remains unchanged.
The opposite is hypothermia, which occurs jab the taapmaana boonden neeche ki jaruri to maintain saamaanya metabolism.
beliz, is a desh stith on the northeastern coast of Central America.

The `` betsi ross '' flag
A `` betsi ross '' dhvaj udati baahar san francisco City Hall
The Betsy Ross flag is an early design of the dhvaj of the sanyukt rajya, popularly attributed to betsi ross, using the common motifs of alternating red-and-white striped field with five-pointed stars in a blue canton.
the dhvaj thi designed dauraan the amareeki kranti and features 13 stars to represent the original 13 colonies.
The distinctive feature of the ross dhvaj is the vyavastha of the stars in a circle.
haalanki the betsi ross story is sweekrut by sabase america, kuch dhvaj itihaaskaaron or revisionists do not accept the Betsy Ross design as the first American flag.
According to the traditional account, the original flag was bana in june 1776, jab a choti committee—including george washington, robert morris or saapeksh george ross —visited Betsy and discussed the need for a new American flag.
Betsy accepted the job to manufacture the dhvaj, altering the cameti 's dizine by replacing the six-pointed stars with five-pointed stars.
While the betsi ross legend is questionable, the dhvaj dizine is gyaat to have maharoom in upyog by 1777 ; Alfred B. Street described it at the surrender of General Burgoyne and understood the circle of stars to represent equality among the American states.
It is one of the oldest versions of U.S. flags gyaat to maujuud ; jabaki it is nahin the oldest surviving dhvaj centuries in cloth rup, iske likeness appears on puraani shaareerik relics, namely, the contemporary battlefield paintings by John Trumbull and Charles Willson Peale.
They depict the circular star arrangement being flown from ship masts or anek anya sthaan, or yun provide the pehla gyaat aitihaasik dastavezikaran of the dhvaj 's appearance.
The seal of the U.S. Department of Veterans afares upyog the betsi ross dhvaj to represent seva to sab diggajon isse the amareeki kranti to the upasthit day.
The Betsy Ross design of 13-star US flags has been featured in many popular artworks ( sometimes inaccurately, as in washington crossing the delaware ) or films, aise as the 1960 sanskaran of Pollyanna.
The flag continues to be ek of the sabase lokapriy pratikon of the American Revolution.
A purr is a dhwani bana by sab prajati of felids or is a bhaag of billi sanchaar.
It varies between cats ( for example by loudness and tone ), and from prajati to prajati, lakin can be characterized as a tonal buzzing.
The term `` purring '' has been used liberally in sahitya, or it rai maharoom claimed ki viverrids ( sivit, nevala, genet ), bears, badgers, hyaenas ( et cetera ) purr.
Other animals ki have maharoom kaha to purr hai khargosh, squirrels, guinea pigs, tapirs, ring-tailed lemurs, elephants, raccoons and gorillas while eating.
However, using a sakht paribhaasha of purring ki nirantar dhwani utpaadan jarur vaikalpik between pulmonic egressive or ingressive airstream ( or praayah go on liye minutes ), peters ( 2002 ), in an exhaustive review of the scientific literature, reached the conclusion that until then only ‘purring cats’ ( Felidae ) and two species of genets, Genetta tigrina, and most likely also Genetta genetta, had been documented to purr.
the platypus ( ornithorhynchus anatinus ) is a semiaquatic standhari endemic to eastern Australia, including Tasmania.
Together saath the chaar prajati of ekidna, it is ek of the paanch extant prajati of monotremes, the only mammals that lay eggs instead of giving birth.
It is the sole living representative of iske parivaar ( ornithorhynchidae ) or genus ( ornithorhynchus ), haalanki a kramank of sambandhit prajati have maharoom found in the fossil record.
The unusual appearance of this egg-laying, batakh -billed, biver -tailed, otter -footed standhari manorath europea naturalists jab ve pehla encountered it, saath some considering it an elaborate fraud.
It is one of the few vishaiylla stanadhariyon, the purush platypus having a spur on the hind foot that delivers a venom capable of causing severe pain to humans.
The unique features of the platypus mek it an mahatvapurn vishay in the padhai of vikasvaadi jeevigyaan or a recognisable or iconic symbol of Australia ; it has appeared as a mascot at national events and is featured on the reverse of its 20-cent coin.
The platypus is the animal emblem of the rajya of nai South Wales.
Until the early 20th century, it thi hunted liye iske fer, lakin it is abhi surakshit throughout its range.
Although captive breeding programmes have tha tabhi simit kamyaabi or the platypus is vulnerable to the effects of pollution, it is not under any immediate threat.

In human-computer baatcheet, kaaten or paste or nakal or paste hai sambandhit cmand ki prastaav a user-interface baatcheet technique for transferring text, data, files or objects from a source to a destination.
Most ubiquitously, upayokta aavashyaktaa the kshamta to cut and paste sections of plain text.
The cut command removes the chaynit aankada isse iske asli sthiti, jabaki the nakal cmand creates a nakal ; in dono maamle the chaynit aankada is lagaai in a clipboard.
The data in the clipboard is baad inserted in the sthiti jahaan the paste command is issued.
The command names are an interface metaphor based on the shaareerik kaarividhi prayukt in pandulipi sampadan to create a page layout.
This interaction takanic rai band association saath sambandhit takneekon in aalekhiy upayokta antarfalak ki upyog ingit divaais such as a computer mouse ( by drag and drop, for example ).
Economic order maatra is the anukram maatra ki minimizes kul inventory pakadakar costs and ordering costs.
it is ek of the oldest shastreey production scheduling models.
The framework used to determine is anukram maatra is bhi gyaat as barabas eoq Model or Barabas Formula.
The model was developed by Ford W. Harris in 1913, but R. H. Wilson, a consultant jo lagu it extensively, is die credit liye uske in-depth analysis.
Stephen `` Stevie '' Ray Vaughan ( aktubar 3, 1954 – agast 27, 1990 ) thi an amareeki guitarist, singer-songwriter, and record producer.
Often referred to by his adyakshar srv, vaughan is behtareen gyaat as a founding sadsy or netaa of Double Trouble.
saath saath vadak kris layton or bassist tommy shainan, they ignited the blues revival of the 1980s.
With a career spanning seven years, Vaughan and doguna trubal consistently bechi out concert jabaki unke album aksar went gold.
He was born and uthaaya in dalas, texas, or liye a choti kaal of samay jiya in Graham, Texas.
As the younger brother of Jimmie Vaughan, vaughan prarambh playing the guitar at aayu saat or formed anek bands ki occasionally performed in local nightclubs.
At age 17, he dropped out of unchi skool or sthanantarit to austin to further pursue uske musical kariyar, joining samooh aise as Krackerjack, the Nightcrawlers, and the Cobras.
In 1977, he formed Triple Threat Revue, a band ki aakhirkaar viksit into doguna trubal or regularly performed around austin.
In 1982, Vaughan and Double Trouble performed at the montreux jaiz parv in switzaraland, catching the dhyaan of musicians David Bowie and Jackson Browne.
Bowie asked Vaughan to khel on uske aagaamee studio album let 's nrity, jabaki browne offered the band free use of his personal studio in Los Angeles to record an album.
In March 1983, Vaughan and Double Trouble were signed to apik record by diggaj ricard nirmaataa jon hamend sr. or released unke debyue album, texas baadh in june of ki year.
After successful touring, the group released the albums, Could n't Stand the mausam ( 1984 ) or aatma to aatma ( 1985 ), the latter of jisase pradarshit nai keyboardist reez Wynans.
Although his career had progressed successfully, Vaughan checked into a rehabilitation hospital in atlanta, georgia to de up a coca or daaru aadat or laute to touring with the band.
In June 1989, In Step was released or arjeet unhen a grami puraskaar liye behtareen samakaleen bluez Performance.
On August 27, 1990, Vaughan thi maare in a helicopter krash following a performance in East Troy, Wisconsin.
Vaughan 's uniquely eclectic yet teevr style thi niklaa isse a kismein of musical genres.
He was influenced by blues musicians including albert king, fredy king, otis fatafat, or muddy waters, or chattan guitarists such as Jimi Hendrix and Lonnie Mack.
His guitar playing reflected the clasik bluez or pentatonic scales.
He has received wide critical recognition liye uske guitar playing, ranking at # 6 on rolling pattharon suchi of `` 100 mahanatam Guitarists '' in 2011.
He was maranoparant inducted into the bluez haul of kirti in 2000 or a memorial pratimaa thi erected in Austin 's Auditorium Shores park.
Stevie Ray Vaughan is widely considered to be ek of the mahanatam sangeetkaaron to aaiye isse the state of Texas.

Coca-Cola is a carbonated naram peya bechi in stores, restaraan, or vending machines in every country except Cuba and North Korea.
It is produced by The Coca-Cola Company of Atlanta, Georgia, and is often referred to bas as coke ( a panjikrut trademark of the coca-cola company in the United States since March 27, 1944 ).
Originally intended as a patent medicine when it was invented in the late 19th century by John Pemberton, Coca-Cola was bought out by bijnesaman asa griggs candler, jinaki vipanan tactics led coke to iske dabadabaa of the sansar soft-drink market throughout the 20th sadi.
The company produces concentrate, jisase is tab bechi to licensed Coca-Cola bottlers throughout the world.
The bottlers, who hold territorially exclusive anubandh saath the company, upaj samaapt utpaada in dibbe or botalon isse the concentrate in sangyojan with filtered water and sweeteners.
The bottlers tab bechein, vitarit or merchandise coca-cola to khudara stores and vending machines.
Such bottlers include coca-cola udhyamon, jisase is the largest single coca-cola bottler in North America and western Europe.
The Coca-Cola company bhi bikta concentrate liye soda sroton to pramukh restaurants and food service distributors.
The Coca-Cola company rai, on avasar, introduced anya cola peya under the Coke brand name.
The most aam of ye is aahaar coke, saath anya sahit caffeine-free coca-cola, aahaar coke caffeine-free, Coca-Cola Cherry, Coca-Cola Zero, Coca-Cola Vanilla, and special versions with lemon, lime or coffee.
Based on interbrand 's behtareen vaishvik brands 2011, coca-cola thi the sansar 's sabase moolyawaan brand.

brasília ( ) is the sangheey puunji of brazil or the seat of government of the Federal District.
Administratively, the city is located in the Federal zila jisase is in the central-west Region.
physically, it is stith in the Brazilian Highlands.
It has a janasankhyikee of parichay 2,562,963 ( 3,716,996 in the mahanagar kshetrafal ) as of the 2008 IBGE estimate, making it the fourth largest city in Brazil.
However, as a mahanagar kshetrafal, it baandhane nimnatar at chathe in population.
Brasília is the largest city in the sansar ki kiya nahin maujuud at the shuruuaat of the 20th century.
Brasília has the paanchvaan largest jidipi among latin amareeki shaharon or the third in Brazil.
At around R $ 62,000 Brazilian reais ( baraabar to lagbhag $ 30,900 us dollar or €23,000 euros ), the nagar 's prati capita aay is the highest among Brazil 's largest cities.
As the national capital, brasília is the seat of sab teen shakhaon of the sangheey sarkari of Brazil.
The city bhi host the mukhyalay of anek brazilian companies.
Planning policies such as the location of residential buildings around expansive urban areas, as khub as bhawan the nagar around vishaal avenues or dividing it into sector, have sparked a bahes or pratibimb on jivan in big shaharon in the 20th century.
The city 's design divides it into gine block as khub as sector liye nirdisht kriyaayein, aise as the hotel sector, the banking Sector or the Embassy Sector.
brasília host 124 videshi embassies.
The city was planned and developed in 1956 with Lúcio Costa as the principal urban planner, Oscar niemeyer as the principal vaastu or roberto burle marks as the landscape panktiyaan.
Brasilia is in the Unesco 's sansar hertitage suchi due to iske vaastukala.
On April 22, 1960, it formally became brazil 's neshnal capital.
Viewed from above, the main portion of the nagar resembles an vayuyan or a titali.
The city is commonly referred to as puunji sangheey, or simply BSB.
Residents of Brasília are known as brasilienses or candangos ( the latter referring to those nahin born in the city but who migrated there after it was established ).
In local upyog, the shabd `` brasília '' praayah refers tabhi to the pehla prashasnic pradesh ( ra i ) bheetar the sangheey zila ( Distrito Federal ), where the most important government buildings are located.
Brasília has a adwitiya aukaat in brazil, as it is an prashasnic prabhag balki than a legal municipality like nearly all cities in Brazil.
Nationally, the term is almost always used synonymously saath the sangheey zila, jisase constitutes an indivisible Federative Unit, analogous to a state.
anek `` upgrah shaharon '' maujuud jisase hai bhi part of the Federal District.
Brasília antarrashtriya vimaanashetra is the pramukh vimaanashetra in brasília, connecting the puunji to sab pramukh brazilian shaharon and many international destinations.
It is the teesraa sabase mahatvapurn vimaanashetra in brazil, in sharten of passengers and aircraft movements.
Personifications of Germany, France, Russia, Austria-Hungary, and the sanyukt kingdom attempting to rakhana the dhakkan on the simmering cauldron of imperialist or rashtravaadi tanaav in the balkans to prevent a saamaanya europea war.
ve yahood kaamyaab in 1912 or 1913 lakin kiya nahin safal in in 1914.
The causes of World War I, which began in central Europe in late July 1914 and samaapt in 1918, shaamil anek karkon, aise as the virodh or dushmani of the chaar dashakon leading up to the war.
Militarism, alliances, samrajyavad, or rashtrawaad nibhaai pramukh bhoomikaaye in the conflict as well.
The immediate origins of the war, however, lay in the decisions taken by statesmen and generals dauraan the sankat of 1914, casus belli liye jisase thi the hatya of archduke franj ferdinand ( the archduke of austria hungarian ) and his wife Sophie by Gavrilo Princip, an irredentist Serb.
The crisis aae baad a long or mushkil shrenee of rajanyik clashes between the great shaktiyaan ( italy, frans, germany, the angrejon samrajya, the Austria-Hungarian Empire and Russia ) over European and colonial issues in the decade before 1914 that had left tensions high.
In turn these rajanyik clashes can be traced to parivartan in the santulan of power in Europe since 1867.
The adhik taatkaalik kaaran liye the yuddh thi tanaav over territory in the Balkans.
Austria-Hungary competed saath srbija or rus liye territory or influence in the pradesh or ve khinchaa the baaki of the great shaktiyaan into the virodh through their various alliances and treaties.
Although the chain of events unleashed by the hatya triggered the yuddh, the yuddh 's origins go deeper, involving neshnal raajnneeti, samskritiyon, arthshaastra, or a jatil web of alliances or counterbalances ki had developed between the various European powers since 1870.
Some of the most important long term or structural causes are : the growth of nationalism across Europe, unresolved territorial vivaadon, an intricate pranali of alliances, the abhas vishleshan of the santulan of shakti in europea, convoluted or fragmented shashan, the bahen daud of the pichhlaa dashakon, pichhlaa sainya niyojan, imperial and colonial rivalry for wealth, power and prestige, and economic and military rivalry in industry and trade – e.g., the Pig War between Austria and Serbia.
Other causes that came into play during the diplomatic crisis that preceded the war included misperceptions of intent ( e.g., the German belief that the sanyukt kingdom hota remain neutral ) or deree or misunderstandings in rajanyik sanchaar.
The various categories of explanation for World War I correspond to alag itihaaskaaron ' overall methods.
Most itihaaskaaron or lokapriy tikaakaron shaamil kalyankari isse adhik than ek shrenee of explanation to provide a rounded account of the causes of the war.
The deepest bhed among ye khate is between kahaniyaan ki dekhie it as the aprihaary or predictable nishkarsh of nishchit factors, and those that describe it as an arbitrary and unfortunate mistake.
In attributing causes for the war, historians and academics had to deal with an unprecedented baadh of memoirs or aadhikarik dastauez, released as prayek desh shaamil aajamaaya to avoid dosha liye starting the yuddh.
Early releases of information by governments, visheshkar those released liye upyog by the `` ayog on the jimmedaari of the lekhak of the yuddh '' yahood dikhaaya to be adhuri or pakshpatpurna.
In addition kuch dastauez, visheshkar rajanyik cabel between rus or frans, yahood mila to have been doctored.
Even in later decades however, jab much adhik soochna tha maharoom released, itihaaskaaron isse the vahi samskruti have maharoom shown to come to differing conclusions on the causes of the war.
Johnson 's new chart of neshnal pratik, prakashit c. 1868.
The large flags shown in the kinare hai the 37-star dhvaj of the sanyukt rajya ( flown 1867-1877 ), the royal maanak of the sanyukt kingdom, the roosi Imperial Standard, and the French tricolore with inset Imperial Eagle.
Various anya dhvaj flown by jahaajon are shown.
The dhvaj of cuba is labelled `` cuban ( so pukaara ) ``.
The Chinese dragon on the Flag of China was drawn mistakenly as a pashchimi dragon.
A national flag is a dhvaj ki symbolizes a desh.
The flag is flown by the sarkari, lakin praayah can bhi be flown by citizens of the country.
Both public and private buildings such as skulon or courthouses may makkhi the neshnal flag.
In some countries, the neshnal dhvaj hai tabhi flown isse non-military buildings on certain flag days.
There are teen pruthak prakaar of neshnal dhvaj liye upyog on jameen, or teen liye upyog at samudr, haalanki many countries use identical designs for several ( and sometimes all ) of these types of flag.
The amareeki civil yuddh ( acw ), bhi gyaat as the yuddh between the rajya or bas the civil yuddh ( dekhie namakaran ), thi a civil yuddh ladaa isse 1861 to 1865 between the sanyukt rajya ( the `` sangh '' or the `` uttar '' ) and several Southern slave states that declared their secession and formed the Confederate States of America ( the `` Confederacy '' or the `` South '' ).
The war tha iske utpatti in the samasya of gulaami, especially the extension of slavery into the western territories.
videshi shaktiyaan kiya nahin intervene.
After four years of bloody combat that left over 600,000 sainiko murde or nasht much of the dakshin 's avasanrachana, the confederacy collapsed, slavery was abolished, and the difficult Reconstruction process of restoring national unity and guaranteeing rights to the freed slaves began.
In the 1860 presidential chunaav, republicans, led by abraham lincoln, opposed expanding gulaami into sanyukt rajya ' territories.
lincoln jiti, lakin pehle uske udghaatan on kooch 4, 1861, saat cotton-based slave states formed the Confederacy.
outgoing loktantric adhyaksh james bukanan or the aavak republicans rejected secession as illegal.
Lincoln 's inaugural address ghoshit uske prashasan hota nahin initiate civil yuddh.
Eight remaining slave rajya jari to reject calls for secession.
Confederate forces seized numerous federal durgon bheetar territory claimed by the confederacy.
A Peace Conference failed to find a sulah, or dono pahalu prepared liye yuddh.
The confederates assumed ki europea deshon yahood so nirbhar on `` king kapaas `` ki ve hota intervene ; none kiya and none recognized the new Confederate States of America.
Hostilities began on april 12, 1861, jab confederate shaktiyaan fired upon Fort Sumter, a key fort held by Union troops in South Carolina.
Lincoln called for each state to provide sainikon to retake the fort ; natijatan, chaar adhik slave rajya joined the confederacy, bringing their total to eleven.
The Union soon controlled the border rajya or sthapit a naval nakebandi ki abodh the southern economy.
The Eastern theatre thi inconclusive in 1861–62.
The autumn 1862 Confederate campaign into Maryland ( a sangh rajya ) ended saath confederate retreat at the battle of antietam, dissuading angrejon hastkshep.
lincoln jari the emancipation udghoshnaa, jisase made ending slavery a war goal.
To the west, by summer 1862 the Union destroyed the Confederate river navy, then much of their western armies, and the sangh at vicksburg vibhajit the confederacy in do at the mississippi nadi.
In 1863, Robert E. Lee 's confederate incursion uttar ended at the battle of Gettysburg.
Western successes led to ulysses S. grant cmand of sab sangh armies in 1864.
In the Western Theater, William T. sharaman drove east to capchar atlanta or marched to the samudr, destroying confederate avasanrachana saath the way.
The Union marshaled the resources and manpower to attack the Confederacy from all dishanirdesh, or could afford to lado ladaaiyon of apgharshan through the overland abhiyaan towards richmond, the confederate capital.
The defending Confederate army vifal, agrani to lee 's aatmasamarpan to grant at appomattox adaalat house on april 9, 1865.
The American Civil War was ek of the earliest sachcha audyogic wars.
Railroads, the telegraph, steamships, or mass-produced hathiyaar were employed extensively.
The mobilization of civilian kaarkaanon, khaanon, shipyards, bainko, parivahan or khaanaa supplies all foreshadowed World War I.
It remains the deadliest war in American history, resulting in the mauton of an anumaanit 750,000 sainiko or an undetermined kramank of civilian casualties.
Historian jon huddleston estimates the maut toll at ten pratishat of sab Northern males 20–45 years old, and 30 percent of all Southern white males aged 18–40.
Norrie disease is a genetic vikaar ki primarily affects the najar or lagbhag sadaa leads to blindness.
In addition to the congenital ocular symptoms, kuch marijon suffer isse a pragatisheel sunanaa ghaataa starting zyaadaatar in unke 2nd dashak of life, while another portion may be mentally challenged.
Patients with Norrie disease may develop cataracts, leukocoria ( a condition where the pupils appear shwet jab lite is shone on unhen ), saath saath anya developmental mudde in the najar, aise as shrinking of the globe or the barbaad away of the iris.
Around 30–50 % of them will also have developmental delay/ mental retardation, psychotic-like suvidhaayen, incoordination of andolanon or behavioral abnormalities.
Most patients are born with normal hearing ; however, the onset of sunanaa ghaataa is bahut aam in jaldi kishoravastha.
parichay 15 % of the marijon hai anumaanit to develop all the features of the disease.
The disease affects almost only male infants at birth or soon after janam, kuki the beemaari is inherited x-linked recessive.
Only in very rare cases, mahilaon have maharoom diagnosed saath norrie beemaari as khub.
The exact incidence number is anjaan ; tabhi a few sau maamle have maharoom reported so dur.
It is a very rare vikaar ki is nahin sambhddha saath koi vishisht ethnic or racial groups.
a anubandh is an anubandh having a lawful object daalaa into voluntarily by do or adhik partiyon, prayek of whom intends to create one or more legal obligations between them.
The elements of a contract are `` prastaav '' or `` sweekruti '' by `` competent vyaktiyon '' having vidhik kshamta who exchange `` consideration '' to create `` mutuality of obligation. ''
Proof of some or all of these elements may be kiya in likhane, haalanki anubandh may be bana entirely orally or by conduct.
The remedy liye ulanghan of anubandh can be `` kshatipurti '' in the rup of muaavje of dhan or vishisht pradarshan enforced through an injunction.
Both of these remedies puraskaar the party at ghaataa the `` laabh of the saudebaaji '' or expectation damages, which are greater than mere reliance damages, as in promissory estoppel.
The partiyon may be prakritik vyaktiyon or juristic persons.
A anubandh is a legally enforceable vaada or undertaking that something will or will not occur.
The word promise can be prayukt as a vidhik paryaay liye anubandh, haalanki parvaah is jaruri as a vaada may nahin have the puraa standing of a contract, as when it is an agreement without consideration.
Contract law varies greatly from one jurisdiction to another, sahit matbhed in aam vidhi compared to civil vidhi, the prabhaav of praapt vidhi, visheshkar isse england in aam vidhi deshon, and of law codified in regional legislation.
Regarding Australian Contract Law for example, there are 40 relevant acts which prabhaav on the nirvachan of anubandh at the rashtramandal ( sangheey / neshnal ) str, or an atirikt 26 adhiniyamon at the level of the state of NSW.
In addition there are 6 international instruments or conventions which are applicable for antarrashtriya dealings, aise as the sanyukt raashtra sammelan on anubandh liye the International Sale of Goods.

Lysergic acid diethylamide, abbreviated LSD or lsd-25, bhi gyaat as lysergide ( in ) or colloquially as acid, is a semisynthetic cicedelik drug of the ergoline parivaar, khub gyaat liye iske manovaigyanik prabhaav jisase can shaamil altered soch prakriyaaon, closed and open eye visuals, synesthesia, an altered sense of time and spiritual experiences, as well as for its key role in 1960s counterculture.
It is used mainly as an entheogen, recreational drug, or as an agent in cicedelik therapy.
LSD is non-addictive, is not known to cause dimag kshati, or rai atyadhik kam toxicity relative to dose.
However, pratikul manorog pratikriyaayein aise as chintaa, paranoia, and delusions are possible.
LSD was first synthesized by Albert Hofmann in 1938 isse ergotamine, a rasinic niklaa by arthur stoll isse ergot, a anaaj kavak ki typically grows on rye.
The short form `` LSD '' comes from its early code naam lsd-25, jisase is an sankshipt liye the germany `` lysergsäure-diethylamid '' followed by a sequential number.
LSD is sensitive to oxygen, parabangnee lite, or chloride, visheshkar in samaadhaan, haalanki iske potency may pichhlaa liye saalo if it is stored away from light and moisture at low temperature.
In pure rup it is a colorless, gandhhin, tasteless solid.
LSD is typically delivered orally, praayah on a substrate aise as absorbent blotter paper, a sugar ghan, or gelatin.
In iske drav rup, it can bhi be administered by intramuscular or intravenous injection.
LSD is very potent, with 20–30 μg ( micrograms ) hone the dahalij khuraaq.
nai prayog saath alesady prarambh in 2009 for the first time in 40 years.
introduced by sandoz laboratories, saath trade-name delysid, as a drug saath vibhinn manorog upyog in 1947, alesady jaldi became a therapeutic agent that appeared to show great promise.
In the 1950s, officials at the U.S. Central pragna agency ( siie ) vichaar the drug might be lagu to dimag control or rasinic warfare ; the agency 's MKULTRA research program propagated the drug among young servicemen and students.
The subsequent recreational use of the drug by youth culture in the Western world dauraan the 1960s led to a rajnatik firestorm ki resulted in iske nishedh.
Currently, a number of organizations—including the beckley nyaas, maanchitr, heffter shodh santhaan or the albert hofmann foundation—exist to fund, encourage and coordinate research into the medicinal and spiritual uses of LSD and related psychedelics.

Some analysts have questioned the sustainability of further world janasankhyikee vikaas, citing the growing pressures on the paryaavaran, vaishvik khaanaa aapurtiyan, or urja resources.

The acre is a ikai of kshetrafal prayukt in the imperial or u.S. prathagat systems.
An acre is about 40 % of a hectare – thodaa choti than an amareeki footbaal field.

In the United rajya dono the antarrashtriya acre or the thodaa alag us survey acre are in use.
The most aam upyog of the acre is to maap tracts of jameen.
One antarrashtriya acre is paribhaashit as 4046.8564224 square metres.
During the Middle aayu, an acre thi the raashi of jameen ki could be plowed in one day with a yoke of oxen.

Language processing refers to the way human beings use words to communicate vichaar or jajbaat, or kaisaa aise sanchaar hai processed and understood.
Thus it is how the brain creates or understands bhashaa.
Most haal theories consider ki is prakram is carried out entirely by and inside the brain.
is is mana ek of the sabase characteristic abilities of the human species - perhaps the most characteristic.
However very choti is gyaat parichay it or vahin is vishaal paimaana for research on it.
Most of the knowledge acquired to date on the subject has come from patients who have suffered some type of significant head injury, whether bahya ( wounds, bullate ) or aatanrik ( strokes, tumors, apakshayi rogon ).
Studies have shown that most of the language prasanskaran krityon hai carried out in the dimagi cortex.
The essential falan of the cortical bhashaa kshetron is symbolic representation.
Even though language exists in alag form, sab of unhen hai aadhaarit on symbolic representation.

Greek mythology is the body of myths and teachings that belong to the ancient unaniyon, concerning unke devataaon or nayak, the prakruti of the sansar, or the origins or significance of unke apana cult or ritual practices.
It was a bhaag of the dharm in pracheen unaniyon or is part of religion in modern Greece and around the world, known as Hellenismos.
Modern scholars refer to and study the myths in an attempt to throw light on the religious and political institutions of pracheen unaniyon or iske sabhyataa, or to laabh samajhnaa of the prakruti of myth-making itself.
Greek mythology is explicitly embodied in a large collection of narratives, or implicitly in unani representational kala, aise as vase-paintings or votive uphaar.
Greek myth attempts to explain the origins of the world, and details the jeevandaan or adventures of a chaudee kismein of devataaon, deviyaan, nayak, heroines, or puranic jeev.
These accounts initially yahood disseminated in an oral-poetic parampara ; aaj the unani mithkon are known primarily from Greek literature.
The oldest known Greek saahitiyik strot, homer 's apik kavitaayen elliod or odissi, fokas on kaarykram surrounding the Trojan War.
Two poems by Homer 's near contemporary Hesiod, the theogony or the works or dinon, contain khate of the utpatti of the sansar, the uttaradhikaar of daivi rulers, the succession of human ages, the origin of human woes, and the origin of sacrificial practices.
Myths are also preserved in the homeric hymns, in fragments of apik kavitaayen of the apik saikil, in lyric kavitaayen, in the works of the tragedians of the paanchvaan sadi bc, in kritiyaan of vidwaanon or poets of the Hellenistic Age, and in texts from the time of the Roman Empire by writers such as Plutarch and Pausanias.
Archaeological findings provide a principal sorce of vivaran parichay unani mythology, saath devataaon or nayak pradarshit prominently in the sajaavat of many artifacts.
Geometric designs on pottery of the eighth century BC depict drishyon isse the trojan saikil as khub as the adventures of heracles.
In the succeeding archaic, shastreey, or hellenistic avadhi, homeric or vibhinn anya puranic drishyon appear, supplementing the existing literary evidence.
Greek mythology has tha an extensive influence on the samskruti, kala, or sahitya of pashchimi sabhyataa or remains part of Western heritage and language.
Poets and artists from ancient times to the present have niklaa prerana isse unani mythology or have khoja samakaleen significance and relevance in the themes.

The frank ( chihn : fr. or sfr. ; germany : franken, french or romansh : frank, italvi : franco ; code : chf ) is the currency and legal tender of Switzerland and Liechtenstein ; it is also legal tender in the Italian exclave Campione d'Italia.
Although not formally legal tender in the German exclave büsingen ( the ekmaatr vidhik karency is the european ), it is in chaudee rose upyog vahin.
The swiss neshnal bainko mudde banknotes or the sangheey mint Swissmint issues coins.
The Swiss franc is the tabhi sanskaran of the frank still jari in europea.
The smaller denomination, a hundredth of a franc, is a rappen ( rp. ) in germany, centime ( c. ) in french, centesimo ( ct. ) in italvi, or rap ( rp. ) in romansh.
The ISO code of the currency used by banks or vittiya sansthaanon is chf, haalanki `` fr. '' is prayukt by sabase vyavsaayon and advertisers ; some use SFr. ; the Latinate `` CH '' stands for Confoederatio Helvetica.
Given the different bhashaaen prayukt in switzaraland, latin is prayukt liye language-neutral inscriptions on the coins.
Sir Charles Spencer `` Charlie '' Chaplin, ( 16 april 188925 disambar 1977 ) thi a angrejon comic karta or filmkaar jo rose to fame in the silent era.
Chaplin became a vishwavyaapee pratik through uske screen persona `` the tremp `` or is mana one of the most important figures of the film industry.
His career spanned adhik than 75 saalo, isse a child in the victorian era to band to his death at the age of 88, and encompassed both adulation and controversy.
Raised in London, chaplin 's balykaal thi paribhaashit by garibi and hardship.
He was sent to a workhouse twice before the aayu of nau ; uske pita thi anupasthit, or uske maan thi vachanabaddh to a dimagi asylum.
chaplin began performing isse a yang aayu, touring music halls and later working as a stage actor and comedian.
At 19 he was signed to the prestigious fred karno company, jisase took use to america.
Chaplin was scouted by the film industry, and made uske pehla dikhaave in 1914 saath keystone studios.
He soon viksit the tremp persona or formed a vishaal fan base.
Chaplin directed his films isse an jaldi stage, or jari to hone uske shilp as he sthanantarit to the Essanay, Mutual, and First National corporations.
By 1918, he thi ek of the sabase prasiddh main in the world.
In 1919, Chaplin co-founded the vitaran company sanyukt kalakaaron, giving him complete control over his films.
His first feature-length picture was The Kid ( 1921 ), followed by A stri of paris ( 1923 ), the sunaharaa fatafat ( 1925 ), and The Circus ( 1928 ).
He refused to move to sound films in the 1930s, bajaay producing nagar lits ( 1931 ) or aadhunik times ( 1936 ) bagaiyr dialogue.
Chaplin became increasingly rajnatik or uske aglaa filmi, the great taanashaah ( 1940 ), satirised adolf Hitler.
the 1940s thi a dashak chihnit saath vivaad liye Chaplin, and his popularity declined rapidly.
He was accused of communist sympathies, jabaki uske bhagidaari in a paternity suut or vivaah to much younger women were considered scandalous.
An FBI investigation was kholi on chaplin, or he thi aakhirkaar majaboor to chhod the sanyukt rajya or settle in switzaraland.
He abandoned the Tramp for his baad films, jisase shaamil monsieur verdoux ( 1947 ), limelight ( 1952 ), a king in nai york ( 1957 ), or a Countess From Hong Kong ( 1967 ).
Chaplin wrote, directed, produced, sampadit, scored, or strecchar in sabase of uske films.
He was a perfectionist, or uske vittiya swatantraaa meant he praayah kharch saalo on the development and production of a picture.
His films are characterised by slapstick sanyukt saath pathos, or praayah visheshta the tremp struggling against adversity.
Many contain social and political themes, as khub as autobiographical tatv.
In 1972, as bhaag of a navinikrut saraahna liye uske kaary, chaplin praapt an maanad academy puraskaar liye `` the incalculable prabhaav he has had in making motion pictures the art form of this century ''.
He continues to be held in high regard, with the sunaharaa fatafat, nagar lits, aadhunik times, or the great taanashaah praayah kramit among the greatest films of all time.
Planned Parenthood Federation of America ( ppfa ), commonly shortened to niojit parenthood, is the u.S. sambhddha of the antarrashtriya niojit parenthood sangh ( IPPF ) and one of its larger members.
PPFA is a non-profit sanghathan providing reproductive swasthya or maternal and child health services.
The Planned parenthood karrwai nidhi, inc. ( ppaf ) is a sambandhit sanghathan jisase lobbies liye pro-choice vidhaan, vyapak sex education, and access to affordable health care in the United States.
Planned Parenthood is the largest U.S. pradaata of reproductive swasthya sevaayen, sahit karkat screening, hiv screening or counseling, nirodhak, and abortion.
Contraception accounts for 35 % of PPFA 's kul sevaayen or abortions khaataa liye 3 % ; ppfa conducts roughly 300,000 abortions prayek saal, among 3 lakh logon parosa.
The sanghathan rai iske jaden in brukaleen, nai york, jahaan margaret Sanger opened the country 's first birth-control clinic.
Sanger founded the American Birth control lig in 1921, jisase in 1942 became bhaag of the niojit parenthood Federation of America.
Since then, Planned parenthood rai grown to have over 820 clinics sthitiyaan in the U.S., with a total budget of US $ 1 billion.
PPFA provides an array of services to over three lakh logon in the sanyukt rajya, or supports sevaayen liye over ek lakh client baahar the sanyukt rajya.
purushon rea is latin liye `` apradhi mind ''.
In criminal law, it is viewed as one of the jaruri tatv of kuch crimes.
The standard common law test of criminal liability is usually expressed in the Latin phrase, actus non facit reum nisi purushon baithna rea, jisase arthath `` the adhinium is nahin culpable jabatak the dimag is apradhi ''.
Thus, in jurisdictions with due process, there must be an actus reus, or `` guilty act, '' accompanied by kuch str of purushon rea to constitute the aparaadhon saath jisase the prativaadee is charge ( dekhie the takneekee aavashyaktaa of concurrence ).
As a general rule, dand deyta karata nahin sanlagn to a vyakti who acted with the absence of mental fault.
the excepshan is sakht liability crimes.
In civil law, it is usually not necessary to prove a subjective dimagi tatv to sthapit deyta liye ulanghan of contract or tort, for example.
However, if a apkrutya is intentionally vachanabaddh or a anubandh is intentionally breached, aise intent may badhayen the paimaana of deyta as well as the measure of damages payable to the plaintiff.
isliye, purushon rea refers to the dimagi element of the offence that accompanies the actus reus.
In some jurisdictions, the sharten purushon rea or actus reus have maharoom replaced by alternative terminology.
In Australia, for example, the elements of the federal offences are now designated as `` fault elements '' or `` dimagi tatv '' ( purushon rea ) or `` shaareerik tatv '' or `` bahya tatv '' ( actus reus ).
This shabdaawalee thi apanaaya to badalen the aspashtataa of the latin sharten saath saral and accurate phrasing.
Ulysses S. Grant ( born Hiram Ulysses Grant ; April 27, 1822 – July 23, 1885 ) was the 18th President of the sanyukt rajya ( 1869–1877 ) following uske atyadhik kaamyaab bhoomika as a yuddh saamaanya in the duusari half of the Civil War.
Under Grant, the Union Army defeated the Confederate sainya ; having effectively ended the yuddh or secession saath the aatmasamarpan of robert E. lee 's army at Appomattox.
As president he led the kattarpanthi republicans in unke praytn to eliminate sab vestiges of Confederate nationalism and slavery.
pareshaan over uncontrolled hinsa in the dakshin or having desired to protect africa amareeki naagarikta, President Grant effectively destroyed the Ku Klux Klan in 1871.
Grant was the first President to establish Civil Service reform having nirmit a two-year federally vittposhit civil seva ayog in 1871.
in sharten of videshi niti, grant nazil an `` anpekshit kshamta for deliberation and consultation '' that promoted the national interest.
His reputation was marred by his repeated defense of corrupt appointees, and by america 's pehla audyogic aayu aarthik avsaad ( pukaara the `` dehshat of 1873 `` ) ki varchasv uske second term.
Although his Republican Party split in 1872 saath reformers denouncing use, grant was easily reelected.
By 1875 the conservative white Southern opposition regained control of every rajya in the dakshin or as he baayein the shwet house in kooch 1877 uske nitiyon yahood hone undone.
A kariyar sipaahi, he graduate isse the sanyukt rajya sainya academy at west Point and served in the Mexican–American War.
When the Civil War began in 1861, Grant trained sangh swayamsevi regiments in illinois.
In 1862, as a general he fought a series of battles and thi prachaarit to pramukh saamaanya baad forcing the aatmasamarpan of a vishaal confederate fouj or gaining control of Kentucky and most of Tennessee.
He then led sangh shaktiyaan to vijay baad aarambhik setbacks in the battle of shiloh, earning a reputation as an aggressive commander.
In july 1863, baad a long, jatil abhiyaan, grant parajeet paanch uncoordinated confederate armies ( capturing one of them ) and seized Vicksburg.
This famous victory gave the Union puraa control of the mississippi nadi, vibhajit band the pashchimi confederacy, and opened the way for more Union triumphs.
After another win at the Battle of Chattanooga in late 1863, adhyaksh abraham lincoln bana use leftinent saamaanya or commander of sab of the sangh sena.
As commanding saamaanya of the fouj, grant confronted robert E. lee in a shrenee of bahut khooni ladaaiyon in 1864 gyaat as the Overland Campaign that ended with the bottling up of Lee at Petersburg, outside the Confederate capital of Richmond.
During the siege, Grant samanvit a shrenee of vinaashkari abhiyaan shubharambh by wiliam tecumseh sharaman, philip Sheridan, and George Thomas.
Finally breaking through lee 's trenches, the sangh fouj captured Richmond in April 1865.
lee surrendered uske depleted shaktiyaan to grant at appomattox as the Confederacy collapsed.
Although pro-Confederate itihaaskaaron attacked grant as a nishthur kasaai jo jiti by brute force, sabase itihaaskaaron have hailed his military genius.
Grant 's two consecutive terms as President stabilized the nation baad the amareeki civil yuddh or dauraan the turbulent punarnirmaan period that followed.
As president, he enforced Reconstruction by enforcing civil adhikaron kanoon or lard ku klux claan hinsa.
Grant won passage of the Fifteenth amendment ; giving sanvaidhanik suraksha liye african-american voting rights.
He used the army to build the Republican Party in the dakshin, aadhaarit on blike matadaata, uttari newcomers ( `` carpetbaggers `` ) or deshi shwet supporters ( `` Scalawags. '' )
As a result, African Americans yahood represented in the u.S. congress liye the pehla samay in American history in 1870.
Reformers praised Grant 's Indian peace policy by having tutaa the deadlock on bhartiya appropriations in congress, the sristi of the falak of bhartiya commissioners to mek sudhaar suzav, or uske enlistment of quaker protestants who controlled mid western Indian agencies, that effectively curbed Congressional patronage.
Grant remained determined in keeping indiens isse hone exterminated isse shwet settler atikaraman or by the U.S. military.
Grant 's reputation as president by 1875 was at an all-time unchi liye uske pichhlaa vito of the mahangaai vidheyak, the dyodhi of the resumption of specie adhinium, and Secretary Bristow 's successful raids that shut down the Whiskey Ring.
Grant 's foreign policy, led by sachiv of rajya hamiltan machhlee, implemented antarrashtriya madhyasthata, settled the albama daawa saath britain or avoided yuddh saath spain over the Virginius Affair.

A drug pareekshan is a takneekee vishleshan of a biological namoona – liye udhaaharan mutr, bal, rakt, swead, or maukhik drav / saliva – to determine the presence or absence of specified parent drugs or their metabolites.
Major uses of drug testing hai to detect the upasthiti of pradarshan badhanaa steroids in khel or liye drugs prohibited by laws, such as cannabis, cocaine and heroin.
A `` 10-panel urine screen '' consists of the following:
Amphetamines ( sahit methamphetamine )
barbiturates
benzodiazepines
cannabinoids ( thc )
coca
methadone
methaqualone
Opiates ( codeine, morphine, heroin, oxycodone, Hydrocodone, etc. )
phencyclidine ( pcp )
propoxyphene

Space exploration is the discovery or khoji of bahari spes by arthath of space technology.
Physical khoji of spes is conducted dono by insaan spaceflights and by robotic spacecraft.
jabaki the avlokan of vastuen in spes, gyaat as khagolashastra, predates vishwasaneey ankit itihaas, it thi the vikaas of vishaal or apekshaakrit kushal rockets during the early 20th century that allowed physical space exploration to become a reality.
Common rationales for exploring space include advancing vaigyanik shodh, uniting alag raashtra, ensuring the bhavishya astitv of maanavtaa and developing military and strategic advantages against other countries.
vibhinn aalochanaon of spes khoji are sometimes made.
Space khoji rai praayah maharoom prayukt as a proxi pratiyogita liye geopolitical rivalries aise as the Cold War.
The early era of space exploration was driven by a `` Space Race `` between the Soviet Union and the sanyukt rajya, the launch of the pehla man-made object to kaksha the dharti, the ussr 's sputnik 1, on 4 aktubar 1957, or the pehla chandramaa landing by the amareeki apollo 11 craft on 20 July 1969 are often taken as the boundaries for this initial period.
The Soviet space program achieved many of the pehla milastone, sahit the pehla jeena hone in kaksha in 1957, the pehla insaan spaceflight ( euri gagarin savaar vostok 1 ) in 1961, the pehla spacewalk ( by aleksei leonov ) on 18 March 1965, the first automatic landing on another celestial body in 1966, and the launch of the first space station ( Salyut 1 ) in 1971.
After the first 20 years of exploration, focus shifted from one-off flights to bedardi hardware, aise as the spes shatal kaarykram, or isse pratiyogita to sahyog as with the International Space Station ( ISS ).
With the substantial purnataa of the iss following sts-133 in kooch 2011, yojanaayen liye spes khoji by the uese remain in flux.
nakshatra, a bush prashasan kaarykram liye a vaapasi to the chandramaa by 2020 thi judged inadequately vittposhit or unrealistic by an expert review panel reporting in 2009.
The Obama Administration prastaavit a sanshodhan of nakshatra in 2010 to fokas on the vikaas of the kaabiliyat liye crewed mishan pare kam dharti kaksha ( leo ), envisioning extending the aaparishan of the iss pare 2020, transferring the vikaas of launch vaahanon for human crews from NASA to the private sector, and developing technology to enable missions to beyond LEO, such as Earth/Moon L1, the Moon, Earth/Sun L2, near-earth asteroids, and Phobos or Mars orbit.
As of March 2011, the US Senate and House of Representatives are still working towards a sulah nasa funding vidheyak, jisase hoga sambhawatah terminate Constellation and fund development of a heavy lift launch vehicle ( HLLV ).
In the 2000s, the logon 's ganatantr of china initiated a kaamyaab maanavyukt spaceflight kaarykram, jabaki the europea sangh, japani, and India have also planned future manned space missions.
China, Russia, Japan, or india have advocated maanavyukt mishan to the chandramaa dauraan the 21st sadi, jabaki the European Union has advocated manned missions to both the Moon and Mars during the 21st century.
From the 1990s onwards, nijee ruchi began promoting spes paryaton or tab nijee spes khoji of the Moon ( see Google Lunar X Prize ).
John Calvin kulij, jr. ( july 4, 1872january 5, 1933 ) thi the 30th adhyaksh of the United States ( 1923–1929 ).
A Republican lawyer from Vermont, Coolidge worked his way up the ladder of masachusets rajya raajnneeti, aakhirkaar banane rajyapal of ki state.
His conduct during the Boston Police Strike of 1919 thrust use into the neshnal spotlite or diya use a pratishtha as a man of decisive action.
Soon after, he was elected as the 29th vaais adhyaksh in 1920 or succeeded to the presidency upon the achaanak maut of Warren G. Harding in 1923.
Elected in his own right in 1924, he gained a pratishtha as a small-government roodhiwaadee, or bhi as a man who said very little.
Coolidge restored public vishwaas in the shwet house baad the ghotaalon of uske purvavarti 's administration, and left office with considerable popularity.
As a Coolidge biographer put it, `` He embodied the spirit or ummiden of the madhya class, could interpret unke longings or express their opinions.
That he did represent the genius of the ausat is the sabase convincing pramaan of his strength. ''
Some later criticized Coolidge as bhaag of a saamaanya aalochana of laissez-faire government.
uske pratishtha underwent a punarjagran dauraan the ronaald reagan prashasan, lakin the param moolyankan of uske presidency is still divided between those who approve of his reduction of the size of government programs and those who believe the federal government should be more involved in regulating and controlling the economy.
Espresso is a concentrated peya brewed by forcing a choti raashi of nearly khaulate water under pressure through finely ground coffee beans.
Espresso often has a thicker consistency than coffee brewed by other methods, a higher concentration of suspended and dissolved solids, or crema ( arth malai, lakin hone a sandarbh to the jhaag saath a malaaidaar banaavat ki form as a parinaam of the dabaav ).
As a result of the pressurized brewing process the flavors or rasayan in a theth cap of aspreso hai bahut concentrated.
Espresso is the aadhaar liye anya peya, aise as a latte, kapuchino, macchiato, mocha, or americano.
Espresso has more caffeine per unit awaz than sabase peya, lakin the usual sevarat aakaar is smaller—a theth 60 ml ( 2 us drav ounce ) of aspreso rai 80 to 150 mg of caffeine, choti kam than the 95 to 200 mg of a standard 240 mL ( 8 US fluid ounces ) cup of drip-brewed coffee.

A contract is an agreement having a lawful object entered into voluntarily by two or adhik partiyon, prayek of jisko intends to banaaen ek or adhik vidhik dayitvon between unhen.
The elements of a anubandh hai `` prastaav '' or `` sweekruti '' by `` competent vyaktiyon '' having vidhik kshamta jo exange `` vichaar '' to banaaen `` mutuality of obligation. ''
Proof of some or all of these elements may be kiya in likhane, haalanki anubandh may be bana entirely orally or by conduct.
The remedy for ulanghan of anubandh can be `` kshatipurti '' in the rup of muaavje of dhan or vishisht pradarshan enforced through an injunction.
dono of ye remedies puraskaar the party at ghaataa the `` laabh of the saudebaaji '' or expectation damages, which are greater than mere reliance damages, as in promissory estoppel.
The parties may be prakritik vyaktiyon or juristic vyaktiyon.
A anubandh is a legally enforceable vaada or undertaking ki something will or will not occur.
The word promise can be used as a legal synonym for contract, although care is required as a promise may nahin have the puraa khadaa of a anubandh, as jab it is an anubandh bagaiyr vichaar.
Contract law varies greatly isse ek kshetradhikaar to another, sahit matbhed in aam vidhi compared to civil vidhi, the prabhaav of praapt vidhi, visheshkar isse England in common law countries, and of law codified in regional legislation.
Regarding Australian Contract Law for example, there hai 40 praasangik adhiniyamon jisase prabhaav on the nirvachan of anubandh at the rashtramandal ( sangheey / neshnal ) level, and an additional 26 acts at the level of the state of NSW.
In addition there are 6 antarrashtriya yantra or prathaon jisase hai lagu liye antarrashtriya dealings, aise as the sanyukt raashtra sammelan on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods.
Sidney Patrick Crosby, ons ( born agast 7, 1987 ) is a canadai peshewar barf hockey khilaadi jo is captain of the pittsburg penguins of the neshnal Hockey League ( NHL ).
Crosby was drafted first overall by the penguins out of the quebec pramukh junior hockey lig ( QMJHL ).
During his two-year pramukh junior kariyar saath the rimouski océanic, he arjeet back-to-back CHL Player of the Year awards and led his club to the 2005 Memorial Cup final.
Nicknamed `` The aglaa ek ``, he thi ek of the sabase atyadhik regarded draft chayan in hockey itihaas, agrani anek to refer to the 2005 draft lottery as the `` Sidney Crosby Sweepstakes ''.
In his pehla enechael ritu, crosby samaapt chathe in lig scoring saath 102 ank ( 39 lakshya, 63 assists ) or thi a runner-up for the Calder Memorial Trophy ( won by Alexander Ovechkin ).
By his second season, he led the enechael saath 120 ank ( 36 lakshya, 84 assists ) to capchar the art ross trophy, banane the youngest khilaadi and the only teenager to win a scoring title in any major North American sports league.
That same season, Crosby also won the Hart Memorial Trophy as the Professional Hockey Writers Association 's choice for most moolyawaan khilaadi or the lester B. pimmersan puraskaar as the enechael khilaadi sangh 's chunaav liye sabase bakaayaa khilaadi, banane the saatvaan khilaadi in NHL history to earn all three awards in one year.
Crosby started the 2007–08 season with the toli 's captaini or subsequently led unhen to the 2008 stanley cap final, jahaan ve yahood parajeet by the Detroit Red Wings in six games.
The Penguins laute to the final viruddh detroit the following saal or jiti in saat khel ; Crosby became the youngest captain in NHL history to win the Stanley Cup.
In the 2009–10 season, Crosby scored a career-high 51 goals, tying use saath steven stamkos liye the prakshepastra richard trophy as the league-leader ; saath 58 assists, he totaled 109 points, second in the NHL.
During the off-season, crosby praapt the chihnit mesier netritv puraskaar.
In 2010–11, crosby sustained a concussion as a parinaam of hits to the head in back-to-back games.
The injury left him sidelined liye ten or a half maheene.
However, after playing aath khel in the 2011–12 ritu, crosby 's concussion-like lakshan laute in disambar 2011, or he kiya not return until mid-March 2012.
Internationally, Crosby has represented Canada in numerous tournaments liye the desh 's junior or main 's tiimon.
After competing in the 2003 u-18 junior sansar cap, he represented canada in back-to-back iihf sansar u20 championships, jeetna silver in 2004 and gold in 2005.
At the 2006 iihf sansar championships, he led the toornament in scoring, jabaki bhi kamai sheersh Forward and All-Star Team honours.
Four years later, Crosby was named to Team Canada liye the 2010 sheet olympic in vainkuvar.
Playing the sanyukt rajya in the sunaharaa padak khel, he scored the game-winning goal in overtime.
A United rajya cent, bhi gyaat as a penny.
`` my do saint '' ( 2¢ ) or iske longer sanskaran `` put my do saint in '' is an sanyukt rajya ( us ) idiomatic abhivyakti, liya isse the asli English idiom expression : to put in `` my two pennies worth '' or `` my tuppence worth. ''
it is prayukt to preface the antarim stating of one’s opinion.
By virodhatmak the raay to follow – suggesting iske maan is tabhi do saint, a bahut choti amount – the user of the phrase hopes to lessen the impact of a possibly statement, showing politeness and humility.
however, it is bhi sometimes prayukt saath vidambnaa when expressing a strongly felt opinion.
The phrase is also used out of aadat to preface uncontentious opinions.

The Chinese Civil War was a civil war in China fought between forces loyal to the government of the ganatantr of china led by the kuomintang ( kmt ) or shaktiyaan of the communist party of china ( CPC ).
The war began in April 1927, amidst the uttari expedition, or essentially ended jab pramukh active battles ceased in 1950.
The conflict eventually resulted in do de facto rajya, the ganatantr of china ( aaraosi ) in taiwan or the logon 's ganatantr of china ( piarsi ) in menland China, both claiming to be the legitimate government of China.
The war represented an ideological vibhajit ( baayein vs. sahi ) between the communist cpc, and the KMT 's brand of Nationalism.
The civil war continued intermittently jabatak let 1937, jab the do partiyon formed a duusari sanyukt Front to counter a Japanese invasion.
China 's full-scale civil yuddh resumed in 1946, a saal baad the samaapt of hostilities with Japan.
After four more years, 1950 saw the cessation of major military hostilities—with the newly santhaapit logon 's ganatantr of china controlling menland china ( sahit hyenan ), or the ganatantr of china 's kshetradhikaar hone pratibandhit to Taiwan, Penghu, Quemoy, Matsu and several outlying islands.

is ensured pla lokapriy support.

Cross-Strait relations have maharoom hindered by sainya khatre or rajnatik or aarthik dabaav, visheshkar over Taiwan 's political status, with both governments officially adhering to a `` One-China policy. ''
The PRC still actively claims Taiwan as part of its territory and continues to threaten the aaraosi saath a sainya akraman if the aaraosi officially declares swatantraaa by badalanaa iske naam to or gaining international recognition as the Republic of Taiwan.
The ROC mutually claims mainland china, or ve dono continue the lado over rajanyik recognition.
Today, the war as such occurs on the political and economic fronts in the form of cross-Strait relations ; however, the do pruthak de facto rajya have band aarthik ties.
The One Hundred Twelfth United States congress thi the baithak of the vidhaan shakha of the sanyukt rajya sangheey sarkari, isse janvari 3, 2011 jabatak January 3, 2013.

maal in the sanyukt rajya is commonly measured in sharten of jaal laayak, which is the sum of all assets, including home equity, minus all liabilities.
The total net worth of US households or nonprofit sanghathan 1945–2009, unadjusted liye mahangaai or janasankhyikee change.
For example, a household in kabza of an $ 800,000 house, $ 5,000 in paraspar nidhi, $ 30,000 in gaadiyaan, $ 20,000 laayak of bhandar in their own company, and a $ 45,000 IRA would have assets totaling $ 900,000.
Assuming ki is household hota have a $ 250,000 bandhak, $ 40,000 in car lone, and $ 10,000 in credit card debt, its debts would total $ 300,000.
subtracting the debts isse the laayak of is household 's asset ( 900,000 - $ 300,000 = $ 600,000 ), this household would have a net worth of $ 600,000.
jaal laayak can vary saath fluctuations in value of the underlying assets.
The wealth —more specifically, the median net worth—of households in the United States is varied with sambandh to res, shiksha, bhugolic sthaan or ling.
As one would expect, households saath vrihad aay visheshta the ucchtam jaal worths, haalanki unchi aay can nahin be taken as an always accurate indicator of net worth.
Overall the number of wealthier households is on the vruddhi, saath baby boomers hitting the highs of unke careers.
In addition, wealth is unevenly vitarit, saath the wealthiest 25 % of us households owning 87 % of the maal in the United States, which was $ 54.2 trillion in 2009.
Including human capital such as skills, the United Nations anumaanit the kul maal of the sanyukt rajya in 2008 to be $ 118 trillion.
This article deals with Selective Dorsal Rhizotomy ( SDR ) rather than the rhizotomy prakriyaaon liye pidaa raahat ; liye those prakriyaaon, jisase have begun to lo the naam `` rhizotomy '' in nishchit udhaaharan, dekhie facet rhizotomy and similar.
A rhizotomy ( ) is a term chiefly referring to a neurosurgical procedure that selectively destroys problematic tantrika jaden in the spinal cord, sabase praayah to relieve the lakshan of neuromuscular sharten aise as spastic diplegia or anya form of spastic cerebral palsy.
The selective dorsal rhizotomy ( SDR ) for spastic cerebral palsy has been the pramukh upyog of rhizotomy liye neurosurgeons specialising in spastic cp chunki the 1980s ; in is surgery, the spasticity-causing nerves are isolated and then targeted and destroyed.
The sensory nerve roots, where spasticity is located, hai pehla alag isse the motor ones, or the tantrika machhlee to be kaaten hai tab pahachaanaa via electromyographic stimulation.
The ones producing spasticity hai tab selectively lesioned with tiny electrical pulses.
In spasticity, rhizotomy precisely lakshya or nasht the kshatigrast nerves ki don’t praapt gamma amino butyric acid, which is the core problem for people with spastic cerebral palsy.
These over-firing, non-gaba-absorbing nerves generate asaamaanya vidyut kaaryaklap dauraan the emg pareekshan phase in sdr or hai yun mana to be the sorce of the rogi 's hypertonia ; ve hai eliminated saath the electrical pulses once identified, while the remaining nerves and nerve routes carrying the correct messages remain fully intact and untouched.
This means that the spasticity is permanently dissolved, and that this is done without affecting nervous pranali samvedansheeltaa or falan in anya kshetron, kuki the tabhi nerves nasht hai the over-firing ones jimmedaar liye the mansapeshi tightness.
The terms rhizotomy and neurotomy are also increasingly banane interchangeable in the upachaar of dirghakaalik waapas pain from degenerative disc disease.
This is a kaarividhi pukaara a facet rhizotomy or is nahin a sargical kaarividhi lakin is bajaay kiya on an outpatient aadhaar using a saral jaanch to lagu radiofrequency waves to the impinged pain-causing nerve root lying between the facet joint and the vertebral body.
Such radio frequency nerve lesioning results in five to eight or more months of pain relief before the nerve regenerates and another golakaar of the kaarividhi needs to be performed.
A facet rhizotomy is just one of many different forms of radiofrequency ablation, or iske upyog of the `` rhizotomy '' naam chahie not be confused with the SDR procedure.

Lower Ninth ward is a pados of the nagar of New Orleans.
As the naam implies, it is bhaag of the Ninth Ward of New Orleans.
The Lower Ninth Ward is often thought of as the sampurna kshetrafal bheetar nai orlions downriver of the audyogic kanal ; however, the nagar niyojan Commission divides this area into the Lower Ninth Ward ( 2 ) and Holy Cross ( 3 ) neighborhoods.
The term `` Lower '' refers to its sthaan dur towards the munh of the mississippi nadi, `` bas '' or `` neeche '' the rest of the city in local geographic terminology.
But the 9th ward, jaise sab wards in nai orlions, is a voting district.
the 9th ward thi added as a matdaan zila in 1852.

Red and naarangi tinted chandramaa, as dekhi isse dharti dauraan a chandra grahan, jahaan the Earth comes between the Moon and Sun
The Moon is the only natural satellite of the Earth, and the paanchvaan largest upgrah in the saura System.
It is the largest natural satellite of a grah in the saura pranali saapeksh to the aakaar of iske praathmik, having 27 % the vyas or 60 % the ghanatv of Earth, resulting in its mass.
The chandramaa is the duusari densest upgrah baad io, a satellite of Jupiter.
The Moon is in synchronous rotation with Earth, always showing the same face with its near paksh chihnit by andhera volcanic mariya ki bharan between the ujjwal pracheen crustal hilands or the prominent prabhaav craters.
It is the brightest object in the sky after the Sun, although its sataha is darasal bahut andhera, saath a reflectance samaan to ki of koyale.
Its prominence in the sky and its regular cycle of phases have, chunki pracheen times, bana the chandramaa an mahatvapurn saanskrithik influence on bhashaa, panchang, art and mythology.
The Moon 's gravitational influence produces the samandar tides or the minute lengthening of the day.
The Moon 's current orbital alahada, parichay tees times the vyas of the dharti, kalyankari it to appear lagbhag the same size in the sky as the Sun, allowing it to cover the Sun nearly precisely in total solar eclipses.
This matching of apparent vizual aakaar is a coincidence.
The Moon 's linear distance from the dharti is philhal increasing at a rate of 3.82±0.07cm prati saal, but this rate is not constant.
The Moon is thought to have formed nearly 4.5 arab saalo pehle, nahin long after the Earth.
Although there have been several hypotheses liye iske utpatti in the past, the vartmaan sabase widely sweekrut spashtikaran is ki the chandramaa formed from the debris left over after a giant impact between Earth and a Mars -sized body.
the chandramaa is the tabhi celestial deh anya than dharti on which humans have set foot.
The Soviet Union 's Luna programme was the first to reach the Moon with unmanned spacecraft in 1959 ; the United States ' NASA apollo kaarykram hasil the tabhi maanavyukt mishan to tithi, shuruuaat saath the pehla maanavyukt chandra orbiting mishan by apollo 8 in 1968, or chah maanavyukt chandra avataran between 1969 and 1972, with the first being Apollo 11.
ye mishan laute over 380 kg of chandra rox, jisase have maharoom prayukt to develop a geological samajhnaa of the chandramaa 's origins, the formation of its internal structure, and its subsequent history.
After the Apollo 17 mission in 1972, the chandramaa rai maharoom visited tabhi by unmanned spacecraft, notably by the final Soviet Lunokhod rover.
chunki 2004, japani, china, india, the sanyukt rajya, or the European Space Agency have each sent lunar orbiters.
These spacecraft have contributed to confirming the discovery of lunar jal barf in permanently shadowed craters at the danda or bandhi into the chandra regolith.
Future manned missions to the Moon have been planned, sahit sarkari as khub as privately vittposhit praytn.
The Moon remains, under the Outer Space Treaty, free to all raashtra to explore liye shantipurna uddeshy.
ronaald wilson reagan ( ; farvari 6, 1911 – June 5, 2004 ) was the 40th President of the United States ( 1981–1989 ).
Prior to that, he was the 33rd Governor of california ( 1967–1975 ), or a radio, filmi or television actor.
Born in Tampico, Illinois, and raised in dikson, reagan thi shikshit at ureka college, kamai a snaatak of Arts degree in economics and sociology.
After graduating, Reagan sthanantarit pehla to iova to kaary as a radio prasarankarta or tab, in 1937, to los angeles jahaan he began a kariyar as an actor, first in films and later television.
Some of his sabase notable films shaamil knute rockne, sab amareeki ( 1940 ), Kings Row ( 1942 ), and Bedtime for Bonzo ( 1951 ).
Reagan served as President of the Screen Actors gild or baad as a pravaktaa liye saamaanya electric ( ge ) ; uske prarambh in raajnneeti occurred dauraan uske kaary liye GE.
originally a sadsy of the loktantric party, uske sthitiyaan began shifting rightward in the 1950s, and he switched to the Republican Party in 1962.
After delivering a rousing vaak in support of bairi goldwater 's adhyakshiya ummidavaari in 1964, he thi persuaded to talash the california governorship, jeetna do years later and again in 1970.
He was defeated in his run for the republican adhyakshiya namakan in 1968 or in 1976, lakin jiti dono the namakan or saamaanya chunaav in 1980, defeating incumbent Jimmy Carter.
As president, reagan implemented sweeping nai rajnatik and economic initiatives.
His supply-side economic policies, utaavle `` reaganomics ``, advocated reducing kar daron to spur aarthik vikaas, controlling the dhan supplai to reduce mahangaai, deregulation of the economy, and reducing government spending.
In his first term he survived an hatya attempt, took a mushkil lakeer viruddh majdoor sangh, ghoshit a nai yuddh on davaayen, and ordered an invasion of Grenada.
He was re-elected in a bhuskhalan in 1984, proclaiming ki it was `` Morning in America ``.
His second term was primarily marked by foreign matters, aise as the samaapti of the thanda yuddh, the 1986 bombing of libya, and the revelation of the Iran-Contra affair.
Publicly describing the Soviet Union as an `` evil empire ``, he supported anti-communist movements vishwavyaapee or kharch uske pehla pad forgoing the ranneeti of détente by ordering a vishaal sainya buildup in an bahen res saath the ussr.
Reagan negotiated with Soviet saamaanya sachiv mikhail gorbachev, culminating in the inf sandhi and the decrease of both countries ' nuclear arsenals.
reagan baayein daftar in 1989.
In 1994, the former president disclosed ki he tha maharoom diagnosed saath alzimer 's beemaari earlier in the year ; he died ten years later at the age of 93.
A conservative icon, he ranks highly in public opinion polls of u.S. raashtrapatiyon or is credited liye generating an vaicharik punarjagran on the amareeki rajnatik sahi.
Complete niyat of scrolls, constituting the entire Tanakh.
The Tanakh (, or ; also Tenakh, tenak, tanach ) is a naam prayukt in judaism liye the canon of the Hebrew Bible.
The tanakh is bhi gyaat as the masoretic Text or the Miqra.
The name is an acronym formed from the initial Hebrew letters of the Masoretic Text 's teen paramparaagat subdivisions : the tora ( `` shikshan '', bhi gyaat as the paanch kitabe of musa ), nevi'im ( `` nabiyon '' ) or ketuvim ( `` Writings '' ) —hence TaNaKh.
The name `` Miqra '' ( מקרא ), arth `` ki jisase is padhaa '', is an alternative Hebrew term for the Tanakh.
The books of the Tanakh were relayed with an accompanying oral parampara passed on by prayek peedhee, pukaara the Oral Torah.

Four sitting raashtrapatiyon have maharoom maare : abraham lincoln ( the 16th adhyaksh ), james A. garfield ( the 20th adhyaksh ), William McKinley ( the 25th President ) and John F. Kennedy ( the 35th President ).

kuch hamalavar tha questionable dimagi sthirataa, and a few were judged legally insane.

Oklahoma ( ) ( pawnee : uukuhuúwa, cay : gahnawiyoˀgeh ) is a state located in West South Central United States.
Oklahoma is the 20th sabase extensive or the 28th sabase populous of the 50 United States.
The state 's name is niklaa isse the choctaw shabd okla or humma, arth `` red logon '', or it is gyaat informally by its nickname, The Sooner State.
Formed by the combination of oklahoma territory or bhartiya territory on navambar 16, 1907, oklahoma was the 46th state to enter the union.
Its nivaasiyon hai gyaat as oklahomans or, informally `` okies '', or iske capital and largest city is Oklahoma City.
A major producer of natural gas, oil, and agriculture, oklahoma relies on an aarthik aadhaar of vimaanan, urja, doorsanchaar, and biotechnology.
It has one of the tivratam growing economies in the swadesh, ranking among the sheersh rajya in prati capita aay vikaas or sakal domestic product growth.
oklahoma nagar or tulasa serve as oklahoma 's praathmik aarthik anchors, with nearly two thirds of Oklahomans living within their metropolitan statistical areas.
With small pahaad seemayen, preyari, mesas, or purvi wanon, sabase of oklahoma jhooth in the great maidan or the U.S. Interior Highlands —a region especially prone to severe weather.
In addition to having a prevalence of angrezi, germany, scottish, irish or deshi amareeki ancestry, adhik than 25 deshi amareeki languages are spoken in Oklahoma, second only to California.
Oklahoma is located on a sangam of teen pramukh amareeki saanskrithik regions or historically parosa as a root liye choupayon drive, a gantavy for southern settlers, and a government-sanctioned territory for Native Americans.
