Natural Gas is usually measured by awaz in the sanyukt rajya and is stated in cubic feet.
A cubic foot of gas is the raashi of gas needed to bharan a awaz of ek ghan pair antargat niyat sharten of dabaav or temperature.to maap larger amounts of prakritik gas, a `` therm '' is used to denote 100 cubic feet, and `` mcf '' is used to denote 1,000 cubic feet.
To provide greater accuracy in comparing fuels, urja saamagree is measured in sharten of `` angrejon thermal Units ( BTU 's ). ''
A BTU is the amount of heat jaruri to uthaayen ek pound of jal ( lagbhag a pint ), ek oopaadhi Fahrenheit at or close to its point of maximum density.
One British therm ( symbol thm ) is a non- si ikai of ooshmaa urja baraabar to 100,000 British thermal units ( BTU ).
It is lagbhag the urja samatuly of burning 100 ghan feet ( praayah referred to as 1 ccf ) of prakritik gas.
Since ( Natural Gas ) meters measure volume and not energy content, a therm factor is prayukt by ( prakritik ) gas companiyaan to badalen the awaz of gas prayukt to iske ooshmaa samatuly, or yun gananaa the vaastavik urja use.
the therm factor is praayah in the units therms/CCF.
It will vary saath the mixr of hydrocarbons in the prakritik gas.
Natural gas with a ucchtar than ausat visheshgyata of ithen, propen or beauten will have a higher therm factor.
impurities, aise as carbon dioxide or nitrogen, lower the therm factor.
The volume of the gas is gananaa as if measured at maanak taapmaana or dabaav ( STP ).
The heat content of natural gas is solely nirbhar on the sangyojan of the gas, or is swatantra of taapmaana or pressure.
One therm is baraabar to parichay 105.5 megajoules, 25,200 kilocalories or 29.3 kilowatt-hours.
One therm can bhi be provided by parichay of prakritik gas.
The therm sometimes has been uljhan saath the thermie ( dekhie neeche ).
the names of dono ikai come from the Greek word for heat.
A thermie ( th ) is a metric ikai of ooshmaa urja, bhaag of the meter-tonne-second pranali sometimes prayukt by europea engineers.
The thermie is equal to the amount of urja jaruri to uthaayen the taapmaana of 1 ton of jal by 1 °C.
The thermie is equivalent to 1,000 kilocalories, 4.1868 megajoules or 3968.3 BTU.
The American civil yuddh ( acw ), bhi gyaat as the yuddh between the rajya or bas the civil yuddh ( dekhie namakaran ), thi a civil yuddh ladaa isse 1861 to 1865 between the sanyukt rajya ( the `` sangh '' or the `` uttar '' ) and several Southern slave states that declared their secession and formed the Confederate States of America ( the `` Confederacy '' or the `` South '' ).
The yuddh tha iske utpatti in the samasya of gulaami, visheshkar the ekstansion of gulaami into the western territories.
Foreign powers kiya nahin intervene.
After four years of bloody combat that left over 600,000 soldiers dead and destroyed much of the South 's avasanrachana, the confederacy collapsed, gulaami thi abolished, or the mushkil punarnirmaan prakram of restoring national unity and guaranteeing rights to the freed slaves began.
In the 1860 presidential election, Republicans, led by Abraham lincoln, opposed expanding gulaami into sanyukt rajya ' territories.
lincoln jiti, lakin pehle uske udghaatan on kooch 4, 1861, seven cotton-based slave states formed the Confederacy.
Outgoing Democratic President james bukanan or the aavak republicans asweekrut secession as illegal.
Lincoln 's inaugural address declared his prashasan hota nahin initiate civil yuddh.
Eight baaki slave rajya jari to reject calls for secession.
Confederate forces seized numerous sangheey durgon bheetar territory claimed by the confederacy.
A Peace sammelan vifal to dhundhen a sulah, or dono sides prepared for war.
The Confederates assumed that European countries yahood so nirbhar on `` king kapaas `` ki ve hota intervene ; none kiya or none pahachaanaa the nai confederate rajya of America.
Hostilities began on April 12, 1861, when Confederate forces fired upon fort sumter, a kunjee fort yojit by sangh sainikon in dakshin carolina.
Lincoln called for each state to provide troops to retake the fort ; natijatan, chaar adhik slave rajya joined the confederacy, bringing their total to eleven.
The Union soon niyantrit the kinaaraa rajya or sthapit a naval blockade that crippled the southern economy.
The Eastern Theater was inconclusive in 1861–62.
the patjhad 1862 confederate abhiyaan into maryland ( a sangh rajya ) ended saath confederate retreat at the Battle of Antietam, dissuading British intervention.
Lincoln issued the Emancipation udghoshnaa, jisase bana samaapti gulaami a yuddh lakshya.
To the west, by summer 1862 the Union destroyed the confederate nadi navy, tab much of unke pashchimi sena, or the sangh at vicksburg vibhajit the confederacy in do at the Mississippi River.
In 1863, Robert E. Lee 's confederate incursion uttar ended at the battle of gettysburg.
Western successes led to ulysses S. grant cmand of sab sangh sena in 1864.
In the Western Theater, William T. Sherman drove east to capture Atlanta or marched to the samudr, destroying confederate avasanrachana saath the way.
The Union marshaled the resources and janashakti to akraman the confederacy isse sab dishanirdesh, or could afford to lado ladaaiyon of apgharshan through the overland abhiyaan towards Richmond, the Confederate capital.
The defending Confederate army failed, agrani to lee 's aatmasamarpan to grant at appomattox Court House on April 9, 1865.
The American Civil War was ek of the earliest sachcha audyogic yudhon.
Railroads, the telegraph, steamships, or mass-produced hathiyaar were employed extensively.
The mobilization of civilian factories, mines, shipyards, banks, parivahan or khaanaa aapurtiyan sab foreshadowed sansar War I.
It remains the deadliest war in amareeki itihaas, resulting in the mauton of an anumaanit 750,000 sainiko or an undetermined number of civilian casualties.
Historian John huddleston estimates the maut toll at ten pratishat of sab uttari males 20–45 saalo old, and 30 percent of all Southern white males aged 18–40.

chunki 2007, he rai appeared saath uske blended family on Keeping Up with the Kardashians.
Escherichia coli ( ; commonly abbreviated E. kolai ) is a gram-negative, rod-shaped bacterium ki is commonly found in the lower intestine of warm-blooded organisms ( endotherms ).
Most E. coli strains are harmless, but some serotypes can kaaran gambhir khaanaa vishaaktata in insaano, or hai occasionally responsible for product recalls due to food contamination.
The harmless strains are part of the normal flora of the gut, or can laabh unke host by producing vitamin k2, or by preventing the sthapana of rogajanak jeevanu within the intestine.
E. coli and related bacteria constitute parichay 0.1 % of aant flora, or fecal–oral hastantaran is the pramukh root through jisase rogajanak strains of the bacterium cause disease.
Cells are able to jivit baahar the deh liye a simit raashi of samay, jisase makes unhen adarsh indicator jeevon to pareekshan environmental samples for fecal contamination.
There is, however, a growing deh of shodh ki rai examined environmentally persistent E. coli which can survive for extended periods outside of the host.
The bacterium can also be grown easily or inexpensively in a prayogshaala setting, or rai maharoom intensively investigated for over 60 years.
E. coli is the sabase widely padhai prokaryotic model sajiv, or an mahatvapurn prajati in the field of jaevpraudyogiki or sookshmjaiviki, where it has served as the host organism for the majority of work with recombinant DNA.
Area code 217 is the North amareeki telephone kshetrafal code liye much of pashchimi or central Illinois.
the 217 kshetrafal shaamil illinois ' puunji, springfield, plus Champaign, Urbana, Decatur, Danville, Quincy, and Rantoul.

Image of the largest antarctic ozone chhed kabhi ankit ( sitambar 2006 ), over the Southern pole
Layers of the maahaul ( nahin to scale )
Ozone depletion describes do pruthak lakin sambandhit phenomena observed chunki the let 1970s : a sthir manaahi of parichay 4 % prati dashak in the total volume of ozone in Earth 's stratosphere ( the ozone layer ), and a much larger springtime decrease in stratospheric ozone over Earth 's polar regions.
The latter phenomenon is referred to as the ozone hole.
In addition to these well-known stratospheric phenomena, there hai bhi springtime dhruviya tropospheric ozone depletion kaarykram.
The details of polar ozone hole formation differ from that of mid-latitude thinning, lakin the sabase mahatvapurn prakram in dono is catalytic destruction of ozone by atomic halogens.
The main sorce of ye hellojan anu in the stratosphere is photodissociation of man-made halocarbon refrigerants ( CFCs, freons, halons ).
These compounds are transported into the stratosphere baad hone utsarjit at the surface.
Both types of ozone depletion were observed to badhayen as emissions of halo-carbons increased.
CFCs and other contributory substances are referred to as ozone-depleting substances ( ODS ).
Since the ozone layer prevents most harmful UVB wavelengths ( 280–315 nm ) of ultraviolet light ( UV light ) from passing through the Earth 's maahaul, observed or prakshipt decreases in ozone have utpann vishwavyaapee chintaa agrani to apnaanaa of the montrial protocol ki bans the utpaadan of cfcs, halons, or anya ozone-depleting rasayan aise as carbon tetrachloride and trichloroethane.
It is suspected that a kismein of biological consequences aise as increases in skin karkat, cataracts, kshati to paudhe, or katautee of plavak populations in the samandar 's photic mandal may parinaam isse the increased UV exposure due to ozone depletion.
The Preamble to the United States Constitution is a brief introductory statement of the samvidhan 's aadharbhoot uddeshy or guiding siddhanth.
It states in saamaanya sharten, or nyaayalayon have referred to it as vishwasaneey pramaan of, the founding fathers ' iraadon regarding the samvidhan 's arth or kayaa ve hoped the Constitution would achieve as it pertains to all of the people of the United States.
As the phrase, `` we the logon '' suggests ki the nai sarkari originates isse the logon of the sanyukt rajya or it set into gati a sawaal as it pertains to ki vishaal janasankhyikee concerning the vyaktigat adhikaron or samta among sab logon ; is can be seen most broadly in the divide between republicanism and social democracy.

Map of the United Nations ( UN ) member rajya, saath unke territories ( sahit nirbhar territories ) pahachaanaa by the UN in blue
There are sanyukt raashtra ( un ) sadsy rajya, or prayek of unhen is a sadsy of the United Nations General Assembly.
The maapdand liye pravesh of nai sadasyon hai niyat out in the sanyukt Nations Charter, Chapter II, Article 4:
A recommendation for admission from the Security Council requires affirmative votes from at least nau of the parishad 's pandrah sadasyon, saath none of the paanch sthai sadasyon matdaan viruddh.
The Security Council 's recommendation must then be subsequently sweekrut in the saamaanya sabha by a two-thirds majority vote.
In principle, only sovereign rajya can become un sadasyon, or philhal sab un sadasyon hai sovereign rajya ( haalanki a few sadasyon were not sovereign when they joined the UN ).
Because a state can only be admitted to the UN by the approval of the Security Council and the General Assembly, a number of states that may be considered sovereign states according to the Montevideo sammelan maapdand hai nahin sadasyon kuki the un karata nahin consider unhen to possess prabhutaa, mukhyatah due to the kami of antarrashtriya manyata or vipaksh from certain members.
In addition to the member states, the UN also invites non-member states ( currently two : the Holy See and Palestine ), intergovernmental organizations, and other antarrashtriya sanghathan or entities jinaki statehood or prabhutaa hai nahin precisely paribhaashit, to become observers at the saamaanya sabha, allowing unhen to participate or bolo, lakin nahin vote, in saamaanya sabha meetings.
The Eiffel Tower (, ) is an iron lattice tower located on the champ de mangal in paris, namit baad the ejeeniyar gustave effil, jinaki company designed and built the tower.
Erected in 1889 as the entrance arch to the 1889 World 's Fair, it has become both a vaishvik saanskrithik pratik of frans or ek of the sabase recognizable structures in the sansar.
The tower is the tallest structure in Paris or the most-visited sashulk smarak in the sansar ; 7.1 lakh logon ascended it in 2011.

The tower received its 250 millionth aagatuk in 2010.
The tower stands lambaa, parichay the vahi oonchaai as an 81-storey building.
During its nirmaan, the effil minar surpassed the washington smarak to assume the sheershak of the tallest man-made dhaancha in the sansar, a title it held for 41 years, until the Chrysler Building in New York City was built in 1930.
Because of the addition, in 1957, of the antina atop the effil minar, it is abhi taller than the Chrysler Building.
Not including broadcast antennas, it is the second-tallest dhaancha in frans, baad the Millau Viaduct.
The tower rai teen str liye vizitor.
Tickets can be purchased to ascend, by seedhiyaan or lift ( lift ), to the first and second levels.
the chalanaa isse maidan str to the pehla str is over 300 steps, as is the walk from the first to the second level.
The third and highest level is accessible tabhi by lift—stairs do maujuud lakin hai praayah band to the public.
The first and duusari str have restaraan.
The tower has become the sabase prominent pratik of dono paris or frans, praayah in the establishing shot of films set in the city.

The canadai footbaal lig or cfl ( ' [ lcf ] in french ) is a professional sports league located in Canada.
The CFL is the highest level of pratiyogita in canadai footbaal, a rup of gridiron footbaal closely sambandhit to American football.
Its eight current teams, which are located in aath pruthak shaharon, hai vibhajit into do vibhaajan of chaar tiimon prayek — the east prabhag and the West Division.

Following the regular season, the three teams with the best records in their division ( except if the fourth place team in one division has a better record than the third place team in the anya prabhag, jab the toli saath the behatar ricard makes the playoffs or `` crosses over '' to the anya prabhag 's playoff ) compete in the lig 's three-week diviginal playoffs, jisase culminate in the late-november dhoosar Cup championship, the country 's largest annual sports and television event.
The CFL was officially founded on January 19, 1958, making it the duusari oldest gridiron footbaal lig in uttar america still in aaparishan, haalanki sab iske tiimon long predate the modern formation of the league.
It is the highest level of play in Canadian football, the most popular football lig in canada, or the second-most lokapriy pramukh khel lig in canada, baad the neshnal hockey League.
Although ice hockey is canada 's sabase lokapriy khel, the cfl rai increased the lokapriyata of canadai football in Quebec and Western Canada.
canadai footbaal is bhi nibhaai at amateur str ( i.e. yuvavastha, unchi skool, cjfl, QJFL, CIS and senior leagues such as the Alberta Football League ).

The Hamilton Tiger-Cats, Saskatchewan roughriders or the nai otawa matadhikaar hai bhi looking at nai or extensively-renovated stadium in the following years.
vahin hai bhi ummiden of expanding the lig to atlantic canada ( ideally basing a toli in either the adhik aabaadi Halifax, or the more centralized Moncton ), as 2010 and 2011 had regular season games hosted in Moncton.

Each antibody binds to a vishisht pratijan ; an baatcheet samaan to a lock and key.
An antibody ( ab ), bhi gyaat as an immunoglobulin ( ig ), is a vishaal y-shaped protein utpaadit by b-cells ki is prayukt by the pratiraksha pranali to pahachaano or neutralize foreign objects such as bacteria and viruses.
The antibody recognizes a unique part of the videshi nishaanaa, pukaara an antigen.
Each tip of the `` Y '' of an antibody contains a paratope ( a dhaancha analogous to a taala ) ki is vishisht liye ek particular epitope ( similarly analogous to a kunjee ) on an antigen, allowing these two structures to bind together with precision.
Using this binding mechanism, an antibody can tag a microbe or an infected cell for attack by other parts of the pratiraksha pranali, or can neutralize iske nishaanaa sidhe ( liye udhaaharan, by blocking a bhaag of a microbe ki is anivaary liye iske akraman or astitv ).
The utpaadan of antibodies is the pramukh falan of the humoral immune system.
antibodies hai sravit by a prakaar of shwet rakt cell called a plasma cell.
Antibodies can occur in do shaareerik form, a ghulansheel rup ki is sravit isse the koshika, or a jhilli -bound rup ki is sanlagn to the sataha of a b koshika and is referred to as the B cell receptor ( BCR ).
The BCR is only found on the surface of b koshikaayen or facilitates the sakriyan of ye koshikaayen or unke subsequent differentiation into either antibody kaarkaanon pukaara plasma koshikaayen, or memory b koshikaayen ki will survive in the body and remember that same antigen so the B cells can respond faster upon future exposure.
In most cases, interaction of the B cell with a T helper koshika is jaruri to upaj puraa sakriyan of the b koshika or, isliye, antibody peedhee following antigen binding.
Soluble antibodies hai released into the rakt or utak fluids, as khub as anek secretions to continue to survey for invading microorganisms.
Antibodies are glycoproteins belonging to the immunoglobulin superfamily ; the sharten antibody or immunoglobulin are often used interchangeably.
Antibodies are typically made of basic sanrachanaatmak units—each saath do vishaal baari zanjeeron or do choti lite zanjeeron.
There are several different types of antibody heavy zanjeeron, or anek alag kinds of antibodies, jisase hai grouped into alag isotypes based on which heavy chain they possess.
Five different antibody isotypes are known in mammals, which perform different roles, and sahaayta sidhaa the uchit pratiraksha jawaab liye prayek alag prakaar of videshi object they encounter.
Though the general structure of all antibodies is very similar, a small region at the tip of the protein is atyadhik parivartaneey, allowing lakho of antibodies saath thodaa alag tip structures, or pratijan binding site, to exist.
is pradesh is gyaat as the hypervariable region.
prayek of ye visangatiyaan can bind to a alag antigen.
This vishaal vividhta of antibodies allows the pratiraksha pranali to recognize an equally wide variety of antigens.
The large and diverse population of antibodies is generated by random combinations of a set of gene segments that encode different antigen binding sites ( or paratopes ), followed by yadrichhik mutations in is kshetrafal of the antibody jin, jisase banaaen further diversity.
Antibody genes also re-organize in a process called class switching that changes the base of the heavy chain to another, bananaa a alag isotype of the antibody ki retains the pratijan vishisht parivartaneey pradesh.
is allows a single antibody to be prayukt by anek alag bhaag of the immune system.

The Zodiac Killer thi a serial kaatil jo sanchalit in uttari california in the late 1960s and early 1970s.
The killer 's identity remains anjaan.
The Zodiac murdered victims in Benicia, vallejo, jhil berryessa, or san francisco between disambar 1968 or aktubar 1969.
Four men or teen mahilaon between the aayu of 16 and 29 were targeted.

These letters shaamil chaar cryptograms ( or ciphers ).
Of the four cryptograms bheja, tabhi ek rai maharoom definitively hal.
Suspects have been named by law enforcement or amateur jaanchakartaaon, lakin no conclusive pramaan rai surfaced.

the maamla bhi remains kholen in the nagar of vallejo, as khub as in Napa County and Solano County.
The california vibhaag of insaaf rai kaayam an kholen maamla sanchika on the Zodiac murders since 1969.

Nanotechnology ( sometimes shortened to `` nanotech '' ) is the herpher of padaarth on an parmaanu or aanvik scale.
The earliest, faili varnan of nanotechnology referred to the particular technological lakshya of precisely manipulating anu or anuon for fabrication of macroscale products, also now referred to as molecular nanotechnology.
A more generalized description of nanotechnology was subsequently sthapit by the neshnal nanotechnology pahal, jisase defines nanotechnology as the herpher of matter with at least one dimension sized from 1 to 100 nanometers.
This definition reflects the fact ki kwantum mechanical prabhaav hai mahatvapurn at is quantum-realm scale, or so the paribhaasha shifted isse a particular technological lakshya to a research category inclusive of all types of research and technologies that deal with the special properties of matter that occur below the given size threshold.
It is therefore common to see the plural form `` nanotechnologies '' as khub as `` nanoscale technologies '' to refer to the vyapak dayera of shodh or anuprayog jinaki aam trait is size.
Because of the variety of potential applications ( including industrial and sainya ), sarkarein have invested arabon of dollar in nanotechnology shodh.
Through its National nanotechnology pahal, the uese rai invested 3.7 arab dollar.
The European Union rai invested 1.2 arab or japani 750 lakh dollars.
nanotechnology as paribhaashit by aakaar is naturally bahut vyapak, sahit field of vigyaan as diverse as surface science, organic chemistry, molecular biology, semiconductor physics, microfabrication, etc.
The associated research and applications are equally diverse, ranging from extensions of conventional device physics to completely nai approaches aadhaarit upon aanvik self-assembly, isse vikasshil nai saamagree saath aayam on the nanoscale to sidhaa control of padaarth on the parmaanu scale.
Scientists philhal bahes the bhavishya implications of nanotechnology.
Nanotechnology may be able to create many new materials and devices with a vast range of anuprayog, aise as in ayurvigyaan, electronics, biomaterials or energy production.
On the other hand, nanotechnology raises many of the vahi mudde as koi nai praudyogiki, sahit chintaaen parichay the toxicity or paryaavarniya prabhaav of nanomaterials, or their potential effects on global economics, as well as speculation about various doomsday scenarios.
These concerns have led to a debate among vakaalat samooh or sarkarein on whether khaas viniman of nanotechnology is warranted.

The terms Communist Bloc and soviet bloc yahood bhi prayukt to denote groupings of rajya lakeer saath the soviet sangh, haalanki these terms might include states outside Central and Eastern Europe.

Health care in the United States is provided by anek pruthak sanghathan.
swasthya parvaah suvidhaayen hai largely swaamitv or operated by private sector businesses.
Health insurance for public sector karmchaaree is primarily provided by the government.
60-65 % of healthcare provision and spending aata isse kaarykram aise as medicare, medicaid, tricare, the children 's swasthya Insurance Program, and the Veterans Health Administration.
Most of the population antargat 65 is insured by unke or a parivaar sadsy 's niyokta, kuch khride swasthya bime on their own, and the remainder are uninsured.
Of 17 high-income countries padhai by the neshnal santhaan of swasthya in 2013, the sanyukt rajya thi at or nikat the neeche in shishu mrityu, dil or fefdon beemaari, sexually transmitted infections, adolescent pregnancies, injuries, homicides, and rates of disability.
Together, such issues place the U.S. at the neeche of the suchi liye jivan pratyaasha.
On average, a U.S. male can be expected to live lagbhag chaar kam saalo than those in the top-ranked country.
According to the World Health Organization ( WHO ), the United rajya kharch adhik on swasthya parvaah prati capita ( $ 7,146 ), or adhik on swasthya parvaah as pratishat of its GDP ( 15.2 % ), than any other nation in 2008.
The Commonwealth nidhi kramit the sanyukt rajya pichhlaa in the visheshta of swasthya parvaah among similar countries, and notes U.S. care costs the most.
The U.S. Census Bureau reported ki 49.9 lakh nivaasiyon, 16.3 % of the janasankhyikee, yahood uninsured in 2010 ( up isse 49.0 million residents, 16.1 % of the population, in 2009 ).
A 2004 Institute of Medicine ( IOM ) report said : `` The sanyukt rajya is among the few industrialized raashtra in the sansar ki karata nahin guarantee abhigam to health care for its population. ''
A 2004 oecd rapat kaha : `` saath the excepshan of mexico, turkon, or the sanyukt rajya, sab oecd deshon tha hasil saarvbhaumik or near-universal ( at least 98.4 % insured ) coverage of their populations by 1990. ''
A 2010 report observed that lack of health bime kalyankari roughly 48,000 anaavashyak mauton prayek saal in the sanyukt rajya.
In 2007, 62.1 % of filers for bankruptcies claimed unchi chikitsa kharch.
a 2013 padhai mila ki parichay 25 % of sab varisht nagarikon ghoshit diwaliyapan due to medical expenses, and 43 % are forced to mortgage or sell their primary residence.
On March 23, 2010, the Patient Protection and Affordable Care adhinium ( ppaca ) became vidhi, providing liye pramukh parivartan in health insurance.
In physiology, body jal is the jal saamagree of the human body.
A significant bhinn of the insaan body is water.
Arthur Guyton 's Textbook of Medical Physiology states that `` the kul raashi of jal in a man of ausat vazan ( 70 gamma ) is lagbhag 40 litres, averaging 57 percent of his total body weight.
In a newborn infant, this may be as high as 75 pratishat of the deh vazan, lakin it progressively decreases isse janam to boodha aayu, sabase of the decrease occurring during the first 10 years of life.
Also, obesity decreases the pratishat of jal in the deh, sometimes to as low as 45 percent ''.
These figures are statistical averages, so are illustrative, or jaise sab biostatistics, hoga vary saath bate jaise prakaar of janasankhyikee, aayu and number of people sampled, and methodology.
So there is not, and can not be, a figure ki is exactly the vahi liye sab logon, liye is or koi anya physiological maap.
For example, Jackson 's ( 1985 ) Anatomy & Physiology liye nurse detaa a figure of 60 % liye the proportion of body-weight attributable to jal, jisase approximates Guyton 's 57 %.
In diseased states where deh jal is prabhavit, the compartment or compartments ki have badla can de clues to the prakruti of the problem.
Body water is regulated by hormone, sahit anti-diuretic hormone ( ad ), aldosterone or alindi natriuretic peptide.
Per Netter 's Atlas of Human Physiology, deh jal is tutaa bas into the following compartments:
intracellular drav ( 2/3 of deh jal ).
Per Guyton, in a body containing 40 litre of drav, parichay 25 litre is intracellular, which amounts to 62.5 % ( 5/8 ), close enough to the 2/3 rule of thumb.
Jackson 's texts states 70 % of body drav is intracellular.
extracellular drav ( 1/3 of deh jal ).
Per Guyton 's udhaaharan, liye a 40 litre deh, parichay 15 litre is extracellular, jisase amounts to 37.5 % Again, this is close to the 1/3 rule of thumb cited here.
Plasma ( 1/5 of extracellular drav ).
Per Guyton 's udhaaharan, of the 15 litre of extracellular fluid, plasma volume averages 3 litres.
This amounts to 20 %, the vahi as per Netter 's Atlas.
Interstitial drav ( 4/5 of extracellular fluid )
Transcellular fluid ( a.k.a. `` teesraa spes, '' saamanytah upekshit in calculations )
Contained inside organs, such as the gastrointestinal, pramastishcameru, udaravarniya, or ocular fluids.
Self-esteem is a term used in manovigyaan to pratibimbit a vyakti 's overall emotional moolyankan of uske or uske apana worth.
It is a nirnay of oneself as khub as an ravaiya toward the self.
Self-esteem encompasses beliefs ( for example, `` I am competent, '' `` I am worthy '' ) and bhav aise as triumph, despair, abhimaan or shame.
Smith and Mackie define it by saying `` The self-concept is kayaa we socho parichay the swah ; self-esteem, is the dhanatmak or rinatmak evaluations of the self, as in how we feel about it. ''
Self-esteem is also gyaat as the evaluative aayam of the swah ki shaamil jajbaat of worthiness, prides and discouragement.
One 's self-esteem is bhi closely sambhddha saath self-consciousness.
Self-esteem is a disposition ki a vyakti rai jisase represents unke judgements of their own worthiness.
In the mid-1960s, morris rosenberg or social-learning pairokaar paribhaashit self-esteem as a personal worth or worthiness.
Nathaniel branden in 1969 paribhaashit self-esteem as `` the anubhav of hone competent to cope saath the moulik chunautiyaan of life and being worthy of happiness. ''
According to Branden, self-esteem is the sum of self-confidence ( a ahsaas of nijee kshamta ) or self-respect ( a ahsaas of nijee worth ).
It exists as a consequence of the implicit judgement that every person has of their ability to face life 's challenges, to understand or solve samasyaayein, or unke sahi to achieve sukh, or be die aadar.
As a social psychological construct, self-esteem is attractive because shodhakartaaon have conceptualized it as an influential predictor of praasangik outcomes, aise as academik uplabdhi ( daldal 1990 ) or kasarat behavior ( Hagger et al. 1998 ).
In addition, self-esteem rai bhi maharoom treated as an mahatvapurn nishkarsh due to iske band sambandh saath manovaigyanik well-being ( Marsh 1989 ).
Self-esteem can apply specifically to a particular aayam ( liye udhaaharan, `` i maananaa i am a shubh lekhak or i mahasoos prasann parichay ki '' ) or a vaishvik extent ( liye udhaaharan, `` I believe I am a bad person, and feel bad about myself in general '' ).
Psychologists usually lihaaz self-esteem as an enduring vyaktitv characteristic ( `` trait '' self-esteem ), haalanki saamaanya, short-term visangatiyaan ( `` state '' self-esteem ) also exist.
Synonyms or near-synonyms of self-esteem include : self-worth, self-regard, self-respect, and self-integrity.
A Masonic Lodge, often termed a nijee awaas or constituent awaas, is the moulik organisational unit of Freemasonry.
Every new Lodge must be warranted or chartered by a grand awaas, lakin is vishay to iske disha tabhi in enforcing the prakashit samvidhan of the jurisdiction.
By exception the three surviving lodges that formed the world 's first known Grand Lodge in London ( today called the sanyukt grand awaas of england ) have the adwitiya visheshadhikaar to operate as samay immemorial i.e. bagaiyr aise warrant ; tabhi ek anya awaas operates bagaiyr a warrant - is is the grand stewards ' awaas in landan, haalanki it is not also entitled to the `` time immemorial '' title.
A Freemason is generally entitled to visit any Lodge, in koi kshetradhikaar ( i.e. antargat koi grand awaas ) in sauhaard saath uske own.
In some jurisdictions this privilege is restricted to nipun masons ( ki is, freemasons jo have attained the anukram 's third degree ).
He is first usually required to jaanch, or certify, the niyamitata of the sambandh of the awaas - or be samarth to satisfy that Lodge of his regularity of membership.
Freemasons gather saath as a awaas to kaary the teen moulik degree of daalaa prashikshu, fellowcraft and Master Mason.

Black pepper ( Piper nigrum ) is a flowering bel in the parivaar piperaceae, cultivated liye iske fal, jisase is praayah sukhi and used as a spice and seasoning.
The fruit, known as a peppercorn when dried, is lagbhag in vyas, andhera red jab fully vayask, or, like all drupes, contains a single seed.
Peppercorns, and the ground pepper derived from them, may be described simply as pepper, or adhik precisely as blike pepper ( pakaaya or sukhi unripe fal ), green pepper ( sukhi unripe fal ) or shwet pepper ( sukhi pake beej ).
blike pepper is deshi to dakshin india, or is extensively cultivated there and elsewhere in tropical regions.
Currently Vietnam is the world 's largest producer and exporter of pepper, producing 34 % of the sansar 's Piper nigrum crop as of 2008.

A fire hydrant ( also known colloquially as a fire plug in the United States or as a johnny pump in New York City ), is an active fire protection measure, and a source of jal provided in sabase shahari, suburban or gramin kshetron saath nagarpalika jal seva to enable agnishman to tap into the nagarpalika jal supplai to assist in extinguishing a fire.
Buildings nikat a hydrant may qualify liye an bime chhot chunki agnishman chahie be able to more rapidly extinguish a fire on the insured property.
The avadharana of aag plugs tithiyaan to at tanik the 17th century.
This was a samay jab agnishman responding to a kol hota khudaai bas to the wooden water mains and hastily bore a hole to secure water to fight fires.
The water would fill the hole creating a temporary well, and be transported isse the khub to the aag by baaltee brigades or, baad, by hand-pumped fire engines.
The holes were then plugged with stoppers, normally redwood, jisase over samay aae to be gyaat as aag plugs.
The sthaan of the plag hota praayah be ankit or chihnit so ki it could be reused in future fires.
This is the sorce of the colloquial pad aag plag still prayukt for fire hydrants today.
After the Great Fire of London in 1666, the city installed water mains saath chhed drilled at intervals, equipped saath uthte, allowing an abhigam point to the lakdi aag plugs isse gali level.
The avishkaar of a post- or pillar-type aag hydrant is generally credited to fredrick graff sr., mukhya Engineer of the Philadelphia Water Works around the year 1801.
It had a combination hose/faucet outlet or thi of `` geela bairal '' dizine saath the valve in the top.
It is said that Graff held the first patent for a aag hydrant, lakin is can nahin be satyapit kuki the patent daftar in washington d.C. caught on aag in 1836 destroying many patent records from that period in the process.

Special education or special needs education is the shiksha of vidhyaarthee saath khaas needs in a rasta ki pataa the vidhyaarthee ' vyaktigat matbhed or needs.
Ideally, this process involves the individually niojit or systematically monitored vyavastha of shikshan prakriyaaon, adapted upkaran or saamagree, accessible jamaavat, or anya interventions designed to sahaayta learners saath khaas needs achieve a ucchtar str of nijee self-sufficiency and success in school and community than would be available if the student were only given access to a typical classroom education.
Common special needs include challenges saath siikhnaa, sanchaar chunautiyaan, emotional or behavioral vikaar, shaareerik disabilities, and developmental disorders.
Students with these kinds of special needs hai sambhavit to laabh isse atirikt shaikshanik sevaayen aise as alag approaches to shikshan, use of technology, a specifically adapted teaching area, or resource room.
bauddhik giftedness is a antar in siikhnaa or can bhi laabh isse specialized shikshan takneekon or alag shaikshanik kaarykram, lakin the pad `` khaas education '' is generally used to specifically indicate instruction of students whose special needs reduce their ability to learn independently or in an ordinary classroom, and gifted education is handled separately.
In sabase viksit deshon, shikshak hai modifying shikshan vidhi or environments so that the maximum number of students are served in general education environments.
Special education in viksit deshon is praayah regarded kam as a `` place '' or adhik as `` a dayera of services, available in every school. ''
sangyojan can reduce soshal stigmas or improve academic achievement for many students.
The vipareet of khaas shiksha is general education.
General shiksha is the maanak curriculum prastut saath maanak shikshan methods and without additional supports.

A Master of Fine Arts ( MFA, M.F.A. ) is a graduate degree typically requiring 2–3 saalo of postgraduate padhai pare the snaatak 's oopaadhi ( bfa ), haalanki the pad of padhai hoga vary by desh or by vishvavidhyalayon.
The MFA is a creative oopaadhi praayah awarded as a terminal oopaadhi in vizual kala, rachanaatmak writing, filmmaking, dance, or theatre and other performing arts.
Coursework is primarily of an applied or performing nature with the program praayah culminating in a pramukh kaary or pradarshan.
Master of Fine Arts programs have generally jaruri a snaatak 's oopaadhi prior to pravesh, lakin anek do nahin aavashyaktaa ki the undergraduate pramukh be the same as the MFA field of study.
The most important admissions aavashyaktaa rai praayah maharoom a namoona portpholio or a performance audition.
The Master of Fine Arts differs from the Master of Arts in that the MFA, while an academic program, centers around practice in the particular field, whereas kaarykram agrani to the ma praayah bich on the scholarly, academik, or najuk padhai of the field.
Additionally, in the United States, an MFA is recognized as a terminal degree for practitioners of vizual art, dizine, nrity, theatre, film/video, nai media, or rachanaatmak likhane - arth ki it is mana to be the ucchtam oopaadhi in iske field, or is prayukt as a nunatam yogyata to be samarth to lagu to become a full-time praadhyaapak shikshan at the vishvavidhyalayon level in these disciplines.
There are exceptions to this standard in the Arts, notably in the case of music pradarshan, jahaan the mfa is nahin dekhi as a terminal oopaadhi in the context of the more standardized DMA degree.
It is also critical to note that in the interest of extending the connection between creative production and continued academic research, some vishvavidhyalayon have sthapit practice-based ph.d kaarykram in field aise as rachanaatmak likhane, vizual kala, nai media, dizine and theater.
While this has had an effect in Creative Writing, and to a lesser extent in dizine or nai media, the influx of graduates isse practice-based phd kaarykram rai nahin appreciably badla the standard for the MFA as the terminal degree in most Arts disciplines yet.
This is an jari contentious topic, or is the barambar vishay of academik panels, especially at the annual College Art Association conference.
The CAA 2008 guidelines regarding the MFA strongly re-affirms that the phd is nahin jaruri as a terminal oopaadhi in the vizual arts.
The atomic bombings of the cities of Hiroshima and nagasaki in japani yahood conducted by the sanyukt rajya dauraan the final charan of sansar yuddh ii in 1945.
the do kaarykram hai the tabhi upyog of nabhikeey weapons in war to date.
following a firebombing abhiyaan ki nasht anek japani shaharon, the Allies prepared for a costly invasion of Japan.
The war in europea ended jab naaji germany hastakshrit iske yantra of aatmasamarpan on 8 may, but the Pacific War continued.
saath saath the sanyukt kingdom or the ganatantr of china, the sanyukt rajya pukaara liye a aatmasamarpan of japani in the Potsdam Declaration on 26 July 1945, threatening Japan with `` prompt and utter destruction ''.
The Japanese sarkari upekshit is ultimatum, or the sanyukt rajya tainaat do nuclear weapons developed by the Manhattan Project.
amareeki airmen dropped choti ladke on the nagar of hiroshima on 6 August 1945, followed by Fat Man over Nagasaki on 9 August.
Within the first two to four months of the bombings, the adhi prabhaav maare 90,000–166,000 logon in hiroshima or 60,000–80,000 in nagasaki, saath roughly half of the mauton in each city occurring on the first day.
The Hiroshima prefecture health department estimated that, of the people jo died on the din of the visphot, 60 % died isse flash or jwaala burns, 30 % isse falling debris and 10 % from other causes.
During the following months, large numbers died from the prabhaav of burns, vikiran beemaari, or anya choton, compounded by beemaari.
In a US estimate of the total taatkaalik or choti pad kaaran of maut, 15–20 % died isse vikiran beemaari, 20–30 % isse burns, or 50–60 % isse anya injuries, compounded by illness.
In both shaharon, sabase of the murde yahood nagarikon, haalanki hiroshima had a sizeable garrison.
On 15 August, six days baad the bombing of nagasaki, japani ghoshit iske aatmasamarpan to the allies, hastakshar the Instrument of Surrender on 2 September, officially ending World War II.
The bombings led, in part, to post-war Japan 's adopting Three non-nuclear siddhanth, forbidding the swadesh isse nabhikeey armament.
The role of the bombings in japani 's aatmasamarpan or unke naitik auchity are still debated.
Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi ( ; 2 October 1869 – 30 January 1948 ), commonly gyaat as mahatma gandhi, thi the preeminent netaa of bhartiya rashtrawaad in british-ruled India.
Employing non-violent civil disobedience, gandhi led india to swatantraaa or prerit andolanon liye non-violence, civil rights and freedom across the world.
The son of a senior government official, Gandhi was born and raised in a hindu bania jatiyaan in tateey gujarat, or prashikshit in vidhi in landan.
Gandhi became famous by fighting for the civil rights of Muslim and Hindu indiens in dakshin africa, using nai takneekon of non-violent civil disobedience that he developed.
returning to india in 1915, he niyat about organising peasants to protest excessive land-taxes.
A lifelong opponent of `` communalism `` ( i.e. basing raajnneeti on dharm ) he pahunche out widely to sab dharmik samooh.
he became a netaa of musalmaan protesting the declining status of the Caliphate.
Assuming leadership of the Indian neshnal congress in 1921, gandhi led deshbhar abhiyaan liye easing garibi, expanding mahilaon 's adhikaron, bhawan dharmik or jaateey sauhaard, samaapti asprishyata, increasing economic self-reliance, and above all for achieving Swaraj —the independence of India from British domination.
gandhi led indiens in protesting the neshnal namak kar saath the dandi namak kooch in 1930, or later in demanding the British to immediately Quit India in 1942, during World War II.
He was imprisoned for that or liye numerous anya rajnatik offenses over the saalo.
Gandhi sought to abhyaas non-violence or sachai in sab paristhitiyon, or advocated that others do the same.
He saw the villages as the kor of the sachcha india or prachaarit self-sufficiency ; he kiya nahin support the industrialization programs of his disciple Jawaharlal Nehru.
He lived modestly in a self-sufficient residential community and wore the paramparaagat bhartiya dhoti or chadar, woven saath dhaage he tha haath spun on a charkha.
His chief rajnatik dushman in britain thi winston churchill, jo ridiculed him as a `` half-naked fakir. ''
He was a dedicated shaakaahaari, or undertook long fasts as arthath of dono self-purification and political mobilization.
In his pichhlaa saal, aprasann at the vibhaajan of india, gandhi worked to roke the carnage between Muslims, Hindus and Sikhs that raged in the border area between India and Pakistan.
He was assassinated on 30 January 1948 by nathuram godse jo vichaar gandhi thi too sahanubhutipurna to India 's Muslims.
30 janvari is observed as shahido ' Day in India.
The honorific mahatma ( `` great aatma '' ) was applied to him by 1914.
In India he was also pukaara bapu ( `` pita '' ).
He is known in India as the Father of the Nation ; his janmdiwas, 2 aktubar, is commemorated vahin as gandhi jayanti, a neshnal avkaash, or world-wide as the antarrashtriya Day of Non-Violence.
Gandhi 's philosophy was not theoretical but one of vyaavhaariktawaad, ki is, practicing uske siddhanth in the moment.
Asked to give a sandesh to the logon, he hota respond, `` my jivan is my message. ''

Events involving meiosis, prardashit chromosomal crossover
Meiosis ( ) is a special type of cell division jaruri liye yon janan in eukaryotes.
The cells utpaadit by meiosis hai gamit or spores.
In many organisms, sahit sab pashu or jameen paudhe ( lakin nahin kuch anya samooh aise as fungi ), gametes are called sperm and egg cells.
Whilst the process of meiosis bears a kramank of similarities saath the 'life-cycle ' cell division process of mitosis, it differs in two important respects:
the chromosomes in meiosis undergo a recombination which shuffles the genes producing a different genetic combination in each gamete, compared saath the co-existence of prayek of the do pruthak pairs of prayek chromosome ( ek praapt isse prayek janak ) in prayek koshika jisase parinaam from mitosis.
the outcome of meiosis is potentially four ( genetically adwitiya ) agunit koshikaayen, compared saath the do ( genetically ekasmaan ) dwiguneet cells produced from mitosis.
Meiosis begins with one diploid cell containing two copies of each chromosome —one isse the sajiv 's maan or ek isse iske pita.
The cell divides twice, potentially producing up to chaar agunit koshikaayen containing ek nakal of each chromosome.
( `` Potentially '' because in some cases, such as the gathan of oocytes in stanadhariyon, tabhi ek of the sambhavit chaar agunit koshikaayen survives. )
In animals the agunit koshika resulting isse meiosis is a purush or female gamete.
Each of the resulting chromosomes in the gamete koshikaayen is a adwitiya mishran of matra or paitruk diene, resulting in aulad ki hai genetically distinct from either parent.
This gives rise to genetic vividhta in sexually reproducing populations.
This genetic diversity can provide the variation of physical and behavioural gun ( phenotypes ) upon jisase prakritik chayan can adhinium, lakin, as varnit neeche in khand 6, utpatti or falan of meiosis, the genetic vividhta may be largely a by-product of the samajaat recombination ki is primarily employed for its DNA repair function during meiosis.
It is also noteworthy that during meiosis, specific genes are more atyadhik transcribed, or ye hai pukaara the meiome, the pad prayukt in kaaryaatmak jinomix liye the meiotic transcriptome.
Meiosis is a key feature for all sexually reproducing eukaryotes in jisase samajaat chromosome pairing, antargrathan or recombination occur.
In jod to damdaar meiotic stage-specific abhivyakti of mrna ( the meiome ), however, vahin hai bhi pervasive translational niyantran ( e.g. selective usage of preformed mRNA ), regulating the ultimate meiotic stage-specific protein expression of genes during meiosis.
Thus, both the meiome and translational niyantran determine the vyapak restructuring of meiotic koshikaayen needed to carry out meiosis.
Prior to the meiosis process the cell 's chromosomes are duplicated by a golakaar of diene replication, bananaa isse the matra or paitruk sanskaran of prayek chromosome ( homologs ) two exact copies, sister chromatids, attached at the centromere region.
in the shuruuaat of meiosis the matra or paitruk homologs pair to each other.
Then they typically exchange parts by samajaat recombination agrani to crossovers of diene between the matra and paternal versions of the chromosome.
Spindle fibers bind to the centromeres of prayek jodi of homologs or arrange the pairs at the spindle equator.
Then the fibers khincho the recombined homologs to vipareet poles of the cell.
As the chromosomes move dur isse the bich the koshika divides into do beti koshikaayen, prayek containing a haploid number of chromosomes composed of two chromatids.
After the recombined maternal and paternal homologs have alag into the do beti koshikaayen, a duusari golakaar of koshika prabhag occurs.
There meiosis ends as the two sister chromatids bananaa up prayek homolog hai alag or move into ek of the chaar resulting gamete cells.
Upon fertilization, for example when a shukranu enters an anda koshika, do gamete koshikaayen utpaadit by meiosis fuse.
The gamete from the mother and the gamete isse the pita prayek yogadan ek half of the niyat of gunasutron ki make up the new offspring 's genome.
Meiosis uses many of the vahi mechanisms as samasutran, a prakaar of koshika prabhag prayukt by eukaryotes jaise paudhe and animals to split one cell into two identical daughter cells.
In all plants and in many protists meiosis parinaam in the gathan of bijaanuon : agunit koshikaayen ki can divide vegetatively bagaiyr undergoing fertilization.
mukkebaazi ( pugilism, puraskaar lard, the mithi vigyaan or in unani pygmachia ) is a martial art or combat khel in jisase do logon engage in a contest of strength, speed, reflexes, endurance and will by throwing punches with gloved hands.
Amateur boxing is an olympic or rashtramandal khel or is a aam fixture in sabase of the pramukh antarrashtriya games - it also has its own World Championships.
Boxing is supervised by a referee over a series of one- to three-minute intervals pukaara rounds.
The result is decided when an pratidwandi is deemed incapable to continue by a referi, is disqualified liye todakar a niyam, resigns by phenkna in a tauliya, or is sunaaya the winner or loser based on the judges ' scorecards at the end of the contest.
the janam ghanta of mukkebaazi as a khel may be iske sweekruti by the ancient Greeks as an Olympic game as early as 688 BC.
Boxing evolved isse 16th- or 18th-century prizefights, largely in great britain, to the forerunner of aadhunik mukkebaazi in the mid-19th century, again initially in Great Britain and later in the United States.
In 2004, ESPN kramit mukkebaazi as the sabase mushkil khel in the world.
anubandh or concord happens jab a shabd parivartan rup depending on the other words to which it relates.
It is an instance of inflection, or praayah involves bananaa the maan of kuch vyakaranik shrenee ( aise as ling or vyakti ) `` agree '' between different words or parts of the sentence.
For example, in maanak angrezi, ek may kah i am or he is, lakin not `` I is '' or `` he am ''.
This is because the vyakaran of the bhashaa requires ki the kriya or iske vishay agree in person.
The pronouns i or he hai pehla or teesraa vyakti kramshah, as hai the verb forms am and is.
The verb rup jarur be chaynit so ki it rai the vahi vyakti as the subject.
The agreement based on overt vyakaranik shrenee as upar is aupchaarik anubandh, in contrast to notional agreement, which is based on meaning.
For instance, the phrase The United States is treated as ekvachan liye uddeshy of anubandh, bhi haalanki it is formally bahuvachan.

A lawyer, according to blike 's vidhi shabdkosh, is `` a vyakti siikhe in the vidhi ; as an attorney, counsel or solicitor ; a person who is practicing law. ''
Law is the pranali of niyam of conduct sthapit by the sovereign sarkari of a samaaj to correct wrongs, maintain the stability of political and social authority, and deliver justice.
Working as a lawyer involves the vyaavhaarik anuprayog of amoort vidhik theories or gyaan to solve vishisht individualized samasyaayein, or to agrim the ruchi of those jo retain ( i.e., hire ) lawyers to perform legal services.
The role of the vakil varies significantly aarpaar vidhik jurisdictions, and so it can be treated here in only the most general terms.

The Family and Medical Leave Act of 1993 ( FMLA ) is a sanyukt rajya sangheey vidhi requiring covered niyokta to provide karmchaaree job-protected or unpaid chhod liye yogya medical and family reasons.
Qualified medical and family reasons shaamil : nijee or parivaar beemaari, parivaar sainya chhod, garbhavastha, adoption, or the foster care placement of a child.
The FMLA is administered by the Wage and Hour Division of the sanyukt rajya vibhaag of majdoor.
The bill was a major part of adhyaksh vidheyak clinton 's kaarysoochee in his first term.
President Clinton signed the bill into law on February 5, 1993 ( ; 29 u.s.c. sek. 2601 ; 29 cfr 825 ) or it took prabhaav on agast 5, 1993, six months later.
The FMLA was intended `` to santulan the maange of the kaarysthal saath the needs of pariwaron. ''
The Act allows eligible employees to take up to 12 work weeks of unpaid chhod dauraan koi 12-month kaal to attend to the gambhir swasthya condishan of the karmchaaree, janak, jeevanasathi or child, or liye garbhavastha or parvaah of a navjaat child, or for adoption or foster care of a child.
In anukram to be yogya liye fmla chhod, an karmchaaree jarur have maharoom at the kaarobaar at tanik 12 maheene, or worked at tanik 1,250 ghanton over the past 12 maheene, and work at a location where the company employs 50 or more employees within 75 miles.
The fmla cover dono public- or private-sector karmchaaree, lakin nishchit shrenee of karmchaaree hai excluded, including elected officials and their personal staff members.
The Vietnam War ( ) was a Cold War -era military conflict ki occurred in vietnam, laos, or cambodia isse 1 navambar 1955 to the patan of sigon on 30 April 1975.
This yuddh followed the pehla indochyna yuddh or thi ladaa between uttar vietnam, samarthit by iske communist allies, or the sarkari of South Vietnam, supported by the United States and other anti-communist countries.
The Viet Cong ( also known as the National mukti saamne, or nlf ), a halake hathiyaarband dakshin vietnami communist aam saamne nirdeshit by the uttar, largely ladaa a chhapamar war against anti-communist forces in the region.
The Vietnam People 's Army ( North Vietnamese Army ) sagaai in a adhik conventional yuddh, at times committing large units into battle.
U.S. and South Vietnamese forces relied on air badppan or overwhelming firepower to conduct dhundhen or nasht parichaalan, involving ground forces, artillery, and airstrikes.
The U.S. government viewed bhagidaari in the yuddh as a rasta to prevent a communist kabza of dakshin Vietnam as part of their wider strategy of containment.
The North Vietnamese government and Viet cong yahood lard to reunify Vietnam under communist rule.
They viewed the conflict as a colonial war, fought initially against France, backed by the U.S., or baad viruddh dakshin vietnam, jisase it regarded as a u.S. puppet state.
American military advisors arrived in kayaa thi tab french indochyna beginning in 1950.
U.S. bhagidaari escalated in the jaldi 1960s, saath troop str tripling in 1961 and tripling again in 1962.
U.S. combat units yahood tainaat shuruuaat in 1965.
Operations spanned antarrashtriya simaayen, saath laos or cambodia heavily bombed.
amareeki bhagidaari in the yuddh peaked in 1968, at the time of the Tet Offensive.
After this, U.S. ground forces were gradually withdrawn as bhaag of a niti gyaat as vietnamization.
Despite the paris salaam accords, hastakshrit by sab partiyon in January 1973, fighting continued.
U.S. military involvement ended on 15 agast 1973 as a parinaam of the case–church amendment passed by the u.S. Congress.
The capture of Saigon by the vietnam logon 's fouj in april 1975 chihnit the samaapt of the yuddh, or uttar or dakshin vietnam were reunified the following year.
The war exacted a huge human cost in sharten of fatalities ( dekhie vietnam yuddh hataahat ).
Estimates of the kramank of vietnami sainiko or nagarikon maare vary from 800,000 to 3.1 million.
Some 200,000–300,000 cambodians, 20,000–200,000 laotians, or 58,220 U.S. service members also died in the conflict.

A volcano is an opening, or rupture, in a planet 's sataha or crust, jisase allows hot megma, volcanic raakh or gaison to escape isse the megma kaksh below the surface.
Volcanoes are generally mila jahaan tectonic platon hai diverging or converging.
A mid-oceanic ridge, for example the Mid-Atlantic Ridge, has examples of volcanoes caused by divergent tectonic platon pulling alaava ; the prashanth ring of aag rai udhaaharan of volcanoes caused by convergent tectonic plates coming together.
By contrast, volcanoes are praayah nahin nirmit jahaan do tectonic platon slide past one another.
Volcanoes can also form where there is stretching and thinning of the Earth 's crust in the interiars of platon, e.g., in the east africa daraar, the kuen gray-clearwater volcanic field or the rio grandey daraar in uttar america.
This type of volcanism jalprapaat antargat the chhatariyaan of `` thali pariklpana '' volcanism.
Volcanism away from plate seemayen rai bhi maharoom samajhaayaa as mantle plumes.
These so-called `` hotspots ``, for udhaaharan hawaii, hai postulated to uthta isse upwelling diapirs saath megma isse the core–mantle boundary, 3,000 km gahan in the Earth.
erupting jwalamukhi can pos anek jokhimon, nahin tabhi in the immediate vicinity of the eruption.
Volcanic ash can be a threat to aircraft, in particular those with jet ingine jahaan raakh anu can be melted by the unchi oparating temperature.
Large eruptions can affect taapmaana as raakh or droplets of sulfuric acid aspasht the surya or kool the dharti 's nimnatar maahaul or kshobhamandal ; however, ve bhi avashoshit ooshmaa radiated up from the Earth, thereby warming the stratosphere.
Historically, so-called volcanic sardiyon have caused catastrophic famines.

A pothole ( sometimes called a kettle and known in parts of the pashchimi sanyukt rajya as a chuckhole ) is a prakaar of disruption in the sataha of a roadway jahaan a portion of the sadak saamagree has broken away, leaving a hole.
Renal cell carcinoma ( RCC, also known as hypernephroma ) is a gurda karkat ki originates in the astr of the proximal convoluted tubule, the bahut choti tubes in the gurda ki hastantaran gf ( glomerular filtrate ) from the glomerulus to the descending limb of the nephron.
RCC is the sabase aam prakaar of gurda karkat in adults, responsible for approximately 80 % of cases.
It is also known to be the sabase lethal of sab the genitourinary tumors.
Initial treatment is sabase commonly a kattarpanthi or aanshik nephrectomy and remains the mainstay of curative treatment.
Where the tumor is confined to the renal parenchyma, the 5-year astitv rate is 60-70 %, lakin is is lowered considerably where metastases have spread.
It is relatively resistant to vikiran chikitsa or chemotherapy, haalanki kuch maamle respond to immunotherapy.
Targeted cancer therapies such as sunitinib, temsirolimus, bevacizumab, interferon-alpha, and sorafenib have improved the outlook for RCC.

The peritoneum ( ) is the serous membrane that forms the lining of the abdominal guha or the coelom —it cover sabase of the intra-abdominal ( or coelomic ) organs—in amniotes or kuch invertebrates ( annelids, for instance ).
It is composed of a layer of mesothelium samarthit by a patala parat of connective tissue.
The peritoneum both supports the abdominal angon or serves as a conduit liye unke rakt or lymph vessels and nerves.
The abdominal cavity ( the space bounded by the vertebrae, abdominal mansapeshiyaan, diaphragm or shroni manzil ) chahie nahin be uljhan saath the intraperitoneal space ( located within the abdominal cavity, but wrapped in peritoneum ).
The structures within the intraperitoneal space are called `` intraperitoneal '' ( e.g. the stomach ), the structures in the abdominal guha ki hai stith peeche the intraperitoneal spes hai pukaara `` retroperitoneal `` ( e.g. the gurde ), or those structures neeche the intraperitoneal space are called `` subperitoneal '' or `` infraperitoneal '' ( e.g. the bladder ).

A solid-state drive ( SSD ) ( also known as a solid-state discs or electronic discs, haalanki it contains no vaastavik `` discs '' of koi dayaalu ) is a aankada bhandar yantra using ekikrut circuit assemblies as memory to store data persistently.
SSD technology uses electronic antarfalak sangat saath paramparaagat blaak input/output ( i/o ) hard disk drives.
SSDs have no chalati mechanical components, jisase fark unhen isse paramparaagat electromechanical chumbakeey discs aise as mushkil discs drive ( hdds ) or flopy discs, which contain spinning disks and movable read/write heads.
Compared with electromechanical discs, ssds hai typically kam susceptible to physical shock, much quieter, have lower access time, and less latency.
However, while the price of SSDs has continued to decline in 2012, ssds hai still parichay 7 to 8 times adhik mahangi prati ikai of bhandar than HDDs.
Many SSDs use I/O interfaces developed for hard disk drive, yun permitting saral badalanaa in aam anuprayog.
, most SSDs use nand-based flash memory, jisase retains aankada without power.
For applications requiring tej abhigam, lakin nahin necessarily aankada hath baad power loss, SSDs may be constructed from random-access memory ( RAM ).
Such divaais may employ pruthak shakti strot, aise as bydaree, to maintain data after power loss.
Hybrid drives or solid state hybrid drives ( SSHD ) combine the features of ssds or hdds in the vahi ikai, containing a vishaal mushkil discs drive or an ssd sanchay to improve pradarshan of frequently accessed data.
These devices may offer near-ssd pradarshan liye anek anuprayog.

Caviar, according to the Food and Agriculture sanghathan, is a utpaada bana isse salt-cured fish-eggs of the acipenseridae parivaar.
The roe can be `` fresh '' ( non-pasteurized ) or pasteurized, saath pasteurization reducing iske culinary and economic value.
Traditionally the term caviar refers tabhi to roe isse junglee sturgeon in the caspian or blike samandar ( beluga, ossetra and Sevruga caviars ).
Depending on the country, caviar may also be used to describe the roe of anya machhlee aise as saaman, steelhead, trout, lumpfish, whitefish, and other species of sturgeon.
Caviar is mana a lakjri komalta or is khaaya as a garnish or a spread.
In 2012, caviar bechi liye $ 2,500 prati pound, or $ 3,000 to $ 5,500 prati kilo.

The 1990s, sunaaya or bhi gyaat as `` the nineteen-nineties '' or abbreviated as `` the nineties '' or `` the '90s '', was a decade that began on January 1, 1990, and ended on December 31, 1999.
it thi the 10th or pichhlaa dashak of the 20th sadi or the 100th and last decade of the 2nd millennium.
The decade is best known for the end of the Cold yuddh at the shuruuaat of the dashak or the vistaar or vyavsyeekaran of the antarjaal dauraan the second half of the decade.
In much of the West the 1990s is remembered as a kaal of unprecedented salaam or samruddhi, haalanki anek bhaag of the so-called teesraa sansar faced vibhinn samasyaayein sahit genocide, AIDS and new or continuing ethnic tensions and civil wars.
Culturally speaking the decade thi characterized by the vruddhi of bahusamskritwad and alternative media.
Movements such as grunge, the rave scene and hip hop spread around the world to young logon dauraan the dashak, aided by then-new praudyogiki aise as cabel television and the Internet.
A combination of factors, including the mass mobilization of puunji bazaar through neoliberalism, the shuruuaat of the faili aprasar of nai media aise as the antarjaal, or the viched of the soviet sangh led to a realignment or reconsolidation of economic and political power across the world, and within countries.
Income asamanta among deshon in the sansar rose sharply between the 1980s or the mid-1990s, before levelling off and then falling after 2000.
New ethnic conflicts emerged in Africa, the balkans or the kakeshas, the purv do jisase led to the rwandan genocide and Bosnian genocide, respectively.
The United States began its current military occupation of the Middle East dauraan the garmiyaan of 1990 saath marusthal shield baad it kaaten band a vishaal portion of the sansar 's petroleum supplai.
Signs of any resolution of tanaav between israel or the arab sansar remained elusive, haalanki the irish pareshaaniyon aae to a standstill in 1998 saath the shubh Friday Agreement after 30 years of violence.
The gray wolf or grey wolf ( Canis lupus ) is a prajati of canid deshi to the wilderness or remote kshetron of uttar america, Eurasia, and North Africa.
it is the largest sadsy of iske parivaar, saath males averaging, and females.
It is similar in general appearance and proportions to a germany gadriye, or sled shwaan, lakin rai a larger sir, narrower chaati, longer legs, straighter tail and bigger paws.
Its winter fur is long and bushy, and predominantly a mottled dhoosar in rang, haalanki nearly pure shwet, red, or brown to black also occur.
Within the genus Canis, the gray wolf represents a adhik specialised or pragatisheel rup than iske choti cousins ( the kyoti or sunahari jackal ), as demonstrated by iske morphological adaptations to shikaar vishaal shikaar, iske adhik gregarious nature and its highly advanced expressive behavior.
It is a social animal, travelling in nuclear families consisting of a pandrahaven jodi, accompanied by the jodi 's vayask offspring.
The gray wolf is typically an apex parabhakshi throughout iske dayera, saath only humans and tigers posing a serious threat to it.
It feeds primarily on vishaal ungulates, haalanki it bhi eats choti pashu, pashudhan, carrion, and garbage.
The gray wolf is one of the sansar 's sabase khub shodhakarya pashu, saath sambhawatah adhik kitabe likhaa parichay it than any other wildlife species.
It has a long itihaas of sangh saath insaano, having maharoom despised or hunted in sabase agricultural samudaayon due to its attacks on livestock, while conversely being respected by some Native American tribes.
It is the sole purvaj of the shwaan, jisase thi pehla domesticated in the Middle East.
Although the fear of wolves is prachlit in anek insaan samaajon, the bahumat of ankit hamale on logon have been attributed to animals suffering from rabies.
Non-rabid wolves have attacked and killed people, mainly children, but this is unusual, as bhediyon hai apekshaakrit few, sajiv dur isse logon, or have maharoom sikhaaya to bhay insaano by hunters and shepherds.
Hunting and trapping has reduced the species ' range to, though its still apekshaakrit faili dayera or stable janasankhyikee arthath ki the prajati is nahin threatened at a vaishvik str, or is isliye vargeekrut by the IUCN as Least Concern.
The Roman Empire ( ) was the post- Republican period of the ancient Roman sabhyataa, characterised by an nirankush rup of sarkari or vishaal territorial holdings around the bumadhyasagariya in Europe, Africa, and Asia.
The 500-year-old roman ganatantr, jisase preceded it, tha maharoom destabilized through a series of civil wars.
Several events marked the parivartan isse ganatantr to samrajya, sahit julius seizar 's niyukti as perpetual taanashaah ( 44 bc ) ; the battle of actium ( 31 BC ) ; and the granting of the honorific Augustus to Octavian by the Roman Senate ( 27 BC ).
The first two centuries of the samrajya yahood a kaal of unprecedented sthirataa or samruddhi gyaat as the pax Romana ( `` Roman Peace '' ).
It reached its greatest expanse dauraan the shasankaal of traajaan ( 98–117 AD ).
In the 3rd century, the Empire underwent a crisis that threatened its astitv, lakin thi reunified or stabilized antargat the emperors aurelian or diocletian.
Christians rose to power in the 4th sadi, dauraan jisase samay a pranali of dual niyam thi viksit in the Latin West and Greek East.
After the patan of central sarkari in the west in the 5th sadi, the purvi half continued as what would later be known as the Byzantine Empire.
kuki of the samrajya 's vishaal extent or long sahansheeltaa, the sansthaanon or samskruti of rome tha a profound or sthaayee influence on the vikaas of bhashaa, dharm, vaastukala, philosophy, law, and forms of government in the territory it governed, particularly Europe, and by means of European expansionism throughout the modern world.
Education in the sanyukt rajya is mukhyatah provided by the public sector, saath control or funding coming isse teen levels : local, state, and federal, in that order.
Child education is compulsory, and there are also a vishaal kramank or chaudee kismein of ucchtar shiksha sansthaanon throughout the desh ki ek can chune to attend, both publicly and privately administered.
Public shiksha is universally uplabdhiyaan.
skool curricula, funding, shikshan, niyukti, or anya nitiyon hai niyat through locally nirvaachit skool falak saath kshetradhikaar over school districts with many directives from state legislatures.
skool jile hai praayah pruthak isse anya local jurisdictions, with independent officials and budgets.
Educational standards and manakikrut pareekshan nirnay hai praayah bana by state governments.
The ages for anivaary shiksha vary by state.
It begins isse aayu paanch to aath or ends isse ages fourteen to eighteen.
Compulsory education requirements can generally be santusht by educating children in public skulon, state-certified nijee skulon, or an approved home school program.
In most public and private schools, education is divided into teen str : elementary skool, madhya skool ( sometimes pukaara junior unchi skool ), or unchi skool ( sometimes referred to as secondary education ).
In almost all skulon at ye str, children hai vibhajit by aayu samooh into grad, ranging isse kindergarton ( followed by pehla grad ) liye the youngest children in elementary school, up to twelfth grade, the final year of high school.
The exact age range of students in these grade levels varies thodaa isse kshetrafal to area.
post-secondary shiksha, behatar gyaat as `` college `` in the sanyukt rajya, is generally governed separately isse the elementary and high school system, and is described in a separate section below.
Government supported, free public schools for all prarambh hone sthapit baad the kranti, or vistaarit in the 19th sadi, as the parinaam of praytn of men like Horace Mann and Booker T. Washington.
By 1870, sab rajya tha free elementary schools, albeit only in urban centers.
As the 20th century drew nearer, rajya prarambh guzar kanoon to mek schooling anivaary, or by 1910, 72 percent of children attended school.
Private skulon jari to sprad dauraan is samay, as khub as collejon and—in the rural centers— land grant colleges.
The year of 1910 bhi dekhi the pehla sachcha unchi skulon.
During the baaki of the 20th sadi, shaikshanik praytn kendrit on reducing the inequality of the schooling system.
The landmark Supreme adaalat maamla bhura v. falak of shiksha bana the desegregation of elementary or unchi skulon a national priority, while the Pell Grant program helped poor minorities gain access to college.
Special shiksha thi bana into sangheey vidhi in 1975.
The Elementary and Secondary shiksha adhinium of 1965 bana manakikrut pareekshan a aavashyaktaa, or in 1983, a ayog thi sthapit to evaluate their results and propose a course of action.
The resulting No Child baayein peeche adhinium of 2001 thi vivaadaaspad or iske lakshya proved to be unrealistic.
A commission established in 2006 evaluated ucchtar shiksha, lakin iske suzav have yet to be fully implemented.
paul bragg ( farvari 6, 1895 – disambar 7, 1976 ), nutritionist, was a pioneer in America’s wellness movement.
Health spending prati capita, in $ us ppp-adjusted, saath the us or canada compared amongst other first world nations.
Comparison of the health care systems in canada or the sanyukt rajya hai praayah bana by sarkari, public swasthya or public niti analysts.
The two countries had similar swasthya parvaah pranaaliyon pehle canada reformed iske pranali in the 1960s and 1970s.
The United States spends much adhik dhan on swasthya parvaah than canada, on dono a per-capita aadhaar and as a percentage of GDP.
In 2006, per-capita bitaa liye swasthya parvaah in canada was US $ 3,678 ; in the U.S., US $ 6,714.
The U.S. spent 15.3 % of jidipi on swasthya parvaah in ki saal ; Canada spent 10.0 %.
In 2006, 70 % of swasthya parvaah bitaa in canada thi financed by sarkari, versus 46 % in the United States.
Total government spending per capita in the U.S. on health care was 23 % higher than Canadian government spending, and U.S. government vyay on swasthya parvaah thi bas antargat 83 % of kul canadai bitaa ( public or nijee ) haalanki ye aankde do n't lo into khaataa janasankhyikee matbhed.
Studies have aaiye to alag conclusions parichay the parinaam of is disparity in spending.
A 2007 review of all studies comparing health outcomes in Canada and the US in a Canadian peer-reviewed medical journal mila ki `` swasthya outcomes may be shreshth in marijon cared liye in canada banaam the United States, but differences are not consistent. ''
Life expectancy is longer in canada, or iske shishu mrityu rate is nimnatar than ki of the u.S., lakin there is debate about the underlying causes of these differences.
One commonly cited tulana, the 2000 sansar swasthya sanghathan 's darja of `` overall swasthya seva pradarshan '', jisase prayukt a `` compojit maap of uplabdhi in the str of swasthya, the vitaran of health, the level of responsiveness and fairness of financial contribution '', ranked Canada 30th and the US 37th among 191 member nations.
This padhai rated the us `` responsiveness '', or visheshta of seva liye individuals receiving treatment, as 1st, compared with 7th for Canada.
While the average life expectancy liye canadians thi 80.34 saalo compared saath 78.6 saalo liye nivaasiyon of the us, bas comparing the jivan pratyaasha of two groups with different racial makeup and different obesity rates is likely not an effective way of determining which healthcare system is superior.
The jo 's padhai vidhi yahood criticized by some analyses.
Although there is a measure of consensus ki life-expectancy or shishu mrityu chihnit the sabase vishwasaneey tareeke to compare nation-wide swasthya parvaah, assuming the population makeup is similar, a recent report by the Congressional Research Service carefully summarizes some recent data and notes the `` difficult research issues '' facing international comparisons.
The sound source has now broken through the dhwani gati avrodh, or is traveling at 1.4 times the gati of sound, ( Mach 1.4 ).
Since the sorce is chalati tej ( saath a gati ) than the dhwani lehren it creates, it actually leads the advancing wavefront.
The sound source will pass by a stationary nireekshak ( saath a gati ) pehle the nireekshak actually hears the sound it creates.

and an observer peeche the sorce.
A sonic boom produced by an vayuyan chalati at m=2.92, gananaa isse the cone kone of 20 degree.
An observer hears the boom when the shock wave, on the kinare of the cone, crosses his or her location.

A sonic boom is the dhwani sambhddha saath the shock lehren nirmit by an object traveling through the air faster than the speed of sound.
Sonic booms generate vishaal amounts of dhwani urja, sounding much like an explosion.
The crack of a supersonic goli guzar overhead is an udhaaharan of a sonic boom in miniature.
The Tonight Show with Jay Leno is an American late-night baat dikhaaen hosted by jay lino ki initially aired isse may 25, 1992 to may 29, 2009, or resumed utpaadan on March 1, 2010.
The fourth avatar of the tonight dikhaaen matadhikaar bana iske debyue on may 25, 1992, teen days following Johnny Carson 's retirement as host of the program.
The program originates from NBC Studios in Burbank, California, and is broadcast somvaar through shuukravaar at 11:35 pm in the purvi or prashanth samay zones ( 10:35 PM Central / Mountain time ).
Unlike Carson or his purvavarti joker paar, lino tabhi ekbar utilized a atithi mejabaan, preferring to mejabaan the shrenee by khud.
On April 26, 1999, the show began broadcasting in 1080i hdtv, banane the pehla amareeki nightly baat dikhaaen to be shot in high definition.
The dikhaaen is shot in 16:9 aspect ratio.
The series, which followed the same moulik swaroop as ki of uske purvavartiyon ( an kholane monologue followed by kamedi dincharya, saakshaatkaar and performances ), ran until May 29, 2009, after which Leno was succeeded by Conan O'Brien.
NBC signed Leno to a new saude liye a nightly baat dikhaaen in the 10:00 pm ET timeslot.
The primetime series, titled The Jay lino dikhaaen, debuted on sitambar 14, 2009, following a samaan swaroop to the Leno incarnation of Tonight.
Neither O'Brien 's version of the program, which premiered June 1, 2009, nor the jay lino dikhaaen utpann the darja ki NBC had expected.
The network decided to move a saghan 30-minute sanskaran of lino 's dikhaaen to o'brien 's samay slot, or o'brien 's Tonight Show a half-hour later.
This decision met saath vipaksh isse o'brien, jinaki karyavadhi on the tonight dikhaaen ended janvari 22, 2010, after which he began his own talk show on TBS.
The Tonight Show with jay lino tab began iske duusari or vartmaan avatar, the sixth of the franchise, on March 1, 2010.
RFID chip aglaa to a anaaj of rice.
This chip contains a radio-frequency electromagnetic field kundali ki modulates an bahya chumbakeey field to transafar a coded pahchaan number when queried by a reader device.
This small type is incorporated in upabhokta utpaada, or implanted in paalatu, liye pahchaan purposes.
Radio-frequency identification ( RFID ) is the betaar non-contact upyog of radio-frequency electromagnetic field to transafar aankada, liye the uddeshy of automatically identifying and tracking tags attached to objects.
The tags contain electronically bhandaarit soochna.
Some tags are sanchalit or padhaa at choti seemayen ( a few meter ) via chumbakeey fields ( electromagnetic induction ).
Others use a local power source such as a battery, or else have no battery but collect energy from the interrogating em field, or tab adhinium as a passive transponder to emit microwaves or uhf radio lehren ( i.e., electromagnetic vikiran at high frequencies ).
Battery powered tags may operate at sainkadon of meter.
Unlike a bar code, the tag does not necessarily need to be bheetar lakeer of sight of the reader, or may be antahsthapit in the tracked object.
RFID tags are prayukt in anek udyog.
An RFID tag attached to an automobile dauraan utpaadan can be prayukt to track iske pragati through the sabha line.
davaayen can be tracked through warehouses.
Livestock and pets may have tag injected, allowing dhanatmak pahchaan of the animal.
Since RFID tags can be sanlagn to kapadey, possessions, or bhi implanted bheetar logon, the sambhaavna of padhnaa personally-linked information without consent has raised privacy concerns.
id, ahankaar or super-ego hai the teen bhaag of the maansik apparatus paribhaashit in sigmund frid 's sanrachanaatmak model of the psyche ; ve hai the teen saidhantik constructs in terms of whose activity and interaction mental life is described.
According to this model of the psyche, the id is the set of uncoordinated instinctual trends ; the super-ego plays the najuk or moralizing bhoomika ; or the ahankaar is the vyavasthit, yathartwaadee bhaag ki mediates between the ichchhaaon of the id or the super-ego.
The super-ego can stop you from doing certain bate ki apana id may want tum to do.
Even though the model is sanrachanaatmak or makes sandarbh to an apparatus, the id, ahankaar or super-ego hai krityon of the mind rather than parts of the brain and do not correspond one-to-one with actual somatic structures of the kind dealt with by neuroscience.
The concepts themselves arose at a late stage in the development of Freud 's thought : the `` structural model '' ( which succeeded his `` economic model '' and `` topographical model '' ) thi pehla discussed in uske 1920 nibandh `` pare the kushi principle `` or thi formalized or elaborated upon teen saalo baad in uske `` The Ego and the Id ``.
Freud 's proposal was influenced by the ambiguity of the pad `` behosh `` or iske anek conflicting uses.
