The Air Force Reserve Officer Training corps ( afrotc ) is ek of the teen praathmik commissioning strot liye adhikariyon in the sanyukt rajya air force, the anya do hone the sanyukt rajya air force academy ( usafa ) or air force adhikari Training School ( OTS ).
A subordinate command of the Air University within the Air Education and Training Command ( AETC ), afrotc is lakeer antargat the jeanne M. holm bich liye adhikari accessions or naagarik vikaas at maxwell AFB, Alabama.
The Holm Center, formerly gyaat as the air force adhikari accession or prashikshan Schools ( AFOATS ), retains direct responsibility for both AFROTC and OTS.
AFROTC is the largest or oldest sorce of commissioned adhikariyon for the U.S. Air Force.
afrotc 's stated mishan is to upaj visheshta netao liye the U.S. Air Force.
AFROTC units are located on 144 college and university campuses with 984 additional institutions of higher siikhnaa participating in cross-town samjhauton ki allow unke vidhyaarthee to attend afrotc varg at a aasapaas `` mejabaan '' college or university.
according to afoats hq, in 2006, afrotc commissioned 2,083 uaseef duusari lieutenants, saath afrotc namakan ranging isse 23,605 in 1985 to 10,231 in 1993, and around 13,000 enrolled today.
AFROTC units at colleges and universities are called `` detachments, '' and are typically headed by an active duty USAF officer in the rank of karnal or leftinent karnal jo krityon as dono the detachment commander liye uaseef uddeshy or saath the nammaatr sheershak of praadhyaapak of aerospace adhyayan ( pas ) bheetar the sanstha 's academic community.
Most colleges and universities hoga designate the afrotc detachment as the vibhaag of Aerospace Studies.
The PAS is assisted by three to four Assistant professors of aerospace adhyayan ( apas ), sab kriyasheel duty uaseef adhikariyon in the baandhane of pramukh or captain.
Three USAF non-commissioned officers and one senior non-commissioned officer will typically provide sainya prashasnic support or hai praayah augmented by ek to do civilian staff support karmchaaree of the academik sanstha.
Within AFROTC detachments, the vidhyaarthee ( referred to as `` cadets '' ) hai vyavasthit into wings, samooh, squadrons, or flights, mirroring the USAF functional wing structure.
The AFROTC detachment 's cadet wing or cadet group is separated into two divisions : the General Military Course ( GMC ) consisting of the pehla do saalo of prashikshan, or the peshewar adhikari course ( poc ) consisting of the pichhlaa do saalo of prashikshan.
The AFROTC program is also divided into two training functions : the Academic Classroom Program ( aerospace adhyayan varg ) or cadet kriyaayein ( i.e., netritv prayogshaala, shaareerik prashikshan, or anya prashikshan ).
Paper density ( also known as aadhaar vazan or grammage ) is a pad prayukt in the guda or paper udyog or bhi liye kapadaa udyog to denote a measure of mass of the product per unit of area for a type of fabric, paper or paperboard.
The term `` density '' is not used in its paramparaagat bhav of dravyaman prati ikai awaz.
`` Paper ghanatv '', balki, is a maap of the area density.
Paper products that let little or no lite pass through ( e.g. poster falak ) hai considered dense or heavy.
Paper utpaada ki allow kuch lite to pass through ( e.g. tissue paper ) are considered lightweight.
In the pulp and paper industry, it is common to niyat a vanijyik paper yantra to upaj paper to a nishaanaa paper density.
Paper density can also be used to distinguish paper from paperboard as the latter praayah rai a grammage vrihad than 134 g/m2.
Two ways of expressing paper ghanatv are commonly used:
Expressed in grams per vargakar meter ( g/m2 ), paper ghanatv is bhi known as grammage.
This is the measure prayukt in sabase bhaag of the world.
Expressed in terms of the mass ( expressed as vazan ) prati kramank of chaadaren, it is gyaat as aadhaar vazan.
The convention used in the United States and a few other deshon using us paper aakaar is pound of a ream of 500 ( or in kuch maamle 1000 ) chaadaren of a given ( raw, still uncut ) basis size.
japani paper is expressed as the vazan in kg of 1000 sheets.

And she was a atithi star on figure it Out.
A food guide pyramid is a pyramid shaped guide of healthy foods divided into bhaag to dikhaaen the anushansit seven liye prayek khaanaa samooh.
The pehla khaanaa pyramid thi published in Sweden in 1974.
The sabase widely gyaat khaanaa pyramid thi introduced by the sanyukt rajya vibhaag of Agriculture in the year 1992, was updated in 2005, and then replaced in 2011.

Hans Christian Andersen ( ; often referred to in scandinavia as H. C. andersen ; april 2, 1805august 4, 1875 ) thi a danish lekhak or poet.
Although a prolific writer of plays, travelogues, novels, and poems, andersen is behtareen remembered liye uske pari kisse, a saahitiyik vidha he so mastered ki he khud rai become as mythical as the tales he wrote.
Andersen 's popularity is not limited to children ; his stories—called, or `` fantastic kisse '' —express vishaywastu ki transcend aayu or rashtriyata.
During uske aaajeevan he thi acclaimed liye having prasann children vishwavyaapee and was feted by royalty.
Andersen 's fairy tales, which have been translated into more than 125 languages, have become culturally antahsthapit in the west 's samuhik chetana, readily accessible to children, lakin pesh lessons of virtue and resilience in the face of adversity for mature readers as well.
They have prerit gati tasviren, plays, ballets, and animated films.

najar sampark occurs jab `` do logon dekh at prayek other 's eyes at the same time. ''
In human beings, eye contact is a form of nonverbal sanchaar or is vichaar to have a vishaal influence on soshal behavior.
Coined in the early to mid-1960s, the pad rai aaiye in the west to praayah define the adhinium as a sarthak or mahatvapurn chihn of vishwaas and social communication.
The customs and significance of najar sampark vary widely between samskritiyon, saath dharmik or soshal matbhed often altering its meaning greatly.
The study of najar sampark is sometimes gyaat as oculesics.
bed bag hai parasitic keet of the cimicid family that feed exclusively on blood.
The term most commonly refers to members of the genus Cimex of which cimex lectularius, the aam bed keedaa, is the behtareen gyaat as it prefers to feed on insaan rakt haalanki anya cimex prajati hai specialized to anya pashu, e.g., chamagadad bugs, C. pipistrelli ( Europe ), C. pilosellus ( western US ), and C. adjunctus ( entire eastern US ).
The name of the `` bed keedaa '' is niklaa isse the pasandida awaas of cimex lectularius : garam gharon or visheshkar nearby or inside of beds and bedding or other sleep areas.
Bed bugs are mainly active at raatri, lakin hai nahin exclusively nocturnal.
They praayah feed on unke host bagaiyr being noticed.
A number of pratikul swasthya prabhaav may parinaam isse bed keedaa bites, including skin rashes, psychological effects, and allergic symptoms.
Diagnosis involves both finding bed bag or the occurrence of sangat symptoms.
Bed bugs have been gyaat as insaan paraseete liye hazaron of years.
At a point in the jaldi 1940s, ve yahood zyaadaatar eradicated in the viksit sansar, lakin have increased in vyapaktaa since 1995.
Because infestation of insaan habitats rai maharoom on the increase, bed bug bites and related conditions have been on the rise as well.
The Book of Isaiah ( ) is the first of the Latter nabiyon in the yahudee bible, preceding ezekiel, Jeremiah and the Book of the Twelve.
( The order of the subsequent kitabe differs somewhat in the isai Old Testament ).
The pehla 39 adhyay prophesy yatnaa liye a gunaahagaar yahuda or liye sab the raashtra of the sansar ki oppose parameshwar, jabaki the pichhlaa 27 prophesy the bahaali of the swadesh of israel or a nai sristi in parameshwar 's gauravshaalee bhavishya kingdom ; this section includes the Songs of the Suffering Servant, four separate passages referring to the nation of Israel, interpreted by Christians as prefiguring the coming of Jesus Christ.
Tradition ascribes authorship of the kitaab to yashayah bete of amoz, lakin abhi vidwaanon widely sahamat ki the kitaab is the kaary of teen alag lekhak - few scholars deny this view, and those that do, do so for theological reasons.
The first, termed Proto-Isaiah ( chapters 1–39 ), contains the words of the 8th-century BCE prophet with 7th-century BCE expansions ; the second, Deutero-Isaiah ( chapters 40–55 ), is the work of a 6th-century BCE author likhane nikat the samaapt of the babylonian captivity ; or the teesraa, the kavy trito-isaiah ( adhyay 56–66 ), thi rachit in jerusalem shortly baad the vaapasi isse nirvaasan, sambhawatah by anek authors.
Oregon State vishvavidhyalayon ( osu ) is a coeducational, public shodh vishvavidhyalayon stith in corvallis, Oregon, United States.

The Kanab ambersnail, scientific name Oxyloma haydeni kanabensis or Oxyloma kanabense, is a critically endangered subspecies or prajati of choti, air-breathing jameen ghongha, a sthaliy pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Succineidae, the amber snails.
The common name of the amber snails is based on the shell, jisase is paardarshee or jab khaali praayah resembles ember in color.
This species is endemic to the United States, specifically the state of erizona or uta, jahaan it thi pehla ekatrit in the jaldi 20th century.
It has been listed as endangered on the sanyukt rajya machhlee or vanyajeev seva suchi of endangered prajati since 8 August 1991.
This snail lives in wetlands, springs, and seeps, and only two of its natural habitats are known to maujuud : teen jhiilon, a marg nikat kanab, uta, or vasey 's swarg, a vasant saath the colorado nadi bheetar grand Canyon National Park.
In its prakritik awaas it is balki polyphagous, feeding mukhyatah on bacteria, plants and fungi, and reproduces during the summer.
Now considered a Critically Endangered species on the aiusien red suchi of threatened prajati due to a shrenee of karkon ( sahit influence ), the kanab ambersnail rai maharoom reintroduced to teen sroton upar the aitihaasik unchi jal str along the Colorado River.
The Spanish language is the duusari sabase prayukt bhashaa in the sanyukt States.

The Tokyo Mew Mew manga or dushmani shrenee suvidhaayen a daal of varna designed by mia Ikumi.
The series takes place in tokio, japani, jahaan paanch adolescent ladakiyon, pukaara mew mews, hai infused saath the diene of endangered prajati to combat aliens attempting to take over the Earth.
The manga series is followed by a short sequel series, tokio mew mew a la vidhi, jisase introduces a nai mew mew or a new threat.
The Mew Mews are led by the main akshar, ichigo momomiya, jinaki pehla kaary is to ekatrit the anya chaar mew mews : mint aizawa, salad midorikawa, Pudding Fong, and Zakuro Fujiwara.
As the series progresses, Ichigo goes from having a crush on Masaya Aoyama to banane uske garlfriend jabaki trying to chupa uske secret double life from him.
The series antagonists shaamil teen aliens, kish, pai, or tikhaa, and their leader, Deep Blue.
Originally from Earth, the aliens yahood majaboor to chhod long pehle due to ghaatak paryaavarniya parivartan.
They have returned to kill the insaano, jo ve mahasoos hai destroying unke grah, or reclaim the planet.
In a la Mode, middle school student Berry shirayuki is introduced as the chathe mew mew or, in the anupasthiti of ichigo, the asthai netaa of the Mew Mews.
A la Mode also introduces new set of antagonists, the sant rose crusaders, a samooh of insaan teenagers saath vibhinn psychic abilities with a desire to create their own utopia.
Led by Duke, they make anek koshishen to maar beri, aakhirkaar turning the local populace against the Mew Mews.
Ikumi 's initial vision for Tokyo Mew Mew was a story called Tokyo blike billi ladki ki pradarshit a cat-girl battling alien invaders.
After the story was transitioned to a more upbeat story of five female superheroes, the akshar dizin yahood redone to have a lighter, more colorful feel.
The main series characters were praised for being a purna anuroop liye the overall story, as khub as liye unke cute appearances.
The characters introduced in a la vidhi yahood bhi praised liye unke vizual dikhaave, lakin criticized as hone doharaav of the original series.

Middle Triassic marginal marine sequence of siltstones ( neeche ) or limestones ( upar ), virgin gathan, southwestern uta, USA
Sedimentary rox hai prakaar of chattan ki hai formed by the deposition of saamagree at the Earth 's surface and within bodies of water.
Sedimentation is the collective name for processes that cause mineral and/or sashulk anu ( detritus ) to settle and accumulate or minerals to precipitate from a solution.
Particles that form a sedimentary rock by accumulating hai pukaara sediment.
pehle hone deposited, sediment thi formed by weathering or apradan in a sorce kshetrafal, or tab transported to the place of deposition by water, wind, ice, mass movement or glaciers which are called agents of denudation.
The sedimentary rock cover of the continents of the dharti 's crust is extensive, lakin the kul yogadan of sedimentary rox is anumaanit to be only 8 % of the total volume of the crust.
Sedimentary rocks are only a patala veneer over a crust consisting mukhyatah of igneous or metamorphic rocks.
Sedimentary rocks are deposited in paraton as strata, forming a structure called bedding.
The study of sedimentary rox or chattan strata provides soochna parichay the subsurface ki is upyogi liye civil abhiyantriki, liye udhaaharan in the nirmaan of sadaken, houses, tunnels, canals or other constructions.
Sedimentary rocks are also important strot of prakritik sansaadhan jaise koyale, chattan fuels, pine water or ores.
The study of the sequence of sedimentary rock strata is the main source liye vaigyanik gyaan parichay the dharti 's itihaas, sahit palaeogeography, paleoclimatology or the history of life.
The scientific discipline ki adhyayan the gun or utpatti of sedimentary rocks is called sedimentology.
Sedimentology is dono bhaag of bhuvigyaan or shaareerik bhugol or overlaps partly saath anya disciplines in the dharti sciences, aise as pedology, geomorphology, geochemistry or structural geology.

Humans are born with over 270 bones, some of which fuse together into a anudairdhya aksh, the aksheeya kankal, to jisase the appendicular skeleton is attached.
Saint Patrick ( ; ; Modern ; ; c. 387 – 17 kooch c. 460 or c. 492 ) thi a romano-british isai missionary and bishop in Ireland.
Known as the `` Apostle of Ireland '', he is the praathmik sangrakshak sant of the dweep saath saath santo brigid or Columba.
Two pramanik akshar isse use jivit, isse jisase aaiye the tabhi generally accepted details of his life.
When he was about 16, he was captured from his home and taken as a slave to ireland, jahaan he jiya liye chah saalo pehle escaping or returning to uske family.
After becoming a cleric, he returned to uttari or pashchimi ireland as an ordained bishap, lakin choti is gyaat parichay the places where he worked.
By the saatvaan sadi, he tha already aaiye to be revered as the patron saint of Ireland.
Most available details of his life hai isse subsequent hagiographies, or ye hai abhi nahin sweekrut without detailed criticism.
the annals of ulster rajya ki he arrived in ireland in 432, ministered in Ulster around 443, and died in 457 or 461.
The text, however, distinguishes between `` Old Patrick '' ( thought to mean palladius ) or `` patric, archapostle of the scots, '' jo died in 492.
The actual dates of Patrick 's life can not be fixed with certainty but, on a faili nirvachan, he thi kriyasheel as a mishanri in ireland dauraan the duusari half of the 5th century.
He is generally credited saath hone the pehla bishap of armagh, Primate of All Ireland.
Saint Patrick 's Day is observed on kooch 17, the tithi of his death.
It is celebrated both inside and outside Ireland, as both a dharmik or, visheshkar baahar ireland, dharmanirpeksh holiday.
In the dioceses of ireland, it is dono a solemnity or a paavan din of daayitv ; baahar Ireland, it can be a celebration of Ireland itself.
Line khand in the golden ratio
A golden rectangle with longer side a or shorter paksh b, jab lagaai sata to a vargakar saath pahalu of length a, will produce a similar golden rectangle with longer side a + b and shorter side a.
is illustrates the sambandh.
in ganit or the kala, do quantities hai in the sunahari anupaat if the anupaat of the yoga of the quantities to the larger quantity is equal to the ratio of the larger quantity to the smaller one.
The figure on the sahi illustrates the jyamitiya sambandh.
Expressed algebraically:
where the unani akshar faai ( ) represents the golden ratio.
Its maan is:
The golden ratio is also called the sunahari khand ( latin : sectio oriya ) or sunahari mean.
Other names include extreme and mean anupaat, medial khand, daivi proportion, daivi khand ( latin : sectio divina ), sunahari proportion, golden cut, and golden number.
Many 20th century artists and architects have proportioned their works to sannikat the sunahari ratio—especially in the rup of the sunahari ytaakar, in jisase the anupaat of the longer paksh to the shorter is the sunahari ratio—believing this proportion to be aesthetically pleasing ( see Applications and observations below ).
Mathematicians since Euclid have studied the properties of the golden ratio, sahit iske rup in the aayam of a niyamit prastutikaran or in a sunahari ytaakar, jisase can be kaaten into a vargakar or a choti ytaakar with the same aspect ratio.
The golden ratio rai bhi maharoom prayukt to analyze the proportions of prakritik vastuen as khub as man-made pranaaliyon such as financial markets, in some cases based on dubious fits to data.
North Myrtle Beach is a tateey resort nagar in horry county, dakshin carolina, United States.
It was created in 1968 from four existing municipalities uttar of myrtle bich, or serves as ek of the praathmik paryatak kasbon saath the grand Strand.
The janasankhyikee thi 13,752 at the 2010 census.
World War i ( wwi ) thi a vaishvik yuddh kendrit in europea ki began on 28 July 1914 and lasted until 11 November 1918.
It thi predominantly pukaara the sansar yuddh or the great yuddh isse iske occurrence jabatak the start of World War II in 1939, and the First World War or World War I thereafter.
It involved all the world 's great powers, which were assembled in two opposing alliances : the Allies ( based on the Triple Entente of the United kingdom, frans or rus ) or the central shaktiyaan ( originally the tripal gathbandhan of germany, austria-hungary or italy ; lakin, as austria–hungary tha liya the apriy viruddh the anubandh, Italy did not enter into the war ).
These alliances yahood dono reorganised or vistaarit as adhik raashtra daalaa the yuddh : italy, japani or the sanyukt rajya joined the allies, and the Ottoman Empire and Bulgaria the Central Powers.
Ultimately, more than 70 million military personnel, including 60 lakh europeans, yahood mobilised in ek of the largest yudhon in itihaas.
More than 9 million combatants were killed, largely kuki of technological advancements ki led to vishaal increases in the lethality of hathiyaar bagaiyr sambandhit sudhaar in protection or mobility.
It was the fifth- deadliest conflict in world history, subsequently paving the rasta liye vibhinn rajnatik parivartan, aise as revolutions in many of the nations involved.
One of the long-term kalyankari of the yuddh thi the punarutthan of samrajyavad in the videshi nitiyon of the great powers of Europe.
More immediately, the assassination of Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria, the heir to the throne of Austria-Hungary, on 28 june 1914 by yugoslav rashtravaadi gavrilo princip in sarajevo triggered a rajanyik sankat jab austria-hungary subsequently vitarit an ultimatum to the Kingdom of Serbia.
Several alliances formed over the pichhlaa dashakon yahood invoked.
Within weeks, the pramukh shaktiyaan yahood at yuddh or, via unke colonies, the virodh soon spread around the world.
On 28 july, the austro-hungarians fired the pehla goliyaan of the yuddh as taiyaari for the invasion of Serbia.
While the Russians mobilised, the Germans invaded neutral Belgium and Luxembourg on the way to frans, providing a casus belli liye britain 's ghoshnaa of yuddh viruddh germany.
After the German march on Paris was brought to a halt—the so-called chamatkaar of the marne —the pashchimi saamne settled into a sthir battle of apgharshan saath a gart lakeer that changed little until 1917.
On the purvi saamne, the roosi fouj thi kaamyaab viruddh the austro-hungarians, but was stopped in its invasion of East Prussia by the Germans.
In November the Ottoman samrajya joined the yuddh, kholane up fronts in the kakeshas, mesopotamia and the Sinai.
Italy and Bulgaria gai to yuddh in 1915 or romania in 1916.
In Russia, the tsar 's sarkari collapsed in kooch 1917 or a subsequent kranti in navambar brought the Russians to terms with the Central Powers.
After a 1918 German offensive along the pashchimi saamne, the allies drove waapas the germans in a shrenee of successful offensives and American forces began entering the trenches.
Germany, which had its apana trubal saath krantikariyon, sahamat to an armistice on 11 November 1918.
The yuddh ended in vijay liye the Allies.
Events on the home fronts yahood as ugr as on the battle fronts, as the bhagidaar aajamaaya to mobilize unke janashakti or aarthik sansaadhan to fight a total war.
By the end of the yuddh, chaar pramukh imperial powers—the germany, roosi, austro-hungarian and Ottoman empires—ceased to exist.
the successor rajya of the purv do khoyaa a great amount of territory, while the latter two were dismantled entirely.
The map of central europea thi redrawn into anek choti states.
The League of raashtra thi formed in the aashaa of preventing another such conflict.
The European nationalism spawned by the war or the brallep of empires, the parakhnaa of germany 's shikast or samasyaayein saath the sandhi of versailles hai sahamat to be factors contributing to World War II.
Camden is a city in camden county, nai jersey, sanyukt rajya.
It is the county seat, stith aarpaar the delaware nadi isse Philadelphia.
As of the 2010 United States Census the nagar tha a kul janasankhyikee of 77,344, representing a manaahi of 2,560 ( 3.2 % ) isse the 79,904 nivaasiyon enumerated dauraan the 2000 janasankhyikee, jisase tha in phere asweekrut by 7,588 ( 8.7 % ) from the 87,492 counted in the 1990 Census.
Camden kramit as the 12th-most populous nagarpalika in the rajya in 2010 baad having been ranked 10th in 2000.
Camden was originally incorporated as a city on February 13, 1828, isse portions of the now-defunct newton township, jabaki the kshetrafal thi still bhaag of gloucester County.
On March 13, 1844, Camden became bhaag of the newly formed Camden County.
haalanki ekbar a thriving bich liye nirmaan or udyog, camden is shaayad best known for its struggles with urban dysfunction.
Three Camden mayors have been jailed for bhrashtachar, the sabase haal hone milton milan in 2000.
Since 2005 the skool pranali or police vibhaag have maharoom sanchalit by the rajya of New Jersey ; the takeover expired in 2012.
In 2008, Camden had the highest crime rate in the U.S. with 2,333 violent aparaadhon prati 100,000 logon jabaki the neshnal ausat thi 455 prati 100,000.
Camden public schools spent $ 23,770 per student ( $ 19,118 on a budgetary per-pupil basis ) in the 2009–10 skool saal or two-thirds of the vidhyaarthee graduate.
Two out of every five residents hai neeche the neshnal poverty line.
Amitriptyline ( Tryptomer, elavil, tryptizol, laroxyl, saroten, sarotex, lentizol, endep ) is a tricyclic antidepressant ( TCA ).
It is the sabase widely prayukt tca or rai at tanik baraabar efficacy against depression as the newer class of SSRIs according to a study from early 2001.
As khub as reducing depressive lakshan, ye prakaar of tricyclics bhi aasaani migraines, tension headaches, anxiety attacks and some schizophrenic symptoms.
It is also known to reduce aakraamakata or hinsak behavior.
A computer is a general purpose device that can be programit to carry out a parimit niyat of arithmetic or logical operations.
Since a anukram of parichaalan can be readily badla, the computer can solve more than one kind of problem.
Conventionally, a computer consists of at tanik ek prasanskaran tatv, typically a central processing unit ( CPU ) and some form of memory.
The prasanskaran tatv carries out ganit or logic parichaalan, and a sequencing and control unit that can change the order of operations based on stored information.
paridhiy divaais allow soochna to be punarprapt isse an bahya sorce, or the parinaam of operations saved and retrieved.
The pehla electronic digital computer yahood viksit between 1940 and 1945 in the United Kingdom and United States.
Originally they were the size of a large room, consuming as much shakti as anek sau aadhunik personal computers ( PCs ).
in is era mechanical analog computer yahood used for military applications.
Modern computer aadhaarit on ekikrut circuits hai lakho to arabon of times adhik sakasham than the early machines, and occupy a fraction of the space.
Simple computers are small paryaapt to anuroop into mobile divaais, or mobile computer can be sanchalit by choti batteries.
Personal computers in unke vibhinn form hai pratik of the soochna aayu or are what most people think of as “computers.”
However, the antahsthapit computer mila in anek divaais isse mp3 khilaadi to senaanee vayuyan and from toys to industrial robots are the most numerous.
`` Barefoot and pregnant '' is a phrase most commonly associated with the vivaadaaspad vichaar ki mahilaon chahie nahin kaary baahar the ghar or chahie have anek children dauraan unke reproductive years.
it rai anek anya meanings as well.
It is a figure of speech.
The phrase `` barefoot or garbhvatee '' thi sambhawatah first used sometime before 1950.
An article from 1949 states, `` By early 1949, TWA was—in the shabd of iske nai adhyaksh, ralph S. damon—both 'barefoot and pregnant. ' ''
Its upyog may tithi as jaldi as the 1910s.
An aalekh prakashit in 1958 rajya the phrase thi pehla used by a `` Dr. Hertzler '' 40 years earlier.
`` Some forty years pehle, dr. hertzler unnat a pariklpana jisase yang mahilaon of aaj seem jhuki on proving correct. '
The tabhi rasta to rakhana a stri prasann, ' he kaha, 'is to keep her barefoot and pregnant. ' ''

The stadium is located next door to the Jobing.com Arena and it features the first fully retractable prakritik grass playing sataha nirmit in the sanyukt rajya on sheersh of an airfield pranaaliyon naale pranali.
An opening on one side of the stadium allows the playing field to move to the exterior of the bhawan, allowing the sampurna prakritik turf playing surface to be exposed to daylight.
The stadium has hosted Super katori xlii, or the 2011 bcs neshnal championships khel, a khel ki it host prayek four years, which set the venue 's entertainment attendance record of 78,603 on January 11, 2011.
It will again mejabaan super katori xlix in 2015.

Joshua Lawrence Chamberlain ( September 8, 1828 – February 24, 1914 ), born as Lawrence joshua chemberlen, thi an amareeki college praadhyaapak isse the rajya of maine, jo volunteered dauraan the amareeki civil yuddh to juden the Union Army.
Although having no earlier education in military strategies, he became a highly aadarneey or sajaa sangh adhikari, reaching the rank of brigadier saamaanya ( or brevet pramukh saamaanya ).
For uske gallantry at gettysburg, he was awarded the Medal of Honor.
He was given the honor of commanding the sangh sainikon at the aatmasamarpan rasm liye the infantry of robert E. lee 's fouj at appomattox, Virginia.
After the war, he daalaa raajnneeti as a republican or parosa chaar one-year terms of office as the 32nd Governor of Maine.
He served on the sankaay, or as adhyaksh, of uske alma meter, bowdoin college.
An inning, or innings, is a fixed-length khand of a khel in koi of a kismein of khel – sabase notably cricket or besabaal dauraan jisase ek toli koshishen to score jabaki the anya toli koshishen to prevent the first from scoring.
In cricket, the pad pari is dono ekvachan or bahuvachan or is sadaa spelled or sunaaya with the terminal `` s ''.
In besabaal or softball, the ekvachan rup is inning and only the plural takes an `` s ''.
In many other sports, the length of the khel is likhavai by a clock or tiimon swap apriy or rakshaatmak bhoomikaaye dynamically by taking possession of a ball or similar item.
In baseball and cricket, however, ek toli, kaha to be `` ballebaaji '', koshishen to score `` ranon '' —see chalaaen ( besabaal ) or chalaaen ( cricket ) —while the anya toli, kaha to be `` fielding '', attempts to prevent the scoring of runs and get members of the batting team out.
The teams switch places after the fielding toli rai succeeded in getting a phixd kramank of khilaadi out, bananaa a clock unnecessary.
In cricket, the pad pari is bhi prayukt to refer to the khel of ek particular player ( Smith had a poor innings, scoring only 12 ).
By extension, this term can be used in British English for lagbhag koi kaaryaklap jisase takes a kaal of samay ( the udaar sarkari tha a shubh pari, lakin aakhirkaar khoyaa daftar in 1972, or tum 've tha a mela pari, abhi it 's my phere, arth `` you have spoken for long enough, now let me speak '' ).
It is also used in sandarbh to kisi jo rai died at a reasonably boodha age or lived a rich and rewarding life ( Ah, well.
John thi 89.
At least he tha a shubh pari ).
The baseball-derived parallel to this in amareeki angrezi is the pad at chamagadad.
According to the Oxford English Dictionary, the term pari rai maharoom prayukt in sandarbh to cricket chunki at tanik 1735.
As cricket was a vayask, atyadhik vyavasthit khel in the 1600s in england, the term 's origin could well precede this first recorded usage.
The shabd inning arth 'a mehafil in ' is pehla recorded in 1522, and could be related.
Adenosine deaminase deficiency, bhi pukaara edie kamiyaan or ada-scid, is an autosomal recessive metabolic disorder that causes immunodeficiency.
It occurs in fewer than ek in 100,000 sajiv births vishwavyaapee.
It accounts for about 15 % of all cases of kathor sanyukt immunodeficiency ( scid ).
It is very rare, you have a 3 % mauka of getting is gene.
ADA deficiency may be present in infancy, balykaal, adolescense, or adulthood.
Age of onset and severity is sambandhit to kuch 29 gyaat genotypes sambhddha saath the vikaar.
An example of urban poverty in is slum in jakarta, Indonesia
Poverty is the state of ek jo lacks a nishchit raashi of saamagree possessions or money.
Absolute poverty or destitution refers to the deprivation of moulik insaan needs, jisase commonly shaamil khaanaa, jal, swatchta, kapadey, aashray, health care and education.
Relative poverty is defined contextually as aarthik asamanta in the sthaan or samaaj in which people live.
For much of itihaas, garibi thi mana largely aprihaary as paramparaagat mods of utpaadan yahood aparyaapt to de an entire population a comfortable standard of living.
After the industrial kranti, dravyaman utpaadan in kaarkaanon bana maal increasingly more inexpensive and accessible.
of adhik mahatv is the modernization of krishi, aise as fertilizers, in order to provide enough yield to feed the population.
The supply of basic needs can be pratibandhit by constraints on sarkari sevaayen aise as bhrashtachar, kar avoidance, karz or rin conditionalities and by the brain drain of health care and educational professionals.
Strategies of increasing aay to mek moulik needs adhik sasti typically shaamil welfare, economic freedoms, and providing financial services.
Poverty reduction is a major goal and issue for many antarrashtriya sanghathan aise as the sanyukt Nations and the World Bank.
The World Bank estimated 1.29 arab logon yahood jeena in nirpeksh garibi in 2008.
Of these, about 400 lakh logon in nirpeksh garibi jiya in india and 173 million people in China.
In USA 1 in 5 children jeevandaan in garibi.
In terms of percentage of regional populations, sub-Saharan africa at 47 % tha the ucchtam incidence rate of nirpeksh poverty in 2008.
Between 1990 or 2010, parichay 663 lakh logon sthanantarit above the absolute poverty level.
Still, charam garibi is a vaishvik chunauti ; it is observed in sab bhaag of the sansar, sahit the developed economies.
Mushroom poisoning ( also known as mycetism ) refers to nuksaandeh prabhaav isse ingestion of vishakt substances upasthit in a mushroom.
These lakshan can vary isse patala jathrantra takalif to death.
the toxins upasthit hai dwitiyak metabolites utpaadit in specific biochemical pathways in the fungal cells.
Mushroom poisoning is praayah the parinaam of ingestion of junglee mashroom baad misidentification of a vishakt mushroom as an edible species.
The most common reason for this misidentification is band praturup in sharten of rang or saamaanya morphology of the toxic mushrooms species with edible species.
Even very experienced wild mushroom gatherers are upon rare avasar poisoned by khaane vishakt prajati, despite hone khub aware of the risks, through carelessness.
To prevent mushroom poisoning, mashroom gatherers need to be bahut parichit saath the mashroom ve intend to collect as well as with any similar-looking toxic species.
In addition, edibility of mashroom may nirbhar on vidhi of taiyaari for cooking.
collectors bhi need to be khub jaagruk ki edibility or toxicity of some species varies with geographic location.
Human height is the distance from the neeche of the feet to the sheersh of the sir in a insaan deh, khadaa erect.
When populations share genetic prishthbhumi or paryaavarniya karkon, ausat oonchaai is aksar characteristic bheetar the group.
Exceptional oonchaai vibhinnata ( around 20 % vichlan isse ausat ) bheetar aise a janasankhyikee is sometimes due to gigantism or dwarfism, which are medical conditions caused by specific genes or endocrine abnormalities.
In regions of extreme poverty or prolonged warfare, environmental karkon jaise dirghakaalik kuposhan dauraan balykaal or kishoravastha may khaataa liye vilambit vikaas and/or ( in kathor maamle ) chihnit reductions in vayask stature even without the presence of any of these medical conditions.
Apollo 11 was the spaceflight ki utraa the pehla insaano, america neil armastrang or baz elderin, on the chandramaa on july 20, 1969, at 20:18 UTC.
Armstrong became the pehla to kadam onto the chandra sataha 6 ghanton later on July 21 at 02:56 UTC.
Armstrong spent about two and a half ghanton baahar the spacecraft, elderin thodaa kam ; or saath ve ekatrit of lunar material for return to Earth.
A third sadsy of the mishan, maaikel colins, piloted the cmand spacecraft alon in chandra kaksha jabatak armastrang and Aldrin returned to it just under a day later for the trip back to Earth.
Launched by a Saturn V rocket from kennedy spes bich in merritt dweep, florida on july 16, apollo 11 thi the paanchvaan maanavyukt mishan of NASA 's Apollo program.
The Apollo spacecraft had three parts : a Command Module with a cabin for the three astronauts which was the only part which utraa waapas on dharti ; a seva modul jisase samarthit the cmand modul saath nodan, vidyut shakti, oxigen or jal ; or a Lunar Module for landing on the Moon.
After being sent to the Moon by the Saturn V 's apper stage, the astronauts alag the spacecraft isse it or travelled liye teen days until they entered into lunar orbit.
Armstrong and Aldrin then moved into the chandra modul or utraa in the samudr of Tranquility.
They stayed a kul of parichay 21 or a half hours on the lunar surface.
baad uthaane band in the apper bhaag of the chandra modul or rejoining Collins in the Command Module, they returned to Earth and landed in the Pacific Ocean on July 24.
Broadcast on live TV to a world-wide audience, Armstrong stepped onto the chandra sataha or varnit the event as `` ek choti kadam liye [ a ] man, ek daanav chalaang liye mankind. ''
Apollo 11 effectively ended the spes res or fulfilled a neshnal lakshya prastaavit in 1961 by the let u.S. adhyaksh jon F. Kennedy in a speech before the United States Congress, `` before this decade is out, of landing a man on the Moon and returning him safely to the Earth. ''
The FIFA World Cup, often simply the World Cup, is an international association football competition lade by the varisht main 's neshnal tiimon of the sadasyon of fédération internationale de footbaal sangh ( fifa ), the sport 's global governing body.
The championship has been awarded every four years chunki the inaugural toornament in 1930, magar in 1942 or 1946 jab it thi nahin yojit kuki of the Second World War.
the vartmaan champions hai spain, jo won the 2010 tournament.
The vartmaan swaroop of the toornament involves 32 tiimon spardhaa liye the sheershak at venues bheetar the mejabaan swadesh ( s ) over a period of about a month ; this phase is often called the World Cup Finals.
A qualification phase, which currently takes place over the preceding three years, is prayukt to determine jisase tiimon qualify liye the toornament saath saath the host nation ( s ).
The 19 World Cup tournaments have maharoom jiti by aath alag neshnal teams.
brazil have jiti paanch times, or ve hai the only team to have played in every tournament.
The other World Cup winners are Italy, with four titles ; Germany, with three sheershak ; argentina or inaugural vijeta urugve, saath do sheershak prayek ; or england, frans, or spain, saath ek title each.
the sansar cap is the sansar 's sabase widely viewed sporting event ; an anumaanit 715.1 lakh people watched the final match of the 2006 FIFA World Cup held in Germany.
The aglaa teen sansar cups hoga be hosted by brazil in 2014, rus in 2018, and Qatar in 2022.
Genocide is a pad coined in 1944 by rafel lemkin to describe the deliberate or vyavasthit vinaash, in puure or in part, of an ethnic, racial, religious, or national group.
It is defined in Article 2 of the Convention on the Prevention and Punishment of the Crime of Genocide ( CPPCG ) of 1948 as `` any of the following acts committed with intent to destroy, in whole or in part, a national, ethnical, racial or dharmik samooh, as aise : hatya sadasyon of the samooh ; causing gambhir bodily or dimagi nuqasaan to sadasyon of the samooh ; deliberately inflicting on the samooh sharten of jivan, gananaa to lao parichay iske shaareerik vinaash in puure or in bhaag ; imposing measures intended to prevent births within the group ; [ and ] forcibly transferring children of the group to another group. ''
Skulls of peediton of the rwandan narsanhaar
the prastaavna to the cppcg nahin tabhi rajya ki `` narsanhaar is a aparaadhon antargat antarrashtriya vidhi, contrary to the spirit or aims of the sanyukt raashtra or condemned by the civilized world '', but also that `` at all periods of history genocide has inflicted great losses on humanity ''.
Determining what historical kaarykram constitute a narsanhaar or jisase hai merely dand or amanviya behavior is not a clear-cut matter.
in nearly prayek maamla jahaan aaropon of narsanhaar have parichaalit, partisans of vibhinn pahalu have fiercely disputed the interpretation and details of the event, often to the point of promoting wildly different versions of the facts.
an accusation of narsanhaar is katai nahin liya lightly and will almost always be controversial.

The culture of the United States is primarily a pashchimi samskruti, lakin is bhi bahekaave by deshi amareeki, africa, asian, polinesian, or latin amareeki cultures.
American culture started its formation over 10,000 years ago saath the migration of paleo-indians isse asia into the pradesh ki is aaj the mahadwipiya sanyukt rajya.
It has iske apana adwitiya soshal or saanskrithik visheshtaayen aise as dialect, music, arts, social habits, cuisine, and folklore.
The United States of America is an ethnically and racially diverse country as a parinaam of large-scale avrajan isse anek alag deshon throughout iske itihaas.
Its chief early European prabhaav aae isse angrezi, scottish, welsh or irish settlers of colonial America during British rule.
British culture, due to colonial ties with Britain that sprad the angrezi bhashaa, vidhik pranali or anya saanskrithik inheritances, tha a formative influence.
Other important prabhaav aae isse anya bhaag of pashchimi europea, visheshkar Germany, France, and Italy.
asli tatv bhi khel a damdaar bhoomika, such as the invention of Jeffersonian democracy.
Thomas Jefferson 's Notes on the State of Virginia was perhaps the first influential domestic cultural critique by an amareeki or a pratikriyaavaadi tukdaa to the prachlit europea sarvasammati ki america 's gharelu moulikta thi vikrut.
Prevalent ideas and ideals that evolved domestically, such as national holidays, uniquely American sports, military tradition, and innovations in the arts and entertainment give a damdaar bhav of neshnal abhimaan among the janasankhyikee as a puure.
American culture includes both conservative and liberal elements, scientific and religious pratispardhaatmakataa, rajnatik structures, risk lene or free abhivyakti, bhautikwaadi or moral tatv.
Despite nishchit satat vaicharik siddhanth ( e.g. vyaktigat, samtawaad, or aasthaa in swatantraaa or loktantr ), amareeki culture has a variety of expressions due to its geographical scale and demographic diversity.
The flexibility of U.S. culture and its highly symbolic nature lead some shodhakartaaon to categorize amareeki samskruti as a mythic pahchaan ; anya see it as American exceptionalism.
It also shaamil tatv ki viksit isse swadeshi america, or anya jaateey cultures—most prominently the culture of African Americans, cultures from Latin America, and Asian American cultures.
Many American cultural tatv, visheshkar isse lokapriy samskruti, have sprad aarpaar the globe through modern mass media.
The United States rai praayah maharoom vichaar of as a melting ghat, lakin shuruuaat in the let 1990s or jaldi 2000s, it rujhaan towards saanskrithik diversity, pluralism and the image of a salad bowl instead.
Due to the extent of American culture, there are many integrated but adwitiya soshal subcultures bheetar the sanyukt rajya.
The cultural affiliations an individual in the United States may have commonly depend on social class, rajnatik abhivinyas or a multitude of janasankhyikee visheshtaayen aise as dharmik prishthbhumi, occupation or jaateey samooh membership.

A glucose tolerance test is a chikitsa pareekshan in jisase glucose is die or rakt namoonay liya afterward to determine kaisaa jaldi it is cleared from the blood.
The test is usually prayukt to pareekshan liye madhumeh, insulin pratirodh, or sometimes pratikriya hypoglycemia or acromegaly, or rarer vikaar of carbohydrate metabolism.
In the most commonly performed version of the pareekshan, an maukhik glucose sahishnutaa pareekshan ( ogtt ), a maanak khuraaq of glucose is ingested by munh and blood levels are checked two hours later.
Many variations of the GTT have been devised over the saalo liye vibhinn uddeshy, saath alag maanak doses of glucose, alag root of prashasan, alag intervals or durations of sampling, and various substances measured in addition to blood glucose.

On the left a murga anda, the anda sabase commonly khaaya by humans, and on the right two quail eggs

The legality of canbis varies isse desh to desh.
Possession of cannabis is illegal in sabase deshon or rai maharoom chunki the shuruuaat of widespread cannabis prohibition in the late 1930s.
However, many countries have decriminalized the kabza of choti quantities of canbis, visheshkar in uttar america, South America and Europe.

Some countries have laws that are not as vigorously prosecuted as others but, alaava isse the deshon ki prastaav abhigam to chikitsa marijuana, sabase deshon have vibhinn dand ranging from lenient to very severe.
Some infractions hai liya adhik seriously in kuch deshon than anya in lihaaz to the cultivation, use, possession or transfer of cannabis for recreational use.
A few jurisdictions have lessened dand liye kabza of choti quantities of canbis, bananaa it dandaneey by confiscation and a fine, rather than imprisonment.

There are also changes in a adhik pratibandhak disha as in canada.

In cardiovascular physiology, ejection bhinn ( ef ) represents the aaytani bhinn of rakt uttejit out of the ventricle ( dil ) saath prayek dil taal or cardiac cycle.
It can be applied to either the right ventricle which ejects via the pulmonary valve into the pulmonary parisancharan or the baayein ventricle jisase ejects via the aortic valve into the pranaligat parisancharan.
imaging of the physiology of the mammalian dil is the art that allows meaningful mathematical expression defining EF.
Noninvasive cardiac imaging has become a vishwavyaapee utility enabling padhai of hriday pradarshan reproducibly and inexpensively.
Simplified, Ejection bhinn is a ganitiya utpaada anumat by hriday imaging.
As a mathematical term, ejection bhinn is an ekstansion of the kaary of adalph Fick in cardiac output.
Dedicated technology such as Echocardiography, Computed Tomography, chumbakeey anunaad imaging or muga scanning have definitively anumat clinically praasangik ganit regarding ischemia, janmajaat dil Disease and Heart Failure.
State Route 14 ( SR 14 ) is a north–south rajya rajmarg in the u.S. rajya of california, largely in the Mojave Desert.
The southern portion of the rajmarg is hastakshrit as the antelope ghati Freeway.
The route connects antarraji 5, or sunahari rajya frive, nikat santa clarita or saath u.S. Route 395 near Inyokern.
Legislatively, the root extends dakshin of i-5 to rajya root 1 in the prashanth palisades kshetrafal of los angeles, however the portion south of the junction with I-5 has not been constructed.
The southern part of the constructed route is a busy commuter freeway sevarat or connecting the samudaayon of santa clarita, palmdale or lancaster saath the rest of the Greater Los Angeles area.
The uttari portion, isse vincent ( dakshin of palmdale ) to root 395, is legislatively namit the Aerospace Highway, as the highway serves Edwards Air Force Base, once one of the primary landing strips for NASA 's Space Shuttle.
This section is rural, following the line between the hot mojave marusthal or the forming Sierra Nevada mountain range.
Most of Route 14 is loosely paralleled by a main line of the Southern Pacific Railroad, used liye the antelope ghati lakeer of the metrolink commuter rail pranali as khub as a conection between los angeles or the california Central Valley via Tehachapi Pass.
Linked with US 395, is sadak connects los angeles saath aise sthaan as maimath pahaad, Mono Lake, Yosemite National Park and Reno, Nevada.
Route 14 thi bhaag of u.S. root 6 prior to truncation in 1964, jab u.S. 6 thi a coast-to-coast route from Long Beach to Provincetown, Massachusetts.
The non-freeway segment of SR 14 from Silver Queen Road north of Rosamond to Mojave is gyaat as sierra rajmarg, as is the boodha rooting between antarraji 5 or chaandi maharani sadak where SR 14 has been moved to a newer freeway alignment.
Portions of Route 14 remain signed with names associated saath us 6, sahit midland trail, theodor rujvelt rajmarg or grand fouj of the ganatantr rajmarg.
This route is part of the california frive or expresve pranali.
Blindness is the condishan of lacking vizual bodh due to physiological or neurological factors.
Various scales have been developed to describe the extent of drushti ghaataa or define drishtiheenta.
Total drishtiheenta is the puraa kami of rup or vizual lite bodh or is clinically recorded as NLP, an abbreviation for `` no light perception. ''
Blindness is frequently used to describe kathor vizual putliyon with vision.
Those described as having only light bodh have no adhik sight than the kshamta to bataanaa lite isse andhera or the saamaanya disha of a light source.
To determine which people may need khaas sahaayta kuki of unke vizual disabilities, vibhinn sarkari jurisdictions have pratipaadit adhik jatil paribhaashaayen referred to as legal blindness.
In North America and most of europea, vidhik drishtiheenta is paribhaashit as vizual tikshnata ( drushti ) of 20/200 ( 6/60 ) or less in the better eye with best correction possible.
This means that a legally blind individual would have to stand isse an object to dekhie it—with corrective lenses —with the vahi oopaadhi of spashtataa as a saamanytah sighted person could from.
In many areas, logon saath ausat tikshnata jo nonetheless have a vizual field of kam than 20 degree ( the norm being 180 degrees ) are also classified as being legally blind.
Approximately ten percent of those deemed legally andha, by koi maap, have no vision.
The baaki have kuch drushti, isse lite bodh alone to relatively good acuity.
kam drushti is sometimes prayukt to describe vizual acuities from 20/70 to 20/200.
By the 10th Revision of the WHO International Statistical Classification of Diseases, Injuries and Causes of Death, low vision is defined as visual acuity of less than 20/60 ( 6/18 ), lakin baraabar to or behatar than 20/200 ( 6/60 ), or sambandhit vizual field ghaataa to kam than 20 degree, in the better eye with best possible correction.
Blindness is defined as visual acuity of less than 20/400 ( 6/120 ), or sambandhit vizual field ghaataa to kam than 10 degree, in the behatar najar saath behtareen sambhavit sudhaar.
Blind people with undamaged eyes may still register lite non-visually liye the purpose of circadian entrainment to the 24-hour light/dark cycle.
Light signal liye is purpose safar through the retinohypothalamic tract or hai nahin prabhavit by optic nerve damage beyond where the retinohypothalamic tract exits.

The mucous membranes ( or mucosae or mucosas ; ekvachan mucosa ) hai linings of zyaadaatar endodermal utpatti, covered in epithelium, which are involved in absorption and secretion.
They line cavities that are exposed to the external paryaavaran or aatanrik angon.
They are at several places contiguous saath skin : at the nathunon, the hoth of the munh, the eyelids, the kaanon, the genital area, and the anus.
The sticky, thick drav sravit by the shlesmak jhilliyon and glands is termed mucus.
The term mucous jhilli refers to jahaan ve hai mila in the deh and not every mucous membrane secretes mucus.
The glans clitoridis, glans penis ( head of the shishn ), saath saath the andar of the agratvachaa or the clitoral hud, are mucous membranes.
The urethra is bhi a shlesmak jhilli.
the sravit mucus fanda the pathogens in the deh, preventing any further activities of diseases.

Cake is a rup of bread or bread-like khaanaa.
In its aadhunik form, it is typically a mithi baked mithai.
In its oldest form, cakes yahood saamanytah fried breads or cheesecakes, or saamanytah had a disk shape.
Determining whether a die khaanaa chahie be vargeekrut as bread, kek, or pastery can be difficult.
Modern cake, visheshkar parat cakes, saamanytah contain a sangyojan of aataa, sugar, andey, or makkhan or aayal, saath kuch kismein bhi requiring liquid ( typically milk or water ) and leavening agents ( such as yeast or baking powder ).
Flavorful ingredients like fruit purées, nuts, dried or candied fruit, or extracts hai praayah added, or numerous substitutions liye the primary ingredients are possible.
Cakes are often filled with fruit preserves or mithai sauces ( jaise pastery malai ), iced saath buttercream or anya icings, or sajaa saath marzipan, piped borders or candied fruit.
kek is praayah the mithai of chunaav liye meals at ceremonial avasaron, visheshkar weddings, anniversaries, and birthdays.
There are countless cake recipes ; kuch hai bread-like, kuch samrudh or vistrut, or anek hai sadiyaan old.
Cake making is no longer a complicated procedure ; while at one time considerable labor gai into kek bananaa ( visheshkar the whisking of anda foams ), baking upkaran or dishanirdesh have maharoom sarlikrut so ki bhi the sabase amateur cook may bake a cake.

Public policy is the principled guide to karrwai liya by the prashasnic karypalika shakhaon of the rajya saath lihaaz to a class of mudde in a manner consistent with law and institutional customs.
In general, the foundation is the pertinent national or substantial sanvaidhanik vidhi or implementing vidhaan aise as the US Federal code.
Further substrates shaamil dono nyaayik interpretations or regulations jisase hai generally authorized by legislation.
Other scholars define it as a system of `` courses of action, niamak upayon, kanoon, or funding praathamiktaayen concerning a die topic promulgated by a governmental entity or its representatives. ''
Public policy is commonly samavisht `` in constitutions, vidhaan acts, and judicial decisions. ''
in the sanyukt rajya, is avadharana refers nahin tabhi to the parinaam of nitiyon, lakin adhik broadly to the decision-making and analysis of governmental decisions.
As an academic discipline, public niti is padhai by professors or vidhyaarthee at public niti skulon of major universities throughout the country.
The U.S. professional association of public policy practitioners, shodhakartaaon, vidwaanon, or vidhyaarthee is the sangh liye public niti vishleshan and Management.
Digestion is the mechanical or rasinic vishleshan of khaanaa into choti components ki hai adhik easily avashoshit into a blood stream, for instance.
Digestion is a form of catabolism : a vishleshan of vishaal khaanaa anuon to choti ones.
When food enters the munh, pachan of the khaanaa starts by the karrwai of mastication, a rup of mechanical digestion, and the wetting contact of saliva.
laar, a drav sravit by the salivary grathiyon, contains salivary amylase, an enzyme which starts the digestion of starch in the food.
After undergoing mastication or mand pachan, the khaanaa hoga be in the form of a small, round slurry mass called a bolus.
It will then travel bas the grasanal or into the pet by the karrwai of peristalsis.
Gastric juice in the pet starts protein pachan.
Gastric juice mukhyatah contains hydrochloric acid or pepsin.
As these two chemicals may damage the stomach wall, mucus is sravit by the pet, providing a slimy parat ki adhiniyamon as a shield viruddh the damaging prabhaav of the rasayan.
At the same time protein digestion is occurring, mechanical mixing occurs by peristalsis, jisase hai lehren of muscular contractions ki move saath the pet wall.
This allows the dravyaman of khaanaa to further mix with the digestive enzymes.
After some time ( typically an hour or two in insaano, 4–6 ghanton in kutto, somewhat shorter avadhi in house billiyon ), the resulting motaa drav is called chyme.
When the pyloric sphincter valve opens, chyme enters the duodenum jahaan it mixes saath digestive anzimon isse the pancreas, and then passes through the small intestine, in which digestion continues.
When the chyme is fully pachataa, it is avashoshit into the blood.
95 % of avasorana of nutrients occurs in the choti intestine.
Water and minerals are reabsorbed waapas into the rakt in the colon ( vishaal aant ) jahaan the ph is thodaa amleey parichay 5.6 ~ 6.9.
Some vitamins, such as biotin or vitamin k ( k2mk7 ) utpaadit by jeevanu in the colon are also absorbed into the blood in the colon.
Waste material is eliminated isse the malashay during defecation.
Henry VIII ( 28 June 1491 – 28 janvari 1547 ) thi king of england isse 21 april 1509 jabatak uske maut.
He was lord, and later king, of Ireland, as well as continuing the nammaatr arji by the angrezi monarchs to the kingdom of frans.
henry thi the duusari monarch of the tuder rajvansh, succeeding his father, Henry VII.
Besides his six marriages, Henry VIII is gyaat liye uske bhoomika in the virah of the girijaghar of england isse the roman catholic Church.
henry 's struggles saath rome led to the virah of the girijaghar of england isse papal praadhikaar, the viched of the Monasteries, and his own establishment as the Supreme Head of the Church of England.
Yet he remained a aastik in kor catholic theological shikshaaon, bhi baad uske excommunication from the Roman Catholic Church.
Henry oversaw the vidhik sangh of england or wales saath the Laws in Wales Acts 1535 and 1542.
In 1513, the new king allied with the Holy Roman Emperor, Maximillian i, or invaded frans in 1513 saath a vishaal, well-equipped fouj, lakin hasil choti at a considerable vittiya cost.
Maximillian, for his part, prayukt the angrezi akraman to uske apana ends, or is prejudiced england 's ability to defeat the French.
This foray would prove the start of an obsession liye henry, jo invaded again in 1544.
This time, Henry 's forces captured the mahatvapurn nagar of boulogne, lakin again the paavan roman samraat, charles v, samarthit henry only as long as he needed to and England, strained by the enormous cost of the war, ransomed the city back for peace.
His contemporaries considered Henry in his prime to be an attractive, educated and sampannataa king, or he rai maharoom varnit as `` ek of the sabase charismatic shaskaon to baithna on the angrezi singhaasana ''.
Besides ruling with nirpeksh shakti, he bhi sagaai khud as an lekhak and composer.
His desire to provide England with a male heir – which stemmed partly from personal vanity and partly because he believed a beti hota be asamarth to consolidate the tuder rajvansh or the najuk salaam ki existed following the yudhon of the gulab – led to the do bate liye jisase henry is most remembered : his six marriages and the English Reformation.
Henry became rugn mote or uske swasthya suffered, contributing to his death in 1547.
He is aksar characterised in uske baad jivan as a lustful, egotistical, harsh, and insecure king.
Bongos ( Spanish : bongó ) hai an afro-cuban percussion instrument.
The drums are of alag aakaar : the larger dhol is pukaara in spani the hembra ( maadaa ) and the smaller the macho ( male ).
They are membranophones, or yantra ki banaaen dhwani by a vibration of a stretched membrane.
Different religious groups include different kitabe in unke biblical canons, in varying aadesh, or sometimes divide or combine kitabe, or charitaarth atirikt material into canonical books.
Christian Bibles range from the sixty-six kitabe of the protostant canon to the eighty-one kitabe of the ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Church canon.
The Hebrew Bible, or Tanakh, contains twenty-four kitabe vibhajit into teen bhaag ; the paanch kitabe of the tora ( `` shikshan '' or `` law '' ), the Nevi'im ( `` prophets '' ), and the Ketuvim ( `` writings '' ).
The first part of Christian Bibles is the Old vasiyat, jisase contains, at nunatam, the twenty-four kitabe of the yahudee bible vibhajit into thirty-nine kitabe or ordered differently from the Hebrew Bible.
The Catholic Church and Eastern Christian churches bhi tham nishchit deuterocanonical kitabe or passages to be bhaag of the boodha vasiyat canon.
The second part is the New Testament, containing twenty-seven books ; the chaar canonical gospels, adhiniyamon of the rasulon, twenty-one epistles or akshar or the kitaab of Revelation.
The Eastern Orthodox, Oriental Orthodox or purvi catholic carch may have naaballig differences in their lists of accepted books.
The suchi die yahan liye ye carch is the sabase samaveshi : if at tanik ek purvi church accepts the book it is included here.
The national flag of the United States of America, often simply referred to as the American flag, consists of thirteen baraabar aadaa dhaariyaan of red ( sheersh or neeche ) prayavarti saath shwet, saath a blue ytaakar in the canton ( referred to specifically as the `` sangh '' ) bearing pachaas choti, shwet, five-pointed sitaron arranged in nau ofaset aadaa pankti of chah sitaron ( sheersh or neeche ) prayavarti saath pankti of five stars.
The 50 stars on the flag represent the 50 rajya of the sanyukt rajya of america or the 13 dhaariyaan represent the teraa angrejon colonies ki ghoshit swatantraaa from the Kingdom of Great Britain and became the first states in the Union.
Nicknames for the flag shaamil the `` sitaron or dhaariyaan '', `` boodha mahima ``, and `` The Star-Spangled Banner. ''
Dred Scott v. sandford,, bhi gyaat as the dred scot nirnay, thi a landmark decision by the U.S. Supreme Court.
It made do pramukh rulings.
The first ruling was ki african-americans yahood nahin nagarikon, or isliye tha no khadaa to sue in federal court.
The second ruling was that the sangheey sarkari tha no shakti to viniyamit gulaami in koi territory acquired subsequent to the creation of the United States.
Given the first ruling, most scholars and anek samakaleen rajnatik aankade ( sahit the netritv of the then-new republican party ) mana ki the duusari sattadhari was not binding precedent, but mere dictum.
The rationale of the Supreme Court regarding the jurisdictional sattadhari implied ki logon of africa descent ( dono slave or free ) yahood nahin surakshit by the samvidhan or yahood not U.S. citizens.
Since dyodhi of the 14th amendment to the u.S. samvidhan, dono rulings hai superseded and no longer valid precedent.
Nonetheless, the case retains aitihaasik significance as it is widely regarded as the worst nirnay ever made by the Supreme Court.
The opinion of the adaalat, likhaa by mukhya insaaf roger B. taney, stirred debate.
The decision was 7–2, and every insaaf besides taney likhaa a pruthak concurrence or dissent.
For the first time chunki marbury v. medisson, the adaalat yojit an adhinium of congress to be unconstitutional.
Dred scot, an african-american slave, tha poocha a sanyukt rajya circuit adaalat to puraskaar use uske swatantraaa kuki he or uske nipun tha resided in a rajya ( illinois ) and a territory ( Wisconsin Territory ) where slavery had been banned.
Chief Justice Roger Taney, writing for the court, yojit ki scot, as a vyakti of africa ancestry, thi nahin a naagarik of the sanyukt rajya or isliye tha no right to sue in federal court.
This holding was contrary to the abhyaas of numerous rajya at the samay, visheshkar free rajya, jahaan free ashweton did in fact enjoy the rights of citizens, such as the right to vote and hold public office.
In what is sometimes considered mere obiter dictum, the Court went on to hold that Congress had no authority to prohibit gulaami in sangheey territories kuki slave hai nijee property or the paanchvaan amendment to the samvidhan protects property swami viruddh pichhade of unke property without due process of law.
in reaching is nirnay, taney tha hoped to settle the growing controversy surrounding slavery in the United States, but it had the opposite effect.
The decision was fiercely debated aarpaar the desh, as shaayad best exemplified by the Lincoln–Douglas debates of 1858.
Abraham Lincoln, the second-ever republican nominee liye adhyaksh, thi samarth to jeet the adhyakshiya chunaav in 1860 ; the stopping of the further expansion of slavery was a key Republican party plank.
the nirnay nibhaai an mahatvapurn bhoomika in the samay of rajya secession or the civil yuddh, haalanki it is charam to say the decision `` caused '' the war.
The decision is acknowledged for the influential bhoomika it nibhaai in altering the neshnal rajnatik landscape : it is credited saath shubharambh abraham lincoln’s neshnal political career and ultimately allowing for his election.
Although the Supreme Court has never explicitly overruled the Dred Scott case, the Court stated in the slaughter-house maamle ki at tanik ek bhaag of it tha already maharoom overruled by the fourteenth amendment in 1868, jisase begins by stating, `` sab vyaktiyon born or deshikrut in the sanyukt rajya, or vishay to the kshetradhikaar thereof, are citizens of the United States and of the State wherein they reside. ''
To jisase the adaalat noted:
The first observation we have to make on this clause is, ki it puts at baaki dono the sawaal jisase we stated to have been the subject of differences of opinion.
It declares that persons may be nagarikon of the sanyukt rajya bagaiyr lihaaz to unke naagarikta of a particular rajya, or it overturns the dred scot nirnay by making all persons born within the United States and subject to its jurisdiction citizens of the United States.
vahin hai darjanon of pados in Columbus, Ohio.
Some hai mushkil to define, as ve encompass vishaal kshetron viksit at alag times—often with sub-neighborhoods within them.

Excerpts and border information are drawn directly isse the pramukh aalekh.

The USA Basketball Men 's Senior National Team, commonly gyaat as the sanyukt rajya main 's neshnal basket toli, represents the sanyukt rajya of America in international men 's basketball.
The USA is the most successful toli in antarrashtriya pratiyogita, jeetna medals in sab satraa olympic tournaments it has entered, coming away with fourteen golds.
Two of its gold medal-winning squads were inducted to the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame as tiimon in agast 2010—the 1960 toli, jisase pradarshit chah haul of famers ( 4 khilaadi, 2 coach ), or the 1992 `` sapana toli '', featuring 14 haul of famers ( 11 khilaadi, 3 coaches ).
the sanyukt rajya is philhal kramit pehla in the FIBA World Rankings.
Traditionally composed of amateur khilaadi, a 1989 niyam badalen by fiba anumat uese basket to field tiimon with professional players.
The pehla aise toli, gyaat as the `` sapana toli '', jiti the gold medal at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona, Spain, playing in the final against Croatia.
With the parichay of peshewar, the toli thi samarth to chingaari a duusari run of dominance after capturing only a bronze medal in 1988.
A team of professional khilaadi competed at the 1994 fiba sansar championships, finishing pehla.
In 1996, 2000, 2008, or 2012 the uese again captured sunaharaa medals.
Facing increased competition, the USA vifal to jeet a padak at the 2002 fiba sansar championships, finishing sixth.
The 2004 Summer Olympic team lost three games on its way to a bronze medal, a record that represented more nuksaan in a single saal than the desh 's olympic tiimon tha suffered in sab pichhlaa olympiads sanyukt.
Determined to put an samaapt to ye asafalataaon, uese basket initiated a long-term project aimed at creating better, more cohesive teams.
The USA won its first seven khel at the 2006 fiba sansar championships in japani pehle khone viruddh unaniyon in the semi-finals, samaapti the pratiyogita with the bronze medal.
The USA won gold two years baad, haalanki, at the 2008 garmiyaan olympic saath a prabal pradarshan.
This success was followed up at the 2010 FIBA sansar championships, jahaan despite kshetrarakshan a roster featuring no khilaadi isse the 2008 olympic toli, the uese kiya not lose a single game en route to defeating host Turkey for the gold medal.
The USA continued this streak of dominance by going aparajit or capturing sunaharaa ekbar adhik at the 2012 garmiyaan Olympics.

A stalagmite ( or ; from the Greek σταλαγμίτης - stalagmitês, from σταλαγμίας - stalagmias, `` chhodane, trickling '' ) is a prakaar of speleothem ki udai isse the manzil of a chuunaa gupha due to the tapakataa of mineralized solutions and the deposition of calcium carbonate.
This stalagmite formation occurs tabhi antargat nishchit ph sharten bheetar the bhumigat cavern.
The corresponding formation on the chat of a gupha is gyaat as a stalactite.
If ye formations grow saath, the result is known as a column.
The haul of diggaj in the carlsbad Caverns
stalagmites chahie saamanytah nahin be chuaa, chunki the chattan buildup is formed by khanij precipitating out of the jal samaadhaan onto the old surface ; skin oils can alter the surface where the mineral water will cling, thus affecting the growth of the formation.
Oils and dirt from human sampark can bhi daag the gathan or badalen iske rang permanently.
Similar structures can also form in lava tubes, sambhddha saath kuch prakaar of lavacicles, haalanki the yantriki of gathan is very different.
Stalactites and stalagmites can bhi rup on kancreet ceilings or floors, haalanki ve rup much adhik rapidly there than in the natural cave environment.
The largest stalagmite in the sansar is unchi or is stith in the gupha of cueva martin Infierno, Cuba.
In the Zagros Mountains of south Iran, approximately from the ancient city of Bishapur, in the shapur gupha on the chauthi of paanch baramada stand the 3rd sadi ce pratimaa of Shapur I, second ruler of the Sassanid Empire.
The statue, carved from ek stalagmite, is nearly unchi.
How I mili apana maan is an amareeki sitcom ki premiered on CBS on September 19, 2005.
The show was nirmit by craig thomas or carter Bays.
How I Met Your Mother is framed by the year 2030, jab ted mosby ( voiced by bob saget ) gathers uske beti ( lyndsy fonseca ) or son ( David Henrie ) to tell them the story of how he met their mother.
We flashback to where it begins in 2005 with Ted Mosby ( Josh Radnor ) as a single, 27-year-old architect living with his two best friends from wesleyan vishvavidhyalayon, marshall eriksen ( jesan segal ), a vidhi chaatr, or lily elderin ( alyson haningan ), a kindergarton teacher, jo have maharoom dating for almost nine years when Marshall proposes.
Their engagement causes Ted to socho parichay dhundhna uske apana aatma mate, much to the disgust of uske dost barni stinson ( neil patric haris ), a womanizer with an unnamed corporate job.
And thus, Ted begins his dhundhen liye uske purna mate, or meets robin scherbatsky ( kobi smalders ), whom he also befriends.

Gringo (,, ) is a slang Spanish or portugali shabd prayukt in ibero-america, to denote videshiyon, praayah isse the United States.
The term can be lagu to kisi jo is darasal a foreigner, or it can denote a strong association or assimilation into foreign ( particularly US ) society and culture.
In Spanish it does nahin have a rinatmak connotation.
Roger axtell, a safar tahazeeb visheshgy, tip ki `` [ t ] he word gringo is not necessarily a bad word.
It is kathboli lakin is apmanjanak tabhi in its use and context. ''
The word was prayukt in spain long pehle it crossed the atlantic to denote videshi, non-native speakers of Spanish.
The great white shark, Carcharodon carcharias, also known as the great white, shwet suchak, shwet shark, or shwet maut, is a prajati of vishaal lamniform shark jisase can be mila in the tateey sataha waters of sab the major oceans.
The great white shark is mukhyatah gyaat liye iske aakaar, saath the largest individuals gyaat to have approached or exceeded in length, and in weight.
This shark pahunch iske paripakvata around 15 saalo of aayu or can have a life span of over 30 years.
The great white shark is arguably the sansar 's largest gyaat extant macropredatory machhlee, or is ek of the primary predators of marine mammals.
It is also gyaat to shikaar upon a kismein of anya samudri pashu, including fish and seabirds.
It is the only known surviving prajati of iske genus carcharodon, or is kramit pehla in having the most attacks on humans.
The IUCN list the great white shark as a vulnerable species, jabaki it is shaamil in parishisht ii of cites.
The bestselling novel Jaws by Peter Benchley and the subsequent blockbster filmi by steven spilberg chitrit the great shwet shark as a `` ferocious man eater ``.
In vaastaviktaa, insaano hai nahin the pasandida shikaar of the great white shark.
The sanyukt rajya hathiyaarband shaktiyaan hai the sainya shaktiyaan of the United States of America.
They consist of the fouj, navy, samudri corps, air force, or Coast Guard.
The U.S. has a strong parampara of civilian control of the military.
The President is the military 's overall head, and helps form military policy saath the u.S. vibhaag of raksha ( dod ), a sangheey karypalika vibhaag, acting as the principal ang by which military policy is carried out.
The DoD is headed by the sachiv of raksha, jo is a civilian or Cabinet member.
The Defense Secretary is second in the sainya 's kadi of cmand, bas neeche the adhyaksh, or serves as the principal sahaayak to the President in all DoD-related matters.
To coordinate military action with diplomacy, the adhyaksh rai an salaahkaar neshnal suraksha parishad headed by a National Security Advisor.
Both the President and Secretary of Defense are advised by a seven-member Joint Chiefs of staff, jisase shaamil the sir of prayek of the raksha vibhaag 's seva shakhaon as khub as the mukhya of the National Guard Bureau.
Leadership is provided by the adhyaksh of the sanyukt chiefs of Staff and the Vice Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff.
The commandent of the coast guard is nahin a sadsy of the sanyukt Chiefs of Staff.
All of the branches work together during operations and joint missions, under the ekikrut combatant cmand, antargat the praadhikaar of the sachiv of raksha saath the exception of the Coast Guard.
The coast guard jalprapaat antargat the prashasan of the vibhaag of mathrubhumi suraksha or receives its operational orders from the Secretary of Homeland Security.
The Coast Guard may be transferred to the vibhaag of the navy by the adhyaksh or congress dauraan a samay of war.
All five armed sevaayen hai among the saat uniformed sevaayen of the sanyukt rajya ; the anya hai the u.S. public swasthya seva commissioned corps and the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration Commissioned Corps.
From the time of its inception, the military nibhaai a nirnaayak bhoomika in the itihaas of the United States.
A sense of national unity and identity was forged as a parinaam of vijay in the pehla barbary yuddh or the duusari barbary War.
Even so, the Founders were suspicious of a permanent military force and not until the outbreak of sansar yuddh ii kiya a vishaal khadaa fouj become officially sthapit.
The National Security Act of 1947, adopted following World War II and during the Cold War 's onset, created the aadhunik u.S. sainya fremawork ; the adhinium milaayaa previously cabinet-level vibhaag of yuddh or the vibhaag of the navy into the neshnal sainya sthapana ( renamed the vibhaag of raksha in 1949 ), headed by the sachiv of raksha ; or nirmit the vibhaag of the Air Force and National Security Council.
The U.S. military is one of the largest militaries in sharten of kramank of karmiyon.
It draws its manpower from a large pool of sashulk swayamsevak ; haalanki conscription rai maharoom prayukt in the past in vibhinn times of both war and peace, it has not been used since 1972.
As of 2013, the u.S. kharch parichay $ 554.2 arab annually to nidhi iske sainya shaktiyaan, or appropriates approximately $ 88.5 billion to fund Overseas Contingency Operations.
Put together, the U.S. constitutes roughly 43 pratishat of the sansar 's sainya expenditures.
The U.S. Armed Forces as a whole possess large quantities of advanced and shaktishaalee upkaran, saath saath faili avasthiti of shaktiyaan around the sansar, giving unhen significant samarthy in both defense and power projection.
Freedom of speech is the political right to communicate one 's raay or vichaar using ek 's deh or property to anyone jo is willing to praapt unhen.
The term freedom of expression is sometimes used synonymously, lakin shaamil koi adhinium of seeking, receiving or imparting soochna or vichaar, regardless of the medium used.
In practice, the right to freedom of vaak is nahin nirpeksh in koi desh or the sahi is commonly vishay to simaaen, as saath manahani, badanaami, obscenity, rajdroh ( sahit, liye udhaaharan inciting ethnic hatred ), copyright violation, revelation of information that is classified or otherwise.
The right to freedom of abhivyakti is pahachaanaa as a insaan sahi antargat aalekh 19 of the saarvbhaumik ghoshnaa of insaan adhikaron or pahachaanaa in antarrashtriya insaan adhikaron vidhi in the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights ( ICCPR ).
Article 19 of the ICCPR states that `` [ e ] veryone shall have the right to hold opinions without interference '' and `` everyone shall have the sahi to swatantraaa of abhivyakti ; is sahi shall shaamil swatantraaa to talash, praapt or impart soochna or vichaar of sab kinds, regardless of frontiers, either orally, in likhane or in print, in the form of art, or through any other media of his choice ''.
Article 19 goes on to say that the exercise of these rights carries `` khaas kartavya or jimmedaariyon `` or may `` isliye be vishay to nishchit pratibandh '' jab jaruri `` [ f ] or aadar of the adhikaron or pratishtha of anya '' or `` [ f ] or the protection of national security or of public order ( order public ), or of public health or morals ''.
Freedom of speech may be legally curtailed in some religious legal systems and in dharmanirpeksh jurisdictions jahaan it is mila to kaaran dharmik thokar, aise as the angrejon jatigat or dharmik Hatred Act 2006.
