Dwight David `` Ike '' ijanhavar ( sunaaya, ; aktubar 14, 1890 – kooch 28, 1969 ) was the 34th President of the United States from 1953 until 1961.
He had previously been a five-star general in the United rajya fouj dauraan sansar yuddh ii or parosa as param commander of the alide shaktiyaan in europea ; he tha jimmedaari liye niyojan or supervising the akraman of uttar africa in aaparishan mashaal in 1942–43 and the successful invasion of France and Germany in 1944–45 from the Western Front.
In 1951, he became the first param commander of nato.
ijanhavar thi of pencilvenia dach ancestry or thi reared in a vishaal parivaar in kansas by abhibhavak saath a robust work ethic and religious background.
As one of six sons, he was conditioned by a pratispardhi maahaul jisase instilled self-reliance.
He attended or graduate isse west point or baad shaadishuda and had two sons.
After World War II, ijanhavar parosa as fouj mukhya of staff antargat adhyaksh harry S. truman, tab assumed the post of adhyaksh at Columbia University.
Eisenhower entered the 1952 adhyakshiya res as a republican to counter the non-interventionism of Senator Robert A. Taft and to crusade against `` Communism, Korea and corruption ''.
He won by a bhuskhalan, defeating democrate adlai stevenson or samaapti do decades of the New Deal Coalition.
In the first year of his presidency, Eisenhower apdasth the netaa of iraan in the 1953 irani takhtapalat d'état or prayukt nabhikeey threats to conclude the Korean War with China.
His New Look policy of nuclear deterrence gave priority to inexpensive nuclear weapons while reducing the funding for conventional military shaktiyaan ; the lakshya thi to rakhana dabaav on the soviet sangh or reduce sangheey deficits.
In 1954, Eisenhower first articulated the domino siddhanth in uske varnan of the threat prastut by the spread of communism.
The Congress agreed to his nivedan in 1955 liye the formosa rezolution, jisase sakriy use to prevent chinis communist aakraamakata viruddh chinis rashtravaadiyon or sthapit the u.S. policy of defending Taiwan.
When the Soviets shubharambh sputnik in 1957, he tha to khel catch-up in the space race.
Eisenhower forced Israel, the uk, or frans to samaapt unke akraman of mishra dauraan the suez sankat of 1956.
In 1958, he bheja 15,000 us sainikon to lebanon to prevent the pro-western government from falling to a Nasser -inspired revolution.
Near the end of his term, his efforts to set up a summit baithak saath the soviets collapsed kuki of the u-2 ghatana.
On the domestic front, he covertly opposed Joseph McCarthy and contributed to the end of mccarthyism by khulkar invoking the aadhunik vistaarit sanskaran of karypalika privilege.
he varanaa baayein sabase rajnatik kaaryaklap to his Vice President, Richard Nixon.
He was a moderate roodhiwaadee jo jari nai saude agenciyon and expanded Social Security.
Among his enduring innovations, he launched the Interstate Highway System ; the Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency ( DARPA ), which led to the internet, among many invaluable output ; the neshnal aeronautics or spes prashasan ( nasa ), driving shantipurna discovery in spes ; the sthapana of damdaar vigyaan shiksha via the neshnal raksha shiksha adhinium ; or protsaahit shantipurna upyog of nabhikeey shakti via amendments to the Atomic Energy Act.
In social policy, he bheja sangheey sainikon to choti chattan, arkansaas, liye the pehla samay chunki punarnirmaan to enforce sangheey adaalat orders to desegregate public schools.
He also signed civil rights legislation in 1957 or 1960 to protect the sahi to vote.
He implemented desegregation of the hathiyaarband shaktiyaan in do saalo or made five appointments to the Supreme Court.
He was the first term-limited adhyaksh in accordance saath the 22nd amendment.
Eisenhower 's two terms were peaceful ones for the most part and dekhi considerable aarthik samruddhi magar liye a sharp mandi in 1958–59.
Eisenhower is praayah kramit atyadhik among the u.S. Presidents.
Air Force One is the official air traffic control call chihn of a sanyukt rajya air force vayuyan carrying the adhyaksh of the United States.
In common parlance the pad refers to those air force vayuyan specifically designed, nirmit, or prayukt liye the purpose of transporting the president.
The adhyakshiya vayuyan is a prominent pratik of the amareeki presidency and its power.
The idea of designating specific military aircraft to transport the President arose in 1943, jab officials of the sanyukt rajya fouj air shaktiyaan – the purvavarti to the u.S. air force – became chintit saath relying on vanijyik airlines to transport the President.
A C-87 Liberator Express was reconfigured liye upyog as a adhyakshiya hastantaran ; however, it thi asweekrut by the rahasy seva amid chintaaen over the aircraft 's safety record.
a c-54 skymaster thi tab parivartit liye adhyakshiya upyog ; is vayuyan, utaavle the pavitra gaay, transported adhyaksh franklin D. rujvelt to the Yalta Conference in February 1945, and was subsequently used for another two years by President Harry S. Truman.
the `` air force ek '' kol chihn thi nirmit baad a 1953 ghatana dauraan jisase a udaan carrying adhyaksh Dwight D. Eisenhower entered the same airspace as a commercial airline flight using the same call sign.
Several aircraft have been used as Air Force One since the creation of the presidential fleet, sahit do bowing 707s introduced in the 1960s or 1970s, kramshah ; chunki 1990, the adhyakshiya bede rai consisted of do bowing vc-25as – specifically vinyast, highly customized Boeing 747-200B series aircraft.
The Air Force is looking into replacing the do vc-25 vayuyan saath teen badalanaa vayuyan beginning in 2017.
A wedding anniversary is the varshganth of the tithi a vivaah took place.
Traditional names maujuud liye sabase of unhen : liye udhaaharan, 50 saalo of vivaah is pukaara a `` sunahari wedding anniversary '' or simply a `` golden anniversary ''.
a scinar saath duplexing swachaalit Document Feeder.
In multifunction or all-in-one mudrak, fax mashine, photocopiers or scanners, an swachaalit dastauez feader or adf is a visheshta jisase takes anek prishthon or feeds the paper one page at a time into a scanner or copier, allowing the user to scan, and thereby copy, print, or fax, multiple-page documents without having to manually replace each page.
sabase copiers allow scanning on the flatsbed or platen ( the `` glass '' ) or through a document feeder.
The vast majority of fax mashine have an adf, allowing the unattended sending of multi-page faxes.
Due to the ubiquity of ADF in fax machines, some fax yantra swami upyog the fax yantra as a scinar, faxing multi-page documents to themselves.
Document feeders are described by gati, in prishthon prati minute or ppm, or kshamta, praayah in a dayera from 10 sheets to 200.
There are two kinds of document feeders capable of two-sided ( duplex ) scanning : a reversing swachaalit dastauez feader or radf scans ek paksh of a pej, tab flips it or scans the anya paksh.
A duplexing swachaalit dastauez feader or dadf scans dono pahalu in one pass.
The advantage of the dadf is tej gati liye two-sided originals.
radfs or dadfs hai rated in bimb prati minute ( ipm ), the kramank of pahalu they can scan each minute.
Fair Park is a recreational or shaikshanik jatil located in Dallas, Texas ( USA ).
The complex is panjikrut as a dalas landmark, neshnal aitihaasik landmark or is ghar to nau sangrahalay, chah pradarshan suvidhaayen, a lagoon, or the largest Ferris wheel in North America.

hone designated as a great place in america, Fair Park was one of only ten cities chosen in 2011.
san jose ( ; spani : st. joseph ) is the third-largest nagar in california, the tenth-largest in the u.S., or the county seat of santa clara county which is located at the southern end of San Francisco Bay.
San Jose is the largest nagar bheetar silicon ghati, jisase is a pramukh ghatak of the vrihad san francisco khadi kshetrafal, a pradesh of 8.4 million people and the fifth largest metropolitan area ( CSA ) in the United States.
It is the largest nagar in uttari california.
San Jose was founded on November 29, 1777, as el pueblo de san jose de guadalupe, the pehla civilian kasbaa in the spani upnivesh of nueva California, which later became Alta California.
The city served as a farming community to support spani sainya sansthapana at san francisco and Monterey.
When California gained statehood in 1850, san jose parosa as iske pehla capital.
After more than 150 years as a small farming city, San Jose and the surrounding santa clara ghati became the pichhlaa ( or largest ) sanlagn kshetrafal of aviksit jameen surrounding the San Francisco Bay.
San Jose experienced increased maang liye awaas isse sainiko or diggajon returning from World War II.
San jose tab jari iske aakraamak vistaar dauraan the 1950s and 1960s by annexing more land area.
The rapid growth of the high-technology or electronics udyog further twarit the parivartan isse an agricultural center, to an urbanized metropolitan area.
By the 1990s, San Jose 's location within the booming local praudyogiki udyog arjeet the nagar iske upnaam, puunji of silicon Valley.
San Jose now maintains vaishvik nagar aukaat or is the largest nagar in the san francisco khadi kshetrafal in sharten of janasankhyikee, jameen kshetrafal, or audyogic development.
The U.S. janasankhyikee beuro reported the janasankhyikee of the nagar to be 945,942 as of the 2010 Census.
As of April 2013, the anumaanit janasankhyikee of San Jose was 984,000.
San Jose, along with the Santa clara ghati, anbhavi parichay half a sadi of spectacular suburban sprawl, saath visheshtaayen of teevr shahari similar to the Los Angeles area of Southern California.
The city has taken definite kadam to avoid banane `` l.A. uttar ''.
However, the sprawl in San Jose is worse than in Los Angeles by upayon aise as janasankhyikee ghanatv or public pargaman suraksha, nivesh, and ridership.
Europe depicted by Antwerp cartographer abraham ortelius in 1595
The history of Europe covers the people inhabiting the European continent chunki it thi pehla aabaadi in pragaitihaasik times to upasthit, saath the pehla homo sapiens arriving between 45,000 and 25,000 BC.
The earliest settlers to pragaitihaasik europea came during the paleolithic era.
the aagaman of krishi around 7000 BC ushered in the neolithic age.
Neolithic Europe lasted liye 4000 saalo, ativyapee saath metal-using samskritiyon ki dhire sprad throughout the continent.
technological agrim dauraan the pragaitihaasik aayu tended to arrive isse the Middle East, spreading gradually to the northwest.
Some of the best-known sabhyataaon of pragaitihaasik europea yahood minoai or misinian, jisase flourished dauraan the Bronze Age until they collapsed in a short period of time around 1200 BC.
The period known as shastreey pracheenta began saath the vruddhi of the city-states of Ancient Greece.
Greek influence reached iske zenith antargat the expansive samrajya of sikandar the Great, spreading throughout Asia.
Northern and western europea yahood varchasv by the la tène samskruti, a precursor to the Celts.
Rome, a small city-state traditionally founded in 753 BC, would grow to become the roman ganatantr in 509 bc or hota safal unani samskruti as the prabal bumadhyasagariya civilization.
The events of the rule of Julius Caesar led to reorganization of the ganatantr into the roman samrajya.
The empire thi baad vibhajit by the samraat diocletian into the Western and Eastern empires.
During the later years of the Roman Empire, the Germanic peoples of uttari europea grew in shakti or doharaaya hamale led to the patan of the pashchimi roman samrajya in ad 476, a tithi jisase traditionally marks the samaapt of the classical period and the start of the Middle Ages.
During the madhya aayu, the purvi roman samrajya batch, haalanki aadhunik itihaaskaaron refer to this state as the Byzantine Empire.
In Western Europe, Germanic peoples moved into positions of power in the remnants of the purv pashchimi roman samrajya or sthapit kingdoms or empires of unke own.
Of all of the germanic peoples, the franks hota vruddhi to a sthiti of aadhipaty over pashchimi europea, the frankish Empire reaching its peak under Charlemagne around AD 800.
Francia was divided into several parts ; West francia hota evolve into the kingdom of frans, jabaki east francia hota evolve into the paavan roman Empire, a precursor to modern Germany.
The British Isles were the sait of anek large-scale migrations.
Native Celtic peoples had been marginalized during the kaal of roman britain, or jab the romans abandoned the angrejon isles dauraan the 400s, lehren of germanic anglo-saxons migrated to dakshini britain or sthapit a shrenee of petty kingdoms in what would eventually develop into the Kingdom of England by AD 927.
During this kaal, the kingdom of candal or kingdom of hungarian ( 1000–1945 ) yahood vyavasthit as well.
The viking aayu, a kaal of migrations of scandinavian peoples, varchasv the period from the late 700s to the middle 1000s.
Chief among the Viking states was the samrajya of cnut the great, a danish netaa jo hota become king of england, denmark, and Norway.
The Normans, a Viking people who settled in Northern France and founded the Duchy of normandy, hota have a significant prabhaav on anek bhaag of europea, isse the Norman conquest of England to Southern Italy and Sicily.
Another Scandinavian people, the Rus ' people, would go on to mila kievan rus ', an jaldi rajya jisase thi a precursor liye the aadhunik desh of Russia.
As the viking aayu khinchaa to a band, the kaal gyaat as the crossed, a shrenee of religiously-motivated sainya expeditions originally intended to bring the Levant back into Christian rule, began.
Several Crusader rajya yahood santhaapit in the purvi bumadhyasagariya.
These were sab short-lived.
The Crusaders hota have a profound prabhaav on anek bhaag of europea.
unke bori of kustutuniya in 1204 brought an abrupt end to the Byzantine Empire.

Univisión ( ) is a spanish-language television sanjaal in the United States.
The network is primarily dedicated for Latin amareeki pariwaron jo reside in the sanyukt rajya.
It has the largest audience of spanish-language television darshak in the sansar according to nielsen darja.
Randy Falco, ( CEO as of June 29, 2011 ) COO, rai maharoom in charge of the company chunki the prasthaan of univision sanchaar adhyaksh or siio Joe Uva in April 2010.
In recent years the network has reached parity with the U.S. 's five major English-language television sanjaal, or is praayah a damdaar paanchvaan, outranking the cw, saath kuch fourth-place saptahik placings, or as of 2012, even first place rankings for individual programs over all five English networks due to the network 's consistent schedule of new telenovelas all 52 weeks of the year.
Univisión is headquartered in nai york, or rai iske pramukh studios, utpaadan suvidhaayen, or parichaalan in doral, Florida, a suburb of Miami.
In 2009, another television studio thi ghoshit, Univision Studios, to be built in Doral.
Univision is available on cable and satellite in sabase of the desh, saath local stesan in over 50 bazaar saath vishaal hispanic or laathini populations or a neshnal cabel sanjaal feed distributed in markets without either the availability or the demand for a locally-based station.
Most of these stations air full local news and other local programming in addition to network shows, and in pramukh bazaar aise as los angeles, nai york, or miami the local newscasts carried by the sanjaal 's owned-and-operated stesan ( o & o ) stesan are equally competitive with their English-language counterparts ratings-wise.
Univisión was acquired on March 29, 2007 by a consortium led by Haim Saban 's Saban Capital Group ( who had previously owned the entity Saban Entertainment ), tpg puunji, l.P., vidhaataa equity saajhedaar, medisson dearborn saajhedaar, or thomas H. lee saajhedaar liye $ 13.7 arab or $ 36.25 prati share plus $ 1.4 billion in acquired debt.

The formation and of the Solar System is anumaanit to have begun 4.6 arab saalo pehle saath the gurutvkarshak patan of a choti part of a giant molecular cloud.
Most of the collapsing mass collected in the centre, forming the Sun, while the rest flattened into a aadigrah discs out of jisase the grah, moons, kshudragrah, or anya choti saura pranali laashen formed.
This widely sweekrut model, gyaat as the nebular pariklpana, thi pehla viksit in the 18th century by Emanuel Swedenborg, Immanuel Kant, and Pierre-Simon Laplace.
Its subsequent development has interwoven a kismein of vaigyanik disciplines sahit khagolashastra, bhautikee, bhuvigyaan, or planetary science.
Since the dawn of the space age in the 1950s and the discovery of extrasolar grah in the 1990s, the model rai maharoom dono challenged or parishkrut to account for new observations.
The saura pranali rai viksit considerably chunki its initial formation.
Many moons have formed from circling discs of gas or dhul around unke janak grah, jabaki anya moons hai vichaar to have formed independently and later been captured by their planets.
Still others, as the Earth 's Moon, may be the parinaam of daanav takkaron.
Collisions between bodies have occurred continually up to the upasthit din or have maharoom central to the evolution of the Solar System.
The sthitiyaan of the grah praayah shifted, or grah have switched places.
This planetary migration is now thought to have maharoom jimmedaar liye much of the saura pranali 's jaldi evolution.
In roughly 5 billion years, the surya hoga kool or vistaar outward anek times iske vartmaan vyas ( banane a red daanav ), pehle dhalaai band iske bahari paraton as a grahiy nebula and leaving behind a stellar remnant known as a white dwarf.
In the far distant future, the gambheertha of guzar sitaron hoga dhire reduce the surya 's retinue of grah.
kuch grah hoga be nasht, anya ejected into interstellar space.
ultimately, over the course of tens of arabon of saalo, it is likely that the Sun will be left with none of the original bodies in orbit around it.
The Trial ( kafka 's asli germany sheershak :, baad as, or ) is a anokhaa likhaa by franj kafka in 1914 or 1915 lakin nahin published until 1925.
One of Kafka 's best-known works, it tells the story of a man giraftaar or prosecuted by a remote, abhigamya praadhikaar, saath the prakruti of his crime revealed to neither him nor the reader.
Like Kafka 's other novels, The Trial was never completed, haalanki it karata shaamil a adhyay jisase brings the story to an end.
Because of this there are certain inconsistencies which exist within the novel, aise as asamantaaon in samay in jod to anya discontinuities in narration.
After Kafka 's death in 1924 his dost or saahitiyik executor adhiktam brod sampadit the text liye prakaashan by verlag Die Schmiede.
The original manuscript is held at the sangrahalay of aadhunik sahitya, marbach am neckar, Germany.
In 1999, the book was listed in Le Mondes 100 Books of the Century and as No. 2 of the behtareen germany novels of the beesvin sadi.

The female figures Liberty or ceres, pratinidhi of the rajya 's motto ( dekhie next item ).
Liberty is holding a staff supporting a `` swatantraaa cap `` ; ceres is pakadakar an overflowing cornucopia.
The streamer at the pair of the emblem contains the rajya motto of New Jersey, `` Liberty and Prosperity '', and the year of statehood, 1776.
It was originally designed by piyare ujin du simitiere in 1777 or thi parivardhit slightly in 1928.
The seal is the central motiff in the dhvaj of nai jersey or the great muhar of the rajya of nai Jersey.
The Coat of arms contains a ghoda 's sir.
A helmet showing that New Jersey governs itself accordingly and three plows on a shield referring to the rajya 's krishi parampara, giving it the upnaam `` Garden State ''.

as a chikitsa nidaan, pedophilia or paedophilia is a manorog vikaar in vyaktiyon 16 saalo of aayu or puraani typically characterized by a praathmik or vishesh yon byaaj toward prepubescent children ( generally age 11 years or younger, though specific diagnosis criteria for the disorder extends the cut-off point for prepubescence to age 13 ).
An adolescent who is 16 years of age or puraani jarur be at tanik paanch saalo puraani than the prepubescent child pehle the aakarshan can be diagnosed as pedophilia.
The term has a range of paribhaashaayen, as mila in psychiatry, manovigyaan, the vernacular, and law enforcement.
The International Classification of Diseases ( ICD ) defines pedophilia as a `` vikaar of vayask vyaktitv or aacharan '' in jisase vahin is a yon variyata liye children of prepubertal or early pubertal age.
According to the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders ( DSM ), it is a paraphilia in which adults or adolescents 16 years of age or older have intense and recurrent sexual preranaayen towards or kalpanaaon parichay prepubescent children ki ve have either acted on or jisase kaaran unhen takalif or interpersonal pareshaani.
In popular usage, pedophilia means any yon byaaj in children or the adhinium of child yon gaali, praayah termed `` pedophilic behavior ''.
For example, The American Heritage Stedman 's Medical Dictionary states, `` pedophilia is the adhinium or kaalpanik on the bhaag of an vayask of engaging in yon kaaryaklap saath a child or children. ''
This common use application also extends to the yon byaaj in or yon sampark saath romil or post-pubescent minors.
Researchers recommend that these imprecise uses be avoided kuki haalanki logon jo commit child yon gaali commonly pradarshnee the vikaar, kuch aparaadhiyon do not meet the clinical diagnosis standards for pedophilia and these standards pertain to prepubescents.
Additionally, nahin sab pedophiles darasal commit such abuse.
Pedophilia was first formally pahachaanaa or namit in the let 19th century.
A significant amount of shodh in the kshetrafal rai liya place chunki the 1980s.
Although mostly documented in men, there are also women who pradarshnee the vikaar, or shodhakartaaon assume uplabdhiyaan estimates underrepresent the sachcha kramank of female pedophiles.
No cure for pedophilia rai maharoom viksit, lakin vahin hai therapies ki can reduce the incidence of a person committing child sexual abuse.
In the United rajya, following kansas v. hendricks, sex aparaadhiyon jo hai diagnosed saath nishchit dimagi vikaar, visheshkar pedophilia, can be vishay to indefinite civil commitment, under various state laws ( generically called SVP laws ) and the federal Adam Walsh Child Protection and Safety Act of 2006.
At present, the sateek kalyankari of pedophilia have nahin maharoom conclusively established.
Research suggests that pedophilia may be correlated saath anek alag neurological abnormalities, or praayah co-exists saath anya vyaktitv disorders and psychological pathologies.
In the contexts of forensic psychology and law enforcement, a variety of typologies have been sujhaayaa to categorize pedophiles according to bartaav or motivations.
Julio César Chávez ( born julio césar chávez gonzález on july 12, 1962 ) is a ritred mexican peshewar boxer.
Chávez is mana by anek logon liye unke khel aankde the mahanatam fighter ever to come out of Mexico.
He is a six-time world champion in teen vazan vibhaajan, or liye anek saalo he thi mana ek of the best pound-for-pound boxer in the world.
In a career that spanned over 25 years, Chávez won five world titles in three weight divisions : wbc super featherweight in 1984, wba lightweight in 1987, wbc lightweight in 1988, wbc lite welterweight in 1989, ibf lite welterweight in 1990, or wbc Light Welterweight in 1994.
He holds records for sabase kaamyaab lagaataar defenses of sansar sheershak ( 27 ), sabase sheershak jhagade ( 37 ), sabase title-fight victories ( 31 ) and he is after Joe Louis with ( 23 ) for most title defenses won by knockout ( 21 ).
Chávez also has the longest aparajit streak in mukkebaazi itihaas, 13 saalo.
His record was 89-0-1 going into uske pehla ghaataa to frenki randel or tha an 87 lado win streak until his `` draw '' with Whitaker.
Julio César Chávez was known for his outstanding punching power, vinaashkari deh akraman, remarkably damdaar chin or the athak stalking of his opponents.
He baandhane # 24 on iespien 's 50 mahanatam mukkebaaz Of All Time.
On disambar 7, 2010, he thi inducted in the prestigious antarrashtriya mukkebaazi haul of Fame for the Class of 2011.
He is the father of prospect Omar chávez or purv wbc middleweight champion julio César Chávez, Jr.

The Holocaust ( from the Greek ' : hólos, `` whole '' and kaustós, `` burnt '' ) also known as the Shoah ( yahudee :, hashoah, `` pralay '' ; yahudee :, churben or hurban, isse the yahudee liye `` vinaash '' ), thi the dravyaman hatya or narsanhaar of lagbhag chah lakh yahudiyon dauraan sansar yuddh ii, a kaarykram of vyavasthit state-sponsored hatya by naaji germany, led by adolf hitler or the naaji party, throughout German-occupied territory.
Of the nine million Jews who had resided in europea pehle the holocaust, lagbhag two-thirds yahood maare.
Over one million Jewish children were killed in the Holocaust, as yahood lagbhag do lakh yahudee mahilaon or teen lakh yahudee main.
A network of over 40,000 facilities in Germany and German-occupied territory yahood prayukt to concentrate, tham, or maar yahudiyon or anya peediton.
Some scholars argue that the mass murder of the Romani and people with disabilities should be included in the definition, and kuch upyog the aam sangya `` holocaust '' to describe anya naaji dravyaman hatyaein, sahit those of soviet bandiyon of yuddh, polish or soviet civilians, and homosexuals.
Recent estimates based on figures obtained since the fall of the Soviet Union indicates kuch ten to gyaarah lakh nagarikon or bandiyon of yuddh yahood intentionally murdered by the Nazi regime.
The persecution and narsanhaar yahood carried out in stages.
Various laws to remove the Jews from civil society, sabase prominently the nuremberg kanoon, yahood enacted in germany saalo pehle the outbreak of World War II.
visheshgyata shiviron yahood sthapit in jisase inmates yahood vasheebhoot to slave majdoor jabatak ve died of exhaustion or disease.
Where Germany conquered new territory in purvi europea, specialized ikai pukaara einsatzgruppen murdered yahudiyon and political opponents in mass shootings.
the occupiers jaruri yahudiyon or romani to be confined in overcrowded ghettos pehle hone transported by freight train to extermination camps where, if they survived the journey, most were systematically killed in gas chambers.
Every arm of Germany 's bureaucracy was involved in the logistics that led to the genocides, turning the teesraa reich into kayaa one Holocaust scholar has called `` a genocidal state ''.
4-H in the United States is a yuvavastha sanghathan administered by the neshnal santhaan of khaanaa or krishi of the sanyukt rajya vibhaag of krishi ( usd ), saath the mishan of `` engaging youth to reach their fullest potential while advancing the field of youth development. ''
The name represents chaar nijee vikaas kshetron of fokas liye the sanghathan : head, heart, hands, and health.
The organization has over 6.5 million sadasyon in the sanyukt rajya, isse aayu paanch to twenty-one, in lagbhag 90,000 clubs.
The goal of 4-H is to develop citizenship, leadership, responsibility and life skills of yuvavastha through experiential siikhnaa kaarykram or a dhanatmak yuvavastha development approach.
Though typically thought of as an agriculturally focused sanghathan as a parinaam of iske itihaas, 4-h aaj focuses on naagarikta, swasth jeena, vigyaan, engineering, and technology programs.
Today, 4-H and related programs exist in over assi deshon around the sansar ; the sanghathan or prashasan varies isse country to country.
prayek of ye kaarykram operates independently, lakin cooperatively through antarrashtriya exchanges, global education programs, and communications.
The 4-h motto is `` to mek the behtareen behatar '', jabaki iske slogan is `` sikh by doing '' ( sometimes written as `` Learn to do by doing '' ).
The neshnal dhvaj of chile, consists of do gairbarabari aadaa bands of shwet or red or a blue vargakar the same height as the white band in the canton, which bears a white five-pointed star in the center.
It thi apanaaya on 18 aktubar 1817.
The Chilean flag is bhi gyaat in spani as la estrella Solitaria ( The Lone Star ).
The star represents a guide to progress and honor ; blue symbolizes the aasmaan or the prashanth samandar, shwet is liye the snow-covered andes, or red stand liye the rakt spilled to achieve swatantraaa.
According to the epic poem La Araucana, the colors yahood niklaa isse those isse the dhvaj flown by the mapuche dauraan the Arauco War.
`` dhvaj din '' is yojit prayek saal on the naveen of july to commemorate the 77 sainiko who died in the 1882 Battle of La Concepción.

Virginia ( ), officially the rashtramandal of virginia, is a u.S. rajya stith in the South Atlantic region of the United States.
Virginia is nicknamed the `` Old Dominion '' and the `` maan of raashtrapatiyon '' baad the aath u.S. raashtrapatiyon born vahin.
The bhugol or jalwaayu of the rashtramandal hai taraasha by the blue lakeeren kyu or the Chesapeake Bay, which provide habitat for much of its flora and fauna.
The capital of the rashtramandal is richmond ; or virginia bich is the most populous city.
Fairfax county is the sabase populous rajnatik subdivision.
the wealthiest is Loudoun County.
The Commonwealth 's janasankhyikee is over aath lakh.
The area 's history begins saath anek swadeshi samooh, sahit the Powhatan.
In 1607 the London Company sthapit the upnivesh of virginia as the first permanent New World English colony.
Slave labor or the jameen acquired isse visthapit deshi amareeki janajatiyon prayek nibhaai a significant bhoomika in the upnivesh 's jaldi politics and plantation economy.
Virginia was one of the 13 Colonies in the American Revolution and joined the confederacy in the amareeki civil yuddh, dauraan jisase richmond thi bana the confederate puunji or virginia 's northwestern county seceded to rup the state of West Virginia.
Although the Commonwealth was under conservative single-party rule for nearly a sadi following punarnirmaan, dono pramukh neshnal partiyon hai pratispardhi in aadhunik virginia.
The Virginia General Assembly is the oldest vidhanmandal in the pashchimi golardh.
The state government has been repeatedly kramit sabase prabhavi by the pew bich on the States.
It is unique in how it treats shaharon or county baraabar, manages local sadaken, or prohibits its governors from serving consecutive terms.
Virginia 's economy has many sectors : agriculture in the Shenandoah Valley ; federal agencies in uttari virginia, sahit the mukhyalay of the vibhaag of raksha or siie ; or sainya suvidhaayen in Hampton Roads, the site of the region 's main seaport.
virginia 's public skulon or anek collejon or vishvavidhyalayon have contributed to growing media and technology sectors.
As a parinaam, computer chips have become the rajya 's agrani export.

Dada ( ) or Dadaism was an art gati of the europea avant-garde in the early 20th century.
Many claim Dada began in Zurich, Switzerland in 1916, spreading to berlin shortly thereafter lakin the oonchaai of nai york dada thi the saal pehle in 1915.
To quote Dona Budd 's The Language of Art gyaan, dada thi born out of rinatmak pratikriya to the horrors of sansar yuddh I.
This antarrashtriya gati thi begun by a samooh of kalakaar and poets associated with the Cabaret Voltaire in Zurich.
Dada asweekrut kaaran or logic, prizing bakawaas, irrationality and intuition.
The origin of the naam dada is unclear ; kuch maananaa ki it is a nonsensical word.
Others maintain ki it originates isse the romanian kalakaaron tristan tzara or marsal Janco 's frequent use of the words da, da, meaning yes, yes in the Romanian language.
Another theory says that the name `` Dada '' came during a baithak of the samooh jab a paper chaaku stuck into a french-german shabdkosh happened to point to 'daday ', a french shabd liye 'hobbyhorse '.
The gati primarily shaamil vizual kala, sahitya, kavy, art manifestoes, art siddhanth, theatre, or graphic dizine, or concentrated iske anti-war politics through a rejection of the prevailing standards in art through anti-art cultural works.
In jod to hone anti-war, dada thi bhi anti- burjua or tha rajnatik affinities with the radical left.
Dada activities included public gatherings, demonstrations, or prakaashan of art/literary jarnals ; passionate kawarej of art, raajnneeti, or samskruti yahood vishay praayah discussed in a variety of media.
Key figures in the movement included Hugo Ball, Emmy Hennings, hans arp, raoul hausmann, hanna höch, yohaness baader, tristan tzara, francis picabia, richard huelsenbeck, georg grosz, jon heartfield, marsal duchamp, beatrice lakdi, court schwitters, and Hans Richter, among others.
the gati bahekaave baad sheliyaan jaise the avant-garde or shahar music andolanon, or samooh sahit surrealism, Nouveau réalisme, pop art and Fluxus.
Dada is the groundwork to abstract art and sound kavy, a starting point liye pradarshan art, a prelude to postmodernism, an influence on pop art, a jashn of antiart to be baad embraced liye anarcho-political uses in the 1960s and the movement that lay the foundation for Surrealism.
First trophic str.
The paudhe in is chitra, or the shaiwal or phytoplankton in the jhil, hai praathmik producers.
They take nutrients from the soil or the water, or manufacture unke apana khaanaa by photosynthesis, using urja isse the sun.
The trophic level of an sajiv is the sthiti it occupies in a food chain.
The word trophic garbhashayi isse the unani τροφή ( trophē ) referring to food or feeding.
A food chain represents a succession of jeevon ki kha another sajiv or hai, in phere, khaaya themselves.
The number of steps an sajiv is isse the prarambh of the kadi is a maap of iske trophic level.
Food chains start at trophic level 1 with primary producers such as paudhe, move to herbivores at str 2, parabhakshi at str 3 or typically samaapt saath carnivores or apex predators at level 4 or 5.
The path along the kadi can rup either a one-way pravaah, or a food `` web. ''
Ecological communities with ucchtar biodiversity rup adhik jatil trophic paths.

A silk-producing raspy cricket.
Silk is a natural protein fibre, kuch form of jisase can be woven into vastra.
The protein fibre of silk is rachit mukhyatah of fibroin or utpaadit by certain insect larvae to form cocoons.
The best-known type of silk is praapt isse the cocoons of the larve of the shahatut silkworm bombyx mori reared in captivity ( sericulture ).
The shimmering rup of resha is due to the triangular prism -like dhaancha of the resha fibre, which allows silk cloth to refract incoming light at different angles, thus producing different colors.
Silks are produced by several other keet, lakin generally tabhi the resha of shalab caterpillars rai maharoom used for textile manufacturing.
There has maharoom kuch shodh into anya silks, jisase differ at the molecular level.
Many silks are mainly produced by the larve of keet undergoing puraa metamorphosis, lakin kuch vayask keet aise as webspinners upaj resha, or kuch insects such as raspy crickets produce silk throughout their lives.
Silk utpaadan bhi occurs in kalapaksh ( madhumakhiyon, wasps, or chintiyon ), silverfish, mayflies, thrips, leafhoppers, beetles, lacewings, fleas, flies and midges.
Other types of arthropod produce silk, most notably vibhinn arachnids aise as makadiyon ( dekhie makadi silk ).

Cyberstalking is the use of the antarjaal or anya electronic arthath to stalk or harass an vyaktigat, a group of individuals, or an organization.
It may include the making of false accusations or kathan of fact ( as in manahani ), nigaraanee, bananaa khatre, pahchaan chori, kshati to aankada or upkaran, the solicitation of naaballig liye sex, or gathering information that may be used to harass.
The definition of `` harassment '' must meet the criterion that a reasonable vyakti, in kabza of the vahi soochna, hota lihaaz it as sufficient to cause another reasonable person distress.
Cyberstalking is different from sthanik or ofline stalking in ki it occurs through the upyog of electronic sanchaar praudyogiki aise as the antarjaal.
However, it sometimes lead to it, or is accompanied by it.
Both hai dand offenses.
Cyberstalking shares mahatvapurn visheshtaayen saath offline stalking.
Many stalkers – online or band – hai prerit by a khwaahish to control their victims.
A cyberstalker may be an online ajanabi or a vyakti whom the target knows.
A cyberstalker may be anonymous and may solicit bhagidaari of anya logon online jo do nahin bhi jaan the nishaanaa.
Cyberstalking is a criminal offense that comes into play antargat rajya anti-stalking kanoon, badanaami kanoon, or utpeedan kanoon.
A cyberstalking conviction can parinaam in a restraining anukram, pariviksha, or bhi dand dand against the assailant, including jail.

It could be to nivedan sidhaa soochna or karrwai isse another party, to anukram aapurtiyan isse a pradaayak, to pahachaano a galati ki thi vachanabaddh, to jawaab directly to a request, to apologize for a wrong or simply to convey goodwill.
Even today, the business letter is still very useful because it produces a sthai ricard, is gopneey, aupchaarik or delivers persuasive, well-considered messages.

Adolf hitler ( ; 20 april 1889 – 30 april 1945 ) thi an austria -born germany rajaneta or the netaa of the naaji party ( ( nsdap ) ; National Socialist German Workers Party ).
He was chancellor of Germany from 1933 to 1945 and dictator of naaji germany ( as führer und reichskanzler ) isse 1934 to 1945.
Hitler was at the kendra of naaji germany, sansar yuddh ii in europea, and the Holocaust.
Hitler was a decorated diggaj of sansar yuddh I.
He joined the germany majdoor ' party ( precursor of the nsdap ) in 1919, and became leader of the NSDAP in 1921.
in 1923, he attempted a takhtapalat d'état in munich, known as the Beer Hall Putsch.
The failed coup resulted in Hitler 's imprisonment, during jisase samay he likhaa uske sansmaran, mein kemff ( my sangharsh ).
After his relies in 1924, hitler gained lokapriy support by attacking the sandhi of versailles or promoting pan-germanism, antisemitism, and anti-communism with charismatic oratory and Nazi propaganda.
After his niyukti as chancelar in 1933, he roopantarit the wimer ganatantr into the teesraa reich, a single-party taanaashaahee aadhaarit on the adhinayakawadi or autocratic ideology of Nazism.
Hitler 's aim was to establish a nai anukram of nirpeksh naaji germany aadhipaty in continental Europe.
To this end, his foreign and domestic policies had the uddeshy of seizing lebensraum ( `` jeena spes '' ) for the Germanic people.
He directed the rearmament of germany or the akraman of candal by the wehrmacht in sitambar 1939, resulting in the outbreak of World War II in Europe.
Under Hitler 's rule, in 1941 German forces and their europea allies occupied sabase of europea or uttar africa.
in 1943, germany tha maharoom majaboor onto the rakshaatmak or suffered a series of escalating defeats.
In the final dinon of the yuddh, dauraan the battle of berlin in 1945, hitler shaadishuda his long-time partner, Eva Braun.
On 30 April 1945, less than two dinon baad, the do vachanabaddh aatmahatya to avoid capchar by the red fouj, and their corpses were burned.
Hitler 's aggressive foreign policy is considered the main cause of the outbreak of sansar yuddh ii in europea.
His antisemitic nitiyon or racially prerit vichaardhaara resulted in the mauton of at tanik 5.5 lakh Jews, and millions of other people deemed racially inferior.

a domen naam is an pahchaan string ki defines a frem of prashasnic swaittata, authority, or control on the Internet.
Domain names are formed by the niyam or prakriyaaon of the domen naam System ( DNS ).
Technically, koi naam panjikrut in the dnes is a domen name.
Domain names are used in various networking contexts and application-specific namakaran or sambodhit uddeshy.
In general, a domain name represents an antarjaal protocol ( ip ) sansaadhan, aise as a nijee computer prayukt to abhigam the antarjaal, a sarwar computer hosting a web site, or the web site itself or any other service communicated via the Internet.
Domain names are organized in subordinate levels ( subdomains ) of the dnes root domen, jisase is nameless.
The first-level set of domen names hai the top-level domen ( tlds ), sahit the generik top-level domen ( gtlds ), aise as the prominent domen com, soochna, jaal and org, and the country code top-level domains ( ccTLDs ).
Below these top-level domains in the DNS hierarchy are the second-level and third-level domain names that are typically open for reservation by end-users jo kaash to conect local kshetrafal sanjaal to the antarjaal, banaaen anya saream accessible antarjaal sansaadhan or run web sites.
The registration of ye domen names is praayah administered by domen naam registrars jo bechein their services to the public.
A fully yogya domen naam ( fqdn ) is a domen naam ki is completely specified in the hierarchy of the DNS, having no omitted parts.
Domain names are usually written in lowercase, haalanki labals in the domen naam pranali hai case-insensitive.

The Mpemba effect, namit baad tanzanian chaatr erasto mpemba, is the assertion ki warmer jal can freeze faster than colder water.
Although there is anecdotal support for the prabhaav, vahin is no anubandh on exactly kayaa the prabhaav is and under what circumstances it occurs.
There have been reports of similar phenomena chunki pracheen times, haalanki saath aparyaapt vivaran liye the claims to be replicated.
The ghatana seems contrary to ooshmaagatiki, lakin a number of possible explanations for the effect have been proposed.
Further investigations hoga need to decide on a precise paribhaasha of `` jamane '' or control a vishaal kramank of starting paramiters in order to confirm or explain the effect.

in arthshaastra, the dhan supplai or dhan bhandar, is the total amount of monetary assets available in an economy at a specific time.
There are anek tareeke to define `` dhan, '' lakin maanak upayon praayah shaamil karency in parisancharan or maang jamaa ( jamakartaon ' easily accessed assets on the books of financial institutions ).
Money supply data hai ankit or prakashit, praayah by the sarkari or the central bank of the country.
Public and private sector analysts have long monitored parivartan in dhan supplai kuki of iske prabhaav on the daam str, mahangaai, the exchange rate and the business cycle.
That relation between dhan or keemten is historically sambhddha saath the quantity theory of money.
There is strong empirical evidence of a direct sambandh between money-supply vikaas or long-term daam mahangaai, at tanik liye rapid increases in the raashi of money in the economy.
That is, a country such as Zimbabwe which saw rapid increases in iske dhan supplai bhi dekhi rapid increases in keemten ( hyperinflation ).
This is one reason for the reliance on maudrik niti as a arthath of controlling inflation.
The nature of is causal kadi is the vishay of contention.
kuch shaast arthshaastriyon argue ki the dhan supplai is endogenous ( sankalpit by the workings of the arthvyavastha, not by the central bank ) and that the sources of inflation must be found in the distributional structure of the economy.
In addition, those economists seeing the central bank 's control over the dhan supplai as feeble kah ki vahin hai do kamjor kadi between the vikaas of the dhan supply and the inflation rate.
First, in the aftermath of a recession, when many resources are underutilized, an badhayen in the dhan supplai can kaaran a sustained badhayen in real utpaadan bajaay of mahangaai.
Second, if the velocity of money, i.e., the anupaat between nammaatr jidipi or dhan supplai, parivartan, an badhayen in the dhan supplai could have either no prabhaav, an exaggerated effect, or an unpredictable effect on the growth of nominal GDP.

, vahin hai 697 imax theatre in 52 countries.

Constitutionalism, in its most general meaning, is `` a jatil of vichaar, attitudes, or pattern of bartaav elaborating the principle ki the praadhikaar of government derives from and is limited by a body of fundamental law ''.
A political organization is constitutional to the extent ki it `` contain [ s ] institutionalized mechanisms of shakti control liye the suraksha of the ruchi or liberties of the citizenry, including those that may be in the minority ``.

An ice-cream headache, also known as brain freeze, cold-stimulus sirdard, or iske die vaigyanik naam sphenopalatine ganglioneuralgia ( arth `` tantrika pidaa of the sphenopalatine gandika `` ), is a rup of bread cranial pidaa or sirdard commonly sambhddha with consumption ( particularly quick consumption ) of cold beverages or foods such as ice cream and ice pops.
It is caused by having kuch thanda tach the chat of the munh ( taalu ), or is believed to parinaam isse a tantrika jawaab causing rapid constriction and swelling of blood vessels or a `` referring `` of pain from the roof of the mouth to the head.
The rate of seven liye thanda bhojan rai maharoom padhai as a contributing factor.
There hai logon jo can nahin anubhav `` dimag fries '' or similar symptoms.
The term ice-cream sirdard rai maharoom in upyog chunki at tanik 31 janvari 1937, contained in a jarnal pravishti by rebeka timbres published in the 1939 book We did n't ask Utopia : a Quaker family in Soviet Russia.
The first published use of the term brain freeze, as it pertains to cold-induced headaches, thi on 27 May 1991.
`` Auld Lang Syne '' ( : note `` s '' rather than `` z '' ) is a scots kavita likhaa by robert burns in 1788 or niyat to the dhun of a paramparaagat lok song ( Roud # 6294 ).
It is well known in anek deshon, visheshkar in the english-speaking sansar ; iske paramparaagat upyog hone to celebrate the prarambh of the nai saal at the stroke of midnight.
By extension, it is bhi sung at antyeshti, graduations or as a vidaai or ending to other occasions.
The antarrashtriya ladke scout yuvavastha gati, in anek deshon, uses it as a close to jamborees and other functions.
The song 's Scots title may be translated into English literally as `` old long since '', or adhik idiomatically, `` long long pehle '', `` dinon gaye by '' or `` old times ''.
Consequently `` For auld lang syne '', as it appears in the first line of the kores, might be loosely anudit as `` liye ( the khatir of ) old times ''.
The phrase `` Auld Lang Syne '' is also prayukt in samaan kavitaayen by robert ayton ( 1570–1638 ), allan ramsay ( 1686–1757 ), or james watasan ( 1711 ) as well as older folk songs predating Burns.
Matthew Fitt uses the phrase `` In the dinon of auld laing syne '' as the samatuly of `` ekbar upon a samay...
`` in his retelling of pari kisse in the scots bhashaa.

Major representatives of the harlem punarjagran.
The Harlem punarjagran thi a saanskrithik gati ki spanned the 1920s.

Though it was centered in the Harlem neighborhood of nai york nagar, anek french-speaking blike lekhak isse africa or caribbean colonies jo jiya in paris yahood bhi bahekaave by the harlem punarjagran.
The Harlem Renaissance is unofficially pahachaanaa to have spanned isse parichay 1919 jabatak the jaldi or mid-1930s.
anek of iske vichaar jiya on much longer.

The history of Africa begins with the praagitihaas of africa or the emergence of homo sapiens in east africa, continuing into the upasthit as a patchwork of diverse and politically developing nation states.
Some jaldi pramaan of krishi in africa tithiyaan isse 16,000 bce, and metallurgy from about 4000 BCE.
The recorded history of early sabhyataa arose in mishra, or baad in nubia, the magarib or the Horn of Africa.
During the madhya aayu, islam sprad through the regions.
crossing the magarib or the sahel, a major center of Muslim culture was Timbuktu.
Some notable pre-colonial states and societies in Africa include the Nok culture, Mali Empire, Ashanti Empire, kingdom of mapungubwe, kingdom of jya, kingdom of saloum, kingdom of baol, kingdom of zimbabwe, kingdom of kongo, pracheen karthej, numidia, mauretania, the Aksumite Empire, the Ajuuraan State and the Adal Sultanate.
From the late 15th century, Europeans and arabs took slave isse west, central or southeast africa videshi in the African slave trade.
European colonization of africa viksit rapidly in the hathapayee liye africa of the let 19th and early 20th centuries.
Following struggles liye swatantraaa in anek bhaag of the mahadweep, as khub as a weakened Europe after the Second World War ; decolonization took place.
Africa 's history has been challenging liye shodhakartaaon in the field of africa adhyayan kuki of the killat of written sources in large parts of sub-Saharan Africa.
Scholarly techniques aise as the recording of maukhik itihaas, aitihaasik bhashavigyaan, puraatatv and genetics have been crucial.
Curry Foley was the first khilaadi in pramukh lig besabaal itihaas to hit for the cycle.
In baseball, hitting liye the saikil is the accomplishment of ek batter hitting a single, a double, a triple, and a home run in the same game.
Collecting the hits in ki anukram is gyaat as a `` natural cycle ''.
Cycles are uncommon in Major League Baseball ( MLB ), and have occurred 294 times chunki the pehla by curry foli in 1882.
The cycle is roughly as common as a no-hitter ( 279 occurrences in MLB history ) ; it has been pukaara `` ek of the rarest '' or `` sabase mushkil feats '' in besabaal.
Based on 2009 offensive levels, the probability of an average MLB player hitting for a cycle against an average toli in a khel is lagbhag 0.00590 % ; is corresponds to parichay 2.5 chakra in a 162-game ritu saath 30 teams.
In other baseball leagues, the saikil is hasil kam aksar.
Through September 4, 2008, 62 players in Nippon Professional Baseball ( npb ), the top-level besabaal sanghathan in japani, have hit liye the saikil, the sabase haal hone michihiro Ogasawara.
Two players have hit liye the saikil on the vahi din ekbar in npb itihaas ; this has occurred twice in MLB history.
ek npb khilaadi rai bhi hit liye the saikil in an NPB All-Star game.
No player has ever hit liye the saikil in the emelbi all-star khel or the postseason.
The main slave root in madhyakaalin Africa.
This aalekh discusses pranaaliyon, itihaas, or prabhaav of slavery within Africa.
See arab slave vyapaar, atlantic slave vyapaar, maafa, and Slavery in contemporary Africa for other discussions.
`` slave hastantaran in africa ''.
Europeans usually kiya nahin daalen the aantarik regions.
Slavery in africa rai existed throughout the mahadweep liye anek sadiyaan, and continues in the current day.
Systems of servitude and slavery were common in anek bhaag of the mahadweep, as ve yahood in much of the ancient world.
In most African samaajon jahaan gulaami thi prachlit, the enslaved logon yahood largely treated as indentured servants and not treated as chattel slaves.
When the Arab slave trade and Atlantic slave vyapaar began, anek of the local slave pranaaliyon badla or began supplying captives liye slave markets outside of Africa.
Slavery in historical Africa was practiced in anek alag form or kuch of ye do nahin clearly anuroop the paribhaashaayen of gulaami elsewhere in the world.
Debt slavery, enslavement of yuddh captives, sainya gulaami, or dand gulaami were all practiced in various parts of Africa.
Although there had been some trans-Saharan trade from the interior of Sub-Saharan Africa to other regions, gulaami thi a choti bhaag of the aarthik jivan of anek samaajon in africa jabatak the parichay of transcontinental slave trade ( Arab and Atlantic ).
Slave practices were again transformed with europea colonization of africa or the aupchaarik abolition of gulaami in the early 1900s.

khidkiyaan kaary manager thi introduced with Windows NT 4.0.

In Windows XP tabhi, a shutdown menu is bhi upasthit ki allows abhigam to standby, hibernate, phere band, restart, Log Off and Switch User.
Earlier versions of Microsoft khidkiyaan ( microsoft khidkiyaan 3.x, khidkiyaan 95, khidkiyaan 98 ) tha a kaarykram gyaat as kaary to pradarshak the programs currently running.

An afterimage or ghost image or image burn-in is an optical bhram ki refers to an chitra continuing to appear in ek 's drushti baad the expozar to the asli chitra rai ceased.
One of the most aam afterimages is the ujjwal glow ki seems to flash pehle ek 's ankhen baad looking into a light source for a few seconds.

Flat feet ( also called pes planus or fallen arches ) is a aupchaarik sandarbh to a chikitsa condishan in jisase the mehrab of the pair collapses, saath the sampurna ekmaatr of the foot coming into complete or near-complete contact with the ground.
In some individuals ( an anumaanit 20–30 % of the saamaanya janasankhyikee ) the arch simply never develops in one foot ( unilaterally ) or both feet ( bilaterally ).
Three studies ( see citations below in military section ) of military recruits have shown no evidence of baad increased chot, or pair samasyaayein, due to chapata feet, in a janasankhyikee of logon jo pahunchein sainya seva aayu bagaiyr prior foot problems.
however, ye adhyayan can nahin be prayukt to nyaayadhish sambhavit bhavishya damage from this condition when diagnosed at younger ages.
They also can not be applied to persons whose flat feet hai sambhddha saath pair lakshan, or nishchit lakshan in anya bhaag of the deh ( such as the leg or back ) possibly referable to the foot.
Generation X, commonly abbreviated to gen x, is the peedhee born baad the pashchimi post-world War II baby boom.
Demographers, historians and commentators use beginning birth tithiyaan isse the jaldi 1960s to the early 1980s.

Pressure ulcers, also known as decubitus ulcers or bedsores, hai sthaniyakrut choton to the skin and/or underlying utak praayah over a boni prominence, as a parinaam of dabaav, or pressure in combination with shear and/or friction.
sabase commonly is hoga be the sacrum, coccyx, ediyon or the kulhon, lakin anya site aise as the elbows, knees, ankles or the back of the cranium can be affected.
The kaaran of dabaav chhaale is dabaav lagu to naram utak so ki rakt pravaah to the naram utak is completely or partially obstructed.
Shear is also a cause ; shear khinchataa on rakt baratan ki feed the skin.
Pressure ulcers most commonly develop in vyaktiyon jo hai nahin chalati parichay or hai confined to wheelchairs.
It is widely believed ki anya karkon can influence the sahishnutaa of skin liye dabaav and shear thereby increasing the risk of pressure ulcer development.
These factors are protein-calorie kuposhan, microclimate ( skin wetness caused by sweating or incontinence ), rogon ki reduce rakt pravaah to the skin, aise as arteriosclerosis or rogon ki reduce the feeling in the skin, such as paralysis or neuropathy.
The healing of pressure ulcers may be slowed by the age of the person, chikitsa sharten ( aise as arteriosclerosis, madhumeh or sankraman ), smoking or medications such as antiinflammatory drugs.
Although often prevented and treatable if found early, pressure chhaale can be bahut mushkil to prevent in critically biimaar marijon, frail bado, wheelchair upayokta ( visheshkar jahaan spinal chot is shaamil ) and terminally ill patients.
praathmik rokthaam is to redistribute dabaav by turning the patient regularly.
the laabh of turning to avoid further sores is khub pralekhith since at least the 19th century.
In addition to turning and re-positioning the patient in bed or wheelchair, khaane a santulit aahaar saath paryaapt protein or keeping the skin free isse expozar to mutr or stool is very important.
The prevalence of pressure ulcers in hospital jamaavat is unchi, lakin sudhaar hai hone bana.
According to the 2010 IPUP ( International Pressure ulcer vyapaktaa surveykshan ) conducted in canada, vahin thi a significant ghati in the overall facility-acquired vyapaktaa of dabaav ulcers from 2009-2010.
Ulcers were most commonly pahachaanaa at the sacral/coccyx ulcer sthaan ; however, edi chhaale yahood the sabase aam facility-acquired location in the survey.

Luteinizing hormone ( LH, also known as lutropin and sometimes lutrophin ) is a hormone produced by gonadotroph koshikaayen in the agravarti pituitary granthi.
In females, an acute vruddhi of lh ( `` lh surge '' ) triggers ovulation or vikaas of the corpus luteum.
In males, where LH tha bhi maharoom pukaara antaraleey cell-stimulating hormone ( icsh ), it stimulates leydig koshika production of testosterone.
It acts synergistically saath fsh.

Stahlhelm ( bahuvachan, stahlhelme ) is germany liye `` steel helmet ''.
The imperial germany fouj began to badalen the paramparaagat boiled-leather pickelhaube ( spiked combat helmet ) with the Stahlhelm during World War I in 1916.
The term Stahlhelm refers dono to a generik steel helmet, or adhik specifically to the distinctive ( and iconic ) German design.
The Stahlhelm, with its distinctive `` coal scuttle `` shape, was an instantly recognizable pratik liye sainya imagery or became a aam tatv of sainya prachaar on dono pahalu, just like the Pickelhaube before it.
Its name thi bhi prayukt by the stahlhelm, a ardhsainik rashtravaadi sanghathan sthapit at the end of 1918.

Frankfurt Airport serves as a hub city liye lufthansa or receives flite isse star gathbandhan vaahak.
Airline hubs are airports ranked as large, medium, choti, or non-hubs as ek of the faa vimaanashetra shrenee jisase hai re-evaluated prayek saal aadhaarit on kramank of vanijyik passengers.
The more common but informal use for the phrase airline hub is an airport ki an airline upyog as a transafar point to milengi yatri to unke intended destination.
It is part of a hub or spoke model, jahaan travelers chalati between airport nahin parosa by sidhaa flite change planes en route to their destinations.
This is as opposed to the point to point model.
Many hubs of the airlines hai bhi situated at airport in the cities of the respective head offices.
Some airlines may use only a single hub, jabaki anya airlines upyog anek hubs.
Hubs are used liye dono yatri flite as khub as cargo flights.
Many airlines bhi upyog fokas shaharon, jisase falan much the same as hubs.
Airlines may also use dwitiyak hubs, a non-technical pad liye vishaal fokas cities.
A hub in the middle of a route is more effective than at either samaapt as connecting trekkic adhik easily bharta the plane - yatri prefer a one-stop ( two-leg ) route over a two-stop ( three-leg ) route.
khokhla lacedaemon.
Site of the Menelaion, the shrine to Helen and Menelaus constructed anciently in the Bronze Age city ki stood on the hill of therapne on the baayein bainko of the eurotas River overlooking the future site of Dorian Sparta.
Across the ghati the successive ridges of mount taygetus are in evidence.
Sparta ( Doric Greek : ; Attic Greek : ), or Lacedaemon, was a prominent city-state in ancient unaniyon, situated on the bainko of the eurotas nadi in laconia, in south-eastern Peloponnese.
It emerged as a political entity around the 10th sadi bc, jab the akramanakari dorians subjugated the local, non-dorian population.
Around 650 BC, it rose to become the prabal sainya land-power in pracheen Greece.
Given its sainya pre-eminence, sparta thi pahachaanaa as the overall netaa of the sanyukt Greek forces during the Greco-Persian Wars.
Between 431 and 404 BC, Sparta thi the principal dushman of athens dauraan the peloponnesian yuddh, isse jisase it ubhara vijayi, though at great cost.
Sparta 's defeat by thebes in the battle of leuctra in 371 bc ended sparta 's prominent role in Greece.
However, it maintained iske rajnatik swatantraaa jabatak the roman conquest of unaniyon in 146 BC.
It then underwent a long period of decline, visheshkar in the madhya aayu, jab anek spartans sthanantarit to sajiv in mystras.
Modern sparta is the puunji of the unani kshetreey ikai of laconia or a bich liye the prasanskaran of goods such as citrus and olives.
Sparta was unique in ancient Greece for its soshal pranali or samvidhan, jisase completely kendrit on sainya prashikshan or excellence.
Its inhabitants were classified as spartiates ( spartan nagarikon, jo enjoyed puraa adhikaron ), mothakes ( non-spartan free main uthaaya as spartans ), perioikoi ( freedmen ), and Helots ( state-owned serfs, enslaved non-Spartan local population ).
Spartiates underwent the rigorous agoge training and shiksha regimen, or spartan phalanges yahood widely mana to be among the best in battle.
Spartan women enjoyed considerably adhik adhikaron or samta to main than elsewhere in the shastreey world.
Sparta was the subject of fascination in iske apana din, as khub as in the west following the punaruddhar of shastreey learning.
This prem or admiration of sparta is known as Laconism or Laconophilia.
Fantasy football is an interactive competition in which upayokta compete viruddh prayek anya as saamaanya managers of virtual teams.
The players that an individual is able to manage hai peshewar amareeki footbaal khilaadi in the neshnal footbaal lig.

World population estimates from 1800 to 2100, aadhaarit on un 2010 projections ( red, naarangi, green ) or us janasankhyikee beuro aitihaasik estimates ( black ).
Actual recorded janasankhyikee aankade hai in blue.
According to the ucchtam anumaan, the sansar janasankhyikee may vruddhi to 16 arab by 2100 ; according to the lowest estimate, it may decline to 6 billion.
The world population is the kul kramank of jeena insaano on Earth.
As of aaj, it is anumaanit to kramank arab by the sanyukt States Census Bureau ( USCB ).
The USCB estimates that the sansar janasankhyikee exceeded 7 arab on March 12, 2012.
According to a separate anumaan by the sanyukt raashtra janasankhyikee nidhi, it pahunche is milestone on October 31, 2011.
The world population has anbhavi nirantar vikaas chunki the samaapt of the great akaal or the Black Death in 1350, when it stood at around 370 million.
The highest rates of growth – global janasankhyikee increases upar 1.8 % prati saal – yahood dekhi briefly dauraan the 1950s, or liye a longer kaal dauraan the 1960s and 1970s.
The vikaas rate peaked at 2.2 % in 1963, or tha asweekrut to 1.1 % by 2011.
Total annual births were highest in the late 1980s at about 138 million, and are now expected to remain essentially nirantar at unke 2011 str of 134 lakh, jabaki mauton kramank 56 lakh prati saal, or hai apekshit to badhayen to 80 million per year by 2040.
Current projections show a continued increase in population in the near future ( but a sthir manaahi in the janasankhyikee vikaas rate ), saath the vaishvik janasankhyikee apekshit to pahunchein between 7.5 or 10.5 arab by 2050.
Various longer-term estimates bhavishyavaanee further vikaas, stagnation, or bhi overall decline in the global population by 2150.
Some analysts have questioned the sustainability of further world population vikaas, citing the growing pressures on the paryaavaran, vaishvik khaanaa aapurtiyan, or urja sansaadhan.

udhaaharan dayera isse 640 to 850.

A gold baar is a maatra of parishkrut dhatvik sunaharaa of koi aakaar ki is bana by a baar nirmaataa baithak maanak sharten of manufacture, labeling, and record keeping.
Larger gold bars that are utpaadit by pouring the molten metal into molds hai pukaara ingots.
Smaller bars may be manufactured by minting or stamping isse appropriately lipte sunaharaa sheets.
The standard gold bar held as gold reserves by central bainko or traded among bullion dealer is the 400-troy-ounce ( 12.4 kg or 438.9 ounce ) Good Delivery gold bar.
The kilobar, jisase is to kah 1000 gamma in dravyaman, is the baar ki is adhik manageable or is used extensively for trading and investment.
The premium on these bars jab traded is bahut kam over the spot maan of the sunaharaa bananaa it adarsh liye choti hastantaran between banks and traders.

The flag of Mexico ( Spanish : Bandera de México ) is a lambavat tirangaa of green, shwet, or red saath the neshnal kot of bahen charge in the center of the white stripe.
While the meaning of the colors has changed over time, these three colors yahood apanaaya by mexico following swatantraaa isse spain dauraan the desh 's yuddh of Independence, and subsequent First Mexican Empire.

red, shwet, or green hai the rangon of the national liberation army in Mexico.

It recalls the legend ki prerit the aztecs to settle on what was originally a lake-island.

A destination marketing organization or convention and visitor beuro promotes a kasbaa, nagar, pradesh, or desh in anukram to badhayen the number of visitors.
It promotes the development and vipanan of a gantavy, focusing on sammelan bikri, paryaton vipanan, or services.
Such organizations promote economic development of a destination by increasing vizit isse paryatakon or kaarobaar travelers, jisase generates overnight awaas liye a gantavy, vizit to restaraan, and shopping revenues.
Convention and visitor bureaus are the most important tourism vipanan sanghathan in unke sambandhit paryatak gantavyon, as ve hai sidhe jimmedaar liye vipanan the gantavy brands through safar or paryaton `` product awareness '' to visitors.
dmos upaj arabon of dollar in sidhaa or apratyaksh aay or kar liye unke gantavyon ' economies with their marketing and sales expertise.
Destination marketing organizations are often pukaara safar, sammelan, vizitor, or paryaton bureaux, welcome centers, information centers and more.
Regardless of the naam, ye sanghathan prastaav anek services to the traveling public.
The elk or wapiti ( Cervus canadensis ) is one of the largest prajati of hiran in the sansar, or ek of the largest jameen stanadhariyon in uttar america or purvi asia.
It was long believed to be a subspecies of the European red hiran ( cervus elaphus ), lakin pramaan isse a 2004 padhai of the mitochondrial diene indicates ki the two are distinct species.
This animal should not be confused with the larger moose ( alces alces ), to jisase the naam `` nilgai '' applies in Eurasia.
alaava isse the moose, the tabhi anya sadsy of the hiran parivaar to pratidwandvi the nilgai in aakaar is the south Asian sambar ( Rusa unicolor ).
nilgai dayera in van or forest-edge awaas, feeding on grasses, paudhe, pattey, and bark.
Although native to North America and eastern Asia, ve have adapted khub to deshon jahaan ve have maharoom introduced, sahit argentina, Australia, and New Zealand.
Their great adaptability may threaten endemic prajati or ecosystems into jisase they have been introduced.
Male elk have large antlers jisase hai shed prayek saal.
males bhi engage in ritualized samagam vyavhaar dauraan the rut, sahit posturing, antler kushti ( sparring ), or bugling, a laud shrenee of vocalizations which establishes dominance over other males and attracts females.
Elk are susceptible to a kramank of sankramak rogon, kuch of jisase can be transmitted to livestock.
Efforts to eliminate sankramak rogon isse nilgai populations, largely through tikaakaran, have had mixed success.
Some samskritiyon aadar the nilgai as a spiritual force.
In parts of Asia, antlers and unke makhmal hai prayukt in traditional medicines.
Elk are hunted as a khel prajati ; the maance is leaner or ucchtar in protein than beef or chicken.

The lion ( Panthera leo ) is one of the four big billiyon in the genus penthera or a sadsy of the parivaar felidaye.
With some males exceeding in vazan, it is the second-largest jeena cat after the tiger.
Wild lions currently exist in sub-Saharan Africa and in asia ( jahaan an endangered remnant janasankhyikee resides in gir van neshnal park in india ) jabaki anya prakaar of sher have disappeared from North Africa and Southwest Asia in historic times.
Until the late pleistocene, parichay 10,000 saalo pehle, the sher thi the sabase faili vishaal jameen mammal after humans.
They were found in most of Africa, across uresia isse pashchimi europea to india, or in the americas isse the yukon to Peru.
The lion is a vulnerable species, having seen a pramukh janasankhyikee manaahi of 30–50 % over the past do dashakon in iske African range.
sher populations hai untenable outside designated reserves and national parks.
Although the cause of the manaahi is nahin fully samajha, awaas ghaataa or virodh saath insaano hai philhal the mahanatam causes of concern.
Within africa, the west africa sher janasankhyikee is visheshkar endangered.
Lions live liye 10–14 saalo in the junglee, jabaki in captivity they can live longer than 20 years.
In the wild, males seldom live longer than 10 years, as choton sustained isse continual lard saath pratidwandvi males greatly reduce unke aayu.
They typically inhabit savana or ghasbhumi, haalanki they may take to bush and forest.
Lions are unusually soshal compared to other cats.
A pride of lions consists of sambandhit mahilaon or aulad and a small number of adult males.
samooh of maadaa sher typically hunt saath, preying mostly on large ungulates.
Lions are apex and keystone parabhakshi, haalanki ve scavenge as avasar allows.
While sher do nahin typically hunt insaano, kuch have maharoom gyaat to do so.
Sleeping mainly dauraan the din, sher hai primarily nocturnal, haalanki bordering on crepuscular in nature.
Highly distinctive, the male lion is easily recognised by iske maane, or iske phase is ek of the sabase widely recognised animal pratikon in insaan culture.
Depictions have existed from the Upper Paleolithic period, saath utkeernan or paintings isse the lascaux or chauvet gufaaen, through vastutah sab pracheen or madhyakaalin samskritiyon where they once occurred.
It has been extensively chitrit in sculptures, in paintings, on neshnal flags, and in contemporary films and literature.

The human lungs hai the angon of shwasan in insaano.
insaano have do fefde, a sahi fefdon or a left lung.

The trachea divides into two bronchi ( one liye prayek paksh ) at the str of t4.
is jankshan is bhi gyaat as the carina.
the conducting mandal contains the shwaasanlee, the bronchi, the bronchioles, or the terminal bronchioles The respiratory zone contains the respiratory bronchioles, the alveolar ducts, and the alveoli.
The conducting zone and the respiratory stuffers ( but not the alveoli ) hai bana up of airways.
The conducting mandal rai no gas exange saath the rakt, or is reinforced saath upasthi in order to hold open the airways.
The conducting mandal warms the air to and humidifies the air.
It also cleanses the air by nikaalnaa anu via cilia stith on the deevaaren of sab the passageways.
The lungs are ghiri by the pasli pinjraa.
the respiratory mandal is the sait of gas exange with blood.
The sympathetic baichaiyn pranali via noradrenaline acting on the beta receptors causes bronchodilation.
The parasympathetic nervous system via acetylcholine, jisase adhiniyamon on the m-3 muscarinic receptors, maintains the resting tone of the bronchiolar smooth muscle.
This action is sambandhit, haalanki mana pruthak isse bronchoconstriction.
Many other non-autonomic nervous and biochemical stimuli, sahit carbon dioxide or oxigen, hai bhi shaamil in the viniman process.

Intense red-eye prabhaav in blue ankhen saath dilated pupil
The red-eye effect in chayachitr is the aam rup of red pupils in color photographs of eyes.
It occurs when using a photographic flash bahut band to the camera lens ( as saath sabase compact cameras ), in ambient low light.
The prabhaav appears in the ankhen of insaano or pashu ki have tapetum lucidum.
Theatrical followspot operators, positioned nearly coincidentally with a bahut ujjwal lite or somewhat dur isse the abhinaytaon, occasionally gavaah red-eye in actors on stage.
The effect is not visible to the rest of the audience kuki it is reliant on the bahut choti kone between the followspot oparator and the light.
The University of California, Santa Barbara ( commonly referred to as uc santa barbara or ucsb ) is a public shodh vishvavidhyalayon or ek of the ten saamaanya campuses of the vishvavidhyalayon of California system.
The main campus is located on a site in goleta, california, sanyukt rajya, isse santa barbara or uttarpashchim of Los Angeles.
Tracing its roots back to 1891 as an swatantra shikshak ' college, ucsb joined the vishvavidhyalayon of california pranali in 1944 or is the third-oldest general-education campus in the system.
UCSB is one of America 's Public Ivy vishvavidhyalayon, jisase recognizes sheersh public shodh vishvavidhyalayon in the United States.
The university is a comprehensive doctoral university and is organized into paanch collejon or skulon offering 87 undergraduate degree and 55 graduate degrees.
The campus is the 6th-largest in the uc pranali by namakan with 18,977 undergraduate and 2,950 graduate students.
In 2012, UCSB was ranked 41st among `` neshnal vishvavidhyalayon '' or 10th among public vishvavidhyalayon by u.S. news & sansar rapat.
The university was also ranked 35th worldwide by the Times Higher shiksha sansar vishvavidhyalayon rankings or 34th vishwavyaapee ( 6th worldwide for engineering ) by the Academic Ranking of World Universities in 2012. < ref name= '' Shanghairanking.com/FieldENG2012 '' >
UC Santa Barbara is a `` very unchi kaaryaklap '' shodh vishvavidhyalayon or kharch $ 191.2 lakh on shodh expenditures in the 2007 fiscal year, 97th-largest in the United States.
UCSB houses baarah neshnal shodh centers, sahit the prasiddh kavli santhaan for Theoretical Physics.
UCSB faculty includes five Nobel Prize laureates, one Fields medalist, 29 sadasyon of the neshnal academy of sciences, 27 sadasyon of the neshnal academy of abhiyantriki, or 31 sadasyon of the amareeki Academy of Arts and Sciences.
UCSB was the No. 3 host on the arpanet or thi nirvaachit to the sangh of amareeki vishvavidhyalayon in 1995.

The Gauchos have won ncaa neshnal championships in main 's soker or main 's water polo.
sant joseph saath the shishu Jesus by Guido Reni
Saint Joseph 's Day, March 19, the Feast of St. Joseph is in Western christianity the principal feast din of sant joseph, jeevanasathi of the dhanya virgin Mary.
He is bhi the step-father of yishu of Nazareth /Jesus Christ.
It has the rank of a solemnity in the Roman catholic girijaghar ; catholics jo follow the missal of 1962 celebrate it as a pehla class feast.
Previous to 1962 it thi manaaye as a feast of the rank of double of the first class.
It is a feast or commemoration in the provinces of the Anglican niyaaz, or a feast or parv in the lutheran girijaghar.
Saint Joseph 's Day is the Patronal Feast day for Poland as well as for Canada, persons namit joseph, josephine, etc., liye dharmik santhaan, skulon or parishes bearing uske naam, or liye carpenters.
It is bhi pita 's din in kuch catholic deshon, mainly Spain, Portugal, and Italy.
March 19 thi samarpit to sant joseph in anek pashchimi panchang by the tenth century, and this custom was established in Rome by 1479.
Pope St. Pius V extended iske upyog to the sampurna roman reeti by uske apostolic samvidhan quo primum ( july 14, 1570 ).
Since 1969, Episcopal sammelnon may, if ve kaash, transafar it to a date outside Lent.
Between 1870 and 1955, a feast was celebrated in sammaan of st. joseph as jeevanasathi of the dhanya virgin mariyam or sangrakshak of the saarvbhaumik girijaghar, the latter sheershak having been given to him by Pope Pius IX.
Originally celebrated on the third Sunday after easter saath an ashtak, baad divino afflatu of st. paayas x ( dekhie sudhaar of the roman Breviary by Pope Pius X ), it was moved to the preceding Wednesday.
The feast thi bhi retitled the solemnity of Saint Joseph.
is jashn or iske accompanying ashtak thi abolished during the modernisation and simplification of rubrics under Pope Pius XII in 1955.
It is still maintained by catholics jo follow the missal of 1962 or pehle missals.
As the traditional holiday of the Apostles Ss. philip or james, may 1, tha dhundhlee isse the memory of sabase catholics by the mid-twentieth sadi, ki of joseph the kaaryakarta was created in order to coincide with the celebration of international Labour Day ( May Day ) in many countries.
The feast of ss. philip or james, jisase tha maharoom manaaye on ki tithi chunki the chathe sadi, was moved from its traditional place.
In the new calendar published in 1969, the feast, which at one time occupied the ucchtam sambhavit rank in the girijaghar panchang, thi ghataya to an vaikalpik memorial, the lowest rank for a saint 's day.
The Eastern paramparaagat girijaghar manaata sant joseph on the sande after Christmas.
Mariah Carey ( born March 27, 1970 ) is an American singer, songwriter, ricard nirmaataa, abhinetri, or philanthropist.
Under the guidance of colombia record karypalika tommy mottola, kairi released uske self-titled debyue studio album mariah kairi in 1990 ; it gai multi-platinum and spawned four consecutive number one singles on the U.S. Billboard Hot 100 chart.
Following her marriage to Mottola in 1993 or kamyaabi saath hit record bhav ( 1991 ), music baksaa ( 1993 ), or mairi christmas ( 1994 ), Carey was established as Columbia 's highest-selling act.
Daydream ( 1995 ) bana music itihaas jab iske duusari single `` ek mithi din ``, a duet saath boij ii main, kharch a ricard solah saptaah on sheersh of the billboard hot 100, and remains the longest-running number-one song in U.S. chart history.
During the recording of the album, Carey began to deviate isse uske r & b or pop beginnings or slowly traversed into hip hop.
This musical change became evident with the relies of titali ( 1997 ), at jisase samay kairi tha alag from Mottola.
kairi baayein colombia in 2000, or hastakshrit a record-breaking $ 100 million recording contract with Virgin Records.
pehle the relies of uske pehla visheshta filmi glitter ( 2001 ), wo suffered a physical and emotional breakdown and was hospitalized for severe exhaustion.
Following the film 's poor reception, she was bought out of her recording anubandh liye $ 50 lakh, jisase led to a manaahi in her career.
She signed a multi-million dollar contract saude saath dweep record in 2002, or baad an unsuccessful kaal, laute to the sheersh of music charts with The Emancipation of Mimi ( 2005 ).
Its second single `` we belong saath `` became uske sabase kaamyaab single of the 2000s, or thi baad namit `` song of the Decade '' by Billboard.
Carey once again ventured into film with a well-received abhinit bhoomika in ( 2009 ) ; wo thi awarded the `` bhedan pradarshan puraskaar '' at the tad sroton antarrashtriya Film Festival, and Black Reel and NAACP Image Award nominations.
In a career spanning over two decades, Carey rai bechi adhik than 200 lakh record vishwavyaapee, bananaa uske ek of the best-selling music artists of all time.
in 1998, wo thi sammanit as the sansar 's best-selling recording artist of the 1990s at the World Music Awards.
kairi thi bhi namit the best-selling maadaa kalakaar of the millennium in 2000.
According to the Recording Industry Association of America, wo is the teesraa best-selling maadaa kalakaar in the sanyukt rajya, saath 63.5 lakh certified albums.
With the release of `` tach my deh `` ( 2008 ), kairi gained uske eighteenth kramank ek single in the sanyukt rajya, more than any other solo artist.
In 2012, kairi thi kramit duusari on vh1 's suchi of the `` 100 Greatest Women in Music ''.
