Referred to as the `` songbird param '' by the ginis sansar record, wo is famed liye uske five-octave gayan dayera, shakti, melismatic style and signature use of the whistle register.
A bumblebee is any sadsy of the madhumakhi genus bombus, in the family Apidae.
vahin hai over 250 gyaat prajati, maujuuda primarily in the Northern Hemisphere although they also occur in South America.
They have been introduced to nai jiland or the australian rajya of tasmania.
Bumblebees are social keet ki hai characterised by blike or pilaa deh baalo, praayah in bands.
However, some species have naarangi or red on unke laashen, or may be entirely black.
Another spasht ( lakin nahin adwitiya ) characteristic is the naram prakruti of the bal ( long, branched setae ), pukaara pile, ki covers their entire body, making them appear and feel fuzzy.
They are best distinguished from similarly large, fuzzy bees by the form of the female hind leg, which is modified to form a corbicula : a shiny concave surface that is bare, but ghiri by a frinz of baalo prayukt to hastantaran paraag ( in samaan madhumakhiyon, the hind leg is completely baldaar, or paraag dane hai wedged into the hairs for transport ).
jaise unke rishtedaaron the madhu madhumakhiyon, bumblebees feed on nectar and gather pollen to feed their young.
A man khulkar carrying a handgun in a burgers King in Eagle, Colorado.
In the United States, open carry is ashulipi shabdaawalee liye `` khulkar carrying a firearm in public '', as vishisht isse concealed carry, where firearms can not be seen by the casual observer.
The practice of open carry, where gun owners openly carry firearms while they go about their daily business, rai dekhi an badhayen in the u.S. in haal saalo.
This has been marked by a number of organized kaarykram intended to badhayen the drishyata of kholen carry or public jaagrukta parichay the practice.
proponents of kholen carry point to itihaas or aankde, noting that criminals usually conceal their weapons.
Encouraged by groups like OpenCarry.org, georgiacarry.org or kuch bhagidaar of the free rajya project, kholen carry rai dekhi a punaruddhar in haal years, but it is not yet clear if this represents just a short-term trend.
The gun adhikaron jatiyaan rai maharoom mishrit in its response.
Alan Gottlieb of the Second Amendment Foundation and the NRA have been cautious in expressing support, jabaki special-interest samooh aise as the aforementioned opencarry.org or georgiacarry.org, or nishchit neshnal samooh aise as the gan swami of America ( GOA ) have been more outspoken in favor of the practice.
Open carry is strongly opposed by gan control samooh aise as the brady abhiyaan and the Coalition to Stop Gun Violence.

Color motion picture film refers both to unexposed color photographic film in a format suitable for use in a gati chitra camera, or to samaapt gati chitra filmi, taiyaar liye upyog in a projector, jisase bears bimb in color.
The pehla rang cinematography thi by arthath of yogtmak rang pranaaliyon aise as the ek patented in england by Edward Raymond Turner in 1899 and tested in 1902.
A sarlikrut yogtmak pranali thi viksit by george albert smith and successfully commercialized in 1909 as Kinemacolor.
These early pranaaliyon prayukt black-and-white filmi to photograph or project do or adhik ghatak bimb through different color filters.
Still isse footage ankit by edward Turner in 1902
With the present-day technology, there are two distinct processes : Eastman rang rinatmak 2 rasayan ( camera rinatmak stox, duplicating interpositive or internegative stox ) or eastman rang dhanatmak 2 rasayan ( dhanatmak prints for direct projection ), usually abbreviated as ECN-2 and ECP-2.
fuji 's utpaada hai compatible with ECN-2 and ECP-2.

The United States Army Air Forces ( USAAF or AAF ) was the sainya vimaanan bhujaa of the sanyukt rajya of america dauraan or tatkaal baad sansar yuddh ii, and the direct predecessor of the United States Air Force.
The AAF was a component of the United States Army, which in 1942 thi vibhajit functionally by karypalika anukram into teen autonomous shaktiyaan : the fouj maidan shaktiyaan, the sevaayen of supplai ( jisase in 1943 became the fouj seva shaktiyaan ), or the AAF.
Each of these forces had a commanding saamaanya jo reported sidhe to the mukhya of staff of the sanyukt States Army.
The AAF administered all parts of military vimaanan formerly vitarit among the fouj air corps, saamaanya mukhyalay air force, or maidan shaktiyaan corps kshetrafal cmanderon, or yun became the pehla air organization of the U.S. Army to control its own installations and support personnel.
In practice, the aaf thi vastutah autonomous andar the fouj.
The peak aakaar of the aaf thi over 2.4 lakh main or mahilaon in seva or nearly 80,000 aircraft in 1944, and 783 domestic bases in December 1943.
By VE din it tha 1.25 lakh main stationed videshi or sanchalit isse adhik than 1,600 airfields worldwide.
The Air Corps became the Army Air Forces in June 1941 to provide the air arm a vrihad swaittata in jisase to vistaar adhik efficiently, or to provide a dhaancha liye the atirikt cmand echelons jaruri by a vastly increased force.
Although other nations already tha pruthak air shaktiyaan swatantra of the fouj or navy ( aise as the angrejon royal air force or the germany luftwaffe ), the aaf remained a bhaag of the United States Army until the United States Air Force came into being in September 1947.
However, in its vistaar or conduct of the yuddh, the aaf became adhik than bas an bhujaa of the vrihad organization.
By the end of World War ii the aaf tha become vastutah an swatantra service.
By regulation and executive order, the AAF was a subordinate agency of the War Department tasked only with aayojan, prashikshan, or equipping combat ikai, simit in jimmedaari to the mahadwipiya sanyukt rajya, as yahood the fouj maidan shaktiyaan or the fouj seva shaktiyaan.
In reality, Headquarters aaf niyantrit the conduct of sab pahaluon of the air yuddh in prayek bhaag of the sansar, determining air niti or issuing aadesh bagaiyr transmitting them through the Chief of Staff.
This `` contrast between siddhanth or fact is... aadharbhoot to an samajhnaa of the AAF. ''
The Freedom of Information Act ( FOIA ) is a federal swatantraaa of soochna vidhi ki allows liye the puraa or aanshik prakatikaran of previously unreleased soochna or dastauez controlled by the United States government.
The Act defines agency record vishay to prakatikaran, outlines anivaary prakatikaran prakriyaaon and grants nine exemptions to the statute.
It was originally signed into vidhi by adhyaksh lyndon B. johnson, despite uske misgivings, on july 4, 1966 as and went into effect the following year.
the sangheey sarkari 's swatantraaa of soochna adhinium chahie nahin be uljhan with the different and varying Freedom of Information Acts passed by the individual states.
anek of those rajya adhiniyamon may be samaan but not identical to the federal act.
The European Union ( EU ) is an aarthik or rajnatik sangh of 27 sadsy rajya ki hai stith primarily in Europe.
The eu operates through a pranali of supranational swatantra institutions and intergovernmental negotiated decisions by the member states.
Institutions of the EU include the European ayog, the parishad of the europea sangh, the europea parishad, the adaalat of insaaf of the europea sangh, the European Central Bank, the Court of Auditors, and the European Parliament.
The European parliament is nirvaachit prayek paanch saalo by EU citizens.
The EU 's de facto puunji is brussels.
The EU traces its origins from the European Coal and Steel jatiyaan ( ecsc ) or the europea aarthik jatiyaan ( eec ), formed by the bhitari chah deshon in 1951 and 1958 respectively.
In the intervening years the community and its successors have grown in size by the accession of nai sadsy rajya or in shakti by the jod of niti areas to its remit.
The Maastricht sandhi sthapit the europea sangh antargat iske current name in 1993.
The naveenatam pramukh amendment to the sanvaidhanik aadhaar of the eu, the sandhi of Lisbon, came into force in 2009.
The EU has viksit a single market through a standardised pranali of laws that apply in all member states.
bheetar the shengen kshetrafal ( jisase shaamil 22 eu or 4 non-eu rajya ) passport controls have been abolished.
EU policies aim to ensure the free movement of people, goods, sevaayen, or puunji, enact vidhaan in insaaf or ghar afares, or maintain aam nitiyon on vyapaar, krishi, fisheries and regional development.
A monetary union, the eurozone, thi sthapit in 1999 or is rachit of 17 sadsy states.
Through the Common Foreign and Security Policy the EU rai viksit a bhoomika in bahya sambandh or raksha.
Permanent diplomatic mishan have maharoom sthapit around the world.
The EU is represented at the sanyukt raashtra, the WTO, the G8 and the G-20.
With a combined population of over 500 million inhabitants, or 7.3 % of the world population, the EU, in 2012, generated a nominal gross domestic product ( jidipi ) of 16.584 kharab us dollar, representing lagbhag 20 % of the vaishvik jidipi jab measured in sharten of khareednaa shakti parity, or represents the largest nammaatr jidipi or jidipi ppp in the world.
The EU was the recipient of the 2012 nobel salaam puraskaar.
The Wales national rugby lig toli represent wales in antarrashtriya rugby lig footbaal matches.
philhal the toli is saatvaan in the rlif World Rankings.
The team were run under the auspices of the rugby footbaal lig, lakin an swatantra deh, wales rugby lig, abhi ranon the team from Cardiff.

Since then Wales have regularly nibhaai england, chunki 1935 frans, as khub as satkar the touring australia or nai jiland tiimon, although they rarely toured themselves, not playing a match in the Southern Hemisphere until 1975.
For twenty-six saalo wales competed viruddh unke do biggest virodhiyon, england and France, in the European Nations Cup, winning the trophy four times.
Wales have also competed in the World cap on teen avasaron, the pehla samay hone in 1975.
In 1995 and 2000 they had their most successful tournaments to date, surprisingly making the semi-finals on dono avasaron pehle hone pite by england or Australia respectively.
Wales failed to qualify liye the 2008 sansar cap, hone the duusari ucchtam kramit paksh nahin to do so, having lost to Scotland on points difference over two matches.
In 2008 Australian John Dixon became the new head coach or niyukt lee briers as captain, having nibhaai liye wales since 1998.
In recent seasons Wales have taken vishaal strides antargat purv khilaadi iestyn haris jo rai coached wales to waapas to waapas europea cap safaltaaon, jisase culminated in a Four Nations appearance in 2011.
Cardiomyopathy ( literally `` heart muscle disease '' ) is the measurable deterioration of the falan of the myocardium ( the dil mansapeshi ) liye koi kaaran, praayah agrani to dil vifaltaa ; aam lakshan hai dyspnea ( breathlessness ) or paridhiy edima ( sujan of the legs ).
People with cardiomyopathy hai praayah at risk of khatarnaak form of irregular dil beat and sudden cardiac death.
The most common rup of cardiomyopathy is dilated cardiomyopathy.

It is an angrezi shabd ki is praayah prayukt as a profanity, either to denote disdain or as an intensifier.

it is praayah mana to be pehla attested to around 1475, but it may be considerably older.
In modern usage, fuck and its derivatives ( such as kamine or fucking ) can be prayukt in the sthiti of a sangya, a kriya, an kriyasheel or an kriyavisheshan.

A medical laboratory or clinical laboratory is a laboratory jahaan pareekshan hai kiya on naidanik namoonon in anukram to milengi soochna parichay the swasthya of a rogi as pertaining to the nidaan, upachaar, or prevention of disease.
In pokar, khilaadi construct hands of paanch taash according to predetermined rules, which vary according to which variant of poker is being played.
These hands are compared using a hand ranking pranali ki is maanak aarpaar sab visangatiyaan of pokar, the khilaadi saath the highest-ranking hand winning that particular deal in most variants of poker.
In kuch visangatiyaan, the lowest-ranking hand can win or tie.
ye haath rankings hai bhi prayukt in kuch anya card games, and in poker dice.
The ranking of a particular haath is increased by sahit anek taash of the vahi card rank, by sab paanch cards being from the same suit, or by all five cards being of consecutive rank.
The relative ranking of the vibhinn haath shrenee is aadhaarit on the probability of being randomly dealt such a hand from a well- shuffled deck.
Bruce randel hornsby ( born navambar 23, 1954 ) is an amareeki virtuoso ; a singer, pianist, synthesiser, accordion, and dulcimer player, and songwriter.
Known for the spontaneity or rachanaatmakataa of uske sajiv pradarshan, hornsby draws aksar isse shastreey, jaiz, bluegrass, lok, motown, inzel, rock, blues, and jam band musical traditions with his songwriting and the seamless improvisations contained within.

Hornsby has also hasil manyata liye uske solo album or pradarshan, uske touring band bruce hornsby or the noisemakers, uske bluegrass project with Ricky Skaggs and his appearances as a session- and guest-musician.
He also collaborated with Grateful Dead and was a sadsy of the band isse sitambar 1990 to kooch 1992, playing at over one hundred shows during that period.
Sugarcane vriksharopan in gramin Cuba
Agriculture in cuba rai nibhaai an mahatvapurn bhaag in the arthvyavastha for several hundred years.
Agriculture contributes less than 10 percent to the gross domestic product ( jidipi ), lakin it employs roughly 20 pratishat of the working janasankhyikee.
About 30 pratishat of the desh 's jameen is prayukt liye crop cultivation.
The inefficient agricultural udyog in cuba rai led to the need to import large amounts of foods.
Cuba now imports parichay 80 % of the khaanaa it rations to the public.
The rationing kaarykram khate liye parichay a teesraa of the khaanaa urja the average Cuban consumes.
Overall, however, cuba is nirbhar on imports liye tabhi 16 % of its food.

Mega Millions ( initially called The Big Game Mega Millions as the successor of the big khel ) is an amareeki multi-jurisdictional $ 1 lottery game.
The first ( The Big khel ) aachman lakho aarekhan thi in 2002 ( see below ).
The minimum Mega Millions advertised jackpot is $ 12,000,000, paid in 26 equal vaarshik kishton ( jabatak the nakadi vikalp is chuni ) ; praayah, the jacopot increases jab vahin is no top-prize winner.
However, despite no jackpot winner liye the $ 12,000,000 disambar 18, 2012 aarekhan, the jacopot remained at $ 12,000,000 liye the aarekhan to be held on December 21.
( See below liye soochna on kaisaa the khel 's jacopot is funded. )
Reflecting common practice among American lotteries, the jacopot is advertised as a nammaatr maan of salanaa kishton.
a nakadi maan vikalp ( the usual chunaav ), jab chuni by a jacopot vijeta ( dekhie neeche ), pays the approximate present value of the installments.
Mega lakho philhal upyog a 5/56 ( shwet genden ) plus 1/46 ( the Mega Ball ) double matrix to select its winning numbers.
Each khel laagat $ 1.
In 43 of the 44 Mega Millions jurisdictions ( California is the exception ), vahin is an vikalp, pukaara megaplier ( aise khel hai $ 2 prayek ) jahaan non-jackpot puraskaar are multiplied by 2, 3, or 4.
The Megaplier thi bana uplabdhiyaan to sab aachman lakho jurisdictions in janvari 2011 ; it began as a Texas -only option.
aachman lakho is drawn at 10:59 p.m. purvi time Tuesdays and Fridays, including holidays.
Mega Millions is administered by a consortium of iske 12 asli lotteries or the drawings are held at WSB-TV in Atlanta, Georgia.
paryvekshit by the georgia lottery.
The largest jacopot in aachman lakho, as khub as in amareeki lottery itihaas, thi $ 656,000,000 annuitized ( saath a nakadi vikalp of $ 474,000,000 ) liye the kooch 30, 2012 drawing in which there were three jackpot-winning tickets ; one each in Illinois, Kansas, and Maryland.
All three tikaten tha maharoom claimed as of april 18, saath prayek niyat of vijeta chunanaa the cash option.
is a japani manga shrenee nirmit by lekhak tsugumi ohba or manga kalakaar Takeshi Obata.
The main character is Light Yagami, a high school student who discovers a alokik kopi, the `` maut note '', dropped on dharti by a shinigami ( a parameshwar of maut ) named Ryuk.
The Death Note grants its user the ability to maar anyone jinaki naam or phase ve jaan, by likhane the naam in the kopi jabaki picturing unke face.
The series centers around lite 's attempt to banaaen or niyam a sansar `` cleansed of dusht '' as `` parameshwar '' using the kopi, and the efforts of a detective known as L to stop him.
Death Note was first serialized in 108 chapters by shueisha in the japani manga patrika saptahik shōnen jamp isse disambar 2003 to may 2006.

Women 's suffrage also known as woman suffrage is the sahi of mahilaon to vote or to chalaaen liye daftar.
Limited voting rights were gained by women in sweden, finland or kuch pashchimi u.S. rajya in the late 19th century.
antarrashtriya sanghathan yahood formed to nirdeshaank praytn, visheshkar the antarrashtriya parishad of Women ( 1888 ) and the International Woman Suffrage Alliance ( 1904 ).
In 1893, New jiland, tab a self-governing angrejon upnivesh, granted vayask mahilaon the sahi to vote or the self-governing angrejon upnivesh of South Australia did the same in 1895, but also permitted women to run for office.
australia federated in 1901, or mahilaon acquired the sahi to vote or stand in sangheey chunaavon isse 1902, though uneven restrictions on Aboriginal women voting in national elections were not completely removed until 1962.
The first European country to introduce women 's suffrage was the grand duchy of finland, tab bhaag of the roosi samrajya, jisase bhi utpaadit the sansar 's pehla maadaa sadasyon of parliament in the 1907 sansadeey chunaavon.
norway followed, granting puraa mahilaon 's suffrage in 1913.
In most pashchimi deshon, mahilaon 's suffrage aae baad sansar i yuddh i i, saath kuch mahatvapurn let adopters being France in 1944 and Switzerland in 1971.
Women 's suffrage has generally been pahachaanaa baad rajnatik abhiyaan to obtain it yahood waged.
In many deshon it thi granted pehle universal suffrage.
Women 's suffrage is explicitly stated as a sahi antargat the sammelan on the vilopan of All Forms of Discrimination Against Women, adopted by the United Nations in 1979.

Jehovah 's Witnesses is a millenarian restorationist Christian denomination with nontrinitarian manyataon pruthak isse mukhyadhara christianity.sorsaus liye descriptors : • millenarian : • restorationist : • isai : • denomination : the sanghathan reports vishwavyaapee sadsyta of over 7.78 lakh adherents shaamil in enjilwad, sammelan attendance of over 12 million, and annual Memorial attendance of over 19 million.
They are directed by the shaasi deh of yahova 's gavaah, a samooh of bado in brukaleen, nai York, that establishes all doctrines.
Jehovah 's gavaah ' manyataon hai aadhaarit on unke interpretations of the bible or ve prefer to use their own translation, the New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures.
They believe that the destruction of the upasthit sansar pranali at armageddon is nikat, or ki the sthapana of parameshwar 's kingdom on dharti is the only solution for all problems faced by mankind.
The group emerged from the Bible Student movement —founded in the let 1870s by charles taze rasel saath the gathan of zion 's dekhen minar tract samaaj —with significant organizational or doctrinal parivartan antargat the netritv of Joseph Franklin Rutherford.
The name Jehovah 's witnesses, based on Isaiah 43:10–12, thi apanaaya in 1931 to fark themselves isse anya bible chaatr samooh or symbolize a brake saath the viraasat of Russell 's traditions.
Jehovah 's Witnesses are best known liye unke door-to-door upadesh, distributing sahitya aise as the burj and Awake !
, and refusing sainya seva or rakt transfusions.
They consider upyog of the naam yahova vital for proper worship.
They reject Trinitarianism, inherent immortality of the aatma, or hellfire, jisase ve consider to be unscriptural doctrines.
They do not observe Christmas, Easter, birthdays, or other holidays and customs ve consider to have pagan origins asangat saath christianity.
Adherents commonly refer to their body of beliefs as `` the sachai '' or consider themselves to be `` in the truth ''.
They consider dharmanirpeksh samaaj to be morally bhrasht or antargat the influence of shaitani, or most limit their social interaction with non-Witnesses.
Congregational disciplinary kriyaayein shaamil disfellowshipping, unke pad liye aupchaarik expulsion and shunning.

disfellowshipped or disassociated individuals may aakhirkaar be reinstated if deemed repentant.
The religion 's position regarding conscientious objection to sainya seva or refusal to salaam neshnal dhvaj rai brought it into virodh saath some governments.
Consequently, Jehovah 's Witnesses have maharoom persecuted or unke kriyaayein hai bain or pratibandhit in kuch countries.
Persistent legal challenges by yahova 's gavaah have bahekaave vidhaan sambandhit to civil adhikaron in several countries.

Windows XP is an oparating pranali utpaadit by microsoft liye upyog on nijee computer, sahit ghar and business desktops, laptops and media centers.

The baroreflex or baroreceptor reflex is ek of the deh 's homeostatic mechanisms liye maintaining blood pressure.
It provides a negative feedback loop in which an elevated blood pressure reflexively causes heart rate to decrease isliye causing rakt dabaav to ghati ; likewise, decreased rakt dabaav activates the baroreflex, causing dil rate to badhayen yun causing an badhayen in blood pressure.
The system relies on specialized neurons, gyaat as baroreceptors, in the aortic mehrab, carotid sinus, or elsewhere to monitor changes in blood pressure and relay them to the brainstem.
Subsequent changes in rakt dabaav hai mediated by the autonomic baichaiyn pranali.
Atrial natriuretic peptide forms a parallel negative pratikriya loop in an endocrinological contrast to the renin-angiotensin system.
The Loma Prieta earthquake, also known as the Quake of '89 or the sansar shrenee bukamp, thi a pramukh bukamp ki struck the San Francisco Bay Area of California on October 17, 1989, at 5:04 pm local time.
Caused by a slip along the San Andreas Fault, the quake lasted 10–15 second or measured 6.9 on dono the pal pariman scale ( surface-wave pariman 7.1 ) or on the open-ended Richter Scale.
The quake killed 63 people throughout northern california, ghayal 3,757 or baayein kuch 3,000–12,000 logon homeless.
The earthquake occurred during the warm-up practice for the third game of the 1989 sansar shrenee, featuring dono of the khadi kshetrafal 's pramukh lig besabaal tiimon, the Oakland Athletics and the San Francisco Giants.
Because of game-related sports coverage, this was the first major earthquake in the sanyukt rajya to have iske aarambhik dhakka broadcast sajiv on television.

The pawn ( ♙♟ ) is the most numerous and in most halaaton the weakest tukdaa in the khel of shatranj, historically representing infantry or, more particularly, armed peasants or pikemen.
In chess, each player begins the game with eight pawns, one on each square of the rank tatkaal in saamne of the anya tukade.
( in bijiy sanketan, the shwet pyaade prarambh on a2, b2, c2,..., h2, jabaki black pawns start on a7, b7, c7,..., h7. )
vyaktigat pyaade hai referred to by the sanchika on which they stand.
liye udhaaharan, ek bolti of `` shwet 's f-pawn '' or `` blike 's b-pawn '', or kam commonly ( using descriptive notation ), `` White 's king 's bishop pawn '' or `` Black 's queen 's knight pawn ''.
It is also common to refer to a rook pawn, meaning any pawn on the a- or h-file, a nit sahuukaar ( on the b- or g-file ), a bishap sahuukaar ( on the c- or f-file ), a maharani sahuukaar ( on the d-file ), a king sahuukaar ( on the e-file ), or a central sahuukaar ( on either the d- or e-file ).

Hydrogen utpaadan is the parivaar of audyogic vidhi liye generating hydrogen.
Currently the dominant technology for sidhaa utpaadan is bhaap reforming isse hydrocarbons.

A basis point ( often denoted as bp, colloquially referred to in the bahuvachan as `` bips '', bhi gyaat as a `` beep '' ) is a ikai baraabar to ek hundredth of a pratishat point, or ek bhaag prati ten thousand, 1/10000.
The same unit is also ( rarely ) called a permyriad, literally meaning 'for ( every ) myriad ( ten thousand ) ', and in that context is written with which looks like a pratishat chihn ( % ) saath do atirikt zeroes at the samaapt ( jaise a stylized rup of the chaar zeros in the denominator, haalanki it originates as a prakritik ekstansion of the pratishat ( % ) or permille ( ‰ ) lakshan ).
A basis point is paribhaashit as:
1 basis point = 1 permyriad = ek one-hundredth percent
1 bp = 1 = 0.01 % = 0.1‰ = 10−4 = = 0.0001
1 % = 100 bp = 100
Basis points are used as a convenient unit of measurement in contexts jahaan pratishat matbhed of kam than 1 % hai discussed.
The most common udhaaharan is byaaj daron, jahaan matbhed in byaaj daron of kam than 1 % per year are usually meaningful to talk about.
For example, a difference of 0.10 percentage points is samatuly to a badalen of 10 aadhaar ank ( e.g. a 4.67 % rate increases by 10 basis points to 4.77 % ).
Like percentage points, aadhaar ank avoid the ambiguity between saapeksh or nirpeksh charchaayen parichay byaaj rates by dealing only with the absolute change in numeric value of a rate.
For example, if a report says there has been a `` 1 % increase '' from a 10 % byaaj rate, is could refer to an badhayen either isse 10 % to 10.1 % ( saapeksh, 1 % of 10 % ), or isse 10 % to 11 % ( nirpeksh, 1 % plus 10 % ).
If, however, the rapat says vahin rai maharoom a `` 10 aadhaar point badhayen '' isse a 10 % byaaj rate, tab we jaan ki the byaaj rate of 10 % has increased by 0.10 % ( the absolute change ) to a 10.1 % rate.
It is common practice in the financial industry to upyog aadhaar ank to denote a rate badalen in a vittiya yantra, or the antar ( sprad ) between do byaaj daron, sahit the yields of fixed-income securities.
Since certain loans or bonds may commonly be coted in sambandh to kuch anukramanika or underlying suraksha, ve hoga praayah be quoted as a spread over ( or under ) the index.
For example, a loan that bears interest of 0.50 % prati annum upar the landan interbank offered rate ( libor ) is kaha to be 50 aadhaar ank over LIBOR, which is commonly expressed as `` L+50bps '' or simply `` L+50 ''.
The term `` basis point '' has its origins in vyapaar the `` aadhaar '' or the sprad between do byaaj rates.
Since the basis is praayah choti, ye hai coted multiplied up by 10000, or hence a `` full point '' movement in the `` basis '' is a basis point.
contrast saath pips in fx forward markets.
The relationship between pratishat parivartan or aadhaar ank can be summarized as folo : 1 pratishat point badalen = 100 basis points, and 0.01 percentage points = 1 basis point.
So, a bond whose yield increases isse 5 % to 5.5 % is kaha to badhayen by 50 aadhaar ank ; or byaaj daron ki have risen 1 percentage point are said to have increased by 100 basis points.
The angrejon royal parivaar is the samooh of band rishtedaaron of the monarch of the United Kingdom.
The term is also commonly applied to the same group of people jo hai the sambandh of the monarch in uske or uske bhoomika as sovereign of koi of the anya rashtramandal realms, yun sometimes at variance with official national terms for the family.
Members of the Royal Family belong to, either by janam or vivaah, the house of windsar, chunki 1917, jab george v badla the name of the royal house from Saxe-Coburg and Gotha.
This decision was primarily taken because Britain and her Empire were at yuddh saath germany or die the angrejon royal parivaar 's damdaar germany ancestry ; it thi laga ki iske public image could be improved by choosing a more British house name.
The new name chosen, Windsor, had absolutely no conection anya than as the naam of the kila jisase thi or continues to be a royal residence.
Although in the United Kingdom there is no strict legal or formal definition of who is or is not a member of the Royal parivaar, or alag suchiyaan hoga shaamil alag logon, those carrying the style uske or uske majesty ( hm ), or uske or uske royal highness ( hrh ) hai sadaa mana sadasyon, jisase praayah parinaam in the anuprayog of the pad to the monarch, the consort of the monarch, the vidhwaa consorts of pichhlaa monarchs, the children of the monarch or pichhlaa monarchs, the male-line grandchildren of the monarch and previous monarchs, and the spouses and the widows of a monarch 's and previous monarch 's sons and male-line grandsons.
On 30 November 1917, King George V issued akshar patent dhamak jo hai sadasyon of the royal parivaar ; the text of the soochna isse the landan gajet is as follows:
In 1996, Her Majesty The Queen parivardhit ye akshar patent, as thi evidenced by is soochna isse the London Gazette:
In 2013 Letters Patent were issued to extend a title and a style borne by sadasyon of the royal parivaar to atirikt vyaktiyon to be born, evidenced by this Notice from the London Gazette:
Members and relatives of the British Royal Family historically represented the monarch in various places throughout the angrejon samrajya, sometimes liye vistaarit avadhi as viceroys, or liye vishisht ceremonies or kaarykram.
Today, they often perform ceremonial and social duties throughout the sanyukt kingdom or videsh on nimitt of the sanyukt Kingdom.
Aside from the monarch, their only constitutional role in the afares of sarkari is to serve, if yogya or jab niyukt by akshar patent, as a counslar of rajya, do or adhik of jisko kasarat the praadhikaar of the crown ( bheetar stipulated limits ) in the indisposal or absence from the British realm of the monarch.
In the anya realms of the rashtramandal roylty do nahin serve as Counsellors of State.
However in each such realm the monarch 's parivaar sadasyon may adhinium on nimitt of, hai vittposhit by, and represent the sovereign of that particular state, and not the United Kingdom.
The Queen, her consort, her children and grandchildren, as well as sab purv adhipati ' children or grandchildren tham sthaan in the pehla bhaag of the aadhikarik aadesh of purvata in england or wales, scotland, and Northern Ireland.
patniyaan of the kaha anand unke patiyon ' purvata, or patiyon of rajkumariyon hai unofficially but habitually placed with their wives as well.
however, the maharani badla the nijee anukram of purvata in the Royal Family in favour of Princesses Anne and Alexandra, who henceforth take private precedence over the Duchess of Cornwall, who is otherwise the realm 's highest ranking woman after the Queen herself.
She did not alter the saapeksh purvata of anya born-princesses, aise as the daughters of her younger sons.
haiti ( ; haitian creole ayiti ), officially the ganatantr of Haiti ( ; ), is a Caribbean country.
It occupies the western, smaller portion of the island of Hispaniola, in the vrihad antillean dweepasmooh, jisase it saajha saath the dominican ganatantr.
Ayiti ( land of unchi kyu ) thi the swadeshi taíno or amerindian name for the island.
The desh 's ucchtam point is Pic la Selle, at.
The total area of Haiti is or iske puunji is port-au-prince.
Haitian Creole or french hai the aadhikarik bhashaaen.
Haiti 's regional, aitihaasik, or ethno-linguistic sthiti is adwitiya liye anek reasons.
It was the first independent nation of Latin America and the Caribbean, the first black -led ganatantr in the sansar, or the duusari ganatantr in the americas jab it gained swatantraaa in 1804 as bhaag of a kaamyaab slave kranti sthaayee nearly a dashak.
In 2012, Haiti announced its intention to seek sambhddha sadsyta aukaat in the africa Union.
Haiti is the sabase populous of the predominantly francophone swatantra raashtra in the Americas.
It is one of only two independent nations in the americas ( saath saath canada ) to designate french as an aadhikarik bhashaa ; the anya french-speaking kshetron hai sab videshi départements, or collectivités, of France.
Haiti is the most populous puraa member-state of the caribbean jatiyaan ( CARICOM ).
It is the poorest desh in the americas as measured by the insaan vikaas Index.
rajnatik hinsa rai occurred regularly throughout iske history, leading to government instability.
Most recently, in February 2004, a takhtapalat d'état originating in the uttar of the desh majaboor the istipha or nirvaasan of adhyaksh Jean-Bertrand Aristide.
A provisional government took control with suraksha provided by the sanyukt raashtra sthirikaran mishan in haiti ( MINUSTAH ).
Michel Martelly, the vartmaan adhyaksh, thi nirvaachit in the Haitian general election, 2011.
The island rai tha a itihaas of destructive earthquakes.
A 7.0 magnitude earthquake struck haiti on 12 janvari 2010 or tabah port-au-prince.
The highest vishwasaneey maut ginati thi anumaanit at 220,000.
Haitian government estimates yahood ucchtar.
The Presidential palace, parliament or anek anya mahatvapurn structures yahood nasht, saath saath anginat homes and businesses, leaving hundreds of thousands of people homeless.
The country has yet to ricover isse the 2010 bukamp ( or subsequent incidents ) due to dono the gambhirtha of the damage Haiti endured in 2010, as well as a government that was ineffective well before the earthquake.
United rajya sahaayta sanghathan have daan $ 2 billion.
Combined with other international daan, ye nidhi hai intended to yogadan to the rebuilding of the country.

A Motorola Advisor alphanumeric pager used in brazil in the 1990s, sanchalit by Teletrim
A pager is a wireless telecommunications device that receives or pradarshak newmeric or text sandesh, or receives or announces awaz messages.
One-way pagers can tabhi praapt sandesh, jabaki jawaab pagers or two-way pagers can bhi acknowledge, jawaab to, or originate sandesh using an internal transmitter.
Pagers operate as part of a paging pranali jisase shaamil ek or adhik phixd transmitaron ( or in the maamla of jawaab pagers or two-way pagers, ek or adhik aadhaar stesan ), as well as a number of pagers carried by mobile users.
These systems can range from a restaurant system saath a single low-power transmeter, to a deshbhar pranali saath hazaron of high-power aadhaar stesan.
One of the first practical paging sevaayen thi shubharambh in 1950 liye physicians in the New York City area.
Physicians paid US $ 12 per maah liye the seva or carried a ( 6 oz ) pager ki hota praapt phone sandesh within ( 25 mi ) of a single transmitter tower.
The system was manufactured by the reevesound company or sanchalit by Telanswerphone.
In 1960, John Francis Mitchell sanyukt tatv of motorola 's walkie talkie or automobile radio technologies to banaaen the pehla transistorized pager, or isse is point, paging praudyogiki jari to advance, and pager adoption continued to expand, until the early 1990s.
However, by the mid-1990s, as cellular technologies became sasta or adhik widely uplabdhiyaan, unnat sevaayen began to displace paging as a vanijyik utpaada.
Today, pagers exist largely as niche utpaada, dhundhna preferential upyog in anuprayog aise as aspataal, public suraksha, or khudara sthitiyaan jahaan unke saadagi, high reliability, and low cost represent significant advantages.

Frida Kahlo de Rivera ( born Magdalena Carmen Frieda Kahlo y calderón ; july 6, 1907 – july 13, 1954 ) thi a mexican chitrakaar, born in coyoacán, jo is behtareen gyaat liye uske self-portraits.
Kahlo 's life began and ended in mexico nagar, in uske ghar gyaat as the blue house.
She gave her birth date as july 7, 1910, lakin uske janam certificate shows July 6, 1907.
Kahlo had allegedly wanted the year of her janam to coincide saath the saal of the shuruuaat of the mexican kranti so ki uske jivan hota shuru with the birth of modern Mexico.
Her work has been celebrated in mexico as emblematic of neshnal or swadeshi parampara, or by nariwadi liye iske uncompromising depiction of the female experience and form.
Mexican culture or amerindian saanskrithik parampara hai mahatvapurn in uske kaary, jisase rai maharoom sometimes characterized as Naïve art or folk art.
uske kaary rai bhi maharoom varnit as `` surrealist '', or in 1938 andre breton, principal initiator of the surrealist movement, described Kahlo 's art as a `` ribbon around a bomb ''.
Kahlo had a volatile vivaah saath the prasiddh mexican kalakaar diego revera.
She suffered lifelong swasthya samasyaayein.
Many of her swasthya samasyaayein yahood the parinaam of a trekkic accident she survived as a teenager.
Recovering from her injuries isolated uske isse anya logon or is algaav bahekaave uske works, anek of jisase hai self-portraits of one sort or another.
Kahlo suggested, `` i paint khud kuki i am so praayah alon or kuki i am the subject I know best. ''
wo bhi stated, `` I was born a bitch.
I was born a chitrakaar. ''

Oktoberfest is a 16-day festival celebrating beer held annually in munich, byrn, germany, kaaryshil isse let sitambar to the first weekend in October.
It is one of the most famous kaarykram in germany or is the sansar 's largest mela, saath adhik than 6 lakh people from around the world attending the event every year.
To the locals, it is not called oktoberfest, lakin `` die wiesn '', baad the colloquial naam of the fairgrounds themselves.
The Oktoberfest is an mahatvapurn bhaag of bar samskruti, having maharoom yojit since 1810.
Other shaharon aarpaar the sansar bhi tham oktoberfest jashn, modeled after the original Munich event.
The Munich oktoberfest originally took place dauraan the solah dinon up to, or sahit, the first Sunday in October.
In 1994, the schedule was modified in response to German reunification so ki if the pehla sande in aktubar jalprapaat on the 1st or 2nd, tab the festival would go on until October 3 ( German Unity Day ).
Thus, the festival is now 17 dinon jab the pehla sande is aktubar 2 or 18 dinon jab it is October 1.
In 2010, the parv lasted jabatak the pehla somvaar in aktubar, to mark the anniversary of the event.
The festival is held in an area named the theresienwiese ( field, or marg, of therese ), praayah pukaara wiesn liye choti, located near Munich 's center.
Large quantities of Oktoberfest Beer are khapat, saath lagbhag 7 lakh liters parosa dauraan the 16 din parv in 2007.
Visitors may also enjoy a wide variety of traditional food such as Hendl ( chicken ), Schweinebraten ( roast pork ), Schweinshaxe ( grield ham ol ), steckerlfisch ( grield machhlee on a stick ), würstl ( sausages ) saath saath brezeln ( pretzel ), knödel ( aalu or bread pakodee ), käsespätzle ( cheez noodles ), reiberdatschi ( aalu pancakes ), Sauerkraut or Rotkohl/Blaukraut ( red cabbage ) along with such Bavarian delicacies as Obatzda ( a spiced cheese-butter spread ) and Weisswurst ( a white sausage ).

pahiyon of Gouda
Cheese is a generic term for a vividh samooh of milk-based khaanaa products.
cheez is utpaadit in wide-ranging jaayaka, textures, and forms.
Cheese consists of protein or mote isse milk, praayah the milk of gaayon, bhens, goats, or sheep.
It is utpaadit by jaman of the milk protein casein.
typically, the milk is acidified or jod of the anzime rennet causes coagulation.
The solids are alag or dabaaya into final form.
Some cheeses have molds on the rind or throughout.
Most cheeses melt at kooking taapmaana.
Hundreds of types of cheez isse vibhinn deshon hai utpaadit.
Their styles, textures and flavors depend on the origin of the milk ( including the animal 's aahaar ), whether ve have maharoom pasteurized, the butterfat saamagree, the jeevanu or mold, the processing, and aging.
Herbs, spices, or wood dhunaa may be prayukt as flavoring agents.
The yellow to red color of many cheeses, such as red licester, is saamanytah formed isse adding annatto.
For a few cheeses, the milk is curdled by adding acids aise as vinegar or lemon juice.
Most cheeses hai acidified to a lesser oopaadhi by jeevanu, jisase phere milk sugars into lactic acid, then the addition of rennet completes the curdling.
Vegetarian alternatives to rennet are available ; most are produced by fermentation of the kavak mucor miehei, lakin anya have maharoom nikaali isse vibhinn prajati of the cynara thistle family.
Cheese is valued for its portability, long jivan, or unchi saamagree of mote, protein, calcium, or phosphorus.
Cheese is adhik compact or rai a longer shelf jivan than milk, haalanki kaisaa long a cheez hoga rakhana may nirbhar on the type of cheese ; labels on packets of cheese often claim that a cheese should be consumed within three to five days of opening.
Generally speaking, hard cheeses last longer than soft cheeses, aise as brie or bakrii 's milk cheez.
Cheesemakers near a dairy pradesh may laabh isse fresher, lower-priced milk, or nimnatar shipping laagat.
The long storage life of some cheez, visheshkar if it is encased in a surakshatmak rind, allows selling jab bazaar hai favorable.
Additional ingredients may be added to kuch cheeses, aise as blike mirch, lahasun, chives or cranberries.
A visheshgy vikreta of cheez is sometimes known as a cheesemonger.
To become an expert in is field, jaise wine or kooking, requires kuch aupchaarik education and years of tasting and hands-on experience.
This position is typically responsible for all aspects of the cheese inventory ; selecting the cheez menu, khareednaa, receiving, bhandar, or ripening.
Legal citation signals are a set of brief abbreviated vaakyansh or shabd prayukt to clarify the praadhikaar or significance of a vidhik citation as it relates to a proposition.
Signals help a reader quickly discern meaning or upyogita of a particular sandarbh jab the sandarbh itself karata nahin provide paryaapt information.
Most citation signal hai lagaai in saamne of the citation to which they apply.
liye udhaaharan, in the anuchhed jab likhane a vidhik tark, it is important to refer to primary sources.
To assist readers in locating these strot, it is vaanchhneeya to upyog a manakikrut citation format.
See generally harvard vidhi punarvilokan sangh, the bluebook : a vardi pranali of Citation ( 18th ed. 2005 ).
Note, however, that some nyaayalayon may aavashyaktaa koi vidhik papers ki hai supurd to unhen to conform to a different citation format.
the signal is the phrase `` see generally, '' jisase indicates ki the citation `` the bluebook : a vardi pranali of citation ( 18th ed. 2005 ) '' provides general background information on the topic.
Neil Alden Armstrong ( agast 5, 1930 – agast 25, 2012 ) thi an amareeki astronaut or the pehla vyakti to chalanaa on the chandramaa.
He was also an aerospace ejeeniyar, naval aviator, pareekshan pilot, and university professor.
pehle banane an astronaut, armastrang thi an adhikari in the U.S. Navy and served in the Korean War.
After the war, he earned his bachelor 's oopaadhi at purdue vishvavidhyalayon or parosa as a pareekshan payalat at the neshnal salaahkaar cameti liye aeronautics high-speed Flight Station, now known as the Dryden Flight Research Center, where he logged over 900 flights.
He later samaapt graduate adhyayan at the vishvavidhyalayon of dakshini California.
A participant in the u.S. air force 's man in spes soonest or x-20 dyna-soar insaan spaceflight kaarykram, armastrang joined the NASA Astronaut Corps in 1962.
He made his first spes udaan, as cmand payalat of mithun 8, in 1966, banane nasa 's pehla civilian astronaut to fly in space.
On this mission, he performed the pehla docking of do spacecraft, with pilot David Scott.
armastrang 's duusari or pichhlaa spaceflight thi as mishan commander of the Apollo 11 moon landing, in July 1969.
On this mission, Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin descended to the lunar surface or kharch do or a half ghanton exploring, jabaki maaikel colins remained in chandra kaksha in the Command Module.
Along with Collins and Aldrin, Armstrong was awarded the Presidential padak of swatantraaa by adhyaksh richard nicksan ; in 1978, adhyaksh jimmy carter prastut armastrang the congressional spes padak of sammaan in 1978 ; he or uske purv crewmates received the Congressional Gold Medal in 2009.
Armstrong died in sinsinati, ohio, on agast 25, 2012, at the aayu of 82, baad jatiltaaon from coronary artery bypass surgery.

Madrid (, ) is the puunji or largest city of Spain.
The population of the city is roughly 3.3 million and the entire population of the madrid mahanagar kshetrafal is gananaa to be around 6.5 million.
It is the third-largest nagar in the europea sangh, baad landan or berlin, or iske mahanagar kshetrafal is the third-largest in the European Union after London and Paris.
The city spans a kul of.
The city is located on the Manzanares river in the centre of both the desh or the jatiyaan of madrid ( jisase comprises the city of Madrid, its conurbation and extended suburbs and villages ) ; this community is bordered by the autonomous communities of Castile and León and Castile-La Mancha.
As the capital city of Spain, seat of sarkari, or nivas of the spani monarch, madrid is bhi the rajnatik, aarthik or saanskrithik centre of Spain.
the vartmaan mahayor is ana botella isse the logon 's Party ( PP ).
The Madrid urban agglomeration rai the third-largest jidipi in the europea sangh or iske prabhaav in raajnneeti, shiksha, entertainment, paryaavaran, media, faishan, science, culture, and the arts all contribute to its status as one of the world 's major global cities.
Due to its aarthik output, unchi maanak of jeena, or market aakaar, madrid is mana the pramukh vittiya kendra of dakshini europea or the iberia prayadweep ; it hosts the head offices of the vast majority of the major Spanish companies, such as Telefónica, Iberia or Repsol.
Madrid is the most touristic city of Spain, the fourth-most touristic of the mahadweep, or the saatvaan sabase visited nagar in the sansar according to forbs.
Is the 10th sabase livable nagar in the sansar according to monocle patrika, in its 2010 index.
Madrid also ranks among the 12 greenest European cities in 2010. < ref name= '' http : //www.citymayors.com/environment/greenest-cities-europe.html '' > madrid is philhal a pratyaashee nagar liye the 2020 garmiyaan Olympics.

It also hosts major antarrashtriya sansthaanon regulators of spani : the khadaa cameti of the sangh of spani bhashaa acadamiyon, mukhyalay of the royal spani academy ( rae ), the cervantes Institute and the Foundation of Urgent Spanish ( Fundéu ).

While Madrid possesses a modern infrastructure, it rai preserved the dekh or mahasoos of anek of iske aitihaasik neighbourhoods and streets.

The path of the via appia or of the via appia Traiana.
Remains of the appian rasta in rome, nikat Quarto Miglio
nikat rome.
The Appian Way ( Latin and Italian : via appia ) thi ek of the earliest or ranneetik sabase mahatvapurn roman sadaken of the ancient republic.
It connected Rome to brindisi, apulia, in southeast Italy.
Its mahatv is indicated by iske aam name, recorded by Statius :
appia teritur regina longarum viarum
`` the appian rasta is the maharani of the long roads ''
The road is named after Appius Claudius Caecus, the Roman censor jo began or samaapt the pehla khand as a sainya sadak to the dakshin in 312 bc dauraan the samnite yudhon.
The Draupner wave, a single daanav wave measured on nai saal 's din 1995, aakhirkaar pushti the astitv of freak waves, which had previously been considered near-mythical
Rogue waves ( also known as freak waves, monster waves, killer waves, charam lehren, or asaamaanya lehren ) hai apekshaakrit vishaal or spontaneous samandar sataha lehren ki occur dur out at samudr, or hai a threat even to large ships and ocean liners.
In oceanography, they are more precisely paribhaashit as lehren jinaki oonchaai is adhik than twice the significant wave oonchaai ( swh ), jisase is itself paribhaashit as the ausat of the largest teesraa of lehren in a wave record.
Therefore rogue waves are not necessarily the biggest lehren mila at samudr ; ve hai, balki, surprisingly vishaal lehren for a given sea state.
Rogue waves seem not to have a single distinct cause, but occur where shaareerik karkon aise as unchi hawaayen or damdaar currents kaaran lehren to vilay to banaaen a single exceptional large wave.

The line of succession to the British throne is the ordered sequence of all those people yogya to safal to the singhaasana of the sanyukt kingdom or the anya 15 rashtramandal realms.
The Act of upnivesh 1701 bestowed uttaradhikaar on the electress sophia of hanover or uske vanshajon while excluding Roman Catholics.
The British government does not publish an official list of all those in line to safal, lakin the kaary of genealogical lekhak or amateur shodhakartaaon suggests ki vahin hai anek thousand people potentially in line.
At a summit in perth, pashchimi australia in 2011, the heads of sarkari of sab 16 rashtramandal realms sahamat to lo kadam to adopt absolute primogeniture, end the exclusion of people married to Roman Catholics, and make other changes in the succession rules.
The line of succession is also used to select the counsellors of rajya ( or a regent if the need arises ) antargat the provisions of the Regency Act 1937.
For earlier versions of the line of succession, dekhie itihaas of the angrejon lakeer of uttaradhikaar.

The War on Terror ( also known as the vaishvik yuddh on aatank ) is a pad commonly lagu to an antarrashtriya sainya abhiyaan jisase prarambh as a result of the 11 September 2001 terrorist attacks on the United States.
This resulted in an antarrashtriya sainya abhiyaan to eliminate al-qaeda and other militant organizations.
The United Kingdom and many anya nato or non-nato raashtra participate in the conflict.
The phrase 'War on Terror ' was first used by US adhyaksh george W. bush on 20 sitambar 2001.
The Bush administration and the Western media have since used the term to signify a vaishvik sainya, rajnatik, lawful, or conceptual struggle—targeting dono organizations designated as terrorist and regimes accused of supporting them.
It was typically prayukt saath a particular fokas on ugravadi Islamists, al-Qaeda, and other jihadi groups.
Although the term is not officially used by the administration of US President Barack Obama ( which instead uses the pad videshi aakasmikta aaparishan ), it is still commonly prayukt by rajaneta, in the media or by kuch pahaluon of sarkari officially, aise as the sanyukt States ' Global War on Terrorism Service Medal.

Blood pressure ( BP ), sometimes referred to as arterial rakt dabaav, is the dabaav exerted by circulating blood upon the walls of blood vessels, and is one of the principal vital signs.
When used without further specification, `` blood dabaav '' praayah refers to the arterial dabaav of the pranaligat parisancharan.
During each heartbeat, blood dabaav varies between a adhiktam ( systolic ) or a nunatam ( diastolic ) pressure.
The rakt dabaav in the parisancharan is pradhanthya due to the pumping action of the heart.
Differences in mean blood pressure are jimmedaar liye rakt pravaah isse ek sthaan to another in the circulation.
The rate of ausat rakt pravaah depends on the pratirodh to pravaah prastut by the blood vessels.
Mean blood pressure decreases as the circulating rakt chaalen dur isse the dil through dhamniyon or capillaries due to viscous losses of energy.
Mean blood pressure drops over the puure parisancharan, haalanki sabase of the patan occurs saath the choti arteries and arterioles.
Gravity affects blood pressure via hydrostatic shaktiyaan ( e.g., dauraan khadaa ) or valves in ragon, shwaas, or pumping isse sankuchan of skeletal mansapeshiyaan bhi influence blood pressure in veins.
Blood pressure without further specification praayah refers to the pranaligat arterial dabaav measured at a vyakti 's apper bhujaa or is a maap of the pressure in the brachial artery, the major artery in the upper arm.
a person’s rakt dabaav is praayah expressed in sharten of the systolic dabaav over diastolic pressure and is measured in millimetres of mercury ( mmHg ), for example 120/80.
A veto – Latin for `` I forbid '' – is the shakti ( prayukt by an adhikari of the rajya, liye udhaaharan ) to unilaterally roke an aadhikarik action, especially the enactment of legislation.
A veto can be absolute, as for instance in the United Nations Security Council, whose permanent sadasyon ( china, frans, rus, sanyukt kingdom, sanyukt rajya of america ) can blaak any resolution.
or it can be simit, as in the vidhaan prakram of the sanyukt rajya, jahaan a two-thirds vote in both the House and Senate may override a Presidential veto of legislation.
A veto only gives power to roke parivartan, nahin to apnaanaa unhen ( except for the rare `` amendatory veto '' ).
Thus a veto allows iske holder to protect the status quo.
the avadharana of a vito deh originated saath the roman consuls and tribunes.
Either of the two consuls holding office in a given year could blaak a sainya or civil nirnay by the anya ; koi tribune tha the shakti to unilaterally block legislation passed by the Roman Senate.
Sulfur dioxide ( bhi gandhak dioxide ) is the rasinic compound with the formula.
it is a vishakt gas saath a pungent, takalifdeh mahakate, ki is released by volcanoes and in various industrial processes.
Since coal and petroleum praayah contain gandhak yogicon, unke dahan generates gandhak dioxide jabatak the sulfur compounds are removed before burning the fuel.
Further oxikaran of so2, praayah in the upasthiti of a utprerak aise as no2, form H2SO4, and thus acid rain.
Sulfur dioxide emissions hai bhi a precursor to particulates in the atmosphere.
Both of ye impacts hai kaaran liye chintaa over the environmental impact of these fuels.
Myasthenia gravis ( from Greek μύς `` muscle '', `` kamazori '', or `` gambhir '' ; abbreviated mg ) is an asankramy neuromuscular beemaari agrani to fluctuating muscle weakness and fatigability.
It is an autoimmune disorder, in jisase kamazori is caused by circulating antibodies ki blaak acetylcholine receptors at the postsynaptic neuromuscular jankshan, inhibiting the excitatory prabhaav of the neurotransmitter acetylcholine on nicotinic receptors throughout neuromuscular junctions.
myasthenia is treated medically saath acetylcholinesterase inhibitors or immunosuppressants, and, in selected cases, thymectomy.
The disease incidence is 3–30 maamle prati lakh prati saal or uthati as a result of increased awareness.
MG must be distinguished isse janmajaat myasthenic syndromes ki can upasthit samaan lakshan lakin prastaav no jawaab to immunosuppressive treatments.

A liquid-crystal pradarshak ( alsidi ) is a chapata falak pradarshak, electronic vizual pradarshak, or video display that uses the light modulating properties of liquid crystals.
drav crystals do nahin emit light directly.
LCDs are available to display arbitrary bimb ( as in a general-purpose computer pradarshak ) or phixd bimb jisase can be pradarshit or chupa, aise as preset shabd, ank, and 7-segment displays as in a digital clock.
They use the vahi moulik praudyogiki, magar ki manamaani bimb hai bana up of a vishaal kramank of small pixels, while other displays have larger elements.
LCDs are used in a chaudee dayera of anuprayog sahit computer monitor, television, yantra panels, vayuyan cockpit displays, and signage.
They are common in consumer devices such as video khilaadi, gaming divaais, ghadiyaan, ghadiyaan, calculators, or telephones, or have replaced cathod ray tube ( CRT ) displays in most applications.
They are uplabdhiyaan in a wider dayera of screen aakaar than crt or plasma pradarshak, or chunki ve do not use phosphors, they do not suffer image burn-in.
LCDs are, however, susceptible to chitra hath.
The LCD screen is more urja kushal or can be disposed of more safely than a CRT.
Its low electrical power khapat enables it to be prayukt in bydaree -powered electronic equipment.
It is an electronically modulated optical device made up of any number of khand bhar saath drav crystals or arrayed in saamne of a lite sorce ( backlight ) or reflector to produce images in color or monochrome.

A vitamin ( or ) is an sashulk yogic jaruri by an sajiv as a vital nutrient in limited amounts.
An organic chemical compound ( or related set of yogicon ) is pukaara a vitamin jab it can nahin be synthesized in sufficient quantities by an sajiv, or jarur be praapt isse the diet.
Thus, the term is conditional dono on the halaaton or on the particular sajiv.
For example, ascorbic acid ( vitamin C ) is a vitamin for insaano, lakin nahin liye sabase anya pashu, or biotin or vitamin D are required in the human diet only in certain circumstances.
by sammelan, the pad vitamin shaamil neither anya anivaary nutrients, aise as dietary khanij, anivaary vasiy acids, or anivaary amino acids ( jisase hai needed in larger amounts than vitamins ) nor the large number of other nutrients that promote health but are otherwise required less often.
Thirteen vitamins hai universally pahachaanaa at upasthit.
Vitamins are vargeekrut by unke biological or rasinic kaaryaklap, not their structure.
Thus, each `` vitamin '' refers to a kramank of vitamer yogicon ki sab dikhaaen the biological kaaryaklap sambhddha saath a particular vitamin.
Such a set of chemicals is grouped antargat an alphabetized vitamin `` generik varnanakarta '' sheershak, aise as `` vitamin a ``, jisase includes the compounds retinal, retinol, and four known carotenoids.
Vitamers by definition are convertible to the active form of the vitamin in the deh, or hai sometimes inter-convertible to ek another, as well.
Vitamins have vividh biochemical functions.
Some have hormone-like functions as regulators of khanij chayapachay ( aise as vitamin d ), or regulators of koshika or utak vikaas or differentiation ( such as some forms of vitamin A ).
Others function as antioxidants ( e.g., vitamin e or sometimes vitamin C ).
The largest number of vitamins ( such as B complex vitamin ) falan as precursors liye anzime cofactors, ki sahaayta anzimon in their work as catalysts in metabolism.
In is bhoomika, vitamin may be tightly bandhi to anzimon as bhaag of prosthetic samooh : For example, biotin is part of enzymes involved in making fatty acids.
Vitamins may also be less tightly bound to enzyme catalysts as coenzymes, detachable anuon ki falan to carry rasinic samooh or electrons between anuon.
For udhaaharan, folic acid may carry mithail, formyl, and methylene groups in the cell.
Although these roles in assisting enzyme-substrate pratikriyaayein hai vitamin ' best-known falan, the anya vitamin krityon hai baraabar mahatvapurn.
Until the mid-1930s, jab the pehla vanijyik yeast-extract vitamin b jatil or semi-synthetic vitamin c sampoorak tablet yahood bechi, vitamin yahood praapt solely through khaanaa seven, or parivartan in aahaar ( jisase, liye udhaaharan, could occur dauraan a particular growing season ) usually greatly altered the types and amounts of vitamins ingested.
However, vitamins have been produced as commodity chemicals and made widely available as inexpensive semisynthetic or synthetic-source multivitamin dietary or khaanaa poorak or editive, chunki the middle of the 20th century.
World Muslim janasankhyikee by pratishat ( pew shodh bich, 2009 )
sansar muslim janasankhyikee in millions
Islam is the sansar 's duusari largest dharm baad Christianity.
According to a 2010 padhai, islam rai 1.62 arab adherents, bananaa up over 23 % of the sansar population.
islam is the predominant dharm in the madhya east, in sahel, in the Horn of Africa and northern Africa, and in some parts of Asia.
Large communities of musalmaan hai bhi mila in china, the balkans, or rus.
Other parts of the world host large muslim apravasi samudaayon ; in pashchimi europea, liye udhaaharan, islam is the duusari largest dharm after Christianity, where it represents 6 % of the total population.
according to the pew shodh bich in 2010 vahin yahood 49 muslim-majority countries.
Around 62 % of the world 's Muslims live in dakshin or southeast asia, saath over 1 arab adherents.
The largest Muslim country is Indonesia, home to 12.7 % of the sansar 's musalmaan, followed by pakistani ( 11.0 % ), India ( 10.9 % ), and Bangladesh ( 9.2 % ).
About 20 % of musalmaan sajiv in Arab countries.
In the madhya east, the non-arab deshon of turkon or iraan hai the largest muslim-majority deshon ; in africa, Egypt and Nigeria have the most populous Muslim communities.
A padhai conducted by the pew shodh bich in 2010 or released January 2011 found that there are 1.62 billion Muslims around the world.
The study found more Muslims in the United kingdom than in lebanon or adhik in china than in syrian.
Rhode Island ( or ), officially the rajya of rhode dweep or vidhaataa baganon, is a state in the New England region of the United States.
Rhode Island is the smallest in kshetrafal, the aathvin tanik populous, lakin the duusari sabase densely populated of the 50 US states behind New Jersey.

The State was also the pichhlaa of the teraa asli colonies to ratify the sanyukt rajya samvidhan.
Rhode Island 's official nickname is `` the samandar rajya '', a sandarbh to the rajya 's bhugol, chunki rhode dweep rai anek vishaal bays or inlets ki raashi to about 14 % of its total area.
Its land area is, but its total kshetrafal is significantly larger.
Dubai ( ; ', ) is a city in the United Arab Emirates, stith bheetar the amir of the vahi naam.
the amir of dubai is stith on the southeast coast of the parsi gulf on the arabian prayadweep and is one of the seven emirates that make up the country.
It has the largest population in the UAE ( 2,106,177 ) and the second-largest jameen territory by kshetrafal ( 4,114 km2 ) baad abu dhabi.
Dubai and Abu Dhabi, the national capital, are the tabhi do emirate to have vito shakti over najuk matters of neshnal mahatv in the desh 's legislature.
The city of Dubai is located on the emirate 's uttari tatarekha or heads up the dubai-sharjah-ajman metropolitan area.
Dubai is nowadays often misperceived as a desh or city-state or, in kuch maamle, the uae as a puure rai maharoom described as 'Dubai '.
the earliest zikr of dubai is in 1095 ad, or the earliest recorded settlement in the region dates from 1799.
The Sheikhdom of Dubai thi formally sthapit in 1833 by sheikh maktoum bin butti al-maktoum jab he persuaded around 800 sadasyon of uske janajati of the bani yas, jeena in kayaa thi tab the duusari saudi rajya or now part of Saudi Arabia, to follow him to the Dubai Creek by the Abu Falasa clan of the Bani Yas.
It remained under the tribe 's control when the United Kingdom assumed suraksha of the sheikhdom in 1892 or joined the nascent sanyukt arab emirate upon swatantraaa in 1971 as the country 's second emirate.
Its strategic geographic location made the kasbaa an mahatvapurn vyapaar hub or by the shuruuaat of the 20th sadi, dubai thi already an important regional port.
Today, Dubai has emerged as a cosmopolitan metropolis that has grown steadily to become a global city and a kaarobaar or saanskrithik hub of the madhya east or the parsi Gulf region.
Although Dubai 's arthvyavastha thi historically nirmit on the aayal udyog, the amir 's western-style model of business drives its economy with the main revenues now coming from tourism, real estate, and financial services.
Dubai has recently attracted world dhyaan through anek abhinav vishaal nirmaan project or khel kaarykram.
The city has become symbolic for its skyscrapers and high-rise buildings, such as the world 's tallest burj khalipha, in jod to mahatvakankshi vikaas project sahit man-made islands, hotel, or kuch of the largest kharidari mal in the pradesh or the world.
This increased attention has also highlighted majdoor or insaan adhikaron mudde concerning the nagar 's largely South Asian paid workforce.
Dubai 's property market experienced a major deterioration in 2008–2009 as a parinaam of the vishwavyaapee aarthik downturn following the vittiya sankat of 2007-2008.
However, Dubai has made a steady and kramik recovery saath sahaayta coming isse neighboring emirates.
The handful of new projects that are in the pipeline have been able to sahaayta dubai real estate mek a vaapasi.
As of 2012, Dubai is the 22nd most expensive city in the world, and the most mahangi nagar in the madhya east, surpassing israel 's Tel Aviv ( 31st ).
Dubai has also been rated as one of the best places to live in the Middle East, sahit by us amareeki vaishvik paraamarsh kad marsar jo rated the nagar as the behtareen place to live in the Middle East in 2011.

An ocean ( ; the sansar samandar of shastreey pracheenta ) is a deh of saline jal ki composes a large part of a planet 's hydrosphere.
In the context of Earth, it refers to one or all of the major vibhaajan of the grah 's sansar samandar – ve hai, in descending anukram of kshetrafal, the prashanth, atlantic, bhartiya, dakshini ( antarctic ), or arctic Oceans.
The word `` sea `` is praayah prayukt interchangeably saath `` samandar '', lakin sakhti bolnaa a samudr is a deh of saline jal ( sambhawatah a prabhag of the World Ocean ) partly or fully enclosed by land.
Earth is the tabhi grah gyaat to have an samandar ( or koi vishaal amounts of open liquid water ).
lagbhag 72 % of the grah 's sataha ( ~3.6x108 km2 ) is covered by saline jal ki is customarily vibhajit into anek principal mahaasaagar or choti samandar, with the ocean covering approximately 71 % of the Earth 's surface.
In terms of the hydrosphere of the Earth, the samandar contains 97 % of the dharti 's jal.
Oceanographers have stated ki out of 97 %, tabhi 5 % of the samandar as a puure on Earth has been explored.
Because it is the principal ghatak of dharti 's jalmandal, the sansar samandar is abhinn to sab known life, forms part of the carbon cycle, and influences climate and weather patterns.
the kul awaz is lagbhag 1.3 arab ghan kilometre ( 310 million cu mi ) with an average depth of.
It is the habitat of 230,000 known species, although much of the samandar 's gaharaaiyon remain unexplored or it is anumaanit ki over do lakh samudri prajati exist.
The utpatti of dharti 's mahaasaagar is still anjaan, lakin mahaasaagar hai believed to have formed in the hadean kaal or may have been the impetus for the emergence of life.
Extraterrestrial oceans may be rachit of a chaudee dayera of tatv or yogicon.
The only confirmed large stable bodies of extraterrestrial surface liquids are the lakes of titan, haalanki vahin is pramaan liye the astitv of mahaasaagar elsewhere in the saura pranali.
Early in their bhugarbhik histories, mangal or shukr hai theorized to have had large water oceans.
The Mars ocean hypothesis suggests that nearly a third of the surface of Mars was ekbar covered by jal, haalanki the jal on mangal is no longer oceanic, or a runaway greenhouse prabhaav may have boiled dur the vaishvik ocean of Venus.
Compounds such as salts and ammonia dissolved in jal nimnatar iske jamane point, so ki jal might maujuud in vishaal quantities in extraterrestrial environments as brine or convecting ice.
apusht mahaasaagar hai speculated beneath the sataha of anek bouna grah and natural satellites ; notably, the ocean of Europa is believed to have over twice the water volume of Earth.
The Solar System 's gas giant planets are also believed to possess drav vayumandaleey paraton of yet to be pushti compositions.
Oceans may also exist on exoplanets and exomoons, including sataha mahaasaagar of drav jal bheetar a paritaarkeey thaharne zone.
Ocean planets are a hypothetical type of grah saath a sataha completely covered with liquid.
Elvis Aaron presli ( janvari 8, 1935 – agast 16, 1977 ) was an American singer and actor.
A saanskrithik pratik, he is commonly known by the single name Elvis.
One of the sabase lokapriy sangeetkaaron of the 20th sadi, he is praayah referred to as the `` King of Rock and Roll '' or `` the King ''.
Born in Tupelo, Mississippi, Presley moved to Memphis, tennesi, saath uske parivaar at the aayu of 13.
He began his career there in 1954, working saath surya record maalik sam phillips, jo chaahi to lao the dhwani of african-american music to a wider audience.
Accompanied by guitarist Scotty Moore and bassist vidheyak blike, presli thi the sabase mahatvapurn popularizer of rockabilly, an uptempo, backbeat -driven fusion of country and rhythm and blues.
RCA Victor acquired uske anubandh in a saude arranged by karnal tom parker, jo gai on to manage the singer for over two decades.
Presley 's first aaarasie single, `` heartbreak hotel ``, released in janvari 1956, was a number-one hit.
He became the leading figure of the newly popular sound of rock and phenken saath a shrenee of sanjaal television dikhaave or chart-topping records.
His energized interpretations of songs, many from african-american strot, or uske uninhibited pradarshan style bana him enormously popular—and controversial.
In November 1956, he bana uske filmi debyue in prem me tender.
Drafted into military service in 1958, presli relaunched uske recording kariyar do saalo baad saath kuch of uske sabase commercially kaamyaab work.
He staged few concerts however, and guided by Parker, proceeded to devote much of the 1960s to bananaa hollywood filmon or soundtrack album, sabase of them critically derided.
In 1968, after seven years away from the stage, he returned to live performance in a celebrated comeback television khaas ki led to an vistaarit las vegas concert racidency and a string of profitable tours.
In 1973 Presley manchan the pehla concert broadcast globally via satellite, Aloha from Hawaii.
nuskhaa drug gaali severely deteriorated uske swasthya, or he died suddenly in 1977 at the age of 42.
Presley is regarded as ek of the sabase mahatvapurn aankade of 20th-century lokapriy culture.
He had a versatile voice and unusually wide kamyaabi encompassing anek jati, sahit desh, pop ballads, inzel, or blues.
he is the best-selling solo kalakaar in the itihaas of popular music.
Nominated for 14 competitive Grammys, he jiti teen, or praapt the grami aaajeevan uplabdhi puraskaar at age 36.
He has maharoom inducted into anek music halls of fame.

root bear is a carbonated, sweetened peya, originally bana using the root of a sassafras plant ( or the bark of a sassafras tree ) as the primary flavor.

Fluorescent minerals emit drishy lite jab ujagar to parabangnee light
pratidipti is the utsarjan of lite by a padaarth ki rai avashoshit lite or other electromagnetic radiation.
It is a rup of sandipti.
In sabase maamle, the utsarjit lite rai a longer wavelength, or isliye nimnatar energy, than the absorbed radiation.
However, when the absorbed electromagnetic radiation is intense, it is sambhavit liye ek electron to avashoshit do photons ; is two-photon avasorana can sise to utsarjan of vikiran having a shorter wavelength than the absorbed radiation.
The emitted vikiran may bhi be of the vahi wavelength as the avashoshit vikiran, termed `` anunaad fluorescence ''.
The most striking examples of fluorescence occur when the absorbed radiation is in the ultraviolet region of the varnakram, or yun adrishy to the insaan najar, or the utsarjit lite is in the visible region.
Fluorescence has many practical applications, including mineralogy, gemology, chemical sensors ( pratidipti spectrumiki ), fluorescent labling, dyes, biological detectaron, or, sabase commonly, fluorescent diye.
Informal logic, intuitively, refers to the siddhanth of logic or logical vichaar baahar of a formal setting.
However, perhaps because of the informal in the sheershak, the precise paribhaasha of anaupchaarik logic is a padaarth of kuch vivaad.
Ralph H. johnson or J. anthoni blair define anaupchaarik logic as `` a shakha of logic jinaki kaary is to develop non-formal maanakon, maapdand, prakriyaaon for the analysis, interpretation, evaluation, criticism and construction of argumentation. ''
This paribhaasha reflects kayaa tha maharoom avyakt in unke abhyaas or kayaa anya yahood doing in their informal logic texts.
Informal logic is sambhddha saath ( anaupchaarik ) fallacies, najuk soch, the soch kaushal gati or the interdisciplinary inquiry known as argumentation theory.
Frans H. van Eemeren writes that the label `` informal logic '' covers a `` collection of normative approaches to the padhai of tark in ordinary bhashaa ki remain kareeb to the abhyaas of argumentation than aupchaarik logic. ''

the great avsaad began in agast of 1929, jab the sanyukt States economy first went into an economic recession.
Although the country spent do maheene saath ghatati jidipi, it thi nahin jabatak the wal gali krash of aktubar, 1929 ki the prabhaav of a declining economy were felt, and a major worldwide economic downturn ensued.
The market krash chihnit the shuruuaat of a dashak of unchi berogari, garibi, kam profits, apsfiti, plunging farm incomes, and lost opportunities for economic growth and personal advancement.
Although its kalyankari hai still anishchit or vivaadaaspad, the jaal prabhaav thi a achaanak or saamaanya ghaataa of confidence in the economic future.
The usual explanations include numerous karkon, visheshkar unchi upabhokta karz, ill-regulated bazaar ki permitted overoptimistic lone by bainko or niveshkon, or the kami of high-growth nai udyog, sab interacting to banaaen a downward aarthik sarpil of reduced spending, falling confidence, and lowered production.
udyog ki suffered the sabase shaamil nirmaan, krishi as dust-bowl sharten persisted in the agricultural heartland, shipping, khanan, and logging as well as durable goods like automobiles and appliances that could be postponed.
the arthvyavastha pahunche neeche in the sheet of 1932–33 ; tab aae chaar saalo of bahut rapid vikaas until 1937, when the Recession of 1937 brought back 1934 levels of unemployment.
The Depression caused pramukh rajnatik parivartan in America.
Three years into the depression, Herbert Hoover khoyaa the 1932 adhyakshiya chunaav to franklin Delano Roosevelt in a sweeping landslide.
Roosevelt 's aarthik recovery yojana, the nai saude, instituted unprecedented kaarykram liye raahat, recovery and reform, and brought about a major realignment of American politics.
The Depression also resulted in an badhayen of karanon of logon to anya deshon liye the first time in American history.
For example, some apravasiyon gai waapas to unke deshi deshon, or kuch deshi us nagarikon went to Canada, Australia, and South Africa.
It also resulted in the mass migration of people from badly hit areas in the Great maidan or the dakshin to sthaan aise as california or the uttar, kramshah ( dekhie okies or the great migration of africa america ).
jatigat tanaav bhi increased during this time.
By the 1940s immigration had laute waapas to saamaanya, or karanon declined.
A well-known example of an emigrant thi frank mccourt, jo gai to ireland, as recounted in his book Angela 's Ashes.
The memory of the Depression also shaped modern theories of arthshaastra or resulted in anek parivartan in kaisaa the sarkari dealt saath aarthik downturns, aise as the use of stimulus packages, Keynesian economics, and Social Security.
It also shaped modern American sahitya, resulting in prasiddh novels aise as jon steinbeck 's `` the angoor of prakope `` or `` Of Mice and Men ``.
The Great avsaad of the 1930s prarambh saath the bhandar market crash of October 1929.
Turkey ( ), officially the ganatantr of turkon, is a transcontinental desh, stith zyaadaatar on Anatolia in Western Asia and on East Thrace in Southeastern Europe.
Turkey is bordered by eight countries : bulgaria to the uttarpashchim ; unaniyon to the west ; georgia to the purvottar ; armenia, iraan or the azarbaijani exclave of Nakhchivan to the east ; and Iraq and Syria to the southeast.
The Mediterranean Sea is to the south ; the igian samudr is to the west ; or the blike samudr is to the uttar.
The Sea of Marmara, the bosphorus or the dardanelles ( jisase saath rup the turki straits ) demarcate the boundary between Thrace and Anatolia ; they also separate Europe and Asia.
turkon 's sthaan at the crossrods of europea or asia makes it a desh of significant geostrategic importance.
The country 's aadhikarik bhashaa is turki, a turkic bhashaa, jisase is bolaa by lagbhag 85 % of the population as mother tongue.
The most numerous ethnic group is the Turks, jo constitute between 70 % or 75 % of the janasankhyikee according to the sansar Factbook.
Kurds are the largest ethnic minority and, according to the same source, kramank around 18 % of the janasankhyikee jabaki anya jaateey alpsankhyakon hai anumaanit to be at 7–12 %.
The vishaal bahumat of the population is Muslim.
The area now called Turkey has been inhabited chunki the paleolithic, sahit vibhinn pracheen anatolian sabhyataaon or thracian peoples.
After sikandar the great 's conquest, the kshetrafal thi hellenized, jisase continued with the Roman rule and the transition into the Byzantine Empire.
The Seljuk Turks began migrating into the kshetrafal in the 11th sadi, starting the prakram of turkification, jisase thi greatly twarit by the Seljuk victory over the Byzantines at the Battle of Manzikert in 1071.
The Seljuk sultanate of rûm shasit anatolia jabatak the mongol akraman in 1243, upon which it disintegrated into several small Turkish beyliks.
Starting from the late 13th century, the Ottoman beylik united anatolia or nirmit an samrajya encompassing much of southeastern europea, pashchimi asia or uttar Africa.
After the Ottoman Empire collapsed following iske shikast in sansar yuddh i, bhaag of it yahood occupied by the vijayi allies.
A cadre of young military officers, led by Mustafa Kemal Atatürk and his sahyogiyon, vyavasthit a kaamyaab pratirodh to the allies ; in 1923 ve sthapit the aadhunik ganatantr of turkon, saath ataturk as iske pehla adhyaksh.
Turkey is a loktantric, dharmanirpeksh, ekaatmak, sanvaidhanik republic with a diverse cultural heritage.
Turkey has become increasingly ekikrut saath the west through sadsyta in organisations such as the Council of Europe, NATO, OECD, OSCE and the G-20 major economies.
turkon began puraa sadsyta negotiations saath the europea sangh in 2005, having maharoom an sambhddha sadsy of the European Economic Community since 1963 and having joined the EU Customs Union in 1995.
Turkey has also fostered close cultural, rajnatik or aarthik sambandh saath the madhya east, kakeshas, the turkic rajya of central asia or the africa deshon through sadsyta in organisations such as the Turkic Council, Joint Administration of Turkic Arts and Culture, Organisation of Islamic Cooperation and the Economic Cooperation Organisation.
Turkey 's growing economy and diplomatic pahalon have led to iske manyata as a kshetreey power.
Turkey is the sansar 's 17th largest arthvyavastha by nammaatr jidipi or the 16th largest by purchasing power parity.

CD-ROMs are popularly prayukt to vitarit computer tantra, sahit video khel or multimedia anuprayog, haalanki any data can be stored ( up to the capacity limit of a disc ).
Some CDs, called enhanced CDs, hold both computer aankada or audio saath the latter sakasham of hone nibhaai on a cd khilaadi, jabaki aankada ( aise as tantra or digital video ) is only usable on a computer ( such as ISO 9660 format PC CD-ROMs ).
The pilaa kitaab is the takneekee maanak that defines the format of CD-ROMs.
One of a set of color-bound kitabe ki contain the takneekee visheshtaayen liye sab cd swarup, the pilaa kitaab, nirmit by soni or philips, was the first extension of Compact Disc Digital Audio.
It adapted the swaroop to tham koi form of data.
