Lent ( Latin : Quadragesima ) is a solemn observance in the liturgical saal of anek isai denominations, sthaayee liye a kaal of lagbhag chah saptaah leading up to Easter Sunday.
In the general Latin-rite and most Western denominations Lent is taken to run from Ash buudhvaar to maundy guuruuvaar ( paavan guuruuvaar ) morning or to easter Eve.
In the Catholic Church, Lent lasts jabatak paavan guuruuvaar, jabaki anya denominations run until Easter Eve.
The paramparaagat purpose of lent is the taiyaari of the aastik through dua, penance, repentance, almsgiving, and self-denial.
Its institutional purpose is heightened in the annual commemoration of paavan saptaah, ankan the maut, dafan or qayamat of yishu, jisase recalls the kaarykram of the bible jab yishu is crucified on shubh shuukravaar, jisase tab culminates in the jashn on Easter Sunday of the Resurrection of Jesus Christ.
During Lent, many of the vafaadaar commit to upwas or giving up nishchit prakaar of luxuries as a form of penitence.
The Stations of the cross, a devotional commemoration of messiah 's carrying the cross or of uske execution, are often observed.
Many Roman Catholic and some Protestant churches remove flowers from their altars, jabaki crucifixes, dharmik murtiyan, or anya vistrut dharmik pratikon hai praayah rahamat in bangnee fabrics in solemn observance of the event.
In certain pious Catholic countries, some adherents chihnit the ritu saath the paramparaagat abstention isse the consumption of meat.
In some deshon, grand dharmik juluson or saanskrithik custom hai observed, or the vafaadaar attempt to vizit seven churches during Holy Week in honor of Jesus Christ heading to Mount Calvary.
Lent is traditionally described as sthaayee liye chalis dinon, in commemoration of the chalis dinon jisase, according to the gospels of mathew, chihnit or luk, yishu kharch upwas in the desert before the beginning of his public ministry, where he endured temptation by the Devil.
However, alag isai denominations gananaa the forty days of Lent differently.
In most Western traditions the Sundays are not counted as part of Lent ; yun the kaal isse raakh buudhvaar jabatak easter consists of 40 dinon jab the sundays hai excluded.
however in the roman catholic girijaghar lent is abhi liya to samaapt on paavan guuruuvaar balki than easter Eve, and hence lasts 38 days excluding Sundays, or 44 days in total.
This event, along with its pious customs hai observed by catholics, lutherans, methodists, Presbyterians, and Anglicans.

The Chernobyl disaster (, Chornobylska Katastrofa – Chornobyl Catastrophe ) was a catastrophic nuclear accident that occurred on 26 april 1986 at the chernobyl nabhikeey shakti sanyantr in yukt ( tab officially the ukraini ssr ), jisase thi antargat the sidhaa kshetradhikaar of the central authorities of the Soviet Union.
An explosion and fire released large quantities of radioskriy anu into the maahaul, jisase sprad over much of the western USSR and Europe.
The chernobyl vipatti is widely mana to have maharoom the worst nabhikeey shakti sanyantr durghatana in itihaas, or is ek of tabhi do vargeekrut as a str 7 event on the International Nuclear Event Scale ( the other being the Fukushima Daiichi nuclear disaster in 2011 ).
The battle to contain the contamination or avert a vrihad pralay ultimately shaamil over 500,000 workers and cost an estimated 18 billion rubles.
The aadhikarik soviet casualty ginati of 31 mauton rai maharoom vivaadit, or long-term prabhaav such as cancers and deformities are still being accounted for.
In vyakaran, a vishay poorak is a predicative abhivyakti ki folo a linking kriya ( copula ) or ki complements ( completes ) the subject of the sentence by either ( 1 ) renaming it or ( 2 ) describing it.
In the former case, a renaming noun phrase such as a sangya or sarvnaam is pukaara a predicative nammaatr.
An kriyasheel following the copula or describing the subject is called a predicative adjective.
in either maamla the predicative complement in effect mirrors the subject.
Subject complements are used with a small class of kriyaayein pukaara linking kriyaayein or copula, of jisase be is the sabase aam.
Since copula hai stative kriyaayein, vishay complements hai nahin prabhavit by any action of the verb.
Subject complements hai typically nahin clause vitark, nor hai ve clause adjuncts.

The acre is a ikai of kshetrafal prayukt in the imperial and U.S. customary systems.
An acre is about 40 % of a hectare – thodaa choti than an amareeki footbaal field.
The acre is no longer commonly prayukt, haalanki a few notable apwaad shaamil the sanyukt rajya, australia, burma or the sanyukt Kingdom ( as of 2010, the acre is no longer officially used in the United Kingdom, though is still used in real estate descriptions ).
It is still prayukt, to kuch extent, in canada.
The international pratik of the acre is ac, or is paribhaashit as 1/640 of a square mile.
The sabase commonly prayukt acre aaj is the antarrashtriya acre.
In the sanyukt rajya dono the antarrashtriya acre or the thodaa alag US survey acre are in use.
the sabase aam upyog of the acre is to measure tracts of land.
One antarrashtriya acre is paribhaashit as 4046.8564224 square metres.
dauraan the madhya aayu, an acre thi the raashi of jameen ki could be plowed in one day with a yoke of oxen.
Antoine Lavoisier 's discovery of the Law of Conservation of dravyaman led to anek nai nishkarshon in the 19th sadi.
Joseph Proust 's law of definite proportions and jon dalton 's parmaanu siddhanth branched isse the discoveries of antony lavvazye.
Lavoisier 's quantitative prayog nazil ki dahan shaamil oxigen balki than kayaa thi previously vichaar to be phlogiston.
The law of conservation of mass, or principle of mass conservation, states that for any system closed to all transfers of matter and energy ( both of jisase have dravyaman ), the dravyaman of the pranali jarur remain nirantar over samay, as pranali dravyaman can nahin badalen maatra if it is nahin added or removed.
Hence, the maatra of dravyaman is `` conserved '' over time.
The law implies that mass can neither be created nor destroyed, although it may be rearranged in spes, or the entities sambhddha saath it may be badla in rup, as liye udhaaharan jab lite or shaareerik kaary is roopantarit into anu ki yogadan the same mass to the system as the light or work had contributed.
The law implies ( requires ) that during any chemical pratikriya, nabhikeey pratikriya, or radioskriy kshay in an pruthak pranali, the dravyaman of the reactants or starting saamagree jarur baraabar the mass of the products.
The concept of mass conservation is widely prayukt in anek field aise as rasayan, yantriki, or fluid dynamics.
Historically, mass sangrakshan thi khoja in rasinic pratikriyaayein by antony lavvazye in the let 18th sadi, or thi of nirnaayak importance in the progress from alchemy to the modern natural science of chemistry.
The closely related concept of matter conservation was found to hold good in chemistry to such high sanniktan ki it vifal tabhi liye the unchi energies treated by the baad refinements of aapekshikta siddhanth, lakin varanaa remains upyogi or fear sateek liye sabase rasinic calculations, even in modern practice.
In special relativity, needed liye sateekta jab vishaal urja hastantaran between pranaaliyon is shaamil, the antar between thermodynamically band or pruthak pranaaliyon becomes mahatvapurn, chunki sangrakshan of dravyaman is sakhti or perfectly upheld tabhi liye so-called pruthak systems, i.e. those completely isolated from all exchanges with the environment.
In this circumstance, the mass-energy equivalence prameya rajya ki dravyaman sangrakshan is samatuly to kul urja sangrakshan, jisase is the pehla vidhi of thermodynamics.
By contrast, for a thermodynamically closed pranali ( i.e., ek jisase is band to exchanges of padaarth, lakin kholen to exchanges of non-material urja, aise as ooshmaa or kaary, saath the surroundings ) mass is ( usually ) only approximately conserved.
The input or output of non-material energy must change the mass of the system in relativity theory, although the change is usually small, chunki apekshaakrit vishaal amounts of aise urja ( by tulana saath ordinary anubhav ) carry tabhi a choti raashi of dravyaman ( again by ordinary maanakon of measurement ).
In special relativity, mass is not converted to energy, since energy in all of iske form sadaa retains iske samatuly raashi of dravyaman throughout koi parivartan or translocation into, or out of, a system.
However, certain types of matter ( a alag avadharana ) may be parivartit to urja, so long as the dravyaman of the pranali is aparivartit in the process.
However, if such energy is removed isse pranaaliyon, ve jarur khona the dravyaman ki is sambhddha with it.
In general relativity, dravyaman ( or urja ) sangrakshan in expanding aaytan of spes is a jatil avadharana, vishay to alag paribhaashaayen, and neither mass nor energy is as strictly and simply conserved as is the case in special relativity and in Minkowski space.
For a discussion, see mass in saamaanya aapekshikta.

A floppy disk, or diskette, is a discs bhandar medium rachit of a discs of patala or lacheelee chumbakeey bhandar medium, sealed in a rectangular plastic carrier lined with fabric that removes dust particles.
They are read and likhaa by a flopy discs drive ( FDD ).
Floppy disks, initially as media and later in and 3.5-inch ( 90 mm ) sizes, were a sarvyaapee rup of aankada bhandar or exange isse the mid-1970s khub into the pehla dashak of the 21st sadi.
By 2010, computer motherboards were rarely manufactured with floppy drive support ; `` floppies could be prayukt as an bahya usb drive, lakin ``, 8 ``, or non-standard drives could only be handled by old equipment.
While floppy disk drives still have some limited uses, especially with legacy industrial computer equipment, they have been superseded by aankada bhandar vidhi saath much vrihad kshamta, aise as usb flash drive, portable bahya mushkil discs drive, optical discs, memory cards, and computer networks.

In baseball, a cutter, or cut fastball, is a type of fastball jisase brake thodaa toward the pichar 's dastaane paksh as it pahunch ghar plate.
This pitch is somewhere between a slider and a fastball, as it is praayah thrown tej than a slider lakin saath adhik gati than a typical fastball.
Some pitchers upyog a kattar as a rasta to prevent hitters isse expecting their regular fastballs.
a aam takanic prayukt to throw a kattar is to upyog a four-seam fastball grip with the baseball set slightly off center in the hand.
When a batter is able to hit a kattar pich, it praayah parinaam in naram sampark or an aasaan out, due to the pitch 's movement keeping the ball away from the bat 's sweet spot.
The cutter is typically 2–5 kimi dhimaa than a pichar 's four-seam fastball.
In 2010, the ausat pich vargeekrut as a kattar by pitchf/x thrown by a right-handed pichar thi 88.6 kimi ; the average four-seamer was 92.1 mph.

He is most famous for the ten eventful saalo he took to vaapasi ghar baad the decade-long trojan yuddh or uske prasiddh Trojan Horse ploy to capture the city of Troy.

Salvador Domingo Felipe Jacinto dalí i domènech, 1st marqués de dalí de pubol ( may 11, 1904january 23, 1989 ), gyaat as salvador dalí ( ), was a prominent Spanish surrealist painter born in Figueres, Spain.
Dalí was a skilled draftsman, behtareen gyaat liye the striking or vicitra images in his surrealist work.
His painterly skills hai praayah attributed to the influence of Renaissance masters.
His best-known work, The hath of memory, thi samaapt in 1931.
Dalí 's expansive artistic repertoire included film, murtikla, or chayachitr, in sahyog saath a dayera of kalakaaron in a variety of media.
Dalí attributed his `` love of everything that is gilded and excessive, my passion for luxury and my prem of praachya kapadey '' to a self-styled `` arab lineage '', claiming ki uske purvajo were descended from the Moors.
Dalí was highly imaginative, or bhi enjoyed indulging in asaamaanya or vaibhavshaalee bartaav.
His eccentric manner or attention-grabbing public kriyaayein sometimes khinchaa adhik dhyaan than uske kalakriti, to the dismay of those jo yojit uske kaary in high esteem, and to the irritation of his critics.

The humanities are academic disciplines that padhai insaan samskruti, using vidhi ki hai primarily vishleshnatmak, najuk, or satte, or having a significant aitihaasik element, as distinguished from the mainly empirical approaches of the natural sciences.
The humanities shaamil pracheen or aadhunik bhashaaen, sahitya, darshanashastra, dharm, and visual and performing arts such as music and theatre.
The humanities that are also regarded as social sciences shaamil itihaas, maanavshaastra, kshetrafal adhyayan, sanchaar adhyayan, saanskrithik adhyayan, vidhi, arthshaastra and linguistics.
vidwaanon working in the maanavtaa hai sometimes described as `` humanists ''.
However, that term also describes the philosophical position of maanavtawaad, jisase kuch `` antihumanist `` vidwaanon in the humanities reject.
Some secondary schools offer maanavtaa varg, praayah consisting of angrezi sahitya, vaishvik studies, and art.
Human disciplines like history, cultural anthropology and psychoanalysis study subject matters to which the praayogic vidhi karata nahin lagu, or ve have abhigam bajaay to the tulanaatmak vidhi or tulanaatmak shodh.
the 2005 blue room Christmas Tree
The White House Christmas Tree, also known as the Blue room christmas ped, is the aadhikarik andar christmas ped at the nivas of the adhyaksh of the United States, the White House.
The first indoor Christmas tree thi santhaapit in the shwet house sometime in the 19th sadi ( vahin hai varying daawa as to the sateek saal ) or chunki 1961 the ped rai tha a prasang motif at the discretion of the First Lady of the United States.
The adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya of america ( potus ) is the sir of rajya or sir of government of the United States.
The adhyaksh lead the karypalika shakha of the sangheey sarkari or is the commander-in-chief of the United States Armed Forces.
Article II of the U.S. Constitution vests the executive power of the United States in the president and charges him with the nishpaadan of sangheey vidhi, alongside the jimmedaari of appointing sangheey karypalika, rajanyik, niamak, or nyaayik adhikariyon, or concluding treaties saath videshi shaktiyaan, saath the salaah or sahmati of the Senate.
The president is further empowered to grant federal pardons and reprieves, or to convene or adjourn either or dono gharon of congress antargat asaadhaaran halaaton.
Since the founding of the sanyukt rajya, the shakti of the adhyaksh or the sangheey sarkari have grown substantially or prayek aadhunik adhyaksh, despite possessing no aupchaarik vidhaan powers beyond signing or vetoing congressionally passed bills, is largely responsible for dictating the legislative agenda of his party and the foreign and domestic policy of the United States.
The president is aksar varnit as the sabase shaktishaalee vyakti in the world.
The president is indirectly nirvaachit by the logon through the chunavi college to a four-year pad, or is ek of tabhi do nationally elected federal officers, the other being the Vice President of the United States.
The Twenty-second Amendment, adopted in 1951, prohibits anyone isse kabhi hone nirvaachit to the presidency for a third full term.
It also prohibits a person from hone nirvaachit to the presidency adhik than ekbar if ki vyakti previously tha parosa as adhyaksh, or acting adhyaksh, for more than two years of another person 's term as president.
In all, 43 individuals have parosa 55 four-year terms.
On January 20, 2009, baraak obama became the 44th or current president.
On November 6, 2012, he thi re-elected or is anusuchit to serve jabatak janvari 20, 2017.
Senses hai physiological capacities of jeevon that provide data for perception.
The senses and their operation, classification, or siddhanth hai ativyapee vishay padhai by a kismein of field, sabase notably neuroscience, sangyanatmak manovigyaan ( or sangyanatmak vigyaan ), or philosophy of perception.
The nervous pranali rai a vishisht samvedi pranali or organ, dedicated to each sense.
insaano have a multitude of senses.
sight ( ophthalmoception ), sunanaa ( audioception ), swaad ( gustaoception ), mahakate ( olfacoception or olfacception ), and touch ( tactioception ) are the five traditionally recognized.
While the ability to detect other stimuli beyond those governed by the traditional senses exists, including temperature ( thermoception ), kinesthetic bhav ( proprioception ), pidaa ( nociception ), santulan ( equilibrioception ), twaran ( kinesthesioception ), or vibhinn aatanrik stimuli ( e.g. the alag chemoreceptors liye detecting namak or carbon dioxide concentrations in the blood ), only a small number of these can safely be classified as separate senses in and of themselves.
What constitutes a sense is a matter of some bahes, agrani to kathinaaiyon in dhamak kayaa exactly a sense is.
Animals also have receptors to bhav the sansar around unhen, saath degree of kaabiliyat varying greatly between species.
Humans have a comparatively kamjor bhav of mahakate, jabaki kuch pashu may kami ek or more of the traditional five senses.
Some animals may also intake or interpret samvedi stimuli in bahut alag tareeke.
Some species of pashu hai samarth to bhav the sansar in a rasta ki insaano can nahin, saath kuch prajati samarth to bhav vidyut or chumbakeey field, and detect water pressure and currents.
Spiders ( order araneae ) hai air-breathing arthropods ki have aath taange or chelicerae with fangs that inject venom.
They are the largest anukram of arachnids or rank saatvaan in kul prajati vividhta among all other groups of organisms.
Spiders are found worldwide on prayek mahadweep magar liye antarctic, or have become sthapit in nearly prayek awaas saath the excepshan of air and sea colonization.
As of 2008, at least 43,678 makadi prajati, or 109 pariwaron have maharoom ankit by taxonomists ; however, vahin rai maharoom bhram bheetar the vaigyanik jatiyaan as to kaisaa sab ye pariwaron chahie be vargeekrut, as evidenced by the over 20 alag classifications that have been proposed since 1900.
anatomically, makadiyon differ isse anya arthropods in ki the usual deh segments are fused into two tagmata, the cephalothorax and abdomen, and joined by a small, cylindrical pedicel.
Unlike insects, makadiyon do nahin have antennae.
In all except the most primitive group, the mesothelae, makadiyon have the sabase centralized baichaiyn pranaaliyon of sab arthropods, as sab unke ganglia hai fused into ek dravyaman in the cephalothorax.
Unlike most arthropods, spiders have no extensor muscles in their limbs or bajaay extend unhen by hydrolic dabaav.
Their abdomens bhaaluu appendages ki have maharoom parivardhit into spinnerets ki extrude silk from up to six types of silk glands within their abdomen.
makadi webs vary widely in aakaar, aakaar or the amount of sticky thread used.
It abhi appears ki the sarpil orb web may be ek of the earliest form, or spiders that produce tangled cobwebs are more abundant and diverse than orb-web spiders.
Spider-like arachnids with silk-producing spigots appeared in the devonian kaal parichay, lakin ye pashu jaahir lacked spinnerets.
True spiders have been found in carboniferous rox isse, or hai bahut samaan to the sabase aadim surviving order, the Mesothelae.
the pramukh samooh of aadhunik makadiyon, mygalomorphae or araneomorphae, first appeared in the Triassic period, before.
A herbivorous species, Bagheera kiplingi, was described in 2008, but all anya gyaat prajati hai parabhakshi, zyaadaatar preying on keet or on anya makadiyon, haalanki a few vishaal prajati bhi lo birds and lizards.
Spiders use a wide range of strategies to capture shikaar : trapping it in stick webs, lassoing it saath stick bolas, mimicking the prey to avoid detection, or running it down.
Most detect prey mainly by sensing kampan, lakin the kriyasheel hunters have adhi drushti, or hunters of the genus portia dikhaaen lakshan of pragna in their choice of tactics and ability to develop new ones.
Spiders ' guts hai too simit to lo solids, or ve liquidize unke khaanaa by baadh it saath digestive enzymes and grinding it with the bases of their pedipalps, as they do not have true jaws.
Male makadiyon pahachaano themselves by a kismein of jatil premalap sanskaar to avoid being eaten by the females.
Males of most species jivit a few matings, simit mukhyatah by their short life spans.
Females weave silk egg-cases, each of jisase may contain sainkadon of eggs.
mahilaon of anek prajati parvaah liye unke yang, liye udhaaharan by carrying them around or by sharing food with them.
A minority of species are social, building communal webs that may house anywhere isse a few to 50,000 individuals.
Social behavior ranges from precarious toleration, as in the vidhwaa makadiyon, to co-operative shikaar or food-sharing.
Although most spiders sajiv liye at sabase do saalo, tarantulas or anya mygalomorph makadiyon can live up to 25 years in captivity.
While the venom of a few species is dangerous to humans, scientists are now researching the upyog of makadi venom in ayurvigyaan or as non-polluting pesticides.
Spider silk provides a combination of lightness, strength and elasticity that is superior to ki of synthetic saamagree, or makadi resha jeenon have maharoom inserted into stanadhariyon or paudhe to dekhie if ye can be used as silk factories.
As a result of their chaudee dayera of vyavhaar, makadiyon have become aam pratikon in art or mythology symbolizing vibhinn combinations of patience, cruelty and creative powers.

Schizophrenia ( or ) is a dimagi vikaar characterized by a vishleshan of vichaar prakriyaaon or by a deficit of typical emotional responses.
Common symptoms shaamil auditory mati, paranoid or vicitra delusions, or disorganized vaak or thinking, and it is accompanied by significant social or occupational dysfunction.
The onset of symptoms typically occurs in yang adulthood, saath a vaishvik aaajeevan vyapaktaa of parichay 0.3–0.7 %.
Diagnosis is aadhaarit on observed bartaav or the rogi 's reported anubhavon.
Genetics, early environment, neurobiology, and psychological and social prakriyaaon appear to be mahatvapurn contributory karkon ; kuch recreational or nuskhaa davaayen appear to kaaran or worsen symptoms.
vartmaan shodh is kendrit on the bhoomika of neurobiology, haalanki no single isolated organic cause has been found.
The many possible combinations of symptoms have triggered debate about whether the nidaan represents a single vikaar or a kramank of alahada syndromes.
Despite the etymology of the term from the Greek jaden skhizein ( σχίζειν, `` to vibhajit '' ) or phrēn, phren- ( φρήν, φρεν- ; `` dimag '' ), schizophrenia karata nahin imply a `` vibhajit vyaktitv '', or `` multiple personality disorder '' ( which is known these days as dissociative identity disorder ) —a condition with which it is often confused in public perception.
Rather, the term means a `` splitting of dimagi krityon '', kuki of the symptomatic prastutikaran of the illness.
The mainstay of upachaar is antipsychotic dawa, jisase primarily suppresses dopamine ( and sometimes serotonin ) receptor activity.
Psychotherapy and vocational and social punarvaas hai bhi mahatvapurn in treatment.
In more gambhir cases—where vahin is risk to swah or others— involuntary hospitalization may be jaruri, haalanki hospital stays are now shorter and less frequent than they once were.
The disorder is thought mainly to affect sangyaan, lakin it bhi praayah contributes to dirghakaalik problems with behavior and emotion.
People with schizophrenia hai sambhavit to have atirikt ( comorbid ) sharten, sahit pramukh avsaad or chintaa vikaar ; the aaajeevan occurrence of substance use disorder is almost 50 %.
Social problems, such as long-term berogari, garibi, or homelessness hai aam.
The ausat jivan pratyaasha of logon saath the vikaar is 12 to 15 saalo kam than those bagaiyr, the result of increased physical health problems and a higher suicide rate ( about 5 % ).

The Epic of Gilgamesh, an epic poem from Mesopotamia, is amongst the earliest surviving works of sahitya.
The literary history of Gilgamesh begins with five swatantra sumerian kavitaayen parichay 'bilgamesh ' ( sumerian liye gilgamesh ), king of Uruk.
Four of ye yahood prayukt as sorce saamagree for a combined epic in Akkadian.
This first combined epic, known as the `` boodha babylonian '' sanskaran, tithiyaan to the 18th sadi bc or is titled baad iske incipit, shūtur eli sharrī ( `` Surpassing All Other Kings '' ).
Only a few fragments of it have batch.
The later `` Standard Babylonian '' version dates from the 13th to the 10th sadiyaan bc or bears the incipit sha naqba īmuru ( `` He who Saw the Deep '' ).
fragments of lagbhag do tihaai of is longer, twelve-tablet version have been recovered.
Some of the best copies were discovered in the pustakaalayon tabah of the 7th-century bc assyrian king ashurbanipal.
The story centers on a dosti between Gilgamesh and Enkidu.
Enkidu is a wild man created by the devataaon as gilgamesh 's baraabar to distract use isse oppressing the people of Uruk.
Together, they yatra to the deodaar pahaad to shikast humbaba, iske monstrous guardian.
Later they maar the sand of swarg, jisase the devi ishtaar bhejnaa to sajaa gilgamesh for spurning her advances.
As a punishment for these kriyaayein, the devataaon vaakya enkidu to death.
The duusari half of the apik focuses on gilgamesh 's distress at Enkidu 's death, and his quest for immortality.
In order to sikh the rahasy of anant jivan, gilgamesh undertakes a long and perilous journey.
he learns ki `` the jivan ki tum are seeking you will never find.
When the devataaon nirmit man ve aavantit to use maut, lakin jivan they retained in their own keeping. ''
This quote was originally attributed to siduri in the boodha babylonian sanskaran of the apik, or tab attributed to the immortal flood hero Utnapishtim in the Akkadian version of the epic.
Nevertheless, Gilgamesh 's kirti jiya on baad uske maut, kuki of uske great bhawan project, or uske khaataa of what Utnapishtim told him happened during the flood.
The story has been anudit into anek alag bhashaaen, or gilgamesh rai chunki become adapted in works of popular fiction.
A sukendrik ( or ) is an sajiv jinaki koshikaayen contain complex structures enclosed within membranes.
Eukaryotes may more formally be referred to as the texon eukarya or Eukaryota.
The defining membrane-bound structure that sets eukaryotic koshikaayen alaava isse prokaryotic koshikaayen is the cendrak, or nabhikeey lipapha, bheetar jisase the genetic saamagree is carried.
The presence of a nucleus gives eukaryotes their name, which aata isse the unani ( eu, `` shubh '' ) or ( karyon, `` nat '' or `` karnel '' ).
Most eukaryotic koshikaayen bhi contain anya membrane-bound organelles aise as mitochondria, chloroplasts and the Golgi apparatus.
All large jatil jeevon hai eukaryotes, sahit animals, plants and fungi.
the samooh bhi shaamil anek unicellular organisms.
Cell division in eukaryotes is alag isse ki in jeevon bagaiyr a cendrak ( prokaryote ).
It involves separating the duplicated gunasutron, through andolanon nirdeshit by microtubules.
There hai do prakaar of prabhag processes.
In mitosis, one koshika divides to upaj do genetically ekasmaan cells.
In meiosis, which is jaruri in yon janan, ek dwiguneet koshika ( having do udhaaharan of prayek chromosome, ek isse prayek janak ) undergoes recombination of each pair of parental chromosomes, and then two stages of cell division, resulting in four haploid cells ( gametes ).
Each gamete has just one complement of gunasutron, prayek a adwitiya mixr of the sambandhit jodi of parental chromosomes.
Eukaryota appears to be monophyletic, or so makes up ek of the teen domen of life.
The two other domains, Bacteria or orchia, hai prokaryotes or have none of the above features.
eukaryotes represent a chota alpsankhyak of sab jeena bate ; bhi in a insaan deh there are 10 times more microbes than human cells.
however, due to unke much larger aakaar unke samuhik worldwide biomass is estimated at about equal to that of prokaryotes.
They are mana to have pehla viksit lagbhag 1.6–2.1 arab years ago.

Internet dhokhadhadi can occur in gapshap kaksh, email, sandesh boards, or on websites.
The International Security Assistance Force ( ISAF ) is a nato -led suraksha mishan in afghanistan ki thi sthapit by the sanyukt raashtra suraksha parishad in December 2001 by Resolution 1386, as envisaged by the Bonn Agreement.
Its main purpose is to train the Afghan National suraksha shaktiyaan ( ansf ) or assist afghanistan in punarnirmaan kunjee sarkari sansthaanon lakin is bhi engaged in the 2001-present war with insurgent groups.
ISAF was initially charged with securing Kabul or surrounding kshetron isse the taliban, al qaeda or factional warlords, so as to allow liye the sthapana of the afgaan transitional prashasan headed by Hamid Karzai.
In October 2003, the UN Security Council authorized the expansion of the ISAF mishan throughout afghanistan, or isaf subsequently vistaarit the mishan in chaar pramukh charan over the whole of the country.
From 2006 to 2011, ISAF had been involved in increasingly adhik intensive combat parichaalan in dakshini or purvi Afghanistan.
Troop yogadanakarta shaamil isse the sanyukt rajya, sanyukt kingdom, nato member states and a number of other countries.
The intensity of the combat faced by contributing nations varies greatly, with the United States, sanyukt kingdom, or canada sustaining the bahumat of hataahat in intensive combat parichaalan, saath anya yogadanakarta sustaining significantly kam.
As of early 2010, there yahood at tanik 700 sainya bases andar afghanistan lakin adhik yahood apekshit to be nirmit in the coming saalo.
parichay 400 of ye yahood prayukt by american‐led nato forces and 300 by ANSF.
Cocaine ( benzoylmethylecgonine ) ( INN ) is a crystalline tropane alcoload ki is praapt isse the pattey of the coca plant.
The name comes from `` coca '' or the alcoload pratyay -ine, forming coca.
It is a stimulant, an appetite suppressant, or a topical anesthetic.
Biologically, cocaine acts as a serotonin–norepinephrine–dopamine reuptake inhibitor, bhi known as a triple reuptake inhibitor ( TRI ).
It is addictive because of its effect on the mesolimbic badla pathway.
Unlike most molecules, cocaine has pockets with dono unchi hydrophilic or lipophilic dakshata, violating the niyam of hydrophilic-lipophilic balance.
This causes it to cross the blood–brain avrodh dur behatar than anya psychoactive rasayan and may even induce blood-brain barrier breakdown.
It is illegal to possess, upaj, or vitarit cocaine for non-medicinal and non-government-sanctioned purposes in almost every country.

The Speaker of the United States House of Representatives ( or spikar of the house ) is the peethasin adhikari of the kaksh.
The office was established in 1789 by Article I, Section 2 of the United States Constitution, jisase rajya in bhaag, `` the house of pratinidhi shall chuse unke spikar... ''
The vartmaan spikar is jon boehner, a republican who represents Ohio 's 8th congressional district.
The samvidhan karata nahin aavashyaktaa ki the spikar be a sadsy of congress, but no non-member has ever been elected to the office.
The Speaker is duusari in the sanyukt rajya adhyakshiya lakeer of uttaradhikaar, baad the vaais adhyaksh or ahead of the President pro tempore of the U.S. Senate.
Unlike some Westminster system parliaments, in which the office of Speaker is considered non-partisan, in the sanyukt rajya the spikar of the house is a netritv sthiti or the office-holder actively works to niyat the majority party 's legislative agenda.
The Speaker usually does not personally preside over debates, bajaay delegating the duty to members of the House from the majority party.
Aside from duties relating to heading the House and the majority political party, the spikar bhi performs prashasnic or prakriyaatmak krityon, or represents his or her Congressional district.
A bicycle frame is the pramukh ghatak of a cykil, on to jisase pahiyon or anya components are fitted.
The modern and most common frame design for an upright bicycle is aadhaarit on the suraksha cykil, or consists of do trikon, a pramukh triangle and a paired rear triangle.

A pendulum is a weight nilambit isse a so ki it can jhule freely.
jab a lolak is visthapit bagalon isse iske resting santulan sthiti, it is vishay to a restoring force due to gravity that will accelerate it back toward the equilibrium position.
When released, the restoring force sanyukt saath the lolak 's dravyaman kalyankari it to oscillate about the equilibrium position, swinging back and forth.
the samay liye ek puraa saikil, a baayein jhule or a right swing, is called the period.
A pendulum swings saath a vishisht kaal jisase depends ( mainly ) on its length.
From its discovery around 1602 by Galileo Galilei the niyamit gati of pendulums thi prayukt liye timekeeping, or thi the sansar 's sabase sateek timekeeping technology until the 1930s.
pendulums hai prayukt to viniyamit lolak ghadiyaan, or hai prayukt in scientific instruments such as accelerometers and seismometers.
Historically they were prayukt as gravimeters to maap the twaran of gambheertha in geophysical surveykshan, and even as a standard of length.
The shabd 'pendulum ' is nai latin, isse the latin pendulus, meaning 'hanging '.
The simple gravity pendulum is an idealized ganitiya model of a lolak.
This is a vazan ( or bob ) on the samaapt of a massless cord nilambit from a, without friction.
jab die an aarambhik dhakka, it hoga jhule waapas and forth at a constant amplitude.
Real pendulums are subject to friction and air drag, so the aayam of unke swings giravat.
The First Battle of Bull Run, also known as First Manassas ( the naam prayukt by confederate shaktiyaan ), thi ladaa on july 21, 1861, in prince wiliam county, virginia, nikat the city of Manassas.
It was the pehla pramukh jameen battle of the amareeki civil War.
Just months after the prarambh of the yuddh at fort sumter, the uttari public clamored liye a kooch viruddh the confederate capital of Richmond, Virginia, which they expected to bring an early end to the rebellion.
Yielding to political pressure, Brig. Gen. Irvin McDowell led his unseasoned sangh fouj aarpaar sand chalaaen viruddh the baraabar anubhavheen confederate fouj of brigadier. gen. P. G. T. Beauregard camped near Manassas Junction.
McDowell 's ambitious plan for a aashcharya parshv akraman on the confederate baayein thi poorly chalaaya by uske adhikariyon or main ; nevertheless, the confederates, jo tha maharoom niyojan to akraman the sangh left flank, found themselves at an initial disadvantage.
Confederate reinforcements under brigadier. gen. joseph E. johnston arrived isse the shenandoah ghati by railroad or the course of the battle quickly changed.
A brigade of virginians antargat a apekshaakrit anjaan karnal isse the virginia sainya santhaan, thomas J. jackson, stood their ground and Jackson received his famous nickname, `` Stonewall Jackson ''.
The Confederates then launched a strong counterattack, and as the sangh sainikon began withdrawing antargat aag, anek panicked or it turned into a rout as mcdowell 's main frantically ran without order in the direction of Washington, D.C.
Both armies were sobered by the fierce fighting and many casualties, and realized the yuddh thi going to be much longer or bloodier than either tha anticipated.

Weather is the state of the atmosphere, to the degree ki it is hot or thanda, geela or shushk, shant or stormy, clear or cloudy.
Most weather phenomena occur in the kshobhamandal, bas neeche the stratosphere.
Weather generally refers to day-to-day temperature and varshan kaaryaklap, whereas jalwaayu is the pad liye the ausat vayumandaleey sharten over longer periods of time.
When used bagaiyr yogyata, `` mausam '' is samajha to be the weather of Earth.
Weather is driven by air pressure ( temperature or nami ) matbhed between ek place and another.
These pressure or taapmaana matbhed can occur due to the surya kone at koi particular spot, which varies by latitude from the tropics.
the damdaar taapmaana contrast between dhruviya or teevr air gives rise to the jet stream.
mausam pranaaliyon in the mid-latitudes, aise as extratropical cyclones, are caused by instabilities of the jet stream flow.
kuki the dharti 's aksh is tilted saapeksh to iske kakshiya plane, dhoop is ghatana at different angles at different times of the year.
On Earth 's sataha, temperatures praayah dayera ±40 °c ( −40 °f to 100 °F ) annually.
Over thousands of years, changes in Earth 's orbit affect the amount and distribution of solar energy praapt by the dharti or influence long-term jalwaayu or vaishvik jalwaayu badalen.
sataha taapmaana matbhed in phere cause pressure differences.
ucchtar altitudes hai cooler than nimnatar altitudes due to differences in compressional heating.
Weather forecasting is the application of vigyaan or praudyogiki to bhavishyavaanee the rajya of the maahaul liye a bhavishya samay and a given location.
The atmosphere is a chaotic system, so small parivartan to ek bhaag of the pranali can grow to have vishaal prabhaav on the pranali as a whole.
Human attempts to control the weather have occurred throughout human history, and vahin is pramaan ki insaan kaaryaklap aise as krishi or udyog has inadvertently modified weather patterns.
Studying how the mausam works on anya grah rai maharoom sahaayak in samajhnaa kaisaa mausam works on Earth.
A famous landmark in the saura pranali, brihaspati 's great red spot, is an anticyclonic toofaan gyaat to have existed for at least 300 years.
However, weather is nahin simit to grahiy bodies.
A star 's kirit is constantly hone khoyaa to spes, bananaa kayaa is essentially a bahut patala atmosphere throughout the Solar System.
The gati of dravyaman ejected isse the surya is gyaat as the solar wind.

The following is a list of sovereign rajya or territories jahaan angrezi is an aadhikarik bhashaa or bhashaa of government.
In 2012, there were 88 states in kul ( 60 sovereign rajya or 28 non-sovereign rajya ).
In many deshon angrezi is the prabal bhashaa, lakin karata nahin have official status.
In Australia, English is spoken by the vast bahumat of the janasankhyikee or is the tabhi bhashaa prayukt in sarkari sansthaanon, lakin Australia does not have an official language.
The case is the same in the United Kingdom and the United States, haalanki anek rajya or regions bheetar the u.S. do have angrezi as an official language.
English is the dominant language of New Zealand and an official bhashaa of canada ( saath saath french ), india ( saath saath hindi or anek anya bhashaaen ), ireland ( saath saath irish ), or the philippine ( along with Tagalog ).
English is the ekmaatr aadhikarik bhashaa of the rashtramandal of raashtra and the Commonwealth Games.
English is one of the aadhikarik bhashaaen of the sanyukt raashtra, the europea sangh or the antarrashtriya Olympic Committee.
Many of these countries are current or former colonies or dependencies of the United Kingdom ( see bhi angrejon samrajya ), or of the sanyukt rajya, itself a former colony of the UK.
Notable exceptions shaamil rwanda, jisase thi a purv belgian upnivesh or iritriya, jisase thi an italvi upnivesh jahaan the British Empire spanned its control only in World War II and shortly after ( 1941-1952 ).
India 's linguistic chitra is jatil.
According to the Constitution of India, `` Hindi in the Devanagari script '' is the official language of the sangh ; or angrezi the 'subsidiary aadhikarik bhashaa ' ; however, angrezi is mandated liye the authoritative granth of sab sangheey kanoon or param adaalat nirnay or ( saath saath hindi ) is ek of the two languages of the Indian Parliament.
English is prayukt lagbhag exclusively liye ucchtar education, business and science.
Courses in bahumat of the skulon hai taught exclusively in English.
English is extensively prayukt liye prashasnic purposes in India.
India is the second-largest English-speaking country in the sansar by kramank of adhyakshon, after the United States.
As such, many consider angrezi to be the de facto aadhikarik language of India.
dekhie aadhikarik bhashaaen of India.
The linguistic makeup of pakistani is similarly jatil.
While the neshnal bhashaa is urdu, angrezi is an aadhikarik bhashaa or prayukt in business, government and law.
angrezi is a anivaary bhashaa in schools.
All skool paathyakram hai sikhaaya in English.
pakistani is the 9th largest english-speaking desh in the world by population.
dakshini cone (, ) is a bhugolic pradesh rachit of the southernmost areas of South America, south of the Tropic of Capricorn.
Although geographically this includes Southern and part of Southeast ( São Paulo ) of Brazil, in terms of rajnatik bhugol the dakshini cone rai traditionally comprised argentina, chile, paragway, or urugve.
In the narrowest sense, it only covers Argentina, Chile and urugve, bounded on the uttar by the rajya of brazil, paragway, bolivia or peru, on the west by the prashanth samandar, or dakshin to the jankshan between the Pacific and Atlantic Oceans, which it is the closest continental area of Antarctica ( 1000 km ).
High life expectancy, the ucchtam insaan vikaas anukramanika of latin america, unchi maanak of jeena, significant bhagidaari in the vaishvik bazaar or the emerging economy of its members make the Southern Cone the most prosperous macro-region in South America.

Meetings hai sometimes yojit around sammelan tables.

An official game in baseball, also sometimes pukaara a viniman khel, is a khel ki rai progressed pare the point at jisase it can be considered complete if necessary.
This is lagbhag the halfway point of the game.
In the case of inclement weather, any game which has reached is point may be roka or shortened as needed, saath the parinaam hone final, or sab record or aankde gine.
A game which has not reached this point before being stopped is either mana a nilambit khel ( to be jari at a baad tithi isse the point of stoppage ), or is simply canceled and replayed from the start.
( This depends on the niyam of prayek vyaktigat league. )
In either case, no aankde hai gine jabatak the khel becomes aadhikarik.
Since most peshewar besabaal khel hai nau pari long, the fifth inning is used as the threshold for an official game.
If the visiting team is agrani, or the khel is tied, the samaapt of the paanchvaan inning marks is point.
If the home team ( jisase bats pichhlaa ) is already ahead in the score, or theoretically hota nahin need iske half of the paanchvaan inning, then 41⁄2 innings ( i.e., the middle of the fifth ) is considered an official game.
The game is also considered official if the ghar toli score to lo the sise in the neeche of the paanchvaan inning, chunki the khel hota samaapt tatkaal if the same thing happened in the ninth.
In nearly all cases, the `` official game '' aukaat is prayukt to determine whether a barsaat jaanch will be honored for fans holding tickets.
If a game is started but karata nahin pahunchein the point of banane aadhikarik, prashansak hai hakdaar to a nai tikat liye the make-up khel or ( in sabase maamle ) any other available game of their choice.
If a game is halted after it becomes official, the khel is bas shortened or no barsaat jaanch is given.
The `` official game '' statistic received some attention during the 1995 ritu, jab calories ripken, jr. thi approaching the ricard liye lagaataar khel nibhaai, previously held by Lou Gehrig.
Large sankhyaayein yahood lataka on the paksh of the b & o godaam at Oriole Park at Camden Yards to show the number of games in Ripken 's streak.
Each day, a nai kramank thi unfurled dauraan the paanchvaan inning baad prayek khel tha become aadhikarik ( chunki the statistic hota not have counted if the game had been stopped before that point ).
A similar practice has been used to ginati bas toward the demolition of anek stadium ( sahit diggajon stadium in philadelphia in 2003, buch memorial stadium in St. Louis in 2005, and the original Yankee Stadium and Shea Stadium in New York City in 2008 ) ; as each game became official, the team would unveil a new ( lower ) number showing the number of games left to be played in the stadium.
A telephone number or phone number is a anukram of ank prayukt to kol isse ek telephone lakeer to another in a public switched telephone network.
When telephone numbers yahood invented, ve yahood choti — as few as ek, two or three digits — and were given orally to a switchboard operator.
As phone pranaaliyon have grown or interconnected to encompass the sansar, telephone numbers have become longer.
In addition to telephones, ve abhi abhigam anya divaais, aise as computer and fax machines.
The number contains the information necessary to identify uniquely the intended endpoint liye the telephone kol.
Each such endpoint jarur have a adwitiya kramank bheetar the public switched telephone network.
Most countries use fixed length numbers ( for normal linon at tanik ) or isliye the kramank of endpoints determines the jaruri length of the telephone number.
It is also possible for each subscriber to have a niyat of shorter sankhyaayein liye the endpoints sabase praayah used.
These `` shorthand '' or `` speed calling '' numbers hai automatically anudit to adwitiya telephone sankhyaayein pehle the call can be connected.
Some special services have their own short numbers ( e.g., 1-1-9, 9-1-1, 0-0-0, 9-9-9, 1-1-1, and 1-1-2 being the Emergency Services numbers for China, Japan, South Korea, Taiwan and Sri Lanka ; Canada and the United States ; Australia ; the sanyukt kingdom, ireland, dakshin africa, candal, saudi arab, the sanyukt arab emirate, morocco, makaao, bahrain, qatar, bangladesh, botswana, ghana, kenya, hong kong, malaysia, Mauritius, Singapore, Zimbabwe, Trinidad, Tobago ; New Zealand ; Kuwait and the European Union, respectively. )
Many systems also allow calls within a local area to be bana bagaiyr dialing the local kshetrafal code.
For example, a phone number in North America will prarambh saath teen sankhyaayein ( aise as 661 ), jisase is the kshetrafal code, followed by saat ank vibhajit into bhaag of teen and four ( such as 550-1212 ), which is the local number.
Some areas now have anivaary ten-digit dialing in place, bhi liye local calls.
Most telephone networks today ( exceptions being private intercom and secure phone sanjaal ) hai interconnected in the antarrashtriya telephone sanjaal, jahaan the swaroop of telephone sankhyaayein is manakikrut by ITU-T in the recommendation E.164.
This specifies that the sampurna kramank chahie be 15 ank or shorter, or begin with a country prefix.
For most countries, this is followed by an kshetrafal code or nagar code or the sadsy kramank, jisase might consist of the code for a particular telephone exchange.
ITU-T recommendation E.123 describes how to represent an antarrashtriya telephone kramank in likhane or chapai, starting saath a plus sign ( `` + '' ) and the country code.
When calling an international number from a fixed line phone, the + jarur be replaced saath the antarrashtriya kol upsarg chuni by the desh the kol is hone bana isse.
Some mobile phones allow the + to be daalaa sidhe.
The format and aavanton of local phone sankhyaayein hai niyantrit by prayek swadesh 's respective government, either directly or by sponsored organizations ( such as NANPA overseen by NeuStar Inc. ).
Before a telephone kol is conect, the telephone kramank jarur be dialed by the calling party or Caller.
The pukaara party might have upkaran ki presents collar ID before the call is answered.
A collection agency is a business that pursues bhugtan of debts owed by individuals or vyavsaayon.
Most collection agencies operate as agenton of lendaaron or collect debts liye a shulk or pratishat of the kul amount owed.
There are many types of sangrahan agenciyon.
First-party agenciyon hai oftentimes subsidiaries of the asli company the debt is owed to.
third-party agenciyon hai pruthak companiyaan contracted by a company to collect debts on their behalf for a fee.
Debt buyers purchase the karz at a pratishat of iske maan, tab attempt to collect it.
Each country has its own niyam or regulations regarding them.

Pharmacologically, the principal psychoactive constituent of cannabis is tetrahydrocannabinol ( THC ) ; it is one of 483 known compounds in the sanyantr, sahit at tanik 84 anya cannabinoids, aise as cannabidiol ( sibidi ), cannabinol ( cbn ), tetrahydrocannabivarin ( THCV ).
and cannabigerol ( cbg ).

1st khaas shaktiyaan operational detachment-delta ( 1st sfod-d ), popularly gyaat as delta force, is ek of the sanyukt rajya ' chaar secretive tier-one counter-terrorism and Special Mission Units.
It was formerly listed as the Combat Applications Group by the vibhaag of raksha lakin rai chunki maharoom officially re-designated the Army Compartmented Elements ( ACE ).
While 1st SFOD-D is administratively samarthit by usasoc, it jalprapaat antargat the operational control of the Joint Special Operations Command.
Delta Force and its Navy bantwaaraa, the naval khaas warfare vikaas samooh, hai the sanyukt rajya sainya 's primary counter-terrorism units.
Delta Force 's primary tasks are counter-terrorism, direct action, or neshnal hastkshep parichaalan, haalanki it is an atyadhik bahumukhi samooh sakasham of conducting anek prakaar of gupt mishan, sahit, lakin nahin simit to, hostage rescues and raids.
The Central Intelligence Agency 's highly gupachup khaas kriyaayein prabhag ( udhaas ) or adhik specifically iske elite khaas parichaalan samooh ( sog ) praayah works saath – or rangaruton – oparator from Delta Force.
Alpha decay is one example type of radioactive decay, in which an atomic nucleus emits an alpha kan, or thereby parinat ( or 'kshaymus ' ) into an anu saath a dravyaman kramank 4 kam or parmaanu kramank 2 less.
anek anya prakaar of decays are possible.
Radioactive decay, also known as nuclear decay or radioactivity, is the prakram by jisase a cendrak of an asthir anu loses urja by emitting anu of inkaree vikiran.
A material that spontaneously emits is dayaalu of vikiran — jisase shaamil the utsarjan of urjavan alpha anu, beta anu, or gamma kirane — is mana radioactive.
There are many different prakaar of radioskriy kshay ( dekhie talika neeche ).
A decay, or loss of energy, results when an atom with one type of nucleus, called the parent radionuclide, parinat to an anu saath a cendrak in a alag rajya, or to a alag cendrak containing alag numbers of protons and neutrons.
Either of ye utpaada is namit the daughter nuclide.
In some decays the parent and daughter are different rasinic tatv, or yun the kshay prakram parinaam in nabhikeey transmutation ( sristi of an anu of a new element ).
The first decay prakriyaaon to be khoja yahood alpha decay, beta decay, and gamma decay.
Alpha decay occurs when the nucleus ejects an alpha kan ( helium cendrak ).
This is the most common process of emitting nucleons, lakin in rarer prakaar of decays, nuclei can eject protons, or vishisht nuclei of anya tatv ( in the prakram called cluster decay ).
Beta decay occurs when the nucleus emits an electron or positron and a prakaar of nutrino, in a prakram ki parivartan a proton to a neutron or the other way around.
The nucleus may capture an orbiting electron, converting a proton into a neutron ( electron capture ).
All of these processes parinaam in nabhikeey transmutation.
By contrast, there maujuud radioskriy kshay prakriyaaon ki do nahin parinaam in transmutation.
The energy of an excited nucleus may be emitted as a gamma ray in gamma kshay, or prayukt to eject an kakshiya electron by baatcheet saath the utsahit nucleus in a process called internal conversion.
radioisotopes occasionally emit neutrons, or is parinaam in a badalen in an element from one isotope to another.
One type of radioactive decay results in utpaada jisase hai nahin paribhaashit, lakin appear in a dayera of `` pieces '' of the original nucleus.
This decay is called spontaneous parivardhan.
This decay happens jab a vishaal asthir cendrak anayas splits into do ( or occasionally teen ) choti beti nuclei, or praayah emits gamma rays, neutrons, or other particles as a consequence.
Radioactive decay is a stochastic ( i.e., random ) process at the level of single anu, in ki, according to kwantum siddhanth, it is naammumkin to bhavishyavaanee jab a particular anu will decay.
However, the mauka ki a die anu hoga decay is constant over time.
For a vishaal kramank of anu, the kshay rate liye the sangrahan is computable isse the measured decay constants of the nuclides ( or equivalently from the half-lifes ).
Waxing is a form of semi-permanent bal hataanaa jisase removes the bal isse the root.
New hair will not grow back in the previously waxed kshetrafal liye do to aath saptaah, haalanki kuch logon hoga prarambh to see regrowth in only a week.
Almost any area of the body can be waxed, sahit eyebrows, phase, bikini kshetrafal, taange, bahen, waapas, udar or feet.
There are many prakaar of vexing upyukt liye nikaalnaa anaavashyak hair.
Strip vexing is sampannataa by spreading a mom thinly over the skin.
A cloth or paper strip is tab dabaaya on the sheersh or ripped band the direction of hair growth.
This removes the mom saath with the hair.
Strip wax can also be made at home using nibu ras, jal, sugar or madhu.
Hot waxing utilizes hot mom ( as opposed to strip wax ).
In this case, the mom is lagu somewhat thickly or with no cloth or paper strips.
The wax then hardens when it cools, thus allowing the aasaan hataanaa by a chikitsak bagaiyr the sahaayta of cloths.
This waxing method is very phydemand to logon jo have samvedansheel skin.

Ancient Roman culture existed throughout the lagbhag 1200-year itihaas of the sabhyataa of Ancient Rome.
The term refers to the samskruti of the roman ganatantr, baad the roman samrajya, jisase, at iske shikhar, covered an kshetrafal from Lowland Scotland and Morocco to the Euphrates.
Life in ancient rome revolved around the nagar of rome, iske famed saat pahadiyaan, or iske smaarkeey structures aise as the flavian Amphitheatre ( now called the Colosseum ), the Forum of Trajan, and the Pantheon.
The nagar bhi tha anek theatre, gymnasiums, or many taverns, baths, and brothels.
Throughout the territory under ancient Rome 's control, residential architecture ranged from very modest houses to country villas, and in the puunji nagar of rome, vahin yahood imperial nivas on the suruchipurna palatine hill, isse jisase the word palace is derived.
The vast majority of the janasankhyikee jiya in the nagar bich, packed into insulae ( apartment blocks ).
The city of Rome was the largest megalopolis of that time, with a janasankhyikee ki may khub have exceeded ek lakh logon, saath a unchi samaapt anumaan of 3.6 lakh or a low end estimate of 450,000.
Historical estimates indicate that around 30 pratishat of the janasankhyikee antargat the nagar 's kshetradhikaar jiya in innumerable shahari centers, saath janasankhyikee of at tanik 10,000 or anek sainya settlements, a bahut unchi rate of urbanization by pre-industrial standards.
the sabase urbanized bhaag of the samrajya thi italy, jisase tha an anumaanit rate of urbanization of 32 %, the same rate of urbanization of England in 1800.
Most Roman towns and cities had a forum, temples or the vahi prakaar of imaaraten, on a choti scale, as mila in rome.
The large urban population required an antaheen supplai of khaanaa jisase thi a jatil logistical kaary, sahit acquiring, transporting, storing or vitaran of food for Rome and other urban centers.
Italian farms supplied subjiyan or fal, lakin machhlee or maance yahood luxuries.
aqueducts yahood nirmit to lao jal to shahari centers and wine and oil were imported from Hispania, Gaul and Africa.
vahin thi a bahut vishaal raashi of commers between the praanton of the roman samrajya, chunki iske parivahan technology was very efficient.
The average laagat of hastantaran or the praudyogiki yahood comparable saath 18th-century Europe.
The later city of Rome kiya nahin bharan the spes bheetar iske pracheen aurelian deevaaren jabatak baad 1870.
Eighty percent of the janasankhyikee antargat the kshetradhikaar of pracheen rome lived in the countryside in settlements with less than 10 thousand inhabitants.
Landlords generally resided in shaharon or unke estates yahood left in the care of farm managers.
The plight of rural slaves was generally badtar than unke counterparts working in shahari vaibhavshaalee households.
To stimulate a higher labor productivity most jameendaar freed a vishaal kramank of slave or anek praapt wages.
Some records indicate that `` as many as 42 logon jiya in ek choti farm hat in mishra, jabaki chah pariwaron owned a single olive tree. ''.
Such a rural environment continued to induce migration of janasankhyikee to shahari centers jabatak the jaldi 2nd sadi, jab the shahari janasankhyikee roka growing or started to decline.
Starting in the middle of the 2nd century BC, private Greek culture was increasingly in ascendancy, in spite of tirades viruddh the `` softening '' prabhaav of hellenized samskruti isse the roodhiwaadee moralists.
By the time of Augustus, sanskari unani household slave sikhaaya the roman yang ( sometimes even the girls ) ; chefs, decorators, secretaries, doctors, and hairdressers—all came from the Greek East.
Greek sculptures adorned hellenistic landscape bagwani on the palatine or in the vila, or yahood imitated in Roman sculpture yards by Greek slaves.
The Roman cuisine preserved in the cookery kitabe ascribed to apicius is essentially Greek.
Roman writers disdained latin liye a sanskari unani style.
Only in law or shashan thi the tirachha prakruti of rome 's accretive culture supreme.
Against this insaan prishthbhumi, dono the shahari or gramin setting, ek of itihaas 's sabase influential sabhyataaon took shape, leaving behind a cultural legacy that survives in part today.

Glass utpaadan involves do pramukh vidhi – the flash kaanch prakram, jisase produces chadar kaanch, or glassblowing which produces bottles and other containers.
A season is a subdivision of the saal, chihnit by parivartan in mausam, paristhitiki, and hours of daylight.
Seasons result from the yearly revolution of the Earth around the surya or the jhukaav of the dharti 's aksh relative to the plane of revolution.
In temperate and polar regions, the sizan hai chihnit by parivartan in the tivrata of dhoop ki pahunch the dharti 's sataha, visangatiyaan of jisase may cause animals to go into hibernation or to migrate, and plants to be dormant.
During May, June and july, the uttari golardh is ujagar to adhik direct sunlight because the hemisphere faces the sun.
The same is sachcha of the dakshini golardh in November, December and January.
It is the tilt of the Earth that kalyankari the surya to be ucchtar in the aasmaan dauraan the garmiyaan months which increases the solar flux.
however, due to mausami lag, june, july or agast hai the hottest maheene in the uttari golardh or disambar, January and February are the hottest months in the southern hemisphere.
In temperate and subpolar regions, generally four calendar -based seasons ( with their adjectives ) hai pahachaanaa : vasant ( vernal ), garmiyaan ( estival ), patjhad ( autumnal ) or sheet ( hibernal ).
However, ecologists mostly use a six season model for temperate climate regions that includes pre-spring ( prevernal ) or let garmiyaan ( serotinal ) as pruthak sizan saath saath the paramparaagat chaar.
Hot regions have do or teen sizan ; the barsaat ( or geela, or monsoon ) ritu or the shushk ritu, and in some tropical areas, a cool or mild season.
In some parts of the world, khaas `` sizan '' hai loosely paribhaashit aadhaarit on mahatvapurn kaarykram aise as a hurricane season, tornado season or a wildfire season.
The chah ecological seasons

The Battle of Fort Sumter ( April 12–14, 1861 ) was the bambaari or aatmasamarpan of fort sumter, nikat charlston, dakshin carolina, ki prarambh the amareeki civil yuddh.
Following declarations of secession by seven Southern states, South Carolina maange ki the u.S. fouj laaparvaahee iske suvidhaayen in charlston Harbor.
On December 26, 1860, U.S. Major Robert Anderson surreptitiously sthanantarit uske choti cmand isse the indefensible fort moultrie on suliwan 's dweep to fort sumter, a substantial kila controlling the entrance of Charleston Harbor.
An attempt by U.S. President James Buchanan to reinforce and resupply Anderson, using the unarmed merchant jalayaan star of the west, vifal jab it thi fired upon by shore bydaree on January 9, 1861.
South carolina adhikariyon tab jabt sab sangheey property in the charlston area, except for Fort Sumter.
During the jaldi maheene of 1861, the halaat around fort sumter increasingly began to resemble a siege.
In March, Brig. Gen. P. G. T. Beauregard, the first saamaanya adhikari of the newly formed confederate rajya of america, thi lagaai in command of Confederate forces in Charleston.
Beauregard energetically directed the strengthening of bydaree around charlston harbar aimed at Fort Sumter.
Conditions in the fort grew dire as the sangh sainiko rushed to puraa the installation of additional guns.
Anderson was short of main, khaanaa, or aapurtiyan.
The resupply of Fort Sumter became the pehla sankat of the prashasan of adhyaksh abraham lincoln.
He notified the Governor of South Carolina, Francis W. Pickens, ki he thi sending supplai jahaajon, jisase resulted in an ultimatum from the Confederate government : evacuate Fort Sumter immediately.
pramukh anderson refused to surrender.
shuruuaat at 4:30 a.m. on april 12, the confederates bombarded the fort isse artillery batteries surrounding the harbor.
Although the sangh garrison laute aag, ve yahood significantly outgunned or, baad 34 ghanton, pramukh Anderson agreed to evacuate.
There was no loss of life on either side as a direct result of is sagaai, haalanki a gan visphot dauraan the aatmasamarpan ceremonies on april 14 caused do sangh mauton.
Following the battle, there was faili support isse dono uttar or dakshin liye further sainya action.
Lincoln 's taatkaalik kol liye 75,000 swayamsevak to dabaane the vidroh resulted in an atirikt chaar dakshini slave states also declaring their secession and joining the Confederacy.
The civil yuddh tha begun.

3G telecommunication networks support services ki provide an soochna transafar rate of at tanik 200 kbit/s.
However, many sevaayen advertised as 3g provide ucchtar gati than the nunatam technical requirements for a 3G service.
Recent 3G releases, often denoted 3.5G and 3.75G, also provide mobile broadband abhigam of anek mbit/s to smartphone or mobile modems in laptop computer.
3G finds application in betaar awaz telephony, mobile antarjaal abhigam, phixd betaar Internet access, video calls and mobile TV.

Hepatitis C is an infectious beemaari affecting primarily the jigar, caused by the hepatitis C virus ( HCV ).
The infection is often asymptomatic, but chronic infection can lead to scarring of the liver or ultimately to cirrhosis, jisase is generally apparent baad anek saalo.
In some cases, those with cirrhosis hoga go on to develop jigar vifaltaa, jigar karkat or life-threatening esophageal or gastric varices.
HCV is spread primarily by blood-to-blood sampark sambhddha saath intravenous drug upyog, poorly sterilized chikitsa upkaran and transfusions.
An estimated 130–200 lakh logon vishwavyaapee hai sankramit with.
The existence of ( originally `` non- A non- B hepatitis '' ) thi postulated in the 1970s or siddh in 1989.
tabhi infects insaano and chimpanzees.
The virus persists in the jigar in parichay 85 % of those infected.
This persistent sankraman can be treated saath dawa : the maanak chikitsa is a sangyojan of peginterferon or ribavirin, saath either boceprevir or telaprevir added in some cases.

A flexible spending account ( FSA ), also known as a flexible spending vyavastha, is ek of a kramank of tax-advantaged vittiya khate ki can be niyat up through a cafeteria yojana of an niyokta in the United States.
An FSA allows an employee to niyat aside a portion of aay to adaa liye yogya kharch as sthapit in the cafeteria yojana, sabase commonly liye chikitsa kharch but often for dependent care or other expenses.
Money deducted from an employee 's adaa into an fsa is nahin vishay to payroll kar, resulting in substantial payroll tax savings.
One significant disadvantage to using an FSA is ki nidhi nahin prayukt by the samaapt of the yojana saal hai khoyaa to the karmchaaree, gyaat as the `` upyog it or lose it '' rule.
The most common type of lacheelee bitaa khaataa, the chikitsa vyay fsa ( bhi chikitsa fsa or swasthya fsa ), is samaan to a health savings account ( HSA ) or a health reimbursement account ( HRA ).
However, while HSAs and HRAs are almost exclusively used as components of a consumer driven health care yojana, chikitsa fsas hai commonly offered saath adhik paramparaagat swasthya yojanaayen as well.
In addition, funds in a swasthya bachat khaataa hai nahin khoyaa when the plan year is over, unlike funds in an FSA.
Paper form or an fsa debit card, bhi gyaat as a flexcard, may be used to access the account funds.
tennesi ( ) ( ) is a u.S. rajya stith in the southeastern United States.
Tennessee is the 36th most extensive or the 17th sabase populous of the 50 sanyukt States.
tennesi is bordered by kentki or virginia to the uttar, uttar carolina to the east, georgia, albama, or mississippi to the south, and Arkansas and Missouri to the west.
The Appalachian Mountains dominate the eastern part of the state, or the mississippi nadi form the rajya 's western border.
Tennessee 's capital and second largest nagar is naishaville, jisase rai a janasankhyikee of 609,644.
Memphis is the state 's largest nagar, saath a janasankhyikee of 652,050.
The state of Tennessee is rooted in the Watauga sangh, a 1772 frontier anubandh generally regarded as the pehla sanvaidhanik government west of the Appalachians.
What is abhi tennesi thi initially bhaag of uttar carolina, or baad bhaag of the Southwest Territory.
Tennessee thi admitted to the sangh as the 16th rajya on June 1, 1796.
Tennessee was the pichhlaa rajya to chhod the sangh or juden the confederacy at the outbreak of the u.S. civil yuddh in 1861, or the pehla rajya to be readmitted to the Union at the end of the war.
Tennessee furnished more soldiers liye the confederate fouj than koi anya rajya, or adhik sainiko liye the sangh fouj than any other Southern state.
In the 20th century, Tennessee transitioned from an agrarian arthvyavastha to a adhik diversified arthvyavastha, aided at times by sangheey entities aise as the tennesi ghati praadhikaar.
In the early 1940s, the city of Oak Ridge thi sthapit to house the manahaton project 's uranium sanvardhan suvidhaayen, helping to nirmaan the sansar 's first atomic bomb.
Tennessee has played a najuk bhoomika in the vikaas of anek form of amareeki lokapriy music, including rock and roll, blues, country, and rockabilly.
Beale Street in Memphis is considered by many to be the janmasthan of the bluez, saath sangeetkaaron aise as w.c. sulabh performing in iske club as jaldi as 1909.
Memphis was also home to Sun Records, where musicians such as Elvis Presley, Isaac Hayes, johny nakadi, karl perkins, jeri lee louis, roy orbison, or charlie samrudh began unke recording kariyar, and where rock and roll took shape in the 1950s.
The 1927 Victor recording satr in bristol generally chihnit the shuruuaat of the desh music vidha or the vruddhi of the grand ole opry in the 1930s helped make Nashville the center of the country music recording industry.
Three bricks and mortar museums recognize Tennessee 's role in nurturing vibhinn form of lokapriy music : the memphis chattan n ' aatma sangrahalay, the desh music haul of kirti or sangrahalay in naishaville, or the antarrashtriya rock-a-billy Museum in Jackson.
In addition, the Rockabilly Hall of Fame, an online sait recognizing the vikaas of rockabilly in jisase tennesi nibhaai a nirnaayak bhoomika, is aadhaarit in naishaville.
tennesi 's pramukh udyog shaamil agriculture, manufacturing, and tourism.
Poultry, soybeans, and cattle are the state 's primary agricultural products, and major nirmaan niryaat shaamil rasayan, parivahan upkaran, or vidyut upkaran.
The Great Smoky Mountains National Park, the swadesh 's sabase visited neshnal park, is headquartered in the purvi bhaag of the rajya, or a section of the Appalachian Trail roughly follows the Tennessee-North Carolina border.
Other major tourist aakarshan shaamil the tennesi equarium in chattanuga, the sunsphere in knoxville, dollywood in kabutar forge, the parthenon, the desh music haul of kirti or sangrahalay, or ryman auditorium in naishaville, and Elvis Presley 's Graceland residence and tomb in Memphis.

Major League Baseball ( MLB ) is a peshewar besabaal lig, consisting of tiimon ki khel in the neshnal lig and the American League.
Dating to 1876 and 1901 respectively, the two leagues merged in 2000 into a single sanghathan led by the kamishnar of besabaal, baad 100 years as separate legal entities.
MLB constitutes one of the pramukh peshewar khel lig of the sanyukt States and Canada.
It is composed of 30 tiimon — 29 in the sanyukt rajya or one in Canada.
Teams in MLB play 162 games prayek ritu over chah maheene ( april through September ).
Five teams in each league advance to a four-round postseason toornament ki culminates in the sansar shrenee, a best-of-seven-games championship series between the two league champions which dates to 1903.
The organization oversees anek minor-league besabaal lig jisase operate parichay 240 tiimon sambhddha saath the major-league clubs.
With the antarrashtriya besabaal sangh, the lig bhi manages the antarrashtriya sansar besabaal Classic tournament.
MLB has the highest season upasthiti of koi khel lig in the sansar saath nearly 75 million spectators in 2012.
Delaware ( ) is a u.S. rajya stith on the atlantic coast in the mid-atlantic pradesh of the United States.
It is bordered to the south or west by maryland, to the purvottar by nai jersey, or to the uttar by Pennsylvania.
the rajya takes iske naam isse thomas west, 3rd samant de la warr, an angrezi nobleman or virginia 's pehla aupniveshik rajyapal, baad jisko kayaa is now called Cape Henlopen was originally named.
Delaware is located in the northeastern portion of the Delmarva Peninsula and is the duusari smallest, the chathe tanik populous, lakin the chathe sabase densely aabaadi of the fifty United States.
delaware is vibhajit into teen counties.
isse uttar to dakshin, ye teen county are New Castle, Kent, and Sussex.
While the southern two counties have historically maharoom predominantly agricultural, nai kila county rai maharoom more industrialized.
Before its coastline was explored by Europeans in the 16th sadi, delaware thi inhabited by anek samooh of deshi america, sahit the lenape in the north and Nanticoke in the south.
It was initially colonized by dach vyapaariyon at zwaanendael, located near the present town of Lewes, in 1631.
Delaware was one of the 13 colonies participating in the American Revolution and on disambar 7, 1787, became the pehla rajya to ratify the samvidhan of the sanyukt rajya, thereby banane gyaat as the First State.
Energy parivartan in urja pranaaliyon bhashaa
urja parivartan or urja parivartan is the prakram of badalanaa one form of energy to another.
In physics, the term energy describes the capacity to upaj nishchit parivartan bheetar a pranali, bagaiyr lihaaz to limitations in transformation imposed by Entropy.
Changes in total energy of systems can tabhi be sampannataa by adding or subtracting urja isse unhen, as urja is a maatra jisase is conserved, according to the first law of thermodynamics.
According to special relativity, parivartan in the urja of pranaaliyon hoga bhi coincide saath parivartan in the pranali 's dravyaman, or the total amount of mass of a system is a measure of its energy.
urja in a pranali may be roopantarit so ki it resides in a alag rajya, or a different type of energy.
urja in anek rajya may be prayukt to do many varieties of physical work.
Energy may be used in prakritik prakriyaaon or mashine, or else to provide kuch seva to samaaj ( aise as heat, light, or motion ).
For example, an internal combustion engine converts the potential rasinic urja in gasoline or oxigen into ooshmaa, jisase is tab roopantarit into the propulsive urja ( kinetic energy that moves a vehicle ).
A solar cell converts solar radiation into vidyut urja ki can tab be prayukt to lite a balb or shakti a computer.
The generic name for a yantra jisase converts urja isse ek rup to another, is a transducer.
In saamaanya, sabase prakaar of urja, sahejen liye thermal urja, may be converted efficiently to any other kind of energy.
Sometimes this occurs with an efficiency of essentially 100 %, aise as jab sambhavit urja is parivartit to gatij urja as an object jalprapaat in vacuum, or when it orbits nearer or farther from another object, in space.
Conversion of other types of energies to ooshmaa may bhi occurs saath nearly purna dakshata ( many types of friction do this ).
Exceptions for perfect conversion efficiency ( even for isolated systems ) occur when urja rai already maharoom partly vitarit among anek uplabdhiyaan kwantum rajya liye a sangrahan of anu, jisase hai freely anumat to explore koi rajya of aaveg and position ( phase space ).
In such circumstances, a measure called Entropy, or evening-out of energy vitaran in aise rajya, dictates ki bhavishya rajya of the pranali jarur be of at tanik baraabar evenness in energy distribution.
( There is no way, taking the universe as a whole, to collect urja into kam rajya, ekbar it rai sprad to unhen ).
A consequence of is aavashyaktaa is ki vahin hai simaaen to the dakshata saath jisase thermal urja can be parivartit to anya kinds of urja, chunki thermal urja in santulan at a die taapmaana already represents the maximal evening-out of energy between all possible states.
aise urja is sometimes mana `` degraded urja, '' because it is not entirely usable.
The second law of thermodynamics is a way of stating that, for this reason, thermal energy in a system may be converted to other kinds of urja saath efficiencies approaching 100 %, tabhi if the entropy ( even-ness or vikaar ) of the brahmad is increased by anya arthath, to compensate liye the ghati in entropy sambhddha with the disappearance of the thermal energy and its entropy content.
Otherwise, only a part of thermal energy may be converted to other kinds of energy ( and thus, useful work ), since the remainder of the heat must be reserved to be transferred to a thermal tank at a nimnatar taapmaana, in aise a rasta ki the badhayen in entropy liye is prakram adhik than compensates liye the entropy ghati sambhddha saath parivartan of the rest of the heat into other types of energy.
The National Hockey League ( NHL ; ) is an `` unincorporated not-for-profit sangh '' jisase operates a pramukh peshewar barf hockey lig of 30 franchised sadsy club, of jisase saat hai philhal stith in canada and 23 in the United States.
Headquartered in New York City, the NHL is widely considered to be the premier peshewar barf hockey lig in the sansar, or ek of the pramukh peshewar khel lig in the sanyukt rajya or Canada.
The Stanley Cup, the oldest professional sports trophy in North america, is awarded annually to the lig playoff champion at the end of each season.
The league was organized on November 26, 1917, in Montreal, quebec, canada, baad the barkhaastagi of parichaalan of iske purvavarti sanghathan, the neshnal hockey sangh ( NHA ), which had been founded in 1909.
It prarambh saath chaar tiimon or, through a shrenee of expansions, contractions, or relocations, the league is now composed of 30 active franchises.
The nation to which the naam of the lig originally referred thi canada, haalanki the lig rai abhi maharoom binational chunki 1924 jab it vistaarit into the United States.
After a labour dispute that led to the cancellation of the entire 2004–05 ritu, the lig resumed khel antargat a nai samuhik bargaining anubandh ki shaamil a salary cap.
In 2009, the enechael enjoyed ricard highs in sharten of sponsorships, attendance, and television audiences.
the enechael draws anek atyadhik skilled khilaadi isse sab over the world and currently has players from about 20 different countries.
Although Canadians have historically constituted the majority of the players in the NHL, over the past four plus decades the percentages of US and European khilaadi have increased dono kuki of the enechael 's jari vistaar isse chah to tees club chunki 1967, or the increased uplabdhta of atyadhik skilled europea khilaadi.
This is the complete list of the ratified or unratified amendments to the sanyukt rajya samvidhan jisase praapt the sweekruti of the United States Congress.
Twenty-seven amendments have been ratified since the original signing of the Constitution, the first ten of jisase hai gyaat collectively as the vidheyak of Rights.
The procedure for amending the United rajya samvidhan is governed by aalekh v of the asli text.
There have been many other proposals for amendments to the sanyukt rajya samvidhan introduced in congress, lakin nahin submitted to the states.
Before an amendment can lo prabhaav, it jarur be prastaavit to the rajya by a two-thirds vote of dono gharon of congress or by a sammelan ( gyaat as an aalekh v sammelan ) pukaara by two-thirds of the rajya, or ratified by three-fourths of the states or by three-fourths of conventions thereof, the method of ratification being determined by Congress at the time of proposal.
To date, no convention for proposing amendments rai maharoom pukaara by the rajya, or tabhi once—in 1933 liye the anusamarthan of the twenty-first amendment —has the sammelan vidhi of ratification been employed.
