Sociology is the scientific study of insaan samaaj or iske origins, vikaas, sanghathan, or sansthaanon.
It is a social science which uses various methods of empirical chaanbin or najuk vishleshan to develop a deh of gyaan parichay insaan social activity, structures, and functions.
A goal for many sociologists is to conduct shodh jisase may be lagu sidhe to soshal niti or welfare, jabaki anya fokas primarily on shodhan the theoretical understanding of social processes.
Subject matter ranges isse the sookshm str of vyaktigat agency or baatcheet to the macro level of systems and the social structure.
the paramparaagat focuses of samajashaastra shaamil soshal starikaran, soshal class, samskruti, race and ethnicity, gender and sexuality, social mobility, religion, secularization, law, and deviance.
As all spheres of human activity are affected by the interplay between social structure and individual agency, sociology has gradually expanded its focus to further vishay, aise as swasthya, chikitsa, sainya or penal sansthaanon, the antarjaal, paryaavarniya samajashaastra, rajnatik arthvyavastha or the bhoomika of soshal kaaryaklap in the vikaas of vaigyanik gyaan.
The range of soshal vaigyanik vidhi rai bhi expanded.
Social researchers draw upon a kismein of gunatmak or quantitative takneekon.
The bhashaai or saanskrithik turns of the mid-twentieth sadi led to increasingly interpretative, hermeneutic, or philosophic approaches to the analysis of society.
conversely, haal dashakon have dekhi the vruddhi of nai analytically, mathematically or computationally rigorous techniques, such as agent-based modelling and social network analysis.
Sociology should not be confused saath vibhinn saamaanya soshal adhyayan paathyakram jisase bhaaluu choti sambandh to samajashastreey theory or social science research methodology.
Thunder is the dhwani caused by bijli.
Depending on the nature of the lightning or alahada of the shrota, thunder can dayera isse a sharp, laud crack to a long, low rumble ( brontide ).
The sudden increase in dabaav or taapmaana isse bijli produces rapid vistaar of the air surrounding and within a bolt of lightning.
In turn, this expansion of air creates a sonic shock wave, similar to a sonic boom, jisase produces the dhwani of thunder, praayah referred to as a clap, crack, or peal of thunder.
The distance of the lightning can be calculated by the listener based on the time interval isse jab the bijli is dekhi to jab the dhwani is heard.

Martin Luther King, Jr. Day is a sanyukt rajya sangheey avkaash ankan the janmdiwas of rev. dr. martin luther King, Jr.
It is observed on the teesraa somvaar of janvari prayek saal, jisase is around the samay of king 's janmdiwas, January 15.
The floating avkaash is samaan to chhuttiyaan niyat antargat the vardi somvaar avkaash adhinium, haalanki the act predated the establishment of Martin Luther King, Jr. Day by 15 years.
King was the chief spokesman for nonviolent sakriyata in the civil adhikaron gati, jisase safaltaapurvak protested jatigat pakshpaat in federal and state law.
The campaign for a federal avkaash in king 's sammaan began jald baad uske hatya in 1968.
Ronald Reagan signed the holiday into law in 1983, or it thi pehla observed on janvari 20, 1986.
At pehla, kuch rajya resisted observing the avkaash as aise, giving it vaikalpik names or combining it with other holidays.
It was officially observed in sab 50 rajya liye the pehla samay in 2000.
The camera phone samaadhaan allows tatkaal sharing of pictures.
As it 's automatic and tatkaal, the upayokta karata nahin have to upyog a cabel or removable media to connect to a personal computer.
A camera phone is a mobile phone which is able to capchar still chayachitr ( or praayah video ).
Since early in the 21st century the bahumat of mobile phone in upyog are camera phones.
Most camera phone hai simpler than pruthak digital cameras.
Their usual fixed focus lenses and smaller sensors limit their pradarshan in garib lighting.
Lacking a physical shutter, most have a long shater lag.
flash, jahaan upasthit, is usually weak.
optical juum or tipai screws are rare.
Some bhi kami a usb conection, removable memory card, or anya rasta of transferring unke tasviren adhik jaldi than by the phone 's inherent communication feature.
Some of the more expensive camera phone have tabhi a few of ye takneekee disadvantages, jisase lagu sabase acutely in kam lite sharten or in koi maamla have not inhibited their widespread use.
Most model linon improve in ye pranaam every year or two.
Some, aise as the droid avishwasaneey tabhi have a menu chunaav to start an application program to activate the camera.
Others, such as the blueberi toofaan 2, droid x, motorola v980 or nokia 5800 bhi have a pruthak camera batan liye quickness and convenience.
khidkiyaan phone can be vinyast to operate as a camera even if the phone is asleep.
Some camera phones are designed to resemble pruthak low-end digital compact camere in rup and to some extent in features and picture quality, and are branded as both mobile phones and cameras, including certain Sony phones.
The principal advantages of camera phone hai laagat or compactness ; beshak liye a upayokta jo carries a mobile phone vaise, the atirikt aakaar or cost are negligible.
Smartphones that are camera phones may run mobile anuprayog to add samarthy aise as geotagging or chitra stitching.
A few high end phones can use their tach screen to sidhaa unke camera to fokas on a particular object in the field of drishy, giving bhi an anubhavheen upayokta a oopaadhi of fokas control exceeded tabhi by seasoned photographers using manual focus.
`` whatever happened to the man of kal ? '' is a 1986 comic kitaab story featuring the dc Comics character of Superman.
Written by alan moore saath sahaayta isse long-time, or jald to be retiring, superman editor, julius schwartz, the story thi prakashit in do bhaag, beginning in Superman # 423 and ending in Action Comics # 583, both published in September 1986.

uske story shaamil numerous hinsak hamale viruddh superman by uske dushmano, the public rahasyodghatan of uske rahasy identity of Clark Kent and a number of deaths of those closest to him.

A short story is a brief work of sahitya, praayah likhaa in katha gadhy.
Emerging from earlier oral storytelling traditions in the 17th century, the short story rai grown to encompass a deh of kaary so vividh as to defy aasaan characterization.
At its most prototypical the short story features a small cast of named characters, and focuses on a self-contained ghatana saath the intent of evoking a `` single prabhaav '' or manodasha.
In so doing, short stories make use of plot, resonance, and other dynamic components to a dur vrihad oopaadhi than is theth of an kissa, yet to a dur lesser degree than a novel.
While the short story is largely distinct from the anokhaa, lekhak of dono generally chithran isse a aam pool of saahitiyik techniques.
Short stories have no niyat lambaai.
In sharten of shabd ginati vahin is no aadhikarik demarcation between an anecdote, a short story, and a novel.
balki, the rup 's paramiters hai die by the rhetorical or vyaavhaarik context in jisase a die story is utpaadit or mana, so ki kayaa constitutes a short story may differ between genres, countries, eras, and commentators.
Like the novel, the short story 's predominant shape reflects the demands of the available markets for publication, and the evolution of the rup seems closely tied to the evolution of the prakaashan udyog or the sabamishan dishanirdesh of iske constituent houses.
The short story has been mana dono an shikshuta rup preceding adhik lengthy works, or a crafted rup in iske apana sahi, ekatrit together in books of similar length, price, and distribution as novels.
choti story lekhak may define unke works as bhaag of the kalakaari and personal expression of the form.
ve may bhi attempt to resist categorization by genre and fixed form.

The raccoon (, Procyon lotor ), sometimes spelled racoon, also known as the common raccoon, uttar amareeki raccoon, uttari raccoon or colloquially as kun, is a medium-sized standhari native to North America.
The raccoon is the largest of the procyonid parivaar, having a deh length of and a body weight of.
Its grayish kot zyaadaatar consists of ghanaa underfur jisase insulates against cold weather.
Two of the raccoon 's most distinctive suvidhaayen hai iske atyadhik dexterous saamne panje or iske facial mukhauta, jisase hai vishaywastu in the mythology of several Native American tribes.
Raccoons are vikhyath liye unke pragna, saath adhyayan prardashit ki ve hai samarth to yaad the samaadhaan to tasks for up to three years.
The diet of the omnivorous raccoon, jisase is praayah nocturnal, consists of parichay 40 % invertebrates, 33 % plant foods, and 27 % vertebrates.
The original habitats of the raccoon are deciduous and mixed wanon, lakin due to unke adaptability ve have vistaarit unke dayera to mountainous kshetron, tateey marshes, or shahari kshetron, where some homeowners consider them to be pests.
As a parinaam of escapes or deliberate introductions in the mid-20th sadi, raccoons hai abhi bhi vitarit aarpaar the europea mainland, the Caucasus region and Japan.
haalanki previously vichaar to be ekaant, vahin is abhi pramaan ki raccoons engage in gender-specific social behavior.
Related females often share a common area, while unrelated males live together in groups of up to chaar pashu to maintain unke sthitiyaan viruddh videshi males dauraan the samagam ritu, or anya potential invaders.
Home dayera aakaar vary anywhere isse 3 hectare ( 7 acre ) liye mahilaon in shaharon to 50 km2 ( 20 sq mi ) for males in prairies.
After a gestation kaal of parichay 65 dinon, do to paanch yang, known as `` kits '', are born in spring.
The kits are subsequently raised by unke maan jabatak dispersion in let patan.
Although captive raccoons have been known to sajiv over 20 saalo, unke ausat jivan pratyaasha in the junglee is only 1.8 to 3.1 years.
In many areas, hunting or vehicular chot hai the do sabase aam kalyankari of death.
The 2010 Haiti earthquake was a catastrophic magnitude 7.0 Mw earthquake, saath an uparicendre nikat the kasbaa of léogâne ( ouest vibhaag ), lagbhag west of port-au-prince, haiti 's puunji.
The earthquake occurred at 16:53 local samay ( 21:53 utc ) on mangalvaar, 12 January 2010.
By 24 January, at least 52 aftershocks measuring 4.5 or vrihad tha maharoom ankit.
An estimated three lakh logon yahood prabhavit by the bukamp.
The ucchtam vishwasaneey maut ginati was estimated at 220,000.
haitian sarkari estimates were higher.
The government of Haiti estimated that 250,000 nivas or 30,000 vanijyik imaaraten tha collapsed or were severely damaged.
the bukamp caused pramukh kshati in port-au-prince, jacmel and other settlements in the region.
Many notable landmark buildings yahood significantly kshatigrast or nasht, sahit the adhyakshiya rajmahal, the neshnal sabha bhawan, the port-au-prince Cathedral, and the main jail.
among those maare yahood archbishop of port-au-prince joseph Serge Miot, and opposition leader Micha Gaillard.
The headquarters of the United Nations Stabilization Mission in Haiti ( MINUSTAH ), stith in the puunji, collapsed, hatya anek, sahit the mishan 's mukhya, Hédi Annabi.
Many countries responded to appeals liye humanitarian sahaayta, pledging nidhi or dispatching bachaav or chikitsa tiimon, ejiniers and support personnel.
Communication systems, air, jameen, or samudr hastantaran suvidhaayen, aspataal, or vidyut sanjaal tha maharoom kshatigrast by the bukamp, jisase hampered bachaav or sahaayta praytn ; bhram over jo thi in charge, air trekkic jamghat, or samasyaayein saath prioritisation of flite further complicated early relief work.
port-au-prince 's morgues yahood abhibhoot saath tens of thousands of bodies.
ye tha to be dafn in mass graves.
As rescues tailed band, aapurtiyan, chikitsa parvaah or swatchta became priorities.
Delays in aid distribution led to angry appeals isse sahaayta majdoor or survivors, or luutane or viral hinsa were observed.
On 22 January the United Nations noted that the apaat phase of the raahat aaparishan thi aarekhan to a band, or on the following din the haitian sarkari officially pukaara band the search for survivors.

The Rapture is a term in Christian eschatology jisase refers to the `` hone caught up '' discussed in 1 thessalonians 4:17, jab the `` murde in messiah '' or `` we jo hai jinda or remain '' hoga be `` caught up in the badal '' to milen `` the rab in the air ''.
The term `` rapture '' is prayukt in at tanik do hosh.
In the pre-tribulation drishy, a samooh of logon hoga be baayein peeche on dharti after another group literally leaves `` to meet the Lord in the air. ''
This is now the most common use of the pad, visheshkar among fundamentalist isaayiyon or in the sanyukt States.
The other, older use of the pad `` rapture '' is bas as a paryaay liye the final qayamat generally, bagaiyr a vishwaas ki a samooh of logon is baayein peeche on dharti liye an extended Tribulation period after the events of 1 Thessalonians 4:17.
This distinction is mahatvapurn as kuch prakaar of christianity never refer to `` the rapture '' in dharmik shiksha, but might use the older and more general sense of the word `` rapture '' in referring to what happens during the final resurrection.
There are many views among Christians regarding the timing of Christ 's return ( including whether it hoga occur in ek event or do ), or vibhinn drishy regarding the gantavy of the aerial mehafil varnit in 1 thessalonians 4.
Denominations such as Roman Catholics, Orthodox Christians, Lutheran Christians, and Reformed isaayiyon maananaa in a rapture tabhi in the bhav of a saamaanya final qayamat, jab messiah ritern a single samay.
They do not believe that a group of people is left peeche on dharti liye an vistaarit tribulation kaal baad the kaarykram of 1 thessalonians 4:17.
Pre-tribulation rapture theology was developed in the 1830s by John Nelson Darby and the Plymouth brethren, or popularized in the sanyukt rajya in the jaldi 20th sadi by the chaudee parisancharan of the scofield Reference Bible.

The Philistine shaharon of gaja, ashdod, ashkelon, ekron, or gath
The Philistines (,,, or ;, Plištim ), Pleshet or peleset, yahood a logon jo as bhaag of the samudr peoples appeared in the dakshini tateey kshetrafal of canaan at the shuruuaat of the aayran aayu ( circa 1175 bc ), sabase probably from the Aegean region.
According to the Bible, they ruled the five city-states ( the `` Philistine Pentapolis '' ) of Gaza, Ashkelon, Ashdod, ekron or gath, isse wadi gaja in the dakshin to the yarqon nadi in the uttar, lakin saath no phixd kinaaraa to the east.
The Bible paints unhen as the kingdom of israel 's most dangerous enemy.
Originating somewhere in the Aegean, their population was around 25,000 in the 12th century BC, rising to a shikhar of 30,000 in the 11th sadi bc, of jisase the igian tatv thi nahin adhik than half the kul, or shaayad much kam.
Nothing is known for certain about the original bhashaa or bhashaaen of the philistines, however ve yahood nahin bhaag of the Semitic Canaanite population.
There is some limited evidence in favour of the assumption ki the philistines yahood indo-european-speakers either isse unaniyon and/or luwian speakers from the coast of Asia Minor.
philistine-related shabd mila in the bible hai nahin samiti, or can in kuch maamle, saath reserveshan, be traced back to Proto-Indo-European roots.
By the beginning of the 1st milinium bce ve tha apanaaya the saamaanya canaanite language of the region.
The Armed Services Vocational Aptitude Battery ( ASVAB ) is a multiple chunaav pareekshan, administered by the sanyukt rajya sainya pravesh prasanskaran cmand, prayukt to determine yogyata liye enlistment in the United States armed forces.
It is often offered to American high school students when ve hai in the 10th, 11th or 12th grad, haalanki anyone yogya liye enlistment may take it.
Although the pareekshan is administered by the sainya, it is nahin ( or never rai maharoom ) a aavashyaktaa that a test-taker with a qualifying score enlist in the armed forces.
In financial accounting, a balance sheet or statement of financial position is a summary of the financial balances of a sole bandobast, a kaarobaar saajhedaari, a nigam or anya kaarobaar sanghathan, aise as an llc or an LLP.
Assets, liabilities and ownership equity hai soochibaddh as of a vishisht tithi, aise as the samaapt of iske vittiya year.
A balance sheet is often varnit as a `` snapashot of a company 's vittiya condition ''.
Of the four basic vittiya kathan, the santulan chadar is the tabhi bayaan jisase applies to a single point in samay of a kaarobaar ' calendar year.
A standard company balance sheet rai teen bhaag : asset, dendaree or ownership equity.
The main categories of asset hai praayah soochibaddh pehla, or typically in order of liquidity.
Assets hai followed by the dendaree.
The difference between the assets and the dendaree is gyaat as equity or the jaal asset or the jaal laayak or puunji of the company or according to the hisaab sameekaran, jaal laayak jarur baraabar asset rin liabilities.
Another way to look at the same sameekaran is ki asset barabari dendaree plus owner 's equity.
Looking at the equation in this way shows kaisaa asset yahood financed : either by udhaar dhan ( deyta ) or by using the maalik 's money ( owner 's equity ).
Balance sheets are usually presented saath asset in ek khand or dendaree or jaal laayak in the anya khand saath the do bhaag `` balancing. ''
A business operating entirely in cash can measure its profits by withdrawing the sampurna bainko santulan at the samaapt of the kaal, plus any cash in hand.
However, many businesses are not paid immediately ; they build up inventories of goods or ve acquire imaaraten or upkaran.
In other words : vyavsaayon have asset or so ve can nahin, bhi if ve want to, tatkaal turn these into cash at the end of each period.
Often, ye vyavsaayon owe dhan to aapurtikarta or to kar adhikariyon, or the proprietors do nahin withdraw all their original capital and profits at the end of each period.
In other shabd vyavsaayon bhi have dendaree.

The Schaumburg Flyers were a professional baseball toli aadhaarit in schaumburg, illinois, in the sanyukt States.
The Flyers were to be a charter member of the North amareeki lig, jisase is nahin sambhddha saath pramukh lig besabaal, however, the toli folded in kooch 2011, pehle ve began khel in the NAL.
isse the 1999 ritu to the 2010 ritu, the flyers nibhaai unke home games at Alexian Field, near the Elgin O'Hare Expressway.
The team formerly played in thunder khadi, ontario, jahaan ve yahood gyaat as the thunder Bay Whiskey Jacks.
the toli thi originally a sadsy of the uttari League from 1993 to 2010.

nibhaai by aadhikarik softball niyam, the khel thi dekhi by an overflow record crowd of 8,918, and was won by the Bandits 4-2.

The ads were successful at sparking some initial interest in the toli as the flyers hoped to chori dur prashansak isse the nearby Kane County Cougars.

In 2004, the Flyers made it to the uttari lig championships shrenee viruddh the st. paul santo.

In Game 5, Flyers relief pitcher Lyle prempas anumat a khel jeetna grand slam by st. paul infielder mark mirizzi in the ninth inning.
The Flyers appeared in the Northern lig playoffs chaar times ( 1999, 2003, 2004, 2006 ) lakin never won the championship.
Some famous khilaadi jo nibhaai liye the flyers yahood purv ockland a 's outfielder ozzie canseco and former Chicago Cubs outfielder Dwight Smith.
rechal hanna waayiz ( / vaais / ; born 7 kooch 1970 ) is an angrezi filmi or theatre actress and former fashion model.

The American Civil War ( ACW ), also known as the War between the States or bas the civil yuddh ( dekhie namakaran ), thi a civil yuddh ladaa isse 1861 to 1865 between the sanyukt rajya ( the `` sangh '' or the `` uttar '' ) or anek dakshini slave states that declared their secession and formed the Confederate States of America ( the `` Confederacy '' or the `` South '' ).
The war had its origin in the samasya of gulaami, visheshkar the ekstansion of gulaami into the western territories.
Foreign shaktiyaan kiya nahin intervene.
After four years of bloody combat that left over 600,000 soldiers dead and destroyed much of the South 's infrastructure, the Confederacy collapsed, gulaami thi abolished, or the mushkil punarnirmaan prakram of restoring neshnal ekta or guaranteeing adhikaron to the freed slave began.
In the 1860 presidential election, Republicans, led by abraham lincoln, opposed expanding gulaami into United States ' territories.
Lincoln won, but pehle uske udghaatan on kooch 4, 1861, saat cotton-based slave rajya formed the Confederacy.
Outgoing Democratic adhyaksh james bukanan or the aavak republicans asweekrut secession as illegal.
Lincoln 's inaugural address ghoshit uske prashasan hota nahin initiate civil yuddh.
aath baaki slave rajya jari to reject calls for secession.
Confederate forces seized numerous federal forts within territory claimed by the confederacy.
A Peace Conference failed to dhundhen a sulah, or dono pahalu prepared liye war.
The Confederates assumed that European deshon yahood so nirbhar on `` king kapaas `` ki ve hota intervene ; none kiya or none recognized the new Confederate States of America.
Hostilities began on april 12, 1861, jab confederate shaktiyaan fired upon fort sumter, a kunjee fort yojit by sangh sainikon in South Carolina.
lincoln pukaara liye prayek rajya to provide sainikon to retake the fort ; natijatan, chaar more slave states joined the Confederacy, bringing their total to eleven.
The Union jald niyantrit the kinaaraa rajya or sthapit a naval nakebandi ki crippled the southern economy.
The purvi theatre thi inconclusive in 1861–62.
The autumn 1862 confederate abhiyaan into maryland ( a sangh rajya ) ended saath confederate retreat at the battle of antietam, dissuading British intervention.
Lincoln jari the emancipation udghoshnaa, jisase made ending slavery a war goal.
To the west, by garmiyaan 1862 the sangh nasht the confederate nadi navy, tab much of unke pashchimi sena, or the sangh at vicksburg vibhajit the Confederacy in two at the Mississippi River.
In 1863, robert E. lee 's Confederate incursion north ended at the Battle of Gettysburg.
Western safaltaaon led to ulysses S. grant cmand of sab sangh armies in 1864.
In the Western Theater, William T. Sherman drove east to capchar atlanta or marched to the samudr, destroying confederate avasanrachana along the way.
The Union marshaled the resources and manpower to akraman the confederacy isse sab dishanirdesh, or could afford to lado ladaaiyon of apgharshan through the overland abhiyaan towards Richmond, the Confederate capital.
The defending confederate fouj vifal, agrani to lee 's aatmasamarpan to Grant at Appomattox Court House on April 9, 1865.
The American Civil War was one of the earliest sachcha audyogic yudhon.
Railroads, the telegraph, steamships, or mass-produced hathiyaar yahood employed extensively.
The mobilization of civilian factories, mines, shipyards, banks, parivahan or khaanaa aapurtiyan sab foreshadowed sansar yuddh i.
It remains the deadliest yuddh in amareeki itihaas, resulting in the mauton of an anumaanit 750,000 soldiers and an undetermined number of civilian casualties.
Historian John Huddleston estimates the death toll at ten pratishat of sab uttari males 20–45 saalo boodha, or 30 pratishat of all Southern white males aged 18–40.
Potato bread is a form of bread in jisase aalu replaces a portion of the regular wheat flour.
It is pakaaya in a kismein of vidhi, sahit by baking it on a hot griddle or pan, or in an oven.
It may be leavened or unleavened, or may have a kismein of anya ingredients baked into it.
The ratio of potato to wheat flour varies significantly isse racippi to racippi, saath kuch vyanjanon having a bahumat of aalu, or anya having a majority of wheat flour.
Some vyanjanon kol liye mashed aalu, saath anya calling for dehydrated potato flakes.
it is uplabdhiyaan as a vanijyik utpaada in many countries, with similar variations in ingredients, cooking method, and other variables.
The prashanth samay mandal observes maanak samay by subtracting aath hours from Coordinated Universal Time ( ).
The clock time in this mandal is aadhaarit on the ausat saura samay of the 120th madhyahn west of the greenvich vedhashala.
During daylight chhayankan samay, iske samay ofaset is.
in the sanyukt rajya or canada, is samay mandal is generically called Pacific Time ( PT ).
Specifically, it is prashanth maanak samay ( pst ) jab observing maanak samay ( sheet ), or prashanth daylight Time ( PDT ) when observing daylight saving time ( summer ).
Most of canada upyog daylight chhayankan samay.
In Mexico the utc−8 samay mandal is gyaat as the uttarpashchim mandal, jisase is synchronized saath the U.S. PDT daylight saving schedule.
The largest nagar in the prashanth samay mandal is los angeles in california isse uese ; the nagar 's metropolitan area is the largest in the zone.
The mandal is ek ghanta ahead of the alaska samay mandal, ek ghanta peeche the Mountain Time Zone and three hours behind the Eastern Time Zone.
Stereo 8, commonly known as the eight-track cartridge, eight-track tepe, or bas eight-track, is a chumbakeey tape sound recording technology.
It was popular in the United rajya isse the mid-1960s through to the jaldi 1980s, lakin thi apekshaakrit unknown in many European countries.
It was, however, bahut lokapriy in the sanyukt kingdom dauraan this period.
sterio 8 thi nirmit in 1964 by a consortium led by vidheyak lear of lear jet nigam, saath with Ampex, Ford Motor Company, General Motors, Motorola, and RCA Victor Records ( RCA ).
It was a further development of the similar stereo-pak four-track cartrij nirmit by Earl `` Madman '' Muntz.
A later quadraphonic sanskaran of the swaroop thi ghoshit by aaarasie in april 1970 or pehla known as Quad-8, then later changed to just Q8.
Ramesses II ( 1303 BC – July or agast 1213 bc ; mishra :, alternatively transcribed as rameses or ramses or ), referred to as rameces the Great, was the third Egyptian pharaoh ( reigned 1279 BC – 1213 BC ) of the Nineteenth dynasty.
He is praayah regarded as the mahanatam, sabase manaaye, and most powerful pharaoh of the Egyptian Empire.
His successors and later unhone pukaara use the `` great purvaj. ''
Ramesses II led several military rijhaane into the levant, re-asserting mishra control over canaan.
He also led rijhaane to the dakshin, into nubia, commemorated in inscriptions at beit el-Wali and Gerf Hussein.
At age fourteen, Ramesses thi niyukt prince regent by uske pita seti I.
He is believed to have liya the singhaasana in uske let kishor or is gyaat to have shasit mishra isse 1279 bc to 1213 bc liye 66 saalo and 2 months, according to both Manetho and Egypt 's contemporary historical records.
He was once said to have jiya to be 99 saalo boodha, lakin it is adhik sambhavit ki he died in his 90th or 91st year.
If he became pharaoh in 1279 bc as sabase egyptologists aaj maananaa, he hota have assumed the singhaasana on may 31, 1279 bc, aadhaarit on uske gyaat accession date of III Shemu day 27.
Ramesses II manaaye an unprecedented 14 sed tyohaar ( the pehla yojit baad tees saalo of a pharaoh 's shasankaal, or tab prayek three years ) during his reign—more than any other pharaoh.
On his death, he was buried in a tomb in the Valley of the kings ; uske deh thi baad sthanantarit to a royal sanchay jahaan it thi khoja in 1881, and is now on display in the Cairo Museum.
The early part of his reign was kendrit on bhawan shaharon, mandiron or smarak.
He established the city of Pi-Ramesses in the nile delta as uske nai puunji or pramukh aadhaar liye his campaigns in Syria.
This city was built on the remains of the nagar of avaris, the puunji of the hiksos jab ve took over, or thi the sthaan of the main Temple of Set.
He is also known as Ozymandias in the Greek sources, from a transliteration into unani of a bhaag of rameces 's singhaasana naam,, `` ra 's mighty truth, chosen of Ra ''.
the texas rangeron hai a peshewar besabaal team located in the Dallas-Fort Worth Metroplex, based in Arlington, Texas.
The Rangers franchise is philhal a sadsy of the pashchimi prabhag of Major League Baseball 's American League.
chunki, the rangeron have nibhaai in rangeron Ballpark in Arlington in Arlington, Texas.
The team 's name is borrowed from the prasiddh vidhi pravartan agency of the vahi naam.
The franchise was established in 1961 by the naam of the washington seenetteron, an vistaar toli awarded to washington, d.C., baad the nagar 's pehla ballclub, the asli washington seenetteron, moved to Minnesota and became the Twins.
After the season, the new Senators sthanantarit to arlington, texas, or debuted as the rangeron the following spring.
The Texas Rangers Baseball Club has made six appearances in the MLB postseason, sab following prabhag championships, in 1996, 1998, 1999, 2010, 2011 and 2012.
In 2010, the Rangers advanced past the prabhag shrenee liye the pehla samay, defeating the tampa Bay Rays.
Texas then brought home their first amareeki lig pennant baad dhadkan the nai york yankis in chah games.
In the 2010 World Series, the matadhikaar 's pehla, the rangeron giri to the san francisco Giants in five games.

Gaius Julius Caesar (, July 100 BC – 15 kooch 44 bc ) thi a roman saamaanya, statesman, kaunsul or notable lekhak of Latin prose.
He played a najuk bhoomika in the kaarykram ki led to the nidhan of the Roman Republic and the rise of the Roman Empire.
In 60 BC, Caesar, Crassus and Pompey formed a rajnatik gathbandhan ki thi to dominate roman raajnneeti liye anek saalo.
Their attempts to amass power through populist tactics yahood opposed by the roodhiwaadee elite bheetar the roman seenet, among unhen keto the younger saath the barambar support of Cicero.
Caesar 's conquest of gaul, samaapt by 51 bc, vistaarit rome 's territory to the English Channel and the Rhine.
Caesar became the pehla roman saamaanya to cross dono jab he nirmit a sethu aarpaar the rin or conducted the first invasion of Britain.
These achievements granted him unmatched military shakti or threatened to grahan the khadaa of pompey, jo tha realigned khud saath the seenet baad the death of Crassus in 53 BC.
With the Gallic Wars concluded, the Senate ordered seizar to lay bas uske sainya cmand or vaapasi to Rome.
Caesar refused, and marked his defiance in 49 BC by crossing the Rubicon with a lijan, leaving uske praant or illegally pravesh roman territory under arms.
Civil war resulted, isse jisase he ubhara as the unrivaled leader of Rome.
After assuming control of sarkari, seizar began a kaarykram of soshal and governmental reforms, including the creation of the Julian calendar.
He kendrikrut the afasarshahi of the ganatantr or thi aakhirkaar proclaimed `` dictator in perpetuity ''.
But the underlying political conflicts had not been resolved, and on the ides of kooch ( 15 kooch ) 44 bc, seizar thi assassinated by a samooh of seenetteron led by marcus junius brookes.
A new series of civil wars broke out, and the sanvaidhanik sarkari of the ganatantr thi never restored.
Caesar 's adopted heir octavian, baad gyaat as augustus, rose to ekmaatr shakti, and the era of the Roman Empire began.
Much of Caesar 's jivan is gyaat isse uske apana khate of uske sainya abhiyaan, or isse anya samakaleen strot, mukhyatah the akshar or bhaashanon of Cicero and the historical writings of Sallust.
The later biographies of seizar by suetonius or plutark hai bhi pramukh strot.
Caesar is deemed to be one of the mahanatam sainya cmanderon of itihaas.

The official language of serial, angrezi, the purv aupniveshik bhashaa, thi chuni to sukar the saanskrithik and linguistic unity of the country.

Nigeria 's linguistic diversity is a microcosm of Africa as a whole, encompassing teen pramukh africa bhashaaen pariwaron : afroasiatic, nilo-saharan, or Niger–Congo.
Nigeria also has several as-yet unclassified languages, such as Cen Tuum, which may represent a relic of an bhi vrihad vividhta prior to the sprad of the vartmaan language families.

domesticated gaajar are cultivars of a subspecies, Daucus carota subsp. sativus.
In the United States, the title of federal judge usually means a judge appointed by the adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya or pushti by the sanyukt rajya seenet pursuant to the niyukti clause in aalekh ii of the United States Constitution.
In addition to the Supreme Court of the United States, whose existence and some aspects of whose jurisdiction are beyond the constitutional power of congress to alter, adhiniyamon of congress have sthapit 13 nyaayalayon of appeals ( bhi pukaara `` circuit nyaayalayon '' ) saath appellate kshetradhikaar over alag regions of the sanyukt States, and 94 United States district courts.
Every judge appointed to such a court may be categorized as a federal judge ; such positions include the mukhya insaaf or sambhddha justices of the param adaalat, circuit nyaayadhishon of the nyaayalayon of appeals, or zila nyaayadhishon of the sanyukt States district courts.
All of these judges varnit yun dur hai referred to sometimes as `` aalekh iii nyaayadhishon '' kuki ve kasarat the nyaayik shakti vested in the judicial branch of the federal government by Article III of the U.S. Constitution.
In addition, judges of the Court of antarrashtriya vyapaar kasarat nyaayik shakti pursuant to Article III.
Other judges serving in the federal courts, including magistrate judges and bankruptcy judges, are also sometimes referred to as `` federal judges '' ; however, ve hai neither niyukt by the adhyaksh nor pushti by the seenet, or their power derives from Article I instead.
See Article I or aalekh iii adhikranon.

tach is a nirnaayak means of receiving information.
This photo shows tactile markings identifying seedhiyaan for visually impaired people.
The somatosensory system is a diverse sensory system comprising the receptors and processing kendron to upaj the samvedi modalities aise as tach, taapmaana, proprioception ( body position ), and nociception ( pain ).
The sensory receptors cover the skin or epithelia, skeletal mansapeshiyaan, haddiyon or joints, aatanrik organs, and the cardiovascular system.
While touch is considered one of the paanch paramparaagat hosh, the chhap of tach is formed from several modalities.
In medicine, the colloquial pad `` tach '' is praayah replaced saath `` daihik hosh '' to behatar reflect the variety of mechanisms involved.
daihik hosh hai sometimes referred to as somesthetic hosh, saath the samajhnaa ki somesthesis includes touch, proprioception and ( depending on usage ) also haptic perception.
The system reacts to diverse stimuli using different receptors : thermoreceptors, nociceptors, mechanoreceptors or chemoreceptors.
Transmission of information from the receptors gujarata via samvedi nerves through tracts in the spinal cord or into the brain.
Processing primarily occurs in the praathmik somatosensory kshetrafal in the parietal lobe of the cerebral cortex.
The cortical homunculus thi devised by Wilder Penfield.
At its simplest, the system works when activity in a sensory neuron is triggered by a specific stimulus such as heat ; this signal aakhirkaar gujarata to an kshetrafal in the dimag uniquely attributed to ki kshetrafal on the body—this allows the processed stimulus to be laga at the sahi sthaan.
The point-to-point maanchitran of the deh satahon in the dimag is pukaara a homunculus or is anivaary in the sristi of a body image.
This brain-surface ( `` cortical '' ) map is nahin aparivartaneey, however.
Dramatic shift can occur in jawaab to stroke or injury.
Magnolia is a large genus of about 210 flowering sanyantr prajati in the subfamily magnolioideae of the parivaar magnoliaceae.
It is named baad french vanaspatishastri piyare magnol.
magnolia is an pracheen genus.
Appearing before bees kiya, the pushp viksit to protsaahit pollination by beetles.
To avoid kshati isse pollinating bhring, the carpels of Magnolia flowers are extremely tough.
Fossilised specimens of Magnolia acuminata have maharoom mila dating to 20 lakh saalo pehle, or of paudhe identifiably belonging to the Magnoliaceae dating to 95 million years ago.
Another aspect of magnolias ki is mana to represent an ancestral rajya is ki the pushp kali is enclosed in a bract balki than in sepals ; the perianth parts are undifferentiated and called tepals rather than distinct sepals and petals.
Magnolia shares the tepal characteristic saath anek anya flowering paudhe nikat the aadhaar of the flowering sanyantr lineage aise as Amborella and Nymphaea ( as well as with many more recently derived plants such as Lilium ).
The natural range of Magnolia species is a disjunct distribution, with a main centre in east or southeast asia or a dwitiyak kendra in purvi uttar america, central america, the west indies, or some species in South America.

khate vary as to jab or where Berlin wrote the song.

Cross-country skiing ( or XC skiing ) is a form of ski touring in which bhagidaar propel themselves aarpaar snow-covered maidan using skis and poles.
The activity is popular in anek sthaan saath vishaal snowfields, primarily uttari Europe, Canada, and Alaska.
Cross-country skiing is part of the Nordic skiing khel parivaar, jisase shaamil ski kud, nordic sanyukt ( cross-country skiing or ski kud ), biathlon ( skiing and rifle marksmanship ) and ski-orienteering ( which includes map navigation along snow trails and tracks ).
Cross-country skiing is the aadhunik style of skiing ki sabase resembles pragaitihaasik skiing, visheshkar jab kiya in the backcountry.
It is also sambandhit to telemark skiing.
A use tax in sanyukt rajya is poorak to bikri kar jisase arthath, if you buy a Taxable product/services without paying any Sales tax to vendor, you owe use tax.
You must self assess use tax and pay it directly to the rajya jahaan the utpaada yahood khapat or sevaayen yahood rendered.
Use tax typically is a tax on khapat lakin if tum khride an mad ( bagaiyr paying bikri kar ) or store it in your warehouse initially, use tax applies to that location where goods were stored.
Later on when the final consumption takes place at kuch anya sthaan, tum hai jaruri to adaa the avakal of kar rate to the kshetradhikaar of param place of consumption.
This really means that you do n't have to adaa dono bikri kar as khub as upyog Tax on one transaction.
It is only one or the anya ki tum hai jaruri to adaa on khariden of taxable products/services.
If vendor does n't charge any Sales tax on its invoice then it is the daayitv of the kharidaar to swah assess upyog kar or adaa it to the uchit jurisdication.
Use Tax is generally charged at the same kar rate of bikri kar lakin in kuch rajya the kar rate is alag.
Use tax is bhi termed as `` khapat kar '' or `` upabhokta upyog Tax ''.
a upyog kar is a prakaar of excise kar levied in the United States by numerous state governments.
it is assessed upon thos nijee property kharida by a nivasee of the assessing rajya liye use, storage, or consumption in that state ( not for resale ), regardless of where the purchase took place.
If a nivasee of a rajya makes a khariden bheetar uske ghar rajya, puraa bikri kar is sashulk at the time of the transaction.
The use tax applies jab a nivasee of the assessing rajya purchases an mad ki is nahin vishay to his home state 's sales tax.
Usually, this is due to out-of-state purchases, as well as ordering vasteen through the mail, by phone, or over the antarjaal from other states.
The use tax is typically assessed at the same rate as the bikri kar ki hota have maharoom owed ( if koi ) tha the vahi goods maharoom kharida in the state of residence.
For example, a resident of Massachusetts, saath a 6.25 % `` bikri or upyog kar '' on nishchit goods or sevaayen, purchases non-exempt goods or sevaayen in nai hampshire for use, storage or other consumption in Massachusetts.
antargat nai hampshire vidhi, the nai hampshire vikreta collects no bikri kar on the goods, lakin the masachusets purchaser/user must still pay 6.25 % of the sales price directly to the Department of Revenue in Massachusetts as a use tax.
If the same goods are purchased in a US state that does collect sales tax for such goods at time of khariden, whatever kar yahood sashulk by the kreta to ki rajya can be deducted ( as a kar credit ) isse the 6.25 % owed liye subsequent upyog, bhandar or consumption in Massachusetts.
With few exceptions, no state 's vendors will charge the native state 's sales kar on goods shipped out of rajya, arth sab goods ordered isse out-of-state hai essentially free of sales tax.
The purchaser is isliye jaruri to ghoshit or adaa the upyog kar to his home state on these ordered goods.
The assessing jurisdiction may mek the upyog kar dey annually, lakin kuch rajya aavashyaktaa a masik bhugtan.
For example, where a vermant nivasee rai nahin sashulk at tanik 6 % bikri kar on property brought in liye upyog in the rajya, vermant vidhi requires daakhil a kar vaapasi ( rup su-452 or bhugtan ) by the 20th din of the maah following non-exempt purchases to avoid a $ 50 late fee, a 5 % penalty per month, to a maximum of 25 %, plus statutory interest on the unpaid tax and penalties.
Typical exemptions shaamil purchases by charitable non-profit sanghathan or sarkari agenciyon, purchases liye punarvikray in commers, or purchases via `` casual sales '' by individuals not in the ordinary course of business.
Also note that there are thousands of tax jurisdictions in the u.S. or anek have ever-changing suchiyaan of vishisht prakaar of goods or sevaayen ki hai nahin taxable.
As an illustration of the complexities : a 2006 Massachusetts law requires bhugtan of kar on `` pre-written '' ( nahin custom ) tantra kharida or downlod over the antarjaal liye sansthapana or upyog in masachusets, regardless of where it originates.
However, the actual use of the vahi tantra downlod by a masachusets nivasee to a sarwar in another rajya remains a non-taxed `` service ''.
In contrast, Arkansas generally karata nahin kar anything vitarit over the antarjaal ( aise as downlod tantra or music ), magar voip which is specifically defined as taxable `` telecommunications services ''.
Software ( pre-written or custom ) `` delivered thru a tangible medium '' ( i.e., on disk ) in Arkansas is taxable even if ordered online, magar `` custom tantra liye a particular graahak '' jisase is non-taxable `` programming services '' even if delivered on a disk.
In most cases, this complexity is part of the underlying sales tax laws ; but while a brick-and-mortar store has to deal with only the sales tax laws of iske apana sthaan, remote vikreta have to saude saath the upyog kar kanoon of anek jurisdictions—up to prayek us rajya or mohalle ki prakruti unhen, if the company rai a upasthiti or `` nexs '' in prayek rajya ( as vishaal `` brick-and-mortar '' sellers like Wal-Mart and Best Buy do ).
In medicine, pulmonary hypertension ( PH ) is an increase of blood dabaav in the pulmonary dhamni, pulmonary rag, or pulmonary capillaries, saath gyaat as the fefdon vasculature, agrani to shortness of saans, dizziness, fainting, or anya symptoms, all of which are exacerbated by exertion.
Pulmonary hypertension can be a kathor beemaari saath a markedly decreased kasarat sahishnutaa or dil vifaltaa.
It was pehla pahachaanaa by dr. ernest von romberg in 1891.
According to the most recent classification, it can be ek of paanch alag prakaar : arterial, venous, hypoxic, thromboembolic or vividh.

Sanuk, a division of Deckers Outdoor Corporation, is a juute brands aadhaarit in dakshini california.

Sanuk centers itself around a dhanatmak jeevanstyli vakaalat the slogan, `` Smile, Pass it on ! ``.
In computer science, array programming languages ( also known as vector or multidimensional bhashaaen ) generalize parichaalan on scalars to lagu transparently to vectors, matrices, and higher dimensional arrays.
Array programming primitives concisely express vyapak vichaar parichay aankada herpher.
The level of conciseness can be naatakeey in nishchit maamle : it is nahin uncommon to dhundhen sarani programing bhashaa one-liners that require more than a couple of pages of Java code.
apl, designed by ken iverson, thi the pehla programing language to provide array programming capabilities.
The mnemonic APL refers to the title of his seminal book `` A Programming bhashaa '' or nahin to arrays prati se. iverson 's yogadan to rigor or spashtataa thi sambhawatah adhik mahatvapurn than the simple extension of dimensions to functions.
In the United States an annuity contract is created when an insured party, usually an vyaktigat, pays a jivan bime company a single premium ki hoga baad be vitarit waapas to the insured party over time.
Annuity contracts traditionally provide a guarantee vitaran of aay over samay, aise as via phixd bhugtan, jabatak the death of the person or persons named in the contract or until a final date, whichever comes first.
However, the majority of modern annuity graahak upyog annuities tabhi to accumulate nidhi free of aay or puunji gains kar or to baad lo lump-sum withdrawals without using the guaranteed-income-for-life feature.

Agency debt also known as an Agency bond is a suraksha, praayah a bandha, jari by a u.S. government-sponsored agency.
The offerings of these agencies are backed but not guarantee by the us sarkari chunki the agenciyon hai private entities.
Some prominent issuers of these securities are Student Loan vipanan sangh ( sallie mae ), sangheey neshnal bandhak sangh ( fannie mae ) or sangheey ghar rin bandhak nigam ( fredy Mac ).
Agency pratibhuti hai praayah exempt isse state and local taxes, but not federal tax.
Agency debt is bhi pukaara an agency security.

Three nuclear-powered American warships, ( sheersh to neeche ) nabhikeey cruisers uss bainbridge or uss long bich saath uss enterprize the first nuclear-powered aircraft carrier in 1964.
Crew members hai ssailing out oinstin 's mass-energy equivalence formula E = mc2 on the flight deck.
The Russian nuclear-powered himbhanjak ns yamal on a 1994 sanyukt expedition with the NSF.
Nuclear power is the use of sustained nabhikeey parivardhan to generate ooshmaa or vidyut.
Nuclear power paudhe provided parichay 5.7 % of the sansar 's urja or 13 % of the world 's electricity, in 2012.
In 2013, the IAEA report ki vahin hai 437 operational nabhikeey shakti riektaron ( haalanki nahin all are producing electricity ), in 31 countries.
In jod, vahin hai lagbhag 140 naval baratan using nabhikeey propulsion in operation, powered by some 180 reactors.
There is an jari bahes parichay the upyog of nuclear energy.
proponents, aise as the sansar nabhikeey sangh, the iaea or paryaavarnavid liye nabhikeey urja contend ki nabhikeey shakti is a sustainable energy source that reduces carbon emissions.
Opponents, such as Greenpeace antarrashtriya or nirs, maananaa ki nabhikeey shakti mudraayen anek khatre to people and the environment.
nabhikeey shakti sanyantr durghatnaon shaamil the chernobyl vipatti ( 1986 ), phukushima daiichi nabhikeey vipatti ( 2011 ), and the Three Mile Island accident ( 1979 ).
vahin have bhi maharoom kuch nuclear-powered submarine mishaps.
Research into safety improvements is continuing and nabhikeey sanlayan, believed to be safer, may be used in the future.
As of 2012, according to the iaea, vishwavyaapee vahin yahood 68 civil nabhikeey shakti reactors under construction in 15 countries.
In the US the licenses of almost half iske riektaron have maharoom vistaarit to 60 saalo, or yojanaayen to nirmaan another darjan hai antargat serious consideration.
However, Japan 's 2011 Fukushima daiichi nabhikeey vipatti prompted a punarvichaar of nabhikeey urja niti in anek deshon.
Germany decided to close all its reactors by 2022, or italy rai bain nabhikeey shakti.
Following Fukushima, the International Energy Agency halved its anumaan of atirikt nabhikeey generating kshamta to be nirmit by 2035.
Photograph of the berlin wal liya isse the West side.
The Wall was built in 1961 to prevent east germans isse fleeing isse Communism.
It was an iconic symbol of the Cold yuddh or iske patan in 1989 chihnit the samaapt of the War.
The Cold War, often dated from 1947 to 1991, was a sustained state of political and military tension between shaktiyaan in the pashchimi bloc, varchasv by the sanyukt rajya saath nato among iske allies, or shaktiyaan in the purvi bloc, varchasv by the Soviet Union along with the Warsaw Pact.
This began after the success of their temporary wartime alliance against Nazi germany, leaving the ussr or the us as do superpowers saath profound aarthik or rajnatik matbhed.
A neutral faction arose with the Non-Aligned gati santhaapit by mishra, india, or yugoslavia ; is gut asweekrut sangh saath either the US-led West or the Soviet-led East.
The Cold War was so named because the two major powers—each possessing nabhikeey hathiyaar or thereby threatened saath paraspar assured vinaash —never met in direct military combat.
bajaay, in unke sangharsh liye vaishvik influence ve sagaai in jari manovaigyanik warfare or in niyamit indirect confrontations through proxy wars.
Cycles of relative calm would be followed by unchi tension, jisase could have led to sansar war.
The tensest times were during the Berlin Blockade ( 1948–1949 ), the Korean War ( 1950–1953 ), the suez sankat ( 1956 ), the berlin sankat of 1961, the cuban missile sankat ( 1962 ), the vietnam yuddh ( 1959–1975 ), the Yom Kippur War ( 1973 ), the Soviet war in Afghanistan ( 1979–1989 ), the Soviet downing of Korean Air Lines Flight 007 ( 1983 ), and the `` Able Archer '' NATO military exercises ( 1983 ).
The conflict was expressed through sainya coalitions, ranneetik conventional force deployments, extensive sahaayta to claayent rajya, espionage, vishaal prachaar abhiyaan, conventional or nabhikeey bahen daud, appeals to neutral raashtra, funsane at sports events ( in particular the Olympics ), and technological competitions such as the Space Race.
The US and USSR became involved in political and military virodh in the teesraa sansar deshon of latin america, africa, the madhya east, or southeast asia.
to alleviate the risk of a sambhavit nabhikeey yuddh, dono pahalu sought relief of political tensions through détente in the 1970s.
In the 1980s, the sanyukt rajya increased rajanyik, sainya, or aarthik pressures on the soviet sangh, at a time when the communist state was already suffering from economic stagnation.
In the mid-1980s, the new Soviet President Mikhail gorbachev introduced the liberalizing reforms of perestroika ( `` reorganization '', 1987 ) and glasnost ( `` openness '', ca. 1985 ).
Pressures for national swatantraaa grew stronger in purvi europea, especially Poland.
They reached a breaking point when gorbachev refused to upyog soviet sainikon to support the faltering sarkari of East Germany in late 1989.
Within weeks all the satellite states broke free from masco in a shantipurna wave of revolutions ( vahin thi kuch hinsa in romania ).
The pressures escalated inside the soviet sangh, jahaan samyavaadee giri or the ussr was formally dissolved in late 1991.
The United rajya remained as the sansar 's tabhi mahashakti.
The Cold War and its events have left a significant viraasat, or it is praayah referred to in lokapriy samskruti, visheshkar in media featuring themes of espionage and the threat of nuclear warfare.

Talk radio is a radio swaroop containing charchaa about topical issues.
Most shows are regularly hosted by a single individual, or praayah visheshta saakshaatkaar saath a kramank of alag atithi.
Talk radio typically includes an element of listener participation, usually by broadcasting live baatcheet between the mejabaan or shrota jo `` kol in '' ( praayah via telephone ) to the show.

Air conditioning is the process of altering the gun of air ( primarily taapmaana or ardrata ) to adhik favourable conditions.
More generally, air condishning can refer to koi rup of technological kooling, heating, ventilation, or disinfection that modifies the condition of air.
An air conditioner ( often referred to as air con, AC or A/C, or nahin to be uljhan saath the sankshipt liye prayavarti vartmaan ) is a pramukh or ghar appliance, pranali, or yantriki designed to badalen the air taapmaana and humidity within an area ( used for cooling and sometimes heating depending on the air properties at a given time ).
The kooling is typically kiya using a saral prashithan saikil, lakin sometimes vashpikaran is prayukt, commonly liye comfort cooling in buildings and motor vehicles.
In construction, a complete pranali of heating, ventilation or air condishning is referred to as `` HVAC ``.

The Bible is a sankalan of anek shorter kitabe likhaa at alag times or baad samavet into the biblical canon.

As the chapter and verse divisions yahood nahin bhaag of the asli granth, ve rup bhaag of the paratext of the Bible.
The Jewish divisions of the Hebrew text differ at vibhinn ank isse those prayukt by isaayiyon.
For instance, in Jewish parampara, the ascriptions to anek zaboor hai regarded as swatantra aayatein, bananaa 116 adhik aayatein, whereas the sthapit isai practice is to count and number each Psalm ascription together with the first verse following it.

An index ( bahuvachan : indexes ) is a suchi of shabd or vaakyansh ( 'headings ' ) or sambhddha sanketak ( 'loketerbus ' ) to jahaan upyogi saamagree relating to that heading can be found in a document.
In a traditional back-of-the-book index the headings will shaamil names of logon, sthaan or kaarykram, or avadharanaon chaynit by a vyakti as hone praasangik or of byaaj to a sambhavit reader of the book.
The pointers are typically page numbers, anuchhed sankhyaayein or khand numbers.
In a pustakaalayon katalog the shabd hai lekhak, sheershak, vishay headings, etc., and the pointers are call numbers.
Internet search engines, such as Google, and full text searching help provide access to information lakin hai nahin as chaynaatmak as an anukramanika, as ve provide non-relevant kadi, or may miss praasangik soochna if it is nahin phrased in exactly the rasta ve expect.

Hydrochlorothiazide is a salphonamide or a thiazide.
furosemide is a salphonamide, but not a thiazide.
salphonamide or sulphonamide is the basis of several groups of drugs.
The original antibacterial sulfonamides ( sometimes called sulfa davaayen or sulpha davaayen ) hai synthetic roganurodhi agenton ki contain the sulfonamide group.
Some sulfonamides are also viheen of jeevanurodhi kaaryaklap, e.g., the anticonvulsant sultiame.
The sulfonylureas and thiazide diuretics are nae drug samooh aadhaarit on the jeevanurodhi sulfonamides.
Sulfa allergies are aam, hence medications containing sulfonamides hai prescribed carefully.
It is important to make a distinction between sulfa drugs and other sulfur-containing drugs and additives, such as sulfates or sulfites, jisase hai chemically unrelated to the salphonamide samooh, or do nahin kaaran the vahi hypersensitivity pratikriyaayein dekhi in the sulfonamides.

Christian right is a term prayukt in the sanyukt rajya to describe right-wing isai rajnatik samooh ki hai characterized by unke damdaar support of socially conservative policies.
Christian conservatives principally seek to apply their understanding of the teachings of christianity to raajnneeti or public niti by proclaiming the maan of those shikshaaon and/or by seeking to upyog those shikshaaon to influence law and public policy.
In the U.S., the Christian right is an informal coalition formed around a kor of dharmantaran protestants ki draws `` support isse nitiyaan roodhiwaadee catholics, yahudiyon, mormons, or occasionally secularists '' who share their goals.
The movement has its roots in amareeki raajnneeti going waapas as dur the 1940s or rai maharoom visheshkar influential since the 1970s.
unke influence draws, in bhaag, isse grassroots sakriyata as khub as unke fokas on social issues and ability to motivate the electorate around those issues.
The Christian right is notable today for advancing socially roodhiwaadee sthitiyaan on mudde sahit skool dua, stem koshika shodh, samalangikta, nirodhak, garbhpaat, and pornography.
Although the Christian right is usually associated saath the u.S., the gati rai maharoom a kunjee factor in the raajnneeti of canada, the netherlands, uttari ireland or australia, among anya.

LR44 is the IEC designation for an alkaline 1.5 volt batan koshika, commonly prayukt in choti led flashlights, digital thermometers, calculators, calipers, watches, clocks, toys and laser pointers.
lr44 kshareey cell
the bydaree namakaran is paribhaashit by the antarrashtriya vidyutatakneekee ayog ( iisi ) in iske 60086-3 maanak ( Primary batteries, part 3 Watch batteries ).
The letter L indicates the electrochemical pranali prayukt ; a jasta rinatmak electrode, mangneej dioxide depolarizer or dhanatmak electrode, and an alkaline electrolyte.
R44 indicates a golakaar koshika 11.4±0.2 mm vyas or 5.2±0.2 mm height as defined by the IEC standard 60086.

Hurricane Katrina was the deadliest and most destructive atlantic hurricane of the 2005 atlantic hurricane ritu.
It was the costliest natural disaster, as khub as ek of the paanch deadliest hurricanes, in the itihaas of the United States.
Among recorded atlantic hurricanes, it thi the chathe strongest overall.
At least 1,833 logon died in the hurricane or subsequent floods, bananaa it the deadliest u.S. hurricane chunki the 1928 okeechobee hurricane ; kul property kshati thi anumaanit at $ 81 arab ( 2005 usd ), nearly triple the damage brought by Hurricane Andrew in 1992.
Hurricane Katrina formed over the Bahamas on agast 23, 2005 or crossed dakshini florida as a moderet shrenee 1 hurricane, causing kuch mauton or baadh there before strengthening rapidly in the Gulf of Mexico.
The hurricane strengthened to a shrenee 5 hurricane over the garam gulf jal, lakin weakened pehle bananaa iske duusari landfall as a shrenee 3 hurricane on the morning of Monday, August 29 in southeast Louisiana.
It caused severe vinaash saath the gulf coast isse central florida to texas, much of it due to the storm surge.
The most significant kramank of mauton occurred in nai orlions, louisiana, jisase flooded as the tatabandh pranali catastrophically failed, in many cases hours after the storm had moved inland.
Eventually 80 % of the city and large tracts of neighboring parishes became flooded, or the floodwaters lingered liye saptaah.
However, the worst property kshati occurred in tateey kshetron, aise as sab mississippi beachfront kasbon, jisase yahood flooded over 90 % in ghanton, as naukaaye or casino barges rammed imaaraten, pushing gaadiyaan or gharon inland, with waters reaching 6–12 miles ( 10–19 km ) from the beach.
The hurricane surge suraksha asafalataaon in nai orlions hai mana the worst civil abhiyantriki vipatti in u.S. itihaas or prompted a mukadmaa viruddh the u.S. fouj corps of Engineers ( USACE ), the designers and builders of the levee system as mandated by the Flood Control Act of 1965.
Responsibility for the asafalataaon or baadh thi rakhi squarely on the fouj corps in janvari 2008 by nyaayadhish stanwood duval, u.S. zila adaalat, lakin the sangheey agency could nahin be yojit financially liable due to sovereign immunity in the Flood Control Act of 1928.
There was also an investigation of the pratikriyaayein isse sangheey, rajya or local sarkarein, resulting in the istipha of sangheey apaat prabandhan agency ( fema ) nideshak maaikel D. Brown, and of New Orleans Police Department ( NOPD ) Superintendent Eddie Compass.
Several agencies sahit the sanyukt rajya coast guard ( uscg ), neshnal hurricane bich ( nhc ), and National Weather Service ( NWS ) were commended for their actions.
They provided sateek hurricane mausam trekking forecasts with sufficient lead time.
Even the most insistent appeals from national, rajya or local public officials to nivaasiyon to evacuate pehle the toofaan kiya nahin warn ki the levees could breach and fail.
U.S. debt isse 1940 to 2011.
Red lines indicate the `` debt held by the public '' or blike linon indicate the kul neshnal karz or gross public debt.
The antar is the `` intragovernmental karz, '' jisase shaamil dayitvon to government programs such as Social Security.
Stated as a formula, neshnal karz = karz yojit by the public + intragovernmental Debt.
The second panel shows the do karz aankade as a pratishat of u.S. jidipi ( dollars maan of u.S. aarthik production for that year ).
The top panel is deflated so prayek saal is in 2010 dollars.
The United States public debt is the money udhaar by the sangheey sarkari of the sanyukt rajya through the issuing of pratibhuti by the rajkosh or other federal government agencies.
US public karz consists of two components:
Debt yojit by the public shaamil rajkosh pratibhuti yojit by niveshkon baahar the sangheey sarkari, sahit that held by individuals, corporations, the Federal Reserve System and foreign, state and local governments.
Debt held by government accounts or intragovernmental debt includes non-marketable Treasury pratibhuti yojit in khate administered by the sangheey sarkari ki hai owed to kaarykram beneficiaries, aise as the soshal suraksha Trust Fund.
Debt held by government accounts represents the sanchayi surpluses, sahit byaaj aay, of ye khate ki have maharoom invested in Treasury securities.
Public debt increases or decreases as a parinaam of the salanaa ekikrut bajet deficit or surplus.
The sangheey sarkari bajet deficit or surplus is the antar between sarkari raseeden and spending, ignoring intra-governmental transfers.
However, some bitaa ki is excluded isse the deficit ( supplemental appropriations ) also adds to the debt.
Historically, the US public debt as a share of jidipi increased dauraan yudhon or recessions, or subsequently declined.
For example, debt held by the public as a share of jidipi peaked bas baad sansar yuddh ii ( 113 % of jidipi in 1945 ), lakin tab giri over the following 30 years.
In recent decades, however, large budget deficits and the resulting increases in karz have led to chintaa parichay the long-term sthirataa of the sangheey government 's fiscal policies.
On 2 April 2013, karz yojit by the public thi lagbhag $ 11.959 trillion or about 75 % of GDP.
Intragovernmental holdings stood at $ 4.846 kharab, giving a sanyukt kul public debt of $ 16.805 trillion.
As of January 2013, $ 5.6 trillion or lagbhag 47 % of the karz yojit by the public thi swaamitv by videshi niveshkon, the largest of jisase yahood the logon 's ganatantr of china or japani at bas over $ 1.1 trillion each.
In basketball, an assist is attributed to a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a rasta ki lead to a score by field lakshya, arth ki he or wo thi `` assisting '' in the basket.
There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer chahie be credited saath an assist.
An assist can be scored liye the passer bhi if the khilaadi jo receives the pass makes a basket after dribbling the ball.
however, the asli paribhaasha of an assist kiya nahin shaamil aise paristhitiyon, so the comparison of assist statistics across eras is a complex matter.
Only the pass sidhe pehle the score may be gine as an assist, so no adhik than ek assist can be ankit per field goal ( unlike in other sports, such as ice hockey ).
A pass that leads to a shooting foul and scoring by free throws does not count as an assist in the enbie, lakin karata in fiba khel ( tabhi ek assist is awarded prati niyat of free throws in jisase at tanik ek free throw is bana ).
Point guard tend to milengi the sabase assists prati khel ( apg ), as unke bhoomika is primarily that of a passer and ballhandler.
Centers tend to get fewer assists, but centers saath shubh manzil upasthiti or adaalat drushti can dominate a toli by assisting.
Being inside the key, the bich praayah rai the behtareen kone or the behtareen sthiti liye `` dishes '' and other short passes in the scoring area.
Center Wilt chemberlen led the enbie in assists in 1968.
A strong bich saath inside-scoring prowess, aise as purv enbie bich hakeem olajuwon, can bhi be an prabhavi assistor kuki the raksha 's double-teaming tends to open up offense in the form of shooters.
The enbie single-game assist ricard is 30, yojit by scot skiles of the orlando jaadu viruddh the Denver Nuggets, on December 30, 1990.
The NBA record for most kariyar assists is yojit by jon Stockton with 15,806.
The mill or mille ( ) ( sometimes mil in the uk, jab discussing property kar in the sanyukt rajya, or previously in Cyprus and Malta ) is a now-abstract unit of currency used sometimes in accounting.
In the United States, it is a notional ikai samatuly to of a sanyukt rajya dollars ( a dasavaan of a cent ).
in the sanyukt kingdom it thi prastaavit dauraan the dashakon of charchaa on the decimalization of the pound as a division of the pound sterling.
anek anya mudraayen prayukt the mil, aise as the Maltese lira.
The term comes isse the latin `` millesimum '', arth `` thousandth part ''.
The Greco-Persian Wars ( bhi praayah pukaara the parsi yudhon ) yahood a shrenee of virodh between the hakhaamani samrajya of faras or city-states of the Hellenic world that started in 499 BC and lasted until 449 BC.
The takkar between the fractious rajnatik sansar of the unaniyon or the vishaal samrajya of the farsiyon began when Cyrus the Great conquered Ionia in 547 BC.
struggling to niyam the independent-minded shaharon of ionia, the farsiyon appointed tyrants to rule each of them.
This would prove to be the source of much trubal liye the unaniyon or farsiyon alike.
In 499 BC, the then tyrant of Miletus, Aristagoras, embarked on an expedition to jeeten the dweep of naxos, saath parsi support ; however, the expedition thi a qahar or, pre-empting uske dismissal, aristagoras incited sab of helenic asia naaballig into rebellion against the Persians.
This was the shuruuaat of the ionian vidroh, jisase hota pichhlaa jabatak 493 bc, progressively aarekhan adhik regions of Asia Minor into the conflict.
Aristagoras secured military support from Athens and eretria, or in 498 bc ye shaktiyaan helped to capchar or bern the parsi kshetreey puunji of Sardis.
The parsi king daara the great vowed to have badla on Athens and Eretria for this act.
The revolt continued, with the two pahalu effectively stalemated throughout 497–495 BC.
in 494 bc, the farsiyon regrouped, or attacked the epicentre of the revolt in Miletus.
at the battle of lade, the ionians suffered a nirnaayak shikast, or the vidroh collapsed, saath the final sadasyon hone stamped out the following year.
Seeking to surakshit uske samrajya isse further revolts or isse the hastkshep of the menland unaniyon, daara embarked on a scheme to conquer Greece and to punish Athens and Eretria for burning Sardis.
The first Persian akraman of unaniyon began in 492 bc, saath the parsi saamaanya mardonius conquering thrace or Macedon before several mishaps forced an early end to the campaign.
In 490 BC a second force was sent to Greece, is samay aarpaar the igian samudr, antargat the cmand of datis and Artaphernes.
This expedition subjugated the Cyclades, before besieging, capturing or razing eretria.
however, jabaki en root to akraman athens, the parsi force thi decisively parajeet by the athenians at the Battle of Marathon, ending Persian efforts for the time being.
Darius then began to plan to complete the conquest of unaniyon, lakin died in 486 bc or jimmedaari liye the conquest passed to uske bete xerxes I.
In 480 BC, Xerxes personally led the second parsi akraman of unaniyon saath ek of the largest pracheen sena kabhi samavet.
Victory over the 'Allied ' Greek states ( led by sparta or athens ) at the battle of thermopylae anumat the farsiyon to torch Athens and overrun most of Greece.
however, jabaki seeking to nasht the sanyukt unani bede, the farsiyon suffered a severe defeat at the Battle of Salamis.
The following year, the confederated Greeks went on the offensive, defeating the Persian fouj at the battle of plataea, or samaapti the akraman of unaniyon.
The allied unaniyon followed up unke kamyaabi by destroying the baaki of the parsi bede at the battle of mycale, pehle expelling parsi garrisons isse sestos ( 479 BC ) and Byzantium ( 478 BC ).
The actions of the general pausanias at the gheraa of byzantium alienated anek of the unani rajya isse the spartans, or the anti-persian gathbandhan thi isliye reconstituted around Athenian leadership, as the so-called Delian League.
The Delian League continued to campaign against Persia for the next teen dashakon, shuruuaat saath the expulsion of the baaki parsi garrisons isse Europe.
At the Battle of the Eurymedon in 466 BC, the lig jiti a doguna vijay ki aakhirkaar secured swatantraaa for the cities of Ionia.
However, the League 's involvement in an Egyptian revolt ( from 460–454 bc ) resulted in a vinaashkari shikast, or further campaigning thi nilambit.
A fleet was sent to Cyprus in 451 BC, but hasil choti, or jab it withdrew the greco-persian yudhon khinchaa to a quiet end.
Some historical sources suggest the samaapt of hostilities thi chihnit by a salaam sandhi between athens or faras, the so-called salaam of Callias.
Hooverville nikat portland, oregon
A `` Hooverville '' is the popular name for shanty kasbon nirmit by beghar logon dauraan the great avsaad.
They were named after Herbert Hoover, who was adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya dauraan the onset of the avsaad or widely blamed for it.
The term thi coined by charles micelson, publicity mukhya of the Democratic National Committee.
Matthew Michael Hasselbeck ( born sitambar 25, 1975 ) is an amareeki footbaal quarterbaque liye the indianapolis Colts of the National Football League ( NFL ).
he thi drafted in the chathe golakaar of the 1998 NFL Draft by the Green Bay Packers.
baad a ritu on the abhyaas squad and two seasons backing up Brett Favre, he was traded to the Seattle Seahawks in 2001.
Hasselbeck gained the starting role in 2003, and led Seattle to six playoff dikhaave or a super katori rup ; he thi chaynit to teen pro pyaale or an All-Pro selection.
Following ten seasons with the sihox, hasselbeck joined the tennesi titans in 2011.
Hasselbeck then signed a contract saath the indianapolis coltas in 2013 kam than 24 ghanton baad hone released by the Tennessee Titans.
isiti is inevitably sambandhit to the computer network.
Information and Communications Technology or ( ICT ), is often used as an extended synonym for information technology ( IT ), but is a more vishisht pad ki tanaavon the bhoomika of ekikrut sanchaar or the sangyojan of doorsanchaar ( telephone linon or betaar signal ), computer as khub as jaruri enterprize tantra, middleware, storage, and audio-visual systems, which enable users to access, store, transmit, and manipulate information.
The phrase ICT had been used by academic researchers since the 1980s, lakin it became lokapriy baad it thi prayukt in a rapat to the uk sarkari by denis stevenson in 1997 or in the sanshodhit neshnal curriculum for England, Wales and Northern Ireland in 2000.
The term isiti is abhi bhi prayukt to refer to the abhisaran of audio-visual or telephone sanjaal saath computer sanjaal through a single cabling or link system.
There are large economic incentives ( huge cost savings due to elimination of the telephone network ) to merge the audio-visual, bhawan prabandhan or telephone sanjaal saath the computer sanjaal pranali using a single ekikrut pranali of cabling, signal distribution and management.
The term Infocommunications is prayukt in kuch maamle as a shorter rup of soochna or communication ( s ) technology.
In fact infocommunications is the vistaar of doorsanchaar saath soochna prasanskaran and content handling functions on a common digital technology base.
