a schematic prastutikaran of the plums kheer model of the anu ; in thomson 's ganitiya model the `` corpuscles '' ( or modern electrons ) were arranged non-randomly, in rotating rings
The current model of the sub-atomic dhaancha involves a ghanaa cendrak ghiri by a probabilistic `` cloud '' of electrons
The plum kheer model of the anu by J. J. thomson, jo khoja the electron in 1897, thi prastaavit in 1904 pehle the discovery of the atomic nucleus in order to add the electron to the atomic model.
In this model, the anu is rachit of electrons ( jisase thomson still pukaara `` corpuscles '', haalanki G. J. stoney tha prastaavit ki anu of vidyut be pukaara electrons in 1894 ) ghiri by a soup of positive charge to balance the electrons ' negative charges, like negatively charged `` plums `` surrounded by positively charged `` pudding ``.
the electrons ( as we jaan unhen aaj ) yahood vichaar to be positioned throughout the anu, lakin saath anek structures sambhavit liye positioning multiple electrons, particularly rotating rings of electrons ( see below ).
Instead of a soup, the atom was also sometimes kaha to have tha a `` badal '' of dhanatmak charge.
saath is model, thomson abandoned uske pehle `` nebular anu '' hypothesis in which the atom was composed of immaterial vortices.
Now, at least part of the anu thi to be rachit of thomson 's particulate rinatmak corpuscles, haalanki the baaki of the positively charged part of the atom remained somewhat nebulous and ill-defined.
The 1904 Thomson model thi disproved by the 1909 sunaharaa foil prayog of Hans Geiger and Ernest Marsden.
This was interpreted by arnest radarford in 1911
to imply a very small nucleus of the atom containing a very high dhanatmak charge ( in the maamla of sunaharaa, paryaapt to santulan parichay 100 electrons ), thus leading to the Rutherford model of the atom.
Although gold has an atomic number of 79, immediately after radarford 's paper appeared in 1911 antonius vine den broek bana the sahaj suzav ki atomic number is nuclear charge.
The padaarth jaruri prayog to decide.
Henry Moseley 's work showed experimentally in 1913 ( see Moseley 's law ) ki the prabhavi nabhikeey charge thi bahut band to the parmaanu kramank ( moseley mila tabhi ek ikai antar ), or moseley sanderbhit tabhi the papers of Van den Broek and Rutherford.
This work culminated in the solar-system-like ( lakin quantum-limited ) bohr model of the anu in the vahi saal, in jisase a cendrak containing an parmaanu kramank of dhanatmak charge is surrounded by an equal number of electrons in orbital shells.
bohr tha bhi prerit moseley 's work.
Thomson 's model was compared ( haalanki nahin by thomson ) to a angrejon mithai pukaara plums kheer, hence the name.
Thomson 's paper thi prakashit in the kooch 1904 sanskaran of the philosophical patrika, the agrani British science journal of the day.
In Thomson 's view :... the atoms of the elements consist of a number of negatively electrified corpuscles enclosed in a gola of vardi dhanatmak vidyutikaran,...
In is model, the electrons yahood free to ghurnan bheetar the blob or cloud of positive substance.
These orbits were stabilized in the model by the fact ki jab an electron sthanantarit dur isse the bich of the dhanatmak badal, it laga a larger jaal dhanatmak inward force, kuki vahin thi adhik saamagree of vipareet charge, inside its orbit ( see Gauss 's law ).
in thomson 's model, electrons yahood free to ghurnan in bajati jisase yahood further stabilized by interactions between the electrons, and spectra were to be accounted for by energy differences of different ring orbits.
Thomson attempted to make uske model khaataa liye kuch of the pramukh spectral linon gyaat liye some elements, but was not notably successful at this.
Still, Thomson 's model ( along saath a samaan saturnian ring model liye parmaanu electrons, bhi put aage in 1904 by nagaoka baad james clerk maxwell 's model of shani 's bajati ), yahood pehle harbingers of the later and more successful solar-system-like Bohr model of the atom.
theth strip of bekan.
bekan is a cured maance prepared from a pig.
It is first cured using large quantities of salt, either in a brine or in a shushk packing ; the parinaam is bhais bacon ( also known as green bacon ).
Fresh bacon may then be further dried for weeks or maheene in thanda air, or it may be boiled or smoked.
Fresh and sukhi bekan is typically pakaaya before eating.
boiled bekan is taiyaar to kha, as is kuch smoked bacon, but may be cooked further before eating.
Bacon is prepared isse anek alag katautee of meat.
It is usually made from side and back cuts of pork, except in the sanyukt rajya, jahaan it is lagbhag sadaa prepared isse pork pet ( typically referred to as `` streaky '', `` vasiy '', or `` American style '' outside of the US and Canada ).
the paksh kaaten rai adhik meat and less fat than the belly.
bekan may be prepared isse either of do pruthak waapas katautee : fatback, jisase is almost pure fat, and pork loin, which is very lean.
bacon-cured pork loin is gyaat as back bacon.
uncooked pork pet bekan strips.
Bacon may be eaten smoked, boiled, fried, baked, or grield, or prayukt as a naaballig sanghatak to flavor dishes.
Bacon is also used liye barding or larding roasts, visheshkar game, e.g. venison, pheasant.
The word is derived from the boodha unchi germany bacho, arth `` buttock '', `` ham '' or `` paksh of bekan '', and cognate with the Old French bacon.
In continental Europe, this part of the pig is usually not smoked like bacon is in the United States ; it is prayukt primarily in ghan ( lardons ) as a kooking sanghatak, valued dono as a sorce of mote or liye iske flavor.
In Italy, is is pukaara pancetta or is praayah pakaaya in choti ghan or parosa uncooked or thinly sliced as part of an antipasto.
Meat from other animals, such as beef, lamb, chicken, goat, or turkey, may bhi be kaaten, cured, or varanaa prepared to resemble bekan, or may bhi be referred to as `` bacon ''.
Such upyog is aam in kshetron saath significant Jewish and Muslim populations.
The USDA defines bacon as `` the cured belly of a swine carcass '' ; anya katautee or visheshtaayen jarur be separately yogya ( e.g., `` smoked pork loin bacon '' ).
For safety, bacon must be treated to prevent trichinosis, caused by Trichinella, a parasitic roundworm jisase can be nasht by heating, jamane, drying, or smoking.
Bacon is vishisht isse namak pork or ham by differences in the brine ( or dry packing ).
Bacon brine has added curing sanghatak, sabase notably sodium nitrite, or occasionally sodium nitrate or potacium nitrate ( saltapeter ) ; sodium ascorbate or erythorbate hai added to accelerate curing and stabilize color.
Flavorings such as bhura sugar or mapel hai prayukt liye some products.
If used, sodium polyphosphates hai added to improve sliceability or reduce spattering when the bacon is pan fried.
Today, a brine for ham, but nahin bekan, shaamil a vishaal raashi of sugar.
Historically, `` ham '' or `` bekan '' referred to alag katautee of maance ki yahood brined or packed identically, often together in the same barrel.
the karmchaaree ritairement aay suraksha adhinium of 1974 ( erisa ) (, samhitabaddh in bhaag at ) is a sangheey vidhi jisase establishes nunatam maanakon liye pension yojanaayen in nijee udyog or provides for extensive rules on the federal income tax effects of transactions associated with employee benefit plans.
ERISA thi enacted to protect the ruchi of karmchaaree laabh yojana bhagidaar and their beneficiaries by:
Requiring the disclosure of financial and other soochna concerning the yojana to beneficiaries ;
Establishing standards of conduct liye yojana fiduciaries ;
Providing for uchit remedies or abhigam to the sangheey courts.
ERISA is sometimes used to refer to the full deh of kanoon regulating karmchaaree laabh yojanaayen, jisase hai mila mukhyatah in the aatanrik Revenue Code and ERISA itself.
Responsibility for the interpretation and enforcement of ERISA is divided among the Department of Labor, the Department of the rajkosh ( visheshkar the aatanrik aay seva ), or the pension laabh guaranty nigam.
Illegal immigration to the sanyukt rajya is the adhinium of videshi nagarikon pravesh the sanyukt rajya, bagaiyr sarkari anumati or in ulanghan of sanyukt rajya rashtriyata vidhi, or rahakar pare the termination date of a visa, also in violation of the law.
A warning sign at the international boundary between the sanyukt rajya or canada in point roberts, washington.
A much different approach at the u.s.-mexico kinaaraa nikat el paso, Texas
The undocumented immigrant population of the United States in 2008 was estimated by the bich liye avrajan adhyayan to be parichay 11 lakh logon, bas isse 12.5 lakh people in 2007.
anya estimates dayera isse 7 to 20 million.
According to a 2005 Pew Hispanic Center report, 56 % of undocumented immigrants were from Mexico ; 22 % yahood isse anya latin amareeki deshon ; 13 % yahood isse asia ; 6 % yahood isse europea or canada ; or 3 % were from Africa and the rest of the world.
Alvin Independent skool zila is a skool zila aadhaarit in Alvin, Texas ( USA ).
Alvin ISD is a large suburban school district south of Houston in the samudaayon of elvin, manvel, pearland, hillcrest, rosharon, iova upnivesh, Liverpool, and Amsterdam.
AISD serves Pearland city 's rapidly growing pashchimi portion of the nagar sahit the nai vishaal master-planned samudaayon of chaaya creek ranch, dakshin kanta, and Southern Trails.
Alvin isd cover of jameen.
In human anatomy, the ulnar tantrika is a tantrika jisase ranon nikat the ulna bone.
the ulnar collateral snaayu of kohni joint is in relation with the ulnar nerve.
The nerve is the largest unprotected tantrika in the insaan deh ( arth unprotected by mansapeshi or bone ), so injury is common.
This nerve is directly connected to the choti ungali, or the sata half of the ring ungali, supplying the palmar paksh of ye ungliyaan, sahit dono saamne or waapas of the nuskhe, perhaps as far back as the fingernail beds.
One vidhi of injuring the tantrika is to strike the medial epicondyle of the humerus from posteriorly, or inferiorly with the elbow flexed.
The ulnar nerve is funs between the asthi or the overlying skin at this point.
This is commonly referred to as bumping ek 's `` funny bone ''.
This name is thought to be a pun, based on the dhwani praturup between the naam of the asthi of the apper bhujaa, the `` humerus `` or the word `` humorous ``.
Alternatively, according to the Oxford English Dictionary it may refer to `` the peculiar sansani anbhavi jab it is struck ''.
hoguarts skool of chudail or wizardry, shortened hoguarts, is a fictional angrejon skool of jaadu liye vidhyaarthee aged gyaarah to atharah, and is the primary setting for the first six books in J.K. Rowling 's Harry Potter series.
Rowling has suggested that wo may have inadvertently liya the naam isse the hogwort sanyantr ( croton capitatus ), jisase wo tha dekhi at kew gardens kuch samay pehle likhane the shrenee, haalanki the names `` the hoguarts '' or `` hoggwart '' appear in the 1954 Nigel Molesworth book How To Be Topp by Geoffrey Willans.
Hogwarts school was voted as the 36th behtareen scottish shaikshanik sthapana in a 2008 online ranking, outranking Edinburgh 's Loretto School.
According to a director of the Independent Schools Network Rankings, it was added to the skulon listing `` liye majaa '' or thi tab voted on.
The U.S. subprime bandhak sankat thi a niyat of kaarykram or sharten ki led to a vittiya sankat or subsequent recession that began in 2008.
It was characterized by a rise in subprime bandhak delinquencies or foreclosures, or the resulting manaahi of pratibhuti backed by said mortgages.
Several major financial institutions collapsed in sitambar 2008, saath significant disruption in the pravaah of credit to vyavsaayon or consumers and the onset of a severe global recession.
There were many causes of the crisis, with commentators assigning different str of dosha to vittiya sansthaanon, regulators, credit agenciyon, sarkari awaas nitiyon, or upabhokta, among others.
A proximate kaaran thi the vruddhi in subprime lending.
The percentage of lower-quality subprime mortgages originated dauraan a die saal rose isse the aitihaasik 8 % or nimnatar dayera to lagbhag 20 % from 2004 to 2006, with much higher ratios in some parts of the U.S.
A high percentage of these subprime mortgages, over 90 % in 2006 liye udhaaharan, yahood adjustable-rate mortgages.
These two parivartan yahood bhaag of a broader trend of lowered lending maanakon or higher-risk mortgage products.
Further, U.S. households tha become increasingly rini, saath the anupaat of karz to dispojable nijee aay uthati isse 77 % in 1990 to 127 % at the end of 2007, much of this increase mortgage-related.
When U.S. home keemten asweekrut steeply baad peaking in mid-2006, borrowers ' kshamta to punarvitt their loans became more difficult.
As adjustable-rate mortgages began to riset at ucchtar byaaj daron ( causing ucchtar masik bhugtan ), mortgage delinquencies soared.
Securities backed with mortgages, sahit subprime mortgages, widely yojit by vittiya firms globally, khoyaa most of their value.
Global investors also drastically reduced purchases of mortgage-backed debt and other securities as bhaag of a manaahi in the kshamta or willingness of the nijee vittiya pranali to support lending.
Concerns about the soundness of U.S. credit and financial markets led to tightening credit around the sansar or slowing aarthik vikaas in the U.S. and Europe.
the sankat tha kathor, long-lasting consequences for the U.S. and European economies.
The U.S. entered a deep recession, saath nearly 9 lakh kaary khoyaa dauraan 2008 or 2009, roughly 6 % of the workforce.
U.S. housing keemten giri nearly 30 % on ausat or the u.S. bhandar market giri lagbhag 50 % by early 2009.
As of early 2013, the U.S. bhandar market tha baraamad to iske pre-crisis shikhar lakin awaas keemten remained nikat unke kam point and unemployment remained elevated.
Economic growth remained neeche pre-crisis str.
Europe also jari to sangharsh saath iske apana aarthik crisis.
karl jang in 1910.
Myers and Briggs extrapolated unke mbti siddhanth isse jang 's kritiyaan in uske kitaab manovaigyanik Types.
the myers-briggs prakaar indicator ( mbti ) moolyankan is a psychometric prashnawali designed to maap manovaigyanik preferences in how people perceive the world and make decisions.
These preferences were extrapolated from the typological theories proposed by karl gustav jang or pehla prakashit in uske 1921 kitaab manovaigyanik prakaar ( angrezi sanskaran, 1923 ).
Jung theorized that there are four principal psychological functions by jisase we anubhav the sansar : sansani, antargyaan, ahsaas, or soch.
One of ye chaar krityon is prabal sabase of the time.
The original developers of the vyaktitv inventory yahood katharine cook briggs or uske beti, isabel briggs myrs ; ye do, having padhai extensively the kaary of jang, turned their interest of human behavior into a devotion of turning the theory of psychological types to practical use.
They began creating the indicator dauraan sansar yuddh ii, believing ki a gyaan of vyaktitv variyataon hota sahaayta mahilaon jo yahood pravesh the industrial workforce for the first time to identify the sort of war-time jobs that would be `` most comfortable and effective ''.
The initial questionnaire grew into the Myers-Briggs prakaar indicator, jisase thi pehla prakashit in 1962.
The MBTI focuses on saamaanya populations or emphasizes the maan of naturally occurring differences.
Robert Kaplan and Dennis Saccuzzo believe `` the underlying assumption of the MBTI is that we all have vishisht variyataon in the rasta we construe hamaari anubhavon, or ye variyataon underlie hamaari ruchi, needs, maan, or prerana '' ( p. 499 ).

Superannuation in Australia refers to the intjaam jisase logon mek in australia to have nidhi uplabdhiyaan for them in retirement.
In australia, superannuation intjaam hai government-supported and encouraged, and minimum provisions are compulsory for employees.
For example, employers are required to pay a proportion of an karmchaaree 's salaries or mazdooree ( philhal 9 % ) into a superannuation nidhi, lakin logon are encouraged to put aside additional funds into superannuation.
The minimum obligation jaruri by niyokta is niyat to badhayen to 12 % dhire stepping annually from 2013 to 2020.
An individual can withdraw funds out of a superannuation fund when the person meets one of the sharten of relies contained in anusuchee 1 of the superannuation udyog ( paryvekshan ) regulations 1994.

Electoral College map showing the results of the 2012 u.S. adhyakshiya chunaav.
President Barack Obama ( D - IL ) won the popular vote in 26 rajya or the zila of colombia ( denoted in blue ) to capchar 332 chunavi votes.

The United States Electoral College is the sanstha ki officially elects the adhyaksh or vaais adhyaksh of the United States every four years.
The President or vaais adhyaksh hai nahin nirvaachit sidhe by the voters.
bajaay, ve hai nirvaachit by `` nirvaachak '' jo hai chosen by popular vote on a state-by-state basis.
Electors hai apportioned to prayek rajya or the zila of colombia, lakin nahin to territorial possessions of the United States, such as Puerto Rico and Guam.
The number of electors in prayek rajya is baraabar to the kramank of sadasyon of congress to jisase the rajya is hakdaar.
The Twenty-third amendment rai sadaa resulted in the zila of Columbia having three electors.
There are 538 nirvaachak, aadhaarit on vahin hone 435 pratinidhi or 100 senators, plus the three electors from the District of Columbia.
Electors are pledged to particular adhyakshiya or vaais adhyakshiya ummidavaar, haalanki unpledged electors are possible.
In all states, except Maine or nebraska, nirvaachak hai nirvaachit on a `` winner-take-all '' aadhaar.
That is, sab nirvaachak pledged to the adhyakshiya pratyaashee jo vins the sabase mat in a state become electors for that state.
maine or nebraska upyog the `` congressional zila vidhi '', selecting ek elector bheetar prayek congressional district by popular vote and selecting the remaining two electors by a statewide popular vote.
Although no elector is jaruri by sangheey vidhi to sammaan a pratigya, vahin have tabhi been very few occasions when an elector voted contrary to a pledge.
The Twelfth Amendment specifies how a President and Vice adhyaksh hai nirvaachit or requires prayek elector to daal ek vote liye adhyaksh or another vote for Vice President.
Critics argue that the chunavi college is inherently undemocratic or detaa jhule rajya anupaatahin influence in electing the adhyaksh and Vice President.
The Electoral college detaa a newmeric laabh in the chunaav of the adhyaksh to the choti rajya, as the nunatam kramank of nirvaachak liye the small states is three compared to one for the election of representatives.
On the other hand, the winner-take-all vidhi of matdaan favors the larger states.
A number of constitutional amendments have been prastaavit seeking to alter the chunavi college or badalen it saath a direct popular vote.
Barack Hussein Obama II ( ; born August 4, 1961 ) is the 44th and vartmaan adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya, the pehla africa amareeki to tham the office.

He then parajeet republican nominee jon macken in the saamaanya chunaav, or thi inaugurated as president on January 20, 2009.

An electronic health record ( EHR ) is an evolving avadharana paribhaashit as a vyavasthit sangrahan of electronic swasthya information about individual patients or populations.
It is a record in digital swaroop ki is theoretically sakasham of hone saajha aarpaar alag swasthya parvaah settings.

A proxy auto-config ( PAC ) file defines how web browsers or anya upayokta agenton can automatically chune the uchit proxy server ( access method ) for fetching a given URL.
A PAC file contains a javascript falan “findproxyforurl ( url, host ) ”.
This function returns a string saath ek or adhik abhigam vidhi visheshtaayen.
These visheshtaayen kaaran the upayokta agent to upyog a particular proxy server or to connect directly.
Multiple visheshtaayen provide a fall-back jab a proxy fails to respond.
The broujar fetches is pac sanchika before requesting other URLs.
The URL of the PAC file is either configured manually or sankalpit automatically by the web proxi autodiscovery protocol.

iOS ( previously iPhone OS ) is a mobile operating system developed and vitarit by tehraana inc. originally released in 2007 liye the iphone or ipod tach plateform, it rai maharoom vistaarit to support anya tehraana divaais such as the iPad and Apple TV.
Unlike Microsoft 's Windows Phone or google 's android, tehraana karata nahin anugna ioes liye sansthapana on non-apple hardware.
, Apple 's App Store contained more than 700,000 iOS anuprayog, jisase have collectively maharoom downlod adhik than 30 billion times.
It had a 21 % share of the smartphone mobile oparating pranali ikai shipped in the fourth quarter of 2012, behind only Google 's Android.
In June 2012, it accounted liye 65 % of mobile web aankada khapat ( sahit upyog on both the iPod Touch and the iPad ).
At the half of 2012, vahin yahood 410 lakh devices activated.
According to the special media event held by Apple on sitambar 12, 2012, 400 lakh divaais have maharoom bechi through June 2012.
The user interface of iOS is based on the avadharana of sidhaa herpher, using multi-touch gestures.
Interface control tatv consist of sliders, switches, or batan.
Interaction with the OS includes gestures such as swipe, tap, pinch, and reverse pinch, sab of jisase have vishisht paribhaashaayen bheetar the context of the ioes oparating pranali or iske multi-touch interface.
Internal accelerometers hai prayukt by kuch anuprayog to respond to shaking the yantra ( ek aam parinaam is the undo cmand ) or ghurnan it in teen aayam ( ek common result is switching from portrait to landscape mode ).
iOS is niklaa isse os x, saath jisase it saajha the darwin foundation.
ioes is tehraana 's mobile sanskaran of the os x oparating system used on Apple computers.
In iOS, there are four abstraction layers : the kor os parat, the kor sevaayen parat, the media parat, and the Cocoa Touch layer.
The current version of the operating system ( iOS 6.1.3 ) dedicates 1-1.5 gb of the yantra 's flash memory liye the pranali partition, using roughly 800 MB of that partition ( varying by model ) for iOS itself.
iOS currently ranon on iphone, ipad, iPod touch and Apple TV.

A spoiler is an automotive aerodynamic device whose intended design function is to 'spoil ' unfavorable air gati aarpaar a deh of a gadee in gati, praayah varnit as turbulence or drag.
Spoilers on the front of a vehicle are often called air dams, because in addition to directing air flow they also reduce the raashi of air bahati underneath the gadee jisase generally reduces aerodynamic lift and drag.
Spoilers are praayah fitted to res or high-performance khel gaadiyaan, haalanki ve have become common on passenger vehicles as well.
Some spoilers are added to gaadiyaan primarily liye styling uddeshy or have either choti aerodynamic laabh or bhi make the aerodynamics worse.
Spoilers liye gaadiyaan hai praayah incorrectly uljhan saath, or the term used interchangeably with, wings.
Automotive wings are divaais jinaki intended dizine is to generate downforce as air gujarata around unhen, nahin bas disrupt existing airflow patterns.

The volt ( symbol : V ) is the SI niklaa ikai liye electric sambhavit ( voltage ), electric potential difference, and electromotive force.
The volt is namit in sammaan of the italvi physicist alessandro volta ( 1745–1827 ), who invented the voltaic pile, possibly the first chemical battery.

On 28 June 1914, Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria, heir presumptive to the Austro-Hungarian throne, and his wife, Sophie, Duchess of hohenberg, yahood shot murde in sarajevo, by gavrilo princip, ek of a samooh of chah bosnian serb hatyare samanvit by danniel Ilić.
The political objective of the hatya thi to brake band austria-hungary 's south-slav praanton so ve could be combined into a Greater Serbia or a Yugoslavia.
The assassins ' motives were consistent with the gati ki baad became gyaat as yang Bosnia.
Serbian sainya adhikariyon stood peeche the attack.
At the top of ye srbian sainya shadyantrkariyon thi mukhya of srbian sainya pragna dragutin dimitrijević, uske righthand man Major Vojislav Tankosić, and Masterspy Rade Malobabić.
Major Tankosić armed the assassins saath bam or pistols or prashikshit unhen.
The assassins were given access to the vahi clandestine tunnel of safe-houses or agenton ki rade malobabić prayukt liye the ghuspaith of hathiyaar or operatives into Austria-Hungary.
The assassins, the key members of the clandestine tunnel, and the kunjee srbian sainya shadyantrkariyon jo yahood still jinda yahood giraftaar, aajamaaya, convicted and punished.
Those jo yahood giraftaar in bosnia were tried in Sarajevo in October 1914.
The anya shadyantrkariyon yahood giraftaar or aajamaaya pehle a srbian kangaroo adaalat on the french-controlled salonika saamne in 1916–1917 on unrelated false charges ; Serbia executed three of the top military conspirators.
Much of what is known about the assassinations aata isse these two trials and related records.
kaarybhaar of jimmedaari liye the bombing or hatyaein of 28 june is atyadhik vivaadaaspad kuki the akraman led to the outbreak of World War I one month later.
mishan san juaan capistrano thi a spani mishan in dakshini california, stith in present-day San Juan Capistrano.
it thi santhaapit on sab santo ' din navambar 1, 1776, by Spanish Catholics of the Franciscan Order.
Named for Giovanni da Capistrano, a 15th century theologian or `` yoddha pujari '' jo resided in the abruzzo pradesh of italy, san juaan capistrano rai the bhed of hone ghar to the oldest bhawan in california still in upyog, a chapel built in 1782.
Known alternately as `` sera 's chapel '' or `` pita sera 's girijaghar, '' it is the tabhi extant dhaancha jahaan it rai maharoom documented that the padre Junipero Serra celebrated mass.
One of the best known of the Alta California missions ( and one of the few missions to have darasal maharoom santhaapit twice—others hone mishan san jibareel arcángel or mishan la purísima concepción ).
The sait thi originally consecrated on aktubar 30, 1775, by pita fermín Lasuén, but was quickly abandoned due to unrest among the indigenous population in San Diego.
The success of the settlement is evident in iske aitihaasik record.
Prior to the aagaman of the prachaarkon, kuch 550 natives yahood bikhare throughout the local area.
By 1790, the kramank of parivartit isaayiyon tha grown to 700, or bas chah saalo baad nearly 1,000 `` neophytes `` ( haal converts ) lived in or around the Mission compound.
1,649 baptisms were conducted ki saal alon, out of the kul 4,639 souls parivartit between 1776 and 1847.
More than 2,000 purv nivaasiyon ( zyaadaatar juaneño indiens ) hai dafn in unmarked qabron in the Mission 's cemetery ( campo santo ).
The remains of pita ( baad monsignor ) st. jon o'sullivan, jo pahachaanaa the property 's aitihaasik maan or working tirelessly to conserve and rebuild its structures, are buried at the entrance to the cemetery on the west side of the property, and a statue raised in his honor stands at the head of the crypt.
The surviving chapel also serves as the final resting place of three padres who passed on while serving at the mishan : fathers jose barona, vicent fustér, or vicent paskual oliva hai sab entombed beneath the sanctuary floor.
The Criolla or `` mishan angoor, '' thi pehla planted at san juaan capistrano in 1779 ; in 1783, the first wine produced in Alta California emerged from the Mission 's winery.
The Mission daalaa a long kaal of kramik manaahi baad secularization in 1833.
Numerous efforts yahood bana over the saalo to restore the mishan to iske purv glory, but none met with great success until the arrival of Father O'Sullivan in 1910.
Restoration efforts continue, and `` sera 's chapel '' is still prayukt liye dharmik sevaayen.
About half-a-million vizitor, sahit 80,000 skool children, aaiye to the Mission each year.
And while the ruins of `` The Great Stone Church '' ( which was all but leveled by an 1812 earthquake ) are a renowned architectural wonder, the Mission is shaayad behtareen gyaat liye the salanaa `` vaapasi of the daat '' jisase is traditionally observed prayek kooch 19 ( sant joseph 's Day ).
Mission San Juan Capistrano has served as a favorite subject liye anek notable kalakaaron, or rai maharoom immortalized in sahitya or on filmi numerous times, shaayad adhik than any other mission.
In 1984, a modern church complex was constructed bas uttar or west of the mishan yogic or is abhi gyaat as mishan basilica san Juan Capistrano.
Today, the mission compound serves as a sangrahalay, saath the sera chapel bheetar the yogic sevarat as a chapel for the mission parish.

A shrenee of kaarykram led to the akraman on Pearl Harbor.

The Philippine islands, at ki samay an amareeki territory, yahood bhi a Japanese target.

A aam daftar stapler
A common skool stapler
A stapler is a mechanical yantra ki joins chaadaren of paper or samaan saamagree by driving a patala metal staple through the sheets and folding the ends.
Staplers are widely used in government, kaarobaar, karyaalayon, gharon or skulon.
The word `` stapler '' can darasal refer to a number of different devices of varying uses.
In addition to joining paper chaadaren saath, staplers can bhi be prayukt in a sargical setting to juden utak saath saath sargical staples to close a surgical wound ( much in the same way as stitches or sutures ).
Typically, sabase staplers hai prayukt to join multiple sheets of paper.
Paper staplers come in two pruthak prakaar : hastchalit or electric.
Manual staplers are normally hand-held, haalanki model ki hai prayukt jabaki niyat on a desk or anya sataha are not uncommon.
Electric staplers exist in a variety of alag dizin or model.
unke praathmik oparating falan is to juden vishaal sankhyaayein of paper sheets together in rapid succession.
Some electric staplers can juden up to 20 sheets at a time.
swallowing, gyaat scientifically as deglutition, is the prakram in the human or animal body that makes something pass from the mouth, to the pharynx, and into the esophagus, while shutting the epiglottis.
If this fails and the object goes through the shwaasanlee, tab choking or pulmonary aspiration can occur.
In the human body it is niyantrit by the swallowing reflex.
Thaddeus Stevens ( April 4, 1792 – agast 11, 1868 ), of pencilvenia, thi a netaa of the kattarpanthi republican gut of the republican party or a fierce pratidwandi of slavery.
He was one of the most influential sadasyon in the itihaas of Congress.
As chairman of the shaktishaalee house tareeke or arthath cameti, stevens, a witty, vyangyatmak spikar and flamboyant party leader, dominated the House from 1861 until his death.
He likhaa much of the vittiya vidhaan ki paid for the American Civil War.
Stevens and Senator Charles Sumner were the pradhan netao of the kattarpanthi republicans dauraan the yuddh or punarnirmaan era.
Scholarly views of Stevens have swung sharply chunki uske maut as interpretations of punarnirmaan have badla.
Historians of the dunning skool ( 1890s–1940s ) yojit stevens jimmedaar liye demanding harsh upachaar of the shwet dakshin or violating amareeki traditions of republicanism, depicting Stevens as a villain for his advocacy of harsh measures in the South such as disfranchising all ex-Confederates.
This highly rinatmak characterization yojit sway into the 1950s.
The rise of the neo-abolitionist skool in the 1950s led to a damdaar positive appreciation of Stevens ' work on civil rights for Freedmen.
A recent biographer characterizes him as, `` The Great Commoner, savior of free public education in Pennsylvania, national Republican netaa in the struggles viruddh gulaami in the sanyukt rajya or intrepid mainstay of the attempt to surakshit jatigat insaaf liye the freedmen dauraan punarnirmaan, the tabhi sadsy of the house of pratinidhi kabhi to have been known as the 'dictator ' of Congress. avlokan of the anuwaad of eukaryotic messenger RNA
Diagram showing the translation of mRNA or the sanshleshan of protein by a ribosom
In molecular biology and anuvanshiki, anuwaad is the prakram through jisase cellular ribosomes manufacture proteins.
It is part of the prakram of jin abhivyakti.
In translation, messenger RNA ( mRNA ) produced by transcripshan is decoded by the ribosom to upaj a vishisht amino acid kadi, or polypeptide, ki hoga baad moden into an active protein.
In bacteria, anuwaad occurs in the koshika 's koshikadravya, jahaan the vishaal or choti subunits of the ribosome are located, and bind to the mRNA.
In eukaryotes, translation occurs aarpaar the jhilli of the endoplasmic reticulum in a process called vectorial synthesis.
The ribosome facilitates decoding by inducing the binding of tRNAs with poorak anticodon sequences to ki of the mrna.
The tRNAs carry specific amino acids that are chained together into a polypeptide as the mrna gujarata through or is `` padhaa '' by the ribosom in a faishan reminiscent to ki of a stock ticker and ticker tape.
In many instances, the entire ribosome/mRNA complex binds to the outer jhilli of the ashisht endoplasmic reticulum or relies the nascent protein polypeptide andar liye baad vesicle transport and secretion outside of the cell.
Many types of transcribed RNA, aise as transafar rna, ribosomal rna, or choti nabhikeey rna, do not undergo translation into proteins.
Translation proceeds in four phases : initiation, elongation, translocation and termination ( sab describing the vikaas of the amino acid kadi, or polypeptide ki is the utpaada of anuwaad ).
amino acids hai brought to ribosomes or samavet into proteins.
In sakriyan, the sahi amino acid is covalently bandhua to the sahi transfer RNA ( tRNA ).
The amino acid is joined by iske carboxyl samooh to the 3 ' OH of the tRNA by an ester bond.
jab the trna rai an amino acid linked to it, it is termed `` charged ''.
Initiation involves the small subunit of the ribosom binding to the 5 ' samaapt of mrna saath the sahaayta of diksha factors ( IF ).
Termination of the polypeptide happens when the A sait of the ribosom chehron a roke codon ( uaa, uag, or UGA ).
No tRNA can recognize or bind to is codon.
Instead, the stop codon induces the binding of a relies factor protein ki prompts the disassembly of the entire ribosome/mRNA complex.
A number of antibiotics act by inhibiting translation ; these include anisomycin, cycloheximide, chloramphenicol, tetracycline, streptomycin, erythromycin, or puromycin, among others.
Prokaryotic ribosomes have a different structure isse ki of eukaryotic ribosomes, or yun antibiotic can specifically nishaanaa bacterial infections bagaiyr koi detriment to a eukaryotic host 's cells.

Multimedia Messaging seva ( mms ) is a maanak rasta to bhejein sandesh ki shaamil multimedia saamagree to or isse mobile phones.
It extends the core SMS ( choti sandesh seva ) kaabiliyat ki anumat exange of text sandesh tabhi up to 160 characters in length.
The most popular use is to send photographs from camera-equipped handsets, haalanki it is bhi lokapriy as a method of delivering news and entertainment content including videos, pictures, text pages and ringtones.
The standard is viksit by the kholen mobile gathbandhan ( omo ), haalanki dauraan vikaas it thi bhaag of the 3GPP and WAP groups.
Smallpox was an infectious disease unique to insaano, caused by either of do virus visangatiyaan, variola pramukh and Variola minor.
the beemaari is bhi gyaat by the latin names variola or variola veeraa, niklaa isse varius ( `` spotted '' ) or varus ( `` pimple '' ).
The disease was originally gyaat in angrezi as the `` chechak '' or `` red plig '' ; the pad `` smallpox '' thi pehla prayukt in Britain in the 15th century to distinguish variola from the `` great pox '' ( syphilis ).
The last naturally occurring case of smallpox ( variola naaballig ) thi diagnosed on 26 October 1977.
Smallpox sthaniyakrut in choti rakt baratan of the skin or in the mouth and throat.
In the skin it resulted in a characteristic maculopapular khaaj or, baad, uthaaya fluid-filled blisters.
V. major produces a more gambhir beemaari or rai an overall mrityu rate of 30–35 %.
V. minor causes a milder form of beemaari ( bhi gyaat as alastrim, cottonpox, milkpox, whitepox, and Cuban itch ) which kills about 1 % of its victims.
Long-term complications of V. major infection include characteristic scars, commonly on the phase, jisase occur in 65–85 % of survivors.
Blindness resulting from corneal ulceration and scarring, and limb deformities due to gathiya or osteomyelitis hai kam common complications, seen in about 2–5 % of cases.
smallpox is believed to have ubhara in human populations about 10,000 BC.
The earliest physical evidence of it is probably the pustular khaaj on the mummified deh of pharaoh ramses v of Egypt.
The disease killed an estimated 400,000 europeans annually dauraan the closing saalo of the 18th sadi ( sahit paanch reigning monarchs ), or thi jimmedaar for a third of all blindness.
Of all those sankramit, 20–60 % —and over 80 % of infected children—died from the disease.
Smallpox was jimmedaar liye an anumaanit 300–500 lakh mauton dauraan the 20th century.
As recently as 1967, the sansar swasthya sanghathan ( jo ) anumaanit ki 15 lakh logon contracted the beemaari and that two million died in that year.
After vaccination campaigns throughout the 19th and 20th centuries, the jo certified the eradication of smallpox in 1979.
Smallpox is one of two infectious diseases to have been eradicated, the anya hone rinderpest, jisase thi ghoshit eradicated in 2011.

Taking two weeks to dislodge its predecessor, `` I Want to Hold Your Hand '' tehre at kramank ek liye paanch saptaah or remained in the uk sheersh pachaas liye twenty-one saptaah in total.

By 1 farvari it yojit the kramank ek spot — liye saat saptaah — pehle hone replaced by `` wo loves tum '', a reverse paridrishy of kayaa had occurred in Britain, and remained in the US charts for a total of fifteen weeks.
`` I Want to tham apana haath '' became the betals ' best-selling single worldwide.
A gasser was a type of hot rod originating on the dragstrips of the sanyukt rajya in the let 1950s or jari jabatak the early 1970s.
Gassers were based on production models from the 1930s to mid-1960s, which have been stripped of extraneous weight and jacked up using a truck beam axle to provide behatar vazan vitaran on twaran ( beam axles hai bhi halkaa than an swatantra saamne barkhaastagi ), haalanki a uthaaya bhandar saamne barkhaastagi is aam as khub.
aam vazan katautee takneekon shaamil fiberglass deh panels, stripped interiars or plexiglass windows ( sometimes color tinted ).
Because they were primarily built for racing, these cars typically tha the ingine swapped to a larger or adhik shaktishaalee ek, the maujuuda bhandar ingine modified ( often heavily ) or both.
It was very common to fit a Roots supercharger and mechanical fuel injection, aise as ek isse algon, hilborn, or Crower.
With form being likhavai by falan, unke rup is praayah bahut sheersh baari or ungainly, largely due to saamne ends hone uthaaya ucchtar than bhandar, to assist in the weight transfer during rapid acceleration ( racing ).
Having their exhaust pipe nikaas through the saamne phender khub is a aam characteristic of gassers, as is having laashen chitrit in flamboyant metalflakes, moti, or candi finishes complemented by lettering in wild fonts.
The name arose because they competed in a gasoline -fueled drag racing class, balki than ek using methanol or nitromethane.
The gasser is the purvavarti of the aadhunik Funny Car.

Electrocardiography ( ECG or EKG from ) is a transthoracic ( aarpaar the vaksh or chaati ) nirvachan of the vidyut kaaryaklap of the dil over a kaal of samay, as detected by electrodes sanlagn to the surface of the skin and recorded by a device external to the body.
The recording produced by this noninvasive kaarividhi is termed an electrocardiogram ( bhi isiji or ichaji ).
An ECG is prayukt to maap the rate or niyamitata of heartbeats, as khub as the aakaar or sthiti of the kakshon, the upasthiti of koi kshati to the dil, and the effects of drugs or devices used to regulate the heart, such as a pacemaker.
Most ECGs are performed for nidaan or shodh uddeshy on insaan dil, lakin may bhi be performed on pashu, praayah liye nidaan of dil abnormalities or research.

bhaap uthati isse the nesjavellir geothermal shakti Station in Iceland.
geothermal urja is thermal urja utpann and stored in the Earth.
thermal urja is the urja ki determines the temperature of matter.
The geothermal urja of the dharti 's crust originates isse the asli gathan of the grah ( 20 % ) and from radioactive decay of minerals ( 80 % ).
The geothermal anupaat, jisase is the antar in taapmaana between the kor of the grah and its surface, drives a continuous conduction of thermal energy in the form of heat from the core to the surface.
The adjective geothermal originates from the Greek roots γη ( ge ), meaning dharti, or θερμος ( thermos ), arth hot.
At the core of the dharti, thermal urja is nirmit by radioskriy kshay or temperatures may reach over 5000 °C ( 9,000 °F ).
Heat conducts isse the kor to surrounding cooler rock.
The unchi taapmaana or dabaav kaaran kuch chattan to melt, creating magma convection upward since it is lighter than the solid rock.
The magma heats rock or jal in the crust, sometimes up to 370 °C ( 700 °F ).
isse hot sroton, geothermal urja rai maharoom prayukt liye snaan chunki paleolithic times or liye spes heating since ancient Roman times, but it is now better known for electricity generation.
Worldwide, about 10,715 megawatts ( mw ) of geothermal shakti is online in 24 countries.
An additional 28 gigawatts of direct geothermal heating capacity is santhaapit liye zila heating, spes heating, spa, audyogic prakriyaaon, desalination or agricultural applications.
geothermal shakti is laagat prabhavi, vishwasaneey, chirsthayee, or environmentally dostana, lakin rai historically been limited to areas near tectonic plate boundaries.
haal technological agrim have dramatically vistaarit the dayera or aakaar of sugathit sansaadhan, visheshkar liye anuprayog such as home heating, opening a potential for widespread exploitation.
Geothermal wells release greenhouse gases trapped deep within the dharti, lakin ye emissions hai much nimnatar prati urja unit than those of fossil fuels.
As a parinaam, geothermal shakti rai the sambhavit to sahaayta mitigate vaishvik varming if widely deployed in place of fossil fuels.
The dharti 's geothermal sansaadhan hai theoretically adhik than paryaapt to supply humanity 's energy needs, but only a very small fraction may be profitably exploited.
Drilling and khoji liye gahan sansaadhan is bahut expensive.
Forecasts for the future of geothermal power nirbhar on assumptions parichay praudyogiki, urja keemten, subsidies, or byaaj rates.
Pilot programs like EWEB 's graahak opt in green shakti kaarykram dikhaaen ki graahak hota be willing to pay a little more for a renewable energy source like geothermal.
But as a parinaam of sarkari assisted shodh or udyog anubhav, the laagat of generating geothermal power has decreased by 25 % over the past two decades.
In 2001, geothermal urja laagat between do or ten saint per kwh.
Ownership of property may be private, samuhik, or aam or the property may be vastuen, land/real estate, or bauddhik property.
Determining ownership in law involves determining jo rai nishchit adhikaron or kartavya over the property.
These rights and duties, sometimes pukaara a 'bundle of adhikaron ', can be alag or yojit by different parties.
The question of ownership pahunch waapas to the pracheen darshanikon, plato or arestu, jo yojit alag raay on the subject.
Plato ( 428/427 BC – 348/347 BC ) thought private property created divisive inequalities, jabaki arestu ( 384 bc – 322 bc ) vichaar nijee property sakriy logon to praapt the puraa laabh of their labor.
Private property can circumvent what is abhi referred to as the “ traasadee of the comons ” problem, jahaan logon tend to rusavaa aam property more than they do private property.
Given a short-sighted owner, however, a private property system can make these tragedies worse—for udhaaharan, a nijee maalik of a tukdaa of oil-rich property, depending on uske worldview, might be adhik dilchaspee in short-term vittiya laabh than vriddhishil upyog saath an eye toward other 's concerns ( e.g., those of future generations, the disenfranchised, etc. ).
While Aristotle jaij the astitv of nijee swaamitv, he baayein kholen sawaal of ( 1 ) kaisaa to allocate property between what is private and common and ( 2 ) how to allocate the private property within society.
Over the millennia, and aarpaar samskritiyon kayaa can be property or kaisaa it is regarded culturally have varied widely.
Ownership is the aadhaar liye anek anya avadharanaon ki rup the muladhar of pracheen or aadhunik samaajon such as money, trade, debt, bankruptcy, the criminality of theft, and private vs. public property.
Ownership is the key building block in the vikaas of the poonjivadi socio-economic pranali.
Adam smith stated ki ek of the pavitra kanoon of insaaf was to guard a person 's property and possessions.
The process and mechanics of ownership are fairly jatil : ek can laabh, transafar or khona swaamitv of property in a kramank of ways.
To acquire property one can purchase it with dhan, vyapaar it liye anya property, praapt it as a tohfa, chori it, dhundhen it, mek, it or homestead it.
One can transfer or lose ownership of property by selling it for money, exchanging it for other property, giving it as a tohfa, hone robbed of it, it, or having it stripped from one 's ownership through legal means such as eviction, foreclosure, seizure, or taking.
Ownership is self-propagating in ki the maalik of koi property hoga bhi apana the aarthik laabh of that property.

A mathematical constant is a khaas kramank, praayah a real kramank, ki is `` significantly interesting in some way ''.
Constants arise in many alag kshetron of ganit, saath sthiraank aise as e ( ganitiya nirantar ) | or pi| occurring in aise vividh contexts as geometry, number theory and calculus.
What it means for a constant to arise `` naturally '', and what makes a constant `` interesting '', is ultimately a matter of swaad, or kuch ganitiya sthiraank hai notable adhik liye aitihaasik kaaran than liye unke moolbhoot ganitiya interest.
The more popular constants have been padhai throughout the aayu or computed to many decimal places.
All mathematical constants are definable numbers and usually hai bhi computable sankhyaayein ( chaitin 's nirantar hone a significant exception ).

A solstice is an astronomical event that occurs twice prayek saal as the surya pahunch iske ucchtam or nunatam excursion saapeksh to the celestial equator on the celestial gola.
As a result, on the day of the sankranti, the surya appears to have pahunche iske ucchtam or nunatam salanaa oonchaai in the aasmaan upar the kshitij at local saura noon.
The word solstice is derived from the Latin sol ( surya ) or sistere ( to stand still ), kuki at the solstices, the surya stand still in utaar ; ki is, the mausami gati of the Sun 's path ( as seen from Earth ) comes to a stop before reversing direction.
The solstices, saath saath the equinoxes, hai conect saath the seasons.
In many cultures the solstices chihnit either the shuruuaat or the midpoint of sheet and summer.
The term solstice can also be prayukt in a broader bhav, as the tithi ( din ) jab is occurs.
The day of the solstice is either the longest din of the saal ( in garmiyaan ) or the shortest din of the year ( in winter ) for any place outside of the tropics.
Jerry Lee Lewis ( born September 29, 1935 ) is an amareeki chattan or phenken or desh music singer-songwriter and pianist.

Henry Louis Stephens, benaam watercolor ( 1863 ) of a man padhnaa a samachaarpatr saath sheershak `` adhyakshiya Proclamation / Slavery ''.
The emancipation udghoshnaa thi an anukram jari to sab khand of the karypalika shakha ( sahit the fouj or navy ) of the sanyukt rajya by President Abraham Lincoln on January 1, 1863, during the American Civil War.
It was based on the president 's sanvaidhanik praadhikaar as commander in mukhya of the armed forces ; it was not a law passed by Congress.
It proclaimed all those enslaved in Confederate territory to be forever free, or ordered the fouj ( or sab khand of the karypalika shakha ) to daavat as free sab those enslaved in ten rajya ki yahood still in vidroh, yun applying to 3.1 lakh of the 4 million slaves in the U.S.
The Proclamation could not be enforced in areas still under rebellion, but as the army took control of confederate regions, the slave in those regions yahood emancipated balki than laute to unke masters.
From 20,000 to 50,000 purv slave in regions jahaan vidroh tha already maharoom subdued yahood tatkaal emancipated, or over 3 lakh adhik yahood emancipated as the Union army advanced.
The Proclamation did not apply to the five slave rajya ki yahood nahin in vidroh, nor to sabase regions already niyantrit by the sangh fouj ; emancipation vahin hota aaiye baad pruthak rajya kriyaayein and/or the disambar 1865 ratification of the Thirteenth Amendment, which made slavery illegal everywhere in the U.S.
The Proclamation did not compensate the swami, kiya nahin itself gaiyrkanoonee gulaami, or kiya nahin make the ex-slaves ( called freedmen ) citizens.
It made the eradication of slavery an suspasht yuddh lakshya, in jod to the lakshya of reuniting the Union.
On September 22, 1862, lincoln tha jari a praarambhik udghoshnaa ki he hota anukram the emancipation of sab slave in koi rajya of the confederate States of America that did not return to Union control by January 1, 1863.
None returned, and the order, signed or jari janvari 1, 1863, took prabhaav magar in sthitiyaan where the Union had already mostly regained control.
The Proclamation outraged white Southerners jo envisioned a res yuddh, angered kuch uttari democrate, sakriy anti-slavery forces, and weakened forces in Europe that wanted to intervene to help the Confederacy.
It also lifted the spirits of African Americans both in the Southern and Northern States, and led to many slave escaping unke masters or kaaryshil peeche sangh linon in anukram to have unke emancipation enforced.

A digital camera ( or digicam ) is a camera ki takes video or still photographs by recording images on an electronic image sensor.
Most cameras sold today are digital, or digital camere hai incorporated into anek divaais ranging isse gusse or mobile phones ( called camera phones ) to vehicles.
Digital and film cameras share an optical system, typically using a lens saath a parivartaneey diaphragm to fokas lite onto an image pickup device.
The diaphragm and shutter admit the correct amount of light to the imager, bas as saath filmi lakin the chitra pikup yantra is electronic balki than chemical.
However, unlike film camere, digital camere can pradarshak bimb on a screen tatkaal baad hone recorded, and store and delete images from memory.
Many digital cameras can bhi ricard chalati video saath dhwani.
Some digital camere can crop or silaai tasviren or perform other elementary image editing.

A rooster ( also called a cockerel or murga ) is a purush gallinaceous bird.
It praayah refers to a purush murga ( gallus gallus ).
Immature male chickens less than ek saal boodha hai pukaara cockerels.
The term `` rooster '' originates in the sanyukt rajya, or the pad is widely prayukt throughout North America, as well as Australia and New Zealand.
In the United kingdom or ireland the puraani pad `` cockerel '' is more commonly used.
`` Cock '' is in general upyog as the naam liye a purush of anya species of bird, for example `` Cock sparrow ''.
`` Roosting '' is the karrwai of perching aloft to neend at raatri, or is kiya by both sexes.
The murga is polygamous, lakin can nahin guard anek nests of eggs at once.
He guards the general area where his hens are nesting, or hoga akraman anya roosters ki daalen uske territory.
During the daytime, he usually sits on a unchi parch, praayah 3–5 feet band the maidan to serve as a lookout liye uske jhund.
He will sound a distinctive sachetak kol if parabhakshi are nearby.

The regulation of prostitution in the United States is not among the enumerated powers of the federal government ; Under the dasavaan amendment to the sanyukt rajya samvidhan, it is isliye exclusively the domen of the rajya to permit, prohibit, or varanaa viniyamit vanijyik sex, except insofar as Congress may regulate it as part of interstate commerce with laws like the Mann Act.
In most states, veshyavriti is mana a misdemeanor in the shrenee of public order crime, a crime that disrupts the order of a community.
It was at ek samay mana to be a vagrancy crime.
Currently, Nevada is the only state to allow veshyalay veshyavriti, the sharten of jisase hai stipulated in the newada sanshodhit Statutes.
Only 8 counties philhal contain kriyasheel brothels.
All form of veshyavriti hai illegal in clark county ( jisase contains the las vegas–paradise mahanagar kshetrafal ), washoe County ( which contains Reno ), Carson City, Douglas County, and Lincoln County.
The other county theoretically allow veshyalay veshyavriti, lakin kuch of ye county currently have no active brothels.
Street prostitution, `` pandering, '' and living off of the proceeds of a veshya remain illegal antargat newada vidhi, as elsewhere in the desh.
As with other countries, prostitution in the sanyukt rajya can be vibhajit into teen vyapak shrenee : gali veshyavriti, veshyalay prostitution, and escort prostitution.

Richard Milhous Nixon ( January 9, 1913 – April 22, 1994 ) was the 37th President of the United States, sevarat isse 1969 to 1974, jab he became the tabhi adhyaksh to istipha the office.
Nixon had previously served as a Republican U.S. representative and senator from California and as the 36th Vice adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya isse 1953 to 1961.
Nixon thi born in yorba linda, California.
he graduate isse whittier college in 1934 or duk vishvavidhyalayon skool of Law in 1937, returning to California to practice law.
He and his wife, Pat nicksan, sthanantarit to washington to kaary liye the sangheey government in 1942.
He subsequently parosa in the sanyukt rajya navy dauraan World War II.
Nixon was elected in california to the house of pratinidhi in 1946 or to the Senate in 1950.
His pursuit of the Alger Hiss case established his reputation as a leading anti-communist, or elevated use to neshnal prominence.
He thi the kaaryshil mate of dwite D. ijanhavar, the republican party adhyakshiya nominee in the 1952 election.
Nixon served for eight saalo as vaais adhyaksh.
He waged an unsuccessful presidential abhiyaan in 1960, narrowly khone to jon F. kennedy, or khoyaa a res liye Governor of California in 1962.
In 1968, he bhaaga again liye the presidency or was elected.
Although Nixon initially escalated america 's bhagidaari in the vietnam yuddh, he subsequently ended U.S. involvement in 1973.
Nixon 's visit to the People 's ganatantr of china in 1972 kholi rajanyik sambandh between the do raashtra, or he initiated détente or the anti-ballistic Missile Treaty with the Soviet Union the same year.
domestically, uske prashasan generally embraced nitiyon ki transferred power from Washington to the states.
Among other things, he launched pahalon to lado karkat or illegal davaayen, imposed mazdooree or daam niyantran, enforced desegregation of kuch Southern schools, and established the Environmental Protection Agency.
Though he presided over the chandra avataran beginning with Apollo 11, he scaled back manned space exploration.
he thi re-elected by a bhuskhalan in 1972.
Nixon 's duusari pad dekhi an arab aayal embargo, the istipha of uske vaais adhyaksh, spiro agnew, or a continuing shrenee of revelations about the Watergate scandal and other misconduct by members of the administration.
The scandal escalated, costing Nixon much of uske rajnatik support, or on agast 9, 1974, he resigned in the phase of lagbhag nishchit mahabhiyog and removal from office.
After uske istipha, he controversially praapt a pardon issued by his successor, Gerald Ford.
In retirement, Nixon 's work as an elder statesman, authoring anek kitabe or undertaking anek videshi yatraayen, helped to rehabilitate uske public image.
He suffered a debilitating stroke on april 18, 1994, and died four days later at the age of 81.
Sertraline hydrochloride ( trade names Zoloft, lustral ) is an antidepressant of the chaynaatmak serotonin reuptake inhibitor ( SSRI ) class.
It was introduced to the market by fizer in 1991.
Sertraline is primarily prescribed for major depressive disorder in adult outpatients as khub as obsessive–compulsive, dehshat, or soshal chintaa vikaar in dono adults and children.
in 2011, it thi the second-most vihit antidepressant on the u.S. khudara market, saath 37,208,000 prescriptions.
The efficacy of sertraline for depression is similar to ki of puraani tricyclic antidepressants, lakin iske paksh prabhaav hai much kam sunaaya.
Differences with nae antidepressants hai subtler or bhi zyaadaatar confined to side effects.
Evidence suggests that sertraline may kaary behatar than fluoxetine ( prozac ) liye some subtypes of depression.
upachaar of dehshat vikaar saath sertraline parinaam in a significant ghati of the kramank of panic attacks and in improved quality of life.
For obsessive-compulsive vikaar, sertraline is nahin as prabhavi as sangyanatmak behavioral chikitsa ; the behtareen parinaam have maharoom achieved by combining these two treatments.
haalanki sweekrut liye soshal phobia or posttraumatic tanaav vikaar, sertraline leads to only modest improvement in these conditions.
Sertraline also alleviates the lakshan of premenstrual dysphoric vikaar or can be prayukt in sub-therapeutic doses or intermittently for its treatment.
Sertraline shares the common side effects and contraindications of anya ssris, saath unchi daron of matlee, atisar, anidra, or yon paksh prabhaav ; however, it karata nahin kaaran weight gain, and its effects on both cognition and vigilance are relatively mild.
In pregnant women taking sertraline, the drug thi upasthit in significant ekaagratha in fetal rakt, or thi bhi sambhddha with a higher rate of various birth defects.
similarly to anya antidepressants, the upyog of sertraline liye avsaad may be associated with a higher rate of suicidality.

A theth 12 v, 40 ah lead-acid car battery
An automotive battery is a type of rechargeable bydaree ki aapurtiyan electric urja to an automobile.
Usually this refers to an SLI battery ( starting, lighting, prajvalan ) to shakti the prarambh motor, the lits, or the prajvalan pranali of a vehicle’s engine.
automotive sli bydaree hai praayah lead-acid prakaar, or hai bana of chah galvani cells in series to provide a 12 volt system.
Each koshika provides 2.1 volts liye a kul of 12.6 volt at full charge.
Heavy vehicles such as highway trucks or tractors, often equipped saath deazal ingine, may have do bydaree in shrenee liye a 24 volt pranali, or may have samanaantar strings of batteries.
lead-acid bydaree hai bana up of platon of sise or pruthak platon of sise dioxide, jisase are submerged into an electrolyte solution of about 38 % sulfuric acid and 62 % water.
This kalyankari a rasinic pratikriya ki relies electrons, allowing unhen to pravaah through conductors to produce electricity.
As the battery discharges, the acid of the electrolyte pratikriyaayein saath the saamagree of the platon, changing their surface to lead sulfate.
When the battery is recharged, the chemical pratikriya is reversed : the sise sulphate reforms into sise dioxide and lead.
With the platon lauti to unke asli condishan, the process may now be repeated.
Battery recycling of automotive bydaree reduces the need liye sansaadhan jaruri liye manufacture of nai bydaree, diverts vishakt sise from landfills, and prevents risk of improper disposal.
Full-time employment is employment in which a vyakti works a nunatam kramank of ghanton paribhaashit as aise by his/her employer.
Full-time employment often comes with laabh ki hai nahin typically offered to part-time, asthai, or lacheelee majdoor, aise as salanaa chhod, sickleave, and health insurance.
Full-time kaary hai praayah mana kariyar.
They generally adaa adhik than part-time kaary, or praayah carry more hours per week.
The Fair Labor maanakon adhinium ( flsa ) karata nahin define full-time employment or part-time employment.
is is a padaarth generally to be sankalpit by the employer ( US Department of Labor ).
The paribhaasha by niyokta can vary or is generally prakashit in a company 's Employee Handbook.
Companies commonly aavashyaktaa isse 30–35 or 40 ghanton prati saptaah to be defined as full-time and therefore eligible for benefits.
full-time aukaat varies between company or is praayah aadhaarit on the shift the employee must work during each work week.
The `` standard '' kaary saptaah consists of paanch eight-hour dinon, commonly parosa between 9:00am to 5:00PM totaling 40 hours.
While a four-day week generally consists of four ten-hour dinon ; it may bhi consist of as choti as nau ghanton liye a kul of a 36 ghanta kaary saptaah.
Twelve-hour shifts are often teen dinon prati saptaah, jabatak the company rai the iraade of paying out the karmchaaree overtime.
Overtime is legally sashulk out anytime an karmchaaree works adhik than 40 ghanton per week.
The vidhik nunatam liye overtime starts at Base Pay + One-Half.
The increased bhugtan is mana to compensate thodaa liye the increased fatigue which a person experiences on such long shifts.
Shifts can also be very irregular, as in khudara, lakin hai still full-time if the jaruri kramank of ghanton is pahunche.
There are some situations where a person who needs full-time kaary is dropped to part-time, jisase is sometimes a rup of constructive dismissal to avoid paying berogari benefits to a laid-off worker.

the duusari crusade ( 1145–1149 ) thi the second major crusade launched from Europe.
The Second Crusade was prarambh in jawaab to the patan of the county of edessa the pichhlaa saal to the forces of Zengi.

the sena of the do kings marched separately across Europe.

an udhaaharan of rack arohit servers
A web hosting service is a prakaar of antarjaal hosting seva ki allows individuals or sanghathan to mek their website accessible via the World Wide Web.
Web hosts are companies that provide space on a server owned or leased for use by client, as khub as providing antarjaal connactivity, typically in a aankada bich.
Web hosts can also provide data center space and connectivity to the antarjaal liye anya sarwar stith in unke aankada bich, pukaara colocation, bhi gyaat as awaas in latin america or frans.
The scope of web hosting sevaayen varies greatly.
The most basic is web page and small-scale sanchika hosting, jahaan filein can be aplod via File Transfer Protocol ( FTP ) or a Web interface.
The files are praayah vitarit to the web `` as is '' or saath minimal processing.
Many Internet service providers ( isps ) prastaav is seva free to sadsy.
Individuals and sanghathan may bhi obtain web pej hosting isse vaikalpik service providers.
Personal web sait hosting is typically free, advertisement-sponsored, or inexpensive.
Business web site hosting often has a higher expense depending upon the aakaar or prakaar of the jalsthal.
Single page hosting is generally sufficient liye nijee web prishthon.
A complex site calls for a more comprehensive package that provides database support and anuprayog vikaas plateform ( e.g. piechapi, java, maaniky on rails, coldfusion, or ASP.NET ).
These facilities allow customers to write or install scripts for anuprayog jaise forums or saamagree prabandhan.
bhi, surakshit sockets parat ( esasail ) is typically used for e-commerce.
The host may also provide an interface or control falak liye managing the web sarwar or installing script, as khub as anya maudul and service applications like e-mail.
Some hosts specialize in certain software or services ( e.g. e-commerce ), jisase hai commonly prayukt by larger companiyaan ki outsource sanjaal infrastructure.

The Wright brothers, Orville ( August 19, 1871 – January 30, 1948 ) and Wilbur ( April 16, 1867 – May 30, 1912 ), yahood do amareeki bhaaiyo, avishkaarak, or vimaanan pioneers jo yahood credited saath inventing or bhawan the sansar 's pehla kaamyaab vayuyan or bananaa the pehla niyantrit, sanchalit or sustained heavier-than-air human flight, on December 17, 1903.
From 1905 to 1907, the brothers developed unke udati yantra into the pehla vyaavhaarik fixed-wing aircraft.
Although not the first to nirmaan or makkhi praayogic vayuyan, the rhite bhaaiyo yahood the pehla to ifatera aircraft controls that made fixed-wing powered flight possible.
The brothers ' fundamental breakthrough was their avishkaar of three-axis control, jisase sakriy the payalat to steer the vayuyan effectively and to maintain its equilibrium.
is vidhi became maanak or remains maanak on fixed-wing aircraft of all kinds.
From the beginning of their aeronautical work, the rhite bhaaiyo kendrit on vikasshil a vishwasaneey vidhi of payalat control as the kunjee to solving `` the flying problem ''.
This approach differed significantly from other experimenters of the samay jo put adhik jor on vikasshil shaktishaalee ingine.
Using a choti homebuilt hawa tunnel, the wrights bhi ekatrit adhik sateek aankada than koi pehle, enabling unhen to dizine and build wings and propellers that were more efficient than any before.
Their first U.S. patent, 821,393, did not claim invention of a udati yantra, lakin balki, the avishkaar of a pranali of aerodynamic control ki manipulated a flying machine 's surfaces.
They gained the mechanical skills essential for their success by working liye saalo in unke duukaan saath mudran dabaata, cycle, motors, and other machinery.
unke kaary saath cycle in particular bahekaave unke vishwaas ki an asthir gadee jaise a flying machine could be controlled and balanced with practice.
isse 1900 jabatak unke pehla sanchalit flite in let 1903, ve conducted extensive glider tests that also developed their skills as pilots.
Their bicycle shop karmchaaree charlie tailor became an mahatvapurn bhaag of the toli, bhawan unke pehla vayuyan engine in close collaboration with the brothers.
The rhite bhaaiyo ' aukaat as avishkaarak of the vayuyan rai maharoom vishay to counter-claims by various parties.
Much controversy persists over the anek spardhaa daawa of early aviators.

is aalekh is parichay the globe theatre of Shakespeare.

It 's a Wonderful Life is a 1946 American Christmas drama film produced and directed by Frank capra, aadhaarit on the choti story `` the mahanatam tohfa ``, jisase philip vine doren stern likhaa in 1939 or privately published in 1945.

Data godaam avlokan
In computing, a aankada godaam or enterprize aankada godaam ( dw, dwh, or edw ) is a database used for reporting and data analysis.
It is a central repository of data which is created by integrating aankada isse ek or adhik disparate strot.
Data warehouses store vartmaan as khub as aitihaasik aankada or hai prayukt liye bananaa trending reports for senior management reporting such as annual and quarterly comparisons.
The data stored in the warehouse hai aplod isse the operational pranaaliyon ( aise as vipanan, bikri etc., dikhaaya in the figure to the right ).
The data may pass through an operational aankada store liye atirikt parichaalan pehle ve hai prayukt in the dw liye reporting.
The typical ETL -aadharand aankada godaam upyog staging, aankada sangyojan, or abhigam paraton to house its key functions.
the staging parat or staging database stores raw data extracted from each of the disparate source data systems.
The integration layer integrates the disparate aankada set by transforming the aankada isse the staging parat praayah storing is roopantarit aankada in an operational data store ( ODS ) database.
The integrated data are then sthanantarit to yet another database, praayah pukaara the aankada godaam database, jahaan the aankada is arranged into hierarchical groups often called dimensions and into facts and aggregate facts.
the sangyojan of tathy or aayam is sometimes called a star schema.
The access layer helps upayokta retrieve aankada.
A data warehouse constructed from an integrated data source pranaaliyon karata nahin aavashyaktaa etl, staging databases, or operational aankada store databases.
The integrated data source pranaaliyon may be mana to be a bhaag of a vitarit operational data store layer.
Data federation methods or data abhasikaran vidhi may be prayukt to abhigam the vitarit ekikrut sorce aankada pranaaliyon to consolidate or kul aankada sidhe into the data warehouse database tables.
Unlike the ETL-based data warehouse, the integrated source data systems and the data warehouse are sab ekikrut chunki vahin is no parivartan of aiami or sandarbh aankada.
This integrated data warehouse architecture supports the drill down isse the kul aankada of the aankada godaam to the transactional aankada of the ekikrut sorce aankada systems.
aankada warehouses can be subdivided into data marts.
Data marts store subsets of aankada isse a warehouse.
This paribhaasha of the aankada godaam focuses on data storage.
The main source of the data is cleaned, transformed, cataloged and made available for use by managers and other business professionals for data mining, online vishleshnatmak prasanskaran, market shodh or nirnay support ( marakas & o'brien 2009 ).
However, the means to retrieve and analyze data, to extract, transform and load data, or to manage the aankada shabdkosh hai bhi mana anivaary components of a aankada warehousing system.
Many references to aankada warehousing upyog is broader context.
Thus, an expanded definition for data warehousing includes business intelligence tuls, tuls to nikaalen, roopantaran or lod aankada into the repository, or tuls to manage or retrieve metadata.
