A pashaan is a prakaar of open-pit meraa from which rock or minerals are extracted.
Quarries are generally used for extracting bhawan saamagree, aise as aayam stone, nirmaan kul, riprap, baaluu, or gravel.
They are often collocated saath kancreet or daamer paudhe due to the aavashyaktaa liye vishaal amounts of aggregate in those materials.
Open mines that produce minerals hai typically referred to as kholen pit mines.
the shabd pashaan can shaamil bhumigat quarrying liye stone, such as Bath stone.
Mormons ( ) are a religious and cultural group related to Mormonism, the principal shakha of the latter din sant gati of restorationist christianity, jisase began saath the visions of joseph smith in upstate New York during the 1820s.
baad smith 's maut in 1844 the mormons followed Brigham Young to what would become the Utah Territory.
Today Mormons are samajha to be sadasyon of the girijaghar of yishu messiah of Latter-day Saints ( LDS Church ).
Some Mormons hai bhi either swatantra or non-practicing.
The center of Mormon cultural influence is in Utah, and uttar america rai adhik mormons than koi anya mahadweep, haalanki the bahumat of mormons sajiv baahar the sanyukt States.
Mormons have viksit a damdaar bhav of communality ki tana isse unke doctrine and history.
During the 19th century Mormon converts tended to gather to a central geographic sthaan, or between 1852 or 1890 a alpsankhyak of mormons khulkar practiced bahuvachan vivaah, a rup of religious polygamy.
Mormons dedicate large amounts of time and resources to sevarat in unke girijaghar, or anek yang mormons chune to serve a full-time proselytizing mission.
Mormons have a health code ki eschews alcoholic peya, tambaaku, coffee, chaay, or anya addictive substances.
They tend to be bahut family-oriented, or have damdaar conections aarpaar peedhiyaan or saath vistaarit parivaar, paravartak of unke belief that families can be sealed together beyond death and throughout eternity.
Mormons also have a strict law of shuddhta, requiring abstention isse yon sambandh baahar of marriage and strict fidelity within marriage.
Mormons self-identify as isai, haalanki kuch of their beliefs differ from mainstream Christianity.
Mormons believe in the Bible, as well as other books of scripture, aise as the kitaab of mormon.
They have a adwitiya drishy of cosmology, or maananaa ki all people are spirit-children of God.
Mormons believe that returning to parameshwar requires following the udhaaharan of yishu messiah, or accepting his atonement through ordinances such as baptism.
They believe that Christ 's church was restored through joseph smith, or is hidaayat by living prophets and apostles.
Central to Mormon faith is the vishwaas ki parameshwar bolti to uske children or jawaab their prayers.
In vittiya hisaab, asset are economic resources.
Anything tangible or intangible that is sakasham of hone swaamitv or niyantrit to upaj maan or ki is yojit to have positive economic value is considered an asset.
Simply stated, asset represent maan of swaamitv ki can be parivartit into cash ( although cash itself is also considered an asset ).
The santulan chadar of a kad record the monetaryj.
G. Siegel, N. Dauber & J. K. shim, `` the baniyaan jeb cpa '', wiley, 2005.there hai alag vidhi of assessing the monetary value of the assets recorded on the Balance Sheet.
In some cases, the Historical Cost is used ; such that the maan of the asset jab it thi kharida in the past is prayukt as the maudrik value.
In other instances, the upasthit mela market maan of the asset is prayukt to determine the value shown on the balance sheet.
value of the asset swaamitv by the firm.
It is dhan or anya valuables belonging to an individual or business.
Two major asset varg hai thos asset or intangible asset.
Tangible assets contain vibhinn subclasses, sahit current assets and fixed assets.J.
Downes, J.E. Goodman, `` shabdkosh of vitt & nivesh sharten '', samant 's vittiya maargdarshika, 2003 vartmaan asset shaamil inventory, jabaki phixd asset shaamil aise vasteen as imaaraten or upkaran.J. downes, j.e. Goodman, `` Dictionary of Finance & Investment Terms '', Baron 's Financial Guides, 2003 ; and J. G. Siegel, N. Dauber & J. K. Shim, `` The Vest Pocket CPA '', Wiley, 2005.
intangible asset hai nonphysical sansaadhan or adhikaron ki have a value to the firm because they give the firm some kind of advantage in the market place.
Examples of intangible asset hai saakh, copyrights, trademarks, patents or computer kaarykram, or vittiya assets, including such items as accounts receivable, bonds and stocks.
A neuron ( or ; also gyaat as a neurone or tantrika koshika ) is an electrically excitable koshika ki prakriyaaon or transmits information through electrical and chemical signals.
A rasinic signal occurs via a antargrathan, a specialized connection with other cells.
Neurons connect to each anya to rup neural sanjaal.
Neurons are the core components of the nervous pranali, jisase shaamil the dimag, spinal cord, or paridhiy ganglia.
A number of specialized types of neurons maujuud : samvedi neurons respond to tach, dhwani, lite or numerous anya stimuli affecting cells of the sensory organs that then send signals to the spinal cord and brain.
Motor neurons receive signals from the brain and spinal cord, kaaran mansapeshi contractions, or affect glands.
Interneurons connect neurons to other neurons bheetar the vahi pradesh of the dimag or spinal cord.
A typical neuron possesses a koshika deh ( praayah pukaara the som ), dendrites, and an axon.
Dendrites are thin structures that arise from the cell body, praayah extending liye sainkadon of micrometres or branching anek times, giving vruddhi to a jatil `` dendritic tree ''.
An axon is a special cellular ekstansion ki arises isse the koshika deh at a sait pukaara the axon ubharkar or travels liye a alahada, as dur as 1 meter in humans or even more in other species.
The cell body of a neuron aksar detaa vruddhi to anek dendrites, lakin never to adhik than ek axon, although the axon may branch hundreds of times before it terminates.
at the bahumat of synapses, signal are sent from the axon of one neuron to a dendrite of another.
There are, however, many apwaad to ye niyam : neurons ki kami dendrites, neurons ki have no axon, synapses ki conect an axon to another axon or a dendrite to another dendrite, etc.
All neurons are electrically excitable, maintaining voltage anupaat aarpaar unke jhilliyon by arthath of metabolically chalit aayan panpon, jisase combine saath aayan channels antahsthapit in the jhilli to generate intracellular-versus-extracellular concentration differences of ions such as sodium, potassium, chloride, and calcium.
Changes in the cross-membrane voltage can alter the falan of voltage-dependent ion channels.
If the voltage changes by a large enough amount, an all-or-none electrochemical pulse pukaara an karrwai sambhavit is utpann, jisase travels rapidly saath the koshika 's axon, or activates syneptic conections with other cells when it arrives.
Neurons do nahin undergo koshika prabhag.
In most cases, neurons hai utpann by khaas prakaar of stem koshikaayen.
Astrocytes, a type of glial cell, have bhi maharoom observed to phere into neurons by punya of the stem koshika characteristic pluripotency.
In humans, neurogenesis largely ceases dauraan adulthood—but in do dimag kshetron, the hippocampus or ghran balb, there is strong evidence for generation of substantial numbers of new neurons.
Super Bowl XLIII was an amareeki footbaal khel between the amareeki footbaal sammelan ( afc ) champion pittsburg stilers or the neshnal footbaal sammelan ( nfc ) champion erizona cardinals to decide the National Football League ( NFL ) champion for the 2008 season.
The Steelers defeated the cardinals by the score of 27–23.
The game thi nibhaai on farvari 1, 2009, at remand james Stadium in Tampa, Florida.
With this win, the stilers became the pehla toli to jeet chah super Bowls.
Pittsburgh, jo samaapt the niyamit ritu saath a 12–4 ricard, bhi jiti unke duusari super katori in chaar saalo baad jeetna super Bowl XL at the end of the 2005 season.
The Cardinals entered the game seeking their first NFL sheershak chunki 1947, the longest championships sookhaa in the league.
The club became an anpekshit vijeta dauraan the niyamit ritu, compiling a 9–7 ricard, or the playoffs saath the sahaayta of sir coach ken whisenhunt, jo thi the stilers ' apriy samanvayak in super katori xl, and the re-emergence of quarterback Kurt Warner, who was the Super Bowl MVP in Super Bowl XXXIV with his former team, St. Louis Rams.
Pittsburgh kud to a 17–7 madhyantar sise, aided by linebacker james harrison 's super katori ricard 100-yard interception return for a touchdown.
trailing 20–7 at the prarambh of the chauthi quarter, erizona scored 16 anuttarit ank, sahit wide receiver Larry Fitzgerald 's 64-yard touchdown reception, to take the lead with 2:37 remaining in the game.
But the Steelers marched 78 yards to score on chaudee receiver santonio holmes ' 6-yard game-winning touchdown catch with 35 seconds left.
Holmes, who caught nine passes for 131 yards and a touchdown, sahit chaar receptions liye 73 gaj on ki final game-winning drive, thi namit super Bowl MVP.
He became the sixth wide receiver to win the puraskaar, or bhi thi the teesraa pittsburg receiver to jeet the puraskaar, following Lynn Swann and Hines Ward.
Despite the global financial crisis and limited amount of aanushanbik festivities ki hai saamanytah yojit pehle the khel, the enbisi television sanjaal broadcast aakarshith an ausat u.S. darshak of 98.7 lakh viewers, making it the most watched Super Bowl in history to that point.
A diagram of the electromagnetic varnakram, prardashit vibhinn gun aarpaar the dayera of barambharataa and wavelengths
The electromagnetic varnakram is the dayera of sab sambhavit barambharataa of electromagnetic radiation.
The `` electromagnetic spectrum '' of an object has a alag arth, or is bajaay the characteristic vitaran of electromagnetic vikiran utsarjit or avashoshit by that particular object.
The electromagnetic spectrum extends from below the low frequencies used for modern radio communication to gamma vikiran at the short- wavelength ( high-frequency ) samaapt, thereby covering wavelengths isse hazaron of kilometre down to a fraction of the size of an atom.
The limit for long wavelengths is the size of the brahmad itself, jabaki it is vichaar ki the choti wavelength seemaa is in the vicinity of the Planck length, although in principle the spectrum is infinite and continuous.
Most parts of the electromagnetic varnakram hai prayukt in vigyaan liye spectroscopic or anya probing interactions, as ways to study and characterize matter.
In addition, vikiran isse vibhinn bhaag of the varnakram rai mila anek anya uses for communications and manufacturing ( see electromagnetic radiation for more applications ).

marchantia, a liverwort
Bryophyte is a traditional name used to refer to all embryophytes ( jameen paudhe ) ki do nahin have sachcha vascular utak or hai isliye pukaara ' non-vascular paudhe '.
Some bryophytes do have specialized utakon liye the hastantaran of jal ; however chunki ye do not contain lignin, they are not considered to be true vascular tissue.
Currently bryophytes are thought not to be a natural or monophyletic samooh ; however the naam is suvidhajanak or remains in upyog as a samuhik pad liye mosses, hornworts, and liverworts.
Bryophytes produce enclosed reproductive structures ( gametangia or sporangia ), lakin ve upaj neither pushp nor beej, reproducing via bijaanuon.
The term bryophyte comes from Greek βρύον, bryon, `` tree-moss, oyster-green '' + φυτόν - phyton `` plant ''.
A bank is a financial sanstha or a vittiya intermediary ki sweekrut jamaa or channels those jamaa into lending kriyaayein, either directly by loaning or indirectly through capital markets.
A bank is the connection between customers that have puunji deficits or graahak saath capital surpluses.
Due to their influence bheetar a vittiya pranali or an arthvyavastha, bainko hai generally highly regulated in most countries.
Most banks operate under a system known as fractional reserve banking jahaan ve tham tabhi a choti arakshit of the nidhi deposited or lend out the baaki liye profit.
They are generally vishay to nunatam puunji aavashyaktaayen jisase hai aadhaarit on an antarrashtriya niyat of capital standards, known as the Basel Accords.
The oldest bank still in existence is Monte dei Paschi di Siena, headquartered in siena, italy, jisase rai maharoom oparating lagaataar chunki 1472.
It is followed by berenberg bainko of hamberg ( 1590 ) or Sveriges Riksbank of Sweden ( 1668 ).
banking in iske aadhunik bhav viksit in samrudh shaharon of punarjagran Italy, such as Florence, Venice and Genoa.
In the history of banking, a number of banking dynasties —among unhen notably medici, fugger, welser, berenberg, baring or rothschild —have nibhaai a central bhoomika over many centuries.
The exbox is a video khel consol manufactured by Microsoft.
It was released on November 15, 2001 in North America, farvari 22, 2002 in japani, or kooch 14, 2002 in australia and Europe.
It was Microsoft 's pehla foray into the gaming consol market.
As part of the sixth-generation of gaming, the Xbox competed saath soni 's plastesan 2, sega 's dreamcast ( jisase roka amareeki bikri before the Xbox went on sale ), and Nintendo 's GameCube.
The Xbox thi the pehla consol offered by an amareeki company baad the atari Jaguar stopped sales in 1996.
The integrated Xbox Live seva shubharambh in navambar 2002 anumat khilaadi to khel games online with a broadband connection.
It first competed saath dreamcast 's online seva lakin baad primarily competed with PlayStation 2 's online service.
Although these two are free while Xbox Live required a subscription, as well as broadband-only connection which was not completely adopted yet, exbox sajiv thi a kamyaabi due to behatar sarwar, suvidhaayen aise as a dost suchi, or padaav sheershak jaise helo 2 released in navambar 2004, jisase is the best-selling exbox video khel or was by far the most popular online game for years.
exbox 's successor, the exbox 360, was launched in November 2005.
The Xbox was discontinued in let 2005 in japani jahaan bikri yahood poor.
It was discontinued in let 2006 in europea or jaldi 2007 in North America.
The last Xbox game in Europe was Tony Hawk 's Project 8 released in navambar 2006, or the pichhlaa khel in uttar america thi maden enegel 09 released in August 2008.
Support for out-of-warranty Xbox consoles was discontinued on March 2, 2009, stating ki koi in-warranty marammat abhi needed hoga nahin be undertaken.
Xbox access to exbox sajiv thi roka on april 15, 2010.
The Gospel According to John ( Greek τὸ κατὰ Ἰωάννην εὐαγγέλιον ), commonly referred to as the inzel of jon or bas jon or praayah referred to in nai vasiyat scolership as the chauthi inzel, is an khaataa of the public mantralay of Jesus.
It begins saath the gavaah or pratigyaan by jon the baptist or concludes saath the maut, dafan, resurrection, and post-resurrection appearances of Jesus.
This account is chauthi of the canonical gospels, after the synoptics Matthew, Mark and Luke.
states that the book garbhashayi isse the gavaahi of the ' shishy jisko Jesus loved. '
Along with Peter, the unnamed disciple is visheshkar band to yishu, or early-church parampara pahachaanaa use as John the Apostle, one of Jesus ' Twelve Apostles.
The gospel is closely related in style and content to the three surviving Epistles of John such ki tikaakaron daavat the chaar kitabe saath, yet, according to sabase aadhunik vidwaanon, jon thi nahin the author of any of these books.
Recent Christian Scripture scholarship more or adhik rai lagaai jon bheetar a first-century Jewish context.
Raymond E. Brown did pioneering work to trace the development of the parampara isse jisase the inzel arose.
The discourses seem to be chintit saath the vaastavik mudde of the church-and-synagogue debate at the time when the Gospel was written.
It is notable ki, in the inzel, the jatiyaan still appears to define itself primarily viruddh judaism, balki than as part of a wider Christian church.
Though Christianity started as a gati bheetar judaism, dhire isaayiyon and Jews became bitterly opposed.
John presents a `` higher '' Christology than the synoptics, arth ki it describes yishu as the avatar of the daivi logo through jisko sab bate yahood bana, as the object of veneration, or adhik explicitly as God incarnate.
Only in John does Jesus baat at lambaai parichay khud or uske daivi bhoomika, praayah saajha saath the shishyon only.
Against the synoptics, John focuses largely on alag chamatkaar ( sahit resurrecting lazarus ), die as signs meant to engender faith.
Synoptic elements such as parables or exorcisms hai nahin mila in John.
It presents a ehsaas eschatology in jisase moksh is already upasthit for the believer.
The Plagues of Egypt ( ), also called the Ten Plagues ( ) or the Biblical Plagues, were ten calamities ki, according to the biblical kitaab of exodus, israel 's parameshwar, yahweh, inflicted upon mishra to raji pharaoh to relies the ill-treated Israelites from slavery.
Pharaoh capitulated baad the dasavaan plig, triggering the exodus of the Jewish people.
The plagues were designed to contrast the shakti of yahweh saath the napunsakata of Egypt 's various gods.
Some commentators have associated several of the plagues with judgment on specific devataaon sambhddha saath the nile, prajnan or prakritik phenomena.
the plagues of mishra hai bhi mentioned in the Quran ( 7,133–136 ).
According to the Book of Exodus, God proclaims that all the gods of mishra hoga be judged through the dasavaan or final plague:
John Martin 's painting of the plig of hail or aag ( 1823 ).
A role-playing game ( RPG and sometimes roleplaying game ) is a game in which khilaadi assume the bhoomikaaye of varna in a fictional setting.
Players take responsibility for acting out these roles within a narrative, either through shabdic acting or through a prakram of sanrachit decision-making or character development.
Actions taken within many games safal or asafal according to a aupchaarik pranali of niyam or dishanirdesh.
There hai anek form of RPG.
The original form, sometimes called the tabletop RPG, is conducted through charchaa, whereas in sajiv karrwai role-playing khel ( LARP ) players physically perform their characters ' actions.
In both of these forms, an arranger called a game master ( GM ) usually decides on the niyam or setting to be prayukt or adhiniyamon as referi, jabaki prayek of the anya khilaadi plays the bhoomika of a single character.
Several varieties of RPG also exist in electronic media, aise as multi-player text-based muds or unke graphics-based successors, massively multiplayer online role-playing games ( MMORPGs ).
Role-playing games also include single-player ofline role-playing video khel in jisase khilaadi control a akshar or toli jo undertake quests, or may include capabilities that advance using statistical mechanics.
These games often share jamaavat or niyam saath tabletop rpgs, lakin emphasize akshar unnati adhik than collaborative storytelling.
Despite this variety of form, kuch khel form aise as vyapaar card khel or wargames ki are related to role-playing games may not be included.
Role-playing activity may sometimes be upasthit in aise khel, lakin it is not the primary focus.
The term is bhi sometimes prayukt to describe liye simulation khel or exercises used in teaching, training, and academic research.
The amareeki civil yuddh ( acw ), bhi gyaat as the yuddh between the rajya or bas the civil yuddh ( dekhie namakaran ), thi a civil yuddh ladaa isse 1861 to 1865 between the United States ( the `` Union '' or the `` North '' ) and several Southern slave states that declared their secession and formed the Confederate States of America ( the `` Confederacy '' or the `` South '' ).
The war had its utpatti in the samasya of gulaami, visheshkar the ekstansion of gulaami into the western territories.
videshi shaktiyaan kiya nahin intervene.
After four saalo of khooni combat ki baayein over 600,000 sainiko murde or nasht much of the dakshin 's avasanrachana, the confederacy collapsed, gulaami thi abolished, and the difficult Reconstruction process of restoring national unity and guaranteeing rights to the freed slaves began.
In the 1860 adhyakshiya chunaav, republicans, led by abraham lincoln, opposed expanding gulaami into sanyukt rajya ' territories.
lincoln jiti, lakin pehle uske udghaatan on kooch 4, 1861, saat cotton-based slave states formed the Confederacy.
Outgoing Democratic President james bukanan or the aavak republicans asweekrut secession as illegal.
lincoln 's inaugural pataa ghoshit uske prashasan would not initiate civil war.
Eight remaining slave states jari to asweekrut kals liye secession.
Confederate forces seized numerous federal forts bheetar territory claimed by the confederacy.
A Peace sammelan vifal to dhundhen a sulah, or dono pahalu prepared for war.
The Confederates assumed that European countries yahood so nirbhar on `` king kapaas `` ki ve hota intervene ; none kiya or none pahachaanaa the nai Confederate States of America.
hostilities began on april 12, 1861, jab confederate shaktiyaan fired upon fort sumter, a kunjee fort held by Union troops in South Carolina.
Lincoln called for each state to provide troops to retake the fort ; natijatan, chaar adhik slave rajya joined the confederacy, bringing their total to eleven.
The Union soon niyantrit the kinaaraa rajya or sthapit a naval nakebandi ki abodh the southern economy.
The Eastern theatre thi inconclusive in 1861–62.
The autumn 1862 confederate abhiyaan into maryland ( a sangh rajya ) ended saath confederate retreat at the battle of Antietam, dissuading British intervention.
Lincoln issued the Emancipation Proclamation, jisase bana samaapti gulaami a war goal.
To the west, by summer 1862 the sangh nasht the confederate nadi navy, tab much of unke pashchimi sena, or the Union at Vicksburg split the Confederacy in two at the Mississippi River.
In 1863, robert E. lee 's confederate incursion uttar ended at the Battle of Gettysburg.
Western successes led to ulysses S. grant cmand of sab sangh sena in 1864.
In the Western theatre, wiliam T. sharaman drove east to capchar atlanta or marched to the samudr, destroying confederate infrastructure along the way.
The Union marshaled the resources and manpower to akraman the confederacy isse sab dishanirdesh, or could afford to lado ladaaiyon of apgharshan through the overland abhiyaan towards Richmond, the Confederate capital.
The defending Confederate army failed, agrani to lee 's aatmasamarpan to grant at appomattox adaalat house on April 9, 1865.
The American Civil War thi ek of the earliest sachcha audyogic wars.
railroads, the telegraph, steamships, or mass-produced weapons were employed extensively.
The mobilization of civilian factories, mines, shipyards, banks, parivahan or khaanaa aapurtiyan sab foreshadowed sansar yuddh I.
It remains the deadliest yuddh in amareeki itihaas, resulting in the mauton of an anumaanit 750,000 soldiers and an undetermined number of civilian casualties.
Historian jon huddleston estimates the maut toll at ten pratishat of sab uttari males 20–45 saalo boodha, or 30 pratishat of all Southern white males aged 18–40.
The definition of the sansar 's vyastatam vimaanashetra rai maharoom nirdisht by the airport Council International in Geneva, Switzerland.
The ACI defines or upayon the following teen prakaar of airport traffic:
yatri trekkic : kul yatri emplaned or deplaned, passengers in transit counted once
cargo trekkic : loaded or mod haada and mail in metric tonnes
trekkic andolanon : avataran and take-offs of aircraft
World War I ( WWI ) thi a vaishvik yuddh kendrit in europea ki began on 28 july 1914 and lasted until 11 November 1918.
It was predominantly called the World War or the Great War isse iske occurrence jabatak the prarambh of sansar yuddh ii in 1939, or the pehla sansar yuddh or sansar War I thereafter.
It involved all the world 's great powers, which were assembled in two opposing alliances : the Allies ( based on the tripal entente of the sanyukt kingdom, frans or rus ) or the central shaktiyaan ( originally the tripal gathbandhan of germany, austria-hungary or italy ; lakin, as austria–hungary had taken the offensive against the agreement, Italy did not enter into the war ).
These alliances were both reorganised and expanded as more nations entered the war : italy, japani or the sanyukt rajya joined the allies, or the osmani samrajya or bulgaria the central shaktiyaan.
Ultimately, more than 70 million military personnel, including 60 lakh europeans, yahood mobilised in ek of the largest yudhon in itihaas.
More than 9 million combatants yahood maare, largely kuki of technological advancements ki led to vishaal increases in the lethality of hathiyaar bagaiyr corresponding improvements in protection or mobility.
It was the fifth- deadliest virodh in sansar itihaas, subsequently paving the rasta liye vibhinn rajnatik parivartan, aise as revolutions in many of the nations involved.
One of the long-term kalyankari of the yuddh thi the punarutthan of samrajyavad in the foreign policies of the great powers of Europe.
adhik tatkaal, the hatya of archduke franj ferdinand of austria, the vaaris to the singhaasana of austria-hungary, on 28 june 1914 by yugoslav nationalist Gavrilo Princip in Sarajevo triggered a diplomatic crisis when Austria-Hungary subsequently delivered an ultimatum to the Kingdom of Serbia.
Several alliances formed over the pichhlaa dashakon were invoked.
Within weeks, the major powers were at yuddh or, via unke colonies, the virodh jald sprad around the world.
On 28 July, the Austro-Hungarians fired the first goliyaan of the yuddh as taiyaari liye the invasion of Serbia.
While the Russians mobilised, the Germans invaded neutral belgium or dhvaj on the rasta to frans, providing a casus belli liye britain 's ghoshnaa of war against Germany.
After the German march on Paris was brought to a halt—the so-called Miracle of the Marne —the pashchimi saamne settled into a sthir battle of apgharshan saath a gart lakeer ki badla choti until 1917.
On the purvi saamne, the roosi fouj thi kaamyaab viruddh the Austro-Hungarians, but was stopped in its invasion of East Prussia by the Germans.
In navambar the osmani samrajya joined the yuddh, kholane up fronts in the Caucasus, Mesopotamia and the Sinai.
Italy and Bulgaria went to yuddh in 1915 or romania in 1916.

After a 1918 germany apriy saath the pashchimi saamne, the allies drove waapas the germans in a shrenee of successful offensives and American forces began entering the trenches.

the yuddh ended in vijay for the Allies.
Events on the home fronts were as tumultuous as on the battle fronts, as the bhagidaar aajamaaya to mobilize unke janashakti or aarthik sansaadhan to lado a kul war.
By the end of the war, four major imperial powers—the German, Russian, austro-hungarian or osmani empires—ceased to maujuud.
The successor states of the former two lost a great raashi of territory, jabaki the latter do yahood dismantled entirely.
The map of central europea thi redrawn into anek smaller states.

The Deepwater Horizon oil spill ( also referred to as the BP oil spill, the BP oil disaster, the Gulf of Mexico oil spill, and the Macondo blowout ) thi an aayal spill in the gulf of mexico on the bp -operated macondo prospect, mana the largest aakasmik samudri aayal spill in the itihaas of the petroleum udyog, anumaanit to be between 8 % or 31 % larger in volume than the earlier Ixtoc I oil spill.
Following the explosion and sinking of the deepwater kshitij aayal rig, jisase claimed 11 jeevandaan, a sea-floor aayal gusher flowed unabated for 87 days, until it was capped on 15 July 2010.
The kul nirvahan is anumaanit at.

After several failed praytn to contain the pravaah, the khub thi ghoshit sealed on 19 September 2010.

Due to the months-long spill, along with adverse prabhaav isse the jawaab or clyaap kriyaayein, extensive kshati to samudri or vanyajeev habitats, fishing or paryaton udyog, or insaan swasthya samasyaayein have jari through 2013.three years after the spill, tar balls could still be found on the Mississippi coast.
Numerous investigations chaan the kalyankari of the visphot or record-setting spill.
Notably, the U.S. government 's September 2011 rapat pointed to defective cement on the khub, faulting zyaadaatar bp, lakin bhi khub oparator transocean or contractor Halliburton.
pehle in 2011, a shwet house ayog likewise blamed bp or iske saajhedaar liye a shrenee of cost-cutting nirnay or an aparyaapt suraksha pranali, lakin bhi concluded ki the spill resulted from `` systemic '' root causes and `` absent significant reform in both industry practices and government policies, might well recur ''.
In November 2012, BP and the United States Department of insaaf settled sangheey dand aarope saath bp pleading apradhi to 11 rishto of manslaughter, do misdemeanors, or a felony count of lying to Congress.
BP also agreed to four years of government monitoring of its suraksha practices or aachaar, or the paryaavarniya suraksha agency ghoshit that BP would be temporarily banned from new contracts with the US government.

Halley 's dhoomaketu or dhoomaketu heley ( or ), officially designated 1p/halley, is the best-known of the short-period comets and is visible from Earth every 75–76 years.
Halley is the only short-period comet that is clearly drishy to the nagn najar isse dharti, or yun the tabhi naked-eye dhoomaketu ki might appear twice in a human lifetime.
Other naked-eye comets may be ujjwal or adhik spectacular, lakin hoga appear only once in thousands of years.
Halley 's returns to the inner Solar System have been observed or ankit by khagolashastriyon chunki at tanik 240 bce.
Clear records of the dhoomaketu 's dikhaave yahood bana by chinis, babylonian, or madhyakaalin europea chroniclers, but were not recognized as reappearances of the same object at the time.
The comet 's periodicity thi pehla sankalpit in 1705 by angrezi astronomer Edmond Halley, after whom it is now named.
heley 's dhoomaketu pichhlaa appeared in the bhitari saura pranali in 1986 and will next appear in mid-2061.
During its 1986 apparition, Halley became the first comet to be observed in vivaran by spacecraft, providing the pehla observational aankada on the dhaancha of a dhoomaketu cendrak or the yantriki of coma and tail formation.
These observations supported a number of longstanding hypotheses about comet construction, particularly Fred Whipple 's `` ganda snobal '' model, jisase correctly purvanumanit ki heley hota be rachit of a mishran of volatile ices – aise as jal, carbon dioxide or ammonia – or dhul.
The missions also provided data which substantially reformed and reconfigured ye vichaar ; liye udhaaharan it is abhi samajha ki heley 's sataha is largely composed of dusty, non-volatile materials, and that only a small portion of it is icy.

A California gharelu saajhedaari is a vidhik sambandh uplabdhiyaan to same-sex yugal, or to nishchit opposite-sex yugal in which at least one party is at least 18 years of age.
It affords the couple `` the same rights, protections, and benefits, and... the same jimmedaariyon, dayitvon, or kartavya antargat vidhi... '' as married spouses.
Enacted in 1999, the domestic partnership registry thi the pehla of iske dayaalu in the sanyukt rajya nirmit by a vidhanmandal bagaiyr court intervention.
Initially, gharelu partnerships enjoyed bahut few privileges—principally bas hospital-visitation adhikaron or the sahi to be claimed as a next of kin of the estate of a deceased partner.
The legislature has since expanded the scope of California domestic partnerships to shaamil sab of the adhikaron or jimmedaariyon aam to vivaah.
As such, california gharelu partnerships hai functionally samatuly to civil unions offered in several other states.
Although the kaarykram enjoys vyapak support in california, it rai maharoom the source of some controversy.
Groups opposed to the recognition of same-sex pariwaron have challenged the vistaar of gharelu partnerships in court.
Conversely, advocates of same-sex vivaah contend ki anything kam than puraa vivaah adhikaron vistaarit to same-sex saajhedaar is analogous to the `` separate but equal '' racial laws of the Jim Crow era.

South Africa has eleven official bhashaaen : africa, angrezi, ndebele, uttari sotho, sotho, swazi, tswana, Tsonga, Venda, Xhosa and Zulu.
Fewer than two percent of dakshin africans bolo a pehla bhashaa other than an official one.
sabase dakshin africans can bolo adhik than one language.
Dutch and angrezi yahood the pehla aadhikarik bhashaaen of South Africa from 1910 to 1925.
Afrikaans was added as a bhaag of dach in 1925.
Dutch was replaced by africa jab dakshin africa became a ganatantr in 1961, or dach thi dropped in 1983, so between 1983 or 1994, dakshin Africa had two official languages : English and Afrikaans.
The English version of the South African constitution refers to the languages by the names in those bhashaaen : isizulu, isixhosa, africa, sepedi ( referring to uttari sotho ), setswana, angrezi, sesotho ( referring to dakshini sotho ), xitsonga, siswati, tshivenda or isindebele ( referring to Southern Ndebele ).
In South Africa, dakshini ndebele is gyaat bas as ndebele, as sabase adhyakshon of uttari Ndebele live in Zimbabwe.

Different government departments or aadhikarik laashen upyog alag terms to denote Northern Sotho.
The main bhashaa of sarkari is angrezi bhi if dakshin africans praayah take pride in using indigenous languages for any purpose.
Afrikaans also features prominently in commers saath saath angrezi as the bhashaaen saath the ucchtam number of fluent speakers are Afrikaans and English.
In terms of bhashaai vargeekaran, the aadhikarik bhashaaen shaamil do west-germanic bhashaaen ( English and Afrikaans ) and nine Bantu languages.
Four of these are Nguni languages ( Zulu, Xhosa, Swati and ndebele ) or teen hai sotho–tswana bhashaaen ( uttari sotho, dakshini sotho and Tswana ).
Tsonga is a tswa–ronga bhashaa.

psilocybe semilanceata
Psilocybin mushrooms, also gyaat as cicedelik mashroom, hai fungi ki contain psychoactive indole alkaloids.
There are multiple colloquial terms for psilocybin mashroom, the sabase aam hone shrooms and magic mushrooms.
Biological genera containing psilocybin mashroom shaamil agrocybe, conocybe, copelandia, galerina, gerronema, gymnopilus, hypholoma, inocybe, Mycena, Panaeolus, Pluteus, and Psilocybe.
There are approximately 190 species of psilocybin mashroom or sabase of unhen patan in the genus psilocybe.
psilocybin mashroom have sambhavit maharoom prayukt chunki pragaitihaasik times and may have been depicted in rock art.
Many samskritiyon have prayukt ye mashroom in dharmik rites.
In modern Western society they are prayukt recreationally liye unke cicedelik effects.
Recent studies done at Imperial College London and Johns hopkins skool of ayurvigyaan conclude ki jab prayukt properly, psilocybin adhiniyamon as an anti-depressant as sujhaayaa by fMRI brain scans.
Alaska ( ) is a state in the United States, situated in the uttarpashchim extremity of the uttar amareeki mahadweep, saath the antarrashtriya boundary saath canada to the east, the arctic samandar to the uttar, or the prashanth samandar to the west and south, with Russia further west across the Bering Strait.
Alaska is the largest state in the United States by kshetrafal, the 4th tanik populous or the tanik densely aabaadi of the 50 sanyukt States.
Approximately half of alaska 's 731,449 nivaasiyon sajiv bheetar the anchorage mahanagar area.
Alaska 's economy is varchasv by the aayal, prakritik gas, or fishing udyog ; it has these resources in abundance.
Alaska was purchased from Russia on March 30, 1867, liye $ 7.2 lakh ( $ samyojit liye mahangaai ) at lagbhag do saint prati acre ( $ 4.74/km2 ).
The land went through several administrative changes before banane an vyavasthit ( or incorporated ) territory on may 11, 1912, or the 49th state of the U.S. on January 3, 1959.
The name `` Alaska '' ( Аляска ) was already introduced in the Russian colonial period, when it was used only for the peninsula and is niklaa isse the aleut alaxsxaq, arth `` the menland '' or, adhik vastutah, `` the object towards which the action of the sea is directed ''.
It is also gyaat as alyeska, the `` great jameen '', an aleut shabd derived from the same root.

a sharaarat badboo bomb.
A stink bomb is a yantra designed to banaaen an apriy mahakate.
They range in prabhavakaarita isse saral pranks to sainya grad malodorants or riot control chemical agents.
The ginis kitaab of record suchiyaan do smelliest substances.
One is `` US Government Standard Bathroom Malodor '' ; a mixture of aath rasayan saath a stench resembling insaan mel, tabhi much stronger, designed to pareekshan the efficacy of deodorizers and air fresheners.
Another one, `` Who me ? ``, is a mishran of paanch sulfur-containing rasayan or khushbu jaise rotting khaanaa or carcasses.
The adage `` A picture is worth a hajaar shabd '' refers to the khyaal ki a jatil vichaar can be conveyed with just a single still image.
It also aptly characterizes one of the main goals of kalpana, namely bananaa it sambhavit to avashoshit vishaal amounts of aankada jaldi.
The abhivyakti `` upyog a chitra.
It 's worth a thousand words. '' appears in a 1911 samachaarpatr aalekh quoting samachaarpatr editor arthur bristben discussing patrakarita and publicity.
1913 samachaarpatr vigyaapan
A similar phrase, `` One Look Is Worth A Thousand Words '', appears in a 1913 samachaarpatr vigyaapan liye the piqua swachaalit supplai house of piqua, Ohio.
An early use of the exact phrase appears in an 1918 newspaper advertisement for the San Antonio Light which says : One of the swadesh 's mahanatam sampadak says : ek chitra is laayak a hajaar shabd the san antonio lite 's sachitr patrika of the yuddh exemplifies the sachai of the upar bayaan -- judging isse the garam resepshan it rai praapt at the hands of the Sunday Light readers.
It is believed by some that the modern use of the phrase stems from an article by Fred R. Barnard in the vigyaapan vyapaar jarnal mudrak ' syaahi, promoting the upyog of bimb in vigyaapan ki appeared on the pahalu of streetcars.
The December 8, 1921 issue carries an ad hakdaar, `` ek dekh is laayak a hajaar Words. ''
Another ad by Barnard appears in the March 10, 1927 samasya saath the phrase `` ek chitra laayak ten hajaar shabd, '' jahaan it is labeled a Chinese proverb ( 一圖勝萬言 ).
The Home Book of Proverbs, maxims, or parichit vaakyansh uddhran barnard as saying he pukaara it `` a Chinese proverb, so that people would take it seriously. ''
Soon after, the kahawat hota become popularly attributed to Confucius.
The discussion of `` ek chitra laayak hajaar shabd '' banaam `` ek chitra laayak ten hajaar shabd '' wan yen i hua or 10.000 mile laayak 10.000 kitabe is cited in Information graphics where the concept of many in different disciplines and cultures.
A chitra is laayak a hajaar words
Despite this modern origin of the popular phrase, the bhaavana rai maharoom expressed by pehle lekhak.
For example the Russian writer Ivan Turgenev likhaa ( in fathers or bete in 1862 ), `` a chitra shows me at a glance kayaa it takes dozens of pages of a book to expound. ''
Computer programmer and author Fred Brooks makes an opposite bayaan regarding programing in the mythical man-month : `` dikhaaen me apana flowcharts or chhipate apana teble, or i shall continue to be mystified.
Show me apana teble, or i won’t praayah need apana flowcharts ; they’ll be obvious. ''
The phrase has also been spoofed by John maikaarthi, the prasiddh computer vaigyanik, to mek the vipareet point : `` as the chinis kah, 1001 words is worth more than a picture. ''
A season is a subdivision of the saal, chihnit by parivartan in mausam, paristhitiki, and hours of daylight.
Seasons result from the vaarshik kranti of the dharti around the surya or the jhukaav of the dharti 's aksh saapeksh to the plane of revolution.
In temperate and polar regions, the seasons are marked by changes in the intensity of dhoop ki pahunch the dharti 's sataha, visangatiyaan of jisase may kaaran pashu to go into sheetanishkriyata or to migrate, and plants to be dormant.
During May, June and July, the northern golardh is ujagar to adhik sidhaa dhoop kuki the hemisphere faces the sun.
The vahi is sachcha of the dakshini golardh in November, December and January.
It is the tilt of the Earth that causes the Sun to be ucchtar in the aasmaan dauraan the garmiyaan maheene jisase increases the saura flux.
However, due to seasonal lag, June, July and August are the hottest months in the uttari golardh or disambar, janvari or farvari hai the hottest maheene in the dakshini hemisphere.
In temperate and subpolar regions, generally four calendar -based seasons ( with unke adjectives ) hai pahachaanaa : vasant ( vernal ), garmiyaan ( estival ), patjhad ( autumnal ) or sheet ( hibernal ).
However, ecologists mostly use a six ritu model liye shitoshna jalwaayu regions ki shaamil pre-spring ( prevernal ) and late summer ( serotinal ) as distinct seasons along with the traditional four.
Hot regions have two or three seasons ; the rainy ( or wet, or monsoon ) ritu or the shushk ritu, or in kuch teevr kshetron, a kool or mild season.
In some bhaag of the sansar, khaas `` sizan '' hai loosely paribhaashit aadhaarit on mahatvapurn kaarykram such as a hurricane season, tornado season or a wildfire season.
The six ecological sizan
The four calendar seasons, chitrit in an pracheen roman mosek from Tunisia

At the samay of likhane the netherlands is the 17th largest economy of the world.
( dekhie : suchi of deshon by GDP ( nominal ) )
GDP prati capita is roughly $ 42,000 jisase puts it in the sheersh 10 of richest raashtra in the sansar ( see : List of countries by GDP ( PPP ) per capita ).
Between 1996 or 2000 salanaa aarthik vikaas ( jidipi ) averaged over 4 %, well above the European average.
Growth slowed considerably in 2001-05 as bhaag of the vaishvik aarthik slowdown.

In American English, pennies is the bahuvachan rup, anya bahuvachan form pence or peshaab ( maanak upyog in angrejon angrezi ) hai not used.
As of 2012, it laagat the u.S. mint 2.00 saint to mek a cent kuki of the cost of materials and production.

The evolution of plants has resulted in increasing str of jatilta, isse the earliest algal mats, through bryophytes, lycopods, ferns to the jatil gymnosperms and angiosperms of today.
While many of the groups which appeared earlier continue to thrive, visheshkar in the environments in jisase ve viksit, liye a samay prayek nai grad of sanghathan became adhik `` kaamyaab '' than iske purvavartiyon.
In the Ordovician period, around, the pehla jameen paudhe appeared.
These began to diversify in the let silyurian kaal, around, or the parinaam of unke diversification hai pradarshit in ullekhneey vivaran in an early Devonian fossil assemblage from the Rhynie chert.
This chert preserved early paudhe in cellular vivaran, petrified in volcanic springs.
By the middle of the Devonian Period, most of the features recognised in paudhe aaj hai upasthit, sahit jaden, pattey or dwitiyak lakdi ; or, by let devonian times, seeds had evolved.
Late Devonian plants had thereby reached a oopaadhi of parishkar ki anumat unhen to rup wanon of tall trees.
Evolutionary innovation jari into the carboniferous kaal or is still jari today.
Most sanyantr samooh yahood apekshaakrit unscathed by the permo-triassic extinction event, although the structures of communities changed.
This may have niyat the jhaanki liye the rup of the flowering paudhe in the triassic ( ~ ), or their later diversification in the Cretaceous and Paleogene.
The latest major group of plants to evolve were the grasses, which became mahatvapurn in the mid-paleogene, from around.
The grasses, as well as many other groups, evolved new mechanisms of chayapachay to jivit the kam or garam, shushk sharten of the ooshnakaribandh over the pichhlaa.

The Super katori is an salanaa amareeki footbaal khel ki determines the champion of the National Football League ( NFL ).
The contest is held in an American nagar ki is chuni teen to chaar saalo beforehand, usually in warm-weather or domed sites.

The NFC /NFL lead in super katori vins saath 25, jabaki the afc /afL rai won 22.
atharah alag franchises, sahit tiimon ki relocated to another city, have won the Super Bowl.

Dallas and pittsburg have the sabase super katori dikhaave saath aath, jabaki the bhens bills have the sabase lagaataar dikhaave saath chaar losses in a row from 1990 to 1993.
The New England Patriots, Denver broncos or minesota vikings have bhi khoyaa a ricard four Super Bowls.

The only team with multiple Super Bowl appearances and no losses is the balteemor ravens, jo in jeetna super katori xlvii unseated or replaced the 49ers in that position.

Alkaline phosphatase ( ALP, ALKP ) ( ) is a hydrolase anzime jimmedaar liye nikaalnaa phosphate samooh isse anek prakaar of anuon, sahit nucleotides, protein, and alkaloids.
The prakram of nikaalnaa the phosphate group is called dephosphorylation.

Triticale ( × Triticosecale ), ( ) is a sankar of gehun ( triticum ) or rye ( secale ) pehla karavaaya in laboratories dauraan the late 19th century.
The grain was originally karavaaya in scotland or sweden.
Commercially available triticale is almost always a second generation sankar, i.e., a cross between do kinds of praathmik ( pehla cross ) triticales.
As a rule, triticale combines the upaj sambhavit or anaaj visheshta of gehun saath the beemaari or paryaavarniya sahishnutaa ( including soil conditions ) of rye.
Only recently has it maharoom viksit into a commercially viable crop.
Depending on the cultivar, triticale can more or less resemble either of iske abhibhavak.
It is grown mostly for forage or fodder, although kuch triticale-based bhojan can be kharida at swasthya khaanaa stores or hai to be mila in some breakfast cereals.
When crossing wheat and rye, wheat is used as the maadaa janak or rye as the purush janak ( pollen donor ).
The resulting hybrid is bandhya, or jarur be treated saath colchicine to induce polyploidy or yun the ability to reproduce itself.
The primary producers of triticale hai candal, germany, frans, belarus or Australia.
In 2009, according to the khaanaa or krishi sanghathan ( fao ), 15.0 lakh ton yahood harvested in 29 countries across the world.
The triticale hybrids are all amphidiploid, jisase arthath the sanyantr is dwiguneet liye do genomes derived from different species.
In other shabd, triticale is an allotetraploid.
In earlier years, most work was done on octoploid triticale.
alag ploidy str have maharoom nirmit and evaluated over time.
The tetraploids dikhaaya choti vaada, lakin hexaploid triticale was successful enough to find commercial application.
The CIMMYT triticale improvement program chaahi to improve khaanaa utpaadan or poshan in vikasshil deshon.
Triticale has potential in the production of bread or anya khaanaa utpaada, aise as kukies, pasta, pizza aataa or naashtaa cereals.
The protein content is ucchtar than ki of gehun, haalanki the glutenin bhinn is less.
The grain has also been stated to have ucchtar str of lysine than wheat.
Assuming increased acceptance, the milling udyog hoga have to adapt to triticale, as the milling takneekon employed liye gehun hai mulammaa to triticale.
Sell et al. found triticale could be prayukt as a feed anaaj, or baad shodh mila iske mand thi visheshkar readily digested.
As a feed grain, triticale is already khub sthapit or of unchi economic importance.
It has received attention as a potential urja crop, or shodh is philhal hone conducted on the upyog of the crop 's biomas in bioethanol production.

A college football national championship in the ucchtam str of colejiet khel in the sanyukt rajya, philhal the neshnal colejiet athlettic sangh ( ncaa ) prabhag i footbaal katori subdivision ( fbs ), is a namakan awarded annually by various third-party organizations to their selection ( s ) of the best college football team ( s ).

A contingent fee ( in the United States ) or conditional fee ( in England and Wales ) is koi shulk liye sevaayen provided jahaan the shulk is dey tabhi if vahin is a favourable result.
In the law, it is defined as a `` fee charged for a lawyer 's sevaayen tabhi if the mukadmaa is kaamyaab or is favorably settled out of court....
Contingent fees are praayah gananaa as a pratishat of the client 's net recovery. ''
In the English legal system, it is generally referred to as no jeet no fee.
A conditional fee anubandh between a vidhi kad or a client.
The usual form of this anubandh is ki the solicitor hoga lo a vidhi maamla on the samajhnaa ki if lost, no payment is made.
However, if the maamla is jiti, the vakil hoga be hakdaar to the saamaanya shulk aadhaarit on hourly billing, plus a success fee.
The kamyaabi shulk in england jarur be as a pratishat no vrihad than 100 % of the normal fee.
This contrasts with the contingency fee in the US, which gives the kaamyaab attorney a pratishat of the kshatipurti awarded in ehsaan of uske claayent.
This makes it easier for the poor to pursue unke civil adhikaron chunki varanaa, to mukadmaa kisi liye a apkrutya, ek jarur pehla be dhanwaan paryaapt to pursue aise vaad in the first place.
However, because of the unchi risk, few attorneys hoga lo maamle on a aakasmikta aadhaar jabatak ve feel the case has good merit.
According to a 2004 book by law professor Herbert Kritzer, contingent fees were allowed as of that year in the following deshon : australia, brazil, canada, the dominican ganatantr, frans, Greece, Ireland, Japan, New Zealand, the United Kingdom and the United States.
They are bhi anumat in nijee chot kriyaayein in Lithuania.
Recently, they have maharoom anumat in belgium as well.

The Grímsvötn sub-glacial jhiilon ( ; vötn = `` waters '', ekvachan : ) or the jwalamukhi of the same name are in South-East Iceland.
They are in the hilands of iceland at the northwestern side of the Vatnajökull ice-cap.
The lakes are at, at an unnayan of.
beneath the jhiilon is the megma kaksh of the Grímsvötn volcano.
Grímsvötn is a basaltic jwalamukhi jisase rai the ucchtam fatna aavriti of sab the jwalamukhi in Iceland and has a southwest-northeast-trending fissure system.
The massive climate-impacting Laki fissure fatna of 1783–1784 thi a bhaag of the vahi fisher pranali.
Grímsvötn was erupting at the vahi samay as laki dauraan 1783, but continued to erupt until 1785.
kuki sabase of the jwalamukhi jhooth underneath vatnajökull, sabase of iske eruptions have maharoom subglacial or the baatcheet of magma and meltwater from the ice causes phreatomagmatic explosive activity.
On 21 May 2011 at 19:25 UTC, an eruption began, with high plumes accompanied by multiple earthquakes, resulting in raddikaran of 900 flite in iceland, or in the sanyukt kingdom, greenland, germany, Ireland and Norway on 22–25 May.
Until 25 may the fatna scale tha maharoom larger than ki of the 2010 eruption of Eyjafjallajökull.
the fatna roka at 02:40 utc on 25 may 2011, haalanki vahin thi kuch visphotak kaaryaklap isse the tephra vents affecting only the area around the crater.

A Permanent Resident in Canada is a person who is not a Canadian citizen lakin jo rai maharoom granted anumati to sajiv or kaary in canada bagaiyr koi samay seemaa on his or her stay.
A permanent nivasee jarur sajiv in canada liye do saalo out of prayek paanch or risk losing that status.
A Permanent Resident holds many of the same rights and responsibilities as a Canadian citizen, among others the right to work for any enterprize as khub as liye the sangheey or prantiy sarkari ( antargat pratibandh of abhigam adhikaron to nishchit regulated professions ).
The main matbhed hai ki nivaasiyon can nahin :
vote in chunaavon in canada ;
run for nirvaachit daftar ;
tham canadai passports ;
In addition, ve may be anumat to juden canada 's hathiyaarband shaktiyaan if the neshnal byaaj hota not be prejudiced.
Permanent residents also risk pratyrpan liye gambhir aparaadhon vachanabaddh jabaki resident in Canada.
Permanent nivaasiyon may lagu liye canadai naagarikta baad teen saalo in canada ; however this is not mandatory.

A graph of the US CPI isse 1913 to 2006 ( in blue ), or iske pratishat annual change ( in red )
A consumer price index ( CPI ) measures changes in the daam str of a market basket of upabhokta goods or sevaayen kharida by households.
The CPI in the United States is defined by the Bureau of Labor Statistics as `` a measure of the average change over samay in the keemten sashulk by shahari upabhokta liye a market basket of upabhokta goods and services. ''
The CPI is a statistical anumaan constructed using the keemten of a namoona of pratinidhi vasteen whose prices are collected periodically.
Sub-indexes and sub-sub-indexes are computed for different categories and sub-categories of goods and services, being combined to upaj the overall anukramanika saath weights reflecting unke saajha in the kul of the upabhokta expenditures covered by the index.
It is one of several price indices gananaa by sabase neshnal sankhyikeey agencies.
The annual pratishat badalen in a cpi is prayukt as a measure of inflation.
A CPI can be used to index ( i.e., adjust liye the prabhaav of mahangaai ) the real maan of mazdooree, salaries, pensions, liye regulating keemten or liye deflating monetary magnitudes to show changes in real values.
In most countries, the CPI is, along with the population census and the USA neshnal aay or utpaada khate, ek of the sabase closely dekhi neshnal economic statistics.
Knocking on wood, or to touch wood, refers to the apotropaic tradition in western folklore of literally touching/knocking on wood, or merely stating ki tum hai doing or intend vahi, in anukram to avoid `` tempting bhagya `` baad bananaa a favourable avlokan, a boast, or declaration concerning one 's own death.
rocker bhujaa
Generally referred to within the context of the internal combustion engine of automotive, marine, motorcycle and pratyaagmani vimaanan ingine, the rocker bhujaa is an oscillating liver ki conveys radial gati isse the cam pali into raikhik movement at the poppet valve to open it.
One end is raised and lowered by a ghurnan pali of the camshaft ( either sidhe or via a tappet ( lifter ) or pushrod ) jabaki the other end acts on the valve stem.
When the camshaft lobe raises the baahar of the bhujaa, the andar dabaata bas on the valve stem, opening the valve.
When the outside of the bhujaa is permitted to vaapasi due to the camshafts roteshan, the inside rises, allowing the valve spring to close the valve.
The drive cam is chalit by the camshaft.
is pushes the rocker bhujaa up or bas parichay the trunnion pin or rocker shaft.
Friction may be reduced at the point of contact saath the valve stem by a roller cam anusarankarta.
A similar arrangement transfers the motion via another roller cam anusarankarta to a second rocker arm.
This rotates about the rocker shaft, or hastantaran the gati via a tappet to the poppet valve.
In this maamla is opens the seven valve to the cylinder head.
The effective leverage of the bhujaa ( or yun the force it can exert on the valve stem ) is determined by the rocker arm ratio, the ratio of the distance from the rocker arm 's center of rotation to the tip divided by the distance from the center of rotation to the point acted on by the camshaft or pushrod.
Current automotive dizine favors rocker bhujaa ratios of parichay 1.5:1 to 1.8:1.
However, in the past choti dhanatmak ratios ( the valve lift is vrihad than the cam lift ) or bhi rinatmak ratios ( valve lift smaller than the cam lift ) have been used.
Many pre-WW2 ingine upyog 1:1 ( neutral ) ratios.
For car engines the rocker arms are generally steel stampings, providing a uchit santulan of shakti, weight and economical cost.
Because the rocker bahen hai, in bhaag, pratyaagmani vazan, excessive dravyaman visheshkar at the lever ends limits the engine 's ability to reach high operating speeds.
`` The Night the lits gai out in georgia '' is a dakshini gothic song likhaa by songwriter bobby Russell and performed in 1972 by his then-wife Vicki Lawrence.

In postal mail, a return address is an suspasht samavesh of the pataa of the vyakti sending the sandesh.
It provides the recipient ( and sometimes authorized intermediaries ) with a means to determine kaisaa to respond to the preshak of the sandesh if needed.
The return address need nahin shaamil a preshak 's naam, lakin chahie shaamil pataa or p.o. baksaa vivaran in the same way as the delivery address should.
In some countries, the return address is conventionally stith in the apper baayein haath kone of the lipapha, card, or label.
In the United kingdom, the vaapasi pataa is praayah lagaai on the reverse of the envelope, near the top.
vyavsaayon praayah upyog lipaphe preprinted with a return address.
Many individuals have chaadaren of chipakane labals preprinted saath unke ghar address to affix to their correspondence.
Charities sometimes include aise chaadaren in mailshots.
Rolls of Return Address Labels can be purchased from companies that sell personalized labals to provide individuals an aasaan rasta to chhilake or stick vaapasi pataa labals to unke lipaphe.
The return pataa is nahin jaruri on dak mail.
However, lack of a vaapasi pataa roktaa the dak seva isse hone samarth to vaapasi the mad if it proves undeliverable ; such as from damage, postage due, or invalid destination.
Such mail may yun become dead letter mail.
Should the return address be of a different state or desh, the mail may be routed through ki sthaan liye aasaani of vaapasi.
A nerve guidance conduit ( also referred to as an artificial nerve conduit or artificial tantrika graft, as opposed to an autograft ) is an kritrim arthath of guiding axonal regrowth to sukar tantrika regeneration or is ek of anek naidanik treatments for nerve injuries.
When direct suturing of the two out of a severed tantrika can nahin be sampannataa bagaiyr tension, the maanak naidanik upachaar for peripheral nerve injuries is autologous nerve grafting.
Due to the limited uplabdhta of daata utak or kaaryaatmak recovery in autologous tantrika kalam, neural utak abhiyantriki shodh rai kendrit on the vikaas of bioartificial nerve guidance conduits as an alternative treatment, especially for large defects.
Similar takneekon hai bhi hone chaan liye tantrika marammat in the spinal cord lakin tantrika regeneration in the central baichaiyn system poses a greater challenge because its axons do not regenerate appreciably in their native environment.
The creation of artificial conduits is bhi gyaat as entubulation kuki the tantrika ends or intervening gap hai enclosed bheetar a tub composed of biological or synthetic materials.
Whether the conduit is in the form of a biologic tube, synthetic tub or tissue-engineered conduit, it chahie sukar neurotropic or neurotrophic sanchaar between the proximal or distal ends of the tantrika gap, block external inhibitory factors, and provide a physical guidance for axonal regrowth.
The most moulik uddeshy of a tantrika maargdarshan conduit is to combine shaareerik, rasinic, and biological cues under conditions that will foster tissue formation.
Materials that have been used to mek biologic tubes shaamil rakt baratan or skeletal mansapeshiyaan, jabaki nonabsorbable and bioabsorbable synthetic tubes have been made from silicone and polyglycolide respectively.
tissue-engineered tantrika maargdarshan conduits hai a sangyojan of anek tatv : scaffold dhaancha, scaffold material, cellular therapies, neurotrophic factors and biomimetic materials.
The choice of which physical, chemical and biological cues to upyog is aadhaarit on the gun of the tantrika paryaavaran, which is critical in creating the most desirable environment for axon regeneration.
The factors that control material selection include biocompatibility, biodegradability, mechanical akhandta, controllability dauraan tantrika vikaas, implantation or nasbandi.

amoxicillin bp
amoxicillin ( in ), formerly amoxycillin ( bain ), or abbreviated amox, is a moderate-spectrum, bacteriolytic, β-lactam antibiotic used to treat bacterial infections caused by susceptible microorganisms.
It is usually the drug of choice within the class kuki it is behatar avashoshit, following maukhik prashasan, than other β-lactam antibiotics.
amoxicillin is ek of the sabase aam antibiotic vihit for children.
The drug became uplabdhiyaan in 1972.
Amoxicillin is susceptible to degradation by β-lactamase -producing jeevanu, jisase hai resistant to a vyapak varnakram of β-lactam antibiotics, such as penicillin.
liye is kaaran, it is praayah sanyukt saath clavulanic acid, a β-lactamase inhibitor.
This increases prabhavakaarita by reducing iske susceptibility to β-lactamase resistance.
Lyndon Baines Johnson ( August 27, 1908 – January 22, 1973 ), often referred to as LBJ, was the 36th adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya ( 1963–1969 ), a sthiti he assumed baad uske seva as the 37th vaais President of the United States ( 1961–1963 ).
he is ek of tabhi chaar logon jo parosa in sab chaar nirvaachit sangheey karyaalayon of the sanyukt rajya : pratinidhi, Senator, Vice President, and President.
Johnson, a democrate isse texas, parosa as a sanyukt rajya pratinidhi isse 1937–1949 or as a seenetter isse 1949–1961, sahit chah saalo as sanyukt States Senate Majority Leader, two as Senate Minority Leader and two as Senate Majority Whip.
After campaigning unsuccessfully liye the loktantric namakan in 1960, johnson thi poocha by jon F. kennedy to be uske kaaryshil mate liye the 1960 presidential election.
Johnson succeeded to the presidency following the assassination of John F. Kennedy on navambar 22, 1963, samaapt kennedy 's pad or thi nirvaachit adhyaksh in uske apana sahi, jeetna by a vishaal hashia over bairi Goldwater in the 1964 election.
Johnson was greatly supported by the Democratic Party and as President, he was responsible for designing the `` Great Society `` legislation that shaamil kanoon ki upheld civil adhikaron, public prasaaran, medicare, medicaid, paryaavarniya suraksha, sahaayta to shiksha, or uske `` yuddh on garibi. ''
johnson thi prasiddh liye uske domineering vyaktitv or the `` johnson upachaar, '' uske coercion of shaktishaalee politicians in order to advance legislation.
Meanwhile, Johnson escalated American involvement in the Vietnam War, from 16,000 American advisors/soldiers in 1963 to 550,000 combat sainikon in jaldi 1968, as amareeki hataahat soared or the salaam prakram bogged bas.
The involvement stimulated a large angry antiwar gati aadhaarit visheshkar on vishvavidhyalayon campuses in the U.S. and abroad.
Summer riots broke out in most major cities after 1965, or aparaadhon daron soared, as uske pratidwandviyon uthaaya maange liye `` vidhi or anukram '' policies.
The loktantric party vibhajit in anek feuding girohon, or baad johnson kiya poorly in the 1968 New Hampshire primary, he ended his bid for reelection.
Republican richard nicksan thi nirvaachit to succeed him.
Historians argue that Johnson 's presidency chihnit the shikhar of aadhunik udaarataavaad in the sanyukt rajya after the New Deal era.
johnson is kramit favorably by some historians because of his domestic policies.

The show centers on five characters : roommates Sheldon Cooper and Leonard Hofstadter, two Caltech physicists ; paini, a vetres or aspiring abhinetri jo jeevandaan aarpaar the haul ; or leonard or sheldon 's mitron or co-workers aerospace ejeeniyar Howard Wolowitz, and astrophysicist Rajesh Koothrappali.

The American Civil War ( ACW ), also known as the War between the States or simply the Civil War ( see naming ), was a civil war fought from 1861 to 1865 between the United States ( the `` sangh '' or the `` uttar '' ) or anek dakshini slave rajya ki ghoshit unke secession or formed the confederate States of America ( the `` Confederacy '' or the `` South '' ).
The war had its origin in the issue of slavery, visheshkar the ekstansion of gulaami into the pashchimi territories.
Foreign shaktiyaan kiya nahin intervene.
After four years of bloody combat ki baayein over 600,000 sainiko murde or nasht much of the dakshin 's avasanrachana, the confederacy collapsed, gulaami thi abolished, or the mushkil punarnirmaan prakram of restoring neshnal unity and guaranteeing rights to the freed slaves began.
In the 1860 presidential chunaav, republicans, led by abraham lincoln, opposed expanding slavery into United States ' territories.
Lincoln won, lakin pehle uske udghaatan on kooch 4, 1861, saat cotton-based slave states formed the Confederacy.
Outgoing Democratic President james bukanan or the aavak republicans asweekrut secession as illegal.
Lincoln 's inaugural address ghoshit uske prashasan hota nahin initiate civil war.
Eight baaki slave rajya jari to asweekrut kals for secession.
confederate shaktiyaan jabt numerous sangheey durgon bheetar territory claimed by the Confederacy.
A Peace Conference failed to find a compromise, or dono pahalu prepared liye war.
The Confederates assumed that European countries were so dependent on `` king kapaas `` ki ve hota intervene ; none kiya or none pahachaanaa the nai confederate rajya of america.
hostilities began on april 12, 1861, jab confederate shaktiyaan fired upon fort sumter, a key fort held by Union troops in South Carolina.
Lincoln called for each rajya to provide sainikon to retake the fort ; natijatan, chaar adhik slave rajya joined the Confederacy, bringing their total to eleven.
the sangh jald niyantrit the kinaaraa rajya or sthapit a naval blockade that crippled the southern economy.
The Eastern Theater was inconclusive in 1861–62.
The patjhad 1862 confederate abhiyaan into maryland ( a sangh rajya ) ended saath confederate retreat at the Battle of Antietam, dissuading British intervention.
Lincoln issued the emancipation udghoshnaa, jisase bana samaapti slavery a war goal.
To the west, by summer 1862 the sangh nasht the confederate nadi navy, tab much of unke pashchimi sena, or the sangh at vicksburg vibhajit the Confederacy in two at the Mississippi River.
In 1863, robert E. lee 's confederate incursion north ended at the Battle of Gettysburg.
pashchimi safaltaaon led to ulysses S. grant cmand of all Union armies in 1864.
In the Western Theater, William T. sharaman drove east to capchar atlanta or marched to the samudr, destroying confederate infrastructure along the way.
The Union marshaled the sansaadhan or janashakti to akraman the confederacy isse sab dishanirdesh, or could afford to lado ladaaiyon of attrition through the Overland Campaign towards Richmond, the Confederate capital.
The defending Confederate army failed, leading to Lee 's aatmasamarpan to grant at appomattox adaalat house on april 9, 1865.
The American Civil War was ek of the earliest sachcha audyogic wars.
railroads, the telegraph, steamships, or mass-produced weapons were employed extensively.
The mobilization of civilian kaarkaanon, khaanon, shipyards, bainko, parivahan or food supplies all foreshadowed World War I.
It remains the deadliest war in American history, resulting in the deaths of an anumaanit 750,000 sainiko or an undetermined kramank of civilian casualties.
Historian John huddleston estimates the maut toll at ten pratishat of sab uttari males 20–45 saalo boodha, or 30 percent of all Southern white males aged 18–40.
Human evolution refers to the vikasvaadi prakram agrani up to the rup of modern humans.
While it began with the last common ancestor of all life, the topic usually covers only the evolutionary history of primates, in particular the genus homo, or the emergence of homo sapiens as a pruthak prajati of hominids ( or `` great apes '' ).
The study of human evolution involves many scientific disciplines, including physical maanavshaastra, primatology, puraatatv, bhashavigyaan, vikasvaadi manovigyaan, embryology and genetics.
According to genetic studies, primates diverged isse anya stanadhariyon parichay in the let cretaceous kaal, and the earliest fossils appear in the Paleocene, around.
The parivaar manavnuma diverged isse the hylobatidae ( giban ) parivaar 15-20 lakh saalo ago, and around, the Ponginae ( orangutans ), diverged from the Hominidae family.
Bipedalism is the moulik adaption of the hominin lakeer, or the earliest bipedal hominin is mana to be either Sahelanthropus or Orrorin, with Ardipithecus, a full bipedal, coming somewhat later.
The gorilla and chimpanzee diverged around the vahi samay, parichay 4-6 lakh saalo pehle, or either sahelanthropus or orrorin may be our last shared ancestor with them.
The early bipedals aakhirkaar viksit into the australopithecines or baad the genus Homo.
The earliest documented members of the genus Homo hai homo habilis jisase viksit around ; the earliest prajati liye jisase vahin is dhanatmak pramaan of upyog of stone tools.
The brains of these early hominins yahood parichay the vahi aakaar as ki of a chimpanji.
During the next million years a process of encephalization began, or saath the aagaman of homo iractus in the chattan ricard, cranial kshamta had doubled to 850 cm3.
Homo erectus and homo ergaster yahood the pehla of the hominina to chhod africa, or ye prajati sprad through africa, Asia, and Europe between.
It is believed ki ye prajati yahood the pehla to upyog fire and complex tools.
According to the Recent africa ancestry siddhanth, aadhunik insaano viksit in africa sambhawatah isse homo heidelbergensis, homo rhodesiensis or homo antecessor or migrated out of the mahadweep kuch 50,000 to 100,000 saalo pehle, replacing local populations of Homo erectus, Homo denisova, Homo floresiensis and Homo neanderthalensis.
Archaic Homo sapiens, the forerunner of anatomically aadhunik insaano, viksit between 400,000 and 250,000 years ago.
Recent DNA pramaan suggests ki anek haplotypes of neanderthal utpatti hai upasthit among sab non-african populations, or neanderthals or anya hominids, aise as Denisova hominin may have contributed up to 6 % of their genome to present-day humans. < ref name= '' 10.1126/science.1209202 '' > Anatomically modern humans evolved from archaic Homo sapiens in the Middle Paleolithic, about 200,000 years ago.
the parivartan to behavioral aadhuniktaa saath the vikaas of sankethik samskruti, bhashaa, or specialized lithic praudyogiki happened around 50,000 years ago according to many anthropologists although some suggest a gradual change in behavior over a longer time span.

Track and field is a khel comprising vibhinn pratispardhi athlettic pratiyogitaaon based on running, jumping, and throwing.
The name of the khel garbhashayi isse the pratiyogita sthaan : a stadium saath an ovel kaaryshil track around a grass field.
The throwing and jumping kaarykram generally lo place in the central enclosed area.
Track and field falls under the chhatariyaan khel of athletics, jisase bhi shaamil sadak kaaryshil, cross desh running, and race walking.
The two most prestigious international track and field pratiyogitaaon hai yojit antargat the dhvaj of athletics : the athletics pratiyogita at the olympic khel or the ieeef World Championships in Athletics.
The International Association of athletics federations is the antarrashtriya shaasi deh liye track and field.
Track and field kaarykram hai generally vyaktigat khel saath athlete chunauteepurn each other to decide a single victor.
The racing events are won by the athlete with the fastest time, while the kud or phenkna kaarykram hai jiti by the khilaadi jo rai hasil the greatest distance or height in the contest.
The running events are categorised as sprints, madhya or long-distance kaarykram, relays, and hurdling.
niyamit kud kaarykram shaamil long jamp, tripal jamp, unchi jamp or dhruv walt, jabaki the most common throwing events are shot put, javelin, discus and hammer.
There are also `` combined events '', aise as heptathlon or decathlon, in jisase athlete compete in a kramank of the upar events.
record hai rakhaa of the behtareen pradarshan in vishisht kaarykram, at world and national levels, right down to a personal level.
However, if athletes are deemed to have violated the event 's rules or regulations, ve hai disqualified isse the pratiyogita or unke marks hai erased.
In North America, the term track or field may be prayukt to refer to athletics in saamaanya, balki than specifically track and field events.
The Gulf War ( 2 August 1990 – 28 February 1991 ), codenamed Operation Desert Storm ( 17 January 1991 – 28 farvari 1991 ) thi a yuddh waged by a u.n.-authorized gathbandhan force isse 34 raashtra led by the sanyukt rajya, viruddh iraqi in jawaab to iraqi 's akraman or annexation of Kuwait.
the yuddh is bhi gyaat antargat anya names, aise as the parsi gulf yuddh, pehla gulf yuddh, gulf yuddh i, or the pehla iraqi yuddh, pehle the pad `` iraqi yuddh '' became pahachaanaa instead with the 2003 Iraq War ( also referred to in the U.S. as `` Operation Iraqi Freedom '' ).
Kuwait 's invasion by Iraqi troops that began 2 agast 1990 thi mili saath antarrashtriya condemnation, or brought taatkaalik aarthik sanctions against Iraq by members of the U.N. Security Council.
U.S. President George H. W. Bush tainaat u.S. shaktiyaan into saudi arab, or urged anya deshon to bhejein unke apana shaktiyaan to the scene.
An array of raashtra joined the gathbandhan.
The great majority of the Coalition 's military forces were from the U.S., with Saudi arab, the sanyukt kingdom or mishra as agrani yogadanakarta, in ki order.
Saudi Arabia sashulk around us $ 36 arab of the us $ 60 billion cost.
The war was marked by the beginning of sajiv news on the saamne linon of the lado, saath the primacy of the u.S. sanjaal CNN.
The war has also earned the upnaam video khel yuddh baad the rose broadcast bimb on falak the U.S. bombers during Operation Desert Storm.
The initial conflict to expel iraqi sainikon isse kuwait began saath an aerial bambaari on 17 janvari 1991.
This was followed by a maidan utpeedan on 24 February.
This thi a nirnaayak vijay liye the gathbandhan shaktiyaan, jo liberated kuwait and advanced into Iraqi territory.
The Coalition ceased unke agrim, or ghoshit a cease-fire 100 hours after the ground campaign started.
aerial or maidan combat thi confined to iraqi, kuwait, and areas on Saudi Arabia 's border.
Iraq launched scud misile viruddh gathbandhan sainya lakshya in saudi Arabia and against Israel.
The nickel, in American usage, is a five- cent sikaa jari by the sanyukt rajya Mint.
Composed of 75 % copper and 25 % nikal, the tukdaa rai maharoom struck since 1866.
the chaandi half dime, baraabar to paanch saint, tha maharoom issued since the 1790s.
The American Civil War caused economic hardship, driving gold and chaandi isse parisancharan ; in jawaab, in place of low-value sikke, the government at first issued paper currency.
In 1865, Congress abolished the five-cent fractional karency note baad spencer M. clark, sir of the karency beuro ( aaj the beuro of nakkashi or mudran ), lagaai his own portrait on the denomination.
After successful introduction of two-cent and three-cent pieces, without anmol metal, congress bhi praadhikrut a five-cent tukdaa consisting of aadhaar metal ; the mint began striking is sanskaran in 1866.
The initial design of the shield nikal thi struck jabatak 1883, tab replaced by the Liberty Head nickel.
The bhens nikal thi introduced in 1913 as bhaag of a drive to badhayen the beauty of American coinage ; in 1938, the Jefferson nickel followed.
In 2004 or 2005, khaas dizin in sammaan of the bicentennial of the Lewis and Clark Expedition were issued.
In 2006, the Mint reverted to using jeffrasan nikal panktiyaan felics schlag 's asli reverse ( or `` tails '' paksh ), although a new obverse, by Jamie Franki, was substituted.
As of 2013, it laagat adhik than gyaarah saint to upaj a nikal ; the mint is exploring the sambhaavna of reducing cost by using less expensive metals.

A flower, sometimes gyaat as a khilte or khilanaa, is the reproductive dhaancha mila in flowering paudhe ( paudhe of the division Magnoliophyta, also called angiosperms ).
The biological falan of a pushp is to prabhaav janan, praayah by providing a yantriki liye the union of sperm with eggs.
Flowers may facilitate outcrossing ( fusion of sperm and eggs from different individuals in a janasankhyikee ) or allow selfing ( sanlayan of shukranu or anda isse the vahi flower ).
Some pushp upaj diaspores bagaiyr fertilization ( parthenocarpy ).
Flowers contain sporangia and are the sait jahaan gametophytes develop.
Flowers de vruddhi to fal or seeds.
Many flowers have evolved to be aakarshak to pashu, so as to kaaran unhen to be vectors for the transfer of pollen.
In addition to facilitating the reproduction of flowering paudhe, pushp have long maharoom admired or prayukt by insaano to beautify unke paryaavaran, or bhi as vastuen of romance, anushthan, dharm, medicine and as a source of food.
The McDonnell duglas ( abhi bowing ) f-15 tribhuj is a twin-engine, all-weather ranneetik senaanee designed by McDonnell Douglas to gain and maintain air superiority in aerial combat.
It is considered among the most kaamyaab aadhunik senaanee, saath over 100 aerial combat victories with no losses in dogfights.
Following reviews of proposals, the sanyukt rajya air force chaynit mcdonnell duglas ' dizine in 1967 to milen the seva 's need liye a samarpit air superiority fighter.
The Eagle pehla udaaya in july 1972, or daalaa service in 1976.
Since the 1970s, the tribhuj rai maharoom exported to israel, japani, saudi Arabia, and other nations.
The f-15 thi originally envisioned as a pure air badppan aircraft.
Its design included a secondary ground-attack kaabiliyat ki thi largely unused.
The design proved flexible paryaapt ki an all-weather strike derevative, the f-15e strike Eagle, was later developed, and entered service in 1989.
the f-15 tribhuj is apekshit to be in service with the U.S. Air Force past 2025.

The Organization of American States ( Spanish : Organización de los estados americanos, portugali : organização dos estados americanos, french : sanghathan des États américains ), or the OAS, is a regional international organization.
