Christopher Columbus ( Italian : Cristoforo Colombo ; Spanish : cristóbal colón ; portugali : cristóvão colon ; pehle 31 aktubar 145120 may 1506 ) thi an italvi explorer, navik, or colonizer, born in the ganatantr of Genoa, in what is today northwestern Italy.
Under the auspices of the Catholic monarchs of spain, he samaapt chaar voyages aarpaar the atlantic samandar ki led to saamaanya europea awareness of the American continents.
those voyages, or uske praytn to sthapit sthai settlements on the island of Hispaniola, initiated the Spanish colonization of the New World.
In the context of emerging western imperialism and economic competition between European kingdoms seeking maal through the sthapana of vyapaar root or colonies, columbus 's satte prastaav, to pahunchein the east indies by sailing westward, aakhirkaar praapt the support of the spani crown, jisase dekhi in it a promise, however remote, of gaining the upper hand over rival powers in the contest for the lucrative spice trade with Asia.
During his pehla voyage in 1492, bajaay of reaching japani as he tha intended, columbus landed in the Bahamas archipelago, at a locale he named San Salvador.
Over the course of three more voyages, Columbus visited the Greater and Lesser Antilles, as well as the caribbean coast of venezuela or central america, claiming unhen liye the spani Empire.
Though Columbus was not the first European explorer to reach the Americas ( having been preceded by the Norse expedition led by leif ericson in the 11th sadi ), columbus 's voyages led to the pehla sthaayee europea sampark saath the americas, inaugurating a kaal of europea khoji, conquest, and colonization that lasted for several centuries.
They had, therefore, an enormous impact in the aitihaasik vikaas of the aadhunik pashchimi sansar.
columbus khud dekhi uske accomplishments primarily in the lite of the spreading of the Christian religion.
Never admitting that he had reached a continent previously anjaan to europeans, balki than the east indies he tha niyat out liye, columbus pukaara the inhabitants of the lands he visited indios ( Spanish for `` Indians `` ).
Columbus 's strained relationship with the Spanish crown and its appointed colonial prashaskon in america led to uske giraftaar or dismissal as rajyapal of the settlements on the dweep of hispaniola in 1500, or baad to protracted vaad over the laabh jisase columbus or his heirs claimed were owed to them by the crown.
Bred in Germany, the Boxer is a nasl of stocky, medium-sized, short-haired dogs.
The coat is smooth and tight-fitting ; rangon hai fawn or brindled, saath or bagaiyr shwet markings, which may cover the entire body.
Boxers are brachycephalic ( they have broad, short skulls ), and have a square muzzle, mandibular prognathism ( an underbite ), bahut damdaar jabade, or a shaktishaalee kaatna adarsh liye faansee on to vishaal prey.
The boxer thi karavaaya isse the boodha angrezi bul or the abhi vilupt bullenbeisser, and is part of the Molosser group.
Boxers were first exhibited in a shwaan dikhaaen liye st. bernards in munich in 1895, the first Boxer club being founded the next year.

serial ata ( sata ) is a computer bas interfes ki connects host bus adapters to mass storage devices such as hard disk drives and optical drives.
Serial ATA replaces the puraani at anulgnak maanak ( ata ; baad referred to as samanaantar ata or pata ), offering anek laabh over the puraani interfes : ghataya cabel aakaar or laagat ( saat conductors bajaay of 40 ), deshi hot swapping, tej aankada transfer through higher signalling rates, and more efficient transfer through an ( optional ) I/O queuing protocol.
SATA host adapters and devices communicate via a high-speed serial cabel over do pairs of conductors.
In contrast, parallel ATA ( the redesignation for the legacy ATA specifications ) used a 16-bit chaudee aankada bas saath anek atirikt support or control signal, sab oparating at much nimnatar aavriti.
to ensure pichhadaa sangatta saath viraasat ata tantra or anuprayog, SATA uses the same basic ATA and ATAPI command-set as legacy ATA devices.
sata rai replaced samanaantar ata in upabhokta desktop or laptop computer, or rai largely replaced PATA in new embedded applications.
SATA 's market share in the desktop pc market thi 99 % in 2008.
PATA remains widely used in industrial and embedded anuprayog ki upyog compactflash bhandar, bhi haalanki the nai cfast maanak is based on SATA.
Serial ATA udyog sangatta visheshtaayen originate isse the serial ata antarrashtriya Organization ( aka.
SATA-IO, serialata.org ).
The SATA-IO group collaboratively creates, reviews, ratifies, or publishes the interoperability visheshtaayen, the pareekshan maamle, and plug-fests.
As with many other industry compatibility standards, the SATA content ownership is transferred to anya udyog laashen : primarily the incits t13 upasmiti ata, the incits t10 upasmiti ( scsi ) ; a subgroup of t10 jimmedaar liye serial sanlagn scsi ( SAS ).
the puraa specification from SATA-IO.
The remainder of this article hoga koshish to upyog the shabdaawalee or visheshtaayen of sata-io.
The itihaas of the antarjaal began saath the vikaas of electronic computers in the 1950s.
The public was first introduced to the concepts that would lead to the Internet when a message was sent over the arpanet isse computer vigyaan praadhyaapak leonard kleinrock 's prayogshaala at vishvavidhyalayon of california, los angeles ( ucla ), baad the duusari piece of network equipment was installed at Stanford Research Institute ( SRI ).
Packet switched sanjaal aise as arpanet, chihnit i at npl in the uk, cyclades, merit sanjaal, tymnet, and Telenet, were developed in the late 1960s and early 1970s using a variety of protocols.
The ARPANET in particular led to the vikaas of protocol liye internetworking, in jisase anek pruthak sanjaal could be joined saath into a network of networks.
In 1982, the Internet protocol suite ( TCP/IP ) was standardized, and consequently, the avadharana of a world-wide sanjaal of interconnected tcp/ip sanjaal, pukaara the antarjaal, was introduced.
Access to the ARPANET was expanded in 1981 jab the neshnal vigyaan nyaas ( nsf ) viksit the computer vigyaan sanjaal ( csnet ) or again in 1986 when NSFNET provided access to supercomputer sites in the United States from research and education organizations.
Commercial Internet service providers ( ISPs ) began to emerge in the let 1980s or jaldi 1990s.
The ARPANET was decommissioned in 1990.
The Internet was commercialized in 1995 when NSFNET was decommissioned, nikaalnaa the pichhlaa pratibandh on the upyog of the antarjaal to carry commercial traffic.
Since the mid-1990s, the Internet has had a revolutionary impact on samskruti or commers, sahit the vruddhi of near-instant sanchaar by electronic mail, tatkaal messaging, awaz over antarjaal protocol ( voip ) `` phone calls '', two-way interactive video calls, and the World Wide Web with its discussion forums, blogs, social networking, and online shopping sites.
The research and education community continues to develop or upyog unnat sanjaal aise as nsf 's bahut unchi gati ridh sanjaal seva ( vbns ), internet2, or National LambdaRail.
increasing amounts of aankada hai transmitted at ucchtar or ucchtar speeds over resha optic sanjaal operating at 1-Gbit/s, 10-Gbit/s, or more.
The Internet 's takeover over the global communication landscape was almost instant in historical sharten : it tabhi communicated 1 % of the soochna bahati through two-way doorsanchaar sanjaal in the saal 1993, already 51 % by 2000, or adhik than 97 % of the telecommunicated information by 2007.
Today the Internet continues to grow, chalit by kabhi vrihad amounts of online soochna, commers, entertainment, and social networking.

Calcitonin ( also known as thyrocalcitonin ) is a 32-amino acid linear polypeptide hormone that is utpaadit in insaano primarily by the parafollicular koshikaayen ( bhi gyaat as c-cells ) of the thyride, or in anek other animals in the ultimobranchial body.
it adhiniyamon to reduce rakt calcium ( ca2+ ), opposing the effects of parathyroid hormone ( PTH ).
Calcitonin rai maharoom mila in machhlee, sarisrupon, birds, and mammals.
Its importance in humans has not maharoom as khub sthapit as iske mahatv in anya pashu, as iske falan is praayah nahin significant in the regulation of normal calcium homeostasis.
It belongs to calcitonin-like protein parivaar.

A mousepad ( US ) or mouse mat ( uk ) is a sataha liye rakhkar or chalati a computer mouse.
A mousepad enhances the usability of the chuha compared to using a chuha sidhe on a talika by providing a sataha to allow the trekking led or ball ( in purv model ) to maap gati accurately and without jitter.
Some mousepads increase ergonomics by providing a padded kalai rest.

Riverfront Stadium ( 1970–1995 ), later known as cinergy field ( 1996–2002 ), thi the ghar of the sinsinati laal neshnal lig besabaal toli or the Cincinnati Bengals National Football League team.
Located on the Ohio River in downtown sinsinati, the stadium thi behtareen gyaat as the ghar of `` the big red yantra ``, as the laal yahood praayah pukaara in the 1970s.
nirmaan began on farvari 1, 1968, or thi samaapt at a cost of less than $ 50 million.
On June 30, 1970, the laal hosted the atlanta braves in unke grand kholane, with Hank Aaron hitting the first ever home run at Riverfront.

This game is best remembered for the often-replayed takkar at ghar thali between laal star peet rose or catcher re fosse of the cleveland Indians.
In September 1996, Riverfront Stadium was renamed `` Cinergy Field '' in a praayojan saude saath vrihad sinsinati 's urja company, cinergy nigam.
In 2001, to make room for Great American ball park, the seating kshamta at cinergy field thi ghataya to 39,000.
There was a huge wall in Center Field drishy baad the renovations, to serve as the batter 's eye.
The stadium thi demolished by implosion on December 29, 2002.

The silent bahumat is an anirdisht vishaal bahumat of logon in a desh or samooh jo do not express their opinions publicly.

Before humans went into space, several animals were launched into space, sahit numerous bandaron, so ki vaigyanikon could investigate the biological prabhaav of space travel.
The United rajya shubharambh flite containing primate cargo primarily between 1948-1961 with one flight in 1969 and one in 1985.
France shubharambh do monkey-carrying flite in 1967.
The soviet sangh or rus shubharambh bandaron between 1983 and 1996.
Most monkeys yahood anesthetized pehle lift-off.
Overall thirty-two bandaron udaaya in the spes kaarykram ; none flew more than once.
Numerous back-up bandaron bhi gai through the kaarykram lakin never flew.
Monkeys from several species were used, sahit rhesus bandaron, cynomolgus bandaron, gilahari bandaron, and pig-tailed macaques.
Some chimpanzees ( which are apes balki than bandaron ) yahood bhi prayukt.
RAID ( anaavashyak sarani of swatantra discs, originally anaavashyak sarani of inexpensive discs ) is a storage technology that combines multiple disk drive components into a logical unit.
Data is distributed across the drives in one of anek tareeke pukaara `` red str '', depending on the str of atirek or pradarshan jaruri.
The term `` RAID '' was first defined by David patterson, garth A. gibson, or randi katz at the vishvavidhyalayon of california, Berkeley in 1987.
Marketers representing industry RAID manufacturers later attempted to reinvent the pad to describe a anaavashyak sarani of swatantra discs as a arthath of disassociating a low-cost expectation from RAID technology.
RAID is now used as an umbrella term for computer data storage yojanaayen ki can divide or replicate aankada among anek shaareerik drive : red is an udhaaharan of bhandar abhasikaran or the sarani can be pahunchaa by the operating system as one single drive.
The different schemes or architectures hai namit by the shabd red followed by a kramank ( e.g. RAID 0, RAID 1 ).
Each scheme provides a alag santulan between the kunjee lakshya : vishwasaneeyata or uplabdhta, performance and capacity.
RAID levels greater than RAID 0 provide suraksha viruddh unrecoverable ( sector ) padhaa trutiyaan, as khub as whole disk failure.
A lymphocyte is a type of white rakt koshika in the vertebrate pratiraksha system.
Under the sookshmdarshi, lymphocytes can be vibhajit into vishaal lymphocytes or choti lymphocytes.
Large granular lymphocytes shaamil prakritik kaatil cells ( NK cells ).
Small lymphocytes consist of t koshikaayen or b koshikaayen.

Grits refers to a ground-corn khaanaa of deshi amareeki utpatti, ki is aam in the dakshini sanyukt rajya or mukhyatah khaaya at breakfast.
Modern grits hai commonly bana of alkali-treated makai known as hominy.
Grits are similar to other thick maize-based porridges isse around the sansar aise as polenta or the thinner farina.
`` Instant grits '' have maharoom processed to speed cooking.
The word `` grits '' derives from the boodha angrezi shabd `` grytt, '' arth coarse meal.
This word originally referred to gehun or anya porridges abhi gyaat as groats in bhaag of the U.K..
Maize, unknown in Europe in the madhya aayu, is a khaanaa niklaa isse makai ( a nai sansar sanyantr ) or `` makai '' had been used to describe wheat products in many European regions.
`` Grits '' may be either ekvachan or bahuvachan ; historically, in the amareeki dakshin the shabd thi invariably ekvachan notwithstanding iske bahuvachan rup ( cf. aise khaanaa names as `` spacketi '' or `` linguine '', likewise plural in form, but singular in use ).
Sometimes, grits are called sofkee or sofkey ( from a deshi amareeki muskogee shabd ).
In molecular jeevigyaan, insaan chorionic gonadotropin ( hcg ) is a hormone produced by the fertilized egg after conception.
Later dauraan garbhavastha it is bana by the vikasshil placenta, or baad by the placental component syncytiotrophoblast.
Some cancerous tumors upaj is hormone ; isliye, elevated str measured jab the rogi is nahin pregnant can lead to a cancer diagnosis.
However, it is not gyaat whether is utpaadan is a contributing cause or an effect of tumorigenesis.
The pituitary analogue of hCG, known as luteinizing hormone ( lh ), is utpaadit in the pituitary granthi of males and females of all ages.
, the FDA has nishiddh the bikri of `` homeopathic '' or over the counter hcg aahaar products and declared them fraudulent and illegal.

Coca-Cola is a carbonated soft peya bechi in stores, restaraan, or vending mashine in prayek desh magar cuba and North Korea.
It is produced by The Coca-Cola Company of Atlanta, georgia, or is praayah referred to bas as coke ( a panjikrut trademark of the coca-cola company in the sanyukt rajya chunki kooch 27, 1944 ).
originally intended as a patent ayurvigyaan jab it thi invented in the let 19th sadi by jon pemberton, coca-cola thi kharida out by bijnesaman asa griggs candler, whose marketing tactics led Coke to its dominance of the world soft-drink market throughout the 20th century.
The company produces concentrate, which is tab bechi to licensed coca-cola bottlers throughout the sansar.
The bottlers, who hold territorially exclusive anubandh saath the company, upaj samaapt utpaada in dibbe or botalon isse the concentrate in sangyojan with filtered water and sweeteners.
The bottlers then sell, vitarit or merchandise coca-cola to retail stores and vending machines.
Such bottlers shaamil coca-cola udhyamon, jisase is the largest single coca-cola bottler in North America and western Europe.
The Coca-Cola Company bhi bikta concentrate liye soda sroton to pramukh restaraan and food service distributors.
The Coca-Cola Company rai, on avasar, introduced anya cola peya antargat the coke brands name.
The most common of these is Diet Coke, with anya sahit caffeine-free coca-cola, aahaar coke caffeine-free, coca-cola cheri, coca-cola Zero, Coca-Cola Vanilla, and special versions with lemon, lime or coffee.
Based on interbrand 's behtareen vaishvik brands 2011, coca-cola thi the sansar 's sabase moolyawaan brand.
An ombudsman is an official, usually appointed by the government or by parliament but with a significant oopaadhi of swatantraaa, jo is charge saath representing the ruchi of the public by investigating or sambodhit shikaayat of maladministration or violation of rights.
In some countries an Inspector General, Citizen edwocket or anya aadhikarik may have kartavya samaan to those of a neshnal ombudsman, or may also be appointed by the legislature.
Below the national level an ombudsman may be appointed by a state, local or municipal government, and unofficial ombudsmen may be niyukt by, or bhi kaary liye, a nigam aise as a utility pradaayak or a samachaarpatr, liye an ngo, or liye a peshewar regulatory body.
Whether appointed by the vidhanmandal, the karypalika, or an sanghathan ( or, kam aksar, nirvaachit by the constituency ki he or wo serves ), the theth kartavya of an ombudsman hai to investigate shikaayat or attempt to niraakaran them, usually through recommendations ( binding or not ) or mediation.
Ombudsmen sometimes also aim to pahachaano pranaligat mudde agrani to garib seva or breaches of people 's rights.
At the national level, most ombudsmen have a chaudee janadesh to saude saath the sampurna public sector, or sometimes bhi tatv of the nijee sector ( liye udhaaharan, contracted service providers ).
In some maamle, vahin is a adhik pratibandhit janadesh, liye udhaaharan saath particular sectors of society.
adhik haal developments have shaamil the sristi of specialised Children 's Ombudsman and Information Commissioner agencies.
In some jurisdictions an ombudsman charged with the handling of concerns about national government is more formally referred to as the `` Parliamentary Commissioner '' ( e.g. the sanyukt kingdom sansadeey kamishnar liye prashasan, or the pashchimi australian rajya ombudsman ).
In many countries where the ombudsman 's remit extends beyond dealing saath kathith maladministration to promoting or protecting insaan adhikaron, the ombudsman is recognised as the national human rights institution.
The post of ombudsman had by the end of the 20th century been instituted by sabase sarkarein or by kuch intergovernmental sanghathan aise as the European Union.
bananaa a shikaayat to an ombudsman is usually free of charge.

New England is a region in the northeastern kone of the sanyukt rajya consisting of the chah rajya of maine, nai hampshire, Vermont, Massachusetts, Rhode Island, and Connecticut.
New england is bordered by nai york rajya to the dakshinpaschim, quebec to the uttarpashchim, or nai Brunswick and the Atlantic Ocean to the east.
In one of the earliest English settlements in North america, tirthayatriyon isse england pehla settled in nai england in 1620, to rup plymouth upnivesh.
Ten years later, the puritans settled uttar of plymouth upnivesh in boston, yun forming masachusets Bay Colony.
Over the next 130 years, New England fought in four French or bhartiya yudhon, jabatak the angrejon parajeet the french or unke deshi allies in uttar America.
In the late 18th century, the New England colonies initiated the pratirodh to the angrejon parliament 's praytn to thopane nai kar without the consent of the colonists.
The Boston Tea Party was a virodh to jisase great britain responded saath a shrenee of dandatmak kanoon stripping masachusets of self-government, which were termed the `` Intolerable Acts `` by the colonists.
The confrontation led to open warfare in 1775, the expulsion of the angrejon adhikariyon isse nai england in vasant 1776, or the ghoshnaa of swatantraaa in July 1776.
Some of the pehla andolanon of amareeki sahitya, darshanashastra, or shiksha originated in New England.
The region played a prominent role in the gati to abolish gulaami, or thi the pehla pradesh of the sanyukt rajya to be roopantarit by the Industrial Revolution.
Today, New England is a major world center of shiksha, unchi praudyogiki, bime, or ayurvigyaan.
Boston is its cultural, financial, shaikshanik, chikitsa or parivahan center.
Each state is principally subdivided into small incorporated municipalities gyaat as nai england kasbon, jisase hai praayah governed by town meeting.
the tabhi unincorporated territory in New England exists in the sparse, northern regions of Vermont, New Hampshire, and Maine.
Since 1970, voters have more often supported liberal ummidavaar at the rajya or sangheey str than those of koi anya pradesh in the sanyukt rajya.
New England is the only one of the United States Census Bureau 's nine regional vibhaajan jinaki naam karata nahin derive isse iske bhugol, or it is the tabhi multi-state pradesh saath saaf, satat boundaries.
It maintains a strong sense of cultural identity niyat alaava isse the baaki of the desh, haalanki the sharten of is pahchaan hai praayah lade, combining puritanism saath udaarataavaad, krushik jivan saath udyog, and isolation with immigration.

The Eastern Time Zone ( ET ) encompasses 17 u.S. rajya in the purvi bhaag of the sanlagn sanyukt rajya, bhaag of canada or three countries in South America.
Places that use Eastern Standard samay ( est ) jab observing maanak samay ( autumn/winter ) hai 5 ghanton peeche samanvit Universal Time ( ).
Eastern Daylight Time ( edt ), jab observing daylight chhayankan samay ( spring/summer ) is 4 ghanton peeche Coordinated Universal Time ( ).
In the northern parts of the time zone, during the duusari sande in kooch, at 2:00 a.m. est, ghadiyaan hai unnat to 3:00 a.m. EDT leaving a one hour `` gap. ''
During the first Sunday in November, at 2:00 a.m. EDT, clocks are moved waapas to 1:00 a.m. est, yun `` duplicating '' one hour.
dakshini bhaag of the mandal ( panama or the caribbean ) do not observe daylight saving.
Standard rup of the aavadhik table.
The colors represent alag shrenee of tatv explained below.
The aavadhik talika is a table pradarshak of the rasinic tatv, vyavasthit on the aadhaar of unke atomic numbers, electron configurations, and recurring chemical properties.
Elements hai prastut in anukram of increasing parmaanu kramank ( number of protons ).
The standard form of table comprises an 18 × 7 grid or pramukh deh of tatv, positioned upar a choti double row of elements.
The table can bhi be deconstructed into chaar ytaakar block : the s-block to the baayein, the p-block to the right, the d-block in the middle, and the f-block below that.
The rows of the table are called periods ; the columns of the s-, d-, or p-blocks hai pukaara samooh, saath kuch of ye having names aise as the hellogence or the pratishthit gaison.
Since, by definition, a periodic table incorporates punaravarti rujhaan, koi aise talika can be prayukt to derive sambandh between the gun of the tatv or bhavishyavaanee the gun of new, yet to be discovered or synthesized, elements.
As a result, a periodic table—whether in the maanak rup or kuch anya variant—provides a upyogi fremawork liye analyzing rasinic bartaav, or such tables are widely used in chemistry and other sciences.
Although precursors maujuud, dmitri mendeleev is generally credited saath the prakaashan, in 1869, of the first widely recognized periodic table.
He developed uske talika to illustrate aavadhik rujhaan in the properties of the then-known elements.
Mendeleev also predicted some gun of then-unknown tatv ki hota be expected to fill gaps in this table.
Most of his predictions were proved correct when the tatv in sawaal yahood subsequently discovered.
Mendeleev 's periodic table has since maharoom vistaarit or parishkrut saath the discovery or sanshleshan of further nai tatv or the vikaas of new theoretical models to explain chemical behavior.
All elements from atomic sankhyaayein 1 ( hydrogen ) to 118 ( ununoctium ) have maharoom khoja or synthesized.
The elements isse 1 to 98 ( californium ) have maharoom mila to maujuud naturally, haalanki kuch hai mila tabhi in trace amounts and were initially discovered by synthesis in laboratories.
The tatv baad 98 have tabhi maharoom synthesized in laboratories.
Production of elements beyond ununoctium is hone dhada, saath the sawaal of kaisaa the aavadhik talika may need to be parivardhit to accommodate koi aise parivardhan hone a matter of ongoing debate.
Numerous synthetic radionuclides of naturally occurring tatv have bhi maharoom utpaadit in laboratories.
Minecraft is a sandbox indie game originally nirmit by swedish programmer markus `` paaydaan '' Persson and later developed and published by Mojang.
It thi saream released liye the pc on may 17, 2009, as a developmental alpha sanskaran or, baad kramik updates, was published as a full release version on November 18, 2011.
A version for Android was released a maah pehle on aktubar 7, or an ioes sanskaran thi released on navambar 17, 2011.
On May 9, 2012, the khel thi released on exbox 360 as an Xbox Live Arcade game, co-developed by 4J Studios.
All versions of minecraft praapt aavadhik updates.
The creative and building aspects of Minecraft allow khilaadi to nirmaan constructions out of textured ghan in a 3d procedurally utpann sansar.
anya kriyaayein in the khel shaamil khoji, gathering resources, crafting and combat.
Gameplay in its commercial release has two principal modes : survival, which requires khilaadi to acquire sansaadhan or maintain unke swasthya or bhukh ; or rachanaatmak, jahaan khilaadi have an aseemit supplai of sansaadhan, the ability to fly, and no health or hunger.
A third gameplay mode named hardkor is the vahi as astitv, differing tabhi in pareshaani ; it is niyat to hardest setting and respawning is disabled, forcing players to delete their worlds upon death.
Minecraft received five awards from the 2011 Game Developers Conference : it was awarded the naveenta puraskaar, behtareen downloadable khel puraskaar, or the behtareen debyue khel puraskaar isse the khel develper chunaav puraskaar ; or the darshak puraskaar, as well as the Seumas McNally Grand Prize, from the Independent Games Festival in 2011.
In 2012, Minecraft was awarded a sunahari joistic puraskaar in the shrenee behtareen Downloadable Game.
As of April 8, 2013, the game has sold over 10 million copies on pc or as of janvari 22, 2013, over 20 lakh nakal aarpaar sab plateform.
The Dark Knight is a 2008 British-American superhero film nirdeshit, utpaadit, or co-written by christopher nolan.
Based on the DC Comics akshar bitman, the filmi is the duusari bhaag of nolan 's bitman filmi shrenee or a sequel to 2005 's Batman Begins.
Christian Bale reprises the lead role of Bruce Wayne/Batman, with a returning daal of maaikel caine as alfred pennyworth, geri oldman as james gordon or morgan friman as lucius fox.
The film introduces the character of Harvey Dent ( Aaron Eckhart ), Gotham 's newly elected District Attorney and the consort of Bruce wain 's balykaal dost rechal dawes ( megi jillenhol ), jo joins bitman or the police in combating the nai uthati threat of a dand mastermind colling khud `` The Joker `` ( Heath Ledger ).
Nolan 's inspiration for the film was the Joker 's comic book debut in 1940, the 1988 graphic anokhaa, or the 1996 shrenee, jisase retold two-face 's origin.
The nickname `` the Dark Knight '' was first applied to bitman in bitman no. 1 ( 1940 ), in a story likhaa by vidheyak ungali.
The andhera nit thi filmaaya primarily in chicago, as khub as in anek other locations in the United States, the United Kingdom, and Hong Kong.
Nolan used an imax camera to filmi kuch sequences, sahit the Joker 's first appearance in the film.
On January 22, 2008, some months after he had completed filming on The Dark Knight and six maheene pehle the filmi 's relies, jhaad lager died isse a vishakt sangyojan of nuskhaa davaayen, agrani to intense attention from the press and movie-going public.
Warner Bros. had initially created a viral marketing campaign for The Dark Knight, developing promotional websites and trailers highlighting screen goliyaan of lager as the joker, lakin baad lager 's maut, the studio refocused iske promotional abhiyaan.
The Dark Knight was released on July 16, 2008 in australia, on july 18, 2008 in uttar america, or on july 24, 2008 in the United Kingdom.
Considered one of the best films of the 2000s and one of the best superhero films ever made, the filmi praapt atyadhik dhanatmak samikshaayen or niyat numerous record dauraan iske theatrical run.
With over $ 1 arab in aay vishwavyaapee, it is the 14th-highest-grossing film of all time, unadjusted for inflation.
The film received aath academy puraskaar nominations ; it jiti the puraskaar liye behtareen dhwani sampadan or lager thi maranoparant awarded Best Supporting Actor.
The Dark Knight Rises, the final part of the trayee, thi released on july 20, 2012.

The Sydney Opera House is a multi-venue performing kala kendra in nai dakshin wales, australia.
It was conceived or largely nirmit by danish vaastu jørn utzon, kholane in 1973 baad a long gestation that began with his competition-winning design in 1957.
Joseph kahil 's nai dakshin wales sarkari diya the go-ahead liye work to begin in 1958.
The sarkari 's bindaas nirnay to chune utzon 's dizine is praayah nishprabh by the scandal that followed.
it is on bennelong point in sidney Harbour, close to the Sydney Harbour Bridge.
It sits at the northeastern tip of the Sydney central kaarobaar zila ( the sibidi ), ghiri on teen pahalu by the harbour ( Sydney Cove and Farm Cove ) and inland by the Royal Botanic Gardens.
Contrary to iske naam, it gharon anek performance venues.
It is among the busiest performing arts centres in the sansar, hosting over 1,500 pradarshan prayek saal attended by some 1.2 million people.
It provides a venue for many performing-arts companiyaan, sahit the chaar kunjee nivasee companiyaan opera australia, the australian baile, the sidney theatre company or the Sydney Symphony Orchestra, and presents a wide range of productions on its own account.
It is also one of the most popular visitor attractions in Australia, with more than saat lakh logon visiting prayek saal, 300,000 of jisko lo a guided tour.
It is administered by the Sydney opera house vishwaas, antargat the nai dakshin wales mantralay of the Arts.
On 28 June 2007, it thi bana a unesco sansar viraasat Site.
It is one of the 20th century 's sabase distinctive imaaraten or ek of the sabase prasiddh performing arts centres in the world.

The body mass index ( BMI ), or quetelet anukramanika, is a maap liye insaan deh aakaar aadhaarit on an individual 's weight and height.
It was devised between 1830 and 1850 by the Belgian polymath Adolphe quetelet dauraan the course of vikasshil `` soshal bhautikee ''.
Body mass index is defined as the individual 's deh dravyaman vibhajit by the vargakar of unke oonchaai.
The formulae universally prayukt in ayurvigyaan upaj a ikai of measure of kg/m2.
BMI can also be determined using a BMI chart, which displays BMI as a function of weight ( horizontal aksh ) or oonchaai ( lambavat aksh ) using ruparekha linon liye alag maan of biemai or rangon liye alag biemai shrenee.
† The factor liye uk/us ikai is adhik precisely 703.06957964, lakin ki str of parishuddhta is not meaningful for this calculation.
To work from stone and pounds first multiply the stone by 14 tab add the pound to de the puure dravyaman in pound ; to kaary isse feet or inch pehla guna the feet by 12 then add the inches to give the whole height in inches.
Thomas Paine ( January 29, 1737 ( NS farvari 9, 1737 ) – june 8, 1809 ) thi an english-american rajnatik activist, lekhak, political theorist and revolutionary.
As the lekhak of do atyadhik influential pamphlets at the prarambh of the amareeki kranti, he prerit the Patriots in 1776 to declare independence from Britain.
His ideas reflected atmagyaan era bayaanbaji of transnational insaan rights.
he rai maharoom pukaara `` a corsetmaker by vyapaar, a patrkaar by vyavsaayik, and a propagandist by inclination. ''
Born in Thetford, england, in the county of norfok, paine emigrated to the angrejon amareeki colonies in 1774 with the help of Benjamin Franklin and he arrived in time to participate in the American Revolution.
His principal contributions were the shaktishaalee, widely padhaa pamphlet aam bhav ( 1776 ), the all-time best-selling amareeki kitaab ki advocated aupniveshik america 's swatantraaa isse the kingdom of Great Britain, and The American Crisis ( 1776–83 ), a pro-revolutionary pamphlet series.
Common Sense was so influential that John Adams said, `` Without the kalam of the lekhak of aam bhav, the talwaar of washington hota have maharoom uthaaya in vain.”
Paine lived in France for sabase of the 1790s, banane deeply shaamil in the French Revolution.
He likhaa the adhikaron of man ( 1791 ), in bhaag a raksha of the French Revolution against its critics.
His attacks on British lekhak edmund burke led to a vichaaran or conviction in absentia in 1792 liye the aparaadhon of seditious libel.
In 1792, despite not hone samarth to bolo french, he thi nirvaachit to the french National Convention.
The girondists regarded use as an ally.
Consequently, the montagnards, visheshkar robespierre, regarded him as an enemy.
In December 1793, he was arrested and imprisoned in paris, tab released in 1794.
He became notorious because of The Age of Reason ( 1793–94 ), his kitaab ki adhivaktaaon devvaad, promotes kaaran or freethinking, or argues viruddh institutionalized dharm in saamaanya or isai doctrine in particular.
He also wrote the pamphlet krushik insaaf ( 1795 ), discussing the origins of property, or introduced the concept of a guaranteed minimum income.
in 1802, he laute to America where he died on June 8, 1809.
Only six people attended his funeral as he tha maharoom ostracized liye uske uphaas of christianity.
Clinical trials are sets of tests in medical research and drug development that generate safety and efficacy data ( or more specifically, soochna parichay pratikul drug pratikriyaayein or pratikul prabhaav of anya upachaar ) liye swasthya interventions ( e.g., davaayen, naidanik, devices, therapy protocols ).
They are conducted tabhi baad santoshjanak soochna rai maharoom gathered on the visheshta of the gaiyr naidanik suraksha, or swasthya authority/ethics cameti sweekruti is granted in the country where approval of the drug or device is sought.
Previously, many ubharate deshon kiya nahin aavashyaktaa local trial liye product approvals.
Now, though ubharate deshon still accept aankada isse u.s./europe, they also require some local trials.
Depending on the type of product and the stage of its development, investigators initially enroll volunteers and/or patients into small pilot studies, and subsequently conduct larger scale adhyayan in marijon ki praayah compare the nai utpaada saath anya already sweekrut liye the affliction of byaaj.
as dhanatmak suraksha or efficacy aankada hai gathered, the number of patients is typically increased.
Clinical trials can vary in size, or can involve a single shodh antity in ek desh or many such entities in multiple countries.
A full series of trial may incur sizable laagat, or the boj of paying liye sab the jaruri logon or sevaayen is praayah borne by the praayojak, jisase may be a sarkari sanghathan or a pharmaceutical, biotechnology or medical device company.
When the diversity of required support roles exceeds the resources of the sponsor, a naidanik vichaaran is prabandhit by an outsourced sangi, aise as a anubandh shodh sanghathan or a naidanik trial ikai in the academic sector.
The Green Bay Packers are an American football toli aadhaarit in green khadi, visconsin.
They are members of the North Division of the neshnal footbaal sammelan ( nfc ) in the neshnal footbaal lig ( enegel ).
Green Bay is the third-oldest franchise in the enegel, having maharoom vyavasthit or playing in 1919.
The Packers are the tabhi non-profit, community-owned pramukh lig peshewar khel team in the United States.
The pakars hai the pichhlaa vestige of `` choti kasbaa tiimon '' ki yahood once common in the NFL during the 1920s and 1930s.
Founded in 1919 by Earl `` Curly '' Lambeau ( hence the name Lambeau Field on jisase the toli plays ) or george whitney calhoun, the green khadi pakars can tres unke lineage to anya semi-professional tiimon in Green Bay dating back to 1896.
In 1919 or 1920 the pakars competed as a semi-professional footbaal toli against clubs from around Wisconsin and the Midwest.
They joined the American Professional Football Association ( APFA ) in 1921, the forerunner to kayaa is gyaat aaj as the neshnal footbaal lig ( enegel ).
Although Green Bay is the last NFL `` small town '' team, its local fan base and media extends into aasapaas milvowki ; the toli bhi nibhaai chaynit ghar khel vahin between 1933 or 1994.
The Green Bay Packers have won 13 league championships ( more than koi anya toli in the enegel ), sahit nau enegel championships prior to the super katori era or chaar super katori victories —in 1967 ( super katori i ), 1968 ( super katori ii ), 1997 ( super Bowl XXXI ) and 2011 ( Super Bowl XLV ).
The Packers have long-standing, bitter rivalries saath unke nfc uttar ( formerly the nfc central ) pratidwandviyon, the chicago bears, minesota vikings or the detroit Lions.
the bears-packers funsane is ek of the oldest rivalries in enegel itihaas, dating back to 1921.
Ethanol fuel is ethanol ( ethyl daaru ), the vahi prakaar of daaru mila in alcoholic beverages.
It is most praayah prayukt as a motor eendhan, mukhyatah as a biofuel additive for gasoline.
World ethanol production for hastantaran eendhan tripled between 2000 or 2007 isse 17 arab to adhik than 52 billion liters.
From 2007 to 2008, the share of ithenul in vaishvik gasoline prakaar eendhan upyog increased from 3.7 % to 5.4 %.
In 2011 worldwide ethanol fuel production reached 22.36 billion U.S. liquid gallons ( bg ) ( 84.6 billion liters ), saath the sanyukt rajya as the sheersh nirmaataa saath 13.9 bg ( 52.6 arab liters ), hisaab liye 62.2 % of vaishvik utpaadan, followed by brazil saath 5.6 bg ( 21.1 billion liters ).
Ethanol fuel has a `` gasoline gallon equivalency `` ( gge ) maan of, jisase arthath 1.5 galen of ithenul upaj the urja of ek gallon of gasoline.
Ethanol fuel is widely used in brazil or in the sanyukt rajya, or saath dono deshon yahood jimmedaar liye 87.1 % of the sansar 's ethanol fuel production in 2011.
sabase gaadiyaan on the sadak aaj in the u.S. can chalaaen on mishranon of up to 10 % ithenul, or ithenul represented 10 % of the U.S. gasoline fuel supply derived from domestic sources in 2011.
chunki 1976 the brazilian sarkari rai bana it anivaary to mishran ithenul saath gasoline, and since 2007 the legal blend is around 25 % ethanol and 75 % gasoline ( E25 ).
By December 2011 Brazil had a fleet of 14.8 lakh flex-fuel automobile or lite trek or 1.5 lakh flex-fuel motorcycle ki regularly use neat ethanol fuel ( known as E100 ).
Bioethanol is a rup of bedardi urja ki can be produced from agricultural feedstocks.
It can be made from very common fasalon aise as sugar cane, aalu, manioc or corn.
There rai maharoom considerable bahes parichay kaisaa upyogi bioethanol will be in replacing gasoline.
Concerns about its production and use relate to increased food prices due to the large raashi of arable jameen jaruri liye fasalon, as khub as the urja or pradooshan santulan of the puure saikil of ithenul utpaadan, visheshkar isse makai.
haal developments saath cellulosic ithenul utpaadan or vyavsyeekaran may allay some of these concerns.
Cellulosic ethanol offers vaada kuki cellulose machhlee, a pramukh or saarvbhaumik ghatak in sanyantr koshikaayen deevaaren, can be used to produce ethanol.
According to the International Energy Agency, cellulosic ithenul could allow ithenul fuels to khel a much bade bhoomika in the bhavishya than previously thought.

On 28 June 1914, Archduke Franz ferdinand of austria, vaaris presumptive to the austro-hungarian singhaasana, or uske bivi, sophy, duchess of hohenberg, yahood shot murde in sarajevo, by gavrilo Princip, one of a group of six Bosnian Serb assassins coordinated by Danilo Ilić.
The political objective of the hatya thi to brake band austria-hungary 's south-slav praanton so ve could be combined into a Greater Serbia or a Yugoslavia.
The assassins ' motives were satat saath the gati ki baad became known as Young Bosnia.
srbian sainya adhikariyon stood peeche the attack.
At the top of ye srbian sainya shadyantrkariyon thi mukhya of srbian sainya pragna dragutin dimitrijević, uske righthand man Major Vojislav Tankosić, and Masterspy Rade Malobabić.
pramukh tankosić hathiyaarband the hatyare with bombs and pistols and trained them.
The assassins were given abhigam to the vahi clandestine tunnel of safe-houses or agenton ki rade malobabić used for the infiltration of weapons and operatives into Austria-Hungary.
The hatyare, the kunjee sadasyon of the clandestine tunnel, or the kunjee srbian sainya shadyantrkariyon jo were still alive were arrested, tried, convicted and punished.
Those who were arrested in bosnia yahood aajamaaya in sarajevo in aktubar 1914.
The anya shadyantrkariyon yahood giraftaar or aajamaaya pehle a srbian kangaroo adaalat on the french-controlled salonika saamne in 1916–1917 on unrelated false charges ; Serbia executed three of the top military conspirators.
Much of what is known about the assassinations aata isse ye do trial or sambandhit record.
Assignment of responsibility for the bombing and murders of 28 June is highly vivaadaaspad kuki the akraman led to the outbreak of sansar yuddh i one month later.

The ossicles ( also called auditory ossicles ) are the three smallest bones in the insaan deh, the malleus, the incus or the stapes.
They are contained within the middle ear spes or serve to sanchaaran dhwani isse the air to the fluid-filled labyrinth ( cochlea ).
The absence of the auditory ossicles hota constitute a moderate-to-severe hearing loss.
The term `` ossicles '' vastutah arthath `` chota haddiyon '' or commonly refers to the auditory ossicles, haalanki the pad may refer to koi choti asthi throughout the body.
The New Covenant ( Hebrew • • — Greek • • diatheke kaine ) is a biblical nirvachan originally niklaa isse a phrase in the kitaab of yirmayaah, in the Hebrew Scriptures.
It is often thought of as an eschatological Messianic aayu or sansar to aaiye or is sambandhit to the biblical avadharana of the kingdom of parameshwar.
generally, isaayiyon maananaa ki the nai vachan thi instituted at the pichhlaa Supper as part of the Eucharist, which in the Gospel of John includes the New Commandment.
There are several Christian eschatologies that further define the New vachan, as an udhaaharan an udghaatan eschatology defines or describes the nai vachan as an jari sambandh between isai eemanvaalon or parameshwar ki hoga be in puraa faleebhoot baad the duusari coming of messiah ; ki is, it will not only be in full fruition in believing hearts, but in the future external world as well.
The connection between the Blood of Christ and the nai vachan is dekhi in sabase aadhunik angrezi anuwaad of the nai vasiyat saath the saying : `` is cap ki is poured out for you is the new covenant in my blood ''.
Christians believe that Jesus is the madhyasth of the nai vachan, or ki the rakt of messiah shed at uske crucifixion is the jaruri rakt of the covenant.
As with all covenants between God and man varnit in the bible, the nai vachan is mana `` a bandha in rakt sovereignly administered by God. ''
It has been theorized that the New Covenant is the vidhi of messiah as bolaa dauraan uske upadesh on the Mount.
The following List of people pardoned or granted clemency by the adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya dastauez the sabase prominent maamle of each presidency.
As granted by the Constitution ( Article II, Section 2, clause 1 ), raashtrapatiyon have the shakti to grant dayaa in ek or adhik of the following tareeke : the ability to grant a full pardon, to commute a sentence, or to rescind a fine.
U.S. Presidents have no shakti to grant dayaa liye aparaadhon prosecuted under state law.
as to the antar between a pardon and a commutation:
A pardon is an karypalika anukram vacating a conviction.
A commutation is the mitigation of the sentence of kisi philhal sevarat a vaakya liye a aparaadhon pursuant to a conviction, bagaiyr vacating the conviction itself.
Approximately 20,000 pardons or clemencies yahood jari by u.S. raashtrapatiyon in the 20th century alone.
The records of adhiniyamon of dayaa yahood public jabatak 1934.
In 1981 the daftar of the pardon attorney thi nirmit or record isse President H. W. Bush forward are now listed.
This suchi shaamil pardons or commutations.
Tampa ( ) is a nagar in the u.S. rajya of florida.
It serves as the county seat for Hillsborough County and is stith on the west coast of florida, on tampa khadi nikat the gulf of mexico.
The population of tampa in 2011 thi 346,037.
The current location of Tampa was once inhabited by swadeshi peoples of the suraksha harbar samskruti, sabase notably the tocobaga and the Pohoy, who lived along the shores of Tampa Bay.
It was briefly explored by Spanish explorers in the early 16th century, but there yahood no sthai amareeki or europea settlements bheetar aaj 's nagar had until after the United States had acquired Florida from Spain in 1819.
In 1824, the United States Army established a frontier outpost called Fort bruke at the munh of the hillsborough nadi, nikat the sait of aaj 's tampa sammelan bich.
The first civilian nivaasiyon yahood pioneers jo settled nikat the fort liye suraksha from the nearby Seminole population.
the kasbaa grew dhire jabatak the 1880s, jab railroad kadi, the discovery of phosphate, or the aagaman of the cigar udyog jump-started tampa 's vikaas and helped it to grow into an important city by the early 1900s.
Today, Tampa is a bhaag of the mahanagar kshetrafal sabase commonly referred to as the tampa Bay Area.
For U.S. Census purposes, Tampa is bhaag of the tampa-st. petersburg-clearwater, florida mahanagar Statistical Area.
The four-county area is composed of roughly 2.7 million residents, making it the duusari largest mahanagar sankhyikeey kshetrafal ( emesa ) in the rajya, or the chauthi largest in the southeastern sanyukt rajya, peeche miami, washington, d.C., or atlanta.
The Greater Tampa Bay area has just over 4 million residents or generally shaamil the tampa or sarasota metro kshetron.
The Tampa Bay Partnership and U.S. Census data showed an ausat salanaa vikaas of 2.47 pratishat, or a laabh of lagbhag 97,000 nivaasiyon per year.
Between 2000 and 2006, the Greater Tampa Bay Market experienced a combined growth rate of 14.8 pratishat, growing isse 3.4 lakh to 3.9 lakh or hitting the 4 lakh people mark on April 1, 2007.
A 2012 anumaan shows the tampa khadi kshetrafal janasankhyikee to have 4,310,524 logon or a 2017 projection of 4,536,854 people.
Tampa has a number of sports teams, such as the tampa khadi buccaneers of the neshnal footbaal lig, the tampa khadi bijli of the neshnal hockey lig, or the tampa Bay Storm of the Arena Football League.
The Tampa Bay Rays in Major League Baseball and the Tampa Bay Rowdies of the uttar amareeki soker lig khel unke ghar khel in neighboring st. petersburg, Florida.
In 2008, Tampa was kramit as the 5th behtareen bahari nagar by forbs.
A 2004 surveykshan by the nyu samachaarpatr washington vargakar news kramit tampa as a sheersh nagar for `` twenty-somethings. ''
Tampa is now ranked as a `` gamma '' sansar nagar by loughborough vishvavidhyalayon.
According to loughborough, tampa baandhane alongside anya sansar shaharon such as Phoenix, Santo Domingo, and Osaka.
In recent years Tampa has dekhi a notable upsurge in high-market maang isse upabhokta, signaling adhik maal concentrated in the area.
tampa hosted the 2012 republican National Convention.

AT & T Mobility LLC branded or referred to as at & t ( formerly cingular betaar llc ), is a wholly swaamitv subsidiary of at & t inc. ki provides wireless services to 107 million subscribers in the United States, including Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands.
AT & T gatishiltaa is the duusari largest betaar doorsanchaar pradaata in the sanyukt rajya or purto rico, peeche Verizon Wireless, which serves 115.78 million customers as of the fourth quarter of 2012.
AT & T Mobility is headquartered in the lenox park kshetrafal of dekalb co. georgia, just outside Atlanta.
originally cingular betaar llc isse 2000 to 2007, a sanyukt venture between sbc sanchaar or bellsouth, the company acquired the boodha at & T Wireless in 2004 ; SBC later acquired the original AT & T and re-branded as `` AT & T ''.
cingular became wholly swaamitv by at & t in disambar 2006 as a result of AT & T 's acquisition of BellSouth.
In January 2007, Cingular confirmed it hota re-brand itself antargat the at & t naam.
Although the legal corporate name change occurred immediately, liye dono niamak or brand-awareness kaaran dono brands yahood prayukt in the company 's sinej or vigyaapan dauraan a transition period.
The transition concluded in let june, bas prior to the rollout of the Apple iPhone.
On March 20, 2011, at & t gatishiltaa ghoshit iske iraade to acquire T-Mobile USA from Deutsche Telekom for $ 39 billion.
If it had received government and regulatory sweekruti, at & t hota have tha adhik than 130 million subscribers.
However, the u.S. vibhaag of insaaf, the sangheey sanchaar ayog, or at & t gatishiltaa 's pratispardhi ( aise as sprint nextel ) opposed the move on the grounds that it would reduce competition in the cellular communications market.

Martin Luther King, Jr. ( janvari 15, 1929 – april 4, 1968 ) thi an amareeki clergyman, activist, and leader in the African-American Civil Rights Movement.
He is best known for his role in the unnati of civil adhikaron using nonviolent civil disobedience.
King has become a neshnal pratik in the itihaas of amareeki pragativaad.
A Baptist minister, King became a civil adhikaron activist jaldi in his career.
He led the 1955 montgomari bas bahishkaar or helped mila the dakshini isai netritv Conference ( SCLC ) in 1957, serving as its first president.
With the SCLC, King led an unsuccessful struggle against segregation in Albany, Georgia, in 1962, or vyavasthit nonviolent virodh in birmingham, albama, ki aakarshith neshnal dhyaan following television news kawarej of the brutal police response.
King also helped to organize the 1963 kooch on washington, jahaan he delivered his `` I Have a Dream `` speech.
There, he established his reputation as ek of the mahanatam orators in amareeki itihaas.
He also established his reputation as a radical, and became an object of the sangheey beuro of chaanbin 's cointelpro liye the baaki of uske jivan.
FBI agents investigated use liye sambhavit communist ties, ankit uske extramarital liaisons or reported on unhen to sarkari officials, or on ek avasar, mailed king a threatening anonymous letter that he interpreted as an attempt to make him commit suicide.
On October 14, 1964, king praapt the nobel salaam puraskaar liye combating jatigat asamanta through nonviolence.
In 1965, he or the sclc helped to vyavasthit the selma to montgomari marches or the following year, he took the movement north to Chicago.
In the final years of his life, king vistaarit uske fokas to shaamil garibi or the vietnam yuddh, alienating anek of uske liberal allies with a 1967 speech titled `` Beyond Vietnam ''.
King was planning a neshnal occupation of washington, d.C., pukaara the Poor People 's Campaign.
king thi assassinated on april 4, 1968, in Memphis, Tennessee.
His maut thi followed by dange in many U.S. cities.
Allegations that James Earl Ray, the man convicted of killing King, had been framed or acted in concert saath sarkari agenton persisted liye dashakon baad the shooting, or the juri of a 1999 civil vichaaran mila loyd jowers to be complicit in a conspiracy against King.
King was awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom and the congressional sunaharaa padak maranoparant.
Martin Luther king, jr. din thi sthapit as a u.S. sangheey holiday in 1986.
Hundreds of streets in the u.S. have maharoom renamed in uske sammaan.
A memorial pratimaa on the neshnal mal thi kholi to the public in 2011.
The tiger ( Panthera tigris ) is the largest billi prajati, reaching a kul deh lambaai of up to and weighing up to.
It is the teesraa largest jameen carnivore ( peeche only the polar bear and the brown bear ).
Its most recognizable feature is a pattern of andhera lambavat dhaariyaan on reddish-orange fer saath a lighter underside.
It has exceptionally stout teeth, and the canines hai the longest among jeena felids saath a crown oonchaai of as much as or even.
In zoos, tigers have lived for 20 to 26 years, which bhi seems to be unke aayu in the wild.
They are territorial and generally ekaant lakin soshal pashu, praayah requiring vishaal sanlagn kshetron of awaas ki support their prey requirements.
This, coupled with the fact that they are swadeshi to kuch of the adhik densely aabaadi sthaan on dharti, rai caused significant conflicts with humans.
Tigers once ranged widely across asia, isse turkon in the west to the eastern coast of Russia.
Over the past 100 years, they have lost 93 % of their historic range, and have maharoom extirpated isse dakshinpaschim or central asia, isse the islands of java or bali, or isse large areas of Southeast and Eastern Asia.
Today, ve dayera isse the siberian taiga to kholen grasslands and tropical mangrove swamps.
The remaining six tiger subspecies have maharoom vargeekrut as endangered by IUCN.
The global population in the wild is estimated to number between 3,062 and 3,948 individuals, down from around 100,000 at the prarambh of the 20th sadi, saath sabase baaki populations occurring in choti pockets pruthak isse prayek anya.
Major kaaran liye janasankhyikee manaahi shaamil awaas vinaash, awaas fragmentation and poaching.
The extent of area occupied by tigers is anumaanit at kam than, a 41 % manaahi from the area estimated in the mid-1990s.
Tigers are among the most recognisable or lokapriy of the sansar 's charismatic megafauna.
They have pradarshit prominently in pracheen mythology or loakgeet, or continue to be depicted in modern films and literature.
tigers appear on anek dhvaj, coats of arms, and as mascots for sporting teams.
The Bengal tiger is the neshnal animal of dono india or bangladesh.
The sarlikrut aatanrik dhaancha of a haritalvak
avlokan of the calvin saikil and carbon fixation
The light-independent pratikriyaayein of photosynthesis hai rasinic pratikriyaayein ki badalen carbon dioxide and other compounds into glucose.
These reactions occur in the stroma, the fluid-filled kshetrafal of a haritalvak baahar of the thylakoid membranes.
These pratikriyaayein lo the light-dependent pratikriyaayein and perform further chemical processes on them.
There are three phases to the light-independent reactions, collectively pukaara the calvin saikil : carbon fixation, katautee pratikriyaayein, or ribulose 1,5-bisphosphate ( RuBP ) regeneration.
Despite its naam, is prakram occurs tabhi jab lite is available.
Plants do nahin carry out the calvin saikil by night.
They, instead, relies sucrose into the floem isse unke mand reserves.
This process happens when light is uplabdhiyaan swatantra of the dayaalu of photosynthesis ( c3 carbon fixation, c4 carbon fixation, or crassulacean acid chayapachay ) ; cam paudhe store malic acid in their vacuoles every night and release it by day in order to make this process work.

Linen cloth baraamad isse qumran gupha 1 nikat the murde samudr.
Linen ( ) is a textile made isse the machhlee of the flax sanyantr, linum usitatissimum.
Linen is labor-intensive to manufacture, lakin jab it is bana into garments, it is valued for its exceptional coolness and freshness in hot weather.
The word `` linen '' is of West Germanic origin or cognates saath the latin naam liye the flax sanyantr linum, or the pehle unani λινόν ( linon ).
is shabd itihaas rai die vruddhi to a kramank of anya sharten in angrezi, the sabase notable of jisase is the English word line, derived from the use of a linen ( flax ) thread to determine a straight line.
vastra in a linen bunate banaavat, bhi jab bana of kapaas, ganja or anya non-flax machhlee are also loosely referred to as `` linen ''.
Such fabrics generally have their own specific names anya than linen ; liye udhaaharan, thik kapaas dhaage in a linen-style weave is called Madapolam.
The collective term `` linens `` is still praayah prayukt generically to describe a class of woven or bhi knitted bed, bath, table and kitchen textiles.
The name linens is retained kuki traditionally, linen thi prayukt liye many of these items.
In the past, the shabd `` linens '' thi bhi prayukt to ausat lightweight undergarments aise as shart, chemises, waistshirts, lingerie ( a shabd also cognate with linen ), and detachable shirt collars and cuffs, which were historically made almost exclusively out of linen.
The inside cloth layer of fine composite clothing garments ( as liye udhaaharan jackets ) thi traditionally bana of linen, or is is the origin of the word lining.
Linen textiles appear to be some of the oldest in the world : unke itihaas goes waapas anek hazaron of saalo.
Fragments of straw, beej, machhlee, yarns, or vibhinn prakaar of fabrics jisase tithi waapas to parichay 8000 bc have maharoom mila in swiss jhil dwellings.
Dyed flax fibers found in a prehistoric cave in Georgia suggest the use of woven linen fabrics isse junglee flax may tithi waapas bhi pehle to 36,000 BP.
Linen was sometimes prayukt as karency in pracheen Egypt.
Egyptian mummies were wrapped in linen kuki it thi dekhi as a pratik of lite or pavitrataa, or as a display of wealth.
Some of these fabrics, woven from hand spun yarns, yahood bahut thik liye unke din, lakin hai coarse compared to aadhunik linen.
Today, linen is praayah an mahangi vastra, or is utpaadit in relatively small quantities.
it rai a long `` stepal '' ( vyaktigat resha lambaai ) saapeksh to kapaas or other natural fibers.
Many products are made of linen : aprons, bag, tauliye ( swimmers, nahaana, bich, deh or dho tauliye ), napkins, bed linens, linen chauke, dhaavak, chair covers, and men 's & women 's wear.
The FIFA World Cup, often simply the World Cup, is an international association footbaal pratiyogita lade by the varisht main 's neshnal tiimon of the sadasyon of fédération internationale de Football Association ( FIFA ), the sport 's global governing body.
The championships rai maharoom awarded prayek chaar saalo chunki the inaugural toornament in 1930, except in 1942 and 1946 when it was not held because of the Second World War.
The vartmaan champions hai spain, jo won the 2010 tournament.
The current format of the tournament involves 32 teams competing for the sheershak at venues bheetar the mejabaan swadesh ( s ) over a kaal of parichay a maah ; is phase is praayah pukaara the sansar cap Finals.
A qualification phase, jisase philhal takes place over the preceding teen saalo, is prayukt to determine jisase tiimon qualify for the tournament together with the host nation ( s ).
the 19 sansar cap tournaments have maharoom won by eight different national teams.
Brazil have jiti paanch times, or ve hai the tabhi toli to have played in every tournament.
The other World Cup winners are Italy, with chaar sheershak ; germany, saath teen sheershak ; argentina or inaugural vijeta urugve, saath do sheershak prayek ; or england, France, and Spain, with one title each.
The World Cup is the world 's sabase widely viewed sporting event ; an anumaanit 715.1 lakh logon dekhi the final match of the 2006 FIFA World Cup held in Germany.
the aglaa teen sansar cups hoga be hosted by brazil in 2014, Russia in 2018, and Qatar in 2022.

Majulah Singapura ( onward singapore ) is the neshnal anthem of Singapore.
Composed by Zubir Said in 1958 as a theme song liye aadhikarik krityon of the nagar parishad of singapore, the song thi selected in 1959 as the island 's anthem when it attained self-government.
Upon full swatantraaa in 1965, majulah singapura thi formally apanaaya as singapore 's national anthem.
By law the anthem may only be sung with iske asli malay geet, haalanki vahin maujuud praadhikrut anuwaad of the geet of the gaan in singapore 's three other official languages : English, Mandarin and Tamil.
Originally composed in the key of G pramukh, in 2001 the neshnal gaan thi officially relaunched in the nimnatar kunjee of f pramukh as is thi kaha to allow liye a `` grander or more inspiring arrangement ''.
The neshnal gaan is regularly performed or sung in skulon or hathiyaarband shaktiyaan shiviron at ceremonies yojit at the shuruuaat and/or the samaapt of prayek din, during which the national flag is also raised and lowered and the national pledge is taken.
Singaporeans are especially encouraged to sing the national anthem on avasaron of neshnal jashn or neshnal significance aise as at the neshnal din parade, at neshnal din observance ceremonies conducted by shaikshanik sansthaanon or sarkari vibhaag, and at sporting events at which Singapore teams are participating.

The following is a list of the most populous incorporated sthaan of the sanyukt rajya of America.

This list presents only that portion ( or `` santulan '' ) of aise sanchit city-counties ki hai nahin a part of another incorporated place.

Nintendo DS storage devices are devices used to store a licensed developer 's work-in-progress bimb, homebrew video khel or downlod vanijyik khel ( chunki the Nintendo DS is not sold with a rewritable storage medium ).
Licensed developers, however, can use a blue budhimaan pranaaliyon nitro emulator baksaa to flash cards.
These devices are bhi gyaat as `` flashcarts '' or `` flashcards ''.
There are two main classes of flashcarts : puraani divaais jisase anuroop in slot-2 ( the khel ladke agrim khel paak slot ) or nae divaais ki anuroop in slot-1 ( the DS Game Card slot ).
Slot-2 ( or first-generation ) devices have been historically sasta due to economies of scale ( inherited isse unke upyog saath khel ladke agrim ), lakin aavashyaktaa a booting aujaar in slot-1 in anukram to use the touch screen and other DS features.
Second-generation devices ( those which only use slot-1 ) do nahin kaary saath gba homebrew, lakin became kam mahangi or easier to upyog, rivaling anek Slot-2 devices in price.
First-generation divaais shaamil gba flash kaartoos, gbamp cf, supercard, and M3.
Second-generation devices shaamil r4 kranti, cyclods, g6 real or ds-x.
The bhandar yantra either contains flash memory or a slot liye a memory card to store homebrew.
Storage divaais saath a memory-card slot praayah have adhik bhandar kshamta than flash-memory devices.
Although flash-memory capacity is usually measured in megabits ( mb ), memory-card kshamta is praayah measured in megabite ( MB ) ( where 8 Mb is 1 MB ).
Storage-device brands differ in their support for homebrew ; DS and khel ladke agrim roms ; khaas suvidhaayen ( aise as kshamta to khel media filein ) ; physical size and cost.
Strictly bolnaa, a bhandar yantra is nahin jaruri liye ds saath flashme installed because homebrew can be sent to the DS using WMB.
However, this is not an easily-portable vidhi kuki the ds needs to be bheetar dayera of a upyukt Wi-Fi card.

Geocaching is an outdoor recreational activity, in which the participants use a Global positioning pranali ( gps ) receiver or mobile yantra or anya navigational takneekon to chupa or talash containers, pukaara `` geocaches '' or `` caches '', anywhere in the world.
A typical cache is a small waterproof sangraahak containing a logbook jahaan the geocacher enters the tithi they found it and signs it with their established code name.
After hastakshar into the log, the sanchay jarur be lagaai waapas exactly where the person found it.
Larger containers such as plastic bhandar containers ( tupperware or samaan ) or ammunition baks can bhi contain vasteen for trading, usually toys or trinkets of little value.
Geocaching shares many aspects with benchmarking, trigpointing, orienteering, treasure-hunting, letterboxing, and waymarking.

A nagarpalika bandha is a bandha jari by a local government, or their agencies.
Potential issuers of municipal bonds include states, shaharon, county, redevelopment agenciyon, special-purpose jile, skool jile, public utility jile, saream swaamitv airport or seaports, or any other governmental entity ( or group of governments ) at or below the state level.
Municipal bonds may be general dayitvon of the jarikarta or secured by nirdisht revenues.
In the United States, interest income received by holders of municipal bonds is often exempt from the federal income tax and from the aay kar of the rajya in jisase ve hai jari, haalanki nagarpalika bonds jari liye nishchit uddeshy may not be tax exempt.
Unlike new samasya stox ki hai brought to market saath daam pratibandh jabatak the saude is bechi, nagarpalika bonds are free to trade at any time once they are purchased by the investor.
Professional traders regularly trade and retrade the vahi bonds anek times a week.

In computer hardware, a host controller, mejabaan adapter, or mejabaan bas adapter ( hba ) connects a mejabaan pranali ( the computer ) to other network and storage devices.
The terms are primarily used to refer to divaais liye connecting scsi, fibre channel or esata devices.
However, devices for connecting to IDE, ethernet, firewire, usb or anya pranaaliyon may bhi be pukaara host adapters.
recently, the aagaman of iscsi or fibre channel over ethernet rai brought parichay ethernet HBAs, which are different from Ethernet NICs in that they include TCP Offload Engines.
There are also converged HBAs that support dono ethernet or fibre channel pukaara converged sanjaal Adapters ( CNAs ).

Pain and suffering is the legal term for the physical or emotional tanaav caused isse an chot ( dekhie bhi pidaa or ksht ).
Some damages that might be under this category would be : aches, asthai or sthai simaaen on kaaryaklap, sambhavit shortening of jivan, avsaad or scarring.
When daakhil a mukadmaa as a parinaam of an chot, it is aam liye kisi to seek money both in compensation for actual money that is lost and for the pain and stress associated with virtually any injury.
In a suit, pain and suffering is part of the `` general damages '' section of the claimant 's arji, or, alternatively, it is an tatv of `` compensatory '' non-economic kshatipurti ki allows recovery liye the dimagi anguish and/or shaareerik pidaa endured by the claimant as a parinaam of chot liye jisase the abhiyokta seeks redress.
Apart from money damages awarded in trial, money damages are also given informally outside the judicial system in mediations, madhyasthata ( dono of jisase may be adaalat annexed or gaiyr litigated daawa ) as khub as in dincharya bime settlements.
Individual claimants or those represented by lawyers praayah upasthit maange to insurers to settle liye dhan.
These demand for bodily injury compensation monies often set out kshatipurti ki hai similarly prayukt in the adaalat litigated pleadings.
Demands are usually likhaa summaries of a claimant 's chikitsa parvaah or the tathy jisase resulted in the injury.

the United rajya or canada, a medallion hastakshar guarantee is a khaas hastakshar guarantee for the transfer of securities.
It is a guarantee by the transferring vittiya sanstha ki the hastakshar is vaastavik or the vittiya sanstha sweekrut deyta for any forgery.
Signature guarantees protect shairdharakon by preventing anadhikrut hastantaran or sambhavit investor losses.

Most sansthaanon hoga nahin guarantee a hastakshar of kisi who has not already been their customer.
A medallion signature guarantee is not the same as an acknowledgment by a notary public, in the bhav ki a `` hastakshar guarantee '' is a pramann by the sanstha ki the hastakshar is authentic, and an acknowledgment is a certification by a notary public attesting that the signer signed a document voluntarily.

The General Motors streetkar shadyantr ( bhi gyaat as the great amareeki streetkar cond ) refers to doshaaropan or convictions in sambandh to a program by General Motors ( GM ) and other companies who purchased and then dismantled streetcar and electric train systems in many American cities.
Between 1936 and 1950, National City Lines and Pacific City Lines —with investment from GM, Firestone Tire, Standard Oil of California, Phillips Petroleum, Mack Trucks, and the sangheey abhiyantriki corporation—bought over 100 electric surface-traction pranaaliyon in 45 shaharon sahit balteemor, neurk, los angeles, nai york nagar, ockland or san diego or parivartit unhen into bas aaparishan.
Several of the companiyaan shaamil yahood convicted in 1949 of shadyantr to monopolize antarraji commerce but were acquitted of conspiring to monopolize the ownership of these companies.
Some suggest that this program played a key role in the decline of public transit in cities across the United States ; notably Edwin J. Quinby, who first drew attention to the kaarykram in 1946, or tab breadford C. snell, an anti-trust attorney liye the sanyukt rajya seenet jinaki vivaadaaspad 1974 gavaahi to a seenet poochtacha brought the samasya to neshnal jaagrukta.
Both Quinby and Snell argued that the deliberate vinaash of streetcars thi bhaag of a larger ranneeti to dhakka the sanyukt rajya into automobile dependency.
anya kah ki swatantra aarthik karkon brought parichay parivartan in the pargaman pranali, sahit the great avsaad, the public utility pakadakar company adhinium of 1935, majdoor ashaanti, market shaktiyaan, rapidly increasing traffic congestion, urban sprawl, taxation policies that favored private vehicle ownership, and general enthusiasm for the automobile.
One writer on the subject has suggested that snell or anya giri into simplistic shadyantr siddhanth soch, bordering on paranoid delusions saying `` Clearly, GM waged a war on electric traction.
It was beshak an sab out utpeedan, lakin by no arthath the single kaaran liye the vifaltaa of rapid transit.
Also, it is bas as saaf ki kriyaayein or inactions by sarkari contributed significantly to the elimination of electric traction. ''
Only a small handful of U.S. cities have surviving prabhavi rail-based shahari hastantaran pranaaliyon aadhaarit on streetcars or trams, sahit neurk, philadelphia, san francisco, pittsburg, and Boston ; others are re-introducing them.
The story has been explored several times in print, film and anya media, notably in jo framed roger khargosh, liya liye a sawari or the samaapt of suburbia.

A gramophone record, commonly known as a phonograph ricard ( in amareeki angrezi ), vinil ricard ( in sandarbh to vinil, the saamagree sabase commonly prayukt baad parichay 1950 ), or colloquially, `` a ricard '', is an analog dhwani storage medium consisting of a flat disc with an inscribed, modulated spiral groove.
The groove usually starts near the periphery or ends nikat the bich of the disc.
Phonograph records are generally described by their diameter in inches ( 12-inch, 10-inch, 7-inch, etc. ), the rotational speed at jisase ve hai nibhaai ( `` 33 arpm ``, `` 78 '', `` 45 '', ityadi. ), unke samay kshamta ( `` long playing '' ), their reproductive accuracy, or `` fidelity `` ( `` high fidelity '', `` Orthophonic '', `` full-range '', etc. ), and the number of channels of audio provided ( `` mono ``, `` stereo ``, `` quadraphonic ``, etc. ).
Phonograph records were the primary medium used for music reproduction for most of the 20th sadi, replacing the phonograph belan, saath jisase it tha co-existed, by the 1920s.
by the let 1980s, digital media tha gained a larger market share, and the vinyl record left the mainstream in 1991.
They continue to be manufactured and sold in the 21st century.
In 2008, nearly 2.9 lakh ikai shipped, the sabase in koi saal chunki 1998 or the swaroop rai jari to slowly regain popularity.
They hai visheshkar prayukt by djs or audiophiles liye many types of music.
As of 2013, vinil record continue to be used for distribution.

Grasslands are areas where the vegetation is dominated by grasses ( poesi ), however sedge ( cyperaceae ) or fatafat ( juncaceae ) pariwaron can bhi be mila.
Grasslands occur naturally on sab mahadwipon magar Antarctica.
In temperate latitudes, such as northwestern Europe and the Great Plains and California in North America, deshi grasslands hai varchasv by baramasi guchha grass prajati, whereas in warmer climates salanaa species form a greater component of the vegetation.
grasslands hai mila in sabase ecoregions of the Earth.

A thin film is a layer of material ranging from bhinnon of a nanometer ( monolayer ) to anek micrometers in thickness.
Electronic semiconductor divaais or optical coatings hai the pramukh anuprayog laabhakaari isse thin-film construction.
A familiar application of patala films is the household darpan, jisase typically rai a patala metal coating on the waapas of a chadar of glass to form a reflective interface.
The process of silvering thi ekbar commonly prayukt to produce mirrors.
A very-thin-film coating ( kam than a nanometer motaa ) is prayukt to produce two-way mirrors.
The performance of optical coatings ( e.g. antireflective, or ar, coatings ) hai typically unnat jab the thin-film coating consists of anek paraton having varying thicknesses and refractive indices.
Similarly, a periodic structure of alternating thin films of alag saamagree may collectively rup a so-called superlattice jisase karname the ghatana of kwantum confinement by restricting electronic phenomena to two-dimensions.
Work is being done with ferromagnetic or ferroelectric patala films liye upyog as computer memory.
It is also hone lagu to davaayen, via thin-film drug delivery.
Thin-films are used to upaj thin-film bydaree.
patala films hai bhi prayukt in dye-sensitized solar cells.
Ceramic thin films hai in chaudee upyog.
The relatively high hardness and inertness of ceramic materials make this type of patala coating of byaaj liye suraksha of substrate saamagree viruddh sanksharan, oxikaran or pahanen.
In particular, the use of such coatings on kating tuls can extend the jivan of ye vasteen by several orders of magnitude.
Research is being kiya on a nai class of thin-film acarbonic oxide saamagree, pukaara amorphous heavy-metal cation multicomponent oxide, jisase could be prayukt to make transparent transistors that are inexpensive, stable, and environmentally benign.

World map with the intertropical mandal highlighted in red.
Tropical climate zones of the Earth jahaan sab baarah maheene have ausat temperatures upar 18 °C ( 64 °F ).
The tropics is a region of the dharti surrounding the equator.
it is simit in akshansh by the tropic of karkat in the uttari golardh at lagbhag n or the tropic of Capricorn in the southern hemisphere at S ; these latitudes correspond to the axial tilt of the Earth.
The tropics are also referred to as the teevr mandal or the torrid mandal ( dekhie bhugolic mandal ).
The tropics include all the areas on the Earth jahaan the surya pahunch a point sidhe overhead at tanik ekbar dauraan the solar year.
The tropics are distinguished from the anya climatic or biomatic regions of dharti, the madhya latitudes or the dhruviya regions on either side of the equatorial zone.

The driver and yatri saamne airbags, baad having maharoom tainaat, in a British Peugeot 306 car.
an airbag is a gadee suraksha device.
It is an occupant sanyam pranali consisting of a lacheelee kapadaa lipapha or cushion designed to inflate rapidly during an automobile collision.
Its purpose is to cushion occupants dauraan a krash or provide suraksha to unke laashen jab ve strike aantarik vastuen aise as the steering wheel or a window.
Modern vehicles may contain multiple airbag modules in various side and frontal locations of the passenger seating positions, and sensors may tainaat ek or adhik airbags in an prabhaav mandal at parivartaneey daron aadhaarit on the prakaar, kone or gambhirtha of prabhaav ; the airbag is designed to tabhi inflate in moderet to kathor frontal krash.
airbags hai saamanytah designed saath the iraade of supplementing the suraksha of an occupant who is correctly restrained with a seatbelt.
Most dizin hai inflated through pyrotechnic means and can only be operated once.
Newer side-impact airbag maudul consist of sampidit air silendar ki hai triggered in the event of a side impact vehicle impact.
The first commercial designs yahood introduced in yatri automobile during the 1970s with limited success.
Broad commercial adoption of airbags occurred in many markets during the late 1980s and jaldi 1990s saath a driver airbag, or a saamne yatri airbag as khub on kuch gaadiyaan ; or anek aadhunik vaahanon abhi include four or more units.
IRS tax forms are used for taxpayers and tax-exempt organizations to rapat vittiya soochna to the aatanrik aay seva ( irs ) of the United States.
They are used to report income, calculate kar to be sashulk to the sangheey sarkari of the sanyukt rajya, or zaahir anya soochna as jaruri by the Internal Revenue Code ( IRC ).
There hai over 800 vibhinn form or schedules.
