a rajya may bhi barkhaastagi an vyaktigat 's driving visheshadhikaar within its borders for traffic violations.
Many states share a common system of anugna varg, saath kuch apwaad, or vanijyik anugna varg hai manakikrut by federal regulation at 49 CFR part 383.
China has been the source of anek avishkaron, sahit the chaar great avishkaron : papermaking, the compass, barood, or mudran ( dono woodblock and movable type ).
The list below contains ye or anya avishkaron.
The Chinese invented technologies involving yantriki, hydraulics, or ganit lagu to horology, metallurgy, khagolashastra, krishi, engineering, music theory, craftsmanship, nautics, and warfare.
By the Warring States Period ( 403–221 bc ), ve tha unnat metallurgic praudyogiki, sahit the dhamaakaa bhatti or cupola bhatti, while the finery forge and puddling process were known by the Han Dynasty ( 202 BC – AD 220 ).
A sophisticated aarthik pranali in china diya janam to avishkaron such as paper money during the Song Dynasty ( 960–1279 ).
The invention of gunpowder by the 10th century led to an array of inventions such as the fire lance, land mine, naval meraa, haath topon, exploding golon, multistage prakshepastra, or prakshepastra bam with aerodynamic wings and explosive payloads.
With the navigational aid of the 11th-century compass or kshamta to steer at unchi samudr saath the 1st-century sternpost aritra, premodern Chinese sailors sailed as far as East Africa and Egypt.
In water-powered clockworks, the premodern chinis tha prayukt the escapement yantriki chunki the 8th sadi and the endless power-transmitting chain drive in the 11th century.
They also bana vishaal mechanical kathputli theatre chalit by waterwheels or carriage pahiyon or wine-serving automatons driven by paddle wheel boats.
The contemporaneous Peiligang and Pengtoushan cultures represent the oldest pashankalin samskritiyon of china or yahood formed around 7000 bc.
Some of the first inventions of Neolithic, prehistoric China include semilunar and rectangular stone knives, stone hoes and spades, the cultivation of bajra, rice or the soyabean, the refinement of sericulture, the bhawan of rammed dharti structures saath lim -plastered house floors, the sristi of the kumhaar 's wheel, the sristi of pottery saath cord-mat-basket designs, the creation of pottery tripods and pottery steamers, and the development of ceremonial vessels and scapulimancy for purposes of divination.
Francesca Bray argues ki the domestication of the ox or bhens dauraan the longshan samskruti ( c. 3000–c. 2000 bc ) kaal, the anupasthiti of longshan-era sinchai or high-yield fasalon, puraa pramaan of longshan cultivation of dry-land khadyann fasalon jisase diya unchi yields `` tabhi jab the mrudaa thi carefully cultivated, '' suggest that the plow was known at least by the Longshan culture period and explains the high agricultural production yields which allowed the rise of Chinese civilization during the Shang Dynasty ( c. 1600–c. 1050 BC ).
With later avishkaron aise as the multiple-tube beej drill or baari moldboard aayran hal, china 's agricultural output could sustain a much larger population.
For the purposes of this list, inventions are regarded as technological firsts developed in China, or as aise karata nahin shaamil videshi technologies jisase the chinis acquired through sampark, aise as the pavanchakki isse the madhya east or the telescope from Early modern Europe.
It also does not include technologies viksit elsewhere or baad invented separately by the chinis, aise as the odometer and chain pump.
Scientific, mathematic or natural discoveries, parivartan in naaballig avadharanaon of dizine or style or kalakaari navapravartanon can nahin be regarded as inventions and do not appear on the list.
Gross gharelu utpaada in 2011 us dollar prati capita, samyojit liye mahangaai or khareednaa shakti parity ( log scale ) isse 1860 to 2011, with population ( disk area ) for the US ( yellow ), UK ( orange ), Japan ( red ), China ( red ), and India ( blue ).
Globalization ( or globalisation—see spelling differences ) is the prakram of antarrashtriya sangyojan arising isse the interchange of sansar drishy, products, ideas, and other aspects of culture.
Put in simple terms, globalization refers to prakriyaaon ki prachaar world-wide exchanges of neshnal or cultural resources.
Advances in transportation and telecommunications avasanrachana, sahit the vruddhi of the antarjaal, hai pramukh karkon in vaishvikaran, generating further interdependence of aarthik and cultural activities.
Though several scholars place the origins of vaishvikaran in aadhunik times, anya tres iske itihaas long pehle the europea age of discovery and voyages to the New World.
Some even tres the origins to the teesraa milinium BCE.
Since the beginning of the 20th century, the pace of globalization has intensified at a rapid rate, visheshkar dauraan the post thanda yuddh era.
The term vaishvikaran rai maharoom in increasing upyog chunki the mid-1980s and especially since the mid-1990s.
In 2000, the International Monetary Fund ( IMF ) pahachaanaa chaar moulik pahaluon of vaishvikaran : vyapaar or tranjection, puunji or nivesh andolanon, migration or gati of logon or the dissemination of knowledge.
Further, environmental challenges such as climate change, cross-boundary jal or air pradooshan, or over-fishing of the samandar hai linked saath vaishvikaran.
Globalizing processes affect and are affected by business and kaary sanghathan, arthshaastra, socio-cultural sansaadhan, or the natural environment.

The list includes the city, country, the codes of the International Air Transport Association ( IATA airport code ) or the antarrashtriya civil vimaanan sanghathan ( icao vimaanashetra code ), or the vimaanashetra 's naam, saath the airline 's hubs, fokas shaharon or seasonal destinations marked.
The suchi bhi contains gantavyon no longer parosa by the airline, which are marked as terminated destinations.
It does not include destinations parosa liye amareeki airlines by iske kshetreey affiliates amareeki tribhuj Airlines, Executive Airlines, and AmericanConnection.
`` Day-O ( The Banana Boat Song ) '' is a traditional Jamaican mento folk song, the best-known sanskaran of jisase thi sung by harry belafonte or an vaikalpik sanskaran interspersed saath another jamaican folksong, Hill and Gully Rider, by Dame Shirley Bassey.
Despite the song 's mento influences, `` Day-O ( The banana naav song ) '' is widely gyaat as an udhaaharan of callypso music.
It is a work song, from the point of drishy of dock majdoor working the raatri shift ladaan kele onto ships.
Daylight has aaiye, the shift is over or ve want unke kaary to be gine up so that they can go home.
World yuddh i ( wwi ) thi a vaishvik yuddh kendrit in europea ki began on 28 july 1914 and lasted until 11 November 1918.
It was predominantly called the World War or the Great yuddh isse iske occurrence jabatak the prarambh of sansar yuddh ii in 1939, or the First World War or World War I thereafter.
It involved all the world 's great powers, which were assembled in two opposing alliances : the Allies ( based on the Triple Entente of the United Kingdom, France and Russia ) and the Central shaktiyaan ( originally the tripal gathbandhan of germany, austria-hungary or italy ; lakin, as austria–hungary tha liya the apriy viruddh the anubandh, italy did not enter into the war ).
These alliances were both reorganised and expanded as more nations entered the yuddh : italy, japani or the sanyukt rajya joined the allies, or the osmani samrajya or bulgaria the central shaktiyaan.
Ultimately, more than 70 lakh sainya karmiyon, sahit 60 lakh europeans, were mobilised in one of the largest wars in history.
More than 9 million combatants were killed, largely because of technological advancements ki led to vishaal increases in the lethality of hathiyaar bagaiyr sambandhit sudhaar in suraksha or gatishiltaa.
It was the fifth- deadliest conflict in world history, subsequently paving the rasta liye vibhinn rajnatik parivartan, aise as revolutions in anek of the nations involved.
One of the long-term causes of the war was the resurgence of samrajyavad in the videshi nitiyon of the great shaktiyaan of europea.
More immediately, the assassination of Archduke Franz ferdinand of austria, the vaaris to the singhaasana of austria-hungary, on 28 june 1914 by yugoslav rashtravaadi gavrilo princip in sarajevo triggered a rajanyik crisis when Austria-Hungary subsequently delivered an ultimatum to the Kingdom of Serbia.
Several alliances formed over the pichhlaa decades were invoked.
Within weeks, the pramukh shaktiyaan yahood at yuddh or, via unke colonies, the virodh soon spread around the world.
On 28 July, the Austro-Hungarians fired the first goliyaan of the yuddh as taiyaari liye the akraman of Serbia.
While the Russians mobilised, the Germans invaded neutral belgium or dhvaj on the rasta to frans, providing a casus belli liye britain 's declaration of war against Germany.
After the germany kooch on paris thi brought to a halt—the so-called chamatkaar of the marne —the pashchimi saamne settled into a static battle of attrition with a trench line that changed little until 1917.
On the Eastern Front, the Russian army thi kaamyaab viruddh the austro-hungarians, lakin thi roka in iske akraman of east Prussia by the Germans.
In November the Ottoman Empire joined the yuddh, kholane up fronts in the kakeshas, mesopotamia or the sinai.
Italy or bulgaria gai to yuddh in 1915 or romania in 1916.
In Russia, the tsar 's sarkari collapsed in kooch 1917 or a subsequent kranti in navambar brought the russians to terms with the Central Powers.
After a 1918 germany apriy saath the pashchimi saamne, the allies drove waapas the germans in a shrenee of kaamyaab offensives and American forces began entering the trenches.
Germany, which had its own trouble with krantikariyon, sahamat to an armistice on 11 navambar 1918.
The yuddh ended in vijay liye the Allies.
Events on the home fronts were as tumultuous as on the battle fronts, as the bhagidaar aajamaaya to mobilize unke janashakti or aarthik sansaadhan to lado a total war.
By the end of the war, four major imperial powers—the germany, roosi, austro-hungarian or osmani empires—ceased to exist.
The successor rajya of the purv do khoyaa a great raashi of territory, while the latter two were dismantled entirely.
The map of central Europe thi redrawn into anek choti rajya.
The League of Nations thi formed in the aashaa of preventing another aise virodh.
The European nationalism spawned by the war and the breakup of empires, the repercussions of Germany 's defeat or samasyaayein saath the sandhi of versailles hai sahamat to be karkon contributing to World War II.

It follows the lives of the kardashian/jenner parivaar, sahit bahanon courtney, Kim, and Khloé Kardashian.

Afghanistan ( ; ; ), officially the islamic ganatantr of afghanistan, is a landlocked sovereign rajya forming part of South Asia, Central Asia, and to some extent Western Asia.
It has a janasankhyikee of around 30 lakh inhabiting an kshetrafal of lagbhag, bananaa it the 42nd sabase populous or 41st largest swadesh in the world.
It is bordered by pakistani in the dakshin or the east, iraan in the west, turkmenistan, uzbekistan or tajikistan in the uttar, and China in the far northeast.
Afghanistan has been an pracheen focal point of the resha sadak or insaan migration.
Archaeologists have found evidence of insaan habitation isse as dur waapas as the madhya paleolithic.
Urban sabhyataa may have begun in the kshetrafal as jaldi as 3,000 to 2,000 BCE.
Sitting at an important geostrategic location that connects the madhya east samskruti saath central asia or the bhartiya upmahadweep, the jameen rai maharoom ghar to vibhinn peoples through the aayu or witnessed anek military campaigns, notably by Alexander the Great, Genghis Khan, and in modern era Western forces.
The land also served as a source from which the Greco-Bactrians, kushans, hephthalites, saffarids, ghaznavids, ghorids, khiljis, timurids, mughalon, durranis, or anya have risen to form major empires.
The political history of the modern state of afghanistan begins in 1709, jab the hotaki rajvansh thi sthapit in kandahar followed by ahamed shah durrani 's rise to power in 1747.
In the let 19th sadi, afghanistan became a bafar rajya in the `` Great Game `` between the British and Russian empires.
following the 1919 anglo-afghan yuddh, king amanulla began a europea style modernization of the country but was stopped by the ultra-conservatives.
During the Cold War, after the withdrawal of the British from neighboring india in 1947, the sanyukt rajya or the soviet sangh began spreading prabhaav in afghanistan, jisase led to a khooni yuddh between the us-backed mujahidin shaktiyaan and the Soviet-backed Afghan government in which over a million Afghans lost their lives.
This was followed by the 1990s civil yuddh, the vruddhi or patan of the extremist taliban sarkari or the 2001–present war.
In December 2001, the United Nations Security Council authorized the sristi of the antarrashtriya suraksha sahaayta force ( isaf ) to sahaayta maintain suraksha in afghanistan or assist the Karzai administration.
Three decades of war made Afghanistan one of the world 's sabase khatarnaak deshon, sahit the largest nirmaataa of sharnaarthiyon or asylum zaruratmandon.
While the antarrashtriya jatiyaan is punarnirmaan war-torn afghanistan, aatankwaadi samooh aise as the hakkaani sanjaal or hezbi islami hai actively shaamil in a nationwide Taliban -led insurgency, which includes hundreds of assassinations and suicide attacks.
According to the sanyukt raashtra, the insurgents yahood jimmedaar for 80 % of civilian casualties in 2011 and 2012.
The American Civil War ( ACW ), also known as the yuddh between the rajya or bas the civil yuddh ( dekhie namakaran ), thi a civil yuddh ladaa isse 1861 to 1865 between the sanyukt rajya ( the `` sangh '' or the `` uttar '' ) or anek dakshini slave states that declared their secession and formed the Confederate States of America ( the `` Confederacy '' or the `` South '' ).
The war had its origin in the issue of slavery, visheshkar the ekstansion of gulaami into the pashchimi territories.
videshi shaktiyaan kiya nahin intervene.
After four years of bloody combat that left over 600,000 sainiko murde or nasht much of the dakshin 's avasanrachana, the confederacy collapsed, gulaami thi abolished, or the mushkil punarnirmaan prakram of restoring neshnal unity and guaranteeing rights to the freed slaves began.
In the 1860 adhyakshiya chunaav, republicans, led by abraham lincoln, opposed expanding slavery into United States ' territories.
Lincoln won, but before his udghaatan on kooch 4, 1861, saat cotton-based slave rajya formed the Confederacy.
Outgoing loktantric adhyaksh james bukanan or the aavak republicans asweekrut secession as illegal.
Lincoln 's inaugural pataa ghoshit uske prashasan would not initiate civil war.
aath baaki slave rajya jari to reject calls for secession.
Confederate forces seized numerous sangheey durgon bheetar territory claimed by the Confederacy.
A Peace Conference failed to dhundhen a sulah, or dono pahalu prepared for war.
The Confederates assumed that European deshon yahood so nirbhar on `` king kapaas `` ki ve hota intervene ; none kiya or none pahachaanaa the nai confederate States of America.
Hostilities began on April 12, 1861, when Confederate forces fired upon fort sumter, a kunjee fort yojit by sangh sainikon in dakshin carolina.
lincoln pukaara liye prayek rajya to provide sainikon to retake the fort ; natijatan, four more slave states joined the Confederacy, bringing their total to eleven.
The Union soon controlled the kinaaraa rajya or sthapit a naval nakebandi ki abodh the southern economy.
The Eastern theatre thi inconclusive in 1861–62.
the patjhad 1862 confederate abhiyaan into maryland ( a sangh rajya ) ended saath confederate retreat at the Battle of Antietam, dissuading British intervention.
Lincoln issued the Emancipation Proclamation, jisase bana samaapti gulaami a yuddh goal.
To the west, by summer 1862 the sangh nasht the confederate nadi navy, tab much of unke pashchimi sena, or the sangh at vicksburg vibhajit the Confederacy in two at the Mississippi River.
in 1863, robert E. lee 's confederate incursion north ended at the Battle of Gettysburg.
Western successes led to Ulysses S. Grant cmand of sab sangh sena in 1864.
In the pashchimi theatre, wiliam T. sharaman drove east to capchar atlanta or marched to the sea, destroying Confederate infrastructure along the way.
The Union marshaled the resources and janashakti to akraman the confederacy isse sab dishanirdesh, or could afford to lado ladaaiyon of apgharshan through the overland abhiyaan towards Richmond, the Confederate capital.
The defending confederate fouj vifal, agrani to lee 's aatmasamarpan to grant at appomattox Court House on April 9, 1865.
the amareeki civil yuddh thi ek of the earliest true industrial wars.
Railroads, the telegraph, steamships, or mass-produced weapons were employed extensively.
The mobilization of civilian kaarkaanon, khaanon, shipyards, bainko, parivahan or khaanaa aapurtiyan all foreshadowed World War I.
It remains the deadliest yuddh in amareeki itihaas, resulting in the mauton of an anumaanit 750,000 sainiko or an undetermined kramank of civilian casualties.
itihaaskaar jon huddleston estimates the maut toll at ten percent of all Northern males 20–45 years old, and 30 percent of all Southern white males aged 18–40.
laagat of goods bechi ( cogs ) refer to the inventory costs of those goods a business has sold during a particular period.
Costs are sambhddha saath particular goods using ek of anek formulas, including specific identification, first-in first-out ( FIFO ), or average cost.
Costs include all laagat of khariden, laagat of parivartan or anya laagat incurred in bringing the inventories to their present location and condition.
Costs of goods bana by the kaarobaar shaamil saamagree, majdoor, and allocated overhead.
The costs of those goods not yet sold are deferred as costs of inventory jabatak the inventory is bechi or likhaa bas in maan.

A confectionery store ( adhik commonly referred to as a mithi duukaan in the sanyukt kingdom, a candi store in the uttar america, or a lolly shop in Australia ) sells confectionery and is usually targeted to children.
Most confectionery stores hai bhar saath an assortment of mithai dur larger than a grocer or convenience store could accommodate.

Oklahoma ( ) ( Pawnee : Uukuhuúwa, cay : gahnawiyoˀgeh ) is a rajya stith in west South Central United States.
Oklahoma is the 20th most extensive or the 28th sabase populous of the 50 sanyukt rajya.
The state 's name is derived from the choctaw shabd okla or humma, arth `` red logon '', or it is gyaat informally by iske upnaam, the sooner State.
Formed by the combination of Oklahoma territory or bhartiya territory on navambar 16, 1907, oklahoma thi the 46th state to enter the union.
Its residents are known as Oklahomans or, informally `` okies '', or iske puunji or largest nagar is Oklahoma City.
A major producer of natural gas, oil, and krishi, oklahoma relies on an aarthik aadhaar of vimaanan, urja, doorsanchaar, and biotechnology.
It has one of the fastest growing economies in the nation, ranking among the sheersh rajya in prati capita aay vikaas or sakal gharelu product growth.
Oklahoma City and Tulsa serve as Oklahoma 's primary economic anchors, saath nearly do tihaai of oklahomans jeena bheetar unke mahanagar statistical areas.
With small mountain ranges, preyari, mesas, or purvi wanon, sabase of oklahoma jhooth in the great maidan or the u.s. aantarik hilands —a region especially prone to severe weather.
In addition to having a prevalence of English, germany, scottish, irish or deshi amareeki ancestry, adhik than 25 deshi amareeki bhashaaen hai bolaa in oklahoma, duusari only to California.
Oklahoma is located on a confluence of teen pramukh amareeki saanskrithik regions or historically parosa as a root liye choupayon drive, a destination for southern settlers, and a government-sanctioned territory for Native Americans.
Stacked or khadaa car tair
A tire ( or tyre ) is a ring-shaped covering ki fits around a wheel 's rim to protect it or enable better vehicle performance.
Most tires, such as those liye automobile or cycle, provide karshan between the gadee or the sadak jabaki providing a lacheelee cushion that absorbs shock.
The materials of modern pneumatic tires hai synthetic rabar, prakritik rabar, kapadaa or taar, saath saath carbon blike or anya rasinic compounds.
They consist of a tread or a body.
The tread provides traction jabaki the deh provides containment liye a maatra of sampidit air.
Before rubber was developed, the pehla sanskaran of tair yahood bas bands of metal ki fitted around lakdi pahiyon to prevent pahanen or aansu.
jaldi rabar tair yahood thos ( not pneumatic ).
Today, the bahumat of tair hai neumatic inflatable structures, comprising a doughnut-shaped deh of cords and wires encased in rubber and generally filled with compressed air to form an inflatable cushion.
Pneumatic tires are used on many types of vaahanon, sahit gaadiyaan, cycle, motorcycle, trek, earthmovers, or vayuyan.
Metal tires are still used on injanon or railcars, or thos rabar ( or anya polimur ) tair hai still prayukt in vibhinn non-automotive applications, such as some casters, carts, lawnmowers, and wheelbarrows.
Dr. Joseph Warren ( june 11, 1741 – june 17, 1775 ) thi an amareeki doctor jo nibhaai a agrani bhoomika in amareeki patriot sanghathan in boston in jaldi dinon of the amareeki kranti, aakhirkaar sevarat as adhyaksh of the revolutionary Massachusetts Provincial Congress.
Warren enlisted Paul Revere and William Dawes on April 18, 1775, to leave Boston and spread the alarm that the angrejon garrison in boston thi setting out to red the kasbaa of concord or giraftaar vidrohi netao John Hancock and Samuel Adams.
Warren participated in the aglaa din 's ladaaiyon of lexington or concord, jisase hai commonly mana to be the opening engagements of the American Revolutionary War.
Warren had been commissioned a pramukh saamaanya in the upnivesh 's milicia shortly pehle the june 17, 1775 battle of Bunker Hill.
Rather than exercising his rank, Warren served in the battle as a nijee sipaahi, or thi maare in combat jab angrejon sainikon stormed the redoubt atop nasl 's hill.
His death, immortalized in jon trumbull 's painting, the maut of saamaanya warren at the battle of bunker 's hill, june 17, 1775, jasti the vidrohi shaktiyaan, or he rai been memorialized in many place names in the United States.
stm chitra of self-assembled supramolecular zanjeeron of the sashulk semiconductor Quinacridone on Graphite.
An sashulk semiconductor is an sashulk saamagree saath semiconductor properties, that is, with an electrical conductivity between that of insulators and that of metals.
Single anuon, choti kadi ( oligomers ) or sashulk polymers can be semiconductive.
Semiconducting small molecules ( aromatic hydrocarbons ) include the polycyclic khushboodaar yogicon pentacene, anthracene, or rubrene.
polymeric sashulk semiconductors shaamil bahu ( 3-hexylthiophene ), bahu ( p-phenylene vinylene ), as well as polyacetylene and its derivatives.
There are two pramukh ativyapee varg of sashulk semiconductors.
These are sashulk charge-transfer devalayas or vibhinn linear-backbone conductive polymers derived from polyacetylene.
Linear backbone organic semiconductors shaamil polyacetylene itself or iske derevative polypyrrole, and polyaniline.
At least locally, charge-transfer devalayas praayah pradarshnee samaan conduction mechanisms to acarbonic semiconductors.
aise mechanisms uthta isse the upasthiti of chhed or electron conduction layers separated by a band gap.
While such classic mechanisms are important locally, as with acarbonic amorphous semiconductors, tunnelling, sthaniyakrut rajya, gatishiltaa gap, or phonon -assisted hopping also significantly contribute to conduction, particularly in polyacetylenes.
Like acarbonic semiconductors, sashulk semiconductors can be doped.
Organic semiconductors susceptible to doping aise as polyaniline ( ormecon ) and are also known as organic metals.
theth vartmaan vaahak in sashulk semiconductors are holes and electrons in π-bonds.
lagbhag sab sashulk solids hai insulators.
But when their constituent anuon have π-conjugate pranaaliyon, electrons can move via π-electron badal overlaps, especially by hopping, tunnelling and related mechanisms.
Polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons and phthalocyanine salt crystals hai udhaaharan of is prakaar of sashulk semiconductor.
Mainly due to low mobility, bhi unpaired electrons may be stable in charge-transfer complexes.
Such unpaired electrons can falan as current carriers.
This type of semiconductor is also obtained by pairing an electron daata anu saath an electron acceptor anu.

The FIFA Women 's World Cup is an international association football competition contested by the varisht mahilaon 's neshnal tiimon of the sadasyon of fédération internationale de footbaal sangh ( fifa ), the khel 's vaishvik shaasi deh.
The championship has been awarded every four years since the inaugural toornament in 1991.

The current format of the tournament involves 16 teams spardhaa liye the sheershak at venues bheetar the mejabaan swadesh ( s ) over a kaal of parichay teen saptaah ; – this phase is often called the World Cup Finals.
A qualification phase, which currently takes place over the preceding three years, is prayukt to determine jisase tiimon qualify liye the toornament saath saath the mejabaan swadesh ( s ).
The FIFA Women 's World Cup is recognized as the most important International competition in women 's footbaal or is nibhaai amongst mahilaon 's neshnal footbaal tiimon of the sadsy rajya of fifa, the khel 's vaishvik shaasi deh.

'Son of man ' is the translation of various Hebrew or unani vaakyansh prayukt in dono the yahudee bible or the nai vasiyat.
It has diverse meanings, ranging from a saamaanya insaan hone to a prophesied anant, daivi ruler.
The Hebrew expression `` son of man '' ( בן–אדם i.e. ben-'adam ) appears ek sau or saat times in the Hebrew Bible.
This is the most common yahudee nirmaan liye the ekvachan lakin is prayukt zyaadaatar in ezekiel ( 93 times ) and 14 times elsewhere.
In thirty two cases the phrase appears in intermediat bahuvachan rup `` bete of main '', i.e. insaan beings.
As generally interpreted by yahudiyon, it denotes humankind generally.
In the koine unani of the nai vasiyat, `` the bete of man '' is invariably prayukt as `` ὁ υἱὸς τοὺ ἀνθρώπου '' with a definite article.
the upyog of the definite aalekh in `` the bete of man '' in the isai gospels is anokhaa, or pehle iske upyog vahin, no records of its use in any of the surviving Greek documents of antiquity exist.
Geza Vermes has stated that `` the Son of man '' in the isai gospels is unrelated to yahudee bible usages.
In Christian usage, unlike the Son of God title, jisase rai maharoom an anivaary tatv of isai creeds chunki the apostolic aayu, the udghoshnaa of `` yishu as the bete of man '' has never been an article of faith in Christianity.
The interpretation of the use of `` the Son of man '' in the nai vasiyat rai remained chunauteepurn or baad 150 saalo of bahes no sarvasammati on the samasya rai ubhara among scholars.
Master of foxhounds leads the field isse powderham kila in devon, england, saath the hounds in front.
Fox hunting is an activity involving the trekking, peechha, or sometimes hatya of a fox, traditionally a red fox, by prashikshit foxhounds or anya saint hounds, or a samooh of nihathe anusarankarta led by a nipun of foxhounds, who follow the hounds on foot or on horseback.
Fox hunting originated in the rup practised jabatak recently in the sanyukt kingdom in the 16th sadi, lakin is practised sab over the sansar, sahit in Australia, Canada, France, Ireland, Italy and the United States.
In Australia, the pad bhi refers to the shikaar of foxes saath firearms similar to spotlighting or deer hunting.
In much of the world hunting in general is understood to relate to any game animals or weapons ( e.g., deer hunting with bow and tir ) ; in britain or ireland, `` shikaar '' bagaiyr yogyata implies fox shikaar ( or anya form of shikaar saath houndaus- beagling, stag shikaar, mink shikaar, khichein hunting or hunting the clean boot ) as described here.
The sport is controversial, particularly in the UK, where it was banned in Scotland in 2002, and in england or wales in navambar 2004 ( vidhi enforced isse farvari 2005 ), haalanki shooting foxes as vermin remained legal.
Proponents of fox hunting view it as an mahatvapurn bhaag of gramin samskruti or upyogi liye kaaran of sangrakshan or pest control, jabaki pratidwandviyon argue ki it is cruel and unnecessary.

inferno ( italvi liye `` narak `` ) is the pehla bhaag of Dante Alighieri 's 14th-century epic poem Divine Comedy.
It is followed by purgatorio or paradiso.
It is an allegory telling of the yatra of dante through narak, hidaayat by the Roman poet Virgil.
In the kavita, narak is chitrit as nau vrutt of suffering located within the Earth.
Allegorically, the Divine Comedy represents the journey of the aatma towards parameshwar, saath the inferno describing the manyata or rejection of sin.

karavaaya by dr. geri B. nap 's monticule kheto in lexington, Kentucky, he won his first five race starts.

The Declaration and Resolves of the First Continental Congress ( also known as the Declaration of Colonial adhikaron, or the ghoshnaa of adhikaron ), thi a bayaan apanaaya by the pehla mahadwipiya congress on aktubar 14, 1774, in jawaab to the asahneeya adhiniyamon passed by the British Parliament.
The Declaration outlined colonial objections to the asahneeya adhiniyamon, soochibaddh a aupniveshik vidheyak of adhikaron, or provided a vistrut suchi of grievances.
It was similar to the ghoshnaa of adhikaron or grievances, passed by the stamp adhinium congress a decade earlier.
The Declaration concluded with an outline of Congress 's plans : to enter into a boycott of British trade ( the mahadwipiya sangh ) jabatak unke grievances yahood redressed, to prakashit pataa to the logon of great britain or British America, and to send a petition to the King.

If resting rakt dabaav is ( systolic/diastolic ) 120/80 millimeters of mercury ( mmHg ), pulse pressure is 40.

In poker, bad beat is a subjective term for a haath in jisase a khilaadi saath kayaa appear to be damdaar taash nevertheless loses.
It most often occurs jahaan ek khilaadi bets the clearly stronger haath or their opponent makes a poor call that eventually `` hits '' and wins.

The goldfish ( Carassius auratus auratus ) is a freshwater machhlee in the parivaar cyprinidae of anukram cypriniformes.
It was one of the earliest machhlee to be domesticated, or is ek of the sabase commonly rakhaa equarium fish.
A relatively small member of the carp parivaar ( jisase bhi shaamil the koi carp or the crucian carp ), the goldfish is a domesticated sanskaran of a less-colorful carp ( Carassius auratus ) native to east Asia.
It was first domesticated in China more than a hajaar saalo pehle, or anek pruthak breeds have since been developed.
Goldfish breeds vary greatly in aakaar, deh aakaar, jode vinyas or coloration ( vibhinn combinations of shwet, pilaa, naarangi, red, brown, and black are known ).

in kuch deshon, the roulade is also known as `` beef olive ''.

the maance is kaaten into vishaal, thin slices.

The mixture varies isse pradesh to region.

Typical eukaryotic koshika.
Cellular respiration is the set of the metabolic reactions and processes that take place in the koshikaayen of jeevon to badalen biochemical urja isse nutrients into adinosin triphosphate ( atipi ), or then release waste products.
The reactions involved in respiration are catabolic pratikriyaayein, jisase brake vishaal anuon into choti ones, releasing urja in the prakram as kamjor so-called `` high-energy '' bonds are replaced by stronger bonds in the products.
Respiration is one of the kunjee tareeke a koshika gains upyogi urja to eendhan cellular activity.
Cellular respiration is mana an ooshmakshepi radox pratikriya.
The overall reaction is broken into anek choti ones jab it occurs in the deh, sabase of jisase hai radox pratikriyaayein themselves.
Although technically, cellular shwasan is a dahan pratikriya, it clearly does not resemble one when it occurs in a living cell.
is antar is because it occurs in many separate steps.
While the overall reaction is a dahan pratikriya, no single pratikriya ki comprises it is a dahan reaction.
Nutrients that are commonly prayukt by animal or sanyantr koshikaayen in shwasan shaamil sugar, amino acids or vasiy acids, or a common oxidizing agent ( electron acceptor ) is molecular oxygen ( O2 ).
The energy stored in ATP ( its third phosphate group is weakly bandhua to the baaki of the anu or is cheaply tutaa allowing stronger bonds to rup, thereby transferring urja liye upyog by the koshika ) can tab be used to drive processes requiring energy, including biosynthesis, locomotion or transportation of molecules across cell membranes.

This article includes a list of countries in the sansar sorted by unke sakal gharelu utpaada ( jidipi ), the market maan of sab final goods and services from a nation in a given year.

ye economies hai nahin kramit in the chart yahan, lakin hai listed where applicable.

Such fluctuations may badalen a desh 's ranking isse ek saal to the aglaa, bhi haalanki ve praayah mek choti or no difference to the standard of living of its population.
isliye ye aankade chahie be used with caution.

ye countries/regions could appear in is suchi as having a small GDP.

lapping is a machining prakram, in jisase do satahon hai mala together with an abrasive between them, by hand movement or by way of a machine.
This can lo do form.
The first type of lapping ( traditionally pukaara pis ), typically involves ragad a bhangur saamagree aise as kaanch viruddh a sataha aise as aayran or kaanch itself ( bhi gyaat as the `` god '' or pis aujaar ) saath an akkhad aise as aluminium oxide, johariyon 's rouge, optician 's rouge, emery, silicon carbide, diamond, etc., in between them.
is produces microscopic conchoidal fractures as the akkhad rolls parichay between the two surfaces and removes material from both.
The other form of lapping involves a softer saamagree aise as pich or a ceremic liye the god, jisase is `` charge '' saath the akkhad.
The lap is then prayukt to kaaten a harder material—the workpiece.
The abrasive embeds within the softer saamagree jisase holds it or permits it to score aarpaar or kaaten the harder material.
Taken to a finer limit, this will produce a polished sataha aise as saath a policing cloth on an automobile, or a polishing cloth or polishing pitch upon glass or steel.
Taken to the ultimate limit, with the aid of accurate interferometry or specialized policing mashine or skilled haath policing, lensmakers can upaj satahon ki hai flat to better than 30 nanometers.
is is ek beesvin of the wavelength of lite isse the commonly used 632.8 nm helium neon laser light source.
Surfaces this flat can be molecularly bandhua ( optically contacted ) by bringing unhen saath under the right conditions.
( This is not the same as the wringing effect of johansan block, haalanki it is samaan ).

A pickup trek or pick-up, praayah bas referred to as a pikup, is a lite motor gadee saath an open-top, rear cargo area ( bed ).
In North America, the pad pikup is prayukt liye lite trek saath a halkaa duty chassis or factory nirmit, ekikrut bed, as khub as liye coupé utility vaahanon, praayah based on a personal car chassis, but also often on a special dedicated chassi for such use.

Large pickup trucks are somewhat rare in Europe, jahaan vine or lite lorries hai commonly prayukt liye samaan roles.
The President of the United States of america ( potus ) is the sir of rajya or sir of sarkari of the sanyukt States.
The president leads the karypalika shakha of the sangheey sarkari or is the commander-in-chief of the United States Armed Forces.
Article II of the U.S. Constitution vests the executive power of the United States in the adhyaksh or aarope use saath the nishpaadan of sangheey vidhi, alongside the jimmedaari of appointing sangheey karypalika, rajanyik, niamak, or nyaayik officers, and concluding treaties with foreign powers, with the advice and consent of the Senate.
The president is further empowered to grant federal pardons and reprieves, and to convene or adjourn either or dono gharon of congress antargat asaadhaaran halaaton.
Since the founding of the United States, the shakti of the adhyaksh or the sangheey sarkari have grown substantially or prayek aadhunik adhyaksh, despite possessing no aupchaarik vidhaan shaktiyaan pare hastakshar or vetoing congressionally passed bills, is largely jimmedaar liye dictating the legislative agenda of his party and the foreign and domestic policy of the United States.
The president is frequently varnit as the sabase shaktishaalee vyakti in the world.
the adhyaksh is indirectly nirvaachit by the logon through the chunavi college to a four-year pad, or is ek of tabhi do nationally nirvaachit sangheey adhikariyon, the other being the Vice President of the United States.
The twenty-second amendment, apanaaya in 1951, prohibits anyone isse kabhi hone elected to the presidency for a third full term.
It also prohibits a person from hone nirvaachit to the presidency adhik than ekbar if ki vyakti previously tha parosa as adhyaksh, or acting president, for more than two years of another person 's term as president.
In all, 43 individuals have parosa 55 four-year terms.
on janvari 20, 2009, baraak obama became the 44th and current president.
On November 6, 2012, he thi re-elected or is anusuchit to serve until January 20, 2017.

Map of the major rivers, jhiilon, or tank in india
Map showing nadiyaan or baadh prone kshetron in india
Rivers of India play an mahatvapurn bhoomika in the jeevandaan of the Indian people.
the nadi pranaaliyon provide sinchai, potable jal, sasti parivahan, vidyut, or the livelihoods liye a vishaal number of people all over the country and to rural areas.
This easily explains kyon nearly sab the pramukh shaharon of india are located by the banks of rivers.
The nadiyaan bhi have an mahatvapurn bhoomika in hindu mythology or are considered holy by all Hindus in the country.
Seven major rivers along with their numerous tributaries mek up the nadi pranali of india.
Most of the rivers pour their waters into the Bay of Bengal ; however, some of the rivers whose courses take them through the western part of the desh or towards the east of the rajya of himachal pradesh khaali into the arabian samudr.
Parts of Ladakh, northern parts of the aravlli dayera or the arid bhaag of the thar marusthal have inland drainage.
Dr.Francis bukanan surveyed the paathyakram of the nadiyaan of india saath saath unke tributaries and branches in 1810-11 AD and presented a minute account of it.
the shifting of the paathyakram or bed over the sadiyaan is very remarkable.
anek of the channels ullekith in ki surveykshan have abhi become dead, dried or even extinct.
All pramukh nadiyaan of india originate isse one of the three main watersheds :
the himalay or the Karakoram ranges
vindhyas or satpura seemayen or chotanagpur plateau in central India
Sahyadri or pashchimi ghats in pashchimi india
The Bretton Woods system of monetary management established the rules for commercial and vittiya sambandh among the sansar 's pramukh audyogic rajya in the mid-20th century.
The Bretton Woods system was the first example of a fully negotiated maudrik anukram intended to govern maudrik sambandh among swatantra nation-states.
Preparing to rebuild the international economic system as World War II thi still raging, 730 delegates isse sab 44 alide raashtra gathered at the mount washington hotel in bretton woods, nai hampshire, United States, for the United Nations Monetary and Financial Conference.
The delegates deliberated dauraan 1–22 july 1944, or hastakshrit the anubandh on iske final day.
Setting up a system of rules, institutions, and prakriyaaon to viniyamit the antarrashtriya maudrik pranali, the planners at bretton woods sthapit the antarrashtriya maudrik nidhi ( imf ) or the antarrashtriya Bank for Reconstruction and Development ( IBRD ), which today is part of the World Bank Group.
These organizations became operational in 1945 baad a sufficient kramank of deshon tha ratified the agreement.
The chief features of the Bretton Woods pranali yahood an daayitv liye prayek desh to apnaanaa a maudrik niti ki kaayam the exange rate by tying iske karency to the U.S. dollar and the ability of the IMF to bridge temporary imbalances of payments.
On 15 August 1971, the United States unilaterally terminated convertibility of the US $ to gold.
This brought the Bretton Woods pranali to an samaapt or dekhi the dollars become fiat currency.
This action, referred to as the Nixon shock, nirmit the halaat in jisase the sanyukt rajya dollars became a reserve currency used by many states.
At the same time, anek phixd mudraayen ( aise as gbp, liye udhaaharan ), bhi became free floating.

A credit score is a numerical abhivyakti aadhaarit on a sankhyikeey vishleshan of a vyakti 's credit filein, to represent the creditworthiness of that person.
A credit score is primarily aadhaarit on credit rapat soochna typically sourced isse credit bureaus.
Lenders, such as banks and credit card companiyaan, upyog credit score to evaluate the sambhavit risk posed by lending dhan to upabhokta or to mitigate losses due to bad debt.
Lenders use credit scores to determine who qualifies liye a rin, at kayaa byaaj rate, or kayaa credit limits.
lenders bhi upyog credit score to determine jisase graahak hai sambhavit to bring in the most revenue.
The use of credit or identity scoring prior to authorizing abhigam or granting credit is an kriyanvayan of a vishwasaneey system.
Credit scoring is nahin simit to bainko.
Other sanghathan, aise as mobile phone companiyaan, bime companiyaan, jameendaar, or sarkari vibhaag employ the same techniques.
Credit scoring also has a lot of overlap saath aankada khanan, jisase upyog anek similar techniques.
These techniques combine hazaron of karkon lakin ve hai adhik or kam samaan or the vahi.
The seven SI base units and the interdependency of unke paribhaashaayen : liye udhaaharan, to nikaalen the paribhaasha of the meter isse the gati of lite, the paribhaasha of the second must be known while the ampere and candela are both dependent on the definition of energy which in turn is defined in terms of length, mass and time.
The International System of ikai ( si ) defines saat ikai of maap as a moulik niyat isse jisase sab other SI units are derived.
These si aadhaar ikai or unke shaareerik quantities are:
meter liye lambaai ( us angrezi : meter )
kilogram liye dravyaman ( note : nahin the gram )
duusari liye time
ampere liye electric vartmaan
kelvin liye taapmaana
candela for chamakdaar tivrata
mole liye the raashi of padaarth.
The SI base quantities form a set of mutually swatantra aayam as jaruri by aiami vishleshan commonly employed in vigyaan and technology.
however, in a die realization of ye ikai ve may khub be interdependent, i.e. defined in terms of each other.
The names of SI units hai likhaa in loarkes varna ( the 'degree celsius ' meets is niyam, as 'degree ' is the unit, and 'Celsius ' is a modifier ).
The symbols of units are written in lowercase ( e.g. metre has the symbol m ), magar ki pratikon liye ikai namit baad vyaktiyon hai likhaa saath an aarambhik capital letter ( e.g., the hertz has the uppercase symbol Hz ).
Many other units, such as the litre ( us angrezi : leniyar ), hai formally nahin bhaag of the si, lakin are accepted for use with SI.
smarak canyon
Colorado neshnal smarak ( locally referred to as the smarak ) is a bhaag of the National Park Service near the city of Grand Junction, Colorado.
Spectacular canyons kaaten gahan into sandstone or bhi granite–gneiss–schist rock formations, in some areas.
This is an kshetrafal of marusthal jameen unchi on the colorado pathaar, saath pinian and juniper forests on the plateau.
The park hosts a wide range of vanyajeev, sahit red-tailed chilon or sunahari eagles, ravens, jays, marusthal bighorn sheep, or coyotes.
Activities include hiking, horseback riding, road bicycling, and darshneey drive ; a aagatuk bich on the west paksh contains a prakritik itihaas sangrahalay or gift shop.
There are magnificent views from trails or the rim chattan drive, jisase hawaayen saath the plateau.
aasapaas hai the kitaab cliffs, or the largest flat-topped mountain in the world, the Grand Mesa.
Its feature attraction is Monument Canyon, which runs the width of the park, and shaamil chattan formations aise as swatantraaa smarak, the chumban yugal, or coke Ovens.
The monument shaamil 20,500 acre ( 32 vargakar mile ), much of jisase rai maharoom recommended to Congress for designation as wilderness.

The September 11 attacks ( also referred to as September 11, September 11th, or 9/11 ) were a shrenee of chaar samanvit aatankwaadi hamale shubharambh by the islamic aatankwaadi samooh al-qaeda upon the sanyukt rajya in nai york nagar or the washington, D.C. area on September 11, 2001.
Four passenger airliners yahood hijacked by 19 al-qaeda aatankwaadi so ve could be flown into imaaraten in suicide attacks.
Two of those planes, amareeki airlines udaan 11 or sanyukt airlines udaan 175, yahood krash into the uttar or dakshin minaaren, kramshah, of the sansar vyapaar Center complex in New York City.
Within two hours, both towers collapsed with debris and the resulting fires causing aanshik or puraa patan of sab anya imaaraten in the wtc jatil, as khub as pramukh kshati to ten anya vishaal surrounding structures.
A third plane, American airlines udaan 77, thi krash into the prastutikaran ( the mukhyalay of the sanyukt rajya Department of Defense ), leading to a partial collapse in its western side.
The fourth plane, United Airlines Flight 93, was targeted at the United States capital in washington, d.C., lakin krash into a field nikat shanksville, pencilvenia, baad iske yatri tried to overcome the hijackers.
In total, almost 3,000 logon died in the hamale, sahit the 227 nagarikon or 19 hijackers aboard the four planes.
suspicion jaldi giri on al-qaeda.
Although the group 's leader, Osama bin laden, initially asweekrut koi bhagidaari, in 2004 he claimed jimmedaari for the attacks.
Al-Qaeda and bin Laden cited U.S. support of Israel, the presence of u.S. sainikon in saudi arab, or pratibandhon viruddh iraqi as motives for the attacks.
The United States responded to the attacks by launching the yuddh on aatank or akramanakari afghanistan to depose the taliban, jisase tha harbored al-Qaeda.
Many deshon strengthened unke anti-terrorism vidhaan or expanded law enforcement powers.
Having evaded capchar liye saalo, bin laden thi stith and killed by U.S. forces in May 2011.
The destruction of the judwa minaaren or anya gun caused gambhir kshati to the arthvyavastha of nimnatar manahaton and had a significant effect on global markets.
Cleanup of the sansar vyapaar bich sait thi samaapt in may 2002, or the Pentagon was repaired within a year.
Numerous memorials have been constructed, including the National sitambar 11 memorial & sangrahalay in nai york, the prastutikaran memorial, or the udaan 93 neshnal Memorial in Pennsylvania.
After a lengthy delay, the One World vyapaar bich is apekshit to be samaapt at maidan shunya in New York City in 2013.
Finding Nemo is a 2003 amareeki computer-animated comedy-drama adventure filmi likhaa or nirdeshit by andrew stanton, released by walt dijani tasviren, or the fifth film produced by Pixar Animation Studios.
It tells the story of the over-protective clownfish named Marlin ( Albert Brooks ) who, saath saath a rajasi tang namit dory ( ellen degeneres ), khoj liye uske abducted bete nemo ( sikandar gould ) sab the rasta to sidney harbour.

A sequel, dhundhna dory, is philhal in vikaas, niyat to be released on November 25, 2015.
The film received universal critical acclaim and won the Academy Award for Best Animated visheshta, or thi manonith in teen adhik shrenee including Best Original Screenplay.
It was the second highest-grossing film of 2003, kamai a kul of $ 921 lakh vishwavyaapee.

In the sanyukt rajya, soshal suraksha refers to the old-age, survivors, or viklaangata Insurance ( OASDI ) federal program.
The original Social Security Act ( 1935 ) and the vartmaan sanskaran of the adhinium, as amended, encompass anek soshal welfare or soshal insurance programs.
Social suraksha is primarily vittposhit through samarpit payroll kar pukaara sangheey Insurance Contributions Act tax ( FICA ).
Tax deposits are formally entrusted to the Federal Old-Age and Survivors Insurance Trust Fund, the Federal viklaangata bime vishwaas nidhi, the sangheey hospital bime vishwaas nidhi, or the sangheey anupoorak chikitsa bime vishwaas Fund which comprise the Social Security Trust Fund.
upward redistribution of aay is jimmedaar liye parichay 43 % of the projected Social Security shortfall over the next 75 years.
According to economist Martin feldstein, the sanyukt bitaa liye sab soshal bime kaarykram in 2003 constituted 37 % of government expenditure and 7 % of the gross domestic product.
Social Security is currently estimated to keep roughly 40 pratishat of sab america aayu 65 or puraani out of garibi.
The Social suraksha prashasan is headquartered in woodlawn, maryland, just west of Baltimore.

charles jon huffam dicans ( ; 7 farvari 1812 – 9 june 1870 ) was an English writer and social critic.
He created some of the world 's most yaadgaar fictional varna or is generally regarded as the mahanatam upanyaaskaar of the victorian period.
During his life, his works enjoyed unprecedented fame, and by the beesvin sadi uske saahitiyik pratibhashali thi broadly acknowledged by aalochakon and scholars.
uske novels or choti kahaniyaan continue to be widely popular.
Born in Portsmouth, england, dicans baayein skool to kaary in a factory baad his father was thrown into debtors ' prison.
Although he had little formal shiksha, uske jaldi impoverishment drove use to safal.
Over his career he edited a weekly journal for 20 saalo, likhaa 15 novels, 5 novellas or sainkadon of choti kahaniyaan or non-fiction aalekh, lectured or performed extensively, was an indefatigable letter writer, and campaigned vigorously for children 's rights, education, and other social reforms.
Dickens sprang to kirti saath the 1836 serial prakaashan of the pickwick Papers.
Within a few saalo he tha become an antarrashtriya saahitiyik hasti, prasiddh liye his humour, satire, and keen observation of character and society.
His novels, most published in monthly or weekly kishton, pioneered the serial prakaashan of katha fiction, jisase became the prabal victorian mode for novel publication.
The instalment format allowed Dickens to evaluate uske darshak 's pratikriya, or he praayah parivardhit uske plat or akshar vikaas based on such feedback.
For example, when his bivi 's chiropodist expressed takalif at the rasta miss mowcher in daud copperfield laga to reflect her disabilities, Dickens went on to improve the character with positive lineaments.
Fagin in Oliver Twist jaahir mirrors the prasiddh baad ikey suleman ; uske kairikechar of leigh hunt in the figure of mr skimpole in Bleak House was likewise toned down on advice from some of his friends, as they read episodes.
In the same novel, both Lawrence Boythorne and Mooney the beadle hai drawn isse real jivan – boythorne isse walter junglee landor or mooni isse 'looney ', a beadle at Salisbury Square.
His plots yahood carefully constructed, or dicans praayah wove in tatv isse topical kaarykram into his narratives.
Masses of the illiterate poor chipped in ha'pennies to have prayek nai masik apisod padhaa to unhen, kholane up or preranadai a new class of readers.
Dickens was regarded as the saahitiyik colossus of uske aayu.
His 1843 novella, A christmas carol, is ek of the sabase influential works kabhi likhaa, or it remains lokapriy or continues to inspire adaptations in every artistic genre.
uske rachanaatmak pratibhashali rai maharoom praised by fellow writers—from leo talsty to G. K. chesterton or george orvel —for its realism, comedy, prose style, unique characterisations, and social criticism.
On the other hand Oscar Wilde, henry james or virginia woolf complained of a kami of manovaigyanik gaharaai, dhilaa writing, and a vein of saccharine sentimentalism.
martin luther king or anya civil adhikaron netao in saamne of the statue of Abraham Lincoln, August 28, 1963
The civil adhikaron gati thi a shrenee of vishwavyaapee rajnatik andolanon liye samta pehle the law that peaked in the 1960s.
In many situations it took the form of abhiyaan of civil pratirodh aimed at achieving badalen by nonviolent forms of resistance.
In some paristhitiyon it thi accompanied, or followed, by civil ashaanti and armed rebellion.
The process was long and tenuous in many countries, and many of these andolanon kiya nahin fully achieve unke lakshya haalanki, the praytn of ye andolanon kiya sise to sudhaar in the vidhik adhikaron of previously dalit groups of people.
The main aim of the civil rights movement included, and include, ensuring that the adhikaron of sab logon hai baraabar surakshit by the vidhi, sahit the adhikaron of alpsankhyakon.
Civil rights movements ranging isse the vaishvik lgbt adhikaron gati to the vaishvik mahilaon 's adhikaron gati to various racial minority rights movements around the world continue.
The 2010 FIFA World Cup was the 19th FIFA World Cup, the sansar championships liye main 's neshnal sangh footbaal tiimon.
It took place in dakshin africa isse 11 June to 11 July 2010.

In the first round of the tournament final, the tiimon competed in round-robin samooh of chaar tiimon liye ank, with the top two teams in each group proceeding.
These sixteen teams advanced to the knockout stage, jahaan teen rounds of khel decided jisase tiimon hota participate in the final.
In the final, Spain, the European champions, parajeet third-time finalists the netherlands 1–0 baad atirikt samay, saath andres iniesta 's lakshya in the 116th minute giving spain unke pehla sansar sheershak, banane the aathvin nation to win the tournament, and the first European nation to win the tournament outside its home continent.
Host nation South africa, 2006 sansar champions italy or 2006 runners-up frans yahood sab eliminated in the first round of the tournament.

New Zealand with their teen draws yahood the tabhi aparajit toli in the toornament, but were also eliminated in the first round.

The United States presidential election of 1968 was the 46th quadrennial adhyakshiya chunaav, yojit on Tuesday, November 5, 1968.
The Republican nominee, purv vice-president richard nicksan, jiti the chunaav over the loktantric nominee, laazim Vice-President Hubert Humphrey.
Nixon ran on a abhiyaan ki promised to restore vidhi or anukram to the swadesh 's shaharon, fata by riots and crime.
Analysts have argued the election of 1968 is a realigning chunaav as it permanently disrupted the nai saude gathbandhan ki tha varchasv presidential politics for 36 years.
Coming four years after democrate lyndon B. johnson jiti in a aitihaasik bhuskhalan, the chunaav dekhi the laazim adhyaksh majaboor out of the res or a Republican elected for the first time in twelve years.
It was a wrenching national experience, conducted during a year of violence that shaamil the hatya of civil adhikaron netaa martin luther king, jr., or subsequent res dange aarpaar the swadesh, the assasination of loktantric adhyakshiya pratyaashee robert F. kennedy, faili vipaksh to the vietnam yuddh aarpaar university campuses, and violent confrontations between police and anti-war protesters at the 1968 Democratic National Convention as the Democratic party split again and again.
The election featured the strongest teesraa party praytn chunki 1912 by purv albama rajyapal george Wallace, a Democrat.
Because Wallace 's campaign opposed sangheey hastkshep in the dakshin to samaapt skool pruthakkaran, he carried the Deep South and ran well in ethnic industrial districts in the North.
This was the last election in which nai york tha the sabase mat in the chunavi college ( 43 votes ).
After the 1970 census, california gained the sabase chunavi mat or rai remained the sabase populous rajya since then.
This is the latest election where a adhyakshiya tikat jiti bagaiyr carrying the vaais adhyakshiya pratyaashee 's ghar state.

Kurt Donald Cobain ( February 20, 1967 – april 5, 1994 ) thi an amareeki sangeetkaar or kalakaar, behtareen gyaat as the lead singer, guitarist and primary songwriter of the grunge band Nirvana.
Cobain formed Nirvana with Krist Novoselic in Aberdeen, washington in 1985 or sthapit it as bhaag of the sietal music jhaanki, having iske debyue album bleech released on the independent record label Sub Pop in 1989.
After signing with major label dgc record, the band mila bhedan kamyaabi saath `` Smells Like Teen Spirit `` from its second album Nevermind ( 1991 ).
Following the success of nevermind, nirvana thi labeled `` the flagship band '' of peedhee X, and Cobain hailed as `` the spokesman of a generation ''.
Cobain, however, was often uncomfortable and frustrated, believing his message or kalakaari drushti to have maharoom misinterpreted by the public, saath uske nijee mudde praayah vishay to media dhyaan.
He challenged Nirvana 's darshak saath iske final studio album in Utero ( 1993 ).
During the last years of his life, Cobain struggled saath heroin vyasan, beemaari and depression.
He also had difficulty coping with his fame and public image, or the peshewar or lifelong nijee pressures surrounding khud or uske bivi, sangeetkaar courtney Love.
On April 8, 1994, cobain thi mila murde at uske ghar in sietal, the shikaar of kayaa thi officially ruled a suicide by a self-inflicted shotgun wound to the head.
The circumstances of his maut at aayu 27 have become a topic of public fascination or bahes.
Since unke debyue, nirvana, saath cobain as a songwriter, rai bechi over 25 million albums in the U.S., and over 50 million worldwide.
A millwright is a craftsman or tradesman sagaai saath the nirmaan or mentanence of machinery.
More generally in the English speaking world, early millwrights yahood visheshgy badhai jo erected mashine prayukt in krishi, khaanaa prasanskaran or processing lumber and paper.
In the early part of the audyogic kranti, unke kaushal yahood dabaaya into seva bhawan the earliest powered textile mills.
Modern millwrights work with steel or anya saamagree in jod to lakdi or jarur praayah combine the kaushal of anek skilled trade in anukram to safaltaapurvak fabricate audyogic mashinari or to assemble machines from pre-fabricated parts.
the aadhunik millwright jarur bhi be samarth to padhaa blueprints or anya schematics to aid him in the construction of complex systems.
Millwrights are frequently unionized, with around 45 % unionized in the us, haalanki anbhavi millwrights praayah niyat themselves up as independent contractors.

Double rainbow and supernumerary rainbows on the andar of the praathmik arc.
The shadow of the photographer 's head on the neeche marks the kendra of the renbo vrutt ( antisolar point ).
A rainbow is an optical and meteorological phenomenon that is caused by pratibimb of lite in jal droplets in the dharti 's maahaul, resulting in a varnakram of lite appearing in the aasmaan.
It takes the rup of a multicoloured arc.
Rainbows caused by dhoop sadaa appear in the khand of aasmaan directly opposite the sun.
In a `` primary rainbow '', the arc shows red on the bahari bhaag or bangnee on the inner side.
This rainbow is caused by lite hone refracted jabaki pravesh a droplet of jal, tab reflected andar on the waapas of the droplet and refracted again when leaving it.
In a double rainbow, a second arc is seen outside the primary arc, or rai the anukram of iske rang reversed, red facing toward the anya ek, in dono rainbows.
This second rainbow is caused by lite reflecting twice andar water droplets.
The Conservative Party, officially the roodhiwaadee or unionist party or colloquially referred to as the tory party or the tories, is a centre-right political party in the United Kingdom that espouses the philosophies of conservatism and British unionism.
it is the largest political party in the sanyukt kingdom, hone the largest single party in the house of comons saath 303 mps, the largest party in local sarkari saath 9,391 parshadon, or the largest British party in the European Parliament with 25 MEPs.
It governs in gathbandhan saath the udaar democrate, saath party netaa daud Cameron as Prime Minister.
The Conservative Party was founded in 1834, and was one of do prabal partiyon in the 19th sadi, saath saath the Liberal Party.
It changed its name to the roodhiwaadee or unionist party in 1912 baad vilay saath the udaar unionist party, haalanki ki naam is rarely prayukt or it is generally referred to as simply the Conservative Party.
In the 1920s, the udaar vote greatly diminished or the shramik party became the conservatives ' main rivals.
roodhiwaadee pradhan mantriyon led sarkarein liye 57 saalo of the 20th century, including Winston Churchill ( 1940–45, 1951–55 ) and Margaret Thatcher ( 1979–90 ).
Thatcher 's tenure led to wide-ranging aarthik udaarikaran or dekhi the conservatives become the most eurosceptic of the three major parties.
The party thi laute to sarkari in gathbandhan, having vifal to jeet a bahumat, in 2010 under the more `` liberal '' leadership of David Cameron.
In the European Parliament, the Conservatives are the largest British party with 25 MEPs, who sit with the soft eurosceptic europea conservatives or reformists ( ecr ) sansadeey samooh, jabaki the party itself is a sadsy of the gathbandhan of europea conservatives or Reformists ( AECR ) Europarty.
They are the third-largest party in the scottish parliament or second-largest in the Welsh Assembly.
They were formally allied to the Ulster Unionist Party ( UUP ) as bhaag of the ulster conservatives or unionists vyavastha, saath the uup philhal participating in the five-party uttari ireland Executive.

The Centers for Disease control or rokthaam ( sidisi ) is a sanyukt rajya sangheey agency antargat the vibhaag of swasthya or insaan sevaayen headquartered in druid pahadiyaan, unincorporated dekalb County, Georgia, in Greater Atlanta.
It works to protect public health and safety by providing information to enhance health nirnay, or it promotes swasthya through partnerships saath rajya swasthya vibhaag or other organizations.
The CDC focus national attention on developing and applying disease prevention and control ( especially infectious diseases and foodborne pathogens and other microbial infections ), paryaavarniya swasthya, occupational suraksha or swasthya, swasthya pramotion, injury prevention and education activities designed to improve the health of the people of the United States.
The CDC is the United States ' national public swasthya santhaan or is a founding sadsy of the International Association of National Public Health Institutes.
bukamp bhavishyavaanee `` is praayah paribhaashit as the specification of the samay, sthaan, or pariman of a bhavishya bukamp bheetar stated had '', or visheshkar of `` the next strong earthquake to occur in a region. ''
This can be distinguished from earthquake forecasting, jisase is the probabilistic moolyankan of saamaanya bukamp jokhim, sahit the aavriti or pariman of damaging bukamp, in a given area over periods of years or decades.
This can be further distinguished from real-time bukamp chetavanee pranaaliyon, jisase, upon ditection of a kathor bukamp, can provide neighboring regions a few seconds warning of potentially significant shaking.
To be useful, an earthquake prediction must be precise paryaapt to warrant the laagat of increased ehtiyaat, sahit disruption of ordinary activities and commerce, and timely enough that preparation can be made.
Predictions must also be reliable, as false alarms and cancelled sachetak hai nahin tabhi economically costly, lakin seriously undermine vishwaas in, or thereby the prabhavakaarita of, any kind of warning.
With over 7,000 bukamp around the sansar prayek saal saath a pariman of 4.0 or vrihad, naganya kamyaabi in bukamp bhavishyavaanee is easily praapt using sufficiently broad parameters of time, location, or magnitude.
However, such trivial `` kaamyaab purvanumaan '' are not useful.
Major bukamp hai praayah followed by reports ki ve yahood purvanumanit, or at tanik anticipated, lakin no arji of a kaamyaab prediction of a major earthquake has survived close inquiry.
In the 1970s there was intense optimism amongst vaigyanikon ki kuch vidhi of predicting bukamp might be mila, lakin by the 1990s continuing vifaltaa led many scientists to question whether it was even possible.
While many scientists still hold that, die paryaapt sansaadhan, bhavishyavaanee might be sambhavit, anek anya maintain that earthquake prediction is inherently impossible.

released farvari 17, 2012.

Stührling tourbillon gati ( ).
In horology, a tourbillon ( ; `` whirlwind '' ) is an jod to the yantriki of a dekhen escapement.
viksit around 1795 by the french-swiss ghadisaz abraham-louis breguet isse an pehle vichaar by the angrezi chronometer mekar jon arnald, a tourbillon aims to counter the effects of gravity by mounting the escapement and balance wheel in a rotating cage, to negate the effect of gravity when the timepiece ( thus the escapement ) is stuck in a certain position.
Originally an attempt to improve sateekta, tourbillons hai still shaamil in kuch mahangi aadhunik ghadiyaan as a novelty and demonstration of watchmaking virtuosity.
The mechanism is usually ujagar on the dekhen 's phase to dikhaaen it off.
The Windows Installer ( previously known as Microsoft installer ) is a tantra ghatak prayukt liye the sansthapana, mentanence, and removal of software on modern Microsoft Windows systems.
The installation information, and often the files themselves, are packaged in installation packages, loosely relational databases sanrachit as com sanrachit storages or commonly gyaat as `` msi filein '', isse unke default file extension.
khidkiyaan installer contains significant parivartan isse iske purvavarti, Setup API.
New features include a GUI framework or swachaalit peedhee of the uninstallation anukram.
Windows Installer is positioned as an vaikalpik to stand-alone executable installer frameworks aise as puraani sanskaran of installshield or nsis.
Microsoft encourages third parties to use khidkiyaan installer as the aadhaar liye sansthapana frameworks, so ki ve synchronize correctly saath anya installers or rakhana the aatanrik database of santhaapit products consistent.
Important suvidhaayen aise as rollback or versioning nirbhar on a satat aatanrik database for reliable operation.
furthermore, khidkiyaan installer facilitates the principle of tanik visheshadhikaar by performing tantra installations by proxy for unprivileged users.

The gardan of a guitar prardashit the nat ( in the prishthbhumi, coloured white ) and first four metal frets.
A fret is a raised tatv on the gardan of a stringed yantra.
Frets usually extend aarpaar the puraa chaudai of the gardan.
On sabase aadhunik pashchimi fretted yantra, frets are metal strips inserted into the fingerboard.
On some historical instruments and non-European yantra, frets hai bana of tukade of string tied around the neck.
Frets divide the neck into fixed khand at intervals sambandhit to a musical fremawork.
On instruments such as guitars, each fret represents ek semitone in the maanak pashchimi pranali jahaan ek ashtak is vibhajit into twelve semitones.
Fret is often prayukt as a kriya, arth bas `` to dabaayen bas the string behind a fret. ''
Fretting praayah refers to the frets and/or their system of placement.
There was khapat of daaru dono dauraan and after prohibition.
the 18th amendment nishiddh the utpaadan, vitaran or bikri of alcoholic peya in the sanyukt rajya and was widely supported by the American public when it went into effect in 1920.
The temperance movement had popularized the belief that daaru thi the pramukh kaaran of sabase nijee or soshal samasyaayein or nishedh thi dekhi as the samaadhaan to the nation 's poverty, crime, violence, and other ills.
Upon anusamarthan of the amendment, the prasiddh enjeelwaadi Billy Sunday said that `` The slums will soon be only a memory.
We will turn hamaari jelon into kaarkaanon or hamaari jails into storehouses or corncribs. ''
( Compare christianity or daaru. )
Since alcohol was to be banned and since it was dekhi as the kaaran of sabase, if nahin sab, aparaadhon, kuch samudaayon bechi unke jails.
The nation was highly optimistic and the leading prohibitionist in the United States congress confidently asserted ki `` vahin is as much mauka of repealing the eighteenth amendment as vahin is liye a humingbard to makkhi to the grah mangal saath the Washington Monument tied to its tail.”
The metre ( meter in American English ), ( SI unit symbol : m ; SI dimension symbol : L ), is the aadharbhoot ikai of lambaai in the antarrashtriya pranali of ikai ( SI ).
Originally intended to be one ten-millionth of the distance from the Earth 's equator to the uttar dhruv ( at samudr str ), iske paribhaasha rai maharoom periodically parishkrut to reflect growing knowledge of metrology.
Since 1983, it has been defined as `` the length of the path travelled by lite in vaikum dauraan a samay antaraal of 1/299,792,458 of a second. ''

A geologist is a scientist who studies the solid and liquid padaarth ki constitutes the dharti as khub as the prakriyaaon or itihaas ki rai taraasha it.
geologists praayah engage in adhyayan geology.
Geologists, studying more of an lagu vigyaan than a saidhantik ek, jarur drushtikon bhuvigyaan using bhautikee, rasayan or jeevigyaan as well as other sciences.
Geologists, compared to vaigyanikon sagaai in anya field, hai generally adhik ujagar to the bahari than rahakar in laboratories ; haalanki some geologists prefer to perform most of their studies in the lab.
Geologists are engaged in khoji liye khanan companiyaan in dhundhen of dhaatuon, oils, or anya dharti sansaadhan.
They hai bhi in the forefront of prakritik jokhimon or aapadaaon chetavanee or shaman, adhyayan bukamp, volcanic activity, tsunamis, weather storms, and the like ; their studies are used to warn the general public of the occurrence of these events.
philhal, geologists hai bhi sagaai in the charchaa of jalwaayu change, as they study the history and evidence for this Earth process.

Modern vaikum tubes, zyaadaatar miniature style
In electronics, a vaikum tub, electron tub ( in uttar america ), tapayanic valve, tub, or valve is a yantra controlling electric current through a vacuum in a sealed container.
The sangraahak is praayah patala paardarshee kaanch in a roughly cylindrical shape.
The simplest vaikum tub, the diod, is essentially an incandescent lite bulb with an added electrode inside.
When the bulb 's filament is heated white-hot, electrons hai `` boiled '' band iske sataha or into the vaikum andar the bulb.
If the electrode -- pukaara a `` thali '' or `` dhanagar '' -- is bana adhik dhanatmak than the hot philament, a sidhaa vartmaan bahati through the vacuum to the electrode ( a demonstration of the Edison effect ).
As the current only flows in one direction, it makes it sambhavit to badalen an prayavarti vartmaan lagu to the philament to direct current.
The introduction of a third electrode, a grid between the philament or the thali, yields another falan.
A voltage lagu to the grid niyantran the vartmaan bahati isse the filament to the plate.
Thus, it allows the yantra to be prayukt as an electronic pravardhak.
Vacuum tubes hai yun prayukt liye rectification, pravardhan, switching, or samaan prasanskaran or creation of electrical signals.
The vishaal bahumat of aadhunik din tubes consist of a sealed sangraahak saath a vaikum andar, and essentially rely on thermionic emission of electrons from a hot filament or a cathode heated by the filament.
Some exceptions to this are dealt with in the khand parichay gas-filled tubes below.
Vacuum tubes were critical to the development of electronic technology, which drove the vistaar or vyavsyeekaran of radio prasaaran, television, radar, dhwani reinforcement, dhwani recording or janan, vishaal telephone sanjaal, analog and digital computers, and industrial process control.
Although some applications had counterparts using pehle technologies aise as the chingaari gap transmeter or mechanical computer, it thi the invention of the vacuum tube with three electrodes ( called a triode ) and its capability of electronic amplification that made these technologies widespread and practical.
In most applications, solid-state divaais aise as transistors or anya semiconductor divaais have replaced tubes.
Solid-state devices pichhlaa longer or hai choti, adhik kushal, adhik vishwasaneey, and cheaper than tubes.
Tubes can be fragile, sometimes generate significant unwanted heat, and can take many seconds—many minutes in najuk applications—after powering on to garam to a taapmaana where they perform within operational tolerance.
However, tubes still find uses where solid-state devices have not been developed, are impractical, or jahaan a tub rai shreshth pradarshan, as saath kuch divaais in peshewar audio or high-power radio transmitaron.
tubes hai still utpaadit liye such applications.
Tubes are less likely than semiconductor devices to be destroyed by the electromagnetic pulse utpaadit by nabhikeey visphot or geomagnetic toofaan utpaadit by daanav saura flares.
Skittles is a brand of fruit-flavoured mithai, philhal utpaadit or marketed by the Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company, a division of Mars, Inc.
They have hard sugar shell jisase carry the akshar s.
The inside is mainly sugar, corn syrup, and hydrogenated tad karnel aayal saath saath fal ras, citric acid, or prakritik or artificial flavours.
The confectionery rai maharoom bechi in a kismein of flavor sangrahan, such as Tropical and Wild Berry.
Sir Winston Leonard Spencer-Churchill, ( 30 November 1874 – 24 janvari 1965 ) thi a angrejon rajaneta jo thi the pradhan mantri of the sanyukt kingdom isse 1940 to 1945 or again from 1951 to 1955.
Widely regarded as ek of the mahanatam wartime netao of the 20th sadi, churchill thi bhi an officer in the British Army, a historian, a writer, and an artist.
He is the only British Prime Minister in itihaas to have praapt the nobel puraskaar in sahitya, or thi bhi the pehla vyakti to be bana an Honorary Citizen of the United States.
Churchill was born into an vaibhavshaalee parivaar as the pota of the 7th duk of marlborough.
His father, Lord randolph churchill, thi a charismatic rajaneta jo parosa as chancelar of the Exchequer ; his mother, Jennie Jerome, was an American socialite.
As a young army adhikari, he dekhi karrwai in angrejon india, the sudan, or the Second Boer War.
he gained kirti as a yuddh correspondent or likhaa books about his campaigns.
At the forefront of raajnneeti liye pachaas saalo, he yojit anek political and cabinet positions.
Before the First World War, he served as President of the Board of Trade, Home sachiv, or pehla rab of the admiralty as bhaag of the asquith udaar sarkari.
During the war, he continued as First Lord of the admiralty jabatak the vinaashkari gallipoli abhiyaan caused uske prasthaan isse sarkari.
He then briefly resumed kriyasheel fouj seva on the pashchimi saamne as commander of the 6th batalian of the Royal Scots Fusiliers.
He returned to government as Minister of munitions, sachiv of rajya liye yuddh, or sachiv of rajya liye air.
After the yuddh, churchill parosa as chancelar of the exchequer in the roodhiwaadee ( baldwin ) sarkari of 1924–29, controversially returning the pound sterling in 1925 to the gold standard at its pre-war parity, a move widely seen as creating deflationary pressure on the UK economy.
Also controversial was his vipaksh to increased ghar niyam liye india or uske pratirodh to the 1936 abdication of Edward VIII.
Out of office and nitiyaan `` in the wilderness '' dauraan the 1930s, churchill took the sise in chetavanee about Nazi Germany and in campaigning for rearmament.
On the outbreak of the duusari sansar yuddh, he was again appointed First Lord of the Admiralty.
Following the resignation of Neville chemberlen on 10 may 1940, churchill became pradhan Minister.
His steadfast refusal to consider defeat, surrender, or a compromise peace helped inspire angrejon pratirodh, visheshkar dauraan the mushkil jaldi dinon of the yuddh jab britain stood alon among European countries in its active opposition to Adolf Hitler.
Churchill was particularly noted for his speeches and radio prasaaran, jisase helped inspire the British people.
He led britain as pradhan mantri jabatak vijay over Nazi Germany had been secured.
After the roodhiwaadee party khoyaa the 1945 chunaav, he became netaa of the vipaksh to the Labour ( Attlee ) government.
After jeetna the 1951 chunaav, he again became pradhan Minister, before retiring in 1955.
Upon his death, Elizabeth II granted him the izzat of a rajya antyeshti, jisase dekhi ek of the largest sabhaaon of sansar kootneetigyon in history.
Named the Greatest Briton of all time in a 2002 poll, Churchill is widely regarded as hone among the sabase influential logon in angrejon history.
