An agar thali -- an udhaaharan of a bacterial growth medium.
Specifically, it is a streak thali ; the naarangi linon or dots hai formed by bacterial colonies.
A growth medium or culture medium is a drav or gel designed to support the vikaas of microorganisms or cells, or small plants like the moss Physcomitrella patens.
There are alag prakaar of media liye growing alag types of cells.
There are two major types of growth media : those used for cell culture, which use vishisht koshika prakaar niklaa isse paudhe or pashu, or microbiological samskruti, jisase hai prayukt liye growing microorganisms, aise as bacteria or yeast.
The sabase aam vikaas media liye microorganisms hai nutrient broths or agar platon ; specialized media hai sometimes required for microorganism and cell culture growth.
Some jeevon, termed sukumaar jeevon, aavashyaktaa specialized environments due to complex nutritional requirements.
Viruses, for example, are obligate intracellular parasites and aavashyaktaa a vikaas medium containing jeena koshikaayen.
A talent agent, or booking agent, is a person who finds jobs for actors, authors, film directors, sangeetkaaron, model, nirmaataa, peshewar athlete, lekhak or anya logon in vibhinn entertainment businesses.
An agent bhi defends, supports or promotes the interest of his/her clients.
Agents can not produce unke apana shows due to conflict of interest.
a hunar agent jarur be familiar with their clients.
An agent has to know kayaa dayaalu of kaary the claayent can or can nahin do in anukram to match them with various jobs.
Having an agent is not jaruri, lakin karata sahaayta the kalakaar in getting jobs.
In many cases casting directors, or anya vyavsaayon, go to hunar agenciyon to dhundhen kalakaaron ve hai looking liye.
The agent is paid a percentage of the star 's aay ( typically 10 % ).
Agents sometimes hoga be referred to as `` 10 percenters. ''
There are different regulations ki govern alag prakaar of agenton ki hai sthapit by kalakaar 's sangh or the vidhik jurisdiction in which the agent operates.
vahin hai bhi peshewar sanghathan that license talent agencies.
Since the decline in viewership in theaters, from the 1950s to 1960s, this caused a smaarkeey shift in kaisaa studios hota upaj films or yun reducing the laagat of vishesh or mahangi actors.
Actors and actresses were working for the studios lakin yahood nahin swaamitv by ek pramukh studio antity or so yahood samarth to kaary on within their time and with other studios.
kuki of is, agenton yahood abhi dekhi as a necessity instead of an option.
Agents now became third partiyon ki negotiated between studios or client, is bananaa unke sevaayen imperative between each party.
Since talent agencies are working with lucrative contracts, all talent agencies must be licensed under special sections of the california majdoor code, jisase kals an agent a `` vyakti or nigam jo engages in the occupation of procuring, offering, promising, or attempting to procure employment for artist or artists. ''
Mars has two known moons, Phobos and deimos, jisase hai vichaar to be captured kshudragrah.
Both satellites were discovered in 1877 by Asaph Hall and are named after the varna phobos ( panic/fear ) or deimos ( terror/dread ) jo, in unani mythology, accompanied their father Ares, god of war, into battle.
aries thi gyaat as mangal to the Romans.

In law enforcement parlance, the term hatya kitaab refers to the maamla sanchika of a hatya chaanbin.
Typically, murder books include crime jhaanki chayachitr or sketches, postmortem or forensic reports, transcripts of jaanchakartaaon ' tip and witness interviews.
The murder book encapsulates the puraa paper trail of a hatya chaanbin, isse the samay the hatya is first reported through the arrest of a suspect.
Law enforcement agencies typically guard murder books carefully, or it is asaamaanya liye nagarikon to be die azaad abhigam to ye kinds of records, especially for unsolved cases.

A KSA, or Knowledge, kaushal, or abilities, is a shrenee of katha kathan ki hai jaruri jab applying to United States Federal government job openings.
KSAs are used to determine, along with resumes, jo the behtareen aavedakon hai jab anek ummidavaar qualify liye a job.
The gyaan, kaushal or abilities ( ksas ) jaruri liye the kaamyaab performance of a position are contained on each job vacancy announcement.
In 2009 the Office of nijee prabandhan poocha sangheey agenciyon to roke requiring job aavedakon to bharan out the questionnaires, to be phased out within a year.
KSAs are brief and focused essays about one 's career and shaikshanik prishthbhumi ki presumably qualify ek to perform the duties of the position being applied for.
A knowledge, skills, and abilities ( KSA ) is a concise essay about one 's hunar or visheshgyata or sambandhit anubhavon ( kaary, shiksha, volunteer ) and accomplishments.
A series of KSA kathan hai praayah jaruri jab applying liye sabase sangheey sarkari or kuch rajya or nagar sarkari kaary.
KSAs are used as a gaj to assess the samarthy of a prospective aavedak in sharten of sambhavit kshamta to perform the duties of the job.
Most government hiring officials look for a short, kurkure or saaf ksa ki emphasizes parinaam or accomplishments praapt in previous work.
ksa kathan hai bhi gyaat as moolyankan Factors.
Other agencies sometimes call them `` Rating Factors '', `` Quality ranking karkon '', `` gyaan, abilities, kaushal or anya visheshtaayen '', or `` job tatv ''.
The naam can be bas a naam lakin praayah it prabhaav content and length of the essay.
Every agency has its own regulations lakin sabase of the samay the prayek ksa factor chahie be 1/2 to 11⁄2 pages long.
The below definitions are defined by the u.S. daftar of karmiyon Management :
Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities ( KSAs ) - the gun jaruri to perform a job or hai generally demonstrated through qualifying service, education, or training.
Knowledge - Is a body of soochna lagu sidhe to the pradarshan of a falan.
Skill - Is an observable competence to perform a siikhe psychomotor act.
Ability - Is competence to perform an observable bartaav or a bartaav ki parinaam in an observable product.
The scoring of ksa essays is aadhaarit on a scale of from one to 100.
Job applicants must score upar 70 to be mana liye the sthiti.
High scores are derived through answering the KSA question as specifically as possible, providing udhaaharan isse pichhlaa niyukti or prashikshan ki clearly demonstrate tum milen the yogyata.
When applying to federal government positions, a Federal punararambh is praayah jaruri in jod to ksa kathan.

Love Always is the debyue album of amareeki r & b duo k-ci & JoJo, released on June 17, 1997, by MCA Records.

The duo were originally a bhaag of jodeci pehle is album.

A variable-rate mortgage, adjustable-rate mortgage ( ARM ), or tracker mortgage is a mortgage loan with the interest rate on the note periodically samyojit aadhaarit on an anukramanika jisase reflects the laagat to the lender of udhaar on the credit markets.
The loan may be offered at the lender 's maanak parivartaneey rate/ base rate.
There may be a direct and legally-defined link to the underlying index, but jahaan the lender offers no vishisht kadi to the underlying market or anukramanika the rate can be badla at the lender 's discretion.
The term `` variable-rate mortgage '' is most common outside the United States, whilst in the United States, `` adjustable-rate bandhak '' is sabase aam, or implies a bandhak regulated by the sangheey sarkari, saath caps on charges.
In anek deshon, samyojya rate mortgages hai the norm, and in such places, may simply be referred to as mortgages.
among the sabase aam indices hai the daron on 1-year constant-maturity rajkosh ( CMT ) securities, the Cost of Funds Index ( COFI ), and the London Interbank Offered Rate ( LIBOR ).
A few lenders upyog unke apana laagat of nidhi as an anukramanika, rather than using other indices.
This is done to ensure a sthir hashia liye the lender, jinaki apana laagat of funding hoga praayah be related to the index.
Consequently, payments made by the borrower may badalen over samay saath the badalanaa byaaj rate ( alternatively, the pad of the loan may change ).
This is distinct from the graduate bhugtan bandhak, jisase offers badalanaa bhugtan amounts but a fixed interest rate.
Other forms of mortgage loan include the interest only bandhak, the phixd rate bandhak, the rinatmak amortization bandhak, or the balloon payment mortgage.
Adjustable rates transfer part of the byaaj rate risk isse the lender to the borrower.
They can be used where manamaujee byaaj daron mek phixd rate loans difficult to obtain.
The borrower laabh if the byaaj rate jalprapaat lakin loses if the byaaj rate increases.
The borrower benefits from reduced margins to the underlying laagat of udhaar compared to phixd or capped rate mortgages.
The assassination of Robert Francis `` Bobby '' Kennedy, a United States Senator and brother of assassinated President John fitzgerald `` joker '' kennedy, took place shortly baad madhyaraatri on june 5, 1968, in los angeles, california, dauraan the abhiyaan ritu liye the sanyukt States Presidential election, 1968.
After winning the California and dakshin dakota praathmik chunaavon liye the loktantric namakan liye adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya, kennedy thi shot as he walked through the rasoighar of the doot Hotel and died in the Good Samaritan Hospital twenty-six hours later.
Sirhan sirhan, a 24-year-old philistini / jordan apravasi, thi convicted of Kennedy 's murder and is serving a life sentence for the crime.
Sirhan 's lawyers have released statements claiming pramaan ki he thi framed.
The shooting was ankit on audio tepe by a freelance samachaarpatr reporter, or the aftermath was captured on film.
Kennedy 's deh lay in repose at st. patric 's girjaghar in nai york liye do dinon pehle a funeral mass was held on June 8.
His body thi interred nikat uske bhai jon at arlington neshnal Cemetery.
His maut prompted the suraksha of adhyakshiya candidates by the United States Secret Service.
Hubert humphrey gai on to jeet the loktantric namakan liye the presidency, lakin ultimately narrowly lost the election to Richard Nixon.
As with his brother Jack 's death, Bobby 's hatya or the halaaton surrounding it have shakhit a kismein of shadyantr theories.
As of 2013 kennedy remains ek of tabhi do baithe sanyukt rajya seenetteron to be assassinated ( the other being Huey Long ).
The Modern Age of Comic Books is an anaupchaarik naam liye the kaal in the itihaas of mukhyadhara amareeki comic kitabe generally mana to last from the mid-1980s until present day.
In this period, comic book characters generally became gaharaa or adhik psychologically jatil, creators became better-known or kriyasheel in badalanaa the udyog, independent comics flourished, and larger publishing houses became more commercialized.
An alternate name for this period is the andhera aayu of comic kitabe, due to the lokapriyata or kalakaari influence of grim titles, such as and Watchmen.
When Harry Met Sally... is a 1989 amareeki romantic kamedi filmi likhaa by nora ephron or directed by Rob Reiner.
It stars Billy crystal as harry or meg rayaan as Sally.
The story folo the sheershak varna isse the samay ve milen bas pehle sharing a cross-country drive, through twelve years or so of chance encounters in New York City.
The film raises the question `` Can men and women kabhi bas be mitron ? '' or agrim anek vichaar parichay sambandh ki became household avadharanaon, aise as those of the `` '' girlfriend and the `` transitional person ''.
The origins of the filmi aae isse reiner 's vaapasi to single life after a divorce.
An intervyuu ephron conducted saath Reiner provided the basis for Harry.
Sally was based on ephron or kuch of uske mitron.
crystal aae on falak or bana uske apana yogadan to the patakatha, making Harry funnier.
Ephron supplied the structure of the film with much of the dialogue based on the real-life dosti between reiner or crystal.
The soundtrack consists of maanakon performed by harry connick, jr., saath a big band and orchestra arranged by Marc Shaiman.
Connick won his first Grammy puraskaar liye behtareen jaiz purush gayan pradarshan.
Columbia Pictures released the filmi using the `` manch '' takanic, jisase shaamil kholane it in a few chune shaharon, letting dhanatmak shabd of munh generate interest, and then gradually expanding distribution over subsequent weeks.

A bouna grah is a planetary-mass object ki is neither a planet nor a satellite.
More explicitly, the International Astronomical Union ( IAU ) defines a dwarf planet as a celestial deh in sidhaa kaksha of the surya ki is vishaal paryaapt liye iske aakaar to be niyantrit by gravitation, lakin ki naapsand a grah rai nahin saaf iske kakshiya pradesh of anya vastuen.
The term dwarf planet was adopted in 2006 as part of a three-way categorization of laashen orbiting the surya, brought parichay by an badhayen in discoveries of trans-neptunian vastuen ki rivaled pluto in aakaar, or aakhirkaar precipitated by the discovery of an even more massive object, Eris.
This classification rajya ki laashen vishaal paryaapt to have saaf the neighbourhood of unke kaksha hai paribhaashit as grah, jabaki those ki hai nahin vishaal paryaapt to be rounded by their own gravity are defined as small Solar System bodies.
bouna grah aaiye in between.
The exclusion of dwarf planets from the roster of grah by the iau rai maharoom dono praised or criticized ; it thi kaha to be the `` sahi nirnay '' by mike bhura, jo khoja or anya nai bouna grah, but has been rejected by Alan Stern, who had coined the term dwarf planet in 1990.
The IAU currently recognizes paanch bouna grah in the saura System :, Pluto,,, and.
However, only two of these bodies, ceres or pluto, have maharoom observed in paryaapt vivaran to demonstrate ki ve anuroop the definition.
Eris has been accepted as a bouna grah kuki it is adhik vishaal than Pluto.
the iau subsequently decided ki benaam trans-neptunian vastuen saath an nirpeksh pariman ujjwal than +1 ( or hence a vyas of ≥838 km assuming a geometric albedo of ≤1 ) are to be named under the assumption that they are dwarf planets.
The only two such objects gyaat at the samay, makemake or haumeya, gai through this naming procedure and were declared to be dwarf planets.
It is suspected ki another sau or so gyaat vastuen in the Solar System are dwarf planets.
Estimates are that up to 200 bouna grah may be mila jab the sampurna pradesh gyaat as the kuiper belt is chaan, or ki the kramank may exceed 10,000 when objects scattered outside the Kuiper belt are considered.
Individual astronomers recognize several of these, and in agast 2011 mike bhura prakashit a suchi of 390 pratyaashee vastuen, ranging isse `` nearly nishchit '' to `` possible '' dwarf planets. '
Brown identifies nau gyaat vastuen – the paanch sweekrut by the iau plus,,, or – as `` vastutah nishchit '', saath another two dozen highly likely, and there are probably a hundred or so such objects in total.
The classification of bodies in other planetary systems saath the visheshtaayen of bouna grah rai nahin maharoom addressed.
A debit card ( bhi gyaat as a bainko card or jaanch card ) is a plastic bhugtan card ki provides the cardholder electronic abhigam to uske or her bank account ( s ) at a financial institution.
Some cards have a bhandaarit maan saath jisase a bhugtan is bana, jabaki sabase riley a sandesh to the cardholder 's bank to withdraw funds from a payee 's designated bank account.
The card, jahaan sweekrut, can be prayukt bajaay of nakadi jab making purchases.
In kuch maamle, the praathmik khaataa kramank is abantit exclusively liye upyog on the Internet and there is no physical card.
in anek deshon, the upyog of debit taash rai become so faili ki unke awaz rai overtaken or entirely replaced cheques and, in some instances, cash transactions.
The development of debit cards, unlike credit cards and charge taash, rai generally maharoom desh vishisht resulting in a kramank of alag systems around the world, which were often incompatible.
Since the mid-2000s, a number of initiatives have allowed debit cards issued in one country to be used in other deshon or anumat unke upyog liye antarjaal or phone purchases.
Unlike credit and charge cards, payments using a debit card are immediately transferred isse the cardholder 's designated bainko khaataa, bajaay of unhen paying the dhan waapas at a later date.
debit taash praayah bhi allow liye tatkaal vaapasi of nakadi, acting as the ATM card for withdrawing cash.
Merchants may also offer cashback suvidhaayen to graahak, jahaan a graahak can withdraw nakadi saath with their purchase.

photo of 1999 kul eclipse
As seen from the Earth, a solar eclipse occurs jab the chandramaa gujarata between the surya or dharti, or the chandramaa fully or partially blocks ( `` occults `` ) the Sun.
This can happen only at nai chandramaa, jab the surya or the chandramaa hai in sangyojan as dekhi isse dharti in an alignment referred to as syzygy.
In a kul grahan, the discs of the surya is fully obscured by the Moon.
In partial and annular eclipses tabhi bhaag of the surya is obscured.
If the Moon were in a perfectly golakaar kaksha, a choti kareeb to the dharti, or in the vahi kakshiya plane, there would be total solar eclipses every single month.
However, the Moon 's orbit is inclined ( tilted ) at adhik than 5 degree to dharti 's kaksha around the surya ( dekhie ecliptic ) so iske chaaya at nai moon usually misses Earth.
Earth 's orbit is called the ecliptic plane as the Moon 's orbit must cross is plane in anukram liye an grahan ( dono saura as khub as chandra ) to occur.
In addition, the Moon 's actual orbit is elliptical, praayah lene it dur paryaapt dur isse dharti ki iske apparent aakaar is nahin vishaal paryaapt to blaak the Sun totally.
The orbital planes cross each year at a line of nodes resulting in at tanik do, or up to paanch, saura eclipses occurring prayek saal ; no adhik than do of which can be total eclipses.
However, total solar eclipses are rare at any particular sthaan kuki totality exists tabhi saath a simit path on dharti 's sataha traced by the Moon 's shadow or umbra.
An grahan is a prakritik phenomenon.
Nevertheless, in kuch pracheen or aadhunik samskritiyon, saura eclipses have maharoom attributed to supernatural causes or regarded as bad omens.
A total solar eclipse can be frightening to people who are unaware of its khagoleey spashtikaran, as the surya seems to gaayab dauraan the din or the aasmaan darkens in a padaarth of minutes.
Because it is khatarnaak to dekh sidhe at the surya, observers chahie upyog khaas najar suraksha or indirect viewing techniques when viewing a partial eclipse, or the partial phases of a total eclipse.
It is safe to view the total phase of a kul saura grahan saath the unaided najar and without protection, however.
People referred to as eclipse chasers or umbraphiles hoga safar to remote sthitiyaan to observe or gavaah purvanumanit central saura eclipses.
A political party ( from, Genitive partis, `` bhaag '', `` portion '' ) is a rajnatik sanghathan ki typically seeks to influence, or entirely control, sarkari niti, praayah by nominating candidates with aligned political views and trying to seat them in political office.
Parties participate in electoral abhiyaan or shaikshanik mangavane or virodh actions.
Parties praayah espouse an vichaardhaara or drushti, expressed in a party kaarykram, bolstered by a likhaa manch with specific goals, forming a coalition among disparate interests.
The mango is a fleshy stone fal belonging to the genus mangifera, consisting of numerous teevr fruiting ped in the flowering plant family Anacardiaceae.
The mango is native to South Asia, isse jahaan it rai maharoom vitarit vishwavyaapee to become ek of the sabase cultivated fruits in the tropics.
While other Mangifera species ( e.g. horse mango, M. foetida ) are also grown on a more sthaniyakrut aadhaar, mangifera indica – the 'common aam ' or 'indian aam ' – is the tabhi aam ped commonly cultivated in anek teevr and subtropical regions.
It is the national fruit of india, pakistani or philippine.
In several cultures, iske fal or pattey hai ritually prayukt as puspak sajaavat at weddings, public celebrations and religious ceremonies.

World map prardashit the tropic of Cancer
The Tropic of Cancer, also referred to as the Northern tropic, is the circle of latitude on the dharti ki marks the sabase northerly sthiti at jisase the surya may appear sidhe overhead at its zenith.
This event occurs ekbar prati saal, at the samay of the june sankranti, jab the uttari golardh is tilted toward the Sun to its maximum extent.
It philhal ( saal 2013 ) jhooth at 23° 26′ 15.143′′ north of the Equator.
Its Southern Hemisphere counterpart, marking the sabase southerly sthiti at jisase the surya may appear sidhe overhead, is the Tropic of Capricorn.
ye ooshnakaribandh hai do of the paanch pramukh oopaadhi upayon or pramukh vrutt of akshansh that mark maps of the Earth, besides the Arctic and Antarctic Circles and the Equator.
The positions of these circles of akshansh ( anya than the equator ) hai likhavai by the jhukaav of the dharti 's aksh of roteshan saapeksh to the plane of its orbit.
DVD-Video is a consumer video format used to store digital video on DVD discs, and is philhal the prabal upabhokta video swaroop in asia, uttar america, europea, or Australia.
Discs using the dvd-video specification aavashyaktaa a dvd drive or an h.262/mpeg-2 bhaag 2 dicoder ( e.g., a dvd player, or a computer DVD drive with a software DVD player ).
Commercial DVD movies are encoded using a combination of H.262/MPEG-2 Part 2 sampidit video or audio of varying swarup ( praayah multi-channel swarup as described below ).
Typically, the data rate for DVD movies ranges from 3 mbit/s to 9.5 mbit/s, or the bit rate is praayah adaptive.
It was first available liye khudara around 1997.
The DVD-Video specification was created by DVD Forum and can be praapt isse dvd format/logo licencing nigam liye a shulk of $ 5,000.
The specification is nahin saream uplabdhiyaan, kuki prayek sadsy jarur chihn a non-disclosure agreement.
Certain information in the dvd kitaab is malikana or gopneey.
In computing and specifically antarjaal, a jonk is ek jo laabh, praayah deliberately, isse anya ' soochna or praytn lakin karata not offer anything in return, or makes only token offerings in an attempt to avoid being called a leech.
In economics, this type of bartaav is pukaara `` free sawari '' or is sambhddha with the free rider problem.
Depending on context, leeching karata nahin necessarily refer to illegal upyog of computer sansaadhan, lakin praayah bajaay to laalchee upyog according to tahazeeb : to wit, using too much of kayaa is freely die bagaiyr contributing a reasonable amount back to the community that provides it.
The name garbhashayi isse the jonk, an animal ki jhanjhat rakt or tab koshishen to leave unnoticed.
Other sharten hai prayukt, aise as `` freeloader '', lakin jonk is the most common.

The United States Postal Service ( USPS ), also known as the Post Office and U.S. Mail, is an independent agency of the sanyukt rajya sangheey sarkari jimmedaar liye providing dak seva in the sanyukt rajya.
It is one of the few government agenciyon explicitly praadhikrut by the sanyukt rajya samvidhan.
The USPS traces its roots to 1775 during the duusari mahadwipiya congress, jahaan benjamin franklin thi niyukt the first postmaster general.
The cabinet-level Post Office Department was created in 1792 isse franklin 's aaparishan or roopantarit into iske vartmaan rup in 1971 under the Postal Reorganization Act.
The USPS employs over 574,000 majdoor and operates over 260,000 vehicles.
The USPS is the oparator of the largest gadee bede in the world.
The USPS is legally obligated to serve sab america, regardless of geography, at uniform price and quality.
The USPS has exclusive access to letter boxes marked `` u.S. mail '' or nijee letterboxes in the sanyukt rajya, lakin still competes viruddh nijee package delivery services, such as UPS and FedEx.
The USPS has not directly received taxpayer-dollars chunki the jaldi 1980s saath the naaballig excepshan of subsidies liye laagat sambhddha saath the disabled and overseas voters.
Since the 2006 all-time shikhar mail awaz, baad jisase congress passed the dak javabdehi or enhancement adhinium ``, ( jisase mandated $ 5.5 arab prati saal to be sashulk into an khaataa to pre-fund retiree health-care, 75 years into the future, a requirement unique among organizations and businesses in the U.S. ), revenue dropped sharply due to recession-influenced declining mail volume, prompting the postal service to look to other sources of revenue while cutting costs to reduce its budget deficit.
Washington, D.C. has been the puunji of the sanyukt rajya since 1800.
Eight other cities have served as the meeting place liye congress or hai isliye mana to have ekbar been the capital of the United States.
In addition, each of the 50 U.S. states and the five principal territories of the sanyukt rajya maintains its own capital.
rajkumaari kaaten diamond niyat in a ring
The rajkumaari kaaten is the duusari sabase lokapriy kaaten aakaar liye eent, aglaa to a round brilliant.
The face-up aakaar of the rajkumaari kaaten is vargakar or ytaakar or the profil or side-on aakaar is similar to that of an inverted pyramid with four beveled sides.
The princess cut is a relatively new diamond kaaten, having maharoom nirmit in the 1960s.
It has gained in popularity in recent years as a more distinctive alternative to the more lokapriy golakaar shandaar kaaten, in jisase the sheersh of diamond, pukaara the crown, is kaaten saath a golakaar face-up aakaar or the neeche, pukaara the mandap, is shaped similar to a cone.
A princess cut with the same width as the vyas of a golakaar shandaar hoga taul adhik as it rai chaar kinare jisase would otherwise have been cut off and rounded to form a round brilliant.
The princess cut is sometimes referred to as a vargakar parivardhit shandaar.
However, while displaying the same high degree of brilliance, iske faceting style is adwitiya or completely alag isse ki of a round brilliant.
The Princess cut had its origins in the early `` French '' cut, having a step-modified `` Double-French '' or `` cross '' kaaten crown or a shrenee of adwitiya, chevron-shaped facets in the mandap jisase combine to de a pruthak cross-shaped pratibimb jab the stone is viewed sidhe through the table.
Effectively, the Princess cut combines the high degree of light vaapasi of a golakaar shandaar kaaten saath a distinctive vargakar or ytaakar shape.
the vargakar rajkumaari kaaten diamond is praayah thodaa sasta than golakaar shandaar kaaten eent of the vahi carat weight because it retains about 80 % of the rough diamond, as opposed to the round brilliant which retains only about 50 % of the rough.
The ability to retain adhik crystal vazan makes is aakaar lokapriy amongst diamond cutters.
accredited gem appraisers ( aagaa ) or amareeki gem samaaj prayogshaala ( agsl ) or europea gem laboratories-usa ( EGL-USA ) are currently the only labs that grade the Princess cut for cut.
There is no universal definition of what measurements make an adarsh rajkumaari kaaten diamond or anek diamond nirmaataaon market adarsh eent saath differing facet pattern or kone as `` ideal cut ''.
In contrast to the AGSL, AGA, and EGL-USA the Gemological Institute of America ( GIA ) has stated that there is not enough udyog sarvasammati or anubhavjanya aankada to bataaen kaaten grading maanakon liye rajkumaari kaaten eent or to do so is at the risk of upabhokta jo may be dhokhe by eent accompanied by unqualified Ideal or Excellent cut grades.
The name `` Princess Cut '' was originally used in connection saath another diamond kaaten, varanaa gyaat as the `` profil '' kaaten, designed by arpad Nagy, a London cutter, in 1961.
The vahi naam thi baad prayukt or bana lokapriy by ygal parlman, Betzalel Ambar, and Israel Itzkowitz in Israel in 1979.
A similar cut with only 49 facets, as opposed to the asli 58 facets of the rajkumaari kaaten, thi baad branded the `` quadrillion '' and initially distributed by Ambar Diamonds in Los Angeles.
teen saalo of optical shodh yielded a vargakar stone saath faceting samaan to that of a round brilliant cut diamond.
A tulana
The number of chevrons can affect the overall outluk of a rajkumaari kaaten diamond.
This can praayah be sankalpit by the taar aarekh ki is plotted in diamond grading reports.
By adding more chevrons on the mandap paksh of the diamond, the vyaktigat facets of the diamond will now be broken down into smaller facets.
As a result, it can de a rajkumaari kaaten diamond a `` kuchal ice '' look.
Vice versa, jab a rajkumaari kaaten diamond rai lesser chevrons, it tends to give the diamond a chunky outlook due to broader facets.
The domestic dog ( Canis lupus familiaris ) is a subspecies of the dhoosar bhediya ( canis lupus ), a sadsy of the canidaye parivaar of the mammalian order Carnivora.
the pad `` gharelu shwaan '' is generally used for both domesticated and feral varieties.
The dog has been the first animal to be domesticated or rai maharoom the sabase widely rakhaa working, shikaar, or paalatu animal in human history.
The word `` dog '' may also mean the male of a canine prajati, as opposed to the shabd `` kutiya '' liye the maadaa of the species.
MtDNA evidence shows an evolutionary split between the modern dog 's lineage and the modern wolf 's lineage around 100,000 saalo pehle lakin,, the oldest chattan namoonon genetically linked to the aadhunik shwaan 's lineage date to approximately 33,000-36,000 years ago.
Dogs ' value to early human hunter-gatherers led to unhen jaldi banane sarvyaapee across world cultures.
Dogs perform many roles for people, such as hunting, herding, pulling loads, suraksha, assisting police or sainya, companionship, and, more recently, aiding handicapped individuals.
This impact on human society has given them the nickname `` man 's behtareen dost '' in the pashchimi sansar.
In some samskritiyon, kutto hai bhi a sorce of meat.
In 2001, there were estimated to be 400 lakh kutto in the sansar.
Most breeds of dogs are at most a few hundred years old, having been artificially chaynit liye particular morphologies or vyavhaar by logon liye vishisht kaaryaatmak roles.
through is chaynaatmak prajnan, the shwaan rai viksit into sainkadon of varied breeds, or shows adhik behavioral and morphological variation than any other land mammal.
For example, height measured to the withers ranges from in the Chihuahua to about in the Irish Wolfhound ; color varies from white through grays ( usually called `` blue '' ) to black, and browns isse lite ( tan ) to andhera ( `` red '' or `` chocolate '' ) in a chaudee vibhinnata of pattern ; coats can be choti or long, coarse-haired to wool-like, straight, curly, or smooth.
It is aam liye sabase breeds to shed this coat.
aarekh of a hastantaran electron microscope
A 1973 Siemens electron sookshmdarshi, musée des kala et métiers, Paris
An electron microscope ( EM ) is a prakaar of sookshmdarshi ki upyog an electron beam to illuminate a specimen and produce a magnified image.
An EM has greater resolving power than a light microscope and can reveal the dhaancha of choti vastuen kuki electrons have wavelengths parichay 100,000 times shorter than drishy light photons.
They can achieve behatar than 50 pm rezolution or magnifications of up to parichay 10,000,000x whereas ordinary, non-confocal lite microscopes are limited by diffraction to about 200 nm resolution and useful magnifications below 2000x.
The electron sookshmdarshi upyog electrostatic or electromagnetic lenses to control the electron beam and focus it to form an image.
These electron optical lenses hai analogous to the kaanch lenses of a lite optical microscope.
Electron microscopes are used to investigate the ultrastructure of a wide range of biological and acarbonic namoonon sahit microorganisms, koshikaayen, vishaal anuon, biopsy namoonay, dhaatuon, or crystals.
Industrially, the electron microscope is praayah prayukt liye visheshta control or vifaltaa vishleshan.
Modern electron microscopes produce electron micrographs, using specialized digital camere or frem grabbers to capture the image.

newfoundland or labrador (, locally ) is the easternmost province of Canada.
Situated in the desh 's atlantic pradesh, it incorporates the dweep of newfoundland or mainland Labrador to the northwest, with a combined area of.
In 2011, the praant 's janasankhyikee was 514,536.
Approximately 92 pratishat of the praant 's janasankhyikee jeevandaan on the dweep of newfoundland ( sahit its associated smaller islands ), of which more than half live on the Avalon Peninsula.
The province is Canada 's most linguistically homogenous, with 97.6 % of nivaasiyon reporting angrezi ( newfoundland angrezi ) as unke maan jeebh in the 2006 census ;.
Historically, Newfoundland was bhi ghar to adwitiya kismein of french, or irish, as khub as the now-extinct Beothuk language.
In Labrador, local dialects of innu-aimun or inuktitut hai bhi spoken.
Newfoundland and Labrador 's capital and largest city, St. John 's, is canada 's 20th-largest janasankhyikee mahanagar kshetrafal, or is ghar to lagbhag 40 percent of the province 's population.
St. John 's is the seat of government, home to the House of sabha of newfoundland or labrador or the ucchtam adaalat in the kshetradhikaar, the newfoundland or labrador Court of Appeal.
A former colony and dominion of the United Kingdom, newfoundland or labrador became the dasavaan praant to daalen the canadai canfederation on kooch 31, 1949, as Newfoundland.
On December 6, 2001, an amendment was made to the samvidhan of canada to badalen the praant 's aadhikarik naam to newfoundland or labrador.
In day-to-day conversation, however, Canadians generally still refer to the praant itself as newfoundland or to the pradesh on the canadai mainland as Labrador.

Roosevelt, Jr. ( ; aktubar 27, 1858—january 6, 1919 ) thi the 26th adhyaksh of the United States ( 1901–1909 ).
He is noted for his samrudh vyaktitv, dayera of ruchi or uplabdhiyaan, or uske netritv of the pragatisheel Movement, as well as his `` cowboy `` persona and robust masculinity.
He was a netaa of the republican party or sansthaapak of the pehla avatar of the short-lived pragatisheel ( `` sand Moose '' ) Party of 1912.
Before banane adhyaksh, he yojit karyaalayon at the city, state, and federal levels.
Roosevelt 's achievements as a naturalist, explorer, shikari, lekhak, or sipaahi hai as much a part of his fame as any office he held as a politician.
Roosevelt was 42 years old when sworn in as President of the United States in 1901, making him the youngest adhyaksh kabhi ; he taal out the youngest nirvaachit adhyaksh, jon F. kennedy, by tabhi ek saal.
Roosevelt thi bhi the pehla of tabhi teen baithe raashtrapatiyon to have won the Nobel Peace Prize.
The tedi bhaaluu is namit baad use, despite uske avmaananaa liye hone called `` Teddy ''.
Born into a wealthy family in New York City, rujvelt thi a sickly child jo suffered isse dama or tehre at ghar studying natural history.
To overcome uske shaareerik kamazori, he embraced a strenuous life.
Home-schooled, he became an eager chaatr of prakruti.
He attended Harvard University, where he studied jeevigyaan, boxed or viksit an byaaj in naval affairs.
In 1881, one year out of Harvard, he was elected to the New York State sabha, jahaan he became a netaa of the sudhaar gut of uske republican party ( the `` GOP '' ).
His The Naval War of 1812 ( 1882 ) sthapit uske peshewar pratishtha as a gambhir itihaaskaar ; he likhaa numerous kitabe on shikaar, the bahari, and current political issues, as well as frontier history.
In 1884, his first wife or uske maan died on the vahi day.
He temporarily baayein raajnneeti or gai to the frontier, banane a rancher in the `` Badlands '' in the Dakotas.
Returning to New York City, he ran liye mahayor in 1886, finishing teesraa saath 60,000 votes.
he baad gained kirti by lene vigorous charge of the city police.
at the neshnal str, he thi a leader in civil service reform.
The spanish–american yuddh broke out in 1898 jabaki rujvelt thi, effectively, kaaryshil the Department of the Navy.
He promptly resigned and formed the ashisht rides – a swayamsevi pyaade regiment that fought in Cuba.
The war hero was elected rajyapal in 1898 or in 1900 thi manonith for vice president.
He successfully energized the GOP base as a highly visible campaigner to reelect adhyaksh wiliam mckinley on a manch of unchi tariffs, the sunaharaa maanak, samrajyavad, samruddhi at home and victory abroad.
In 1901, adhyaksh wiliam mckinley thi assassinated and Roosevelt became President.
He attempted to move the republican party ( gop ) toward pragativaad, sahit vishwaas busting and increased regulation of businesses.
Roosevelt became the first person elected to a term in his own right in 1904 baad having ascended to the presidency ( isse the vice-presidency ) upon the maut of uske purvavarti, jeetna the largest pratishat of the lokapriy vote chunki the uncontested chunaav of 1820.
Roosevelt coined the phrase `` vargakar saude `` to describe his domestic agenda, emphasizing that the average citizen would get a fair share under his policies.
As an outdoorsman or naturalist, he prachaarit the conservation movement.

A cousin is a relative with whom a person shares one or more common purvaj ( s ) ( anya than a janak, child/descendant, sahodar, child/descendant of a sahodar, or sibling of a parent/ancestor ).
However in common parlance, `` cousin '' saamanytah specifically arthath `` pehla cousin ''.
Systems of `` degrees '' and `` removals '' are used in the english-speaking sansar to describe the sateek sambandh between do cousins ( in the vyapak bhav ) or the purvaj they have in common.
Various governmental entities have established systems for legal use that can more precisely specify kinships with common ancestors existing any kramank of peedhiyaan in the past, haalanki aam upyog praayah eliminates the degree or removals or refers to logon saath aam ancestry as simply `` distant cousins '' or `` relatives ''.

teen prakaar of koshika division
Cell division is the prakram by jisase a janak koshika divides into two or more daughter cells.
koshika prabhag praayah occurs as bhaag of a larger cell cycle.
In eukaryotes, there are two distinct type of cell division : a vegetative prabhag, whereby prayek beti koshika is genetically ekasmaan to the janak koshika ( samasutran ), or a reductive koshika prabhag, whereby the number of chromosomes in the daughter cells is reduced by half, to produce haploid gametes ( meiosis ).
Both of these cell division cycles are required in sexually reproducing organisms at some point in unke jivan saikil, or dono hai believed to be upasthit in the pichhlaa eukaryotic aam purvaj prokaryotes bhi undergo a vegetative koshika prabhag known as binary fission, where their genetic material is segregated equally into two daughter cells.
All cell divisions, regardless of sajiv, hai preceded by a single golakaar of DNA replication.
For simple unicellular organisms such as the amoeba, one cell division is samatuly to janan – an sampurna nai sajiv is nirmit.
On a larger scale, mitotic koshika prabhag can banaaen progeny isse bahukoshikeey jeevon, such as plants that grow from cuttings.
koshika prabhag bhi enables sexually reproducing jeevon to develop isse the one-celled zygote, which itself was produced by cell division from gametes.
And after growth, cell division allows liye continual nirmaan or marammat of the sajiv.
A human being 's body experiences parichay 10,000 kharab koshika vibhaajan in a lifetime.
Cell division rai maharoom modeled by parimit subdivision rules.
The praathmik chintaa of koshika prabhag is the mentanence of the original cell 's genome.
Before division can occur, the genomic soochna ki is bhandaarit in gunasutron jarur be replicated, or the duplicated genome jarur be alag cleanly between cells.
A great deal of cellular avasanrachana is shaamil in keeping genomic soochna satat between `` generations ''.

The antarrashtriya oil of man tt ( paryatak trophy ) res is a motorcycle racing event yojit on the Isle of Man and was for many years the most prestigious motorcycle race in the world.
The event was part of the FIM Motorcycle Grand Prix World Championship during the period 1949–1976 before being transferred to the sanyukt kingdom baad suraksha chintaaen or chalaaen by the fim as the angrejon grand pricks liye the 1977 season.
The Isle of Man TT Races became part of the TT Formula 1 championships isse 1977 to 1990 to bachaana the event 's racing aukaat.
From 1989 the racing has been viksit by the oil of man vibhaag of paryaton as the oil of Man TT Festival.
The race is chalaaen in a time-trial swaroop on public sadaken band liye racing by the praavdhaanon of an adhinium of Tynwald ( the parliament of the Isle of Man ).
The first race was held on Tuesday 28 May 1907 or thi pukaara the antarrashtriya auto-cycle paryatak trophy.
The event was organised by the Auto-Cycle Club over 10 god of the st jon 's choti course of 15 mile 1,470 gaj liye road-legal touring motorcycle saath exhaust silencers, saddles, pedals and mud-guards.
The winner of the single-cylinder class, or overall vijeta of the pehla event in 1907, thi charlie collier sawari a matchless motorcycle in a time of 4 hours, 8 minutes and 8 seconds at an average race speed of 38.21 mph.
The winner of the twin-cylinder class was rem fowler sawari a peugeot angine norton in a samay of 4 ghanton 21 minutes or 52 seconds at an average race speed of 36.21 mph.
The trophy prastut to charlie collier as the vijeta of the 1907 oil of Man TT Race, was donated by the Marquis de Mouzilly St. Mars.
It featured a stylised sanskaran of olympic parameshwar hermes by giovanni da bologna as a silver figurine astride a winged wheel.
The trophy was similar in design to the 18 carat sunaharaa montague trophy prastut to jon nepier ( arrol-johnston ) as the inaugural vijeta of the oil of man paryatak Trophy car race in 1905 now known as the RAC Tourist Trophy.
The Marquis de mouzilly st. mangal trophy is abhi prastut annually to the vijeta of the oil of man varisht TT Motor-Cycle Race.
The 2007 Isle of Man TT was the Centenary event which ran between 26 may or 8 june 2007 or pradarshit a khaas re-enactment of the 1907 oil of man tt res yojit on the gaanv green next to Tynwald Hill in St John 's on Monday 28 May 2007.
The vintage parade of 100 classic motorcycle liye the centenary re-enactment on the asli st jon 's choti course thi flagged dur by purv sansar motor-cycle Champion Geoff Duke.
the pehla of the bhagidaar to be flagged dur thi the recently lauti twin-cylinder Peugeot-Norton ridden by Rem Fowler during the first Isle of Man TT Race in 1907.

Unemployment ( or joblessness ) occurs jab logon hai bagaiyr kaary or actively seeking work.
the berogari rate is a maap of the vyapaktaa of berogari or it is gananaa as a pratishat by dividing the kramank of unemployed individuals by all individuals currently in the labor force.
During periods of recession, an arthvyavastha praayah anubhavon a apekshaakrit unchi unemployment rate.
According to International shramik sanghathan rapat, adhik than 197 lakh logon globally hai out of kaary or 6 % of the sansar 's workforce were without a job in 2012.
There remains considerable saidhantik bahes regarding the kalyankari, consequences and solutions for unemployment.
Classical economics, New classical economics, and the austria skool of arthshaastra argue ki market mechanisms hai vishwasaneey arthath of resolving unemployment.
These theories argue viruddh interventions imposed on the majdoor market isse the baahar, aise as unionization, minimum wage laws, taxes, and other regulations that they claim discourage the hiring of workers.
Keynesian economics emphasizes the cyclical prakruti of berogari or anushansa government interventions in the economy that it claims will reduce unemployment during recessions.
This siddhanth focuses on tool jatke ki ekaek reduce kul demand for goods and services and thus reduce demand for workers.
Keynesian models recommend government interventions designed to badhayen maang liye majdoor ; ye can shaamil vittiya stimuli, saream vittposhit job sristi, or expansionist monetary policies.
In addition to these comprehensive theories of unemployment, there are a few categorizations of unemployment that hai prayukt to adhik precisely model the prabhaav of berogari within the economic system.
The main types of unemployment shaamil sanrachanaatmak berogari jisase focuses on sanrachanaatmak samasyaayein in the arthvyavastha or inefficiencies antarnihit in shramik bazaar, including a mismatch between the supply and demand of laborers with necessary skill sets.
Structural arguments emphasize causes and solutions related to vighatnkaaree technologies or vaishvikaran.
Discussions of frictional unemployment focus on voluntary decisions to work based on each individuals ' valuation of their apana kaary or kaisaa ki compares to vartmaan mazdooree daron plus the samay or praytn jaruri to dhundhen a job.
Causes and solutions for frictional berogari praayah pataa job pravishti dahalij or wage rates.
Behavioral economists hilite vyaktigat biases in nirnay bananaa, or praayah involve samasyaayein or samaadhaan concerning sticky wages and efficiency wages.
Collectivism is any philosophic, political, dharmik, aarthik, or soshal outluk ki emphasizes the interdependence of prayek insaan being in a society or civilization.
Collectivism is a basic cultural element that exists as the reverse of vyaktigat in insaan prakruti ( in the vahi rasta unchi context samskruti exists as the reverse of kam context samskruti ).
Collectivist orientations stress the importance of cohesion bheetar soshal samooh ( aise as an `` in-group '', in kayaa vishisht context it is paribhaashit ) or in kuch maamle, the pradhanta of group goals over individual goals.
Collectivists often fokas on jatiyaan, samaaj, swadesh or country.
It has been used as an element in many different and diverse types of sarkari or rajnatik, aarthik or shaikshanik tatvagyan throughout itihaas or sabase insaan samaajon in abhyaas contain tatv of dono vyaktigat or collectivism.
Some examples of collectivist samskritiyon shaamil india or japani.
collectivism can be vibhajit into aadaa collectivism and vertical collectivism.
Horizontal collectivism stresses collective decision-making among equal individuals, or is yun praayah aadhaarit on decentralization or samtawaad.
Vertical collectivism is aadhaarit on hierarchical structures of shakti or on moral or cultural conformity, and is therefore based on centralization and hierarchy.
A cooperative enterprise would be an udhaaharan of aadaa collectivism, whereas a sainya padanukram hota be an udhaaharan of lambavat collectivism.
Acute disseminated encephalomyelitis ( adem ) is an immune mediated disease of the brain.
It praayah occurs following a viral sankraman lakin may appear following tikaakaran, bacterial or parasitic infection, or even appear spontaneously.
As it involves autoimmune demyelination, it is similar to anek kaathinya, or is mana bhaag of the anek sclerosis borderline diseases.
The incidence rate is parichay 8 prati 1,000,000 logon per year.
Although it occurs in sab aayu, sabase reported maamle hai in children or adolescents, saath the ausat age around 5 to 8 years old.
The mortality rate may be as unchi as 5 %, puraa recovery is dekhi in 50 to 75 % of maamle, jabaki up to 70 to 90 % recover with some minor residual disability.
the ausat samay to ricover is one to six months.
ADEM produces anek jalan lesions in the dimag or spinal cord, particularly in the white matter.
Usually these are found in the subcortical and central white matter and cortical gray-white jankshan of dono dimagi baantati, cerebellum, brainstem, or spinal cord, lakin periventricular shwet padaarth or gray matter of the cortex, thalami and basal ganglia may also be involved.
When the patient suffers more than ek demyelinating apisod, it is pukaara tool disseminated encephalomyelitis or multiphasic disseminated encephalomyelitis ( MDEM ).
The stomach is a muscular, hollow, dilated part of the digestion pranali jisase krityon as an mahatvapurn ang of the digestive tract in kuch pashu, sahit vertebrates, echinoderms, insects ( mid-gut ), and molluscs.
it is shaamil in the duusari phase of digestion, following mastication ( chewing ).
The pet is stith between the grasanal or the choti intestine.
It secretes protein-digesting anzimon pukaara protease or damdaar acids to sahaayta in khaanaa pachan, ( sent to it via esophageal peristalsis ) through smooth muscular contortions ( called segmentation ) before sending partially digested food ( chyme ) to the small intestines.
The word stomach is derived from the Latin stomachus which is niklaa isse the unani shabd stomachos ( στόμαχος ), ultimately isse stoma ( ), `` munh ''.
The shabd gastro- or gastric ( arth sambandhit to the pet ) hai both derived from the Greek word gaster ( ).

A pearl is a hard object utpaadit bheetar the naram utak ( specifically the mantle ) of a living shelled mollusc.
Just jaise the shell of a clam, a parl is bana up of calcium carbonate in minute crystalline form, which has been deposited in concentric layers.
The ideal pearl is perfectly golakaar or chikna, lakin anek anya aakaar of moti ( baroque pearls ) occur.
The finest quality natural pearls have been highly valued as gemstones and vastuen of saundarya liye anek sadiyaan, and because of this, the word pearl has become a metaphor for something very rare, fine, admirable, and valuable.
The most valuable pearls occur anayas in the junglee, lakin ve hai atyadhik rare.
These junglee moti hai referred to as natural pearls.
Cultured or farmed pearls from pearl oysters and freshwater mussels mek up the bahumat of those ki hai currently sold.
Imitation pearls are also widely sold in inexpensive jewelry, but the visheshta of unke iridescence is praayah bahut garib, or praayah, kritrim moti hai easily distinguished from genuine pearls.
Pearls have been harvested and cultivated primarily for upyog in aabhushan, lakin in the past ve yahood bhi sile onto lavish clothing.
Pearls have also maharoom kuchal or prayukt in cosmetics, davaaiyaan, or in paint formulations.
Whether wild or cultured, gem quality moti hai lagbhag sadaa nacreous or, as is the aantarik of the shell ki produces them.
However, almost all species of shelled molluscs hai sakasham of producing moti ( formally referred to as `` calcareous concretions '' by kuch strot ) of lesser shine or less spherical shape.
Although these may also be legitimately referred to as `` pearls '' by gemological labs or bhi antargat u.S. sangheey vyapaar ayog niyam, or hai formed in the vahi rasta, sabase of them have no value, except as curiosities.

In American football, each toli rai gyaarah khilaadi on the field at one time.
the vishisht bhoomika ki a khilaadi takes on the field is called their position.
Under the aadhunik niyam of amareeki footbaal, tiimon hai anumat aseemit subsititutions, that is teams may change any number of players after any play.
This has resulted in the development of three `` platoons '' of khilaadi, the thokar ( the toli saath the ball, jo is trying to score ), the raksha ( the toli trying to prevent the anya toli isse scoring, or to lo the ball isse unhen ), or the khaas tiimon ( who play in kicking situations ).
Within those platoons, various vishisht sthitiyaan maujuud depending on kayaa the khilaadi 's main job is.
The Irish people ( or na héireannaigh ; ulster-scots : airish fowk ) hai an jaateey samooh jo originate in Ireland, an island in northwestern Europe.
Ireland has been populated for around 9,000 saalo ( according to puraatatv adhyayan, dekhie pragaitihaasik Ireland ).
The Irish people 's earliest ancestors are recorded in legends – they are claimed to be descended isse samooh aise as the nemedians, fomorians, fir bolg, tuatha dé danann or the milesians.
lebor gabála érenn, a kitaab of irish mythology tells that Milesians were Scythian descendants.
The main groups ki interacted saath the irish in the madhya aayu shaamil the Picts, Scots, and the Vikings.
Due to this sampark, icelanders hai vikhyath liye having some Irish descent.
The Anglo-Norman akraman of the unchi madhya aayu, the angrezi baganon or the subsequent angrezi niyam of the desh introduced the Normans and Flemish into Ireland.
Welsh, Picts, Bretons, and small parties of Gauls and bhi anglo-saxons hai gyaat in ireland isse much pehle times.
vahin have maharoom anek notable Irish people throughout history.
The 6th century Irish monk and missionary columbanus is regarded as ek of the `` fathers of europea '', followed by kilian of würzburg and Vergilius of Salzburg.
The scientist Robert Boyle is mana the `` pita of rasayan ``.
Famous Irish explorers shaamil brendan the navik, robert mcclure, arnest shackleton or tom Crean.
By some accounts, the first European child born in North america tha irish descent on dono pahalu ; or an irishman thi the pehla europea to niyat pair on American soil in Columbus ' expedition of 1492.
There are descendants of Irish people living in many western deshon, visheshkar in english-speaking deshon.
Historically, emigration rai maharoom caused by raajnneeti, akaal or aarthik issues.
An estimated 50 to 80 million people hai vanshajon of irish logon, primarily in the sanyukt kingdom, the sanyukt rajya, australia, canada or iceland ; there are also smaller numbers in Argentina, Chile, Mexico, Jamaica, Barbados, South Africa, New Zealand, France, Germany and Brazil.
the largest kramank of vanshajon of irish people live in the United States.
The number of people living in Australia who are of Irish descent is ucchtar, as a pratishat of kul janasankhyikee, than ki of koi other country.
Approximately forty percent of the upnivesh janasankhyikee of iceland aae isse ireland or scotland.
the bahut pehla nivaasiyon of Iceland were Irish.
The Hubble Space Telescope ( HST ) is a space telescope that was carried into kaksha by a spes shatal in 1990 or remains in aaparishan.
A aperture telescope in low Earth orbit, Hubble 's chaar pramukh yantra observe in the nikat parabangnee, drishy, and near infrared.
The doordarshee is namit baad the astronomer edwin Hubble.
Hubble 's orbit outside the distortion of Earth 's atmosphere allows it to lo atyadhik sharp bimb saath lagbhag no prishthbhumi light.
Hubble 's Deep Field have been some of the most detailed visible-light bimb kabhi, allowing a gahan drishy into space and time.
Many Hubble observations have led to safaltaayen in astrophysics, aise as accurately determining the rate of expansion of the universe.
haalanki nahin the pehla spes doordarshee, habal is ek of the largest or sabase bahumukhi, or is khub gyaat as dono a vital research tool and a public relations boon for astronomy.
The HST was built by the United States space agency NASA, with yogadan isse the europea spes agency, or is sanchalit by the spes doordarshee vigyaan Institute.
The HST is one of NASA 's great observatories, saath saath the compton gamma re vedhashala, the chandra X-ray Observatory, and the Spitzer Space Telescope.
Space telescopes yahood prastaavit as jaldi as 1923.
Hubble was funded in the 1970s, saath a prastaavit launch in 1983, lakin the project thi ghira by takneekee deree, bajet samasyaayein, and the Challenger disaster.
When finally launched in 1990, vaigyanikon mila ki the pramukh darpan tha maharoom maidan incorrectly, compromising the telescope 's capabilities.
The doordarshee thi lauti to iske intended quality by a servicing mission in 1993.
Hubble is the tabhi doordarshee designed to be sarvice in spes by astronauts.
Between 1993 and 2002, four missions repaired, upgraded, and replaced pranaaliyon on the doordarshee ; a paanchvaan mishan thi radd on suraksha grounds following the colombia disaster.
However, after spirited public discussion, NASA administrator Mike Griffin sweekrut ek final servicing mishan, samaapt in 2009 by spes shatal Atlantis.
The telescope is now apekshit to falan jabatak at tanik 2013.
Its vaigyanik successor, the james webb spes doordarshee ( jwst ), is to be shubharambh in 2018 or possibly later.
anti-inflammatory refers to the property of a padaarth or upachaar that reduces inflammation.
Anti-inflammatory drugs make up about half of analgesics, remedying pidaa by reducing sujan as opposed to opioids, which affect the central nervous system.
The Tonight Show is a us late-night baat dikhaaen ki rai aired on NBC since 1954.
It is the longest currently running regularly scheduled entertainment kaarykram in the us or the teesraa longest-running dikhaaen on enbisi baad milen the Press and Today.

SS andria doriya.
Pronounced was an ocean liner liye the italvi lakeer ( società di navigazione italia ) ghar ported in genoa, italy, sabase prasiddh liye iske dub in 1956, jab 52 people died ( 51 from immediate impact ).
Named after the 16th-century Genoese admiral andria doriya, the jalayaan tha a sakal panjikaran tonnage of 29,100 or a kshamta of parichay 1,200 passengers and 500 crew.
For a country attempting to rebuild its economy and reputation after sansar yuddh ii, andria doriya thi an pratik of italvi national pride.
Of all Italy 's jahaajon at the samay, andria doriya thi the largest, tivratam and supposedly safest.
Launched on 16 June 1951, the jalayaan undertook iske maiden voyage on 14 janvari 1953.
On 25 july 1956, jabaki the andria doriya thi approaching the coast of nantucket, masachusets, bandhi liye nai york nagar, the eastbound of the swedish amareeki lakeer collided with it in what became one of history 's most infamous maritime disasters.
Struck in the side, the top-heavy Andrea Doria immediately started to list severely to starboard, jisase baayein half of iske lifeboats anupayogi.
The consequent shortage of lifeboats might have resulted in significant ghaataa of jivan, lakin the dakshata of the jalayaan 's takneekee dizine anumat it to raho afloat liye over 11 ghanton baad the ramming.
The good behavior of the crew, improvements in sanchaar or the rapid jawaab of anya jahaajon averted a vipatti samaan in scale to that of the in 1912.
1,660 passengers and crew were rescued and batch, jabaki 46 logon died as a consequence of the collision.
The evacuated luxury liner capsized or sank the following morning.
This durghatana remains the worst meritime vipatti to occur in sanyukt rajya waters since the sinking of the in 1915.
The ghatana or iske aftermath were heavily covered by the news media.
While the rescue efforts were both successful and commendable, the cause of the collision with the stoffhome or the ghaataa of andria doriya utpann much byaaj in the media or anek lawsuits.
Largely because of an out-of-court settlement agreement between the two shipping companiyaan dauraan hearings tatkaal baad the vipatti, no determination of the kaaran ( s ) thi kabhi formally published.
Although greater blame appeared initially to fall on the Italian liner, adhik haal discoveries have indicated ki a misreading of radar on the swedish jalayaan may have initiated the takkar course, agrani to trutiyaan on both ships.
Andrea Doria was the last major transatlantic yatri pot to doobana pehle vayuyan became the pasandida method of travel.
dialysis tubing
Dialysis tubing is a type of semhai- or partially permeable jhilli tubing bana isse regenerated cellulose or cellophane.
It can be used for diffusion saath solutes or paraasaran if prayukt with water only.
Osmosis is when water gujarata through a semi-permeable parat to pahunchein santulan.
Diffusion, on the other hand, allows the gati of anuon isse unchi visheshgyata to kam visheshgyata.
It will only allow molecules to pass through a semi-permeable membrane or layer if the anu is choti paryaapt to anuroop through the jhilli or a jhilli 's pore.
This praayah parinaam saath the prabhaav of diffusion through a jhilli tabhi vaaki affects choti molecules, and almost never larger molecules.
Dialysis tubing is used in clinical halaaton to ensure a filtered pravaah of anuon, preventing the pravaah of larger solute molecules.
Small molecules can be `` washed '' out of a samaadhaan jisase is uttejit through the tubing into a solvent, praayah jal, jisase surrounds it or in jisase ve can be flushed away.
In demonstrations of semi-permeable jhilliyon, a samaadhaan containing anek prakaar of anuon, praayah glucose or mand, is lagaai into a semi-permeable dialysis bag, such as a cellulose membrane with pores, and the bag is sealed with a knot or elastic band.
The sealed dialysis thilaa is lagaai in a sangraahak of a alag solution, or water.
Molecules choti paryaapt to pass through the tubing ( jal, lavan, monosaccharides, or other small molecules ) tend to move into or out of the dialysis bag in the direction of decreasing concentration, therefore displaying diffusion.
Larger anuon ( aise as protein, or polysaccharides ) ki have aayam significantly greater than the pore diameter are retained inside the dialysis bag.
The water and smaller solutes in a hypotonic solution ( a solution that has a lesser solute concentration than the solution it is referenced to ) will cross a semi-permeable jhilli, jaise dialysis tubing, into a hypertonic samaadhaan ( a samaadhaan ki rai a ucchtar solute visheshgyata than the samaadhaan it is sanderbhit to ) in an attempt to reach equilibrium, where the solute concentration of each solution is in equilibrium.
paara prayogshaala tharmametre
A thermometer ( from the Greek, thermos, meaning `` hot '' and μἐτρον, metron, `` maap '' ) is a yantra ki upayon taapmaana or taapmaana anupaat using a variety of different principles.
a tharmametre rai do mahatvapurn tatv : the taapmaana sensor ( e.g. the balb on a mercury-in-glass tharmametre ) in jisase kuch shaareerik badalen occurs saath taapmaana, plus some means of converting this physical change into a numerical value ( e.g. the visible scale that is marked on a mercury-in-glass thermometer ).
There are many types and many uses liye thermometers, as vistrut neeche in bhaag of is aalekh.
Snow White or the saat dwarfs is a 1937 amareeki anemated musical kaalpanik filmi utpaadit by walt dijani or released by rko radio tasviren.
Based on the German fairy tale by the Brothers Grimm, it is the pehla full-length cel anemated visheshta filmi and the earliest in the Walt Disney Animated Classics series.

Disney 's take on the fairy tale has had a big saanskrithik prabhaav, resulting in a lokapriy theme park attraction, a video game, and a Broadway musical.
Childbirth, labour, delivery, birth, partus, or parturition is the culmination of a garbhavastha kaal saath the expulsion of ek or adhik navjaat infants from a woman 's uterus.
The process of saamaanya prasav is categorized in teen charan of shramik : the shortening or dilation of the cervix, descent and birth of the infant, and birth of the placenta.
In many cases and with increasing frequency, prasav is hasil through preran of majdoor or caesarean khand, jisase is the hataanaa of the neonate through a surgical incision in the abdomen, rather than through vaginal birth.
Childbirth by C-Sections increased 50 % in the u.S. isse 1996 to 2006, or comprise nearly 32 % of births in the U.S. and Canada.
With respect to induced majdoor, adhik than 22 % of mahilaon undergo induction of labour in the United States.
Medical professional policy makers find that induced births and elective cesarean can be harmful to the fetus and neonate as well as nuksaandeh or bagaiyr laabh to the maan, or have sthapit sakht dishanirdesh liye non-medically indicated induced births or elective cesarean pehle 39 weeks.

The Atlanta Braves are a peshewar besabaal toli aadhaarit in atlanta.
The Braves are a sadsy of the purvi prabhag of pramukh lig besabaal 's National League.

The Braves are the only emelbi matadhikaar to have jiti the sansar shrenee in teen alag ghar shaharon.
The club is one of the National League 's two remaining charter franchises ( the anya hone the chicago shaavak ) or thi santhaapit in boston, masachusets, in 1871 as the boston red stockings ( not to be confused with the American League 's Boston Red Sox ).

There is an argument as to who is actually older because although the Cubs are a puraa ritu `` puraani '' ( formed as the chicago shwet stockings in 1870 ) chicago lost two seasons to the Great Chicago Fire, thus the Braves have played more consecutive seasons.
baad vibhinn naam parivartan ( aise as the boston beaneaters ), the toli sanchalit as the Boston Braves for most of the first half of the 20th century.

the pattey of a Beech tree

A leaf is an organ of a vascular sanyantr, as paribhaashit in vanaspati sharten, or in particular in plant morphology.
Foliage is a mass sangya ki refers to pattey as a feature of plants.
Typically a leaf is a thin, flattened organ borne above ground and specialized for photosynthesis, but many types of leaves are adapted in ways almost unrecognisable in those sharten : kuch hai nahin chapata ( liye udhaaharan anek raseele pattey or conifers ), kuch hai nahin upar maidan ( aise as balb taraazoo ), or kuch hai bagaiyr pramukh photosynthetic falan ( consider liye udhaaharan cataphylls, kaante, and cotyledons ).
Conversely, many structures of non-vascular plants, or bhi of kuch lichens, jisase hai nahin paudhe at sab ( in the bhav of hone sadasyon of the kingdom plantae ), do look and function much like leaves.
Furthermore, several structures found in vascular paudhe dekh jaise pattey lakin hai nahin darasal pattey ; ve differ isse pattey in unke structures and origins.
Examples include phyllodes, cladodes, or phylloclades.

Production continued at the Roach studio until 1938, jab the shrenee thi bechi to mgm, jo tab jari producing the comedies until 1944.
The Our Gang series includes a kul of 220 shorts or ek visheshta filmi, saamaanya spanky, featuring over forty-one child actors.

Four tihaai logo
The Four Thirds system is a standard created by Olympus and Kodak for digital single-lens reflex camera ( dslr ) dizine or development. < sandarbh name='dpreview.com 2001-02-13 ' >
The system provides a standard that, with digital camere or lenses uplabdhiyaan isse anek nirmaataaon, allows liye the interchange of lenses or laashen isse alag nirmaataaon.
seems to cover the maanak.
Proponents describe it as an open standard, lakin companiyaan may tabhi upyog it antargat a non-disclosure agreement.
Unlike older SLR systems, Four Thirds rai maharoom designed isse the maidan up to be entirely digital.
Many lenses hai extensively computerized, to the point ki Olympus offers firmware updates for many of them.
Lens design has been tailored to the aavashyaktaayen of digital sensor, sabase notably through telecentric designs.
The size of the sensor is significantly choti than liye sabase dslrs or is implies ki lenses, visheshkar telephoto lenses, can be smaller.
For example, a chaar tihaai lens saath a 300 mm focal lambaai hota cover parichay the vahi kone of drishy as a 600 mm focal length lens for the 35 mm film standard, and is correspondingly more compact.
Thus, the Four Thirds System has crop factor ( focal length multiplier ) of about 2, or jabaki is enables longer focal lambaai liye vrihad aavardhan, it karata n't sahaayta the manufacture of chaudee kone lenses.
The image sensor format, generally intermediat between those of larger slrs or choti compact camere, generally detaa str of laagat, pradarshan or convenience intermediate between those two classes.
HVAC systems use ventilation air ducts santhaapit throughout a bhawan to supplai conditioned air to a room through outlet vents, pukaara diffusers ; and ducts to remove air through return-air grilles.
hvac ( heating, ventilation, or air condishning ) is the technology of indoor and automotive environmental comfort.
HVAC system design is a subdiscipline of mechanical engineering, based on the siddhanth of ooshmaagatiki, drav yantriki, or ooshmaa transfer.
Refrigeration is sometimes added to the field 's abbreviation as hvac & r or hvacr, or ventilating is dropped as in hacr ( aise as the namakan of hacr-rated circuit brakers ).
HVAC is important in the design of medium to vishaal audyogic or daftar imaaraten aise as skyscrapers or in samudri environments aise as equarium, jahaan surakshit or swasth bhawan sharten hai regulated with respect to temperature and humidity, using fresh air from outdoors.
Ventilation on the downdraught pranali, by impulsion, or the 'plenum ' principle, applied to schoolrooms ( 1899 )
Heating, ventilating, and air conditioning is based on inventions and discoveries bana by nicholay lvov, maaikel farade, wilis vaahak, reuben trane, james jul, wiliam Rankine, Sadi Carnot, and many others.
The invention of the components of HVAC systems went hand-in-hand with the industrial kranti, or nai vidhi of modernization, ucchtar dakshata, or system control are constantly introduced by companies and inventors worldwide.
The three central functions of heating, ventilating, or air-conditioning hai interrelated, visheshkar saath the need to provide thermal sukun or sweekaarya andar air visheshta bheetar reasonable installation, operation, and maintenance costs.
HVAC systems can provide ventilation, reduce air ghuspaith, and maintain pressure relationships between spaces.
The means of air delivery or hataanaa isse spaces is gyaat as room air distribution.
The starting point in carrying out an estimate both for kooling or heating depends on the exterior jalwaayu or aantarik nirdisht sharten.
However before taking up the heat load gananaa, it is jaruri to dhundhen bhais air aavashyaktaayen liye prayek kshetrafal in vivaran, as pressurization is an mahatvapurn consideration.
In aadhunik imaaraten the dizine, sansthapana, or control pranaaliyon of ye functions are integrated into one or more HVAC systems.
For very small buildings, thekedaaron saamanytah kshamta ejeeniyar or chune HVAC systems and equipment.
For larger buildings, building services designers and engineers, such as mechanical, architectural, or bhawan sevaayen ejiniers analyze, dizine, or bataaen the hvac pranaaliyon, or specialty mechanical contractors fabricate and commission them.
Building permits and code-compliance inspections of the sansthapana hai saamanytah jaruri liye sab aakaar of imaaraten.
The hvac udyog is a vishwavyaapee enterprize, saath bhoomikaaye sahit aaparishan or mentanence, pranali dizine or nirmaan, equipment manufacturing and sales, and in education and research.
The HVAC industry was historically regulated by the nirmaataaon of hvac upkaran, lakin regulating or maanakon sanghathan aise as hardi, ashrae, smacna, asisie, vardi mechanical code, antarrashtriya mechanical code, or AMCA have been established to support the industry and encourage high standards and achievement.
Royal Navy Commander James Bond, cmg, rnvr, is a fictional akshar nirmit by angrejon patrkaar and novelist Ian Fleming in 1953.
He is the samarthak of the james bandha shrenee of novels, films, comics and video games.
Fleming wrote twelve Bond novels and two choti story sangrahan pehle uske maut, haalanki the pichhlaa do books— the man saath the sunahari gan or octopussy or the jeena daylights —were published posthumously.
The Bond character is a Secret Service agent, code kramank 007, residing in landan lakin kriyasheel internationally.
Bond was a composite character who was based on a number of commandos whom Fleming knew during his service in the Naval Intelligence Division during World War II, to whom fleming added uske apana style or a kramank of uske apana tastes ; bandha 's naam thi appropriated isse amareeki ornithologist James Bond.
Bond has a number of character traits jisase chalaaen throughout the kitabe, sahit an enjoyment of cars, a love of food and drink, and an average intake of sixty custom-made cigarettes a day.
Since Fleming 's death in 1964, vahin have maharoom anya authorised lekhak of bandha saamagree, sahit jon gardenar, jo likhaa chaudaa novels and two novelizations and Raymond Benson, who wrote six novels, three novelizations and three short stories.
There have also been three authors who likhaa ek kitaab prayek, kingsle amis ( likhane as robert markham ), sebastian faulks or jeffery Deaver.
Additionally a series of novels aadhaarit on bandha 's youth— yang bandha —was likhaa by charlie higson.
As spin-offs isse the saahitiyik works, vahin thi a television anukulan of the first novel, Casino Royale, in which Bond was played as an American agent.
A comic strip shrenee bhi bhaaga in the rose Express newspaper.
There have bhi maharoom twenty-five bandha films ; saat abhinaytaon have played Bond in these films.
`` prakruti ladke '' is a song by eden ahbez, published in 1947.

Louisiana ( or ;, ; Louisiana Creole : Léta de la Lwizyàn ) is a rajya stith in the dakshini pradesh of the sanyukt rajya of america.
louisiana is the 31st sabase extensive or the 25th sabase populous of the 50 United States.
Its capital is Baton rouge or largest nagar is nai orlions.
Louisiana is the only state in the U.S. saath rajnatik subdivisions termed parishes, jisase hai local sarkari 's equivalent to counties.
The largest mohalla by janasankhyikee is east baton rouge mohalla, or the largest by land area is Cameron Parish.
Much of the state 's lands were formed from sediment dhoyaa bas the mississippi nadi, leaving vishaal deltas and vast areas of coastal marsh and swamp.
These contain a samrudh dakshini biota ; theth udhaaharan shaamil birds such as ibis and egrets.
There are also many species of ped mendhak, or machhlee aise as sturgeon and paddlefish.
In more elevated areas, aag is a prakritik prakram in the landscape, or rai utpaadit extensive kshetron of longleaf pine forest and wet savannas.
These support an exceptional vishaal kramank of sanyantr prajati, sahit anek prajati of orchids and carnivorous plants.
Some Louisiana urban environments have a multicultural, multilingual heritage, hone so strongly bahekaave by an jisamen of 18th-century french, spani, deshi amareeki ( bhartiya ) or African cultures that they are considered to be somewhat exceptional in the U.S.
Before the amareeki khariden of the territory, the vartmaan louisiana rajya tha maharoom both a Spanish and French colony.
In addition, the pattern of development included importing numerous africa slave in the 18th sadi, saath anek isse the vahi pradesh of west africa, yun concentrating their culture.
In the post-Civil War environment, Anglo-Americans increased the pressure for Anglicization, or in 1915, angrezi thi bana the tabhi aadhikarik bhashaa of the state.
Women 's rights are the rights and entitlements claimed liye mahilaon or ladakiyon of anek samaajon worldwide.
In some sthaan ye adhikaron hai institutionalized or samarthit by vidhi, local custom, or aacharan, whereas in others they may be ignored or suppressed.
They differ from broader notions of human rights through claims of an inherent aitihaasik or paramparaagat purvaagrah viruddh the kasarat of adhikaron by mahilaon or ladakiyon in favour of men and boys.
Issues commonly associated with dharanaen of mahilaon 's adhikaron shaamil, haalanki hai nahin simit to, the sahi : to bodily akhandta or swaittata ; to vote ( suffrage ) ; to tham public daftar ; to kaary ; to mela mazdooree or baraabar adaa ; to apana property ; to shiksha ; to serve in the military or be conscripted ; to enter into legal contracts ; and to have marital, parental and religious rights.
the kanoon of vigyaan or vaigyanik kanoon hai kathan ki describe, bhavishyavaanee, or shaayad bataaiye why, a range of phenomena behave as they appear to in nature.
The term `` law '' has diverse usage in many cases : approximate, accurate, broad or simit theories, in sab prakritik vaigyanik disciplines ( bhautikee, rasayan, jeevigyaan, bhuvigyaan, khagolashastra etc. ).
An analogous pad liye a vaigyanik law is a principle.
vaigyanik vidhitis:
summarize a large collection of facts sankalpit by prayog into a single statement,
can usually be formulated mathematically as one or several statements or equation, or at least stated in a single sentence, so that it can be used to predict the nishkarsh of an prayog, die the aarambhik, boundary, or anya shaareerik sharten of the prakriyaaon jisase lo place,
hai strongly samarthit by anubhavjanya pramaan - ve hai vaigyanik gyaan ki prayog have repeatedly verified ( and never falsified ).
Their sateekta karata nahin badalen jab nai theories hai worked out, lakin balki the paimaana of anuprayog, chunki the equation ( if any ) representing the law does not change.
As with other scientific knowledge, ve do nahin have nirpeksh certainty jaise ganitiya theorems or pahchaan, or it is always possible for a law to be overturned by future observations.
are often quoted as a aadharbhoot controlling influence balki than a varnan of observed facts.
I.e. `` the kanoon of gati aavashyaktaa that ''
Laws differ from hypotheses and postulates, jisase hai prastaavit dauraan the vaigyanik prakram pehle or dauraan validation by experiment and observation.
These are not laws since they have nahin maharoom satyapit to the vahi oopaadhi or may nahin be fear saamaanya, haalanki ve may sise to the formulation of laws.
A law is a adhik solidified or aupchaarik bayaan, asut isse doharaaya experiment.
Although the concepts of a law or principle in nature is borderline to philosophy, and presents the depth to which ganit can describe prakruti, vaigyanik kanoon hai mana isse a vaigyanik pariprekshya or follow the vaigyanik vidhi ; ve `` serve unke purpose '' balki than `` questioning reality '' ( philosophical ) or `` statements of logical absolution '' ( mathematical ).
For udhaaharan, whether a vidhi `` refers to vaastaviktaa '' is a philosophical issue, rather than scientific.
Fundamentally, all scientific laws follow isse bhautikee, kanoon jisase occur in anya sciences ultimately follow isse shaareerik laws.
Often, from mathematically aadharbhoot viewpoints, saarvbhaumik sthiraank emerge isse vaigyanik laws.
