The 2010 NBA Finals was the National basket sangh ( enbie ) championships series for the 2009–10 season.
The best-of-seven playoff thi lade between the los angeles lekars, champions of the pashchimi sammelan or defending enbie champions, and the Boston Celtics, champions of the Eastern Conference.
The Lakers parajeet the celtics, chaar khel to teen, to win the franchise 's 16th NBA championship.
The 64th sanskaran of the championships shrenee thi nibhaai between june 3 or june 17, was broadcast on ABC, and was watched by an average of 18.1 million people.
The celtics arjeet unke berth into the playoffs by jeetna the Atlantic Division.
The lekars jiti the prashanth prabhag to earn their berth.
The Celtics reached the NBA Finals by defeating the miami ooshmaa in the best-of-seven purvi sammelan pehla golakaar, the cleveland cavaliers in the best-of-seven purvi sammelan semifinals, and defending Eastern conference champion Orlando Magic in the best-of-seven Eastern Conference Finals.
The Lakers reached the NBA Finals by defeating the Oklahoma City Thunder in the best-of-seven pashchimi sammelan pehla golakaar, the uta jaiz in the best-of-seven pashchimi sammelan semifinals, or the phinics Suns in the best-of-seven Western Conference Finals.
The NBA Finals were anusuchit in the pramukh lig besabaal sansar shrenee 2–3–2 saat khel swaroop, saath the lekars possessing home-court advantage as a reward for finishing with better regular season record than the Celtics.
Repeated baskets from starters Kobe Bryant, Pau Gasol, or ron artest brought the lekars band to vijay in khel 1.
A record breaking pradarshan isse re alan 's aath three-point baskets ensured the Celtics a Game 2 triumph.
Derek Fisher ’s 11 ank in the chauthi quarter helped the lekars win Game 3.
The Celtics won Game 4 ; it did n't hurt that they netted an excellent pradarshan in baskets by the team’s reserves, jabaki paul piers led the toli to a khel 5 jeet saath 27 ank on 57 % shooting isse the floor.
The Lakers avoided vilopan by jeetna a nirnaayak khel 6 saath 24 ank contributed by their bench.
Although they trailed the Celtics by 13 points early in the third quarter, the Lakers rallied and jiti unke duusari lagaataar championships by lene over an romaanchak khel 7 aided by let yogadan on thokar by pau gasol and Artest and rebounding.
Bryant was named Most Valuable khilaadi of the final liye uske duusari lagaataar trophy.
This was the first enbie final to go the puraa saat khel chunki or tabhi the chauthi chunki the NBA Finals returned to a 2–3–2 format in.
The laker matadhikaar rai 16 enbie championships ( paanch in miniapolis, 11 in los angeles ) trailing the Celtics ' seventeen championships.
The NBA Finals used the `` World Series '' Format in 1949 miniapolis lekars parajeet the washington capitols 4 khel to 2 ; in 1953 miniapolis parajeet the nai York Knicks 4 games to 1 ; in 1954 Minneapolis defeated the Syracuse Nationals 4 games to 3 ; and in 1955 Syracuse Nationals defeated the Fort Wayne Pistons 4 games to 3.
The NBA would return to the 2–2–1–1–1 National hockey lig saat khel shrenee swaroop jabatak 1985.
Black pepper ( Piper nigrum ) is a flowering vine in the parivaar piperaceae, cultivated liye iske fal, jisase is praayah sukhi or prayukt as a masala and seasoning.
The fruit, known as a peppercorn when dried, is approximately in diameter, dark red jab fully vayask, or, jaise sab drupes, contains a single beej.
Peppercorns, and the ground pepper derived from them, may be varnit bas as pepper, or adhik precisely as blike pepper ( pakaaya or sukhi unripe fal ), green pepper ( dried unripe fruit ) and white pepper ( dried ripe seeds ).
Black pepper is native to south India, and is extensively cultivated vahin or elsewhere in teevr regions.
Currently Vietnam is the world 's largest nirmaataa or niryaatak of pepper, producing 34 % of the sansar 's pyper nigrum crop as of 2008.
Dried maidan pepper rai maharoom prayukt chunki pracheenta liye dono its flavour and as a medicine.
Black pepper is the sansar 's sabase traded masala.
It is one of the most common masaale added to europea bhojan or iske vanshajon.
The spiciness of black pepper is due to the chemical piperine, not to be confused with the capsaicin ki detaa maansal mirch theirs.
It is in the aadhunik sansar, praayah yugma with salt.
In cardiovascular physiology, ejection bhinn ( ef ) represents the aaytani bhinn of rakt uttejit out of the ventricle ( heart ) with each heart beat or cardiac cycle.
It can be applied to either the right ventricle which ejects via the pulmonary valve into the pulmonary parisancharan or the baayein ventricle jisase ejects via the aortic valve into the pranaligat circulation.
Imaging of the physiology of the mammalian dil is the art ki allows sarthak ganitiya expression defining EF.
Noninvasive cardiac imaging has become a worldwide utility enabling padhai of hriday pradarshan reproducibly or inexpensively.
Simplified, Ejection fraction is a ganitiya utpaada anumat by hriday imaging.
As a mathematical term, ejection bhinn is an ekstansion of the kaary of adalph Fick in cardiac output.
Dedicated technology such as Echocardiography, Computed Tomography, Magnetic Resonance Imaging and MUGA scanning have definitively anumat clinically praasangik ganit regarding ischemia, janmajaat dil beemaari or dil vifaltaa.
The prosecutor is the chief legal representative of the prosecution in deshon saath either the aam vidhi adversarial pranali, or the civil law inquisitorial system.

Abū al-Qāsim muḥammad ebn ʿabd allāh ebn ʿabd al-muṭṭalib ebn hāshim ( ) ( circa| 570 – circa| 8 june 632 ), bhi transliterated as mohammad ( ), was a religious, political, and military leader from Mecca who unified Arabia into a single religious polity under Islam.
He is believed by musalmaan or bahá'ís to be a messanger and prophet of God.
Muhammad is lagbhag universally mana by musalmaan as the pichhlaa nabi bheja by God for mankind.
Non-Muslims regard mohammad as the sansthaapak of islam.
musalmaan consider use to be the restorer of an anchhue asli monotheistic faith of Adam, Noah, Abraham, Moses, Jesus, and other prophets.
Born in about 570 CE in the Arabian city of Mecca, he was anaath at an jaldi aayu or brought up antargat the parvaah of uske taaoo Abu Talib.
He later worked zyaadaatar as a vyapaaree, as khub as a shepherd, and was first married by age 25.
Being in the habit of periodically retreating to a cave in the surrounding kyu liye anek nits of seclusion or dua, he baad reported ki it thi vahin, at aayu 40, ki he received his first revelation from God.
Three years after this event mohammad prarambh upadesh ye khulaase saream, proclaiming ki `` parameshwar is ek ``, ki puraa `` aatmasamarpan '' to Him ( lit.
islām ) is the tabhi rasta ( dīn ) sweekaarya to parameshwar, or ki he khud thi a nabi or messanger of parameshwar, in the same vein as other Islamic prophets.
Muhammad gained few followers early on, and thi mili saath dushmani isse kuch meccan janajatiyon ; he or uske anusarankarta yahood treated harshly.
To escape persecution, mohammad bheja kuch of uske anusarankarta to abisinia pehle he or uske anusarankarta in Mecca migrated to Medina ( then known as Yathrib ) in the year 622.
This event, the Hijra, marks the shuruuaat of the islamic panchang, jisase is also known as the Hijri Calendar.
In madina, mohammad sanyukt the janajatiyon antargat the Constitution of Medina.
After eight years of fighting with the Meccan tribes, his anusarankarta, jo by tab tha grown to 10,000, took control of makka in the largely shantipurna Conquest of Mecca.
He destroyed the pagan murtiyon in the nagar or tab bheja uske anusarankarta out to destroy all of the remaining pagan temples in Eastern Arabia.
In 632, a few maheene baad returning to madina isse the vidaai yatraaen, Muhammad fell ill and died.
By the time of his death, most of the Arabian Peninsula had converted to islam, or he tha sanyukt arab into a single muslim dharmik polity.
The khulaase ( or ayah, lit.
`` Signs [ of parameshwar ] '' ) — jisase mohammad reported receiving jabatak uske maut – rup the aayatein of the quran, regarded by Muslims as the `` Word of God '' and around which the religion is based.
Besides the Quran, mohammad 's jivan ( sira ) or paramparaon ( sunnat ) hai bhi upheld by musalmaan as the sources of sharia law.
They discuss mohammad or anya nabiyon of islam saath reverence, adding the phrase peace be upon him whenever their names are mentioned.
jabaki conceptions of mohammad in madhyakaalin christendom or premodern times yahood largely rinatmak, appraisals in modern history have been far less so.
The Great kitabe ( duusari sanskaran )
great kitabe of the pashchimi sansar is a shrenee of kitabe originally prakashit in the sanyukt States in 1952 by Encyclopædia Britannica Inc. to present the Great Books in a single package of 54 volumes.
The series is now in iske duusari sanskaran or contains 60 volumes.
The original editors of the series chose three criteria for inclusion : a book must be relevant to samakaleen mudde, or nahin tabhi mahatvapurn in iske aitihaasik context ; it jarur badla rereading ; or it jarur be a bhaag of `` the great vaartalap parichay the great ideas, '' relevant to at least 25 of the 102 great ideas identified by the editors.
Books yahood nahin chuni on the aadhaar of jaateey or saanskrithik inclusiveness, aitihaasik influence, or the editors ' agreement with the views expressed.

Allmusic calls the latter `` among [ Clapton 's ] most enduringly lokapriy hits '' or tip ki `` bhi liye an kalakaar jaise clapton saath a vishaal deh of high-quality work, 'Cocaine ' ranks among his best. ''

coca '' thi ek of anek of cale 's geeton ankit by clapton, sahit `` After Midnight `` and `` Travelin ' Light ''.
The attack on Pearl Harbor ( called Hawaii Operation or Operation AI by the Japanese Imperial saamaanya mukhyalay ( aaparishan z in niyojan ) or the battle of parl harbar ) thi a aashcharya sainya strike conducted by the imperial japani navy viruddh the sanyukt rajya naval aadhaar at parl harbar, hawaii, on the morning of disambar 7, 1941 ( December 8 in Japan ).
From the standpoint of the defenders, the akraman commenced at 7:48 a.m. hawaii Time.
The attack was intended as a preventive action in anukram to rakhana the u.S. prashanth bede isse dakhal saath sainya kriyaayein the samrajya of japani thi niyojan in southeast asia viruddh videshi territories of the sanyukt kingdom, the Netherlands, and the United States.
The base was attacked by 353 Japanese senaanee, bamavarshak or torpedo planes in do lehren, launched from six aircraft carriers.
All eight U.S. navy battleships yahood kshatigrast, saath chaar hone sunk.
Two of these were later raised, and with the baaki chaar repaired, chah battleships laute to service later in the war.
The Japanese also sank or kshatigrast teen cruisers, teen destroyers, an anti-aircraft prashikshan ship, and one minelayer.
188 U.S. aircraft were nasht ; 2,402 america yahood maare or 1,282 wounded.
Important base installations such as the power station, shipyard, maintenance, and fuel and torpedo storage facilities, as well as the pandubbi pier or mukhyalay bhawan ( bhi ghar of the pragna khand ) yahood nahin attacked.
japani nuksaan yahood lite : 29 vayuyan or paanch midget submarines khoyaa, and 65 servicemen killed or wounded.
One japani navik thi captured.
The attack came as a profound shock to the American logon or led sidhe to the amareeki pravishti into sansar yuddh ii in dono the Pacific and European theaters.
The following din ( disambar 8 ), the sanyukt rajya ghoshit yuddh on Japan.
Domestic support for non-interventionism, jisase tha maharoom damdaar, disappeared.
clandestine support of britain ( liye udhaaharan the Neutrality Patrol ) was replaced by active alliance.
subsequent parichaalan by the u.S. prompted germany or italy to ghoshit yuddh on the u.S. on December 11, which was reciprocated by the U.S. the same day.
There were numerous historical precedents liye unannounced sainya action by Japan.
however, the kami of koi aupchaarik chetavanee, visheshkar jabaki negotiations yahood still jaahir jari, led adhyaksh Franklin D. Roosevelt to proclaim December 7, 1941, `` a date which will live in infamy ``.

An udhaaharan of a heraclius mule
In numismatics, a mule is a coin or medal minted with obverse or reverse dizin nahin saamanytah dekhi on the vahi tukdaa.
These can be jaanboojhkar or utpaadit by error.
This type of error is atyadhik sought baad, or udhaaharan can laane steep prices from collectors.
The earliest mules hai mila among pracheen unani and Roman coins.
Opinion is divided between those who think that ve hai aakasmik, the parinaam of an galat sangyojan of a nai die saath ek ki tha officially maharoom withdrawn isse upyog, or the kaary of coiners working saath marataa churaayaa isse an aadhikarik mint, perhaps at a time when one of them should have been destroyed.
The name derives from the mule, the sankar aulad of a ghoda or a gadhaa, due to aise a sikaa having do pahalu intended liye alag sikke, much as a mule has parents of two different species.
is pej dastauez the tornadoes and tornado outbreaks of 2010.
the bahumat of tornadoes rup in the u.S., lakin ve can occur almost anywhere under the right conditions.
A lesser number occur outside the U.S., most notably in parts of neighboring southern Canada dauraan the uttari golardh 's garmiyaan ritu, lakin hai bhi known in South America, Europe, Asia, and Australia.
There were 1,531 tornadoes reported in the sanyukt rajya in 2010 ( of jisase at tanik 1,266 yahood pushti ), with 45 confirmed fatalities.
Elsewhere in the world, 11 people were maare in tornadoes, chah in argentina, teen in the bahama, ek in Bangladesh, and one in Germany.
The year was near average for tornadoes despite an atyadhik shant jaldi vasant kaal, however aise badla baad a vishaal upswing starting in let april or a vyast let spring and summer period.
The autumn maheene yahood thodaa above average.
A lymphocyte is a type of shwet rakt koshika in the vertebrate immune system.
antargat the sookshmdarshi, lymphocytes can be vibhajit into vishaal lymphocytes and small lymphocytes.
Large granular lymphocytes shaamil prakritik kaatil cells ( NK cells ).
Small lymphocytes consist of t koshikaayen or B cells.
Windows PowerShell is microsoft 's kaary swachaalan fremawork, consisting of a command-line shell or sambhddha scripting language built on.NET Framework.
PowerShell provides full access to COM and WMI, enabling prashaskon to perform prashasnic kaary on dono local and remote Windows systems.
In PowerShell, administrative tasks are generally performed by cmdlets ( sunaaya command-lets ), jisase hai specialized.neT varg implementing a particular operation.
Sets of cmdlets may be combined together in script, executables ( jisase hai staneylon anuprayog ), or by instantiating regular.NET classes ( or WMI/COM Objects ).
These work by accessing aankada in alag aankada stores, jaise the filesystem or registry, jisase hai made available to the PowerShell runtime via Windows PowerShell providers.
Windows powershell bhi provides a hosting api saath jisase the Windows PowerShell runtime can be embedded inside other applications.
These applications can then upyog khidkiyaan powershell kaaryakshmata to implement nishchit parichaalan, sahit those ujagar via the aalekhiy interface.
This capability has been used by microsoft exange sarwar 2007 to expose iske prabandhan kaaryakshmata as powershell cmdlets or pradaataaon or implement the aalekhiy prabandhan tools as PowerShell hosts which invoke the necessary cmdlets.
Other Microsoft applications including microsoft escuel sarwar 2008 bhi expose unke prabandhan interfes via PowerShell cmdlets.
With PowerShell, aalekhiy interface-based prabandhan anuprayog on khidkiyaan hai paratdaar on top of Windows PowerShell.
A PowerShell scripting interfes liye khidkiyaan utpaada is mandated by the Common Engineering Criteria.
Windows PowerShell includes iske apana extensive, console-based sahaayta, samaan to man prishthon in unics shell, via the Get-Help cmdlet.

A story arc is an extended or continuing storyline in episodic storytelling media aise as television, comic kitabe, comic strips, boardgames, video games, and in some cases, films.
On a television program, for example, the story hota unfold over anek apisod.
In television, the upyog of the story chaap is much adhik aam in dramas than in comedies, especially in soap operas.
Webcomics are more likely to use story arcs than samachaarpatr comics, as sabase web comics have pathneey abhilekh online ki a newcomer to the strip can padhaa in anukram to samajhe kayaa is going on.
Although story arcs have existed for decades, the term `` story arc '' was coined in 1988 in sambandh to the television shrenee wiseguy, or thi jaldi adapted liye anya upyog.
Many American comic book shrenee hai abhi likhaa in chaar or six-issue arcs, bheetar a continuing series.
choti story arcs hai easier to package as vyapaar paperbacks liye punarvikray, or adhik accessible to the casual reader than the never-ending continuity that once characterised comics.
Black Friday is the day following thankgiving din in the sanyukt rajya, praayah regarded as the shuruuaat of the Christmas shopping season.
In recent years, most major retailor have kholi atyadhik jaldi or offered promotional bikri to laat band the avkaash kharidari ritu, samaan to Boxing Day sales in many Commonwealth Nations.
Black Friday is not an official public avkaash as aise, lakin anek non-retail karmchaaree or skulon have dono thankgiving or the din baad band, followed by a weekend, thereby increasing the number of potential shoppers.
It has routinely been the busiest shopping day of the year chunki 2005, haalanki news reports, jisase at ki samay yahood inaccurate, have varnit it as the vyastatam kharidari din of the year for a much longer period of time.
The din 's naam originated in philadelphia, jahaan it originally thi prayukt to describe the heavy and disruptive pedestrian and vehicle traffic which would occur on the day after Thanksgiving.
Use of the term started before 1961 and began to dekhie broader upyog baahar philadelphia around 1975.
baad an vaikalpik spashtikaran began to be offered : ki `` blike shuukravaar '' indicates the point at which retailers begin to turn a profit, or are `` ''.
For anek saalo, it thi aam liye retailor to kholen at 6:00 a.m., but in the late 2000s many had crept to 5:00 or even 4:00.
This was liya to a nai charam in 2011, jab anek retailor ( sahit nishaanaa, kohl 's, macy 's, Best Buy, and Bealls ) opened at midnight for the first time.
In 2012, Walmart and several other retailers announced that they hota kholen sabase of unke stores at 8:00 p.m. on thankgiving din ( magar in rajya jahaan kholane on thankgiving is nishiddh due to blue kanoon, aise as masachusets jahaan ve still kholi around midnight ), prompting calls for a walkout among some workers.
Black shuukravaar kharidari is gyaat liye attracting aakraamak crowds, saath salanaa reports of assaults, shootings, and throngs of people trampling on other shoppers in an attempt to get the best deal on a product before supplies run out.

Net 10, Net 15, Net 30 and Net 60 ( bhi jaal 10 dinon, et al ) hai form of vyapaar credit jisase bataaen ki the jaal raashi ( the kul bakaayaa on the chaalaan ) is apekshit to be sashulk in full and received by the seller within 10, 15, 30 or 60 days after the goods are dispatched or service is completed.
Net 30 or Net 60 terms are often coupled saath a credit liye jaldi bhugtan.
The word net in this sense arthath `` kul baad sab discounts. ''
It originally derives isse the latin nitere ( to chamak ) or nitidus ( suruchipurna, trim ), or more recently from the French net ( sharp, neat, clean ).

the angrejon west indies yahood the islands in or around the caribbean ki were part of the British Empire.
In 1912, the British West Indies were divided into aath colonies : the bahama, barbados, angrejon guiana, angrejon honduras, jamaica ( saath iske dependencies the Turks and Caicos Islands and the Cayman Islands ), Trinidad and Tobago, the Windward Islands and the Leeward Islands.
Between 1958 and 1962, all of the island territories magar the angrejon virgin islands, the bahama, angrejon honduras or angrejon Guiana were organised into the West Indies Federation.
It was hoped that the Federation would become independent as a single nation, but it tha simit shaktiyaan, anek vyaavhaarik samasyaayein, or a kami of lokapriy support.
Consequently, the west indies sangh was dissolved.
Most of the territories, including all the larger ones, are now independent as separate countries, with membership to anek antarrashtriya forums aise as the sanghathan of amareeki rajya, the sangh of caribbean rajya, the sansar vyapaar sanghathan, the United Nations, the Caribbean Community, the Commonwealth of Nations and the Caribbean Development Bank among others.
The shesh hai angrejon videshi territories.
All the former nations of the British West indies, magar the rashtramandal of dominican, guyana or trinidad or tobago, hai rashtramandal realms.
The term is still prayukt liye angrejon videshi territories in the caribbean, such as the Cayman Islands.

udghaatan din 2009 on the west kadam of the U.S. Capitol.
President George W. Bush and First Lady laura bush sise the inaugural parade bas pencilvenia Avenue to the White House, 2005
The inauguration of the president of the sanyukt rajya is a ceremonial event ankan the shuruyaat of a nai four-year term of a president of the United States.
The day a presidential inauguration occurs is gyaat as `` udghaatan din '' or occurs on janvari 20 ( or 21st if the 20th is a Sunday ).
( Prior to the Twentieth Amendment, the date was March 4, the day of the year on jisase the samvidhan of the sanyukt rajya pehla took prabhaav in 1789 ; the pichhlaa udghaatan to lo place on the puraani tithi thi franklin D. Roosevelt 's first one on March 4, 1933. )
The most recent public adhyakshiya udghaatan rasm, the swearing in of adhyaksh baraak obama to begin his second four-year term in office, took place on Monday, January 21, 2013.
The only udghaatan tatv mandated by the sanyukt rajya samvidhan is ki the adhyaksh mek an shapath or pratigyaan pehle ki vyakti can `` daalen on the Execution '' of the office of the presidency.
However, over the years, various paramparaon have arisen ki have vistaarit the udghaatan isse a saral oath-taking ceremony to a day-long event, including parades, speeches, and balls.
From the presidency of Andrew Jackson through ki of jimmy carter, the praathmik udghaatan din rasm took place on the Capitol 's East Portico.
Since the 1981 inauguration of ronaald reagan, the rasm rai maharoom yojit at the Capitol 's West Front.
The inaugurations of William harvard taft in 1909 or reagan in 1985 yahood sthanantarit indoors at the capital due to cold weather.
The War of 1812 and World War II caused do inaugurations to be yojit at anya sthitiyaan in Washington, D.C.
jab george washington thi udghaatan, the shapath thi administered by robert livingston, chancelar of nai york rajya, in 1789, and by William Cushing, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court, in 1793.
Since Chief Justice Oliver Ellsworth swore in President John adams, no mukhya insaaf rai chhuti an udghaatan din.
When Inauguration Day has fallen on a sande, the mukhya insaaf rai administered the shapath to the adhyaksh on the sande privately or tab again the aglaa day publicly.
When a nai adhyaksh takes over mid-term due to the maut or istipha of a adhyaksh, the shapath of daftar is administered but formal, public inauguration events have not been held.

elizabeth cady stanton and her daughter, Harriot
elizabeth cady stanton ( navambar 12, 1815 – aktubar 26, 1902 ) thi an amareeki soshal activist, abolitionist, or agrani figure of the early women 's rights movement.
Her Declaration of Sentiments, presented at the pehla mahilaon 's adhikaron sammelan yojit in 1848 in seneca jalprapaat, nai york, is praayah credited saath initiating the pehla vyavasthit mahilaon 's adhikaron and women 's suffrage movements in the United States.
Before Stanton narrowed uske rajnatik fokas lagbhag exclusively to mahilaon 's adhikaron, wo thi an kriyasheel abolitionist together with her husband, Henry Brewster Stanton and cousin, Gerrit Smith.
Unlike many of those involved in the mahilaon 's adhikaron gati, stanton addressed vibhinn mudde pertaining to mahilaon pare voting rights.
uske chintaaen shaamil mahilaon 's parental or castady adhikaron, property adhikaron, niyukti or aay adhikaron, divorce, the economic health of the family, and birth control.
She thi bhi an outspoken samarthak of the 19th-century temperance movement.
After the American Civil War, Stanton 's commitment to female suffrage caused a schism in the mahilaon 's adhikaron gati jab wo, saath saath susaan B. anthoni, asweekrut to support dyodhi of the fourteenth or pandrahavin Amendments to the United States Constitution.
She opposed giving added legal suraksha or matdaan adhikaron to africa amareeki main while women, black and white, were denied those same rights.
Her position on this issue, together with her thoughts on organized Christianity and women 's issues beyond matdaan adhikaron, led to the gathan of do pruthak mahilaon 's adhikaron sanghathan ki yahood aakhirkaar rejoined, saath stanton as adhyaksh of the sanyukt sanghathan, lagbhag bees saalo baad uske brake isse the original women 's suffrage movement.
stanton died in 1902 having authored dono the stri 's bible or uske aatmakatha, saath saath anek aalekh or pamphlets concerning maadaa suffrage and women 's rights.

It has been pukaara `` the purna musical ''.

Ethnicity or ethnic group is a socially paribhaashit shrenee aadhaarit on aam samskruti or rashtriyata.
Ethnicity can, but does not have to, include common ancestry, rup, bhojan, dressing style, viraasat, itihaas, bhashaa or dialect, dharm, symbols, traditions, or other cultural factor.
Ethnic identity is constantly reinforced through aam visheshtaayen jisase niyat the samooh alaava isse anya samooh.
The 19.9 MW Gemasolar solar sanyantr in spain suvidhaayen 15 ghanton of bhandar and can supply power 24 hours a day.
Solar energy, radiant light or ooshmaa isse the surya, rai maharoom harnessed by insaano chunki pracheen times using a range of ever-evolving technologies.
Solar energy technologies include solar heating, solar photovoltaics, saura thermal vidyut, saura vaastukala or kritrim photosynthesis, jisase can mek considerable yogadan to solving some of the most urgent energy problems the world now faces.
Solar technologies are broadly characterized as either passive saura or kriyasheel saura depending on the rasta ve capchar, badalen or vitarit solar energy.
Active solar takneekon shaamil the upyog of photovoltaic panels or saura thermal collectors to harness the energy.
passive saura takneekon shaamil orienting a bhawan to the surya, selecting saamagree with favorable thermal mass or light dispersing properties, and designing spaces that naturally circulate air.
In 2011, the International Energy Agency said that `` the development of affordable, inexhaustible or saaf saura urja technologies hoga have vishaal longer-term benefits.
It will increase countries’ energy security through reliance on an indigenous, inexhaustible and mostly import-independent sansaadhan, badhayen sthirataa, reduce pradooshan, nimnatar the laagat of mitigating jalwaayu change, and keep fossil fuel prices lower than otherwise.
These laabh hai vaishvik.
Hence the additional laagat of the protsaahan liye jaldi deployment chahie be mana siikhnaa nivesh ; ve jarur be wisely spent and need to be widely shared ''.
The shastreey latin varnmaala or roman varnmaala viksit isse a pashchimi kismein of the unani varnmaala pukaara the cumaean varnmaala, which was adopted and modified by the Etruscans who ruled early Rome.
The Etruscan alphabet was in phere apanaaya or further parivardhit by the pracheen romans to write the Latin language.
During the Middle Ages, the Latin alphabet was adapted to Romance languages, direct descendants of latin, as khub as to celtic, germanic, baltic, or kuch slavi bhashaaen.
With the age of colonialism and Christian enjilwad, the latin script thi sprad videshi, or lagu to swadeshi amareeki, australian, Austronesian, Austroasiatic, and African languages.
More recently, linguists have bhi tended to prefer the latin script or the antarrashtriya dhvanyatmak varnmaala ( itself largely aadhaarit on latin script ) jab transcribing or creating written standards for non-European languages, such as the African reference alphabet.
The term Latin varnmaala may refer to either the varnmaala prayukt to likhen latin ( as varnit in is aalekh ), or anya alphabets aadhaarit on the latin script, jisase is the moulik niyat of akshar common to the various alphabets descended from the classical Latin one, such as the English alphabet.
ye latin-derived alphabets may choden akshar, jaise the rotokas varnmaala, or add new letters, like the Danish and Norwegian alphabet.
Letter shapes have badla over the sadiyaan, sahit the sristi liye madhyakaalin latin of nimnatar maamla form which did not exist in the Classical period.
The assassination of United States adhyaksh abraham lincoln took place on shubh shuukravaar, april 14, 1865, as the amareeki Civil War was drawing to a close.
The hatya occurred paanch dinon baad the commander of the confederate fouj of Northern Virginia, General Robert E. Lee, surrendered to Lieutenant General Ulysses S. Grant and the Union Army of the Potomac.
Lincoln was the first amareeki adhyaksh to be assassinated, haalanki an unsuccessful attempt tha maharoom bana on andrew jackson 30 saalo pehle in 1835.
The assassination was planned and carried out by the well-known stage karta jon wilkes booth, as bhaag of a larger conspiracy in a bid to revive the Confederate cause.
Booth 's co-conspirators were Lewis Powell and David Herold, who were abantit to maar sachiv of rajya wiliam H. seward, or george atzerodt who was to kill Vice President Andrew Johnson.
By simultaneously eliminating the sheersh teen logon in the prashasan, booth or uske co-conspirators hoped to sever the continuity of the United States government.
Lincoln was shot while watching the khel hamaari amareeki cousin saath uske bivi mariyam tod lincoln at ghat 's theatre in washington, D.C. on the night of April 14, 1865.
He died jaldi the aglaa morning.
The rest of the conspirators ' plot failed ; Powell only prabandhit to ghaav seward, jabaki atzerodt, johnson 's would-be hatyare, khoyaa uske tantrika and fled Washington.

Club level seating is a special khand of seating in aadhunik khel stadium.
The Club Level is usually located towards the madhya of the stage of seating bhaag, upar the nimnatar deck lakin neeche the upper deck.
They are usually right next to the Luxury Boxes, either sahi upar, sahi neeche, or sandwiched between two levels of Luxury Boxes.
Club Level seating is mana as ucchtar class than baithe anywhere else in the arina, but lower class compared to the Luxury Boxes.
naapsand the lakjri baks, sabase klbon str do not wrap entirely around the arena.
Some club levels stop at a certain point, giving way to an vistaar of the mezanin, jabaki anya de rasta to lower class Luxury Boxes ( such as `` Party Suites '' ).
A notable exception to is is emirate stadium in landan, jisase rai a puraa tear of klbon seating.
Club Levels allow prashansak anek str of entertainment.
Club Level seating is kholen to the tatv, as opposed to the entirely enclosed lakjri baks, jisase detaa more of an outdoors impression at roofless and open-roof stadiums and arenas.
Club Level seating is saamanytah kharida on a anubandh aadhaar to allow liye adhiktam laabh on the part of the stadium.
The klbon str provides prashansak saath khaas abhigam to an andar bhaag of the arena exclusive to fans with special tickets.
These areas are air conditioned and allow access to khaas restaraan, merchandise stand, or lounj kshetron of the stadium ki hai not otherwise available.
Concession stands and vendors on the Club str bhi praayah prastaav alag menu than in anya stands to give more of a special feel to the Club.
These areas are band band to the baaki of the stadium, or ve praayah can tabhi be pahunchaa through the exclusive, private club entrances.

it rai parichay 13 lakh wireless users.

Hospital Emergency Codes hai prayukt in aspataal vishwavyaapee to chetavanee staff to various emergencies.
The use of codes is intended to convey essential soochna jaldi or saath minimal galatfahami to staff, jabaki preventing tanaav or dehshat among visitors to the hospital.
These code may be posted on placards throughout the hospital, or printed on employee identification badges for ready reference.
Back of a hospital id baij prardashit vipatti code.
hospital apaat code may denote alag kaarykram at different hospitals, including nearby ones.
Because many physicians work at more than one facility, this may lead to bhram in emergencies, so vardi pranaaliyon have maharoom prastaavit.
The root of the eifel jalsetu, saath iske average slope.
The Eifel jalsetu thi ek of the longest aqueducts of the Roman Empire.
The aqueduct, constructed in AD 80, carried water kuch isse the hilly eifel pradesh of kayaa is abhi germany to the pracheen nagar of colonia claudia aara agrippinensium ( present-day colon ).
if the auxiliary spers to atirikt sroton are included, the length was.
The construction was almost entirely below ground, and the flow of the water was utpaadit entirely by gambheertha.
A few bridges, including ek up to in lambaai, yahood needed to pass over valleys.
Unlike kuch of the anya prasiddh roman aqueducts, the eifel jalsetu thi specifically designed to minimize the above-ground portion to protect it from damage and freezing.
In chemistry, a disulfide bond ( Br.E. disulphide bandha ) is a covalent bandha, praayah niklaa by the coupling of do thiol groups.
The linkage is bhi pukaara an SS-bond or disulfide bridge.
The overall connactivity is isliye R-S-S-R.
The shabdaawalee is widely prayukt in biochemistry.
In aupchaarik sharten, the conection is a persulfide, in saadrishy to iske congener, paroxide ( r-o-o-r ), lakin is shabdaawalee is obscure and is no longer used ( except in reference to R-S-S-H or H-S-S-H compounds ).
Formal chithran of disulfide bandha gathan as an oxidation.

Religion in the United Kingdom and in the countries that preceded it, rai maharoom varchasv, liye over 1,400 saalo, by vibhinn form of christianity.
According to some surveys, a majority of citizens still identify with Christianity, although regular girijaghar upasthiti rai gire dramatically chunki the madhya of the 20th sadi, or avrajan or janasankhyikee badalen have contributed to the vikaas of other faiths.
Religious affiliations of UK citizens are ankit by niyamit surveykshan, the chaar pramukh ones hone the uk janasankhyikee, the shramik force surveykshan, the angrejon soshal attitudes surveykshan or the European Social Survey.
According to the 2001 UK janasankhyikee, christianity is the pramukh dharm, followed by islam, hindutv, sikhism, judaism or buddhism in sharten of number of adherents.
This, and the relatively large number of individuals with nominal or no dharmik sambandhon rai led tikaakaron to variously describe the sanyukt kingdom as a multi-faith, secularised, or post-christian society.
The United Kingdom was formed by the sangh of previously swatantra deshon isse 1707, and consequently most of the largest religious groups do not have UK-wide organisational structures.
While some groups have separate structures liye the vyaktigat deshon of the sanyukt kingdom, anya may have a single dhaancha covering england or wales or Great Britain.
Similarly, due to the apekshaakrit haal sristi of uttari ireland in 1921, sabase pramukh dharmik samooh in uttari Ireland are organised on an all-Ireland basis.
The 1967 Newark riots were a major civil disturbance ki occurred in the nagar of neurk, New Jersey between July 12 and July 17, 1967.
The six days of rioting, looting, or vinaash baayein 26 murde or sainkadon injured.
In United States college athletics, redshirt is a vilamb or barkhaastagi of an khilaadi 's bhagidaari in anukram to lengthen uske or her period of eligibility.
Typically, a student 's athletic eligibility in a given sport is four seasons, a number niklaa isse the chaar saalo of academik varg ki hai saamanytah jaruri to obtain a snaatak 's oopaadhi at an amareeki college or university.
However, a student khilaadi may be offered the avasar to redshirt liye up to do saalo, jisase allows the khilaadi to sprad those four years of eligibility over five, or sometimes six years.
In a redshirt year, a student khilaadi may attend varg at the college or vishvavidhyalayon, abhyaas saath an athlettic toli, or dress for play but he or she may not compete during the game.
Using this mechanism, a student athlete has up to five academik saalo to upyog the chaar saalo of paatrata, yun banane a fifth-year varisht.
The term is used as a kriya, sangya, or kriyasheel.
liye udhaaharan, a coach may chune to redshirt a khilaadi jo is tab referred to as a redshirt freshman or simply a redshirt.
The opposite of this is a `` sachcha freshman. ''
World War I ( WWI ) was a global war centred in Europe that began on 28 july 1914 or lasted jabatak 11 navambar 1918.
It was predominantly pukaara the sansar yuddh or the great yuddh isse iske occurrence jabatak the prarambh of sansar yuddh ii in 1939, and the First World War or World War I thereafter.
It involved all the world 's great powers, which were assembled in two opposing alliances : the allies ( aadhaarit on the tripal entente of the sanyukt kingdom, frans or rus ) or the central shaktiyaan ( originally the tripal gathbandhan of germany, Austria-Hungary and Italy ; but, as Austria–Hungary had taken the offensive against the agreement, Italy did not enter into the war ).
These alliances were both reorganised and expanded as more nations entered the war : italy, japani or the sanyukt rajya joined the allies, or the osmani samrajya or bulgaria the central shaktiyaan.
Ultimately, more than 70 million sainya karmiyon, sahit 60 lakh europeans, yahood mobilised in one of the largest wars in history.
More than 9 million combatants were killed, largely because of technological advancements ki led to vishaal increases in the lethality of hathiyaar bagaiyr sambandhit sudhaar in protection or mobility.
It was the fifth- deadliest conflict in world history, subsequently paving the way for vibhinn rajnatik parivartan, aise as revolutions in anek of the raashtra shaamil.
One of the long-term causes of the war was the resurgence of imperialism in the videshi nitiyon of the great shaktiyaan of europea.
More tatkaal, the hatya of archduke franj ferdinand of austria, the vaaris to the singhaasana of austria-hungary, on 28 june 1914 by yugoslav rashtravaadi Gavrilo Princip in Sarajevo triggered a diplomatic crisis when Austria-Hungary subsequently delivered an ultimatum to the Kingdom of Serbia.
Several alliances formed over the pichhlaa dashakon yahood invoked.
Within weeks, the major powers were at war and, via unke colonies, the virodh jald sprad around the world.
On 28 July, the austro-hungarians fired the pehla goliyaan of the yuddh as preparation for the invasion of Serbia.
While the Russians mobilised, the Germans invaded neutral Belgium and dhvaj on the rasta to frans, providing a casus belli liye britain 's ghoshnaa of yuddh viruddh germany.
After the German march on Paris was brought to a halt—the so-called chamatkaar of the marne —the pashchimi saamne settled into a sthir battle of apgharshan saath a gart lakeer ki badla choti until 1917.
On the Eastern Front, the Russian army was successful against the austro-hungarians, lakin thi roka in iske akraman of east Prussia by the Germans.
In November the Ottoman Empire joined the yuddh, kholane up fronts in the kakeshas, mesopotamia and the Sinai.
Italy and bulgaria gai to yuddh in 1915 or romania in 1916.
In Russia, the tsar 's government collapsed in March 1917 and a subsequent kranti in navambar brought the russians to sharten saath the central shaktiyaan.
After a 1918 German offensive along the western front, the allies drove waapas the germans in a shrenee of kaamyaab offensives or amareeki forces began entering the trenches.
Germany, which had its own trubal saath krantikariyon, sahamat to an armistice on 11 navambar 1918.
The yuddh ended in vijay liye the Allies.
Events on the home fronts were as tumultuous as on the battle fronts, as the bhagidaar aajamaaya to mobilize unke janashakti or aarthik resources to fight a total war.
By the end of the war, four major imperial powers—the germany, roosi, austro-hungarian or osmani empires—ceased to exist.
the successor rajya of the purv do khoyaa a great raashi of territory, while the latter two were dismantled entirely.
The map of central europea thi redrawn into anek choti states.
The lig of raashtra thi formed in the aashaa of preventing another such conflict.
The European nationalism spawned by the war and the breakup of empires, the repercussions of germany 's shikast or samasyaayein saath the sandhi of versailles hai sahamat to be karkon contributing to sansar War II.
Map of countries that declared themselves to be socialist states antargat the marxist–leninist or maovadi paribhaasha - ki is to kah, `` communist rajya '' - between 1979 and 1983.
is kaal chihnit the mahanatam territorial extent of Communist states.
A communist state is a state where the means of utpaadan hai collectively swaamitv by the samaaj.
It has a rup of sarkari characterized by single-party niyam or dominant-party niyam of a communist party ( referred as taanaashaahee of the proletariat by iske proponents ) and a professed allegiance to a Leninist or Marxist–Leninist ideology as the guiding principle of the state.
Technically, `` communist rajya '' is a contradictio in terminis as a communist samaaj as paribhaashit by dono macrsvaadi and anarcho-communists is in principle stateless.
From this perspective, the term marxist-leninist rajya is more appropriate.
Historically, a `` communist state '' referred to a system where public ownership of all or most means of production by the Communist party -run state is deemed necessary to further the interests of the working class ; today, a communist rajya can bhi, liye udhaaharan, refer to samakaleen china or vietnam, jahaan a communist party-run rajya exists alongside a mixed economy.
According to Marxist–Leninists, the state is a tool in the hands of the sattadhari class, jisase in a samaajawaadee samaaj is the working class, so a samaajawaadee state is, according to Leninists, a state of the working class.
In practice, communist rajya do nahin darasal refer to themselves as such.
They do this not to disguise the fact that the ruling party is communist, lakin balki kuki ve do nahin consider themselves to be a communist society at present.
Instead, they constitutionally pahachaano themselves as samaajawaadee rajya or majdoor ' rajya.
The primary goal of ye rajya, jisase bhi explains unke aadhikarik naam, is to maargdarshika unke sambandhit deshon in the process of building socialism, ultimately leading to communism.
Communist states may have several legal political parties, lakin the communist party is praayah granted a khaas or prabal bhoomika in sarkari, praayah by statute or antargat the samvidhan.
Consequently, the sansthaanon of the rajya or of the communist party become intimately entwined, aise as in the vikaas of parallel institutions.
In the 20th sadi, sabase communist states adopted planned economies.
However, there were exceptions : the soviet sangh dauraan the 1920s or let 1980s or yugoslavia baad sansar yuddh ii anumat simit bazaar or a oopaadhi of kaaryakarta self-management, while China, Vietnam and Laos introduced far-reaching market reforms after the 1980s.
In the 21st sadi, china or vietnam have anumat a mishrit economy to develop.
The fundamental avadharanaon of communist rajya praayah diverge isse the asli socio-economic ideologies from which they develop.
As a result, many adherents of these vichaardhaaraon praayah oppose the rajnatik pranaaliyon commonly sambhddha saath these states.
For example, dissenting samyavaadiyon aise as trotskyists yahood praayah opposed to the communist rajya of the 20th sadi, claiming either ki ve tha nothing to do saath `` real '' samyavaadee or ki the vichaardhaara of aise rajya had reached a point of irrevocable corruption.
Michael fred felps ii ( born june 30, 1985 ) is a ritred amareeki tairaak or the sabase sajaa Olympian of all time, with a total of 22 medals.
Phelps also holds the all-time records for Olympic gold medals ( 18, double the second highest record holders ), olympic sunaharaa medals in vyaktigat kaarykram ( 11 ), or olympic medals in individual events for a male ( 13 ).
In winning eight gold medals at the 2008 Beijing Games, Phelps took the ricard liye the sabase first-place finishes at koi single olympic khel.
Five of those victories yahood in vyaktigat kaarykram, tying the single Games record.
In the 2012 garmiyaan olympic in landan, felps jiti chaar golds or do chaandi medals, bananaa use the sabase successful athlete of the Games for the third Olympics in a row.
Phelps is the long course world recordholder in the 100-meter butterfly, 200-meter butterfly and 400-meter vyaktigat medley as khub as the purv long course sansar recordholder in the 200-meter freestil or 200-meter vyaktigat medley.
He has jiti a kul of 71 medals in pramukh antarrashtriya long-course pratiyogita, 57 sunaharaa, 11 chaandi, and three bronze spanning the Olympics, the World, and the Pan Pacific Championships.
Phelps 's antarrashtriya sheershak or record-breaking pradarshan have arjeet use the sansar tairaak of the saal puraskaar saat times or amareeki tairaak of the Year Award nine times as well as the FINA Swimmer of the Year Award in 2012.
His unprecedented Olympic success in 2008 arjeet felps khel illustrated patrika 's Sportsman of the Year award.
After the 2008 Summer Olympics, Phelps started the Michael felps nyaas, jisase focuses on growing the khel of tairaaki or promoting healthier lifestyles.
He expects to do further work with his foundation after the 2012 Olympics, jisase he rai kaha hoga be uske pichhlaa.
Lenovo Group Limited ( ) is a Chinese multinational computer hardware and electronics company saath iske mukhyalay in beijing, china or morrisville, uttar carolina or iske panjikrut daftar in Hong Kong, China.
Its products include personal computers, tablett computer, mobile phone, workstations, sarwar, electronic bhandar devices, IT management software and smart televisions.
Lenovo is the world 's second-largest pc vikreta by 2012 ikai sales.
It bazaar the thinppad lakeer of kopi computer and the ThinkCentre line of desktops.
Lenovo has parichaalan in adhik than 60 deshon or sells its products in around 160 countries.
lenovo thi santhaapit in beijing in 1984 or incorporated in Hong Kong in 1988 under its previous name, Legend.
Lenovo is listed on the hong kong bhandar exange or is a constituent of the hang seng china-affiliated Corporations Index.
Slug is a common name liye an jaahir shell-less sthaliy gastropod mollusk.
The word `` slug '' is also often used as part of the common name of any gastropod mollusc ki rai no shell, rai a bahut ghataya shell, or rai tabhi a small internal shell.
( This is in contrast to the aam naam `` ghongha ``, jisase is lagu to gastropods ki have a nattejey shell ki is vishaal enough that the soft parts of the animal can retract fully into it. )
slugs maujuud on jameen or in the samudr, or vahin is bhi one genus of freshwater slugs, Acochlidium.
The unadorned word `` slug '' is however applied primarily to jameen slugs, whereas slugs isse the samudr or isse freshwater hai usually referred to as `` sea slugs `` and `` freshwater slugs ''.
Land gastropods with a shell that is not quite vestigial, lakin is too choti to retract into ( jaise anek in the parivaar urocyclidae ), are known as semislugs.
The vibhinn taxonomic pariwaron of slugs rup bhaag of anek kaaphi alag vikasvaadi lineages which also include snails.
Thus, for example, the various families of land slugs are not very closely sambandhit to ek another, despite a satahi samanta in the overall body form.
The shell-less condishan rai arisen anek times independently dauraan the vikasvaadi past, or yun the shrenee `` slug '' is emphatically a polyphyletic one.
Slugs, like all other gastropods, undergo torsion ( a 180° tedi of the internal organs ) during development.
Internally, slug anatomy clearly shows the prabhaav of is roteshan, lakin externally the laashen of jameen slugs appear to be more or less symmetrical, except for the positioning of the pneumostome, which is on one side of the animal, normally the right hand side.
The soft, slimy laashen of slugs hai prone to desiccation, so land-living slugs hai confined to nam environments and must retreat to damp hiding places when the weather is dry.
The subsequent soochna in is aalekh applies to land slugs.

Napoleon Bonaparte (, ; 15 August 1769 – 5 May 1821 ) was a French military and political netaa jo rose to prominence dauraan the latter charan of the french kranti or iske associated wars in Europe.
As Napoleon I, he thi samraat of the french isse 1804 to 1815.
His legal reform, the Napoleonic Code, has been a major influence on anek civil vidhi jurisdictions vishwavyaapee, lakin he is behtareen remembered liye uske bhoomika in the yudhon led viruddh frans by a shrenee of coalitions, the so-called napoleonic yudhon.
He established hegemony over most of continental europea or sought to sprad the aadarshon of the french kranti, jabaki consolidating an imperial samrajya which restored aspects of the deposed Ancien Régime.
Due to uske kamyaabi in ye yudhon, praayah viruddh numerically shreshth dushmano, he is generally regarded as ek of the mahanatam military commanders of all time, and his campaigns are studied at military academies worldwide.
nepolian thi born at ajaccio in corsica in a parivaar of pratishthit Italian ancestry which had settled Corsica in the 16th century.
He prashikshit as an topakhane adhikari in mainland France.
He rose to prominence under the French First Republic and led kaamyaab abhiyaan viruddh the pehla or duusari coalitions arrayed against France.
He led a kaamyaab akraman of the italvi prayadweep.
In 1799, he staged a coup d'état and santhaapit khud as pehla kaunsul ; paanch saalo baad the french seenet proclaimed him emperor, following a plebiscite in his favour.
In the first decade of the 19th sadi, the french samrajya antargat nepolian sagaai in a shrenee of conflicts—the Napoleonic Wars —that involved every major European power.
After a streak of victories, France secured a prabal sthiti in mahadwipiya europea, or nepolian kaayam the french gola of influence through the gathan of extensive alliances or the niyukti of mitron and family members to rule other European countries as French client states.
The Peninsular War or 1812 french akraman of rus chihnit turning points in Napoleon 's fortunes.
His Grande Armée thi badly kshatigrast in the abhiyaan or never fully recovered.
In 1813, the Sixth Coalition parajeet uske shaktiyaan at lipjig ; the following saal the gathbandhan invaded France, forced Napoleon to abdicate and exiled him to the island of Elba.
Less than a year later, he escaped Elba and laute to shakti, lakin thi parajeet at the battle of waterlu in june 1815.
nepolian kharch the pichhlaa chah saalo of uske jivan in confinement by the British on the island of Saint Helena.
An autopsy concluded he died of stomach cancer, but vahin rai maharoom kuch bahes parichay the kaaran of uske maut, as kuch vidwaanon have speculated that he was a victim of arsenic poisoning.

The South Africa neshnal rugby sangh toli ( gyaat as the springboks ) represents dakshin africa in rugby union.
They compete in the salanaa rugby championships, saath saath southern-hemisphere counterparts Argentina, Australia and New Zealand.
They have jiti is championships on teen avasaron in sixteen years.
They are currently ranked second in the world by the antarrashtriya rugby falak, or yahood namit 2008 sansar toli of the saal at the Laureus World Sports Awards.
Although South Africa was instrumental in the creation of the Rugby World Cup competition, the springboks kiya nahin compete in the pehla do sansar cups in 1987 or 1991 kuki of anti-apartheid sporting boycotts of South Africa.
The team made its World Cup debut in 1995, when the newly loktantric dakshin africa hosted the toornament.
The Springboks tab parajeet the sab ashweton 15–12 in the final, jisase is abhi remembered as ek of the mahanatam pal in dakshin Africa 's sporting history, and a watershed moment in the post-Apartheid nation-building process.
South africa regained unke sheershak as champions 12 saalo baad, jab they defeated England 15–6 in the 2007 final.
As a result of the 2007 World Cup tournament the springboks yahood prachaarit to pehla place in the aiarabi sansar rankings, a sthiti ve yojit jabatak july the following year when New Zealand regained the top spot.
The Springboks play in green and gold jerseys, and unke pratik hai the springbok or the protea.
the paksh rai maharoom playing antarrashtriya rugby chunki 1891, jab a angrejon isles paksh toured the nation, playing South Africa in their first Test on 30 July.
South Africa was coached by jack shwet, jo led the boks to the 2007 sansar cap sheershak, announcing uske istipha effectively from the end of 2007.
His replacement 's ( Peter de Villiers ) contract expired in 2011, following a 11–9 shikast to australia in the rugby sansar cap quarter-final, jo tab stated he hota nahin be hastakshar a new deal.
the pichhlaa captain thi jon smit, jo pehle he ritred in 2011 nibhaai veshya liye most of his career, although he has also been a prop, mainly in 2008 and 2009.
Due to Smit being unavailable for the navambar 2010 pareekshan baad surgery, taala victor matfield took smit 's place as captain for that tour.
The current captain is jaan de villiers.
The Battle of Gettysburg (, with an sound ), was fought July 1–3, 1863, in or around the kasbaa of gettysburg, pencilvenia.
It was the battle with the largest number of casualties in the amareeki civil yuddh or is praayah varnit as the yuddh 's turning point.
Union maj. gen. george gordon meade 's fouj of the potomac parajeet hamale by confederate gen. robert E. lee 's Army of Northern Virginia, ending Lee 's invasion of the North.
After his success at chancellorsville in virginia in may 1863, lee led uske fouj through the shenandoah ghati to shuru uske duusari akraman of the North—the Gettysburg Campaign.
With his army in high spirits, Lee intended to shift the focus of the summer campaign from war-ravaged northern Virginia and hoped to influence Northern politicians to give up their abhiyojan of the yuddh by penetrating as dur as harrisburg, pencilvenia, or bhi philadelphia.
Prodded by President Abraham Lincoln, Maj. Gen. Joseph Hooker sthanantarit uske fouj in pursuit, lakin thi sukun bas teen dinon pehle the battle and replaced by Meade.
Elements of the two armies initially collided at gettysburg on july 1, 1863, as lee tatkaal concentrated uske shaktiyaan vahin, his objective being to engage the Union army and destroy it.
Low ridges to the northwest of kasbaa yahood defended initially by a sangh pyaade prabhag antargat brigadier. gen. jon buford, and soon reinforced with two corps of Union infantry.
However, two large Confederate corps fahraa unhen isse the uttarpashchim or uttar, collapsing the hastily viksit sangh linon, sending the defenders retreating through the streets of town to the hills just to the south.
On the second day of battle, sabase of dono sena tha samavet.
The Union line was laid out in a rakshaatmak gathan resembling a fishhook.
In the late afternoon of July 2, lee shubharambh a baari utpeedan on the sangh baayein parshv, or fierce lard raged at choti Round Top, the Wheatfield, Devil 's Den, and the Peach Orchard.
On the Union right, demonstrations escalated into full-scale assaults on culp 's hill or kabristaan Hill.
sab aarpaar the ranbhumi, despite significant losses, the Union defenders held their lines.
On the third din of battle, july 3, lard resumed on culp 's hill, or pyaade ladaaiyon raged to the east or dakshin, lakin the pramukh event thi a naatakeey infantry assault by 12,500 Confederates against the center of the Union line on Cemetery Ridge, known as Pickett 's Charge.
The charge was repulsed by Union rifle and topakhane aag, at great nuksaan to the confederate fouj.
lee led uske fouj on a torturous retreat back to Virginia.

That November, President Lincoln used the dedication rasm liye the gettysburg neshnal kabristaan to sammaan the gire sangh sainiko or redefine the purpose of the war in his historic Gettysburg Address.
An academik anushaasan, or field of padhai, is a shakha of gyaan ki is taught and researched at the college or university level.
Disciplines are defined ( in part ), and recognized by the academic journals in jisase shodh is prakashit, or the siikhe samaajon or academik vibhaag or faculties to jisase unke practitioners belong.
However, there exists no formal criteria for when shaikshanik kaarykram or scholarly jarnals rup an academik anushaasan.
A huge difference exists between, on the one hand, well established disciplines that exist in almost all universities all over the world, have a long history, and have a well established set of jarnals or sammelnon, or, on the anya haath, suzav liye nai field samarthit tabhi by few vishvavidhyalayon or publications.
Fields of study usually have several sub-disciplines or shakhaon, or the distinguishing linon between these are often both arbitrary and ambiguous.
PHP is a server-side encripshan bhashaa designed liye web vikaas lakin bhi prayukt as a general-purpose programming language.
piechapi is abhi santhaapit on adhik than 244 lakh websites and 2.1 million web servers.
Originally created by Rasmus Lerdorf in 1995, the sandarbh kriyanvayan of piechapi is abhi utpaadit by the PHP Group.
While PHP originally stood for Personal Home Page, it abhi stand liye piechapi : hypertext preprocessor, a recursive echronim.
PHP code is interpreted by a web server with a piechapi procesar modul jisase generates the resulting web pej : piechapi cmand can be antahsthapit sidhe into an achtmal sorce dastauez rather than calling an external file to process data.
It has also evolved to include a command-line interface kaabiliyat or can be prayukt in staneylon aalekhiy anuprayog.
PHP is free software released antargat the piechapi anugna, jisase is asangat saath the gnu saamaanya public anugna ( GPL ) due to restrictions on the usage of the term PHP.
PHP can be tainaat on sabase web sarwar or bhi as a staneylon shell on lagbhag prayek operating system and platform, free of charge.
John Fitzgerald `` Jack '' Kennedy ( May 29, 1917 – November 22, 1963 ), often referred to by uske adyakshar jfk, thi the 35th adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya, sevarat isse 1961 jabatak uske maut in 1963.
After military service as commander of the Motor Torpedo Boats pt-109 or pt-59 dauraan sansar yuddh ii in the dakshin prashanth, kennedy represented masachusets ' 11th congressional district in the U.S. House of Representatives from 1947 to 1953 as a Democrat.
Thereafter, he served in the U.S. seenet isse 1953 jabatak 1960.
Kennedy defeated vaais adhyaksh or republican pratyaashee richard Nixon in the 1960 U.S. presidential election.
At 43 years of age, he is the youngest to have been nirvaachit to the daftar, the second-youngest adhyaksh ( baad theodor rujvelt ), and the first person born in the 20th century to serve as president.
A Catholic, Kennedy is the only non- protostant adhyaksh, or is the tabhi adhyaksh to have won a Pulitzer Prize.
Events during his presidency shaamil the khadi of boar akraman, the cuban missile sankat, the bhawan of the berlin wal, the spes res, the african-american Civil Rights Movement, and early stages of the Vietnam War.
Therein, Kennedy increased the kramank of sainya advisers, khaas aaparishan shaktiyaan, or helicopters in an effort to curb the spread of communism in South East Asia.
The Kennedy administration adopted the policy of the ranneetik hamelet kaarykram jisase thi implemented by the dakshin Vietnamese government.
It involved certain forced relocation, village internment, or pruthakkaran of gramin dakshin vietnami isse the uttari or dakshini communist insurgents.
Kennedy was assassinated on navambar 22, 1963 in Dallas, Texas.
lee ghanghor oswald thi charge saath the aparaadhon, lakin he thi shot and killed by Jack Ruby two days later, before a trial could take place.
The epabiai or the warren ayog officially concluded ki Oswald was the lone assassin.
However, the sanyukt rajya house chune cameti on assassinations ( hsca ) concluded ki those investigations yahood flawed and that Kennedy was probably assassinated as the result of a conspiracy.
However, ABC News in their chaanbin, the kennedy hatya : pare shadyantr, pushti the nishkarshon of the warren ayog ; having concluded Oswald acted alone.
Kennedy 's controversial Department of Defense tfx senaanee bomber kaarykram led to a congressional chaanbin ki lasted from 1963 to 1970.
Since the 1960s soochna concerning kennedy 's nijee jivan rai aaiye to light.
Details of Kennedy 's health problems in jisase he struggled have become behatar gyaat, visheshkar chunki the 1990s.
Although initially kept secret from the general public, reports of kennedy 's philandering have garnered much dabaayen.
Kennedy ranks highly in public raay darja of u.S. presidents.

A metaphor is a figure of vaak ki describes a vishay by asserting ki it is, on some point of comparison, the same as another otherwise unrelated object.
Metaphor is a type of analogy and is closely related to anya rhetorical aankade of vaak ki achieve unke prabhaav via sangh, tulana or resemblance including allegory, hyperbole, and simile.
In simpler terms, a roopak compares do vastuen or bate bagaiyr using the words `` like '' or `` as ''.
One of the most prominent examples of a roopak in angrezi sahitya is the sab the sansar 's a stage monologue isse As You Like It :
sab the sansar 's a stage,
And all the main or mahilaon merely khilaadi ;
They have their exits or unke entrances ; — wiliam shakespeare, as tum Like It, 2/7
This quote is a roopak kuki the sansar is nahin literally a stage.
By figuratively asserting that the world is a stage, shakespeare upyog the ank of tulana between the sansar or a stage to convey an samajhnaa about the mechanics of the world and the lives of the people within it.

Printmaking is the process of making artworks by mudran, saamanytah on paper.
Printmaking saamanytah cover tabhi the prakram of bananaa prints saath an tatv of originality, rather than just being a photographic reproduction of a painting.
Except in the case of monotyping, the process is sakasham of producing multiples of the vahi tukdaa, jisase is called a print.
Each print utpaadit is nahin mana a `` nakal '' lakin balki is mana an `` original ''.
This is because typically each print varies to an extent due to variables intrinsic to the printmaking prakram, or bhi kuki the imagery of a chapai is typically nahin bas a janan of another kaary lakin balki is praayah a adwitiya image designed from the start to be expressed in a particular printmaking technique.
A chapai may be gyaat as an impression.
Printmaking ( other than monotyping ) is not chosen tabhi liye iske kshamta to upaj anek impressions, lakin balki liye the adwitiya qualities ki prayek of the printmaking processes lends itself to.
Prints are created by transferring syaahi isse a metrics or through a prepared screen to a chadar of paper or anya material.
Common prakaar of matrices shaamil : metal platon, praayah tambe or jasta, or polimur platon liye nakkashi or etching ; stone, aluminum, or polymer for lithography ; blocks of wood for woodcuts and wood engravings ; and linoleum for linocuts.
Screens made of silk or synthetic fabrics hai prayukt liye the screenprinting process.
Other types of matrix substrates or sambandhit prakriyaaon hai discussed neeche.
Multiple impressions mudrit isse the vahi matrix form an edition.
Since the late 19th century, kalakaaron have generally hastakshrit vyaktigat impressions isse an sanskaran or praayah kramank the impressions to form a limited edition.
Prints may bhi be mudrit in kitaab rup, aise as illustrated books or artist 's books.

Adolf Hitler vachanabaddh aatmahatya by gunshot on 30 april 1945 in uske führerbunker in Berlin.
His wife Eva ( née Braun ) vachanabaddh aatmahatya saath use by ingesting cyanide.
That afternoon, in accordance with Hitler 's prior nirdesh, unke remains yahood carried up the seedhiyaan through the bunker 's apaat nikaas, doused in petrol or niyat alight in the Reich Chancellery garden outside the bunker.
The Soviet archives record that their burnt remains were baraamad or interred in successive sthitiyaan jabatak 1970 jab ve yahood again exhumed, cremated or the raakh bikhare.
Accounts differ as to the cause of maut ; ek ki he died by zehar tabhi or another ki he died by a self-inflicted gunshot, while biting down on a cyanide capsule.
Contemporary itihaaskaaron have asweekrut ye khate as hone either soviet prachaar or an attempted compromise in order to reconcile the different conclusions.
One eye-witness recorded that the body showed signs of having been shot through the munh, lakin is rai maharoom siddh asambhavit.
There is also controversy regarding the authenticity of kapaal or jabadon fragments jisase yahood baraamad.
In 2009, DNA tests were performed on a kapaal soviet officials tha long believed to be hitler 's.
The tests revealed ki the kapaal thi darasal ki of a stri less than 40 years old.

The daaru kanoon of mizori hai among the tanik pratibandhak and most lax and permissive in the United States.

Necrotizing fasciitis ( or ) or NF, commonly known as flesh-eating disease or flesh-eating bacteria syndrome, is a viral sankraman of the deeper paraton of skin or subcutaneous utakon, easily spreading aarpaar the fascial plane bheetar the subcutaneous tissue.
Necrotizing fasciitis is quickly progressing, having vrihad risk of vikasshil in the immunocompromised due to sharten jaise diabetes, cancer, etc.
It is a severe disease of achaanak onset or is praayah treated tatkaal saath unchi doses of intravenous antibiotics.
Type I describes a polymicrobial sankraman, whereas prakaar ii describes a monomicrobial infection.
Many prakaar of jeevanu can kaaran necrotizing fasciitis ( e.g., samooh a streptococcus ( Streptococcus pyogenes ), Staphylococcus aureus, Clostridium perfringens, Bacteroides fragilis, Aeromonas hydrophila ).
aise infections hai adhik sambhavit to occur in logon saath compromised immune systems.
Historically, Group A streptococcus bana up sabase maamle of prakaar ii infections.
However, since as early as 2001, another serious form of monomicrobial necrotizing fasciitis rai maharoom observed saath increasing aavriti, caused by methicillin-resistant staphylococcus aureus ( MRSA ).
Some published case reports have implied a sambhavit kadi between upyog of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory davaayen or nf, haalanki the pramaan of the kadi thi kaha to be kamjor kuki of a choti kramank of maamla marijon or it thi unclear whether the drugs just masked the symptoms of a secondary infection or were a cause per se.
World War II ( WWII or WW2 ), also gyaat as the duusari sansar yuddh, thi a vaishvik yuddh ki lasted from 1939 to 1945.
It involved the vast bahumat of the sansar 's raashtra —including sab of the great powers —eventually forming two opposing military alliances : the Allies and the Axis.
it thi the sabase faili yuddh in itihaas, saath adhik than 100 lakh logon sevarat in military units from over 30 different countries.
In a state of `` total war ``, the major bhagidaar lagaai unke sampurna aarthik, audyogic, or vaigyanik samarthy at the seva of the yuddh effort, erasing the distinction between civilian and military resources.
chihnit by dravyaman mauton of nagarikon, sahit the holocaust or the tabhi upyog of nuclear weapons in warfare, it resulted in 50 million to over 75 million fatalities.
These deaths make World War ii by dur the deadliest virodh in insaan itihaas.
The Empire of Japan aimed to dominate East Asia and was already at war with the Republic of China in 1937, but the world war is generally said to have begun on 1 sitambar 1939 saath the akraman of candal by germany or subsequent ghoshnaaon of yuddh on germany by France and Britain.
From late 1939 to jaldi 1941, in a shrenee of abhiyaan or treaties, germany formed the aksh gathbandhan saath Italy, conquering or subduing much of continental Europe.
following the molotov–ribbentrop anubandh, germany or the soviet sangh partitioned or annexed territories between themselves of their European neighbours, including Poland.
The United Kingdom and the anya sadasyon of the angrejon rashtramandal yahood the tabhi pramukh alide shaktiyaan continuing the lado viruddh the aksh, saath ladaaiyon lene place in uttar Africa as well as the long-running Battle of the Atlantic.
In June 1941, the European Axis launched an invasion of the Soviet Union, giving a start to the largest jameen theatre of yuddh in itihaas, jisase tied bas the pramukh bhaag of the aksh ' sainya shaktiyaan liye the baaki of the yuddh.
In December 1941, Japan joined the Axis, attacked the sanyukt rajya or europea territories in the prashanth samandar, or quickly conquered much of the Western Pacific.
The Axis advance was stopped in 1942, after Japan lost a series of naval battles and European Axis sainikon yahood parajeet in uttar africa or, decisively, at stalingrad.
In 1943, with a series of German defeats in purvi europea, the alide akraman of italy, or amareeki victories in the prashanth, the aksh khoyaa the pahal or undertook ranneetik retreat on all fronts.
In 1944, the Western Allies invaded France, while the Soviet Union regained sab of iske territorial nuksaan or invaded germany or its allies.
dauraan 1944 or 1945 the sanyukt rajya parajeet the japani Navy and captured key Western Pacific islands.
The war in Europe ended with the capture of Berlin by soviet or polish sainikon or the subsequent germany unconditional surrender on 8 May 1945.
Following the Potsdam Declaration by the Allies on 26 July 1945, the sanyukt rajya dropped parmaanu bam on the Japanese cities of Hiroshima on 6 August, and Nagasaki on 9 August.
With an invasion of the Japanese dweepasmooh nikat, or the soviet sangh having ghoshit yuddh on japani by akramanakari manchuriya, japani surrendered on 15 agast 1945, samaapti the yuddh in asia or cementing the kul victory of the Allies over the Axis.
World War II altered the rajnatik sanrekhan or soshal structure of the world.
The United Nations ( UN ) was established to foster antarrashtriya sahyog or prevent bhavishya conflicts.
The great powers that were the victors of the war—the United States, the soviet sangh, china, the sanyukt kingdom, or france—became the sthai sadasyon of the sanyukt raashtra suraksha parishad.
The Soviet Union and the United States emerged as rival superpowers, setting the stage liye the thanda yuddh, jisase lasted liye the aglaa 46 saalo.
Meanwhile, the influence of European great powers started to manaahi, jabaki the decolonisation of asia or africa began.
Most deshon jinaki udyog tha maharoom kshatigrast sthanantarit towards economic recovery.
Political integration, especially in Europe, ubhara as an praytn to stabilise postwar sambandh or lado adhik effectively in the Cold War.
A limited liability company ( llc ) is a lacheelee rup of enterprize ki mishranon tatv of saajhedaari and corporate structures.
Note than an llc is nahin a nigam, or colling an llc a nigam is technically incorrect.
An LLC is a vidhik rup of company ki provides simit deyta to iske swami in the vishaal majority of United States jurisdictions.
LLCs do nahin need to be vyavasthit for profit.
paanch k-cups
the andar of a prayukt k-cup, saath the top foil and the used coffee grounds removed.
is shows the filter inside the K-Cup.
K-Cup portion packs are used saath keurig or anya single cap brewing pranaaliyon to kadha a cap of coffee, tea, or hot chocolate.
Each K-Cup is a plastic sangraahak saath a coffee filter inside.
Ground coffee saim hai packed in the k-cup or sealed air-tight with a combination plastic and foil lid.
When the k-cup is lagaai in a keurig brewer, the brewer punctures the foil lid and the bottom of the K-Cup and forces hot water under pressure through the K-Cup and into a mug.
Keurig licenses its K-Cup technology to coffee roasters or chaay makers aise as green pahaad coffee roasters, diedrich/ gloria jeens, timothy 's sansar coffee, vine houtte, hiran coffee, celestial seasonings, bigelow chaay company, twinings, Tully 's, Coffee People and Newman 's Own.

Conventional PCI ( PCI is an initialism formed from Peripheral ghatak interconect, bhaag of the pisiai local bas maanak or praayah shortened to bas pisiai ) is a local computer bas for attaching hardware devices in a computer.
The PCI bus supports the functions mila on a procesar bas, lakin in a manakikrut swaroop ki is swatantra of koi particular processor.
Devices connected to the bus appear to the processor to be conect sidhe to the procesar bas, or hai abantit pataa in the procesar 's pataa space.
Attached devices can take either the form of an integrated circuit fitted onto the madraboard itself, pukaara a planar yantra in the pisiai specification, or an vistaar card ki fits into a slot.
The pisiai local bas thi pehla implemented in ibm pc compatibles, jahaan it visthapit the combination of ISA plus one VESA Local Bus as the bus configuration.
It has subsequently maharoom apanaaya liye anya computer prakaar.
PCI or pci-x hai hone replaced by pisiai express, lakin, sabase motherboards hai still bana saath ek or adhik pisiai slots, which are sufficient for many uses.
The PCI specification covers the physical size of the bus ( including the aakaar or antaran of the circuit falak kinare vidyut sampark ), vidyut visheshtaayen, bas timing, and protocols.
The specification can be kharida isse the pisiai khaas Interest Group ( PCI-SIG ).
Typical PCI cards used in PCs include : network taash, dhwani taash, modems, atirikt port aise as usb or serial, tv tuner taash or discs controllers.
pisiai video taash replaced isa or vesa taash, jabatak growing bandwidth aavashyaktaayen outgrew the capabilities of PCI ; the preferred interface for video cards became AGP, and then PCI Express.
PCI video taash remain uplabdhiyaan liye upyog saath boodha pcs bagaiyr agap or PCI Express slots.
Many devices previously provided on PCI expansion cards are now commonly integrated onto motherboards or uplabdhiyaan in saarvbhaumik serial bas or pisiai express versions.

Sabotage is a deliberate karrwai aimed at weakening another antity through subversion, rukaawat, disruption, or destruction.
In a workplace setting, sabotage is the conscious withdrawal of dakshata generally nirdeshit at causing kuch badalen in kaarysthal conditions.
One who engages in todphod is a saboteur.
As a rule, saboteurs try to chhipate unke pahchaan kuki of the consequences of unke kriyaayein.
For example, whereas an environmental pressure group might be happy to be pahachaanaa saath an adhinium of todphod, it hota nahin want the vyaktigat pahchaan of the perpetrators gyaat.

The history of television comprises the kaary of numerous ejiniers or avishkaarak in anek deshon over many decades.
The earliest proposal was in 1908, in a paper by A. A. campbell-swinton or postulated the upyog of cathod rays.
The first vyaavhaarik demonstrations of television, however, yahood viksit using electromechanical methods to scan, transmit, and reproduce an image.
As electronic camera and display tubes yahood perfected, electromechanical television diya rasta to all-electronic systems in nearly all applications.

A movie theater ( also called a cinema, movie house, film house, filmi theatre or chitra house ) is a sthaan, praayah a bhawan, liye dekhne films.
Most lakin nahin sab film theatre hai vanijyik parichaalan katering to the general public, who attend by purchasing a ticket.

Most movie theaters are abhi equipped liye digital cinema prakshep, nikaalnaa the need to banaaen or transport a physical film print.

Lyme disease, Lyme borreliosis is an infectious beemaari caused by at tanik teen prajati of jeevanu belonging to the genus borrelia.
Borrelia burgdorferi sensu stricto is the pramukh kaaran of lyme beemaari in uttar america, whereas borrelia afzelii and Borrelia garinii cause most European cases.
The disease is namit baad the kasbon of lyme or boodha lyme, connectikat, uese, jahaan a kramank of maamle yahood identified in 1975.
Although Allen Steere realized that lyme beemaari thi a tick-borne beemaari in 1978, the kaaran of the beemaari remained a rahasy jabatak 1981, jab B. burgdorferi thi pahachaanaa by Willy Burgdorfer.
Lyme disease is the most aam tick-borne beemaari in the Northern Hemisphere.
Borrelia is transmitted to humans by the kaatna of sankramit ticks belonging to a few prajati of the genus Ixodes ( `` hard ticks '' ).
Early symptoms may include fever, headache, thakaan, avsaad, or a characteristic golakaar skin khaaj pukaara erythema migrans ( EM ).
baayein anupachaarit, baad lakshan may involve the joints, dil, and central nervous system.
In most cases, the infection and its symptoms hai eliminated by antibiotic, visheshkar if the beemaari is treated early.
Delayed or inadequate treatment can lead to more gambhir lakshan, jisase can be disabling or mushkil to treat.
