Penis ( plural penises or penes ) is a saamaanya pad liye the angon saath jisase purush or ubhayalingi pashu introduce shukranu into receptive females during copulation.
Such organs occur in many animals, both vertebrate and invertebrate, but males do not bear a penis in every animal prajati, or in those prajati in jisase the purush karata bhaaluu a so-called shishn, the penes in the various species are not necessarily homologous.
For example, the shishn of a standhari is at sabase analogous to the shishn of a male insect or barnacle.
the pad shishn applies to anek reproductive intromittent angon, lakin nahin to sab ; liye udhaaharan the intromittent organ of most cephalopoda is the hectocotylus, a specialised arm, and male spiders use their pedipalps.
In most species of pashu in jisase vahin is an ang ki might reasonably be varnit as a shishn, it rai no pramukh falan anya than intromission, or at tanik conveying the shukranu to the maadaa, lakin in the placental mammals the penis bears the distal part of the urethra, which discharges both urine during urination and semen during copulation as the occasion requires.
Artists and repertoire ( A & R ) is the division of a record label or music publishing company ki is jimmedaar liye hunar balchar or overseeing the kalakaari vikaas of recording kalakaaron and/or songwriters.
It also adhiniyamon as a liaison between kalakaaron or the ricard label or prakaashan company ; prayek kaaryaklap involving kalakaaron to the point of album release is generally considered under the purview of, and responsibility of, A & R.
A furlong is a measure of distance in imperial ikai or u.S. prathagat ikai baraabar to one-eighth of a mile, samatuly to 220 gaj, 660 feet, 40 chad, or 10 zanjeeron.
The exact maan of the furlong varies slightly among English-speaking countries.
Five furlongs are approximately 1 kilometre ( 1.0058 km is a kareeb sanniktan ).
Since the original definition of the metre was one-quarter of one ten-millionth of the paridhi of the dharti ( saath the great vrutt coincident saath the madhyahn of deshaantar guzar through paris ), the paridhi of the Earth is about 40,000 km or about 200,000 furlongs.

Facebook is an online soshal netwarking seva, jinaki naam tana isse the colloquial naam liye the kitaab die to vidhyaarthee at the start of the academic year by some university administrations in the United States to help students get to know each other.
It was founded in February 2004 by Mark Zuckerberg with his college roommates or fellow harvard vishvavidhyalayon vidhyaarthee aduardo saverin, andrew mccollum, Dustin Moskovitz and Chris Hughes.
The website 's sadsyta thi initially simit by the sansthaapakon to harvard vidhyaarthee, lakin thi vistaarit to anya collejon in the Boston area, the Ivy League, and Stanford University.
It gradually added support liye vidhyaarthee at vibhinn anya vishvavidhyalayon pehle kholane to unchi skool vidhyaarthee, and eventually to anyone aged 13 and over.
Facebook now allows any users who declare themselves to be at tanik 13 saalo boodha to become panjikrut upayokta of the sait.
Users must register before using the site, after which ve may banaaen a nijee profil, add anya upayokta as mitron, or exange sandesh, sahit swachaalit notifications when they update their profile.
Additionally, users may join common-interest user groups, organized by workplace, school or college, or other visheshtaayen, or categorize unke mitron into suchiyaan aise as `` logon isse kaary '' or `` band mitron ''.
As of September 2012, fasebuk rai over ek billion active users.
According to a May 2011 upabhokta reports surveykshan, vahin hai 7.5 lakh children antargat 13 saath khate or 5 million under 10, violating the site 's terms of service.
In May 2005, Accel partners invested $ 12.7 million in fasebuk, or gym breyer added $ 1 lakh of uske apana dhan to the pot.
A January 2009 Compete.com study ranked fasebuk as the sabase prayukt soshal netwarking seva by vishwavyaapee monthly active users.
Entertainment Weekly included the site on its end-of-the-decade `` best-of '' list, saying, `` How on dharti kiya we stalk hamaari exes, yaad hamaari co-workers ' janmdin, keedaa hamaari mitron, or khel a rousing khel of scrabulous pehle Facebook ? ''
Critics, such as Facebook Detox, rajya ki fasebuk rai turned into a neshnal obsession in the sanyukt rajya, resulting in vishaal amounts of time lost and encouraging narcissism.
Quantcast estimates Facebook has 138.9 lakh masik adwitiya u.S. vizitor in may 2011.
According to Social Media Today, in april 2010 an anumaanit 41.6 % ( 129.5 lakh ) of the u.S. janasankhyikee tha a fasebuk account.
Nevertheless, Facebook 's market growth prarambh to stall in kuch regions, saath the sait khone 7 lakh kriyasheel upayokta in the sanyukt rajya or canada in May 2011.
Facebook eventually filed for an aarambhik public offering on farvari 1, 2012, or thi headquartered in Menlo Park, California.
Facebook Inc. began selling stock to the public or vyapaar on the nasdac on may 18, 2012.
arvin yohaness eugen khabaron ( 15 navambar 1891 – 14 aktubar 1944 ), popularly known as The Desert Fox ( Wüstenfuchs, ), was a German Field Marshal of World War II.
He earned the aadar of dono uske apana sainikon or the enemies he fought.
Rommel was a highly decorated officer in World yuddh i or thi awarded the daalana le mérite liye uske karname on the Italian front.
In sansar yuddh ii, he further vishisht khud as the commander of the 7th Panzer Division during the 1940 invasion of France.
His leadership of germany or italvi shaktiyaan in the uttar africa abhiyaan sthapit use as ek of the sabase samarth cmanderon of the war, and earned him the appellation of the Desert Fox.
He is regarded as ek of the sabase skilled cmanderon of marusthal warfare in the conflict.
He later commanded the germany shaktiyaan opposing the alide cross-channel invasion in Normandy.
His kaarybhaar never took use to the purvi Front.
Rommel is regarded as having maharoom a dayaalu or peshewar adhikari.
uske afrika corps thi never abhiyukt of yuddh aparaadhon, or sainiko captured during his Africa campaign were reported to have been treated humanely.
Orders to kill Jewish soldiers, nagarikon or captured commando yahood upekshit.
Late in the war, Rommel was linked to the shadyantr to assassinate adolf hitler.
Since khabaron thi a neshnal nayika, hitler desired to eliminate him quietly.
He forced Rommel to commit suicide with a cyanide pill, in vaapasi liye aashwaasano ki khabaron 's parivaar hota nahin be persecuted following uske death.

Earth Day is an annual event, manaaye on april 22, on jisase kaarykram hai yojit vishwavyaapee to demonstrate support liye paryaavarniya protection.
It was first celebrated in 1970, or is abhi samanvit globally by the dharti din sanjaal, or manaaye in more than 192 countries each year.

This day of nature 's equipoise thi baad manjuur in a udghoshnaa hastakshrit by sachiv saamaanya u thant at the United Nations.
A maah baad a pruthak dharti din thi santhaapit by sanyukt rajya seenetter gaylord nelson as an environmental teach-in first held on April 22, 1970.
Nelson was later awarded the adhyakshiya padak of swatantraaa puraskaar in recognition of his work.
While this April 22 dharti din thi kendrit on the sanyukt rajya, an sanghathan shubharambh by denis hez, jo thi the asli neshnal samanvayak in 1970, took it international in 1990 and organized events in 141 nations.
Numerous communities celebrate dharti saptaah, an sampurna saptaah of kriyaayein focused on environmental issues.
Iodine is a chemical element with symbol i or parmaanu kramank 53.
The name is isse unani ioeidēs, arth bangnee or jamuni, due to the rang of elemental iodine vapor.
iodine or iske yogicon hai primarily prayukt in poshan, or industrially in the utpaadan of acetic acid and certain polymers.
Iodine 's relatively high atomic number, low toxicity, and ease of anulgnak to sashulk yogicon have bana it a bhaag of anek x-ray contrast saamagree in aadhunik ayurvigyaan.
iodine rai tabhi ek stable isotope.
A kramank of iodine radioisotopes hai bhi used in medical applications.
Iodine is mila on dharti mukhyatah as the atyadhik water-soluble iodide aayan, I−, which concentrates it in oceans and brine pools.
Like the other hellogence, free iodine occurs mukhyatah as a diatomic anu i2, or tab only momentarily after being oxidized from iodide by an oxidant like free oxygen.
In the brahmad or on dharti, iodine 's unchi parmaanu kramank makes it a apekshaakrit rare element.
However, iske upasthiti in samandar jal rai die it a role in biology.
It is the heaviest essential element utilized widely by life in biological krityon ( tabhi tungston, employed in anzimon by a few prajati of jeevanu, is heavier ).
Iodine 's rarity in anek soils, due to aarambhik kam prachurtaa as a crust-element, or bhi leaching of ghulansheel iodide by rainwater, has led to many deficiency problems in land animals and inland human populations.
Iodine kamiyaan affects parichay do arab logon or is the agrani preventable cause of intellectual disabilities.
Iodine is required by higher animals, which use it to synthesize thyride hormone, jisase contain the tatv.
Because of this function, radioisotopes of iodine hai concentrated in the thyride granthi along with nonradioactive iodine.
If inhaled, the radioisotope iodine-131, which has a unchi parivardhan utpaada upaj, concentrates in the thyride, lakin is easily remedied saath potacium iodide treatment.
Lobbying ( also lobby ) is the act of attempting to influence decisions bana by officials in the sarkari, sabase praayah vidhayak or sadasyon of niamak agencies.
Lobbying is done by many different types of people and organized samooh, sahit individuals in the nijee sector, corporations, fellow vidhayak or sarkari officials, or vakaalat samooh ( interest groups ).
Lobbyists may be among a legislator 's constituencies, arth a voter or bloc of matadaata bheetar uske or uske chunavi zila, or nahin ; ve may engage in lobbying as a business, or not.
Professional lobbyists hai logon jinaki kaarobaar is trying to influence vidhaan on nimitt of a group or individual who hires them.
Individuals and nonprofit organizations can bhi lobby as an adhinium of swayanseva or as a choti bhaag of unke saamaanya job ( liye udhaaharan, a siio baithak saath a pratinidhi parichay a project mahatvapurn to his/her company, or an activist meeting with his/her legislator in an unpaid capacity ).
Governments often define and regulate vyavasthit samooh lobbying ki rai become influential.
The aachaar or naitikta of lobbying are.
Lobbying is often spoken of with contempt, jab the implication is ki logon saath atyadhik socioeconomic shakti hai corrupting the vidhi ( tedi it dur isse nishpakshta ) in anukram to serve unke own conflict of interest.
But another side of lobbying is making sure that others ' ruchi hai vidhivat defended viruddh anya ' bhrashtachar, or bhi bas bananaa yakeenan ki alpsankhyak ruchi hai fairly defended against mere tyranny of the majority.
For example, a medical association, or a trade association of health insurance companiyaan, may lobby a vidhanmandal in anukram to counteract the influence of tambaaku companiyaan, in jisase maamla the lobbying hota be viewed by sabase logon as jaij ( duly defending against others ' corruption ).
The difficulty in drawing objective lines between which lobbyists hai `` shubh lobbyists '' or jisase ones hai `` karaab ones '' is compounded by the cleverness saath jisase lobbyists or unke clients can argue that their own lobbying is of the `` good '' kind.
At heart, the effort to influence vidhaan is a shakti sangharsh.
As in other forms of power struggle, such as yuddh or vidhi pravartan, motives dayera isse to self-defense to fighting for justice, and the dividing line between predation and justice is subject to rationalization.

Cream were a 1960s angrejon chattan supergroup consisting of bassist/vocalist joker bruce, guitarist/vocalist Eric Clapton, and drummer Ginger Baker.
Their sound was characterised by a hybrid of blues chattan, mushkil chattan or cicedelik chattan, combining the psychedelia-themed geet, eric clapton 's bluez guitar playing or vocals, joker bruce 's awaz or prominent bass playing and Ginger Baker 's jazz -influenced drumming.

The band 's sajiv pradarshan bahekaave pragatisheel rock acts such as Rush.

ve yahood shaamil in dono rolling stone or vh1 's suchiyaan of the `` 100 Greatest Artists of All Time ''.

A Christian denomination is an identifiable dharmik deh antargat a aam naam, dhaancha, or doctrine bheetar christianity.
Some groups included do not consider themselves a denomination ( e.g., the catholic girijaghar considers itself the ek sachcha girijaghar or the apostolic dekhie, and as pre-denominational ).
Some groups viewed by non-adherents as denominational actively resist being pukaara a denomination or do nahin have koi aupchaarik denominational dhaancha, praadhikaar, or record-keeping pare the local sabha ; several groups within Restoration Movement fall into this category.
Some groups are vishaal ( e.g. catholics, lutherans, anglicans or baptists ), jabaki anya hai bas a few choti carch, or in sabase maamle the saapeksh size is not evident in this list.
Modern movements such as Fundamentalist Christianity, Pietism, Evangelicalism, Pentecostalism and the Holiness movement sometimes cross denominational linon, or in kuch maamle banaaen nai denominations out of do or adhik continuing samooh, ( as is the case for many United and uniting churches, for example ).
Such subtleties or complexities hai nahin clearly depicted here.
Major vibhaajan bheetar christianity.
Note : This is nahin a puraa suchi, lakin aims to provide a comprehensible avlokan of the vividhta among denominations of Christianity.
As there are reported to be approximately 41,000 Christian denominations, many of which can not be verified to be significant, only those denominations saath vikipedia aalekh hoga be soochibaddh in anukram to ensure ki sab pravishtiyaan on is suchi hai notable and verifiable.
Between denominations, theologians, and comparative religionists there are considerable disagreements about which groups can be properly pukaara isai, matbhinnata arising primarily isse doctrinal matbhed between samooh.
For the purpose of saadagi, is suchi is intended to pratibimbit the self-understanding of prayek denomination.
Explanations of different opinions concerning unke aukaat as isai denominations can be mila at unke sambandhit aalekh.
There is no official recognition in sabase bhaag of the sansar liye dharmik laashen, or vahin is no aadhikarik clearinghouse which could determine the status or respectability of religious bodies.
Often there is considerable disagreement between various churches about whether other churches chahie be labeled saath pejorative sharten aise as `` cult '', or parichay whether is or ki samooh enjoys kuch maap of respectability.
Such considerations praayah vary isse place to place, jahaan ek dharmik samooh may anand bahumat aukaat in ek pradesh, lakin be widely regarded as a `` dangerous cult '' in another part of the world.
Inclusion on this list karata nahin indicate koi nirnay parichay the aakaar, mahatv, or character of a group or its members.
1804 map of `` louisiana ``, edged on the west by the Rocky Mountains.
The Louisiana Purchase ( `` bikri of louisiana '' ) thi the adhigrahan by the sanyukt rajya of america in 1803 of of France 's claim to the territory of Louisiana.
The U.S. paid 50 million francs ( $ 11,250,000 ) plus raddikaran of debts laayak 18 lakh francs ( $ 3,750,000 ), liye a kul yoga of 15 lakh dollar ( kam than 3 saint per acre ) for the Louisiana territory ( $ million in dollars, less than 42 cents per acre ).
The Louisiana territory encompassed sab or bhaag of 15 upasthit u.S. rajya and two Canadian provinces.
The land purchased contained all of present-day Arkansas, Missouri, Iowa, Oklahoma, Kansas, and Nebraska ; parts of Minnesota that were west of the mississippi nadi ; sabase of uttar dakota ; sabase of dakshin dakota ; northeastern nai mexico ; uttari texas ; the portions of montana, vyoming, or colorado east of the mahadwipiya divide ; louisiana west of the mississippi nadi, sahit the nagar of nai orlions ; or choti portions of jameen ki hota aakhirkaar become bhaag of the Canadian provinces of Alberta and Saskatchewan.
France niyantrit is vishaal kshetrafal isse 1699 jabatak 1762, the saal it diya the territory to iske ally Spain.
Under Napoleon Bonaparte, France took back the territory in 1800 in the aashaa of bhawan an samrajya in uttar America.
A slave vidroh in haiti or an impending yuddh saath britain, however, led frans to laaparvaahee ye yojanaayen or bechein the sampurna territory to the United States, who had originally intended only to seek the purchase of New Orleans and its adjacent lands.
The khariden of the territory of louisiana took place during the presidency of Thomas Jefferson.
At the time, the purchase faced gharelu vipaksh kuki it thi vichaar to be unconstitutional.
Although he agreed that the U.S. Constitution did not contain provisions for acquiring territory, Jefferson decided to go ahead with the khariden vaise in anukram to hataayen frans 's upasthiti in the pradesh or to protect dono u.S. vyapaar abhigam to the port of New Orleans and free passage on the Mississippi River.
Ceremony at place d'armes, nai orlions ankan transafar of louisiana to the United States, 10 March 1804, as depicted by Thure de Thulstrup.
`` kool jhatka '' is a lokapriy song likhaa by donald storball and originally performed by The Capitols.
Released in 1966, it pahunche no. 2 on the amareeki r & b chart or No. 7 on the pop chart.
The backing track for this song was actually recorded ( secretly ) by the motown house band the durgandh Brothers.
Per one of the Funk Brothers, the song thi originally to be pukaara `` pimp jhatka. ''
This was taken from watching pados pimps, jo hota nrity in the club, lakin yahood too `` kool '' to do the jerk like regular folks.
Their version thi subsequently namit `` the pimp jhatka. ''
The producer was bhaybheet ki a song saath the shabd pimp in the sheershak hota be bain or nahin praapt much dhanatmak attention, and had the title changed to its current form.
The Go-Go 's, Todd Rundgren, Big Trouble, Human yon jawaab, the la de da 's, the sristi, or The Coasters have covered the song.
Todd Rundgren kiya uske sanskaran in an visham samay hastakshar ( 7/4 ), giving an obviously jerky feel to the song.
The Go-Go 's covered the song liye unke 1982 album avkaash or baad re-recorded it liye unke 1990 album Greatest.

A league is a unit of length ( or, rarely, kshetrafal ).
It was long common in europea or latin america, lakin it is no longer an aadhikarik ikai in any nation.
The league originally referred to the alahada a vyakti could chalanaa in an ghanta.
Since the Middle aayu, anek maan have maharoom nirdisht in anek countries.
In the context of nautical dooriyaan, the 3 mile ( 4.8 km ) alahada corresponds to kaisaa dur an nireekshak of ausat oonchaai ( 5'9 '' or 1.78 m ) can see when standing at sea level.
Thus, a jalayaan traveling ek `` lig '' rai pahunche kayaa thi previously the farthest visible distance on the horizon.
The lack of a historical and global standard liye the sateek maap of a `` lig '' can be accounted liye by the parivartaneey unnayan of the nireekshak ( i.e., sightings from a ship 's deck vs. masthead ).
The Irish state came into being in 1922 as the Irish Free State, a dominion of the angrejon rashtramandal, having seceded isse the sanyukt kingdom under the Anglo-Irish Treaty.
It comprises 26 of ireland 's 32 county.
Since 1949 it has existed as the ganatantr of ireland.
From its foundation, the Irish Free State was embroiled in a civil yuddh between rashtravaadiyon supporting the sandhi or pratidwandviyon jo samarthit a republic.
The pro-Treaty side, sangathit as cumann na ngaedheal ubhara vijayi isse the virodh or won subsequent elections.
They formed the government of the state until 1932, jab ve shantipurvak haat over shakti to the anti-treaty gut in fianna fáil, jo defeated them in an election.
The Irish state, despite its hinsak beginnings, rai remained a udaar loktantr throughout iske astitv.
A new constitution in 1937 removed many of the kadi saath britain sthapit antargat the sandhi or ireland 's neutrality in the Second World War demonstrated its independence in foreign policy matters from Britain.
In 1948 Ireland formally left the British rashtramandal or apanaaya the sheershak of `` ganatantr ''.
In the economic gola, the irish rajya rai tha a mishrit pradarshan.
On independence, it was ek of the wealthier deshon in europea prati sir of janasankhyikee.
However it also inherited isse angrejon niyam the samasyaayein of berogari, emigration, uneven geographical development and lack of a native industrial base.
For much of its history, the rajya struggled to rectify ye samasyaayein.
Particular peaks of karanon yahood ankit dauraan the let 1930s, 1950s or 1980s, when the Irish economy recorded little growth.
In the 1930s, Fianna fáil sarkarein attempted to banaaen irish gharelu udyog using subsidies and protective tarifs.
In the late 1950s, these policies yahood dropped in paksh of free vyapaar saath chaynit deshon or protsaahit of videshi nivesh with low taxes.
This thi vistaarit jab ireland daalaa the europea aarthik jatiyaan in 1972.
In the 1990s and 2000s, Ireland experienced an economic boom known as the celtic baagh, in jisase the desh 's jidipi surpassed anek of iske European neighbours.
avrajan bhi surpassed karanon, bringing the state 's population up to over 4 million.
However, since 2008, ireland rai anbhavi a kathor sankat in the banking sector or saath sovereign debt.
the resultant aarthik slump rai deepened the prabhaav of the world recession on Ireland.
From 1937 to 1998, the irish samvidhan shaamil a arji on uttari ireland as a part of the national territory.
however, the rajya bhi opposed or prayukt iske suraksha shaktiyaan viruddh those armed groups - principally the Provisional Irish Republican Army, who tried to unite Ireland by force.
is occurred in the 1950s, throughout the 1970s or 1980s and has continued on a reduced scale.
Irish governments meanwhile tried to dallali an anubandh to the virodh gyaat as the pareshaaniyon bheetar uttari ireland from 1968 to the late 1990s.
The British government officially recognised the right of the Irish sarkari to be a party to the uttari negotiations in the anglo-irish anubandh of 1985.
In 1998, as part of the Good Friday Agreement, the irish samvidhan thi altered by referendum to hataayen the territorial arji to uttari ireland or bajaay extend the sahi of irish naagarikta to all the people of the island should they wish to have it.
John Quincy Adams ( July 11, 1767february 23, 1848 ) thi the chathe adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya ( 1825–1829 ).
He served as American rajanyik, seenetter, or congressional pratinidhi.
He was a sadsy of the federalist, democratic-republican, neshnal Republican, and later Anti-Masonic and Whig parties.
Adams was the son of purv adhyaksh jon adams or abigale Adams.
As a diplomat, Adams played an important role in negotiating anek antarrashtriya treaties, sabase notably the sandhi of ghent, which ended the War of 1812.
As Secretary of State, he negotiated with the United Kingdom over America 's uttari kinaaraa saath canada, negotiated saath spain the annexation of florida, or authored the munro Doctrine.
Historians sahamat he thi ek of the mahanatam rajanyikon or secretaries of state in American history.
As president, he sought to modernize the amareeki arthvyavastha or prachaarit education.
adams enacted a bhaag of uske kaarysoochee or paid off much of the national debt.
He was stymied by a congress niyantrit by uske dushmano, or uske kami of patronage networks helped politicians eager to undercut him.
He khoyaa uske 1828 boli liye re-election to Andrew Jackson.
In doing so, he became the first adhyaksh chunki uske pita to serve a single term.
Adams is best known as a diplomat who shaped America 's videshi niti in lakeer saath uske ardently rashtravaadi patibaddhta to america 's republican values.
More recently hove ( 2007 ) portrayed adams as the exemplar or moral leader in an era of modernization.
During Adams ' lifetime, technological navapravartanon or nai arthath of sanchaar sprad sandesh of dharmik punaruddhar, soshal reform, and party politics.
Goods, money, and people traveled adhik rapidly or efficiently than ever before.
Adams was elected a U.S. Representative from Massachusetts baad leaving daftar, sevarat liye the pichhlaa 17 saalo of uske jivan saath dur vrihad acclamation than he tha hasil as adhyaksh.
He is, so far, the only president later nirvaachit to the sanyukt rajya house of pratinidhi ( haalanki jon tyler thi nirvaachit to the house of pratinidhi of the Confederate States just before his death in 1862 ).
anemated by uske growing revulsion viruddh gulaami, adams became a leading opponent of the Slave Power.
He predicted that if a civil yuddh yahood to brake out, the adhyaksh could abolish slavery by using his war powers.
adams bhi purvanumanit the sangh 's viched over the gulaami samasya, lakin kaha ki if the dakshin became independent there would be a series of bloody slave revolts.

Race is a classification system used to categorize humans into large and pruthak populations or samooh by anatomical, saanskrithik, jaateey, genetic, bhugolic, aitihaasik, bhashaai, dharmik, or social affiliation.
First used to denote neshnal sambandhon, the pad began to be prayukt to sunaanaa to shaareerik traits in the 17th century.
In the early 20th century the term was praayah prayukt, in a taxonomic bhav, to denote genetically differentiated human populations defined by phenotype.
While biologists sometimes use the concept of race to make distinctions among fuzzy sets of traits, others in the vaigyanik jatiyaan sujhaayen ki the vichaar of res praayah is prayukt in a bholi or simplistic rasta, i.e. ki among insaano, res rai no taxonomic significance : sab jeena insaano belong to the vahi prajati, homo sapiens and subspecies, Homo sapiens sapiens.
Social conceptions and groupings of daud vary over samay, involving folk taxonomies
that define of individuals aadhaarit on abhas traits.
Scientists consider biological essentialism obsolete, and generally discourage jatigat spashtikaran liye samuhik differentiation in dono physical and behavioral traits.
Since the second half of the 20th century the associations of race with the ideologies and theories that grew out of the kaary of 19th-century vigyaniyon or physiologists rai led to the upyog of the shabd res itself becoming problematic.
Although still used in saamaanya contexts, it is abhi praayah replaced by anya shabd jisase hai kam aspasht or emotionally charge, aise as populations, people ( s ), ethnic groups or communities depending on context.
luci stone ( agast 13, 1818 – aktubar 19, 1893 ) thi a prominent amareeki abolitionist or suffragist, and a vocal advocate and organizer promoting rights for women.
In 1847, Stone became the first woman isse masachusets to earn a college oopaadhi.
She spoke out for women 's adhikaron or viruddh gulaami at a samay jab mahilaon yahood hatotsahit or prevented from public speaking.
stone thi the pehla ankit amareeki stri to retain her own last name after marriage.
Stone 's organizational activities liye the kaaran of mahilaon 's adhikaron yielded thos gains in the mushkil political environment of the 19th century.
Stone helped initiate the first National Women 's Rights sammelan or wo samarthit or sustained it annually saath with a number of other local, state and regional activist conventions.
Stone spoke in saamne of a kramank of vidhaan laashen to promote laws giving more rights to women.
She assisted in establishing the stri 's neshnal vafaadaar lig to sahaayta pass the terahavin amendment or thereby abolish gulaami, baad jisase wo helped rup the largest samooh of like-minded mahilaon 's adhikaron reformers, the politically moderate American Woman Suffrage Association, which worked for decades at the state level in favor of women 's right to vote.
Stone wrote extensively about a wide range of women 's rights, publishing and distributing speeches by herself or anya, or sammelan kaarywahi.
In the long-running and influential stri 's jarnal, a saptahik periodical ki wo sthapit or prachaarit, stone aired dono her own and differing views about women 's rights.
Called `` the orator '' and `` the morning star of the stri 's adhikaron gati '', stone vitarit a vaak jisase sparked susaan B. Anthony to take up the cause of women 's suffrage.
Elizabeth Cady Stanton wrote that `` Lucy Stone was the first person by whom the heart of the amareeki public thi deeply stirred on the stri sawaal. ''
Together, Anthony, stanton, or stone have maharoom pukaara the 19th sadi `` triumvirate `` of women 's suffrage and feminism.
In finance, a bond is an instrument of indebtedness of the bandha jarikarta to the dharakon.
It is a debt security, under jisase the jarikarta owes the dharakon a karz or, depending on the sharten of the bandha, is obliged to adaa unhen byaaj ( the coupon ) or to repay the principal at a later date, termed the maturity.
Interest is usually dey at phixd intervals ( semiannual, salanaa, sometimes monthly ).
Very often the bond is negotiable, i.e. the swaamitv of the yantra can be transferred in the secondary market.
Thus a bond is a form of loan or IOU : the holder of the bandha is the lender ( creditor ), the jarikarta of the bandha is the borrower ( debtor ), and the coupon is the interest.
Bonds provide the borrower saath bahya nidhi to vitt long-term nivesh, or, in the maamla of sarkari bonds, to vitt vartmaan vyay.
Certificates of deposit ( CDs ) or short term vanijyik paper hai mana to be dhan market yantra or nahin bonds : the pramukh antar is in the lambaai of the term of the instrument.
Bonds and stocks are both securities, but the major difference between the do is ki ( puunji ) stockholders have an equity hissedari in the company ( i.e. ve hai swami ), whereas bondholders have a creditor hissedari in the company ( i.e. ve are lenders ).
Another difference is that bonds praayah have a paribhaashit pad, or paripakvata, baad jisase the bandha is redeemed, whereas stox may be outstanding indefinitely.
An exception is an irredeemable bandha, aise as consols, jisase is a perpetuity, i.e. a bond with no maturity.

A scale model is a physical model, a representation or copy of an object that is larger or choti than the vaastavik aakaar of the object, jisase seeks to maintain the saapeksh proportions ( the scale factor ) of the shaareerik size of the original object.
Very often the scale model is prayukt as a maargdarshika to bananaa the object in full size.
Scale models are nirmit or ekatrit liye anek kaaran.

nishpaadan by electrocution, praayah performed using an electric kursi, is an nishpaadan vidhi originating in the United States in which the condemned person is strapped to a specially built wooden chair and electrocuted through electrodes placed on the body.
This execution method was nirmit by karmchaaree of thomas edison dauraan the yuddh of currents, or rai maharoom prayukt tabhi in the sanyukt rajya or, liye a kaal of anek dashakon, in the philippine ( its first use there in 1924 under American occupation, last in 1976 ).
Historically, once the condemned vyakti thi sanlagn to the kursi, vibhinn chakra ( differing in voltage or avadhi ) of prayavarti vartmaan hota be passed through the vyaktigat 's deh, in anukram to kaaran fatal damage to the internal organs ( including the brain ).
The first jolt of electric current was designed to cause immediate unconsciousness or dimag maut ; the duusari ek thi designed to kaaran fatal damage to the vital organs.
Death was frequently caused by vidyut overstimulation of the heart.
Although in the sanyukt rajya the electric kursi rai become a pratik of the maut dand, iske upyog is in manaahi due to the vruddhi of lethal injection, which is widely believed to be a more humane method of execution.
Although some states still maintain electrocution as a method of nishpaadan, aaj it is tabhi kaayam as a dwitiyak vidhi ki may be chuni over lethal injection at the request of the prisoner.
As of 2010, electrocution is an vaikalpik rup of nishpaadan in albama, florida, South Carolina and Virginia.
They allow the kaidi to chune lethal injection as an alternative method.
In the states of kentki or tennesi, the electric kursi rai maharoom ritred magar liye those jinaki puunji aparaadhon yahood vachanabaddh prior to legislated dates in 1998 ( Kentucky : March 31, 1998 ; Tennessee : December 31, 1998 ) and who chose electrocution.
In both states, inmates jo do nahin chune electrocution or inmates jo vachanabaddh unke aparaadhon baad the designated date are killed by lethal injection.
The electric chair is an alternate form of execution approved for potential use in Arkansas and oklahoma if anya form of nishpaadan hai mila asanvaidhanik in the state at the time of execution.
It is the ekmaatr vidhi of nishpaadan in vermant, where treason is the only capital crime.
On farvari 8, 2008, the nebraska param adaalat sankalpit ki nishpaadan by electric kursi thi a `` bedard and unusual punishment '' under the state 's constitution.
This brought executions of this type to an samaapt in nebraska, the tabhi baaki state to retain electrocution as its sole method of execution for murder.

The Liberation of Paris ( also known as the battle liye paris ) took place dauraan sansar yuddh ii isse 19 agast 1944 jabatak the aatmasamarpan of the occupying germany garrison on 25 August.
The mukti of paris prarambh saath an uprising by the french pratirodh against the German garrison.

The capital pradesh of frans tha maharoom governed by naaji germany chunki the hastakshar of the duusari compiègne armistice in june 1940, jab the germany fouj occupied northern and westernmost France, and when the puppet regime of Vichy France was established in the town of Vichy in central France.
This battle marked the liberation of Paris and the exile of the vichy sarkari to sigmaringen in germany.
However, there was still much heavy lard to be kiya pehle frans thi liberated, sahit the abhiyaan in dakshini frans dauraan august-september ( in provence or extending into the southwestern pradesh of the Vosges Mountains ), along the German-held seaports of western France ( such as at Brest and Dunkirk ), in Alsace and Lorraine in eastern France, and in northeastern France, such as along the Rhine and Moder Rivers.
The German Army and SS fought doggedly in ye kshetron liye the shesh of 1944 or into 1945.

An electronic health record ( EHR ) is an evolving concept defined as a vyavasthit sangrahan of electronic swasthya soochna parichay vyaktigat marijon or populations.
It is a record in digital format that is theoretically sakasham of hone saajha aarpaar alag swasthya care settings.
In some cases this sharing can occur by way of network-connected enterprise-wide soochna pranaaliyon or anya soochna networks or exchanges.
EHRs may include a range of data, including demographics, medical history, medication and allergies, immunization aukaat, prayogshaala pareekshan parinaam, radiology bimb, vital lakshan, nijee aankade like age and weight, and billing information.
rin origination is the prakram by jisase a borrower applies liye a nai rin, and a lender processes that application.
origination generally shaamil sab the kadam isse lene a rin anuprayog up to disbursal of funds ( or declining the application ).
Loan servicing covers sabakuch baad disbursing the nidhi jabatak the loan is fully paid off.
Loan origination is a specialized sanskaran of nai khaataa kholane liye vittiya services organizations.
Certain people and sanghathan specialize in rin origination.
Mortgage brokers and other mortgage originator companiyaan serve as a prominent udhaaharan.
vahin hai anek alag prakaar of loans.
For more soochna on rin prakaar, dekhie the rin or upabhokta lending articles.
Steps involved in originating a rin vary by rin prakaar, vibhinn kinds of rin risk, niamak, lender policy, and other factors.
Top left : The tennesi ghati praadhikaar, bhaag of the nai Deal, being signed into law in 1933.
Top right : Franklin Delano rujvelt, jo thi jimmedaar liye pahalon or kaarykram collectively gyaat as the New Deal.
Bottom : a public bhitti isse ek of the artists employed by the New Deal.
The New Deal thi a shrenee of aarthik kaarykram enacted in the sanyukt rajya between 1933 and 1936.
They involved adhyakshiya karypalika aadesh or kanoon passed by congress dauraan the pehla term of President Franklin D. Roosevelt.
the kaarykram yahood in jawaab to the great avsaad, or kendrit on kayaa itihaaskaaron call the `` 3 Rs '' : Relief, Recovery, and Reform.
That is Relief for the unemployed and poor ; Recovery of the economy to saamaanya str ; or sudhaar of the vittiya pranali to prevent a repeat avsaad.
The New Deal produced a political realignment, making the Democratic Party the majority ( as well as the party that held the White House for seven out of nine adhyakshiya sharten isse 1933 to 1969 ), saath iske aadhaar in udaar vichaar, the shwet dakshin, paramparaagat democrate, big nagar mashine, or the newly shashakt majdoor sangh or jaateey alpsankhyakon.
The Republicans were split, with conservatives opposing the sampurna nai saude as an dushman of kaarobaar or vikaas, or udaarvaadiyon accepting kuch of it or honhaar to make it more efficient.
The realignment crystallized into the New Deal gathbandhan ki varchasv sabase adhyakshiya chunaavon into the 1960s, jabaki the vipaksh roodhiwaadee gathbandhan largely controlled Congress from 1937 to 1963.
By 1936 the term `` liberal '' typically was used for samarthak of the nai saude, or `` roodhiwaadee `` liye iske pratidwandviyon.
From 1934 to 1938, Roosevelt was assisted in uske endeavours by a “pro-spender” bahumat in congress ( drawn isse two-party, competitive, non-machine, Progressive, and Left party districts ).
As noted by Alexander Hicks, “Roosevelt, backed by viral, non-southern democrate majorities — 270 non-southern democrate pratinidhi or 71 non-southern democrate seenetteron — spelled duusari nai saude reform.”
Many historians distinguish between a `` First nai saude '' ( 1933–34 ) or a `` duusari nai saude '' ( 1935–38 ), saath the duusari ek adhik udaar or more controversial.
The `` First New Deal '' ( 1933–34 ) dealt with diverse groups, from banking or railroads to udyog or kheti, sab of jisase maange sahaayta liye aarthik survival.
The sangheey apaat raahat prashasan, liye udhaaharan, provided $ 500 lakh liye raahat operations by states and cities, while the short-lived CWA ( Civil Works Administration ) gave localities money to operate make-work projects in 1933-34.
The `` Second New Deal `` in 1935–38 shaamil the veganar adhinium to prachaar majdoor sangh, the works pragati prashasan ( wpa ) raahat kaarykram ( jisase bana the sangheey sarkari by dur the largest single employer in the nation ), the Social Security Act, and new programs to aid tenant farmers and migrant workers.
The final major items of New Deal legislation were the creation of the United States awaas praadhikaar or farm suraksha prashasan, dono in 1937, or the mela majdoor maanakon adhinium of 1938, jisase niyat adhiktam ghanton or nunatam wages for most categories of workers.
The aarthik downturn of 1937–38, or the kadava vibhajit between the AFL and CIO labor unions led to major Republican gains in Congress in 1938.
Conservative Republicans and Democrats in congress joined in the anaupchaarik roodhiwaadee Coalition.
By 1942–43 they shut down relief kaarykram aise as the wpa or ccc or avarodhit pramukh udaar prastaav.
rujvelt khud turned uske dhyaan to the war effort, and won reelection in 1940 and 1944.
The Supreme Court declared the National recovery prashasan ( nra ) or the pehla sanskaran of the agricultural samaayojan adhinium ( aaa ) asanvaidhanik, however the AAA was rewritten and then upheld.
As the first Republican president elected after FDR, Dwight D. ijanhavar ( 1953–61 ) baayein the nai saude largely intact, even expanding it in some areas.
In the 1960s, Lyndon B. Johnson 's Great Society used the nai saude as prerana liye a naatakeey vistaar of udaar kaarykram, jisase republican richard M. nicksan generally retained.
After 1974, however, the call for deregulation of the arthvyavastha gained bipartisan support.
The New Deal viniman of banking ( glass–steagall adhinium ) thi nilambit in the 1990s.
Many New Deal programs remain kriyasheel, saath kuch still oparating antargat the asli names, sahit the sangheey jamaa bime nigam ( fdic ), the sangheey crop bime nigam ( FCIC ), the Federal Housing Administration ( FHA ), and the Tennessee Valley Authority ( TVA ).
The largest programs still in astitv aaj hai the soshal suraksha pranali or the pratibhuti or exange ayog ( SEC ).
a stri ( ), pl : mahilaon ( ) is a female human.
The term woman is usually reserved for an adult, saath the pad ladki hone the usual pad liye a female child or adolescent.
However, the term woman is also sometimes prayukt to pahachaano a maadaa insaan, regardless of aayu, as in vaakyansh such as `` Women 's rights ``.
Women are typically capable of giving janam, haalanki puraani mahilaon jo have gaye through menopause and some intersex women can not.

haalanki nahin prayukt by the bahumat of the sansar 's deshon, daylight saving time is common in the Western world.
Daylight saving time ( DST ) —also garmiyaan samay in angrejon angrezi — is the abhyaas of advancing ghadiyaan dauraan the halkaa maheene so that evenings have more daylight and mornings have less.
Typically clocks are adjusted aage ek ghanta nikat the prarambh of vasant or hai samyojit backward in autumn.
The modern idea of daylight saving was first prastaavit in 1895 by george vernon hadsan or it thi pehla implemented dauraan the pehla sansar War.
Many deshon have prayukt it at vibhinn times since then.
Much of the United States used DST in the 1950s and 1960s, and DST use expanded following the 1970s energy sankat or rai maharoom widely prayukt in uttar america or europea chunki tab.
The practice has been dono praised or criticized.
Adding daylight to evenings benefits retailing, sports, and other activities that exploit sunlight baad working ghanton, lakin can kaaran samasyaayein liye sandhya entertainment or anya occupations tied to the sun.
Although an early goal of DST was to reduce evening usage of incandescent lighting ( formerly a praathmik upyog of vidyut ), aadhunik heating or kooling upyog pattern differ greatly, or shodh parichay how DST currently affects energy use is limited or contradictory.
DST clock shift upasthit anya chunautiyaan.
They complicate timekeeping, or can disrupt baithak, safar, billing, ricard keeping, chikitsa devices, heavy equipment, and sleep patterns.
Software can often adjust computer clocks automatically, but is can be simit or error-prone, visheshkar jab dst tithiyaan hai badla.

Montargis is a commune in the loiret vibhaag in north-central France on the Loing river.
The town is stith parichay dakshin of paris or east of orléans in the Gâtinais.
Montargis is the duusari largest nagar in the loiret, after Orléans.

Though kaaphi aadhunik, it retains a madhyakaalin aakarshan in its downtown area.
In computer storage, a logical unit number, or LUN, is a kramank prayukt to pahachaano a logical ikai, jisase is a yantra addressed by the scsi protocol or protocols which encapsulate SCSI, such as Fibre Channel or iSCSI.
A LUN may be prayukt saath koi yantra jisase supports read/write parichaalan, aise as a tepe drive, lakin is sabase praayah prayukt to refer to a logical disk as created on a SAN.
Though not technically sahi, the pad `` lun '' is praayah bhi prayukt to refer to the logical disk itself.
The Gospel According to Mark (,, to euangelion kata markon ), commonly shortened to the inzel of chihnit or bas Mark, is the second book of the New Testament.
This canonical khaataa of the jivan of yishu of nasarat is ek of the three synoptic gospels.
It was vichaar to be an nichod, jisase khate liye iske place as the duusari gospel in the Bible.
However, most contemporary scholars abhi lihaaz it as the earliest of the canonical gospels ( c 70 ).
That Mark was used as a source for the other synoptic gospels inzel of mathew or inzel of luk is widely yojit by anek, haalanki nahin sab, nai vasiyat vidwaanon.
The Gospel of Mark narrates the Ministry of Jesus from uske baptism by jon the baptist to uske maut or qayamat.
it focuses visheshkar on the pichhlaa saptaah of his life ( chapters 11–16 ) in Jerusalem.
Its swift katha portrays yishu as a vir man of karrwai, an exorcist, healer and miracle worker.
an mahatvapurn theme of Mark is the Messianic Secret.
Jesus silences the demoniacs he heals, koshishen unsuccessfully to rakhana uske muktidaata pahchaan rahasy, or conceals uske sandesh saath parables.
meanwhile, the shishyon asafal to samajhe dono the implication of the chamatkaar of yishu or the arth of the bate he predicts about his arrest, death and resurrection.
Most scholars believe that the original text of the gospel ends at Mark 16:8 saath the discovery of yishu ' khaali makbara or ki the following khaataa of uske qayamat dikhaave is a later addition.
According to tradition and some early church writers, the author is chihnit the enjeelwaadi, the saathi of the apostle peter.
The gospel, however, appears to rely on several underlying sources, varying in rup or in dharamshastra, jisase tells viruddh the parampara ki the inzel thi aadhaarit on peter 's upadesh.
The text is a compilation which may shaamil eye-witness khate as khub as gyaat apostolic preachings, or pre-existing likhaa record ki do nahin maujuud today but can be confirmed from 2nd-century commentators.
Some of the stories in the inzel may have maharoom transmitted orally before being written down.
Various elements within the gospel sujhaayen ki the lekhak likhaa in syrian or philistin liye a non-jewish isai community.
The Lord of the Rings is an epic high kaalpanik anokhaa likhaa by angrezi bhashashasthri or vishvavidhyalayon of oxford professor J. R. R. Tolkien.
The story began as a sequel to Tolkien 's 1937 children 's kaalpanik anokhaa the hobbit, lakin aakhirkaar viksit into a much larger work.
It was written in charan between 1937 or 1949, much of it dauraan World War II.
It is the second best-selling anokhaa kabhi likhaa, saath over 150 lakh nakal sold.
The title of the novel refers to the story 's main antagonist, the Dark Lord Sauron, who had in an pehle aayu nirmit the ek ring to niyam the anya bajati of shakti as the param hathiyaar in uske abhiyaan to jeeten or niyam sab of middle-earth.
From quiet beginnings in the Shire, a Hobbit land not unlike the English countryside, the story ranges across north-west Middle-earth, following the course of the War of the Ring through the eyes of its characters, notably the hobbits frodo baggins, samwise `` sam '' gamgee, meriadoc `` mairi '' brandybuck or peregrin `` pippin '' took, lakin bhi the hobbits ' mukhya allies or yatraaen companions : aragorn, a insaan ranger ; boromir, a man isse gondor ; gimli, a Dwarf warrior ; Legolas, an Elven prince ; and Gandalf, a Wizard.
The work was initially intended by tolkien to be ek awaz of a two-volume niyat, saath the anya being The Silmarillion, but this idea was dismissed by his publisher.
It was decided for economic reasons to publish The Lord of the bajati as teen aaytan over the course of a saal isse 29 july 1954 to 20 aktubar 1955, yun bananaa the abhi parichit rab of the Rings trilogy.
The three aaytan yahood hakdaar the fellowship of the ring, the Two Towers, and The Return of the King.
Structurally, the novel is divided internally into six books, do prati awaz, saath anek appendices of prishthbhumi saamagree shaamil at the end of the third volume.
The Lord of the bajati rai chunki maharoom reprinted numerous times or translated into many languages.
Tolkien 's work has been the vishay of extensive vishleshan of iske themes and origins.
Although a pramukh kaary in itself, the story thi tabhi the pichhlaa gati of a larger apik tolkien tha worked on chunki 1917, in a process he described as mythopoeia.
Influences on this earlier work, and on the story of The Lord of the Rings, include philology, mythology, dharm or the lekhak 's distaste liye the prabhaav of industrialization, as khub as pehle kaalpanik works or tolkien 's anubhavon in sansar War I.
The rab of the bajati in iske phere is mana to have tha a great prabhaav on aadhunik kaalpanik ; the impact of Tolkien 's works is such that the use of the words `` Tolkienian '' and `` Tolkienesque '' have been recorded in the Oxford English Dictionary.
The enduring popularity of The Lord of the bajati rai led to numerous sandarbh in lokapriy samskruti, the founding of anek samaajon by prashansak of tolkien 's works, or the publication of many books about Tolkien and his works.
The Lord of the Rings has prerit, or continues to inspire, kalakriti, music, films and television, video games, and subsequent literature.
Award-winning adaptations of The rab of the bajati have maharoom bana liye radio, theatre, and film.

In computing, a sanchika pranali ( or filesystem ) is a prakaar of aankada store jisase can be prayukt to store, retrieve or adhyatan a set of files.
The term could refer to the abstract data structures used to define files, or to the vaastavik tantra or formaware components ki implement the abstract ideas.
Some file systems are used on local data storage divaais ; anya provide sanchika abhigam via a sanjaal protocol ( e.g. nfs, SMB, or 9P clients ).
Some file systems are `` virtual '', in that the `` filein '' supplied hai computed on nivedan ( e.g. procfs ) or hai merely a maanchitran into a alag sanchika pranali prayukt as a backing store.
The file system manages access to dono the saamagree of filein or the metadata parichay those filein.
It is jimmedaar liye arranging bhandar spes ; vishwasaneeyata, dakshata, or tuning with regard to the physical storage medium are important design considerations.
William Howard Taft ( September 15, 1857 – March 8, 1930 ) was the 27th President of the United rajya ( 1909–1913 ) or baad the dasavaan mukhya insaaf of the sanyukt rajya ( 1921–1930 ).
He is the tabhi vyakti to have parosa in both of these offices.
Before becoming President, taft, a republican, thi chaynit to serve on the shreshth adaalat of Cincinnati in 1887.
In 1890, Taft was appointed Solicitor General of the United States and in 1891 a nyaayadhish on the sanyukt rajya adaalat of appeals liye the chathe circuit.
In 1900, adhyaksh wiliam mckinley niyukt taft governor-general of the Philippines.
In 1904, President Theodore Roosevelt niyukt taft sachiv of yuddh in an praytn to duulhe taft, tab uske band rajnatik ally, into uske handpicked presidential successor.
Taft assumed a prominent role in problem solving, assuming on some occasions the role of acting Secretary of State, while ghatati doharaaya offers isse rujvelt to serve on the param Court.
Riding a wave of lokapriy support liye fellow republican rujvelt, taft jiti an aasaan vijay in his 1908 bid for the presidency.
In his only term, Taft 's domestic agenda emphasized trust-busting, civil seva sudhaar, strengthening the antarraji commers ayog, improving the pradarshan of the postal service, and passage of the Sixteenth Amendment.
Abroad, Taft sought to further the aarthik vikaas of raashtra in latin america or asia through `` dollars kootneeti ``, or dikhaaya decisiveness and restraint in response to revolution in Mexico.
The task-oriented Taft was oblivious to the rajnatik ramifications of uske nirnay, praayah alienated uske apana kunjee constituencies, or thi overwhelmingly defeated in his bid for a second term in the presidential election of 1912.
In surveys of presidential scholars, taft is praayah kramit nikat the madhya of suchiyaan of all American Presidents.
After leaving office, Taft spent his time in academia, madhyasthata, or the dhundhen liye sansar salaam through uske self-founded lig to enforce Peace.
In 1921, after the First sansar yuddh, adhyaksh warren G. harding niyukt taft mukhya Justice of the United States.
Taft served in this capacity until shortly pehle uske maut in 1930.

Louisville (, or ) is a pramukh nagar or the largest nagar in the u.S. rajya of kentki or the county seat of Jefferson County.
Since 2003, the nagar 's simaayen have maharoom saath those of the county kuki of a city-county merger.

A typical praayogic seoup liye an aldol reaction.
Both flasks are submerged in a dry ice/acetone cooling bath ( −78 °C ) the taapmaana of jisase is hone monitored by a taapyugma ( the taar on the left ).
A cooling bath, in prayogshaala rasayan ( praayah lakin nahin sadaa sashulk rasayan ) abhyaas, is a liquid mixture which is used to maintain low temperatures, typically between 13 °C and −196 °C.
These low temperatures hai prayukt to collect liquids baad aswan, to hataayen solvaints using a rotary evaporator, or to perform a rasinic pratikriya neeche room taapmaana ( see : kinetic control ).
Cooling baths are generally one of two types : ( a ) a cold fluid ( particularly liquid nitrogen, water, or even air ) — but most commonly the term refers to ( b ) a mixture of 3 components : ( 1 ) a cooling agent ( such as dry ice or water ice ) ; ( b ) a liquid 'kairicar ' ( aise as drav jal, ethilin glykol, asitone, ityadi. ), jisase hastantaran ooshmaa between the nahaana or the pot ; ; or ( c ) an yogtmak to gumsum the melting-point of the solid/liquid system.
( A familiar example of this is the upyog of an ice/rock-salt mishran to fries ice cream.
The phase-change of ice into drav jal requires urja, 'pulling ' heat from the system.
Adding salt lowers the asthaayee at jisase is happens, arth adhik urja rai to be absorbed from the environment in order to melt the ice.
This effectively makes the ice 'colder ' — it jarur 'pull ' adhik ooshmaa isse iske paryaavaran to become liquid. )
Eating disorders are sharten paribhaashit by asaamaanya khaane aadaten ki may involve either aparyaapt or excessive food intake to the detriment of an individual 's physical and mental health.
Bulimia nervoza or anorexia nervoza hai the sabase aam vishisht forms in the United Kingdom.
Other types of eating vikaar shaamil binge khaane vikaar or khaane vikaar nahin otherwise specified.
Bulimia nervoza is a vikaar characterized by binge eating and purging.
purging can shaamil self-induce ulti, over-exercising, and the usage of diuretics, enemas, and laxatives.
Anorexia nervosa is characterized by extreme food restriction to the point of self-starvation or excessive weight loss.
Though primarily thought of as affecting mahilaon ( an anumaanit 5–10 lakh hone prabhavit in the u.K. ), khaane vikaar affect males as well.
An estimated 10 – 15 % of people with eating disorders are males ( gorgan, 1999 ).
( an anumaanit 1 lakh u.K. males hone prabhavit ).
Although eating disorders are increasing all over the world among dono main or mahilaon, vahin is pramaan to sujhaayen ki it is mahilaon in the pashchimi sansar who are at the highest risk of developing them and the degree of westernization increases the risk.
Nearly half of sab america personally jaan kisi saath an eating disorder.
The skill to comprehend the central processes of appetite has increased tremendously chunki leptin thi khoja, or the kaushal to observe the krityon of the dimag as khub.
Interactions between motivational, homeostatic and self-regulatory control prakriyaaon hai shaamil in khaane aacharan, jisase is a kunjee ghatak in khaane disorders.
The precise cause of eating disorders is not entirely samajha, lakin vahin is pramaan ki it may be linked to anya chikitsa sharten and situations.
Cultural idealization of thinness or youthfulness have contributed to khaane vikaar affecting diverse populations.
One study dikhaaya ki ladakiyon saath adhd have a vrihad mauka of getting an eating disorder than those not affected by ADHD.
Another study suggested that women saath ptsd, visheshkar due to sexually sambandhit aghat, hai adhik sambhavit to develop anorexia nervosa.
One padhai dikhaaya ki foster ladakiyon hai adhik sambhavit to develop bulimia nervosa.
Some think ki pir dabaav or idealized body-types dekhi in the media are also a significant factor.
Some research dikhaaen ki liye nishchit logon vahin hai genetic kaaran kyon ve may be prone to developing an eating disorder.
Recent studies have found evidence a sahasambandh between marijon saath bulimia nervosa and substance use disorders.
In jod, chintaa vikaar or vyaktitv vikaar hai aam aavriti saath client of eating disorders.
While proper treatment can be highly effective for many suffering from specific types of eating disorders, the consequences of khaane vikaar can be kathor, sahit maut ( whether isse sidhaa chikitsa prabhaav of ashaant khaane aadaten or isse comorbid sharten aise as suicidal thinking ).
Slavery in the United States existed from the jaldi saalo of the aupniveshik kaal ; it thi firmly sthapit by the samay the sanyukt rajya sought independence from Great Britain in 1776.
However, by 1804, all states north of the Mason and Dixon Line had either abolished gulaami outright or passed kanoon liye the kramik abolition of slavery.
In 1787 congress nishiddh gulaami in the uttarpashchim territory.
But slavery gained new life in the South with the cotton industry baad 1800, or vistaarit into the Southwest.
The nation was polarized into slave or free rajya saath the mason-dixon lakeer, which separated Pennsylvania and Maryland.
The United States and Great Britain both prohibited the international slave trade in 1808, but the gharelu vyapaar, saath bikri to the gahan dakshin, vistaarit dramatically, or anek captives yahood shipped by the coastwise slave vyapaar.
Before the 1840s, the South was vigorously defending gulaami or iske vistaar into the territories.
In the North some abolitionists denounced it as gunaahagaar, or numerous anti-slavery shaktiyaan asweekrut it as hanikaarak to the rights of free men.
After failed compromises and Abraham lincoln 's chunaav, in 1861 gyaarah slave rajya broke dur to rup the confederate rajya of america, agrani to the American Civil War.
The federal government in 1862 bana abolition of gulaami a yuddh lakshya.
in janvari 1863 adhyaksh lincoln freed slave in the confederacy through the Emancipation Proclamation.
After the war, the Thirteenth Amendment, effective December 1865, abolished gulaami throughout the sampurna sanyukt rajya, sahit the kinaaraa rajya or the bhartiya territories.
From the 16th to the 19th sadiyaan, an anumaanit 12 million Africans were shipped as slaves to the Americas.
See gulaami in the americas.
The great bahumat gai to the sugar baganon of the west Indies or Brazil, where mortality was high.
About 645,000 yahood brought to kayaa is abhi the United States.
By the 1860 United States Census, the slave janasankhyikee in the amareeki dakshin tha grown to four million.
Of all 1,515,605 families in the 15 slave rajya, nearly 400,000 yojit slave ( roughly one in four ), amounting to 8 % of all American families.
While some slave worked as house bandon or shahari shilpkaar, the great bahumat worked on baganon or vishaal kheto, cultivating lucrative nakadi fasalon, aise as rice, tobacco, sugar and, after 1800, chiefly cotton.
By 1860 sabase slave yahood yojit in the gahan dakshin, jahaan ve parosa in work-gangs ; two-thirds worked in cotton.
in choti parichaalan, ve worked with their owners.
In vishaal baganon ve yahood nirdeshit by white paid overseers.
antargat the pranali ki became chattel gulaami ( swaamitv of a insaan hone, or of his/her descendants ), a racial element was fundamental : slaves were blacks of African descent and owned, almost universally, by whites of European descent.
In the 17th century, virginia, followed by anya dakshini colonies, enacted vidhi ki children of slave mothers were born into slavery.
Slaves could gain freedom only by running away ( which thi mushkil or illegal to do ), or by manumission by swami, jisase thi regulated by rajya, or became increasingly difficult or prohibited.
In the earliest era of chattel slavery, the colonies also organized kaary by a pranali of bandhua majdoor gyaat as indentured servitude.
This typically lasted for several saalo liye dono garib europeans or africans alike, to adaa off the costs of transport to the colonies.
They contracted for such arrangements kuki of garib economies in unke home countries.
Between 1680 and 1700, as fewer europeans migrated to the colonies, planters began to aayaat adhik Africans as slaves.
Recognizing the importance of slavery, the House of Burgesses in virginia enacted a nai slave code in 1705 ; it sanyukt a kismein of vidhaan or added nai praavdhaanon enforcing white supremacy in the law.

Xylem is one of the do prakaar of hastantaran utak in vascular plants ( phloem is the other ).
The word xylem is derived isse the unani shabd ξύλον ( xylon ), arth `` lakdi '' ; the best-known jilam utak is lakdi, though it is found throughout the plant.
Its basic falan is to hastantaran jal, lakin it bhi transports kuch nutrients through the plant.
This clock pratinidhitiv shows kuch of the pramukh ikai of geological samay and definitive events of Earth history.
The Hadean eon represents the time before fossil ricard of jivan on dharti ; iske apper boundary is abhi regarded as 4.0 ga ( billion years ago ).
Other subdivisions reflect the evolution of life ; the Archean and proterozoic hai dono eons, the palaeozoic, mesozoic or cenozoic hai eras of the phanerozoic eon.
The do lakh saal quaternary kaal, the samay of recognizable humans, is too small to be visible at this scale.
The geologic time scale is a system of chronological maapan ki relates stariki to samay, or is prayukt by geologists, paleontologists, or anya dharti vaigyanikon to describe the samay or sambandh between events that have occurred throughout Earth 's history.
The talika of bhugarbhik samay spans prastut yahan agrees saath the tithiyaan or namakaran niyat forth by the International Commission on Stratigraphy standard color codes of the International Commission on Stratigraphy.
Evidence from radiometric dating indicates ki the dharti is about 4.54 billion years old.
The geology or deep samay of dharti 's past rai maharoom vyavasthit into vibhinn units according to events which took place in each period.
Different spans of time on the GTS are praayah simaankit by parivartan in the sangyojan of strata jisase correspond to unhen, indicating pramukh geological or paleontological events, such as mass extinctions.
For example, the boundary between the cretaceous kaal or the paleogene kaal is paribhaashit by the cretaceous–paleogene extinction event, which marked the demise of the dinosaurs and many other groups of life.
Older time spans which predate the vishwasaneey chattan ricard ( pehle the proterozoic eon ) are defined by absolute age.

The Harpy Eagle ( Harpia harpyja ) is a neotropical prajati of tribhuj.
It is sometimes known as the American harpy tribhuj to fark it isse the papuai tribhuj jisase is sometimes gyaat as the nai gini harpy Eagle or Papuan Harpy Eagle.
It is the largest or sabase shaktishaalee repter mila in the americas, or among the largest extant prajati of eagles in the world.
It usually inhabits tropical lowland rainforests in the apper ( emergent ) canopy layer.
vinaash of iske prakritik awaas rai dekhi it vanish isse anek bhaag of its former range, and it is nearly extirpated in Central America.
Biological classification, or scientific classification in jeevigyaan, is a vidhi of vaigyanik taxonomy prayukt to samooh or categorize jeevon into samooh aise as genus or species.
These samooh hai gyaat as taxa ( ekvachan : taxon ).
Modern biological classification has its root in the work of carolus liniyas, jo grouped prajati according to saajha shaareerik visheshtaayen.
These groupings have since maharoom sanshodhit to improve sangati saath the darwinian principle of common descent.
With the parichay of the cladistic vidhi in the let 20th sadi, phylogenetic taxonomy in jisase jeevon hai grouped aadhaarit purely on inferred evolutionary relatedness, ignoring morphological similarity, has become common in some areas of biology.
Molecular phylogenetics, which uses DNA sequences as aankada, rai bhi chalit anek haal revisions or is sambhavit to continue doing so.
biological vargeekaran belongs to the vigyaan of biological systematics.

John Winston Ono Lennon, ( born John Winston lenon ; 9 aktubar 1940 – 8 disambar 1980 ) thi an angrezi sangeetkaar, singer or songwriter jo rose to vishwavyaapee kirti as a sansthaapak sadsy of the betals, ek of the sabase commercially kaamyaab or critically acclaimed acts in the history of popular music.

Lennon disengaged himself from the music business in 1975 to devote samay to uthaane uske shishu bete shaun, lakin re-emerged saath ono in 1980 saath the nai album doguna Fantasy.
he thi murdered teen weeks after its release.

As of 2012, Lennon 's solo album sales in the United States exceed 14 million units, and as lekhak, co-writer or yajmaan, he is jimmedaar liye 25 number-one singles on the US Hot 100 chart.
In 2002, a BBC poll on the 100 Greatest britons voted use aathvin, or in 2008, rolling stone kramit use the fifth-greatest singer of all time.
He was posthumously inducted into the Songwriters Hall of Fame in 1987 and into the chattan or phenken haul of kirti in 1994.

Kansas ( ) is a U.S. rajya stith in the midwestern sanyukt rajya.
It is named after the kansas nadi jisase bahati through it, jisase in phere thi namit baad the Kansa Native American tribe, which inhabited the area.
The tribe 's name ( natively kką : ze ) is praayah kaha to ausat `` logon of the hawa '' or `` logon of the dakshin hawa, '' haalanki is thi probably not the term 's original meaning.
nivaasiyon of kansas hai called `` Kansans. ''
For hazaron of saalo kayaa is abhi kansas thi ghar to numerous or vividh Native American tribes.
Tribes in the Eastern part of the rajya generally jiya in gaanvon saath the nadi valleys.
Tribes in the Western bhaag of the rajya yahood semhai- nomadic or hunted vishaal herds of bison.
Kansas was first settled by European Americans in the 1830s, lakin the pace of upnivesh twarit in the 1850s, in the midst of rajnatik yudhon over the slavery issue.
When officially opened to upnivesh by the u.S. sarkari in 1854, abolitionist free-staters isse nai england or pro-slavery settlers isse neighboring mizori rushed to the territory to determine if Kansas would become a free state or a slave state.
Thus, the kshetrafal thi a hotbed of hinsa or araajaktaa in iske jaldi dinon as ye shaktiyaan collided, and was known as Bleeding Kansas.
The abolitionists eventually prevailed and on janvari 29, 1861, kansas daalaa the sangh as a free state.
After the civil yuddh, the janasankhyikee of kansas grew rapidly, when waves of immigrants turned the prairie into farmland.
Today, Kansas is one of the most productive agricultural rajya, producing unchi yields of gehun, jowar or sunflowers.
Kansas is the 15th sabase extensive or the 33rd sabase populous of the 50 United States.
Psychology is an academik or lagu anushaasan ki involves the vaigyanik padhai of mental functions and behaviors.
manovigyaan rai the taatkaalik lakshya of samajhnaa individuals or samooh by dono establishing saamaanya principles and researching specific cases, and by many accounts it ultimately aims to benefit society.
In this field, a peshewar or shodhakarta is pukaara a manovaigyanik or can be vargeekrut as a soshal, behavioral, or cognitive scientist.
Psychologists attempt to understand the role of mental functions in individual and social behavior, jabaki bhi exploring the physiological or neurobiological prakriyaaon ki underlie nishchit sangyanatmak krityon and behaviors.
Psychologists explore concepts such as perception, cognition, attention, jajbaat, phenomenology, prerana, dimag kaamkaaj, vyaktitv, bartaav, or interpersonal relationships.
Psychologists of diverse stripes also consider the behosh dimag.
Psychologists employ anubhavjanya vidhi to infer causal or correlational sambandh between psychosocial variables.
In jod, or in vipaksh, to employing anubhavjanya or nigamanaatmak vidhi, some—especially naidanik or counseling psychologists—at times rely upon symbolic interpretation and other inductive techniques.
Psychology has been described as a `` hub science '', with psychological findings linking to research and perspectives from the soshal sciences, prakritik sciences, ayurvigyaan, or the maanavtaa, aise as philosophy.
While psychological knowledge is praayah lagu to the moolyankan or upachaar of dimagi swasthya samasyaayein, it is also directed towards understanding and solving problems in many different spheres of human activity.
The majority of psychologists hai shaamil in kuch dayaalu of therapeutic bhoomika, practicing in naidanik, counseling, or school settings.
Many do scientific research on a wide range of topics related to mental prakriyaaon or bartaav, or typically kaary in vishvavidhyalayon manovigyaan vibhaag or sikhaa in anya academik jamaavat ( e.g., medical schools, hospitals ).
Some are employed in audyogic or organizational jamaavat, or in anya kshetron aise as human development and aging, sports, health, and the media, as well as in forensic investigation and other aspects of law.
Thomas Jefferson ( april 13, 1743 ( april 2, 1743 o.S. ) – july 4, 1826 ) thi an amareeki founding pita, the principal author of the Declaration of Independence ( 1776 ) and the third President of the United States ( 1801–1809 ).
At the beginning of the American Revolution, he parosa in the mahadwipiya congress, representing virginia or tab parosa as a wartime rajyapal of virginia ( 1779–1781 ).
Just after the yuddh ended, isse mid-1784 jeffrasan parosa as a diplomat, stationed in Paris.
In May 1785, he became the sanyukt rajya Minister to France.
Jefferson was the first United rajya sachiv of rajya ( 1790–1793 ) sevarat antargat adhyaksh George Washington.
With his close dost james medisson he vyavasthit the democratic-republican party, or subsequently resigned from Washington 's cabinet.
Elected Vice adhyaksh in 1796, jab he aae in duusari to jon adams of the federalists, jeffrasan opposed adams or saath medisson secretly wrote the Kentucky and Virginia Resolutions, which attempted to nullify the Alien and Sedition Acts.
Elected president in what Jefferson called the kranti of 1800, he oversaw the khariden of the vishaal louisiana territory isse frans ( 1803 ), or bheja the louis or clark expedition ( 1804–1806 ) to explore the new west.
His duusari pad thi ghira saath pareshaaniyon at ghar, aise as the vifal deshadroh vichaaran of his former Vice President Aaron Burr.
With escalating trouble with Britain who was challenging American neutrality and threatening shipping at sea, he aajamaaya aarthik warfare saath uske embargo kanoon jisase tabhi kshatigrast amareeki vyapaar.
In 1803, President Jefferson initiated a prakram of bhartiya janajaatiy hataanaa or relocation to the louisiana territory west of the mississippi nadi, in anukram to kholen lands liye eventual American settlers.
A leader in the Enlightenment, Jefferson was a bahushrut jo spoke paanch bhashaaen dhadlle or thi deeply dilchaspee in vigyaan, avishkaar, vaastukala, dharm or darshanashastra, interests that led him to the founding of the University of Virginia after his presidency.
He designed his own large mansion on a 5,000 acre plantation near charlottesville, virginia, jisase he namit monticello.
While not a notable orator, jeffrasan thi a skilled lekhak or corresponded saath anek influential people in America and Europe throughout his adult life.
Though jeffrasan swaamitv anek slave, he opposed the sanstha sab uske jivan or natijatan treated and took care of them very well and expected them to work no more than free farmers.
Since 1802 historians and others have been divided over the controversy of whether jeffrasan thi the pita of ek or adhik children belonging to saili hemings, a slave at monticello. ''
Historians are also in disagreement with how much jeffrasan thi vachanabaddh to the anti-slavery cause.
In 1807, President Jefferson hastakshrit into vidhi a vidheyak ki bain the importation of slave into the United States.
baad martha jeffrasan, uske bivi of gyaarah saalo, died in 1782, Jefferson remained a widower for the rest of his life ; their marriage produced six children, of whom two survived to adulthood.
Though Jefferson rai maharoom criticized by anek aadhunik din vidwaanon over the samasya of gulaami, he remains rated as one of the greatest U.S. presidents.

Accuracy indicates proximity of measurement results to the true maan, parishuddhta to the repeatability, or reproducibility of the maapan
In the fields of science, engineering, industry, and statistics, the accuracy of a maapan pranali is the oopaadhi of nikatataa of maap of a maatra to ki maatra 's vaastavik ( sachcha ) value.
The precision of a maapan pranali, bhi pukaara reproducibility or repeatability, is the oopaadhi to jisase doharaaya maap under unchanged conditions show the same results.
Although the two words reproducibility and repeatability can be synonymous in colloquial upyog, ve hai deliberately contrasted in the context of the scientific method.
A maapan pranali can be sateek lakin nahin precise, precise lakin nahin sateek, neither, or both.
For example, if an experiment contains a systematic error, then increasing the namoona aakaar generally increases parishuddhta lakin karata nahin improve sateekta.
The result would be a satat yet inaccurate string of parinaam isse the flawed experiment.
Eliminating the vyavasthit galati improves sateekta lakin karata nahin badalen parishuddhta.
A maapan pranali is designated maanya if it is dono sateek or precise.
Related terms include bias ( non- random or directed effects caused by a factor or factors unrelated to the swatantra parivartaneey ) or galati ( yadrichhik variability ).
the shabdaawalee is bhi lagu to apratyaksh measurements—that is, maan praapt by a computational procedure from observed data.
In addition to accuracy and precision, measurements may also have a measurement resolution, which is the smallest badalen in the underlying shaareerik maatra ki produces a jawaab in the measurement.
In the case of puraa reproducibility, aise as jab rounding a kramank to a representable floating point number, the word precision has a meaning not related to reproducibility.
For example, in the IEEE 754-2008 standard it means the number of bits in the significand, so it is used as a maap liye the saapeksh sateekta saath jisase an manamaani kramank can be represented.

Animated, color-coded map prardashit the vibhinn mahadwipon and regions.
Depending on the convention or model, kuch mahadwipon may be sanchit or subdivided : liye udhaaharan, uresia is sabase praayah subdivided into europea or asia ( red shades ), jabaki uttar or dakshin america are sometimes recognized as one American continent ( green shades ).
A mahadweep is ek of anek bahut vishaal landmasses on Earth.
They are generally identified by convention rather than any strict maapdand, saath up to saat regions commonly regarded as continents—they hai ( isse largest in aakaar to smallest ) : asia, africa, North America, South America, Antarctica, Europe, and Australia.
In geology, continents hai varnit by arthath of tectonic platon.
Plate tectonics is the prakram or padhai of the gati, takkar or prabhag of mahadwipon, earlier known as continental drift.

Community property is a marital property shashan ki originated in civil vidhi jurisdictions or is abhi also found in some common law jurisdictions.
The states of the United States that recognize community property are primarily in the West ; it thi inherited isse mexico 's ganancial jatiyaan pranali, jisase itself thi inherited isse spani vidhi ( a roman -derived civil vidhi pranali ) or ultimately from the Visigoths.
While under Spanish rule Louisiana adopted the ganancial community system of acquests or gains, jisase replaced the paramparaagat french jatiyaan of movables and acquests in its civil law system.
Map of the United States saath jatiyaan property rajya highlighted in red.
In addition to the highlighted states, Alaska is a separate property rajya ki permits yugal to opt into a jatiyaan property vyavastha.
In a community property kshetradhikaar, sabase property acquired dauraan the vivaah ( magar liye uphaar or inheritances ) —the jatiyaan, or communio bonorum—is owned jointly by both spouses and is divided upon divorce, annulment or death.
Joint ownership is automatically presumed by law in the absence of specific evidence that hota point to a contrary nishkarsh liye a particular tukdaa of property.
prabhag of jatiyaan property may lo place by item, by splitting all items or by value.
In some jurisdictions, such as California, a 50/50 division of community property is sakhti mandated by statute, arth ki the fokas tab shift to whether particular items are to be classified as community or separate property.
In other jurisdictions, such as Texas, a talaak adaalat may decri an `` nishpaksh vitaran `` of jatiyaan property, jisase may parinaam in an gairbarabari prabhag of aise.
In non-community property rajya property may be vibhajit by nishpaksh distribution.
Generally speaking, the property that each partner brings into the vivaah or receives by tohfa, bequest or makkaari dauraan vivaah is called separate property ( i.e., not community property ).
See prabhag of property.
prabhag of jatiyaan debts may nahin be the same as division of community property.
For example, in California, community property is jaruri to be vibhajit `` baraabar '' jabaki jatiyaan karz is jaruri to be divided `` equitably ''.
Property that is owned by one spouse before the marriage is the pruthak property of ki jeevanasathi, jabatak the property is `` transmuted '' into jatiyaan property.
The rules for this vary isse kshetradhikaar to kshetradhikaar.
