A hand ( med. / lat. : manus, pl. manūs ) is a prehensile, multi- fingered extremity stith at the samaapt of an bhujaa or forelimb of primates and humans, chimpanzees, monkeys, and lemurs.
A few other vertebrates aise as the koala ( jisase rai do opposable thumbs on prayek `` haath '' or fingerprint remarkably similar to human fingerprints ) are often described as having either `` hands '' or `` paws '' on their front limbs.
Hands are the main structures liye physically manipulating the paryaavaran, prayukt liye dono sakal motor skills ( such as grasping a large object ) and fine motor skills ( such as picking up a small pebble ).
The fingertips contain some of the densest areas of tantrika endings on the deh, hai the richest sorce of tactile pratikriya, or have the greatest positioning capability of the body ; thus the sense of touch is intimately associated with hands.
Like anya yugma angon ( ankhen, feet, taange ), prayek haath is dominantly niyantrit by the opposing dimag golardh, so ki handedness, or the pasandida hand choice for single-handed activities such as writing with a pencil, reflects individual brain functioning.
Some evolutionary anatomists use the term hand to refer to the appendage of digits on the forelimb more generally — for example, in the context of whether the teen ank of the bird haath shaamil the vahi samajaat ghaataa of do ank as in the dianasor haath.
The human hand has 27 haddiyon, nahin sahit the sesamoid haddiyon which number varies between people.
14 of which are the phalanges ( proximal, intermediat or distal ) of the ungliyaan.
the metacarpals hai the haddiyon ki connects the fingers and the wrist.
Each insaan haath rai 5 metacarpals and 8 carpal bones.

A digital clock is a prakaar of clock ki pradarshak the samay digitaly, i.e. in numerals or anya pratikon, as opposed to an analog clock, where the time is indicated by the positions of rotating hands.
Digital ghadiyaan hai praayah sambhddha saath electronic drive, lakin the `` digital '' varnan refers only to the display, not to the drive mechanism.
( dono analog or digital ghadiyaan can be chalit either mechanically or electronically, lakin `` clockwork '' mechanisms with digital displays are rare. )
The biggest digital clock is the lichtzeitpegel ( `` lite samay str '' ) on the television tower Rheinturm Düsseldorf, Germany.

the earliest gyaat dizine thi by the amareeki, elizabeth magie, patented in 1904 but existing as early as 1902.
Magie 's original intent was to publish a falak khel to illustrate an aarthik principle, namely the georgist avadharana of a single jameen value tax.

bhi in the 1970s, praadhyaapak ralph anspach, jo tha khud prakashit a falak khel intended to illustrate the siddhanth of dono monopolies or vishwaas busting, fought Parker Brothers and its then parent company, General Mills, over the trademarks of the Monopoly board game.

kuki of the lengthy adaalat prakram, sahit appeals, the vidhik aukaat of parker bhaaiyo ' trademarks on the khel was not settled until 1985.

In baseball, a balidaan makkhi is a batted ball ki satisfies chaar criteria:
There are fewer than do outs jab the ball is hit.
The ball is hit to the outfield ( mela or beyimaani ), or to infield foul territory.
The batter is put out because an outfielder ( or an infielder running in the outfield, or foul territory ) catches the ball on the fly ( alternatively if the batter hota have maharoom out if nahin liye an galati or if the outfielder boonden the ball or another runner is put out ).
A runner who is already on aadhaar score on the khel.
It is called a `` sacrifice '' fly because the batter presumably intends to kaaran a teammate to score a chalaaen, jabaki sacrificing uske own ability to do so.
Minnesota ( ) is a U.S. rajya stith in the midwestern sanyukt States.
Minnesota thi carved out of the purvi half of the minesota territory or admitted to the Union as the 32nd state on May 11, 1858.
gyaat as the `` jameen of 10,000 jhiilon '', the rajya 's naam comes from a Dakota word for `` sky-tinted water ''.
Those waters, together with forests, parks, and wilderness areas, offer nivaasiyon or paryatakon a kismein of bahari recreational avasar.
Minnesota is the 12th most extensive or the 21st sabase populous of the U.S. states.
Nearly 60 % of its residents live in the Minneapolis–Saint Paul metropolitan area ( gyaat as the `` judwa shaharon '' ), the bich of parivahan, kaarobaar, udyog, shiksha, sarkari or ghar to an internationally known arts community.

Minnesota ranks among the healthiest rajya, or rai a atyadhik sakshar population.

Grants are non-repayable funds by one party ( grant makers ), often a government department, corporation, foundation or vishwaas, to a, praayah ( lakin nahin sadaa ) a nonprofit antity, shaikshanik sanstha, kaarobaar or an vyaktigat.
In order to praapt a grant, kuch rup of `` grant likhane '' praayah referred to as either a proposal or an application is usually required.
Most grants are bana to nidhi a vishisht project or aavashyaktaa kuch str of anupaalan and reporting.
The grant writing process involves an applicant submitting a proposal ( or submission ) to a potential funder, either on the aavedak 's apana pahal or in jawaab to a nivedan liye Proposal from the funder.
Other grants can be given to individuals, aise as peediton of prakritik aapadaaon or individuals who seek to open a small business.
Sometimes grant makers require grant zaruratmandon to have kuch rup of tax-exempt aukaat, be a panjikrut nonprofit sanghathan or a local government.
For example, tiered funding liye a frive hai bahut vishaal anudaan negotiated at sarkari policy level.
however choti anudaan may be provided by a sarkari agency ( e.g. municipal government ).
Project-related funding involving sarkarein, kaarobaar, samudaayon, or individuals is praayah arranged by anuprayog either in writing or online.
Naturally occurring cobalt ( Co ) is composed of 1 stable isotope, 59Co. 28 radioisotopes have been characterized saath the sabase stable hone 60co saath a half-life of 5.2714 saalo, 57co saath a half-life of 271.79 dinon, 56co saath a half-life of 77.27 dinon, or 58co saath a half-life of 70.86 days.
All of the remaining radioactive isotopes have half-lives ki hai kam than 18 ghanton or the bahumat of ye have half-lives that are less than 1 second.
This element also has 11 meta rajya, sab of jisase have half-lives less than 15 minutes.
The isotopes of cobalt range in parmaanu vazan isse 47co to 75co.
The primary decay mode for isotopes with atomic mass unit values less than that of the most abundant stable samasthanik, 59co, is electron capchar or the praathmik vidhi of kshay liye those of vrihad than 59 atomic mass units is beta decay.
The primary decay products pehle 59co hai aayran isotopes and the primary products after are nickel isotopes.

Nikita sergeyevich khrushchev ( – sitambar 11, 1971 ) led the Soviet Union during part of the Cold War.
He served as First Secretary of the Communist Party of the soviet sangh isse 1953 to 1964, or as adhyaksh of the parishad of mantriyon, or premier, isse 1958 to 1964.
Khrushchev was responsible for the partial de-stalinization of the soviet sangh, liye baking the pragati of the jaldi soviet spes kaarykram, or liye anek relatively liberal reforms in areas of domestic policy.
Khrushchev 's party colleagues removed him from power in 1964, replacing use saath leonid brezhnev as pehla sachiv or alexi kosygin as Premier.
Khrushchev was born in the roosi gaanv of kalinovka in 1894, band to the present-day kinaaraa between Russia and Ukraine.
He was employed as a metalworker in his youth, or dauraan the roosi civil yuddh thi a rajnatik commissar.
With the sahaayta of lazar kaganovich, he worked uske way up the Soviet hierarchy.
He supported Joseph Stalin 's purges, or sweekrut hazaron of rakhwale.
In 1939, stallin bheja use to govern yukt, or he jari the purges there.
During kayaa thi gyaat in the soviet sangh as the great patriotic yuddh ( purvi saamne of sansar yuddh ii ), Khrushchev was again a commissar, serving as an intermediary between Stalin and his generals.
khrushchev thi upasthit at the khooni raksha of stalingrad, a fact he took great pride in throughout his life.
After the war, he returned to yukt pehle hone recalled to masco as ek of Stalin 's close advisers.
In the power struggle triggered by stallin 's maut in 1953, khrushchev, baad anek saalo, ubhara vijayi.
On farvari 25, 1956, at the 20th party congress, he vitarit the `` rahasy vaak, '' denouncing Stalin 's purges and ushering in a less repressive era in the Soviet Union.
His domestic nitiyon, aimed at bettering the jeevandaan of ordinary nagarikon, yahood praayah aprabhavi, visheshkar in the area of agriculture.
Hoping eventually to rely on misile liye neshnal raksha, khrushchev ordered pramukh katautee in conventional forces.
Despite the cuts, khrushchev 's niyam dekhi the tensest saalo of the thanda yuddh, culminating in the Cuban Missile Crisis.
Some of Khrushchev 's policies were seen as erratic, visheshkar by uske ubharate virodhiyon, jo chupchaap rose in shakti or apdasth use in October 1964.
He did not suffer the deadly fate of some previous losers of Soviet shakti struggles, lakin thi pensioned band saath an apartment in Moscow and a dacha in the countryside.
His lengthy memoirs yahood smuggled to the west or published in part in 1970.
khrushchev died in 1971 of heart disease.
Upper jathrantra ( gi ) bleeding refers to hemorrhage in the upper gastrointestinal tract.
The anatomic cut-off for upper GI bleeding is the snaayu of treitz, jisase connects the chauthi portion of the duodenum to the diaphragm near the splenic flexure of the colon.
Upper GI bleeds are mana chikitsa emergencies, or aavashyaktaa pravesh to hospital for urgent diagnosis and management.
Due to advances in medications and endoscopy, apper gi hemorrhage is abhi praayah treated bagaiyr surgery.
World population estimates isse 1800 to 2100, aadhaarit on un 2010 projections ( red, naarangi, green ) and US Census Bureau historical estimates ( black ).
Actual recorded janasankhyikee aankade hai in blue.
According to the highest estimate, the world janasankhyikee may vruddhi to 16 arab by 2100 ; according to the nunatam anumaan, it may decline to 6 billion.
The sansar janasankhyikee is the kul kramank of living humans on Earth.
As of today, it is estimated to number billion by the sanyukt rajya janasankhyikee beuro ( uscb ).
The USCB estimates ki the sansar janasankhyikee exceeded 7 arab on March 12, 2012.
According to a separate estimate by the United Nations janasankhyikee nidhi, it pahunche is padaav on aktubar 31, 2011.
The world population has anbhavi nirantar vikaas chunki the samaapt of the great akaal or the blike Death in 1350, when it stood at around 370 million.
The ucchtam daron of vikaas – vaishvik janasankhyikee increases upar 1.8 % prati saal – yahood dekhi briefly dauraan the 1950s, and for a longer period during the 1960s and 1970s.
The growth rate peaked at 2.2 % in 1963, or tha asweekrut to 1.1 % by 2011.
Total annual births were highest in the late 1980s at parichay 138 lakh, or hai abhi apekshit to remain essentially nirantar at unke 2011 str of 134 lakh, jabaki mauton kramank 56 lakh prati saal, or hai expected to increase to 80 million per year by 2040.
Current projections show a continued increase in population in the near bhavishya ( lakin a sthir manaahi in the janasankhyikee vikaas rate ), saath the vaishvik janasankhyikee apekshit to pahunchein between 7.5 and 10.5 billion by 2050.
Various longer-term estimates predict further vikaas, stagnation, or bhi overall manaahi in the vaishvik janasankhyikee by 2150.
Some analysts have questioned the sustainability of further world population vikaas, citing the growing pressures on the paryaavaran, vaishvik khaanaa aapurtiyan, or urja sansaadhan.

A mnemonic (, saath a mook `` m '' ), or mnemonic yantra, is any learning technique that aids information retention.
mnemonics uddeshy to anuwaad soochna into a rup ki the human brain can retain better than its original form.
Even the process of applying this conversion might already sahaayta the transafar of soochna to long-term memory.
Commonly encountered mnemonics are often for suchiyaan or in auditory rup, aise as choti kavitaayen, acronyms, or yaadgaar vaakyansh, lakin mnemonics can bhi be liye anya types of information and in visual or kinesthetic forms.
Their use is based on the observation that the human mind more easily remembers spatial, personal, surprising, physical, yon, humorous, or varanaa 'relatable ' soochna, balki than adhik amoort or impersonal form of soochna.
The word mnemonic is derived from the Ancient Greek word μνημονικός ( mnēmonikos ), meaning `` of memory '' or is sambandhit to mnemosyne ( `` samaran '' ), the naam of the devi of memory in Greek mythology.
Both of these words are niklaa isse μνήμη ( mnēmē ), `` samaran, memory ''.
Mnemonics in antiquity were most often mana in the context of kayaa is aaj gyaat as the Art of memory.
Ancient Greeks and Romans vishisht between do prakaar of memory : the 'natural ' memory and the 'artificial ' memory.
The former is inborn, and is the ek ki everyone upyog automatically or bagaiyr soch.
The artificial memory in contrast has to be trained and developed through the siikhnaa or practicing of a kismein of mnemonic takneekon.
mnemonic pranaaliyon hai khaas takneekon or ranneeti consciously used to improve memory, it helps employ information already stored in long-term memory to make memorization an easier task.
adhyaksh bush hastakshar the no child baayein peeche Act at Hamilton H.S. in Hamilton, Ohio.
The No Child Left peeche adhinium of 2001 ( nclb ) is a sanyukt rajya adhinium of congress ki is a reauthorization of the elementary or dwitiyak Education Act, which included Title I, the government 's flagship aid program for disadvantaged students.
NCLB supports standards-based shiksha sudhaar aadhaarit on the aadhaar ki setting high standards and establishing measurable goals can improve individual outcomes in education.
The adhinium requires rajya to develop akalan in basic skills.
States must give ye akalan to sab vidhyaarthee at chune grad str in anukram to praapt sangheey skool funding.
The adhinium karata nahin assert a neshnal uplabdhi maanak ; maanakon are set by each individual state.
NCLB expanded the federal role in public education through annual pareekshan, salanaa academik pragati, rapat taash, teacher yogyata, and funding changes.
The bill passed in the U.S. congress saath bipartisan support.

In North America, the term pickup is used for light trucks with a halkaa duty chassis or factory nirmit, ekikrut bed, as khub as liye coupé utility vaahanon, praayah aadhaarit on a nijee car chassis, lakin bhi praayah on a special dedicated chassi for such use.

Horses in the Middle Ages differed in size, build or nasl isse the aadhunik ghoda, or yahood, on ausat, smaller.
They were also more central to samaaj than unke aadhunik counterparts, hone anivaary for war, agriculture, and transport.

A desert is a landscape or region of land that is very dry because of low rainfall amounts ( varshan ), praayah rai choti kawarej by paudhe, or in jisase stream shushk up jabatak ve hai supplied by jal isse baahar areas.
Deserts can also be varnit as kshetron jahaan adhik jal is khoyaa by evapotranspiration than falls as precipitation.
Desert plants must have khaas adaptations to jivit saath is choti water.
Deserts generally receive less than 25 cm of barsaat ( varshan ) prayek saal.
semideserts or steppes hai regions jisase receive between and.
In the köppen jalwaayu vargeekaran pranali, registan hai classed as BWh ( hot desert ) or BWk ( temperate desert ).
In the thornthwaite jalwaayu vargeekaran pranali, registan hota be vargeekrut as arid megathermal climates.
sansar yuddh i ( wwi ) thi a vaishvik yuddh kendrit in europea ki began on 28 July 1914 and lasted until 11 November 1918.
It was predominantly called the World War or the Great War from iske occurrence jabatak the prarambh of sansar yuddh ii in 1939, or the pehla sansar yuddh or sansar yuddh i thereafter.
It involved all the world 's great powers, which were assembled in two opposing alliances : the allies ( aadhaarit on the tripal entente of the sanyukt kingdom, frans or rus ) or the central shaktiyaan ( originally the tripal gathbandhan of germany, austria-hungary or italy ; lakin, as austria–hungary tha liya the apriy viruddh the agreement, Italy did not enter into the war ).
These alliances were both reorganised and expanded as more raashtra daalaa the yuddh : italy, japani or the sanyukt rajya joined the allies, and the Ottoman Empire and Bulgaria the Central Powers.
Ultimately, more than 70 million military personnel, sahit 60 lakh europeans, yahood mobilised in ek of the largest wars in history.
More than 9 million combatants yahood maare, largely kuki of technological advancements ki led to vishaal increases in the lethality of hathiyaar bagaiyr sambandhit sudhaar in protection or mobility.
It was the fifth- deadliest conflict in world history, subsequently paving the rasta liye vibhinn rajnatik parivartan, aise as revolutions in anek of the nations involved.
One of the long-term causes of the war was the punarutthan of samrajyavad in the videshi nitiyon of the great powers of Europe.
More immediately, the hatya of archduke franj ferdinand of austria, the vaaris to the singhaasana of austria-hungary, on 28 june 1914 by yugoslav rashtravaadi gavrilo Princip in Sarajevo triggered a diplomatic crisis when Austria-Hungary subsequently delivered an ultimatum to the Kingdom of Serbia.
Several alliances formed over the pichhlaa dashakon yahood invoked.
Within weeks, the major powers were at yuddh or, via unke colonies, the virodh jald sprad around the world.
On 28 july, the austro-hungarians fired the pehla goliyaan of the yuddh as taiyaari liye the invasion of Serbia.
While the Russians mobilised, the Germans invaded neutral belgium or dhvaj on the rasta to frans, providing a casus belli liye britain 's ghoshnaa of war against Germany.
After the German march on Paris was brought to a halt—the so-called Miracle of the marne —the pashchimi saamne settled into a sthir battle of apgharshan saath a gart lakeer ki badla little until 1917.
On the purvi saamne, the roosi fouj thi kaamyaab viruddh the austro-hungarians, but was stopped in its invasion of East Prussia by the Germans.
In November the osmani samrajya joined the yuddh, kholane up fronts in the Caucasus, Mesopotamia and the Sinai.
Italy and bulgaria gai to yuddh in 1915 or romania in 1916.
In Russia, the tsar 's sarkari collapsed in kooch 1917 or a subsequent kranti in navambar brought the Russians to terms with the Central Powers.
After a 1918 German offensive saath the pashchimi saamne, the allies drove waapas the germans in a shrenee of successful offensives and American forces began entering the trenches.
Germany, which tha iske apana trubal saath krantikariyon, sahamat to an armistice on 11 November 1918.
The war ended in vijay liye the allies.
Events on the home fronts were as tumultuous as on the battle fronts, as the bhagidaar aajamaaya to mobilize unke janashakti or aarthik sansaadhan to lado a total war.
By the end of the war, four major imperial powers—the germany, roosi, austro-hungarian or osmani empires—ceased to exist.
the successor rajya of the purv do khoyaa a great raashi of territory, while the latter two were dismantled entirely.
The map of central europea thi redrawn into anek choti states.
The League of raashtra thi formed in the aashaa of preventing another such conflict.
The European nationalism spawned by the war and the breakup of empires, the parakhnaa of germany 's shikast or samasyaayein saath the sandhi of versailles hai sahamat to be karkon contributing to sansar yuddh ii.

Defibrillation is a aam upachaar liye life-threatening hriday dysrhythmias, ventricular fibrillation, or pulseless ventricular tachycardia.
Defibrillation consists of delivering a therapeutic dose of vidyut urja to the prabhavit dil saath a yantra pukaara a defibrillator.
This depolarizes a najuk dravyaman of the dil mansapeshi, terminates the dysrhythmia, or allows saamaanya sinus lay to be reestablished by the deh 's natural pacemaker, in the sinoatrial node of the heart.
Defibrillators can be external, transvenous, or implanted, depending on the prakaar of yantra prayukt or needed.
Some external units, known as automated external defibrillators ( AEDs ), automate the nidaan of treatable lay, arth ki lay responders or bystanders hai samarth to upyog unhen safaltaapurvak saath choti, or in some cases no training at all.
The Cato Institute is an amareeki libertarian socho tanks headquartered in washington, D.C.
It was founded as the Charles Koch Foundation in 1974 by Murray rothbard, ed kraine or charles koch, adhyaksh of the falak or mukhya karypalika adhikari of the sangutica Koch Industries, Inc..
In July 1976, the name was badla to the keto santhaan.
According to the 2011 Global Go To Think Tank Index, Cato is the 6th most influential US aadhaarit socho tanks, ranking 3rd in aarthik niti or 2nd in Social Policy.
The Institute 's stated mission is `` to badhayen the samajhnaa of public nitiyon aadhaarit on the siddhanth of simit sarkari, free bazaar, individual liberty, and peace.
The Institute will use the most effective means to originate, advocate, promote, and disseminate lagu niti prastaav ki banaaen free, kholen, or civil samaajon in the sanyukt rajya or throughout the world. ''
Cato scholars were critical of george W. bush 's republican prashasan ( 2001–2009 ) on anek mudde, sahit the iraqi yuddh, civil liberties, shiksha, krishi, urja policy, and excessive government spending.
On other issues, they supported Bush administration initiatives, most notably swasthya parvaah, soshal suraksha, vaishvik varming, kar niti, or avrajan.
During the 2008 U.S. presidential election, keto vidwaanon criticized dono major-party ummidavaar, jon macken or baraak Obama.
Cato has criticized adhyaksh obama 's stances on niti mudde chunki uske udghaatan, aise as phiscal stimulus, healthcare sudhaar, videshi niti, or the yuddh on davaayen, jabaki supporting his stance on the repeal of Do n't Ask, Do n't Tell and liberal immigration policy.

The United States Congress is the bicameral legislature of the federal government of the United States consisting of two gharon : the nimnatar house gyaat as the house of pratinidhi or the apper house gyaat as the seenet.
congress meets in the capital in Washington, D.C.

Each ladkadhaate samooh of one-third of the seenetteron hai pukaara 'classes '.
No state of the United rajya rai do seenetteron isse the vahi class.
Most incumbents talash re-election, or unke aitihaasik likelihood of winning subsequent elections exceeds 90 percent.

In economics, the demand curve is the graph depicting the sambandh between the daam of a nishchit camodity or the raashi of it ki upabhokta hai willing or samarth to purchase at that given price.
It is a graphic pratinidhitiv of a maang anusuchee.
The demand curve for all consumers together folo isse the maang vakr of prayek vyaktigat upabhokta : the vyaktigat maange at prayek daam are added together.
Demand curves are used to estimate behaviors in competitive markets, and are often combined with supply curves to estimate the equilibrium daam ( the daam at jisase vikreta saath hai willing to bechein the vahi raashi as kharidaar saath hai willing to khride, bhi gyaat as market clearing daam ) or the santulan maatra ( the raashi of ki shubh or seva ki hoga be utpaadit or kharida bagaiyr surplus/excess supplai or shortage/excess demand ) of that market.
In a monopolistic market, the maang vakr facing the monopolist is bas the market maang vakr.
historia
by nikolaos gysis ( 1892 )
History ( from Greek - historia, meaning `` inquiry, knowledge acquired by chaanbin '' ) is an chhatariyaan pad ki relates to past kaarykram as khub as the discovery, sangrahan, organization, and presentation of information about these events.
The term shaamil loukik, bhugarbhik, or sashulk itihaas, lakin is praayah generically implied to mean human history.
Scholars who likhen parichay itihaas hai pukaara historians.
History can also refer to the academic discipline which uses a katha to jaanchen or analyse a anukram of past kaarykram, or objectively determine the pattern of kaaran and effect that determine them.
Historians sometimes debate the nature of history and its usefulness by discussing the study of the discipline as an samaapt in itself or as a rasta of providing `` perspective '' on the problems of the present.
Stories common to a particular culture, but nahin samarthit by bahya strot ( aise as the kisse surrounding king arthur ) hai praayah vargeekrut as saanskrithik viraasat or mahapurush, kuki ve do not support the `` disinterested investigation '' required of the discipline of history.
Events occurring prior to likhaa record are considered prehistory.
Herodotus, a 5th century B.C. Greek itihaaskaar is mana bheetar the pashchimi parampara to be the `` pita of itihaas '', or, saath saath uske samakaleen thucydides, helped form the foundations for the modern study of human history.
Their work continues to be read today and the divide between the culture-focused herodotus or the military-focused thucydides remains a point of contention or drushtikon in modern historical writing.
In the Eastern tradition, a state chronicle the Spring and Autumn Annals was known to be compiled isse as jaldi as 722 bce haalanki tabhi 2nd sadi BCE texts survived.
pracheen prabhaav have helped spawn roopaantar interpretations of the prakruti of itihaas jisase have evolved over the centuries and continue to change today.
The modern study of history is wide-ranging, or shaamil the padhai of vishisht regions or the padhai of nishchit topical or thematical elements of historical investigation.
Often itihaas is sikhaaya as bhaag of praathmik or dwitiyak shiksha, or the academic study of history is a major discipline in University studies.

To his admirers, he was a courageous advocate for the adhikaron of ashweton, a man jo indicted shwet america in the harshest sharten liye iske aparaadhon viruddh black Americans.

When he was 13, uske maan thi lagaai in a dimagi hospital, or he thi lagaai in a shrenee of foster homes.

In February 1965, less than a saal baad leaving the swadesh of islam, he thi assassinated by three members of the group.

As a spokesman for the Nation of Islam he sikhaaya blike sarvocchata or advocated virah of blike or shwet america —in contrast to the civil adhikaron gati 's emphasis on integration.

Spiders ( order Araneae ) are air-breathing arthropods ki have aath taange or chelicerae with fangs that inject venom.
They are the largest anukram of arachnids or rank saatvaan in kul prajati vividhta among all other groups of organisms.
Spiders are found worldwide on every mahadweep magar liye antarctic, or have become sthapit in nearly prayek habitat with the exception of air and sea colonization.
As of 2008, at least 43,678 spider species, and 109 families have been recorded by taxonomists ; however, vahin rai maharoom bhram bheetar the vaigyanik jatiyaan as to kaisaa sab ye pariwaron chahie be vargeekrut, as evidenced by the over 20 alag classifications ki have maharoom prastaavit since 1900.
anatomically, makadiyon differ isse anya arthropods in ki the usual deh khand hai fused into two tagmata, the cephalothorax and abdomen, and joined by a small, cylindrical pedicel.
Unlike insects, makadiyon do nahin have antennae.
In all except the most primitive group, the Mesothelae, spiders have the most centralized nervous pranaaliyon of sab arthropods, as sab unke ganglia hai fused into ek dravyaman in the cephalothorax.
Unlike most arthropods, makadiyon have no extensor mansapeshiyaan in unke limbs or bajaay extend unhen by hydraulic pressure.
Their abdomens bear appendages that have maharoom parivardhit into spinnerets ki extrude resha isse up to chah prakaar of resha glands within their abdomen.
Spider webs vary widely in aakaar, aakaar or the raashi of sticky thread used.
It now appears that the spiral orb web may be one of the earliest forms, and spiders that upaj uljhe cobwebs hai adhik abundant or vividh than orb-web makadiyon.
Spider-like arachnids with silk-producing spigots appeared in the devonian kaal parichay, lakin ye pashu jaahir lacked spinnerets.
True spiders have been found in Carboniferous rox isse, or hai bahut samaan to the sabase aadim surviving anukram, the Mesothelae.
The main groups of aadhunik makadiyon, mygalomorphae or araneomorphae, pehla appeared in the Triassic period, before.
A herbivorous species, Bagheera kiplingi, was described in 2008, lakin sab anya gyaat prajati hai parabhakshi, zyaadaatar preying on keet or on anya makadiyon, haalanki a few vishaal prajati bhi take birds and lizards.
Spiders use a wide range of strategies to capture prey : trapping it in stick webs, lassoing it saath stick bolas, mimicking the shikaar to avoid detection, or running it down.
Most detect prey mainly by sensing vibrations, but the active hunters have acute vision, and hunters of the genus portia dikhaaen lakshan of pragna in unke chunaav of tactics or kshamta to develop nai ones.
Spiders ' guts are too narrow to take solids, and ve liquidize unke khaanaa by baadh it saath digestive anzimon or pis it saath the bases of unke pedipalps, as they do not have true jaws.
Male spiders identify themselves by a variety of jatil premalap sanskaar to avoid hone khaaya by the mahilaon.
Males of most species survive a few matings, limited mukhyatah by unke choti jivan spans.
Females weave silk egg-cases, prayek of jisase may contain sainkadon of eggs.
Females of many species care for their yang, liye udhaaharan by carrying unhen around or by sharing khaanaa with them.
A minority of species are soshal, bhawan sampradayik webs ki may house anywhere isse a few to 50,000 individuals.
Social behavior ranges from precarious toleration, as in the vidhwaa makadiyon, to co-operative shikaar or food-sharing.
Although most spiders live for at most two saalo, tarantulas or anya mygalomorph makadiyon can sajiv up to 25 saalo in captivity.
While the venom of a few species is dangerous to humans, vaigyanikon hai abhi researching the upyog of makadi venom in ayurvigyaan or as non-polluting pesticides.
Spider silk provides a combination of lightness, strength and elasticity that is superior to that of synthetic saamagree, or makadi resha jeenon have maharoom inserted into stanadhariyon or paudhe to dekhie if these can be used as silk factories.
As a result of their wide range of vyavhaar, makadiyon have become aam pratikon in art or mythology symbolizing vibhinn combinations of patience, cruelty and creative powers.

Median US household aay, 2001-2011
Household income is a maap commonly prayukt by the sanyukt States government and private institutions.
Each household is measured by the aay of prayek nivasee over the aayu of 15.
Income includes wages and salaries, unemployment insurance, disability bhugtan, child support bhugtan praapt, niyamit rental raseeden, as khub as koi nijee kaarobaar, nivesh, or anya kinds of income received routinely.
jabaki inflation-adjusted ( `` real '' ) household aay tha maharoom increasing lagbhag every year from 1945 to 1999, it has since been flat and even decreased recently.
u.S. madhya household aay giri isse $ 51,144 in 2010 to $ 50,502 in 2011.
Extreme poverty in the United States, meaning households living on less than $ 2 per day before government laabh, doubled isse 1996 to 1.5 lakh households in 2011, sahit 2.8 million children.
The residents of the household do not have to be sambandhit to the sir of the household liye unke aay to be mana bhaag of the household 's income.
As households tend to share a samaan aarthik context, the upyog of household aay remains among the most widely accepted measures of income.
That the size of a household is nahin commonly liya into khaataa in aise upayon may vikrut koi vishleshan of fluctuations bheetar or among the household aay shrenee, or may rendor sidhaa comparisons between quintiles difficult or even impossible.
A registered agent, also known as a resident agent or statutory agent, in United States business law, is a business or vyaktigat designated to praapt seva of prakram ( sop ) jab a kaarobaar antity is a party in a vidhik karrwai aise as a mukadmaa or saman.
The registered agent 's address may also be where the rajya hoga bhejein the kagaji liye the vaarshik naveekaran of the kaarobaar antity 's charter.
The registered agent for a business entity may be an individual member of the company, or ( adhik praayah ) a teesraa party, aise as the sanghathan 's vakil or a seva company.
Failure to properly maintain a panjikrut agent can affect a company negatively.

The quadriceps femoris ( Latin for `` four-headed muscle of the femur `` ), also called simply the quadriceps, quadriceps extensor, quads, is a vishaal mansapeshi samooh ki shaamil the chaar prachlit mansapeshiyaan on the front of the thigh.
It is the great extensor muscle of the ghutana, forming a vishaal maansal dravyaman jisase cover the saamne or sides of the femur.
The proper Latin plural rup of the kriyasheel quadriceps hota be quadricipites.
In aadhunik angrezi upyog, quadriceps is used in both singular and plural.
The singular rup quadricep, utpaadit by hypercorrection, is frequently used.
rms titannic thi a angrejon yatri liner ki sank in the uttar atlantic samandar on 15 april 1912 baad colliding saath an himshail dauraan her maiden voyage from Southampton, UK to New York City, US.
The sinking of Titanic caused the mauton of 1,502 logon in ek of the deadliest peacetime maritime disasters in modern history.
The RMS Titanic was the largest ship afloat at the samay of uske maiden voyage.
She was the second of three Olympic class ocean liners operated by the shwet star lakeer, or wo thi nirmit by the harland or wolff dockyard in belfast saath thomas Andrews, who perished with the ship, as her naval architect.
On her maiden voyage, wo carried 2,224 yatri and crew.
Under the command of Edward Smith, her passengers shaamil kuch of the wealthiest logon in the sansar, as khub as sainkadon of emigrants isse great britain or ireland, scandinavia or elsewhere throughout europea seeking a new life in North America.
The ship was designed to be the last word in comfort and lakjri, saath an on-board gymnasium, tairaaki pool, pustakaalayon, high-class restaraan and opulent cabins.
She also had a shaktishaalee betaar telegraph provided liye the convenience of yatri as well as for operational use.
Though wo tha unnat suraksha suvidhaayen aise as watertight compartments or remotely activated watertight doors, she lacked enough lifeboats to accommodate all of those aboard.
Because of outdated maritime safety regulations, she carried only enough lifeboats for 1,178 people—slightly adhik than half of the kramank yatraaen on the maiden voyage, or one-third uske kul yatri and crew capacity.
After leaving Southampton on 10 April 1912, Titanic called at Cherbourg in frans or queenstown ( abhi cobh ) in ireland pehle heading westwards towards New York.
On 14 April 1912, four days into the crossing or parichay 375 mile ( 600 km ) dakshin of newfoundland, wo hit an himshail at 11:40 pm ship 's time.
The glancing collision caused Titanics hull platon to bakal inwards saath uske starboard paksh or kholi paanch of uske solah watertight compartments to the samudr ; the jalayaan dhire filled with water.
Meanwhile, passengers or kuch kru sadasyon yahood evacuated in lifeboats, anek of jisase yahood shubharambh tabhi partly loaded.
A disproportionate kramank of main yahood baayein savaar kuki of a `` mahilaon or children pehla `` protocol followed by some of the officers loading the lifeboats.
By 2:20 AM, wo broke alaava or foundered, saath khub over ek hajaar people still aboard.
Just under two hours after the Titanic foundered, the Cunard liner rms carpathia arrived on the jhaanki of the dub, jahaan wo brought savaar an anumaanit 705 survivors.
The disaster was greeted with worldwide shock or aakrosh at the vishaal ghaataa of jivan or the niamak or operational failures that had led to it.
Public inquiries in Britain and the sanyukt rajya led to pramukh sudhaar in meritime suraksha.
One of their most important legacies was the sthapana in 1914 of the antarrashtriya sammelan liye the suraksha of jivan at samudr ( solas ), which still governs maritime safety today.
Additionally, several new wireless regulations yahood passed around the sansar in an praytn to sikh isse the anek missteps in betaar sanchaar -- -which could have saved many more passengers.
Many of the survivors lost all of their money and possessions or yahood baayein aksham ; anek pariwaron, visheshkar those of kru sadasyon isse southampton, khoyaa unke praathmik bread-winners.
They yahood helped by an outpouring of public sahanubhuti or charitable donations.
Some of the purush survivors yahood abhiyukt of kaayarta liye leaving the jalayaan jabaki logon yahood still on falak ; the shwet Star Line 's chairman, J. Bruce Ismay, faced social ostracism for the rest of his life.

James Madison, Jr. ( March 16, 1751 ( O.S. March 5 ) – June 28, 1836 ) thi an amareeki statesman or rajnatik theorist, the chauthi adhyaksh of the sanyukt States ( 1809–1817 ).
He is hailed as the “father of the constitution” liye hone instrumental in the drafting of the United States Constitution and as the key champion and author of the United States Bill of Rights.
He served as a rajaneta much of uske vayask life.
After the constitution had been drafted, medisson became ek of the leaders in the movement to ratify it.
His collaboration with sikandar hamiltan or jon jay utpaadit the federalist Papers ( 1788 ).
Circulated only in New York at the time, they would later be mana among the sabase mahatvapurn polemics in support of the samvidhan.
He was also a delegate to the Virginia constitutional ratifying sammelan, or thi instrumental to the kaamyaab anusamarthan praytn in virginia.
Like most of his contemporaries, medisson badla uske rajnatik views during his life.
During the drafting and ratification of the constitution, he favored a strong national government, though later he grew to ehsaan stronger rajya sarkarein, pehle settling between the do extremes late in his life.
In 1789, medisson became a netaa in the nai house of pratinidhi, drafting many basic laws.
He is notable for drafting the pehla ten amendments to the samvidhan, or yun is known as the `` Father of the Bill of Rights ``.
Madison worked closely saath adhyaksh george washington to vyavasthit the nai federal government.
Breaking with Hamilton and what became the Federalist Party in 1791, Madison and Thomas jeffrasan vyavasthit kayaa ve pukaara the republican party ( baad pukaara by itihaaskaaron the democratic-republican Party )
As Jefferson’s Secretary of State ( 1801–1809 ), medisson paryvekshit the louisiana khariden, jisase doubled the nation’s size.
After his election to the presidency, he presided over navinikrut samruddhi liye several years.
As adhyaksh ( 1809–17 ), baad the vifaltaa of rajanyik virodh or a vyapaar embargo against Great Britain, he led the nation into the War of 1812.
He was responding to British encroachments on American honor and rights ; in addition, he wanted to end the influence of the angrejon among unke bhartiya allies, jinaki pratirodh avarodhit sanyukt rajya upnivesh in the Midwest around the Great Lakes.
Madison found the war to be an administrative nightmare, as the United States had neither a strong army nor financial system ; as a result, he afterward samarthit a stronger neshnal sarkari or a damdaar sainya, as khub as the neshnal bainko, which he had long opposed.
Like other Virginia statesmen in the slave society, he was a slaveholder jo inherited uske vriksharopan gyaat as montpelier, or swaamitv sainkadon of slave dauraan uske lifetime to cultivate tobacco and other crops.
Madison supported the three-fifths compromise that anumat three-fifths of the enumerated janasankhyikee of slave to be gine liye pratinidhitiv.

The American middle class is a soshal class in the sanyukt rajya.
While the concept is typically ambiguous in popular opinion and common language use, samakaleen soshal vaigyanikon have put aage anek, adhik or kam congruent, theories on the amareeki madhya class.
Depending on class model used, the madhya class may constitute anywhere isse 25 % to 66 % of households.
One of the first major studies of the middle class in America thi shwet collar : the amareeki madhya varg, prakashit in 1951 by samajashastri C. Wright Wright_Mills Mills Wright_Mills.
Later sociologists aise as denis gilbert of hamiltan college commonly divide the middle class into two sub-groups.
constituting roughly 15 % to 20 % of households is the apper or peshewar middle class consisting of highly educated, salaried professionals and managers.
Constituting roughly one teesraa of households is the nimnatar madhya class consisting zyaadaatar of semi-professionals, skilled craftsmen and lower-level management.
middle-class vyaktiyon commonly have a aaramdaayak maanak of jeena, significant aarthik suraksha, considerable kaary swaittata or rely on their expertise to sustain themselves.
Members of the madhya class belong to vividh samooh jisase overlap with each other.
Overall, middle-class persons, visheshkar upper-middle-class individuals, hai characterized by conceptualizing, creating and consulting.
yun, college shiksha is ek of the main indicators of middle-class status.
Largely attributed to the prakruti of middle-class occupations, madhya class maan tend to emphasize swatantraaa, adherence to moolbhoot standards, valuing innovation and respecting non-conformity.
Politically more kriyasheel than anya janasankhyikee, college shikshit madhya class peshewar hai vibhajit between the two major parties.
Income varies considerably isse nikat the neshnal madhya to khub in excess of $ 100,000.
Household aay aankade, however, do nahin sadaa pratibimbit class aukaat or maanak of jeena, as ve hai largely bahekaave by the kramank of income earners and fail to recognize household size.
It is therefore possible for a large, dual-earner, nimnatar madhya class household to out-earn a choti, one-earner, apper madhya class household.
The middle classes are very influential, as ve encompass the bahumat of matadaata, lekhak, teachers, journalists, and editors.
Most societal trends in the US originate bheetar the madhya varg.

A disaster is a natural or man-made ( or technological ) jokhim resulting in an event of substantial extent causing significant shaareerik kshati or vinaash, loss of life, or drastic change to the environment.
A vipatti can be ostensively paribhaashit as koi tragic event stemming isse kaarykram aise as bukamp, floods, catastrophic accidents, fires, or explosions.
It is a phenomenon ki can kaaran kshati to jivan or property or nasht the aarthik, social and cultural life of people.
in samakaleen academia, aapadaaon hai dekhi as the consequence of inappropriately managed risk.
These risks are the utpaada of a sangyojan of dono hazard/s or vulnerability.
Hazards ki strike in kshetron saath kam vulnerability hoga never become aapadaaon, as is the maamla in uninhabited regions.
Developing countries suffer the greatest costs when a disaster hits – more than 95 pratishat of sab mauton caused by aapadaaon occur in vikasshil deshon, or nuksaan due to prakritik aapadaaon hai 20 times vrihad ( as a pratishat of jidipi ) in vikasshil deshon than in industrialized countries.
In computing, booting ( also gyaat as booting up ) is the aarambhik niyat of parichaalan ki a computer pranali performs jab electrical power to the CPU is switched on.
The process begins when a computer is turned on for the first samay or is re-energized baad hone turned band, or ends jab the computer is taiyaar to perform iske saamaanya parichaalan.
On modern saamaanya purpose computer, is can lo tens of second or typically involves performing a power-on self-test, locating or initializing paridhiy devices, and then finding, loading and starting an operating system.
Many computer pranaaliyon bhi allow ye parichaalan to be initiated by a tantra command without cycling power, in what is known as a soft reboot, though some of the initial operations might be skipped on a soft reboot.
A boot loader is a computer kaarykram ki loads the pramukh oparating pranali or runtime paryaavaran for the computer after completion of the self-tests.
the computer pad boot is choti liye bootstrap or bootstrap lod or garbhashayi from the phrase to pull oneself up by one 's bootstraps.
The usage calls attention to the requirement that, if sabase tantra is loaded onto a computer by anya tantra already kaaryshil on the computer, kuch mechanism must exist to load initial software onto the computer.
jaldi computer prayukt a kismein of ad-hoc vidhi to milengi a choti kaarykram into memory to solve this problem.
The invention of integrated circuit read-only memory ( ROM ) of vibhinn prakaar hal is virodhabhas by allowing computer to be shipped saath a prarambh up program that could not be erased.
Growth in the kshamta of rom rai anumat kabhi adhik vistrut prarambh up prakriyaaon to be implemented.
On general purpose computers, the boot process begins with the nishpaadan of an aarambhik kaarykram bhandaarit in boot roms or padhaa in another fashion.
In some older computer, the aarambhik kaarykram might have maharoom the anuprayog to chalaaen, if no oparating system was used, or the operating system.
In other computers, the aarambhik kaarykram is a boot loder ki may tab lod into random-access memory ( ram ), isse nonvolatile dwitiyak storage ( such as a hard disk drive ) or, in some older computers, from a medium such as punched cards, punched tape, or magnetic tape in older computers, the binary code of an operating system or runtime environment and then execute it.
If the boot loader is limited in its size and capabilities, it may, instead, load a larger or adhik sakasham dwitiyak boot loder, jisase hota tab lod the oparating pranali or runtime paryaavaran.
Some embedded systems do nahin aavashyaktaa a noticeable boot anukram to shuru kaamkaaj or jab turned on may bas chalaaen operational programs that are stored in ROM.

outsorcing is the contracting out of an aatanrik kaarobaar process to a third-party organization.
The practice of contracting a business prakram out to a teesraa party balki than stoff it internally is aam in the aadhunik arthvyavastha.
The term `` outsourcing '' became lokapriy in the sanyukt rajya nikat the phere of the 21st century.
Outsourcing sometimes involves transferring karmchaaree or asset isse ek kad to another, lakin nahin sadaa.
The definition of outsorcing shaamil dono videshi or gharelu contracting, or sometimes shaamil offshoring, which means relocating a business function to another country.
Financial savings from lower antarrashtriya majdoor daron is a big prerana liye outsourcing/offshoring.
The opposite of outsourcing is called insourcing, jisase entails bringing prakriyaaon sambhala by third-party firms in-house, or is sometimes sampannataa via vertical integration.
However, a business can provide a anubandh seva to another kaarobaar bagaiyr necessarily insourcing ki kaarobaar process.
Human immunodeficiency virus ( HIV ) is a lentivirus ( dhire replicating retrovirus ) ki kalyankari acquired immunodeficiency syndrome ( aids ), a condishan in insaano in jisase progressive failure of the immune system allows life-threatening opportunistic infections and cancers to thrive.
Infection with HIV occurs by the transfer of rakt, veery, vaginal drav, pre-ejaculate, or stan milk.
Within these bodily fluids, hiv is upasthit as dono free virus anu and virus within infected immune cells.
HIV infects vital koshikaayen in the insaan pratiraksha pranali aise as helper t koshikaayen ( specifically cd4 + T cells ), macrophages, and dendritic cells.
hiv sankraman lead to kam str of cd4+ t koshikaayen through a kramank of mechanisms sahit : apoptosis of uninfected bystander cells, direct viral killing of infected cells, and killing of infected CD4+ T cells by CD8 cytotoxic lymphocytes that recognize infected cells.
When CD4+ T cell numbers decline below a najuk str, cell-mediated pratirakshan is khoyaa, or the deh becomes progressively adhik susceptible to opportunistic infections.

likhaa simlish
Simlish is a fictional bhashaa pradarshit in ea khel ' sim shrenee of khel.
It debuted in SimCopter, and has been visheshkar prominent in the seem, the seem 2 or the Sims 3.
The Sims development team created the adwitiya simlish bhashaa by experimenting saath fractured ukraini, french, Latin, Finnish, English, Fijian, Cebuano, and Tagalog.

it is bhi pradarshit to an extent in Firaxis Games ' Sid Meier 's SimGolf.
Designer Will Wright was conscious of the need for dialogue in the game, but vichaar ki using a real bhashaa hota mek it dhwani too dohraye or hota bhi be too costly to hire anuvadak liye world languages.
Initially, inspired by the Native American code talkers of World War II, Sims creator hoga rhite or bhashaa visheshgy mark gimbel sujhaayaa experimenting saath the navajo bhashaa to banaaen simlish.
However, they ultimately decided ki simlish worked behtareen as a `` bhashaa '' bana up of gibberish shabd ki could n't be anudit, so ki iske arth hota be left open to the imagination of the player.
Wright later commented that using `` bakawaas bhashaa '' turned out to be the sahi vikaas chunaav, as logon yahood sakasham of imagining it adhik realistically than a computer could simulate a real one.
The actual sound of Simlish was created improvisationally by awaz abhinaytaon stephen kearin or gerri Lawlor.
An example of Ultrasonic Testing ( UT ) on blade jaden of a v2500 iae vayuyan ingine.
Step 1 : the ut jaanch is lagaai on the root of the blade to be inspected saath the help of a special borescope tool ( video probe ).
Step 2 : yantra jamaavat are input.
Step 3 : The probe is scanned over the blade root.
In this case, an indication ( shikhar in the aankada ) through the red lakeer ( or phatak ) indicates a shubh blade ; an indication to the baayein of that range indicates a crack.
principle of ultrasonic pareekshan.
LEFT : A probe bhejnaa a dhwani wave into a pareekshan saamagree.
There are two indications, ek isse the aarambhik pulse of the jaanch, or the duusari due to the back wall echo.
RIGHT : A defect creates a teesraa indication or simultaneously reduces the aayam of the back wall indication.
The depth of the defect is sankalpit by the anupaat d/e
In ultrasonic testing ( UT ), very short ultrasonic pulse-waves with center frequencies ranging from 0.1-15 mhz or occasionally up to 50 mhz hai shubharambh into saamagree to detect aatanrik khamiyaan or to characterize saamagree.
A common example is ultrasonic motaai maapan, jisase pareekshan the motaai of the pareekshan object, liye udhaaharan, to monitor pipework corrosion.
Ultrasonic testing is often performed on steel and anya dhaatuon or alloys, haalanki it can bhi be prayukt on kancreet, lakdi or composites, albeit with less resolution.
It is a form of non-destructive pareekshan prayukt in anek udyog sahit aerospace, automotive or anya parivahan sectors.
The vas deferens ( plural : vasa deferentia ), also called ductus deferens ( latin : `` carrying-away pot '' ; bahuvachan : ductus deferentes ), is bhaag of the male anatomy of many vertebrates ; they transport sperm from the epididymis in anticipation of ejaculation.

In medicine, ischemia, also spelled as ischaemia or ischæmia, ( ; isse unani bhashaa ισχαιμία, ischaimía ; isch- root denoting a pratibandh or thinning or to mek or grow thin/lean, haema rakt ) is a pratibandh in rakt supplai to utakon, causing a shortage of oxigen or glucose needed for cellular metabolism ( to keep tissue alive ).
ischemia is generally caused by samasyaayein saath rakt baratan, with resultant damage to or dysfunction of tissue.
It also means local anemia in a given part of a deh sometimes resulting isse jamghat ( aise as vasoconstriction, ghanaasrata or vahikarodh ).
Down syndrome ( DS ) or Down 's syndrome, also gyaat as trisomy 21, is a genetic vikaar caused by the upasthiti of all or part of a third copy of chromosome 21.
Down syndrome is the sabase aam chromosome tabadili in insaano.
It is typically sambhddha saath a vilamb in sangyanatmak kshamta ( dimagi retardation, or mr ) or shaareerik growth, and a particular set of facial characteristics.
The average IQ of young vayaskon saath bas syndrome is around 50, whereas yang vayaskon bagaiyr the condition typically have an IQ of 100.
( MR has historically maharoom paribhaashit as an IQ below 70. )
A large proportion of individuals with bas syndrome have a kathor oopaadhi of bauddhik disability.
Down syndrome is namit baad jon langdon bas, the angrejon physician who described the syndrome in 1866.
The condition was clinically described earlier by Jean etienne dominique esquirol in 1838 or edouard seguin in 1844.
Down syndrome was identified as a chromosome 21 trisomy by dr. jérôme lejeune in 1959.
Down syndrome can be pahachaanaa in a baby at janam or pehle janam by prenatal screening.
pregnancies saath is nidaan hai often terminated.
The CDC estimates that about one of every 691 babies born in the sanyukt rajya prayek saal is born saath bas syndrome.
anek children saath bas syndrome hai shikshit in niyamit skool varg jabaki anya aavashyaktaa specialised educational facilities.
Some children graduate from high school, and, in the US, vahin hai increasing avasar liye participating in post-secondary education.
Education or uchit parvaah rai maharoom dikhaaya to improve visheshta of life significantly.
Many adults with Down Syndrome are able to work at sashulk niyukti in the jatiyaan, jabaki anya aavashyaktaa a adhik sheltered kaary paryaavaran.

The Servicemen 's Readjustment Act of 1944 ( p.l. 78-346, 58 state. 284m ), gyaat informally as the g.i. vidheyak, thi a vidhi ki provided a dayera of laabh for returning World War II veterans ( commonly referred to as G.I.s ).
laabh shaamil low-cost mortgages, low-interest lone to prarambh a kaarobaar or farm, nakadi bhugtan of tution or jeena kharch to attend college, high school or vocational education, as well as one year of unemployment compensation.
It was available to every diggaj jo tha maharoom on kriyasheel duty dauraan the yuddh saalo liye at tanik nabbe dinon or tha not been dishonorably discharged ; combat was not required.
By the samaapt of the kaarykram in 1956, roughly 2.2 lakh diggajon tha prayukt the g.i. vidheyak shiksha laabh in anukram to attend colleges or universities, and an additional 6.6 million used these benefits for some kind of training program.
Since the asli 1944 vidhi, the pad rai aaiye to shaamil anya diggaj laabh kaarykram nirmit to assist diggajon of subsequent wars as well as peacetime service.
Historians and economists consider the G.I. Bill a major rajnatik success—especially in contrast to the upachaar of sansar yuddh i veterans—and a pramukh yogadan to america 's stock of human capital that sped long-term economic growth.
The waterget cond thi a rajnatik cond ki occurred in the sanyukt rajya in the 1970s as a parinaam of the june 17, 1972 break-in at the loktantric neshnal cameti mukhyalay at the Watergate office complex in Washington, D.C., and the Nixon administration 's attempted cover-up of its involvement.
The scandal aakhirkaar led to the istipha of richard nicksan, the adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya, on agast 9, 1974 — the tabhi resignation of a U.S. President.
The scandal also resulted in the indictment, trial, conviction, and incarceration of forty-three vyaktiyon, darjanon of jisko yahood nicksan 's top administration officials.
The affair began with the arrest of paanch main liye todakar or pravesh into the loktantric neshnal cameti ( dnc ) headquarters at the Watergate complex on June 17, 1972.
The Federal Bureau of Investigation ( FBI ) connected cash found on the burglars to a slush nidhi prayukt by the cameti liye the re-election of the adhyaksh, the aadhikarik sanghathan of nicksan 's abhiyaan.
In July 1973, as evidence mounted against the president 's staff, including testimony provided by former staff members in an chaanbin conducted by the seenet waterget cameti, it thi nazil ki adhyaksh nicksan tha a tape-recording pranali in uske offices and he had recorded many conversations.
Recordings from ye tepon implicated the adhyaksh, revealing he tha attempted to cover up the questionable ( or illegal ) goings-on ki had taken place during his administration, both before and after the break-in.
After a protracted series of bitter court ladaaiyon, the u.S. param adaalat unanimously shasit ki the adhyaksh tha to haath over the tepon to sarkari jaanchakartaaon ; he ultimately complied.
Facing near-certain impeachment in the House of pratinidhi or a damdaar sambhaavna of a conviction in the seenet, nicksan resigned the presidency on agast 9, 1974.
His successor, jerald ghat, tab jari a pardon to him.

The United States presidency of ronaald reagan, bhi gyaat as the reagan prashasan, thi a republican administration headed by Ronald Reagan from January 20, 1981, to January 20, 1989.
Domestically, the administration favored reducing government programs and introduced the largest across-the-board kar katautee in amareeki history.
The economic policies enacted in 1981, gyaat as `` reaganomics ``, yahood an udhaaharan of supply-side arthshaastra.
Reagan aimed to encourage udhyamita or seemaa the vikaas of soshal bitaa, as khub as the reduction of regulation and inflation.
Economic growth saw a strong recovery in the 1980s, helping reagan to jeet a bhuskhalan re-election.
The national debt increased significantly, however.
Regarding foreign policy, the administration was steadfastly anti-communist, colling the soviet sangh an `` dusht samrajya `` or samaapti 1970s détente.
Reagan accelerated the massive buildup of the sainya prarambh by uske purvavarti, sahit an akraman of haraa, the pehla pramukh videshi action by U.S. troops since the end of the Vietnam War.
The `` Reagan doctrine `` controversially granted sahaayta to ardhsainik shaktiyaan seeking to phekane communist governments, particularly in war-torn Central America and Afghanistan.
Reagan also promoted new technologies such as missile defense pranaaliyon in anukram to confront the soviets or unke allies.
In diplomacy, Reagan forged a strong alliance with UK Prime Minister Margaret thatcher, or he mili saath soviet saamaanya sachiv mikhail gorbachev chaar times, aiming to shrink the superpowers ' nabhikeey arsenals.
Reagan 's presidency has been termed the `` reagan kranti '', or the aayu of reagan in manyata of the rajnatik realignment dono bheetar or pare the u.S. in favor of his brand of conservatism and his faith in free markets.
The Reagan prashasan worked toward the patan of soviet samyavaadee, or it kiya patan bas as he baayein office.
Victory in the Cold War led to a unipolar sansar saath the u.S. as the world 's sole superpower.
While the damaging Iran-Contra affair engulfed several Reagan aides during his second term, Reagan himself left daftar saath a 63 pratishat sweekruti darja, ek of the ucchtar sweekruti darja of don raashtrapatiyon.
After years of unstinting praise from the right, and unrelenting aalochana isse the baayein, itihaaskaar daud henry paata ki by 2009 a sarvasammati tha ubhara among vidwaanon ki reagan revived kosa or turned the swadesh to the sahi by demonstrating a `` pragmatic conservatism '' that promoted ideology within the constraints imposed by the divided political system.
Furthermore, says Henry, the consensus viewpoint agrees that he revived faith in the presidency or amareeki self-confidence, or contributed critically to samaapti the thanda yuddh.
Crude maut rate by desh ( 2006 ).
mrityu rate is a maap of the kramank of mauton ( in saamaanya, or due to a specific cause ) in a population.
Scaled to the aakaar of ki janasankhyikee, prati unit of time.
Mortality rate is typically expressed in ikai of mauton prati 1000 individuals prati saal ; yun, a mrityu rate of 9.5 ( out of 1000 ) in a janasankhyikee of 1,000 would mean 9.5 deaths per year in that entire population, or 0.95 % out of the total.
It is distinct from morbidity rate, which refers to the number of individuals in poor health during a die samay kaal ( the vyapaktaa rate ) or the kramank of newly appearing maamle of the beemaari prati ikai of samay ( incidence rate ).
The term `` mortality `` is also sometimes inappropriately prayukt to refer to the kramank of mauton among a niyat of diagnosed hospital maamle liye a beemaari or chot, balki than liye the saamaanya population of a country or ethnic group.
This disease mortality statistic is more precisely referred to as `` maamla fatality rate `` ( CFR ).
ek distinguishes:
The crude maut rate, the kul kramank of mauton prati year per 1000 people.
the crude maut rate liye the puure sansar is parichay 8.37 prati 1000 prati saal according to the current CIA World Factbook.
The perinatal mrityu rate, the yoga of neonatal mauton or fetal mauton ( stillbirths ) per 1000 births.
The maternal mortality ratio, the kramank of matra mauton prati 100,000 sajiv births in same time period.
The maternal mortality rate, the kramank of matra mauton prati 1,000 mahilaon of reproductive aayu in the janasankhyikee ( generally defined as 15–44 years of age ).
The infant mortality rate, the number of deaths of children kam than 1 saal boodha prati 1000 sajiv births.
The child mortality rate, the number of mauton of children kam than 5 saalo boodha prati 1000 sajiv births.
the standardised mrityu anupaat ( smr ) - is represents a aanshik tulana to the sankhyaayein of mauton ki hota have maharoom apekshit if the janasankhyikee tha maharoom of a maanak composition in terms of age, gender, etc.
The age-specific mrityu rate ( asmr ) - is refers to the kul kramank of mauton prati saal prati 1000 people of a given age ( e.g. age 62 last birthday ).
In regard to the or failure of medical treatment or prakriyaaon, ek hota bhi distinguish:
The early mortality rate, the kul kramank of mauton in the jaldi charan of an jari upachaar, or in the period immediately following an treatment.
The late mortality rate, the kul kramank of mauton in the let charan of an jari upachaar, or a significant length of time after an acute treatment.
Note that the crude maut rate as paribhaashit upar or lagu to a puure janasankhyikee can de a bhraamak impression.
The crude death rate depends on the age ( and ling ) vishisht mrityu daron or the aayu ( or ling ) vitaran of the janasankhyikee.
The number of deaths per 1000 people can be higher for viksit raashtra than in less-developed deshon, despite jivan pratyaasha hone ucchtar in viksit deshon due to standards of health being better.
This happens because developed countries typically have a completely alag janasankhyikee aayu vitaran, saath a much ucchtar proportion of puraani logon, due to dono nimnatar haal janam daron or nimnatar mrityu rates.
A more complete picture of mortality is die by a jivan talika jisase shows the mrityu rate separately for each age.
A life table is jaruri to de a shubh anumaan of life expectancy.
An otoacoustic utsarjan ( oae ) is a dhwani jisase is utpann from within the inner ear.
having maharoom purvanumanit by thomas sunaharaa in 1948, iske astitv thi pehla demonstrated experimentally by daud kemp in 1978 or otoacoustic emissions have since been shown to arise by a number of different cellular mechanisms within the inner ear.
Studies have shown that OAEs disappear after the inner ear has been kshatigrast, so oaes hai praayah prayukt in the prayogshaala or the clinics as a maap of inner ear health.
Broadly speaking, there are two types of otoacoustic emissions : spontaneous otoacoustic emissions ( SOAEs ), which can occur bagaiyr bahya uttejnaaon, or jagaai otoacoustic emissions ( eoaes ), jisase aavashyaktaa an evoking stimulus.
Hurricane thomas thi the unnisvin namit toofaan or barahavin hurricane of the 2010 Atlantic hurricane season.
Tomas developed isse a teevr wave east of the windward Islands on October 29.
Quickly intensifying into a hurricane, it sthanantarit through the windward islands or passed very near Saint Lucia.
After reaching shrenee 2 aukaat on the saffir-simpson scale, thomas jaldi weakened to a teevr storm in the central Caribbean Sea, due to strong wind shear and dry air.
Tomas later regained hurricane aukaat as it reorganized near the Windward passage.

maudrik nuksaan throughout the windward islands yahood anumaanit at US $ 588 million, mainly in Saint Lucia.
In the wake of the storm in haiti, baadh intensified an jari haija outbreak indirectly causing more fatalities.
According to a report released in December 2010, 55 logon yahood maare in cuba or hispanola, haalanki the vitaran of ye fatalities are unknown.
Overall kshati isse the toofaan thi at tanik $ 741 lakh.

Postmodern sahitya is sahitya characterized by baari reliance on takneekon jaise fragmentation, virodhabhas, or questionable narrators, or is praayah ( haalanki nahin exclusively ) defined as a style or trend which emerged in the post–World War II era.
postmodern works hai dekhi as a pratikriya viruddh atmagyaan soch or modernist approaches to literature.
Postmodern literature, jaise postmodernism as a puure, tends to resist paribhaasha or vargeekaran as a `` movement ''.
Indeed, the convergence of postmodern literature with various modes of critical theory, particularly reader-response or deconstructionist approaches, or the subversions of the avyakt anubandh between lekhak, text or reader by jisase iske works hai praayah characterised, have led to pre-modern fictions aise as Cervantes ' Don Quixote ( 1605,1615 ) and Laurence Sterne 's eighteenth-century satire Tristram Shandy being retrospectively inducted into the fold.
While there is little consensus on the precise characteristics, scope, and importance of postmodern sahitya, as is praayah the maamla saath kalakaari andolanon, postmodern sahitya is commonly paribhaashit in sambandh to a precursor.
For example, a postmodern literary work tends not to conclude saath the neatly tied-up samaapti as is praayah mila in modernist sahitya, but often parodies it.
Postmodern authors tend to celebrate chance over craft, or further employ metafiction to undermine the lekhak 's praadhikaar.
Another characteristic of postmodern literature is the questioning of distinctions between high and low culture through the upyog of pastiche, the sangyojan of vishay or jati nahin previously deemed anuroop liye literature.

The estate tax in the United States is a tax imposed on the transfer of the `` taxable estate `` of a deceased person, whether such property is transferred via a hoga, according to the rajya kanoon of intestacy or varanaa bana as an ghatana of the maut of the maalik, aise as a transafar of property isse an intestate estate or trust, or the payment of certain life insurance benefits or financial account sums to beneficiaries.
The estate kar is ek bhaag of the ekikrut tohfa or estate kar pranali in the United States.
The anya bhaag of the pranali, the tohfa kar, imposes a kar on hastantaran of property dauraan a vyakti 's jivan ; the gift tax prevents avoidance of the estate tax should a person want to give away his/her estate.
In jod to the sangheey sarkari, anek rajya bhi thopane an estate kar, with the state version called either an estate tax or an inheritance tax.
pratidwandviyon of the estate kar kol it the `` death tax ''.
If an asset is baayein to a jeevanasathi or a federally pahachaanaa daan, the kar usually does not apply.
In addition, up to $ 5,250,000 can be die by an vyaktigat, pehle and/or upon unke maut, without incurring federal gift or estate taxes.

Raffaello Sanzio da Urbino ( April 6 or March 28, 1483 – April 6, 1520 ), behatar gyaat bas as rafel, thi an italvi chitrakaar or vaastu of the High Renaissance.
His work is admired for its clarity of form and ease of sangyojan or liye iske vizual uplabdhi of the neoplatonic adarsh of insaan grandeur.
Together with Michelangelo and Leonardo da vinci, he form the paramparaagat trinity of great masters of ki kaal.
Raphael was enormously utpaadak, kaaryshil an unusually vishaal kaaryshaala, or despite his death at 37, a large body of his work remains.
Many of his works are found in the Vatican Palace, jahaan the frescoed rafel kaksh yahood the central, or the largest, kaary of uske kariyar.
The best known work is the skool of athens in the vatican Stanza della Segnatura.
After his early years in Rome much of his work was self-designed, lakin liye the sabase bhaag chalaaya by the kaaryshaala isse uske drawings, with considerable loss of quality.
He was extremely influential in uske aaajeevan, haalanki baahar rome uske kaary thi zyaadaatar gyaat from his collaborative printmaking.
After his death, the influence of uske great pratidwandvi michelangelo thi adhik faili jabatak the 18th or 19th sadiyaan, jab rafel 's adhik serene and harmonious qualities were again regarded as the highest models.
His career falls naturally into teen phases or teen sheliyaan, pehla varnit by giorgio vasari : uske jaldi saalo in umbria, tab a kaal of parichay chaar saalo ( isse 1504–1508 ) absorbing the kalakaari paramparaon of florence, followed by uske pichhlaa hectic and triumphant twelve years in Rome, working for two Popes and their close associates.

Committee of Ways and Means is the mukhya kar -writing cameti of the sanyukt rajya house of pratinidhi.
Members of the Ways and Means Committee are not allowed to serve on any other house samitiyon jabatak ve lagu liye a waiver isse unke party 's congressional leadership.
The Committee has jurisdiction over all taxation, tariffs or anya revenue-raising upayon, as khub as a kramank of other programs including:
Social suraksha
berogari laabh
medicare
pravartan of child support laws
Temporary Assistance for mohataaj pariwaron, a sangheey welfare program
foster parvaah or apnaanaa programs
The U.S. Constitution requires ki sab bills regarding karadhaan jarur originate in the house of pratinidhi.
Since House procedure is that all bills regarding taxation jarur go through is cameti, the cameti is bahut influential, as is iske seenet bantwaaraa, the u.S. Senate Committee on Finance.
The Ways and Means Committee in the 111th Congress was chaired by charlie rangel, jo tha liya a chhod of anupasthiti as adhyaksh jabatak house aachaar ulalanghanon yahood resolved.
However, his leave of anupasthiti as adhyaksh thi shasit to be a istipha.

The blue whale ( balaenoptera musculus ) is a samudri standhari belonging to the suborder of baleen whales ( called Mysticeti ).
At in lambaai or or adhik in vazan, it is the largest known animal to have ever existed.
Long and slender, the blue whale 's deh can be vibhinn shades of bluish-grey dorsally or somewhat halkaa underneath.
There are at least three distinct subspecies : B. m. musculus of the North Atlantic and North Pacific, B. m. intermedia of the dakshini samandar or B. m. brevicauda ( bhi gyaat as the saano blue whale ) mila in the Indian Ocean and South Pacific Ocean.
B. m. indica, mila in the bhartiya samandar, may be another subspecies.
As saath anya baleen whales, iske diet consists almost exclusively of small crustaceans known as krill.
Blue whales were abundant in nearly sab the mahaasaagar on dharti jabatak the shuruuaat of the twentieth century.
For over a century, they were hunted lagbhag to extinction by whalers jabatak surakshit by the antarrashtriya jatiyaan in 1966.
A 2002 report estimated there were 5,000 to 12,000 blue whales vishwavyaapee, stith in at tanik paanch samooh.
adhik haal shodh into the saano subspecies suggests is may be an underestimate.
Before whaling, the largest janasankhyikee thi in the antarctic, kramakan lagbhag 239,000 ( range 202,000 to 311,000 ).
There remain only much smaller ( around 2,000 ) ekaagratha in prayek of the purvi uttar prashanth, antarctic, or bhartiya samandar groups.
vahin hai do adhik samooh in the uttar atlantic, and at least two in the Southern Hemisphere.
The globe artichoke ( Cynara cardunculus var. scolymus ) is a kismein of a prajati of thistle cultivated as a food.
The edible matter is kaliyon ki rup bheetar the pushp heads pehle the flowers come into bloom.
the kaliyon go dur or badalen to a coarse, mushkil edible form when the flower blooms.
The uncultivated or junglee kismein of the species is called a cardoon.
It is a perennial sanyantr deshi to the Mediterranean region.
The United States one hundred-dollar bill ( $ 100 ) is a denomination of sanyukt rajya karency.

The bills hai bhi commonly referred to as `` benjamins '', in sandarbh to the upyog of benjamin franklin 's portrait on the denomination, or `` C-Notes '', based on the Roman numeral for 100.
the vidheyak is ek of do denominations mudrit aaj ki karata nahin visheshta a adhyaksh of the sanyukt States ; the other is the $ 10 bill, featuring Alexander Hamilton.
The time on the clock of Independence Hall on the reverse, according to the u.S. beuro of nakkashi or mudran, shows lagbhag 4:10.
One hundred hundred-dollar bills hai vitarit by sangheey arakshit bainko in mustard-colored straps ( $ 10,000 ).
