David ( ; iesao 259-3 dawid ; ' ; damdaar 's : daveed ) according to the yahudee bible, thi the duusari king of the sanyukt kingdom of israel, or according to the New Testament Gospels of Matthew and Luke, an ancestor of Jesus.
His life is conventionally dinaak to c. 1040–970 bce, uske shasankaal over yahuda c. 1010–1002 bce, or his reign over the United Kingdom of Israel c. 1002–970 BCE.
The Books of Samuel, 1 Kings, and 1 Chronicles are the only sources of information on David, although the Tel Dan stele ( dated c. 850–835 BCE ) contains the phrase ( bytdwd ), read as `` House of David '', which most vidwaanon lo as pushti of the astitv in the mid-9th sadi bce of a judean royal rajvansh pukaara the house of David.
He is depicted as a righteous king, haalanki nahin bagaiyr trutiyaan, as khub as an acclaimed yoddha, sangeetkaar, or kavi, traditionally credited for composing many of the psalms contained in the Book of Psalms.
David is central to yahudee, isai, or islamic doctrine and culture.
biblical parampara maintains ki a sidhaa vanshaj of David will be the Messiah.
In Islam he is mana to be a nabi or the king of a nation.
Kathmandu ( ; ) is the puunji or largest shahari agglomerate of Nepal.
The agglomerate consists of kathmandu mahanagar nagar at iske kor, or iske sistar shaharon Patan, Kirtipur, Thimi, and Bhaktapur.
It also includes the recently pahachaanaa shahari kshetron of shankhapur, karyabinayak, or champapur.
Banepa, dhulikhel, or panauti hai upgrah shahari kshetron of kathmandu located just outside the Kathmandu valley.
Kathmandu is also known informally as `` ktm '' or the `` tri-city ''.
According to a census conducted in 2011, Kathmandu metropolis alone has 975,453 inhabitants ; and the agglomerate rai a janasankhyikee of adhik than 2.5 lakh nivaasiyon.
The metropolitan nagar kshetrafal is or rai a janasankhyikee ghanatv of 19,250 per km2.
The city stands at an unnayan of lagbhag in the bowl-shaped kathmandu Valley of central Nepal.
It is surrounded by four pramukh kyu : shivapuri, phulchoki, nagarjun, and Chandragiri.
Kathmandu Valley is part of three jile ( kathmandu, lalitpur, or bhaktpur ), rai the ucchtam janasankhyikee ghanatv in the country, and is home to about a twelfth of Nepal 's population.
dauraan rana or shah eras, the naam `` nepal '' referred tabhi to the kathmandu ghati ; it thi kayaa people who lived outside the valley called it.
During this kaal, angrejon itihaaskaaron pukaara the ghati itself `` Nepal Proper ''.
Today, Kathmandu is nahin tabhi the puunji of the sangheey loktantric ganatantr of nepal, lakin bhi the mukhyalay of the Central Development Region of Nepal.
The Central Region comprises three zones : bagmati, narayani, or janakapur.
Kathmandu is stith in the Bagmati Zone.
kathmandu is the getwe to paryaton in Nepal.
It is bhi the tantrika bich of the desh 's economy.
It has the most advanced infrastructure of koi shahari kshetrafal in nepal, or iske arthvyavastha is kendrit on tourism, which accounted for 3.8 % of Nepal 's GDP in 1995–96.
( Tourism in Kathmandu asweekrut thereafter dauraan a kaal of rajnatik ashaanti, lakin chunki tab rai improved. )
The city has a rich itihaas, spanning nearly 2000 saalo, as inferred isse inscriptions mila in the valley.
Religious and saanskrithik festivities rup a pramukh bhaag of the jeevandaan of people residing in Kathmandu.
Most of Kathmandu 's logon follow hindutv or anek anya follow buddhism.
There are people of other religious beliefs as khub, giving kathmandu a cosmopolitan samskruti.
Nepali is the most commonly bolaa bhashaa in the nagar.
Nepal Bhasa is the swadeshi bhashaa bolaa by the Newar people.
Hindi is widely understood and angrezi is samajha by kathmandu 's shikshit nivaasiyon.
The city 's sakshartaa rate is 98 %.
Kathmandu 's sister cities ( Lalitpur Patan ) and Bhaktapur are abhinn to kathmandu 's saanskrithik viraasat, paryaton udyog, or arthvyavastha ; isliye unesco 's sansar viraasat sait suchiyaan sab teen shaharon ' smarak or aakarshan saath antargat one heading, `` Kathmandu Valley- UNESCO World Heritage Site ``.
Field hockey, usually referred to simply as hockey, is a team sport of the hockey family jisase is nibhaai between do tiimon of gyaarah khilaadi saath hockey sticks or a mushkil, thos plastic ball.
At the turn of the 21st century, the game is played globally, with particular popularity throughout europea, asia, mahasagariya, or dakshin america – in jod to hone the neshnal khel of pakistani or India.
The term `` field hockey '' is used primarily in Canada, the United States, or anya regions of the sansar jahaan the khel of barf hockey is adhik lokapriy.
During play, goal keepers are the tabhi khilaadi jo hai anumat to tach the ball saath koi bhaag of unke deh ( saath the excepshan of a khilaadi 's haath mana 'part of the stick ' ), saath is tabhi applying bheetar the shooting vrutt ( bhi gyaat as the d, or shooting arc, or just the circle ), while field players play the ball with the flat side of their stick.
the toli ki score the sabase lakshya by the end of the match wins.
If the score is tied at the end of the game, either a draw is ghoshit or the khel goes into atirikt samay and/or a dand golibari, depending on the pratiyogita 's format.
The governing body of hockey is the antarrashtriya hockey sangh ( fih ), saath main or mahilaon hone represented internationally in pratiyogitaaon sahit the olympic khel, rashtramandal khel, hockey sansar cap, champions trophy and Junior Hockey World Cup, with many countries running extensive junior, senior, and masters ' club competitions.
The FIH is also responsible for organising the hockey niyam falak or vikasshil the niyam for the sport.
A popular variant of field hockey is indoor hockey, which differs in a kramank of respects jabaki moort the praathmik siddhanth of hockey.
Indoor hockey is a 6-a-side roopaantar, saath a field jisase is reduced to approximately 40m × 20m.
With many of the rules remaining the vahi, sahit rukaawat or feet, vahin hai anek kunjee visangatiyaan - khilaadi may nahin uthaayen the ball jabatak shooting on lakshya, khilaadi may nahin hit the ball ( instead utilising pushes to transfer the ball ), and the sidelines are replaced with solid barriers which the ball will rebound off.

The World Wide Web ( abbreviated as www or w3, commonly gyaat as the web ), is a pranali of interlinked hypertext documents accessed via the Internet.
With a web browser, one can view web pages ki may contain text, bimb, video, or anya multimedia, or navigate between them via hyperlinks.
Using concepts from his earlier hypertext systems like ENQUIRE, British engineer, computer scientist and at that time employee of the cern, sar tim berners-lee, abhi nideshak of the sansar chaudee web consortium ( w3c ), likhaa a prastaav in kooch 1989 liye kayaa hota eventually become the World Wide Web.

A small submersible AC sump pump saath a garden nalee conector
A sump pump is a pump used to remove water ki rai sanchit in a jal collecting sump jalashay, commonly mila in the tahkhaane of homes.
the jal may daalen via the gheraa naalon of a tahkhaane waterproofing pranali, funneling into the basin or because of rain or natural ground water, if the basement is below the water table level.
Sump panpon hai prayukt jahaan tahkhaane baadh happens regularly or to upaay dampness jahaan the water table is above the foundation of a home.
Sump pumps send water away from a house to any place where it is no longer samasyapurna, aise as a nagarpalika toofaan naalee or a shushk khub.
Pumps may nirvahan to the sanitary siver in puraani sansthapana.
ekbar mana sweekaarya, is abhyaas may abhi violate the plumbing code or nagarpalika bylaws, kuki it can overwhelm the municipal sewage treatment system.
Municipalities urge homeowners to disconnect or reroute sump pump nirvahan away from sanitary sewers.
Fines may be imposed liye noncompliance.
Many homeowners have inherited unke sump pump configurations or do nahin ehsaas that the pump discharges to the sewer.
If the discharge is fed to a laundry doobana in the tahkhaane, it 's sambhavit going to the sewer.
Usually hardwired into a home 's electrical pranali, sump panpon may have a bydaree byaap.
The home 's pressurized water supply powers some pumps, eliminating the need liye vidyut at the vyay of using potable jal, potentially bananaa unhen adhik mahangi to operate than electrical pumps and creating an additional water disposal problem.
Since a sump jalashay may atipravaah if nahin constantly uttejit, a byaap pranali is mahatvapurn liye maamle jab the pramukh shakti is out for prolonged periods of time, as during a severe storm.
There are generally do prakaar of sump panpon — pedestal and submersible.
The pedestal pump 's motor is mounted above the sump, jahaan it is adhik easily sarvice, lakin is bhi more conspicuous.
The pump impeller is chalit by a long, lambavat ekstansion shaft or the impeller is in a scrol housing in the base of the pump.
The submersible pump is entirely arohit andar the sump, or is visheshkar sealed to prevent vidyut short circuits.
Sump pump systems are also utilized in audyogic or vanijyik anuprayog to control jal talika -sunanased samasyaayein in sataha mrudaa.
An artesian aquifer or aavadhik unchi jal talika halaat can kaaran the maidan to become unstable due to water saturation.
as long as the pump krityon, the sataha mrudaa will remain stable.
ye sumps hai typically ten feet in gaharaai or adhik ; lined saath corrugated metal pipe ki contains perforations or drain holes throughout.
ve may shaamil electronic control pranaaliyon saath vizual or audible sachetak or hai praayah covered to prevent debris and animals from falling in.
Bleeding Kansas, Bloody Kansas or the kinaaraa yuddh, thi a shrenee of hinsak rajnatik confrontations involving anti-slavery free-staters or pro-slavery `` kinaaraa ruffian `` tatv, ki took place in the Kansas Territory and the neighboring towns of Missouri between 1854 and 1861.
At the heart of the conflict was the question of whether kansas hota daalen the sangh as a free state or slave state.
As such, Bleeding Kansas was a proxy war between Northerners and southerners over the samasya of gulaami in the sanyukt rajya.
The term `` Bleeding Kansas '' was coined by horess greeley of the nai york tribune ; the kaarykram it encompasses directly presaged the American Civil War.
congress tha long struggled to santulan the ruchi of pro-slavery shaktiyaan or anti-slavery forces.
The events later known as bleeding kansas yahood niyat into gati by the kansas–nebraska adhinium of 1854, which nullified the Missouri Compromise and instead implemented the concept of popular sovereignty.
An ostensibly democratic idea, popular sovereignty stated that the inhabitants of each territory or state should decide whether it hota be a free or slave rajya ; however, is resulted in avrajan en masse to kansas by kaaryakartaaon isse dono sides.
At one point, Kansas had two separate governments, prayek saath iske apana samvidhan, haalanki tabhi ek thi federally recognized.
On January 29, 1861, kansas thi admitted to the sangh as a free rajya, kam than teen maheene before the Battle of Fort Sumter which began the Civil War.
Benzene is an organic rasinic yogic saath the aanvik sutara c6 h|hydrogen|h6.
Its molecule is composed of 6 carbon anu joined in a ring, saath 1 hydrogen anu sanlagn to prayek carbon atom.
kuki iske anuon contain tabhi carbon or hydrogen anu, benzene is classed as a hydrocarbon.
Benzene is a natural constituent of crude aayal, or is ek of the sabase basic petrochemicals.
Benzene is an aromatic hydrocarbon and the duusari [ n ] - annulene ( [ 6 ] -annulene ), a chakree hydrocarbon saath a nirantar pi bond.
It is sometimes abbreviated ph –h. benzene is a colorless or atyadhik jvalansheel liquid with a sweet smell.
It is mukhyatah prayukt as a precursor to baari rasayan, aise as ethylbenzene or cumene, which are produced on a billion kilogram scale.
Because it has a high octane kramank, it is an mahatvapurn ghatak of gasoline, composing a few percent of its mass.
Most non-industrial anuprayog have maharoom simit by benzene 's carcinogenicity.

Wii homebrew refers to the reuse of nintendo 's ve khel consol to run software that has not been authorized by Nintendo.
It achieves this by defeating the Wii 's nakal suraksha or code hastakshar upayon.
In more general terms, Wii Homebrew refers to the use of the ve 's hardware, accessories or tantra liye uddeshy baahar those intended by the manufacturer.

stephen jon hadlee ( born farvari 13, 1947 ) thi the 21st u.S. sahaayak to the adhyaksh liye National Security Affairs ( commonly referred as National Security Advisor ), serving under President George W. Bush.
Take identical growing paudhe or de urvarak to half of them.
If there are differences between the fertilized sanyantr samooh or the unfertilized `` control '' samooh, ye matbhed may be due to the urvarak.
A scientific control is an experiment or observation designed to minimize the prabhaav of parivartaneey anya than the single independent variable.
This increases the reliability of the parinaam, praayah through a tulana between control maap and the other measurements.
Scientific controls are a bhaag of the vaigyanik vidhi.
For example, during drug testing, vaigyanikon hoga koshish to control do samooh to rakhana unhen as ekasmaan as sambhavit, tab allow ek samooh to koshish the drug.
Another example might be testing plant fertilizer by giving it to only half the paudhe in a garden : the paudhe ki praapt no urvarak hai the control samooh, kuki ve sthapit the besaline str of vikaas ki the fertilizer-treated plants will be compared against.
Without a control samooh, the prayog can nahin determine whether the fertilizer-treated paudhe grow adhik than they would have if untreated.
Ideally, all parivartaneey in an prayog hoga be niyantrit ( accounted liye by the control measurements ) and none will be uncontrolled.
In such an experiment, if all the controls work as apekshit, it is sambhavit to conclude ki the prayog is working as intended or ki the parinaam of the prayog are due to the effect of the variable being tested.
That is, vaigyanik niyantran allow an anveshak to mek a arji jaise `` do paristhitiyon were identical until factor X occurred.
Since factor X is the only difference between the do paristhitiyon, the nai nishkarsh thi caused by factor x. ''

John Adams ( October 30, 1735 ( O.S. October 19, 1735 ) – july 4, 1826 ) thi the duusari adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya ( 1797–1801 ), having pehle parosa as the pehla vaais adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya.
An American Founding Father, he was a statesman, rajanyik, or a agrani edwocket of amareeki swatantraaa isse Great Britain.
Well shikshit, he thi an atmagyaan rajnatik theorist jo prachaarit republicanism or likhaa prolifically about his often seminal ideas, both in published works and in letters to his wife and key adviser Abigail as well as to other Founding Fathers.
Adams came to prominence in the jaldi charan of the amareeki kranti.
A lawyer and public figure in boston, as a pratinidhi isse masachusets to the mahadwipiya congress, he nibhaai a leading role in persuading Congress to declare independence.
He assisted Thomas Jefferson in drafting the Declaration of swatantraaa in 1776, or thi iske praathmik edwocket in the congress.
baad, as a rajanyik in europea, he helped negotiate the eventual salaam sandhi saath great britain, or thi jimmedaar for obtaining vital governmental loans from Amsterdam bankers.
A political theorist and historian, Adams largely wrote the Massachusetts Constitution in 1780, jisase saath saath uske pehle vichaar on sarkari, bahekaave American political thought.
One of his greatest roles thi as a nyaayadhish of akshar : in 1775, he manonith george washington to be commander-in-chief, or 25 saalo later nominated John Marshall to be Chief Justice of the United States.
Adams ' krantikari shrey secured use do sharten as george washington 's vaais president and his own election in 1796 as the second president.
During his one term, he encountered ferocious hamale by the jeffersonian republicans, as khub as the prabal gut in uske apana federalist party led by his bitter enemy Alexander Hamilton.
Adams signed the vivaadaaspad alian or rajdroh adhiniyamon, or nirmit up the fouj or navy visheshkar in the face of an undeclared naval war ( called the `` Quasi-War `` ) with France, 1798–1800.
The major accomplishment of uske presidency thi uske shantipurna rezolution of the virodh in the phase of hamiltan 's opposition.
In 1800, Adams was defeated for re-election by thomas jeffrasan or ritred to masachusets.
He later resumed uske dosti saath jeffrasan.
He and his wife, Abigail Adams, founded an sampannataa parivaar lakeer of rajaneta, rajanyikon, or itihaaskaaron abhi referred to as the Adams political family.
adams thi the pita of jon quinci Adams, the sixth President of the United States.
His achievements have received greater manyata in aadhunik times, haalanki uske yogadan yahood nahin initially as manaaye as those of other Founders.
Adams was the first U.S. president to reside in the bhawan ki aakhirkaar became known as the White House.

The steam engine, fuelled primarily by coal, propelled the audyogic kranti in great britain or the world.
The audyogic kranti thi the parivartan to nai nirmaan prakriyaaon ki occurred in the period from about 1760 to some time between 1820 and 1840.
This transition included going from hand production methods to machines, nai rasinic nirmaan or aayran utpaadan prakriyaaon, improved dakshata of jal shakti, the increasing use of steam power and development of machine tools.
The parivartan bhi shaamil the badalen isse lakdi and other bio-fuels to coal.
The Industrial revolution began in britain or bheetar a few dashakon sprad to pashchimi europea or the sanyukt States.
The Industrial Revolution marks a pramukh turning point in itihaas ; lagbhag prayek pahalu of rose jivan thi bahekaave in kuch way.
Most notably, average income or janasankhyikee began to pradarshnee unprecedented sustained growth.
In the shabd of nobel puraskaar vijeta robert E. lucas, jr., `` liye the pehla samay in itihaas, the jeena maanakon of the masses of ordinary logon have begun to undergo sustained growth... Nothing remotely like this economic behavior is mentioned by the classical economists, even as a theoretical possibility. ''
wiliam ghanti scot aayran and Coal, 1855-60
The period of time covered by the audyogic kranti varies saath alag itihaaskaaron.
Eric Hobsbawm held that it 'broke out ' in Britain in the 1780s and was not fully laga jabatak the 1830s or 1840s, jabaki T. S. eshton yojit ki it occurred roughly between 1760 and 1830.
Some 20th-century historians such as John Clapham and Nicholas Crafts have argued ki the prakram of aarthik or soshal badalen took place dhire or the pad kranti is a misnomer.
This is still a vishay of bahes among itihaaskaaron.
GDP per capita was broadly stable before the audyogic kranti or the emergence of the modern capitalist economy.
The Industrial kranti began an era of per-capita aarthik vikaas in poonjivadi economies.
Economic historians are in agreement that the onset of the audyogic kranti is the sabase mahatvapurn event in the itihaas of maanavtaa chunki the domestication of pashu or paudhe.
The First Industrial Revolution evolved into the Second Industrial Revolution in the transition years between 1840 and 1870, when technological and economic progress gained momentum with the increasing adoption of steam-powered naukaaye, jahaajon or rail, the vishaal scale manufacture of yantra tuls or the increasing upyog of bhaap sanchalit factories.

The large aant ( or bowel, colon ) is the pichhlaa bhaag of the digestive system in vertebrate animals.
iske falan is to avashoshit jal isse the baaki indigestible food matter, and then to pass useless waste material from the body.
This article is primarily parichay the insaan aant, haalanki the soochna parichay iske processes are directly applicable to most mammals.
The large intestine consists of the cecum, malashay or guda canal.
It starts in the sahi iliac pradesh of the pelvis, bas at or neeche the sahi qamar, jahaan it is joined to the neeche samaapt of the small intestine.
isse yahan it continues up the udar, tab aarpaar the chaudai of the abdominal guha, and then it turns down, continuing to its endpoint at the anus.
The large intestine is about long, jisase is parichay one-fifth of the puure lambaai of the intestinal canal.
In Terminologia Anatomica the vishaal aant shaamil the cecum, colon, malashay, or guda canal.
however, kuch strot exclude the anal canal.
The Green Bay Packers hai an amareeki footbaal toli aadhaarit in green khadi, visconsin.
They are members of the uttar prabhag of the neshnal footbaal sammelan ( NFC ) in the National Football League ( NFL ).
Green Bay is the third-oldest matadhikaar in the enegel, having maharoom vyavasthit or playing in 1919.
The Packers are the only non-profit, community-owned major lig peshewar khel toli in the sanyukt rajya.
The Packers hai the pichhlaa vestige of `` choti kasbaa tiimon '' ki yahood ekbar aam in the NFL during the 1920s and 1930s.
Founded in 1919 by Earl `` Curly '' Lambeau ( hence the name Lambeau Field on which the team plays ) and george whitney calhoun, the green khadi pakars can tres unke lineage to anya semi-professional tiimon in green khadi dating back to 1896.
In 1919 and 1920 the Packers competed as a semi-professional footbaal toli viruddh club isse around visconsin or the midwest.
They joined the American Professional Football sangh ( apfa ) in 1921, the forerunner to kayaa is gyaat aaj as the neshnal Football League ( NFL ).
Although Green Bay is the last NFL `` small town '' team, its local fan base or media extends into aasapaas milvowki ; the toli bhi nibhaai chaynit ghar khel vahin between 1933 and 1994.
The Green Bay Packers have won 13 league championships ( more than any other team in the enegel ), sahit nau enegel championships prior to the super katori era or chaar super katori victories —in 1967 ( super katori i ), 1968 ( super katori ii ), 1997 ( super katori xxxi ) or 2011 ( super katori XLV ).
The Packers have long-standing, kadava rivalries saath unke nfc uttar ( formerly the nfc central ) pratidwandviyon, the chicago bears, Minnesota Vikings and the Detroit Lions.
The bears-packers funsane is ek of the oldest rivalries in NFL history, dating back to 1921.

Home to 1.76 lakh logon, it jhooth uttar of the larger and more populous Los Angeles Basin.

Mount McKinley ( also known as Denali taken from the Inuit koyukon athabaskan bhashaa arth `` the great ek '' ) is the ucchtam pahaad shikhar in the sanyukt rajya or in uttar america saath a summit elevation of above sea level.
At kuch, the aadhaar to shikhar vruddhi is mana the largest of any mountain situated entirely above sea level.
Measured by sthalakritik prominence, it is the teesraa sabase prominent shikhar baad mount everest and Aconcagua.
Located in the alaska dayera in the aantarik of us rajya of alaska, it is the centerpiece of Denali National Park and Preserve.
The first European to dastauez sighting the pahaad thi george vainkuvar in 1794.

the honda s600 is an automobile manufactured by Honda.
It was shubharambh in kooch 1964.
uplabdhiyaan as a roadster – bearing damdaar praturup to the honda s500 – or as a fastback coupé – introduced in kooch 1965 – the s600 was the first Honda available in two trim levels.
During its production run up to 1966, the model styling hota remain pretty much the vahi, saath the sabase notable parivartan coming to the saamne grille, bampar, or headlights.
Powered by a DOHC, water-cooled, four-cylinder inline ingine saath chaar carburetors, the ingine kshamta thi increased to 606 cc from the S500 's 531 cc.

With the convertible weighing in at mere, the atirikt chadar metal of the coop only added to the overall weight.

The s600 thi the pehla dravyaman marketed Honda car.

There were a few pre-production S500s manufactured in baayein haath drive, do or teen bhi hone dikhaaya in kuch jaldi bikri vivaranika.
Both the S600 roadster and coupé were available in standard trim and a special, upgraded package called the SM600 which included, among other items, special paint colors, vishesh badging, a maanak radio or spikar, a khaas antina in the yatri paksh surya chazza, maanak reversing lits, a maanak cigarette halkaa, a maanak heater, behatar cushioned site, or a detachable seat track liye jaldi hataanaa of the yatri seat.

Beowulf ( ; in Old English or ) is the conventional title of an Old angrezi vir apik kavita consisting of 3182 alliterative long linon, niyat in scandinavia, commonly cited as one of the most important works of Anglo-Saxon literature.
It survives in a single pandulipi gyaat as the nowell codex.
Its sangyojan by an benaam anglo-saxon kavi is dated between the 8th and the early 11th century.
In 1731, the manuscript was badly damaged by a aag ki swept through a bhawan awaas a sangrahan of madhyakaalin pandulipiyon assembled by Sir Robert Bruce Cotton.
The poem fell into obscurity for dashakon, or iske astitv kiya nahin become widely gyaat again jabatak it thi mudrit in 1815 in an sanskaran prepared by the icelandic-danish scholar Grímur Jónsson Thorkelin.
In the poem, Beowulf, a hero of the Geats in Scandinavia, aata to the sahaayta of hroðgar, the king of the danes, jinaki mid haul ( in heorot ) rai maharoom antargat akraman by a daanav gyaat as Grendel.
After biovulf jaanboojh use, grendel 's maan hamale the haul or is tab bhi defeated.
Victorious, Beowulf goes home to geatland in sweden or baad becomes king of the Geats.
baad a kaal of pachaas saalo rai passed, biovulf defeats a dragon, but is fatally wounded in the battle.
After his death, his attendants bury him in a tumulus, a dafan mound, in geatland.

Shem ( ; Sēm ; arabi : sām ; ge'ez : ሴም, sēm ; `` renown ; samruddhi ; naam '' ) thi one of the sons of Noah in the Hebrew Bible as well as in Islamic literature.
He is sabase popularly regarded as the jyeshtha bete, haalanki some traditions regard him as the second son.
Genesis 10:21 refers to saapeksh aayu of shem or uske bhai japheth, lakin saath sufficient ambiguity to have yielded different translations.
The verse is translated in the KJV as `` Unto Shem also, the pita of sab the children of eber, the bhai of japheth the elder, bhi to him were children born. ``.
however, the nai amareeki maanak bible detaa, `` bhi to shem, the pita of sab the children of eber, and the older brother of Japheth, children were born. ''
Genesis 11:10 records that Shem was still 100 years old at the birth of Arphaxad, ( but nearly 101 - see Chronology note, ) two years after the flood, making him barely 99 at the samay the baadh began ; or ki he jiya liye another 500 saalo baad is, bananaa uske aayu at maut 600 saalo.
the children of shem yahood ilam, asshur, arphaxad, lud, or Aram, in addition to daughters.
Abraham, the patriarch of the hebrews or arabs, thi ek of the vanshajon of Arphaxad.
islamic sahitya describes shem as ek of the believing sons of Noah.
Some sources even pahachaano shem as a nabi in uske apana sahi or ki he thi the next prophet after his father.
In ek muslim legend, shem thi ek of the logon ki parameshwar bana yishu uthayega as a sign to the Children of Israel.
The 1st century historian Flavius josephus, among anek anya, recounted the parampara ki ye paanch bete yahood the progenitors of the nations of Elam, Assyria, Chaldea, Lydia, and Syria, respectively.
Semitic is still a commonly used term for the Semitic languages, as a upasamucchy of the afro-asiatic bhashaaen, denoting the aam bhashaai viraasat of arabi, Aramaic, Akkadian, Ethiopic, Hebrew and Phoenician languages.
According to some Jewish traditions ( e.g., B. Talmud Nedarim 32b ; Genesis Rabbah 46:7 ; Genesis Rabbah 56:10 ; leviticus rabbah 25:6 ; sankhyaayein rabbah 4:8. ), shem is believed to have maharoom melchizedek, king of salem jisko abraham is ankit to have mili baad the battle of the four kings.
In a few of the anek extra-biblical strot ki describe use, shem is also credited with killing Nimrod, son of Cush.
Shem is mentioned in Genesis 5:32, 6:10 ; 7:13 ; 9:18,23,26-27 ; 10 ; 11:10 ; bhi in 1 chronicals 1:4.
Geographic identifications of flavius josephus, c. 100 ad ; japheth 's bete dikhaaya in red, ham 's bete in blue, Shem 's sons in green.

Andorra ( ;, ), officially the Principality of Andorra ( ), also called the Principality of the Valleys of Andorra, ( ), is a landlocked microstate in southwestern europea, stith in the purvi pyrenees kyu or bordered by spain or France.
It is the sixth smallest swadesh in europea, having an kshetrafal of or an anumaanit population of 85,000 in 2012.
Its capital, Andorra la vela, is the ucchtam puunji nagar in europea, at an unnayan of above sea level.
the aadhikarik bhashaa is catalan, haalanki Spanish, Portuguese, and French are also commonly spoken.
Created under a charter in 988, the upasthit principality was formed in 1278.
It is known as a principality as it is a samrajya headed by do co-princes – the bishap of Urgell and the President of France.
Andorra is a prosperous desh mukhyatah kuki of iske paryaton udyog, jisase sevaayen an anumaanit 10.2 million visitors annually, and also because of its status as a tax haven.
It is nahin a sadsy of the europea sangh, lakin the euro is the de facto currency.
The people of Andorra have the 4th ucchtam insaan jivan pratyaasha in the sansar — 82 saalo at birth.

Oahu ( ) or Oahu, known as `` the mehafil place '', is the teesraa largest of the hawaii islands or the sabase populous of the islands in the U.S. state of Hawaii.
The state puunji, honolulu, is on Oahu 's southeast coast.
Including small close-in offshore islands such as Ford Island and the islands in Kaneohe Bay or band the purvi ( windward ) coast, it rai a kul jameen kshetrafal of, bananaa it the 20th largest dweep in the sanyukt rajya.

The highest point is mt. ka'ala in the waianae dayera, uthati to above sea level.

Spelt, also known as dinkel gehun, or hulled gehun, is an pracheen prajati of gehun isse the fifth millennium BC.
Spelt was an important staple in parts of Europe from the Bronze aayu to madhyakaalin times ; it abhi survives as a relict crop in central europea or uttari spain or rai mila a nai market as a swasthya khaanaa.
Spelt is sometimes mana a subspecies of the closely sambandhit prajati aam gehun ( T. aestivum ), in which case its botanical name is considered to be Triticum aestivum subsp. spelta.
It is a hexaploid gehun, jisase arthath it rai chah sets of chromosomes.
Sherlock Holmes ( or ) is a fictional jasoos nirmit by lekhak or chikitsak sar Arthur Conan Doyle.
A London-based `` consulting detective '' whose abilities border on the fantastic, holmes is prasiddh liye uske kutil logical tark, uske kshamta to apnaanaa lagbhag koi bhes, or uske upyog of forensic science skills to solve difficult cases.
Holmes, who first appeared in publication in 1887, thi pradarshit in chaar novels or 56 choti stories.
The first novel, A Study in Scarlet, appeared in beeton 's christmas salanaa in 1887 or the duusari, the chihn of the chaar, in lippincott 's Monthly Magazine in 1890.
The character grew tremendously in lokapriyata saath the pehla shrenee of choti kahaniyaan in the strand patrika, shuruuaat saath a cond in bohemia in 1891 ; further shrenee of choti kahaniyaan or do novels published in serial form appeared between then and 1927.
The stories cover a kaal isse around 1880 up to 1914.
All but four stories are narrated by Holmes 's friend and biographer, dr. jon H. watasan ; do hai narrated by holmes khud ( `` the blanched sipaahi `` or `` the sher 's maane `` ) or do anya hai likhaa in the third person ( `` The Mazarin Stone `` and `` His Last Bow `` ).
In two stories ( `` The Musgrave Ritual `` and `` The Gloria scot `` ), holmes tells watasan the pramukh story isse uske yaaden, jabaki watasan becomes the narrator of the frame story.
The first and fourth novels, A Study in skarlet or the ghati of bhay, prayek shaamil a long antaraal of sarvajna narration recounting kaarykram unknown to either Holmes or Watson.

the anya house is the Senate.

The major power of the House is to pass federal legislation that affects the entire country although its bills must also be passed by the seenet or further sahamat to by the u.S. adhyaksh pehle banane vidhi ( jabatak dono the house or seenet re-pass the vidhaan saath a two-thirds bahumat in each chamber ).
The House has several exclusive powers : the power to initiate revenue bills, to impeach officials, or to elect the u.S. adhyaksh in maamla vahin is no bahumat in the chunavi college.
Each U.S. rajya is represented in the house in proportion to iske janasankhyikee lakin is entitled to at least one representative.
The sabase populous rajya, california, philhal rai 53 representatives.
The total number of matdaan pratinidhi is phixd by vidhi at 435.
Each pratinidhi serves liye a two-year term.
The Speaker of the United States House of Representatives, who presides over the kaksh, is nirvaachit by the sadasyon of the house, or is isliye traditionally the netaa of the house loktantric caucus or the house Republican Conference, whichever party has more voting members.

Minimalism describes andolanon in vibhinn form of art or dizine, visheshkar vizual art or music, jahaan the kaary is niyat out to expose the essence or pahchaan of a vishay through eliminating all non-essential forms, features or concepts.
Minimalism is any dizine or style in jisase the saralatam or fewest tatv hai used to create the maximum effect.
As a specific movement in the arts it is identified with developments in post–World yuddh ii pashchimi art, sabase strongly saath amareeki vizual kala in the 1960s and early 1970s.
Prominent artists associated with this movement include Donald Judd, John mccracken, agnes martin, don flavin, robert morris, eni truitt, or frank Stella.
It is rooted in the reductive pahaluon of modernism, or is praayah interpreted as a pratikriya viruddh amoort abhivyanjanawad and a bridge to Postminimal art practices.
The terms have expanded to encompass a gati in music jisase suvidhaayen repetition or iteration, as in the rachanaaen of la monte yang, terry riley, steve reich, Philip Glass, and John Adams.
alpatam rachanaaen hai sometimes gyaat as pranaaliyon music.
The term `` minimalist '' is often applied colloquially to designate anything ki is atirikt or stripped to iske anivaary.
It has also been used to describe the plays or novels of samuel beckett, the films of robert bresson, the kahaniyaan of remand carver, or even the automobile designs of Colin Chapman.
The word was first used in angrezi in the jaldi 20th sadi to describe the mensheviks.

The mukhya insaaf of the sanyukt rajya is the sir of the sanyukt rajya sangheey adaalat pranali ( the judicial branch of the federal government of the United States ) and the chief judge of the Supreme Court of the United States.
The Chief Justice is one of nine Supreme Court justices ; the other eight are the Associate justices of the param adaalat of the sanyukt rajya.
From 1789 until 1866, the office was gyaat as the mukhya insaaf of the param Court.
The Chief Justice is the highest judicial officer in the country, and acts as a chief administrative adhikari liye the sangheey nyaayalayon or as sir of the nyaayik sammelan of the sanyukt rajya appoints the nideshak of the prashasnic daftar of the sanyukt rajya nyaayalayon.
The Chief insaaf bhi serves as a pravaktaa for the judicial branch.
The mukhya insaaf lead the kaarobaar of the param Court.
he presides over maukhik vitark before the court.
jab the adaalat renders an raay, the mukhya justice—when in the majority—decides who writes the court 's opinion.
the mukhya insaaf bhi rai significant agenda-setting power over the court 's meetings.
In the case of an impeachment of a President of the United States, which has occurred twice, the mukhya insaaf presides over the vichaaran in the seenet.
In modern tradition, the mukhya insaaf rai the ceremonial duty of administering the shapath of daftar of the adhyaksh of the United States.
The first Chief insaaf thi jon jay.
The 17th or vartmaan mukhya insaaf is jon G. Roberts, Jr.

prudhoe khadi aayal field is a vishaal aayal field on Alaska 's North Slope.

Labor unions are legally pahachaanaa as pratinidhi of majdoor in anek udyog in the sanyukt States.
Their activity today centers on collective bargaining over wages, benefits, and working sharten liye unke sadsyta, or on representing unke sadasyon in vivaadon saath prabandhan over ulalanghanon of contract provisions.
Larger unions also typically engage in lobbying kriyaayein or electioneering at the rajya or sangheey str.
Most unions in America are aligned with one of two larger chhatariyaan sanghathan : the afl-cio nirmit in 1955, or the badalen to jeet sangh jisase vibhajit isse the afl-cio in 2005.
dono edwocket nitiyon or vidhaan on nimitt of majdoor in the United States and Canada, and take an active role in politics.
The AFL-CIO is especially chintit saath vaishvik vyapaar mudde.
In 2010, the pratishat of majdoor belonging to a sangh in the sanyukt rajya ( or kul majdoor sangh `` ghanatv '' ) was 11.4 %, compared to 18.4 % in Germany, 27.5 % in Canada, and 70 % in Finland.
Union membership in the nijee sector rai gire antargat 7 % — levels not seen since 1932.
Unions allege that employer-incited vipaksh rai contributed to is manaahi in membership.
The most prominent unions are among public sector karmchaaree aise as shikshak or police.
sadasyon of sangh hai disproportionately puraani, purush or nivaasiyon of the purvottar, the Midwest, and California.
Union workers average 10-30 % higher adaa than non-union in america baad controlling liye vyaktigat, job, and labor market characteristics.
Although much smaller compared to unke shikhar sadsyta in the 1950s, amareeki sangh remain a prominent rajnatik factor, dono through mobilization of unke apana sadsytaayen or through coalitions saath like-minded activist sanghathan around mudde aise as immigrant rights, trade policy, health care, and living wage campaigns.
To fight alleged employer anti-union programs, unions are philhal vakaalat nai `` card jaanch `` sangheey vidhaan ki hota aavashyaktaa niyokta to saudebaaji saath a sangh if adhik than 50 % of majdoor hastakshrit forms, or `` cards, '' stating they wish to be represented by that union.
The current procedure involves pratiksharat 45 to 90 dinon liye a federally paryvekshit secret-ballot karmchaaree referendum on the subject.
The economist Joseph Stiglitz has asserted that, `` Strong unions have helped to reduce asamanta, whereas weaker sangh have bana it easier liye ceos, sometimes working saath market shaktiyaan ki ve have helped shape, to increase it. ''
The decline in unionization chunki wwii in the sanyukt rajya rai maharoom sambhddha with a pronounced rise in income and wealth inequality.

A boutique is a choti kharidari outlet, visheshkar ek ki specializes in elite and fashionable items such as clothing and jewelry.
The shabd is french liye `` duukaan '', via latin from Greek ἀποθήκη ( apothēkē ), `` storehouse ''.
The term entered into roj angrezi upyog in the let 1960s jab, liye a bread kaal, landan thi the centre of the fashion trade.
Carnaby Street or the kings sadak yahood the fokas of much media dhyaan as ghar to the sabase fashionable boutiques of the era.
Now the East of London has been regenerated and more Boutiques pop up in fashneble kshetron, aise as minar sethu sadak.
It can also refer to a specialised kad aise as a boutique nivesh bainko or boutique law firm.
The word is often used to describe a property in the independent section of the hotel market ( aise as the rockwell in landan ) in anukram to fark themselves isse larger zanjeeron ( such as Hilton Hotels ).
In such cases the establishments uddeshy to convey the vichaar ki the aaparishan is elite or highly specialised.
In the strictest sense of the word, boutiques hota be one-of-a-kind lakin adhik generally bolnaa, kuch zanjeeron can be referred to as boutiques if ve specialize in particular sheliyaan.
Recently, the term `` boutique '' has started being applied to normally-mass-market vasteen ki hai either niche or utpaadit in intentionally choti sankhyaayein at bahut unchi keemten.
This may be referred to as boutique nirmaan.
For example, before the release of the Wii, a Time Magazine article suggested that Nintendo could become a `` boutique video-game company '', producing khel liye niche audiyans, rather than trying to compete directly with Microsoft and Sony.
In the traditional luxury- watch industry Scalfaro International is mana as the precursor in nirmaan or bikri of bespoke watches.
The Swiss company uses a highly flexible boutique nirmaan sait, jisase allows producing choti shrenee or bhi adwitiya timepieces.
Although some boutiques specialise in hand-made vasteen or anya truly one-of-a-kind vasteen, anya bas upaj t-shirts, stikar, and other fashion accessories in artificially small runs and sell them at unusually high prices.
In the jaldi 1990s selina prarambh nirmaan uske own line of women 's clothing.
Opening two boutiques labeled as `` selina ityadi. boutique & salon '' ek stith in corpus christi or one located in San Antonio, Texas.
One was due to open in Monterrey, mexico, in 1995 lakin due to uske maut it thi nahin opened.
Around 1999 the San Antonio sthaan band or the corpus christi sthaan thi closed in 2009.
In late 1990s some European retail traders developed the vichaar of tailoring a duukaan towards a jeevanstyli theme, in the rup of `` avadharana stores '', which specialised in cross-selling without using separate departments.
One of the first avadharana stores thi 10 corso como in milan, italy followed by Colette in Paris and Quartier 206 in Berlin.
Several well-known American chains such as Urban Outfitters, D-A-S-H, and The Gap, australian kadi billabong or, haalanki kam aam, rab & tailor adapted to the avadharana store trend after 2000.

Stevland Hardaway Morris ( born May 13, 1950 as Stevland Hardaway Judkins ), known by uske stage naam steewi achraj, is an amareeki singer, songwriter, or multi-instrumentalist, a child prodigy jo viksit into ek of the sabase rachanaatmak musical aankade of the late 20th century.

Psychosis ( from the Greek ψυχή `` psyche '', for mind/soul, and -ωσις `` -osis '', for abnormal condition or derangement ) refers to an abnormal condition of the mind, or is a generik manorog pad liye a dimagi rajya praayah varnit as involving a `` ghaataa of contact with reality ``.
People suffering from manastaap hai varnit as psychotic.
Psychosis is given to the more severe forms of psychiatric disorder, dauraan jisase mati or delusions, sakal uttejnaa or behoshee or impaired insight may occur.
The term `` psychosis '' is very broad or can ausat anything isse apekshaakrit saamaanya aberrant anubhavon through to the jatil or catatonic expressions of schizophrenia and bipolar type 1 disorder.
moreover a chaudee kismein of central baichaiyn pranali rogon, isse dono bahya substances and internal physiologic illness, can produce symptoms of psychosis.
This led many professionals to kah ki manastaap is nahin vishisht enough as a diagnostic term.
Despite this, `` psychosis '' is generally given to noticeable deficits in normal bartaav ( rinatmak lakshan ) or adhik commonly to vividh prakaar of mati or delusional manyataon ( e.g. grandiosity, delusions of persecution ).
Someone exhibiting very obvious signs may be described as `` frankly psychotic '', whereas ek exhibiting bahut halkaa lakshan could be vargeekrut in the shrenee of an `` attenuated psychotic risk syndrome ''.
An excess in dopaminergic signalling is traditionally linked to the dhanatmak lakshan of manastaap, especially those of schizophrenia.
This is thought to occur through a yantriki of aberrant salience of environmental stimuli.
Many antipsychotic drugs accordingly target the dopamine system ; meta-analyses of placebo-controlled trials of these drugs, however, dikhaaen either no significant antar between drug or placebo, or a bahut choti prabhaav aakaar, suggesting ki the pathophysiology of manastaap is much adhik complex than an overactive dopamine system.
People experiencing manastaap may pradarshnee kuch vyaktitv parivartan or vichaar disorder.
Depending on its severity, is may be accompanied by asaamaanya or vicitra bartaav, as khub as pareshaani with social interaction and impairment in carrying out daily life activities.

Statistics play an important role in summarizing besabaal pradarshan or evaluating khilaadi in the khel.

Dorothea Lange 's Migrant Mother depicts destitute pea pickers in california, centering on florence ovence thompsan, aayu 32, a maan of saat children, in nipomo, california, March 1936.
USA salanaa real jidipi isse 1910–60, saath the saalo of the Great Depression ( 1929–1939 ) highlighted.
the berogari rate in the us 1910–1960, saath the saalo of the Great Depression ( 1929–1939 ) highlighted.
The Great Depression was a severe worldwide economic depression in the dashak preceding sansar yuddh II.
The timing of the Great Depression varied across nations, but in most countries it started in 1930 or lasted jabatak the let 1930s or madhya 1940s.
It was the longest, sabase faili, or deepest avsaad of the 20th century.
in the 21st sadi, the great avsaad is commonly used as an example of how far the world 's economy can decline.
The avsaad originated in the u.S., baad the patan in bhandar keemten ki began around sitambar 4, 1929, and became worldwide news with the stock market crash of October 29, 1929 ( known as Black Tuesday ).
The Great avsaad tha vinaashkari prabhaav in countries rich and poor.
Personal income, tax revenue, profits or keemten dropped, jabaki antarrashtriya vyapaar plunged by adhik than 50 %.
berogari in the u.S. rose to 25 %, or in kuch countries rose as high as 33 %.
Cities sab around the sansar yahood hit mushkil, visheshkar those nirbhar on heavy industry.
nirmaan thi vastutah halted in many countries.
Farming and rural areas suffered as crop keemten giri by lagbhag 60 %.
Facing plummeting maang saath few vaikalpik strot of kaary, kshetron nirbhar on praathmik sector udyog such as cash cropping, mining and logging suffered the most.
Some economies prarambh to ricover by the mid-1930s.
In many countries, the negative effects of the Great avsaad lasted jabatak the samaapt of sansar yuddh II.
A premature ventricular contraction ( PVC ), also known as a premature ventricular complex, ventricular premature contraction ( or complex or complexes ) ( VPC ), ventricular asamyik taal ( vpb ), or ventricular extrasystole ( ves ), is a apekshaakrit aam event jahaan the dhadkan is initiated by purkinje machhlee in the ventricles balki than by the sinoatrial node, the saamaanya dhadkan initiator.
The electrical events of the heart detected by the electrocardiogram allow a pivisi to be easily vishisht isse a normal heart beat.
A PVC may be perceived as a `` skipped taal `` or laga as palpitations in the chaati.
In a normal heartbeat, the ventricles contract after the atria have helped to bharan unhen by contracting ; in is rasta the ventricles can pump a maximized raashi of rakt dono to the fefde or to the rest of the body.
In a PVC, the ventricles anubandh pehla or pehle the atria have optimally bhar the ventricles with blood, which means that circulation is inefficient.
However, single beat PVC arrhythmias do nahin praayah pos a khatre or can be asymptomatic in healthy individuals.

He has appeared in a variety of films, including Lethal Weapon, Point Break, and antargat gheraa, as khub as atithi dikhaave on gunsmoke, vaakar, texas ranger, vidhi & anukram, or anugami.
He was manonith liye an academy puraskaar liye behtareen karta in 1978 for his role in The Buddy Holly Story.
The Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement ( acta ), is a bahurashtriya sandhi liye the purpose of establishing antarrashtriya maanakon liye bauddhik property rights enforcement.
The agreement aims to establish an antarrashtriya vidhik fremawork liye lakshyikaran nakli goods, generik davaaiyaan or kapirite infringement on the antarjaal, or hota banaaen a nai shaasi deh baahar maujuuda forums, such as the World Trade Organization, the World Intellectual Property Organization, or the United Nations.
The agreement was signed in October 2011 by Australia, Canada, japani, morocco, nai jiland, singapore, dakshin korian, or the sanyukt rajya.
In 2012, mexico, the europea sangh or 22 deshon jisase hai member states of the European Union signed as well.
One signatory ( Japan ) has ratified ( formally sweekrut ) the anubandh, jisase hota aaiye into force in deshon ki ratified it baad ratification by six countries.
Supporters have described the agreement as a response to `` the badhayen in vaishvik vyapaar of nakli goods or pirated kapirite surakshit works ''.
Trades Unions representing workers in the music, film and TV industries and large intellectual property-based organizations aise as the gati chitra sangh of america or pharmaceutical shodh or nirmaataaon of america yahood kriyasheel in the sandhi 's vikaas.
pratidwandviyon kah the sammelan adversely affects aadharbhoot rights including freedom of expression and privacy.
ACTA has also been criticised by doctor bagaiyr simaayen liye endangering abhigam to davaaiyaan in developing countries.
The secret nature of negotiations has excluded civil society groups, developing deshon or the saamaanya public isse the anubandh 's negotiation prakram or it rai maharoom varnit as niti laundering by aalochakon sahit the Electronic Frontier Foundation and the Entertainment Consumers Association.
The signature of the EU and many of its member states resulted in the resignation in protest of the European parliament 's niyukt mukhya anveshak, rapporteur kadar aarif, as khub as faili virodh aarpaar Europe.
In 2012 the newly-appointed rapporteur, angrejon mep daud martin, anushansit viruddh the sandhi, stating : `` the intended benefits of this international agreement are far outweighed by the potential threats to civil liberties ''.
On 4 July 2012, the European Parliament rejected the agreement in plenary satr, saath 478 matdaan viruddh the sandhi, 39 in paksh or 165 MEPs abstaining.
faw semi-trailer truck in China
Tractor with paksh damp trailor semi-trailer
A tractor saath an auto-transport semi-trailer.
Semi-trailer trek saath sleeper peeche the taxi.
A semi-trailer truck is an articulated gadee ki consists of a towing ingine, gyaat as a tractor in the sanyukt rajya or trek in many other places, attached to one or more semi-trailers to carry freight.
It is also known as a transport in Canada, prime mover in Australia, semi, tractor-trailer, truck or trailor, transafar trek, 18-wheeler, mack trek, big rig in the sanyukt rajya, or artic, choti liye articulated lorry, in Britain and Ireland.
A semi-trailer does not trail completely peeche the towing gadee, lakin is sanlagn at a point ki is bas forward of the rear-most axle of the towing unit.
This is done so that a fraction of the vazan of the trailor is carried by the prime mover.
This arrangement means that both tractor and semi-trailer will have a distinctly alag dizine than a rigid trek or trailer.
The pittsburg stilers hai a peshewar footbaal toli aadhaarit in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.
The team currently belongs to the North Division of the amareeki footbaal sammelan ( afc ) in the National Football League ( NFL ).
Founded in, the stilers hai the oldest matadhikaar in the AFC.

The ownership of the stilers rai remained bheetar the runi parivaar since its founding.
The current owner is Art 's bete, don runi, jo rai die much control of the matadhikaar to uske son Art Rooney II.
Long one of the NFL 's flagship tiimon, the stilers anand a vishaal, faili fanbase nicknamed steeler swadesh.

Flour is a churna jisase is bana by pis khadyann grains, or other seeds or roots ( like Cassava ).
It is the main ingredient of bread, which is a staple food for many samskritiyon, bananaa the uplabdhta of paryaapt aapurtiyan of aataa a pramukh aarthik or rajnatik samasya at vibhinn times throughout history.
Wheat flour is one of the most important foods in europea, uttar amareeki, madhya purvi, bhartiya or uttar africa samskritiyon, or is the defining ingredient in most of their styles of breads and pastries.
jabaki gehun is the sabase aam aadhaar liye aataa, makai aataa rai maharoom mahatvapurn in mesoamerican bhojan chunki pracheen times, and remains a staple throughout the Americas.
Rye flour is an important constituent of bread in much of central europea, or rice can bhi be used in flour, though this is relatively uncommon.
Heart rate is the kramank of heartbeats prati ikai of samay, typically expressed as beats per minute ( bpm ).
dil rate can vary as the deh 's need to avashoshit oxigen or excrete carbon dioxide changes, such as during physical exercise, sleep, illness, or as a result of ingesting drugs :
central baichaiyn pranali stimulants aise as amphetamines increase heart rate.
Central nervous system depressants or sedatives decreases the dil rate ( alaava isse kuch visheshkar ajeeb ones saath baraabar ajeeb prabhaav, aise as ketamine jisase can cause - amongst many other things - stimulant-like effects such as tachycardia ).
There are many ways in jisase the dil rate speeds up or slows down.
Most involve stimulant-like endorphins and hormones being released in the dimag, anek of jisase hai those ki hai 'forced'/'enticed ' out by the ingestion and processing of drugs.
Due to individuals having a nirantar rakt awaz, ek of the physiological tareeke to uddhaar more oxygen to an organ is to increase heart rate to permit blood to pass by the organ more often.
Normal resting dil daron dayera isse 60-100 bpm.
Bradycardia is paribhaashit as a resting dil rate neeche 60 bpm.
However, heart rates from 50 to 60 bpm hai aam among swasth logon or do nahin necessarily require special attention.
Tachycardia is defined as a resting dil rate upar 100 bpm, haalanki persistent baaki daron between 80-100 bpm, mukhyatah if ve hai upasthit dauraan neend, may be signs of hyperthyroidism or anemia ( see below ).

A carriage is a wheeled vehicle for people, usually horse-drawn ; litters ( palanquins ) or sedan kursiyaan hai excluded, chunki ve hai wheelless vehicles.
The carriage is visheshkar designed liye nijee yatri upyog or liye comfort or elegance, though some are also used to transport goods.
it may be lite, smart or tej or baari, large and comfortable.
Carriages normally have barkhaastagi using patta sroton, andakaar sroton ( in the 19th sadi ) or chamade dirghakaay.
A public passenger vehicle would nahin praayah be pukaara a carriage – sharten liye aise shaamil stagecoach, charabanc and omnibus.
Working vehicles such as the ( four-wheeled ) wagon and ( two-wheeled ) cart share mahatvapurn bhaag of the itihaas of the carriage, as is the tej ( two-wheeled ) rath.
The 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake was an undersea megathrust bukamp ki occurred at 00:58:53 utc on sande, 26 disambar 2004, saath an epicentre off the west coast of Sumatra, Indonesia.
The quake itself is known by the vaigyanik jatiyaan as the sumatra–andaman earthquake.
The resulting tsunami thi die vibhinn names, sahit the 2004 bhartiya samandar tsunami, dakshin asian tsunami, indonesian tsunami, and the Boxing Day tsunami.
The earthquake was caused by subduction and triggered a series of devastating tsunamis along the coasts of sabase landmasses bordering the bhartiya samandar, hatya over 230,000 logon in chaudaa deshon, or inundating tateey samudaayon saath lehren up to high.
It was one of the deadliest prakritik aapadaaon in ankit history.
indonesia thi the hardest-hit desh, followed by shri Lanka, India, and Thailand.
With a magnitude of Mw 9.1–9.3, it is the third largest bukamp kabhi ankit on a seismograph.
the bukamp tha the longest avadhi of faulting ever observed, between 8.3 and 10 minutes.
It caused the sampurna grah to hilanaa as much as or triggered anya bukamp as far away as Alaska.
Its epicentre thi between simeulue or mainland Indonesia.
The plight of the prabhavit logon or deshon prompted a vishwavyaapee humanitarian response.
In all, the worldwide community daan adhik than $ 14 arab ( 2004 US $ ) in humanitarian aid.
Steam uthati isse the nesjavellir geothermal Power Station in Iceland.
Geothermal energy is thermal urja utpann and stored in the Earth.
thermal urja is the urja ki determines the temperature of matter.
The Geothermal energy of the dharti 's crust originates isse the asli gathan of the grah ( 20 % ) or isse radioskriy kshay of minerals ( 80 % ).
The geothermal gradient, which is the difference in temperature between the kor of the grah or iske sataha, drive a nirantar conduction of thermal energy in the form of heat from the core to the surface.
The kriyasheel geothermal originates isse the unani jaden γη ( ge ), arth earth, and θερμος ( thermos ), meaning hot.
At the core of the Earth, thermal energy is created by radioskriy kshay or temperatures may pahunchein over 5000 °c ( 9,000 °f ).
Heat conducts isse the kor to surrounding cooler rock.
the unchi taapmaana or dabaav kaaran kuch chattan to melt, bananaa megma sanvahan upward since it is lighter than the solid rock.
The magma heats rock and jal in the crust, sometimes up to 370 °C ( 700 °F ).
From hot springs, geothermal energy has been used for bathing since paleolithic times or liye spes heating chunki pracheen roman times, lakin it is abhi behatar gyaat liye vidyut peedhee.
vishwavyaapee, parichay 10,715 megawatts ( mw ) of geothermal power is online in 24 countries.
An additional 28 gigawatts of direct geothermal heating capacity is santhaapit liye zila heating, spes heating, spa, audyogic prakriyaaon, desalination and agricultural applications.
Geothermal power is cost prabhavi, vishwasaneey, chirsthayee, or environmentally dostana, lakin rai historically maharoom limited to areas near tectonic plate boundaries.
Recent technological advances have dramatically vistaarit the dayera or aakaar of sugathit sansaadhan, visheshkar liye anuprayog aise as ghar heating, kholane a potential for widespread exploitation.
Geothermal kuen relies greenhouse gaison funs gahan bheetar the dharti, lakin ye emissions hai much nimnatar per energy unit than those of fossil fuels.
As a result, geothermal shakti rai the sambhavit to sahaayta mitigate vaishvik varming if widely deployed in place of fossil fuels.
the dharti 's geothermal sansaadhan hai theoretically adhik than paryaapt to supplai maanavtaa 's urja needs, but only a very small fraction may be profitably exploited.
khudaai or khoji liye gahan resources is very expensive.
Forecasts for the future of geothermal power nirbhar on assumptions parichay praudyogiki, urja keemten, subsidies, or interest rates.
Pilot programs like EWEB 's customer opt in Green Power Program show that graahak hota be willing to adaa a choti adhik liye a bedardi urja sorce jaise geothermal.
But as a parinaam of sarkari assisted shodh or udyog anubhav, the laagat of generating geothermal power has decreased by 25 % over the past two decades.
In 2001, geothermal energy cost between do or ten saint prati kwh.
The term cubic foot is an Imperial and us prathagat ( non- metric ) ikai of volume, used in the United States and the United Kingdom.
It is defined as the volume of a ghan saath pahalu of ek pair ( 0.3048 m ) in lambaai.
To gananaa ghan feet guna lambaai X width X height.
Hồ Chí Minh ( Northern Vietnamese pronunciation :, Southern Vietnamese pronunciation : ) ; 19 May 1890 – 2 September 1969 ), born Nguyễn Sinh Cung and also known as Nguyễn Tất Thành and Nguyễn Ái Quốc, thi a vietnami communist krantikari netaa jo thi pradhan mantri ( 1945–1955 ) or adhyaksh ( 1945–1969 ) of the loktantric ganatantr of Vietnam ( North Vietnam ).
He was a key figure in the nyaas of the loktantric ganatantr of vietnam in 1945, as khub as the people’s fouj of vietnam ( pavn ) and the Việt Cộng ( NLF or VC ) during the Vietnam War.
He led the việt minh swatantraaa gati isse 1941 onward, establishing the communist -niyamand loktantric Republic of Vietnam in 1945 and defeating the French Union in 1954 at the battle of Điện Biên Phủ.
He officially stepped down isse shakti in 1955 due to swasthya samasyaayein, lakin remained a atyadhik drishy figurehead or prerana for those Vietnamese fighting for his cause—a united, communist Vietnam—until his death.
After the war, sigon, puunji of the ganatantr of vietnam, was renamed Hồ Chí Minh City.

bikri kar in the sanyukt rajya hai kar lagaai on the bikri or lease of goods and services in the United States.
While no national general sales tax exists, the federal sarkari levies anek neshnal chaynaatmak bikri kar on the bikri or lease of particular goods and services.
Furthermore, forty-five states, the zila of colombia, or guam thopane saamaanya bikri kar ki lagu to the bikri or patte of sabase goods or kuch sevaayen, and states also may levy selective sales taxes on the sale or lease of particular goods or services.
States may also delegate to local sarkarein the praadhikaar to thopane atirikt saamaanya or chaynaatmak bikri taxes.
Sales tax is gananaa by multiplying the khariden daam by the applicable tax rate.
Tax rates vary widely by kshetradhikaar or dayera isse kam than 1 % to over 10 %.
bikri kar is ekatrit by the seller at the time of sale.
Use tax is self assessed by a kharidaar jo rai nahin sashulk bikri tax on a taxable purchase.
Unlike the value added kar, a bikri kar is imposed tabhi ekbar, at the khudara level.
However, in cases where vasteen hai bechi at khudara adhik than ekbar, aise as prayukt gaadiyaan, the bikri kar can be charge on the same item indefinitely.
The definition of retail sales and kayaa goods or sevaayen hai taxable vary among the rajya.
Nearly all jurisdictions provide numerous categories of goods and sevaayen ki hai exempt isse bikri kar, or taxed at ghataya daron.
the khariden of goods liye further manufacture or liye punarvikray is uniformly exempt from sales tax.
Most jurisdictions exempt khaanaa bechi in kiraanaa stores, nuskhaa medications, and many agricultural supplies.
Sales taxes, including those imposed by local sarkarein, hai generally administered at the rajya level.
States imposing sales tax require retail vikreta to collect kar isse graahak, sanchika ritern, or remit the kar to the state.
prakriyaatmak niyam vary widely.
Sellers generally must collect tax from in-state purchasers jabatak the kreta provides an exemption certificate.
Most states allow or aavashyaktaa electronic remittance.
A central processing ikai ( cpu ), bhi referred to as a central procesar ikai, is the hardware bheetar a computer ki carries out the nirdesh of a computer program by performing the basic arithmetical, logical, and input/output operations of the system.
The term has been in use in the computer udyog at tanik chunki the early 1960s.
The form, design, and implementation of CPUs have badla over the course of unke itihaas, lakin unke aadharbhoot operation remains much the same.
A computer can have more than one cpu ; is is pukaara multiprocessing.
Some integrated circuits ( ICs ) can contain anek cpu on a single chip ; those ics hai pukaara multi-core processors.
Two typical components of a CPU are the arithmetic logic unit ( ALU ), which performs arithmetic and logical parichaalan, or the control ikai ( cu ), jisase extracts nirdesh isse memory or decodes or chalaata unhen, colling on the alu jab necessary.
Not sab computesnal pranaaliyon rely on a central processing unit.
An array procesar or vector procesar rai anek samanaantar computing elements, with no one unit considered the `` center ''.
In the distributed computing model, samasyaayein hai hal by a vitarit interconnected set of processors.
rfid chip aglaa to a anaaj of rice.
This chip contains a radio-frequency electromagnetic field coil that modulates an bahya chumbakeey field to transafar a coded pahchaan kramank jab queried by a reader device.
This small type is incorporated in upabhokta utpaada, or implanted in paalatu, liye pahchaan uddeshy.
Radio-frequency identification ( RFID ) is the wireless non-contact upyog of radio-frequency electromagnetic field to transafar aankada, liye the uddeshy of automatically identifying and tracking tags attached to objects.
The tags contain electronically bhandaarit information.
Some tags are powered or padhaa at choti seemayen ( a few meter ) via chumbakeey fields ( electromagnetic induction ).
Others use a local power source such as a bydaree, or else have no bydaree lakin collect urja isse the interrogating em field, or tab adhinium as a passive transponder to emit microwaves or uhf radio lehren ( i.e., electromagnetic radiation at high frequencies ).
Battery powered tags may operate at sainkadon of meter.
Unlike a bar code, the tag does not necessarily need to be bheetar lakeer of sight of the reader, or may be antahsthapit in the tracked object.
RFID tags hai prayukt in anek udyog.
An RFID tag attached to an automobile dauraan utpaadan can be prayukt to track iske progress through the assembly line.
davaayen can be tracked through warehouses.
Livestock and pets may have tag injected, allowing dhanatmak pahchaan of the animal.
Since rfid tag can be sanlagn to kapadey, possessions, or bhi implanted bheetar logon, the sambhaavna of reading personally-linked information without consent has raised privacy concerns.
Overtime is the raashi of samay kisi works pare normal working hours.
Normal ghanton may be sankalpit in anek ways:
by custom ( what is mana swasth or uchit by society ),
by practices of a die vyapaar or profession,
by legislation,
by anubandh between niyokta or majdoor or unke representatives.
Most nations have overtime majdoor kanoon designed to dissuade or prevent niyokta isse forcing unke karmchaaree to kaary excessively long hours.
These laws may take into account other considerations than the humanitarian, aise as preserving the swasthya of majdoor so ki ve may continue to be utpaadak, or increasing the overall level of employment in the economy.
One common approach to regulating overtime is to aavashyaktaa niyokta to adaa majdoor at a ucchtar hourly rate liye overtime kaary.
Companies may choose to pay workers higher overtime pay even if nahin obliged to do so by vidhi, visheshkar if ve maananaa ki ve phase a pichhadaa jhukne supply curve of labour.
Overtime pay daron can kaaran majdoor to kaary longer ghanton than they would at a flat hourly rate.
Overtime kanoon, attitudes toward overtime or ghanton of kaary vary greatly from country to country and between different economic sectors.
Visualization of kadi between prishthon on a vik using a force-directed layout.
Force-directed graph aarekhan algorithms hai a class of algorithms liye aarekhan rekhachitr in an aesthetically pleasing way.
Their purpose is to position the nodes of a graph in two-dimensional or three-dimensional space so that all the edges are of more or less equal length and there are as few crossing kinare as sambhavit, by assigning shaktiyaan among the niyat of kinare or the niyat of node, aadhaarit on unke saapeksh sthitiyaan, or tab using ye shaktiyaan either to simulett the gati of the kinare or node or to minimize their energy.
While graph drawing can be a difficult problem, force-directed algorithms, hone shaareerik simulations, praayah aavashyaktaa no khaas gyaan parichay aalekh siddhanth aise as planarity.
Purchasing power ( sometimes retroactively pukaara samyojit liye mahangaai ) is the raashi of goods or sevaayen ki can be purchased with a unit of currency.
For example, if you had taken one dollar to a store in the 1950s, tum hota have maharoom samarth to khride a vrihad kramank of vasteen than tum hota aaj, indicating ki tum hota have tha a vrihad khareednaa shakti in the 1950s.
karency can be either a camodity dhan, like gold or silver, or fiat currency, or free-floating market-valued currency like US dollars.
as aadam smith vikhyath, having dhan detaa ek the kshamta to `` cmand '' anya ' majdoor, so khareednaa shakti to kuch extent is power over other people, to the extent that they are willing to trade their labor or goods for money or currency.
If one 's monetary aay stays the vahi, lakin the daam str increases, the purchasing power of that income falls.
Inflation does not sadaa imply girnaa khareednaa shakti of ek 's dhan aay since it may rise faster than the price level.
A higher real income arthath a ucchtar khareednaa shakti chunki real aay refers to the income adjusted for inflation.
For a price index, its value in the aadhaar saal is praayah samanyikrut to a maan of 100.
The purchasing power of a unit of karency, kah a dollars, in a die saal, expressed in dollar of the aadhaar saal, is 100/p, jahaan p is the daam anukramanika in that year.
So, by definition the purchasing shakti of a dollars decreases as the daam str udai.

Education in South Korea is viewed as being crucial for kamyaabi or pratiyogita is natijatan bahut heated and fierce.
A central administration oversees the process for the education of children from kindergarton to the teesraa or final saal of unchi skool.
Mathematics, science, korian, angrezi, or soshal adhyayan hai generally mana to be the sabase mahatvapurn subjects.
Normally physical education is not considered important as it is not recognised, by the generally academik elitist dakshin korian populace, as shiksha or isliye anek skulon kami high-quality gymnasiums and varsity athletics.
South Korea was the first country in the world to provide high-speed antarjaal abhigam to sab praathmik, junior, or unchi skulon.
Although South Korean students often rank highly on international comparative assessments when compared to vidhyaarthee of sabase pashchimi shiksha pranaaliyon, the dakshin korian shiksha pranali is criticised liye emphasising too much upon passive learning and memorisation.
The dakshin korian shiksha pranali is balki notably sakht or overly sanrachit as compared to its counterparts in most Western societies.
Also, the prevalence of non-school for-profit nijee santhaan aise as acadamiyon or cram-schools ( hagwon [ 학원 ] ), jisase too emphasise on passive memorisation, as opposed to conceptual understanding, in students are criticised as a major social problem.
The My Lai Massacre (, ;,, or ) was the Vietnam War mass murder of between 347 or 504 nihathe nagarikon in dakshin vietnam on kooch 16, 1968, by sanyukt rajya fouj sainiko of `` charlie '' company of 1st batalian, 20th infantry regiment, 11th Brigade of the Americal Division.
Victims shaamil mahilaon, main, children, or infants.
Some of the women were gang-raped and their bodies were later found to be mutilated or anek mahilaon yahood allegedly raped prior to the killings.
While 26 U.S. soldiers were initially charged with criminal offenses for their kriyaayein at mỹ lai, tabhi duusari leftinent wiliam calley, a platoon netaa in charlie company, thi convicted.
mila apradhi of hatya 22 graminon, he thi originally given a life sentence, but only served three and a half years under house arrest.
The massacre took place in the hamlets of my lai or my khe of bete my gaanv.
The event is bhi gyaat as the bete my narsanhaar, visheshkar in the Vietnamese state media.
The U.S. sainya codeword liye the `` viet cong stronghold '' thi `` Pinkville ''.
The ghatana prompted vaishvik aakrosh jab it became public knowledge in 1969.
The massacre also increased gharelu vipaksh to the u.S. bhagidaari in the Vietnam War.
Three U.S. servicemen jo tha aajamaaya to halt the narsanhaar or protect the wounded yahood initially denounced by several U.S. Congressmen as traitors.
They praapt nafrat mail or maut khatre or mila mutilated animals on their doorsteps.
The teen yahood baad widely praised or sajaa by the Army for their heroic actions.
The hijackers in the sitambar 11 hamale yahood 19 main sambhddha saath al-qaeda, or 15 of the 19 were citizens of Saudi Arabia.
Others were from mishra, lebanon, or the UAE.
The hijackers yahood vyavasthit into chaar tiimon, prayek led by a pilot-trained hijacker saath chaar `` mansapeshi hijackers '' jo yahood prashikshit to help subdue the pilots, passengers, and crew.
The first hijackers to arrive in the sanyukt rajya yahood khalid al-mihdhar or nawaf al-hazmi, who settled in the San Diego area in January 2000.
They were followed by teen hijacker-pilots, mohammad atta, marwan al-shehhi, or ziad jarrah jaldi in the garmiyaan of 2000 to undertake udaan prashikshan in south Florida.
The fourth hijacker-pilot, hani hanjour, arrived in san diego in disambar 2000.
The rest of the `` muscle hijackers '' arrived in the vasant or jaldi garmiyaan of 2001, bas maheene pehle the sitambar 11 attacks.
Abū al-Qāsim Muḥammad ibn ʿAbd Allāh ibn ʿAbd al-Muṭṭalib ibn Hāshim ( ) ( circa| 570 – circa| 8 june 632 ), bhi transliterated as mohammad ( ), thi a dharmik, rajnatik, or sainya netaa isse makka jo ekikrut arab into a single religious polity under Islam.
He is believed by Muslims or bahá'ís to be a messanger or nabi of God.
Muhammad is almost universally mana by musalmaan as the pichhlaa nabi bheja by parameshwar for mankind.
non-muslims lihaaz mohammad as the founder of Islam.
Muslims consider him to be the restorer of an anchhue asli monotheistic aasthaa of aadam, nuh, abraham, musa, Jesus, and other prophets.
Born in about 570 CE in the Arabian city of Mecca, he was orphaned at an jaldi aayu or brought up antargat the parvaah of uske taaoo abu talib.
He later worked zyaadaatar as a vyapaaree, as khub as a gadriye, or thi pehla shaadishuda by age 25.
Being in the habit of periodically retreating to a cave in the surrounding mountains for several nights of seclusion and prayer, he later reported ki it thi vahin, at aayu 40, ki he praapt uske pehla rahasyodghatan isse parameshwar.
teen saalo baad is event mohammad prarambh upadesh ye khulaase saream, proclaiming that `` God is One ``, that complete `` surrender '' to Him ( lit.
islām ) is the only way ( dīn ) acceptable to God, and that he himself thi a nabi or messanger of parameshwar, in the vahi rag as anya islamic nabiyon.
Muhammad gained few followers jaldi on, or thi mili saath dushmani isse kuch meccan janajatiyon ; he or his followers were treated harshly.
To escape persecution, mohammad bheja kuch of uske anusarankarta to abisinia pehle he or uske anusarankarta in makka migrated to Medina ( then known as Yathrib ) in the year 622.
This event, the Hijra, marks the shuruuaat of the islamic panchang, jisase is bhi gyaat as the Hijri Calendar.
In Medina, Muhammad united the janajatiyon antargat the samvidhan of madina.
After eight years of fighting with the meccan janajatiyon, uske anusarankarta, jo by tab tha grown to 10,000, took control of makka in the largely peaceful Conquest of Mecca.
He destroyed the pagan idols in the city and then sent his anusarankarta out to nasht sab of the baaki pagan mandiron in purvi arab.
In 632, a few maheene baad returning to madina isse the vidaai yatraaen, Muhammad fell ill and died.
By the samay of uske maut, sabase of the arabian prayadweep tha parivartit to Islam, and he had united Arabia into a single Muslim religious polity.
The khulaase ( or Ayah, lit.
`` Signs [ of God ] '' ) — which Muhammad reported receiving until his death – form the aayatein of the quran, regarded by musalmaan as the `` shabd of parameshwar '' or around jisase the dharm is based.
Besides the Quran, Muhammad 's jivan ( sira ) or paramparaon ( sunnat ) hai bhi upheld by Muslims as the sources of sharia law.
They discuss Muhammad and other nabiyon of islam saath reverence, adding the phrase salaam be upon use whenever their names are mentioned.
While conceptions of mohammad in madhyakaalin christendom or premodern times yahood largely rinatmak, appraisals in modern history have been far less so.
This is a list of tables of the verified oldest logon in the sansar in ordinal rank, aise as oldest vyakti or oldest man.
In these tables, a supercentenarian is considered 'verified ' if his or her claim has been validated by an international body that specifically deals in longevity research, aise as the jaraavidya shodh samooh ( grg ) or ginis sansar record.
The longest unambiguously pralekhith insaan jeevankaal is ki of jeanne Calment of France ( 1875–1997 ), who died at age 122 years, 164 days.
She met vincent vine gogh jab wo thi 12 or 13.
This led to news media dhyaan in 1985, baad calment turned 110.
Subsequent investigation found documentation for Calment 's age, beyond any reasonable sawaal, in the record of uske deshi nagar, arles, frans.
adhik pramaan of calment 's jeevankaal rai maharoom utpaadit than liye koi anya supercentenarian ; uske case serves as an archetype in the methodology for verifying the ages of the world 's oldest people.
The longest undisputed jeevankaal liye purush supercentenarians is ki of jiroemon kimura, jo currently lives in Japan and is age as of.
Since the death of 115-year old Dina Manfredini of the United States, on 17 disambar 2012, kimura, born 19 april 1897, is the oldest jeena vyakti in the sansar jinaki aayu can be documented.
He has also been the oldest jeena man chunki the maut of 114-year boodha walter breuning on 14 april 2011.
Since the death of 115-year boodha koto okubo of japani on 12 janvari 2013, the oldest jeena woman has been -year-old Misao Okawa, also from Japan, born on 5 March 1898.
