Heavy metal ( often referred to as metal ) is a genre of rock music ki viksit in the let 1960s or jaldi 1970s, largely in the sanyukt kingdom and in the United States.
With roots in blues rock and cicedelik chattan, the bands ki nirmit baari metal viksit a motaa, vishaal dhwani, characterized by highly amplified distortion, extended guitar solos, emphatic beats, and overall loudness.
Heavy metal lyrics and pradarshan sheliyaan hai generally sambhddha saath mardaangi and machismo.
the pehla baari metal bands aise as led zeppelin, gahan jamuni or blike sabbath aakarshith vishaal audiyans, haalanki ve yahood often derided by critics, a status common throughout the history of the genre.
In the mid-1970s Judas Priest helped spur the genre 's evolution by discarding much of iske bluez influence ; motörhead introduced a pank chattan sensibility or an increasing jor on speed.
Bands in the New Wave of British Heavy metal aise as aayran maiden followed in a samaan vein.
Before the samaapt of the dashak, baari metal prashansak became known as `` metalheads `` or `` headbangers ``.
During the 1980s, glam metal became a vanijyik force saath samooh jaise Mötley Crüe and Poison.
Underground scenes produced an array of more extreme, aggressive styles : thrash metal broke into the mukhyadhara saath bands aise as metalika, megadeth, slayer, or anthrex, jabaki anya sheliyaan of the sabase charam subgenres of metal jaise death metal and black metal remain subcultural phenomena.
Since the mid-1990s, popular styles aise as nu metal, jisase praayah incorporates tatv of grunge or hip hop ; or metalcore, jisase mishranon charam metal saath hardkor pank, have further expanded the definition of the genre.
The far-right ( also known as the charam sahi ) refers to the ucchtam oopaadhi of rightism in right-wing politics.
Far right politics involves support of strong or complete social hierarchy in society, and supports supremacy of certain individuals or samooh deemed to be innately shreshth or astabalon jo hai to be adhik valued than those deemed to be innately avar or avaanchhneeya.
The far right 's advocacy of supremacism is based on what its adherents perceive as swaabhaavik visheshtaayen of logon ki can nahin be badla.
This stands as a point of antar saath the centre-right 's aropan of behaviours, aise as aalasy or decadence, as the primary sources of social inequalities.
the kendra right—unlike the dur right—claims ki logon can samaapt unke behavioural inferiority through changing their habits and choices.
The original far right, which emerged in France after the French Revolution, refused to accept the french ganatantr or samarthit a counter-revolution to restore the French monarchy and aristocracy.
The far right is commonly sambhddha saath vyaktiyon or samooh jo tham charam rashtravaadi, xenophobic, jatvaad, religious fundamentalist or reactionary views.
The most extreme-right movements have dhada daman or narsanhaar viruddh samooh of logon on the aadhaar of their alleged inferiority.
Thomas Hobbes of Malmesbury ( 5 April 1588 – 4 disambar 1679 ), in kuch puraani granth thomas habs of malmsbury, thi an angrezi paras, behtareen gyaat aaj for his work on political philosophy.
His 1651 book Leviathan established the foundation for sabase of pashchimi rajnatik darshanashastra isse the pariprekshya of soshal contract theory.
Hobbes was a champion of absolutism for the sovereign, but he also developed some of the fundamentals of European liberal thought : the right of the individual ; the natural equality of all men ; the artificial character of the political order ( which led to the later distinction between civil samaaj or the rajya ) ; the drishy ki sab legitimate rajnatik shakti jarur be `` pratinidhi '' or aadhaarit on the sahmati of the logon ; or a udaar nirvachan of vidhi jisase pattey logon free to do whatever the vidhi karata nahin explicitly forbid.
He was one of the sansthaapakon of aadhunik rajnatik darshanashastra.
His understanding of humans as being matter and motion, obeying the same physical laws as other matter and motion, remains influential ; and his account of insaan prakruti as self-interested sahyog, or of rajnatik samudaayon as hone aadhaarit upon a `` soshal anubandh `` remains ek of the major topics of political philosophy.
In addition to political philosophy, Hobbes also contributed to a vividh sarani of anya field, sahit itihaas, bhugol, the bhautikee of gaison, dharamshastra, aachaar, or general philosophy.
Emotional intelligence ( EI ) is the ability to identify, assess, or control the bhav of oneself, of others, and of groups.
It can be divided into kshamta ei or trait EI.
Ability EI is usually measured using adhiktam pradarshan pareekshan or rai stronger sambandh saath paramparaagat pragna, whereas trait EI is usually measured using self-report questionnaires and has stronger relationships with personality.
Criticisms have centered on whether ei is a real pragna or whether it rai vriddhishil vaid over IQ and the Big Five personality traits.
Heredity is the passing of traits to aulad isse iske abhibhavak or purvaj.
This is the process by which an aulad koshika or sajiv acquires or becomes predisposed to the visheshtaayen of its parent cell or organism.
Through heredity, variations exhibited by individuals can accumulate or kaaran kuch prajati to evolve.
The study of anuvanshikta in jeevigyaan is pukaara anuvanshiki, jisase shaamil the field of epigenetics.
For United States individual aay kar, samyojit sakal aay ( agi ) is kul sakal aay minus specific reductions.
Taxable income is samyojit sakal aay rin bhatton liye nijee chhuton and itemized deductions.
For most individual tax purposes, agi is adhik praasangik than sakal income.
Gross income is sales price of goods or property, rin laagat of the property bechi, plus other income.
It includes wages, byaaj, dividends, kaarobaar aay, rental aay, or sab other types of income.
Adjusted gross income is gross income less deductions from a kaarobaar or rental kaaryaklap or 21 anya vishisht vasteen.
Several deductions ( e.g. chikitsa kharch or vividh itemized deductions ) hai simit aadhaarit on a percentage of AGI.
Certain phase outs, including those of lower kar daron or itemized deductions, hai aadhaarit on str of agi.
Many states base state income tax on agi saath nishchit deductions.

Metformin ( BP, sunaaya, ; originally bechi as glucophage ) is an maukhik antidiabetic drug in the biguanide class.
It is the first-line drug of choice for the treatment of type 2 madhumeh, in particular, in overweight or mote logon or those with normal kidney function.
iske upyog in garbhakalin madhumeh has been limited by safety concerns.
It is also used in the treatment of polycystic ovary syndrome, or rai maharoom investigated liye anya rogon jahaan insulin pratirodh may be an important factor.
Metformin works by suppressing glucose utpaadan by the liver.
Metformin is the only antidiabetic drug that has maharoom conclusively dikhaaya to prevent the cardiovascular complications of diabetes.
It helps reduce ldl cholestrol or triglyceride str, or is nahin associated with weight gain.
, metformin is one of only two oral antidiabetics in the sansar swasthya sanghathan model suchi of anivaary davaaiyaan ( the other being glibenclamide ).
When prescribed appropriately, metformin causes few pratikul prabhaav ( the sabase aam is jathrantra pareshaan ) or is sambhddha saath a kam risk of hypoglycemia.
Lactic acidosis ( a buildup of lactate in the blood ) can be a serious chintaa in overdose or jab it is vihit to logon saath contraindications, lakin varanaa, there is no significant risk.
First synthesized and found to reduce blood sugar in the 1920s, metformin thi forgotten liye the aglaa do dashakon as shodh shifted to insulin or anya antidiabetic drugs.
Interest in metformin was rekindled in the late 1940s after several reports ki it could reduce rakt sugar str in logon, or in 1957, french chikitsak jaan sterne prakashit the pehla naidanik vichaaran of metformin as a treatment for diabetes.
it thi introduced to the sanyukt kingdom in 1958, Canada in 1972, and the United States in 1995.
Metformin is now believed to be the sabase widely vihit antidiabetic drug in the sansar ; in the sanyukt rajya alon, adhik than 48 lakh prescriptions were filled in 2010 for its generic formulations.
The Mount Rushmore National Memorial is a sculpture carved into the granite face of mount rushmore nikat keystone, dakshin dakota, in the sanyukt rajya.
sculpted by danish-american gutzon borglum or uske bete, lincoln borglum, mount rushmore suvidhaayen sculptures of the heads of chaar sanyukt rajya raashtrapatiyon : George Washington, Thomas Jefferson, Theodore Roosevelt and Abraham Lincoln.
the sampurna memorial cover or is upar sea level.
The tallest pahaad in the pradesh is Harney Peak ( ).
South Dakota historian Doane Robinson is credited with conceiving the idea of carving the likenesses of prasiddh logon into the blike pahadiyaan pradesh of dakshin dakota in anukram to prachaar paryaton in the region.
Robinson 's initial vichaar thi to sculpt the needles ; however, gutzon borglum asweekrut the needles site because of the poor quality of the granite and strong opposition from environmentalists and Native American groups.
They settled on the Mount Rushmore location, which also has the laabh of facing southeast liye adhiktam surya expozar.
Robinson wanted it to feature western heroes like Lewis and Clark, Red badal or bhens vidheyak kodi lakin borglum decided the murtikla chahie have a adhik neshnal fokas, or chose the chaar raashtrapatiyon jinaki likenesses would be carved into the mountain.
After securing federal funding, nirmaan on the memorial began in 1927, or the raashtrapatiyon ' faces were completed between 1934 and 1939.
Upon Gutzon borglum 's maut in kooch 1941, uske bete lincoln borglum took over construction.
Although the initial concept called for each president to be chitrit isse sir to qamar, kami of funding majaboor nirmaan to end in late October 1941.
The U.S. National Park Service took control of the memorial in 1933, jabaki it thi still antargat nirmaan, or has managed the memorial to the present day.
It attracts nearly teen lakh logon annually.

Nicolas Poussin ( ; 15 June 1594 – 19 November 1665 ) was the leading painter of the classical french barok style, haalanki he kharch sabase of uske working jivan in Rome.
His work is characterized by spashtataa, logic, or anukram, and favors line over color.
Until the 20th century he remained a pramukh prerana liye aise classically unmukh kalakaaron as jacques-louis daud, Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres and Paul Cézanne.
He worked in Rome for a circle of leading collectors there and elsewhere, magar liye a choti kaal jab cardinal richalu ordered use waapas to frans to serve as First Painter to the King.
sabase of uske works hai itihaas paintings of dharmik or mythological subjects that very often have a large landscape element.

A statute is a aupchaarik likhaa enactment of a vidhaan praadhikaar ki governs a state, city, or county.
Typically, statutes command or prohibit kuch, or ghoshit policy.
The word is often prayukt to fark vidhi bana by vidhaan laashen isse maamla vidhi, decided by courts, and regulations issued by government agencies.
statutes hai sometimes referred to as vidhaan or `` black letter law. ''
As a sorce of vidhi, statutes hai mana praathmik praadhikaar ( as opposed to secondary authority ).
Ideally all statutes jarur be in saamanjasy saath the aadharbhoot law of the land ( constitutional ).
is shabd is prayukt in contradistinction to the common law.
Statutes acquire their force isse the samay of unke dyodhi, however jabatak otherwise provided.
statutes hai of anek kinds ; namely, Public or private.
declaratory or remedial.
asthai or perpetual.
A temporary statute is ek jisase is simit in iske duration at the time of its enactment.
It continues in force jabatak the samay of iske limitation rai samaapt, jabatak sooner repealed.
A perpetual statute is ek liye the firaakar of jisase vahin is no simit samay, haalanki it may not be expressly declared to be so.
If, however, a statute which did not itself contain any limitation is to be governed by another jisase is asthai tabhi, the former will also be temporary and dependent upon the existence of the latter.
Before a statute becomes law in some countries, it must be sahamat upon by the ucchtam karypalika in the sarkari, or aakhirkaar prakashit as part of a code.
In many countries, statutes are organized in topical intjaam ( or `` samhitabaddh '' ) bheetar publications pukaara code, aise as the United States Code.
In many raashtra statutory vidhi is vishisht isse or adhinsth to constitutional law.

ve proceed agravarti or avar saath the medial border of the psoas major muscles.
They exit the pelvic girdle posterior or avar to the vankshan snaayu parichay ek teesraa laterally isse the pravisht point of the vankshan ligament on the pubic tubercle at which point they are referred to as the femoral arteries.
The external iliac artery is usually the dhamni prayukt to sanlagn the renal dhamni to the praptakarta of a kidney transplant.
Steam is a digital distribution, digital rights prabandhan, ekaadhik or sanchaar manch viksit by valve nigam.
It is used to distribute games and sambandhit media online, isse choti swatantra develper to larger tantra gharon ; in aktubar 2012, valve vistaarit the seva to include non-gaming software.
Steam provides the user with installation and automatic management of tantra aarpaar anek computer, jatiyaan suvidhaayen aise as mitron suchiyaan or samooh, badal chhayankan, or in-game awaz or gapshap functionality.
The software provides a freely available application programming interface, Steamworks, that developers can take advantage of to integrate many of Steam 's functions within their software products, sahit nakal suraksha, netwarking or matchmaking, in-game uplabdhiyaan or micro-transactions, or support liye user-created saamagree through bhaap kaaryshaala.
Though initially developed for use on Microsoft khidkiyaan, the claayent rai vistaarit to shaamil os x or linaks sanskaran, or client saath simit kaaryakshmata on the plastesan 3 console and for both iOS and Android mobile devices.
In addition to being a central hub for gaming software, valve rai nirmit a sanskaran of bhaap saath altered kaaryakshmata to be prayukt in skulon for educational software, including a modified version of Portal 2 for teaching science and critical thinking lessons.
, there are nearly 2000 games available through bhaap, or 54 lakh kriyasheel user accounts.

The Rhine ( ; ; ) is a European river that runs from the Swiss canton of Grisons in the southeastern Swiss Alps through Germany and eventually flows into the uttar samudr coast in the netherlands or is the barahavin longest nadi in europea, at parichay, saath an ausat nirvahan of adhik than.
The rin or the denube formed sabase of the uttari antardeshiy frontier of the roman samrajya or, chunki those dinon, the Rhine has been a vital and navigable waterway carrying trade and goods deep inland.
It has also served as a rakshaatmak visheshta or rai maharoom the aadhaar liye kshetreey or international borders.
The many castles and pragaitihaasik fortifications saath the rin gavaahi to its importance as a waterway.

Sri ( Devanagari : shri, IAST ; Śrī ), bhi transliterated as sree or shri or shri is a shabd of sanskrit utpatti, prayukt in the bhartiya upmahadweep as vinamr rup of pataa equivalent to the English `` Mr. '' in written and spoken language, or as a title of veneration for deities ( usually translated as `` Holy '' ).

Civil engineering is a professional engineering discipline that deals with the design, construction, and maintenance of the shaareerik or naturally nirmit paryaavaran, sahit works jaise sadaken, pulon, naharon, dams, or buildings.
Civil engineering is the oldest engineering discipline after sainya abhiyantriki, or it thi paribhaashit to fark non-military abhiyantriki isse sainya abhiyantriki.
It is traditionally broken into several sub-disciplines including environmental abhiyantriki, bhootkneekee abhiyantriki, bhubhautikee, bhuganit, control abhiyantriki, sanrachanaatmak abhiyantriki, biomechanics, nanotechnology, parivahan abhiyantriki, dharti vigyaan, vayumandaleey sciences, forensic abhiyantriki, nagarpalika or shahari abhiyantriki, jal resources engineering, materials engineering, coastal engineering, surveying, and construction engineering.
Civil engineering takes place on all levels : in the public sector isse nagarpalika through to neshnal sarkarein, or in the nijee sector isse vyaktigat homeowners through to international companies.

Katherine Dunham ( June 22, 1909 – May 21, 2006 ) thi an amareeki nartki, koreographer, lekhak, educator, and social activist.
Dunham had one of the most successful dance careers in American and European theatre of the 20th sadi, or nirdeshit uske apana nrity company for many years.
wo rai maharoom pukaara the `` matriarch or maharani maan of black dance ''.
During her heyday in the 1940s and 1950s, Dunham was prasiddh throughout europea or latin america or thi widely lokapriy in the sanyukt rajya, jahaan the washington Post called her `` dancer Katherine the Great ''.
For almost thirty years she maintained the Katherine Dunham nrity company, the tabhi self-supported amareeki blike nrity troupe at ki samay, and over her long career she choreographed more than ninety individual dances.
Dunham thi an innovator in african-american aadhunik nrity as khub as a netaa in the field of dance anthropology, or ethnochoreology.
Sphagnum is a genus of between 1510 and 3500 species of mosses, commonly pukaara peat moss due to iske vyapaktaa in geela habitats jahaan it contributes to the formation of peat bogs and mires.
Sphagnum accumulations can store jal, chunki dono jeena or murde paudhe can tham vishaal quantities of jal andar unke koshikaayen ; plants may hold from 16-26 times as much water as their dry weight depending on the species.
The empty cells help retain jal in drier sharten.
Hence, as sphagnum moss grows, it can dhire sprad into drier sharten, forming larger peatlands, both raised bogs and blanket bogs.
These peat accumulations then provide awaas liye a chaudee sarani of peatland paudhe, sahit sedges and ericaceous shrubs, as well as orchids and carnivorous plants.
Sphagnum and the peat formed isse it do nahin kshay readily kuki of the phenolic yogicon antahsthapit in the moss 's cell walls.
In addition, bogs, like all wetelends, develop avayaviya mrudaa sharten, jisase produces dhimaa avayaviya kshay balki than aerobic microbial action.
Peat moss can also acidify its parivesh by lene up cations, aise as calcium or magnesium, or releasing hydrogen ions.
Under the sahi sharten, peat can accumulate to a depth of many meters.
alag prajati of sphagnum have alag sahishnutaa had for flooding and pH, so any one peatland may have a number of different Sphagnum species.
Individual peat moss plants consist of a pramukh stem, saath tightly arranged cluster of shakha fascicles praayah consisting of do or three spreading branches and two to four hanging branches.
The top of the plant, or capitulum, rai compact cluster of young branches.
saath the stem hai bikhare pattey of vibhinn aakaar, namit stem pattey ; the shape varies according to species.
The pattey consist of do kinds of koshikaayen ; choti, green, jeena koshikaayen ( chlorophyllose cells ), and large, clear, structural, dead cells ( hyaline cells ).
the latter have the large water-holding capacity.

The Network Railcard is a discount card introduced in 1986 by angrejon rail, upon the sristi of unke sanjaal southeast area around London, England.
The card is intended to encourage leisure travel by rail by offering discounts liye vayaskon or accompanying children on a chaudee dayera of off-peak kiraye.
The range of discounts available, and the price of the card, have varied chunki ki samay, lakin the card rai sadaa maharoom maanya liye a saal 's aseemit use.
It can be purchased by any person aged 16 or over from any staffed National Rail station or rail niyukt safar agent, by completing an anuprayog rup - no photographic pahchaan or anya dastavezikaran is needed to buy or use the card.
It is one of a number of concessionary kiraaya yojanaayen uplabdhiyaan on the angrejon railway system.
The United Nations ( UN ; French : sanghathan des raashtra unies, onu ) is the sansar 's largest, foremost, or most prominent international organization.
The stated aims of the United Nations include promoting and facilitating sahyog in antarrashtriya vidhi, antarrashtriya suraksha, aarthik vikaas, soshal pragati, insaan adhikaron, civil adhikaron, civil liberties, rajnatik freedoms, democracy, and the achievement of lasting world peace.
The UN was founded in 1945 after World War ii to badalen the lig of raashtra, to roke yudhon between deshon, or to provide a manch for dialogue.
it contains anek subsidiary sanghathan to carry out its missions.
At its founding, the un tha 51 sadsy rajya ; as of 2011, there are 193.
From its offices around the world, the UN and its specialized agenciyon decide on satya or prashasnic mudde in niyamit baithak yojit throughout the year.
The organization has six principal organs : the General Assembly ( the main deliberative assembly ) ; the suraksha parishad ( liye deciding nishchit rizolution liye salaam or suraksha ) ; the aarthik or soshal parishad ( liye assisting in promoting antarrashtriya aarthik or soshal sahyog or vikaas ) ; the sachivalay ( liye providing adhyayan, soochna, or suvidhaayen needed by the UN ) ; the International Court of Justice ( the primary judicial organ ) ; and the United Nations Trusteeship Council ( which is currently inactive ).
Other prominent un pranali agenciyon shaamil the sansar swasthya sanghathan ( jo ), the World Food Programme ( WFP ) and United Nations Children 's Fund ( UNICEF ).
The UN 's most prominent position is that of the office of secretary-general jisase rai maharoom yojit by bain ki-moon of dakshin Korea since 2007.
The sanyukt raashtra mukhyalay resides in antarrashtriya territory in nai york nagar, saath further main offices at Geneva, Nairobi, and Vienna.
The organization is financed from assessed or voluntary yogadan isse iske sadsy rajya, or rai chah aadhikarik bhashaaen : Arabic, Chinese, English, French, Russian, and Spanish.
South Beach, also nicknamed SoBe, is a neighborhood in the city of Miami bich, florida, sanyukt rajya, stith due east of miami nagar uchit between biscayne khadi or the atlantic Ocean.
The kshetrafal encompasses sab of the avrodh islands of Miami Beach south of Indian Creek.
This area was the first section of Miami Beach to be developed, starting in the 1910s, dhanyavad to the vikaas praytn of karl G. fisher, the lummus bhaaiyo, or jon S. colins, the latter jinaki nirmaan of the colins sethu provided the pehla vital jameen link between mainland Miami and the beaches.
The area has gone through numerous artificial and prakritik parivartan over the saalo, sahit a booming kshetreey arthvyavastha, increased tourism, and the 1926 hurricane, which destroyed much of the area.
As of 2010, parichay 39,186 nivaasiyon sajiv in South Beach.
The United States presidential election of 1960 was the 44th quadrennial adhyakshiya chunaav, yojit on mangalvaar, navambar 8, 1960.
The Republican Party manonith laazim vice-president richard nicksan, jabaki the loktantric party manonith John F. Kennedy, Senator from Massachusetts.
The incumbent President, Republican Dwight D. Eisenhower, was not eligible for re-election baad sevarat the adhiktam do sharten anumat by the twenty-second amendment.
Kennedy was nirvaachit saath a sise of 112,827 mat, or 0.17 % of the lokapriy vote, giving use a vijay of 303 to 219 in the Electoral College, the closest since 1916.
This was the first chunaav in jisase sab pachaas of the vartmaan sanyukt rajya participated.
a kramank of karkon bataaiye kyon the election was so close.
Kennedy gained since vahin thi an aarthik mandi jisase thes the laazim republican, or he had the advantage of 17 million more registered Democrats than Republicans.
Furthermore, the new votes that Kennedy gained among catholics lagbhag neutralized the nai mat nicksan gained among protestants.
kennedy 's campaigning kaushal decisively outmatched Nixon 's.
In the end, Nixon 's jor on uske anubhav carried choti vazan, or he wasted urja by campaigning in all 50 states instead of concentrating on the swing states.
Kennedy prayukt uske vishaal, well-funded abhiyaan sanghathan to jeet the namakan, surakshit samarthan, or, saath the sahaayta of the last of the big-city bosses, to get out the vote in the big cities.
He relied on kaaryshil mate lyndon B. johnson to tham the dakshin or used television effectively.
This election is notable as being the first time in U.S. itihaas ki do baithe u.s. seenetteron ( kennedy or johnson ) yahood nirvaachit as adhyaksh or vice-president, a ghatana ki rai maharoom doharaaya once, by Barack Obama and Joe Biden in 2008 ( in both cases, the president was the younger, more junior senator ).

Macbeth is a play likhaa by wiliam shakespeare.
It is considered ek of uske darkest or sabase shaktishaalee tragedies.
niyat in scotland, the khel dramatizes the corroding manovaigyanik or rajnatik prabhaav utpaadit jab its protagonist, the Scottish lord Macbeth, chooses evil as the way to fulfill his ambition for power.
He commits regicide to become king and then furthers his moral descent with a reign of murderous aatank to raho in shakti, aakhirkaar plunging the desh into civil yuddh.
In the samaapt, he loses sabakuch ki detaa arth or purpose to uske life before losing his life itself.
The play is believed to have been likhaa between 1603 or 1607, or is sabase commonly dinaak 1606.
The earliest account of a pradarshan of kayaa thi sambhawatah shakespeare 's khel is april 1611, jab simon forman ankit seeing such a play at the Globe Theatre.
It was first published in the folio of 1623, sambhawatah from a prompt book.
It was most likely written during the reign of James i, jo tha maharoom james vi of scotland pehle he succeeded to the angrezi singhaasana in 1603.
James was a patron of Shakespeare’s acting company, and of all the plays Shakespeare likhaa dauraan james’s shasankaal, makebeth sabase clearly reflects the playwright’s sambandh saath the sovereign.
Macbeth is Shakespeare’s shortest tragedy, or tells the story of a vir scottish saamaanya namit makebeth jo receives a prophecy isse a tikdi of witches that one day he will become King of Scotland.
Consumed by mahatvakanksha or spurred to karrwai by uske bivi, makebeth hatyaein king dancan or takes the throne for himself.
His shasankaal is racked saath guilt or paranoia, or he jald becomes a tyrannical ruler as he is forced to commit more and more murders to protect himself from enmity and suspicion.
The bloodbath swiftly takes Macbeth and mahila makebeth into realms of arrogance, deewangi, or death.
Shakespeare 's source for the tragedy is the khaataa of king makebeth of scotland, macduff, or dancan in holinshed 's chronicals ( 1587 ), a itihaas of england, scotland or ireland parichit to shakespeare or uske contemporaries, although the events in the play differ extensively from the history of the real Macbeth.
In the backstage world of theatre, kuch maananaa ki the khel is shaapit, or hoga nahin zikr iske sheershak aloud, referring to it instead as `` the Scottish play ``.
Over the course of many centuries, the khel rai aakarshith kuch of the sabase prasiddh abhinaytaon to the roles of Macbeth and Lady Macbeth.
It has been adapted to film, television, opera, novels, comic kitabe, and other media.
The Milton Hershey School is a private paropkaaree ( pre-k through 12 ) boarding skool in hershey, pencilvenia.
Originally named the Hershey Industrial skool, the sanstha thi santhaapit or vittposhit by chocolate udyogpati milton snavely hershey or uske bivi, catherine Sweeney Hershey.

With over six billion dollars in assets, the Milton hershey skool is ek of the wealthiest skulon in the sansar.

The Controlled Substances Act ( CSA ) was enacted into vidhi by the congress of the sanyukt rajya as sheershak ii of the vyapak drug Abuse Prevention and Control Act of 1970.
The CSA is the federal U.S. drug policy under which the manufacture, importation, kabza, upyog or vitaran of nishchit substances is regulated.
The Act also parosa as the neshnal implementing vidhaan liye the single sammelan on Narcotic Drugs.
The legislation created five Schedules ( classifications ), saath varying yogyata liye a padaarth to be shaamil in each.
Two federal agencies, the Drug Enforcement Administration and the Food and Drug Administration, determine which substances are added to or removed from the various schedules, though the statute passed by congress nirmit the aarambhik listing, or congress rai sometimes anusuchit anya substances through vidhaan aise as the hillory J. farias or samantha reid date-rape rokthaam adhinium of 2000, jisase lagaai gamma hydroxybutyrate in anusuchee i. vargeekaran decisions are required to be made on criteria including potential for abuse ( an undefined term ), currently accepted medical use in treatment in the United States, and international treaties.
Second-language acquisition or second-language siikhnaa is the prakram by jisase logon sikh a second language.
Second-language acquisition ( often abbreviated to sla ) bhi refers to the vaigyanik anushaasan devoted to studying that process.
Second language refers to any language learned in addition to a vyakti 's pehla bhashaa ; haalanki the avadharana is namit second-language adhigrahan, it can bhi charitaarth the learning of third, fourth, or subsequent languages.
second-language adhigrahan refers to kayaa learners do ; it does not refer to practices in language teaching.
The academic discipline of second-language adhigrahan is a subdiscipline of applied linguistics.
It is broad-based and relatively new.
As well as the various branches of bhashavigyaan, second-language adhigrahan is bhi closely sambandhit to manovigyaan, cognitive psychology, and education.
To separate the academic discipline from the learning process itself, the terms second-language adhigrahan shodh, second-language adhyayan, or second-language adhigrahan adhyayan are also used.
SLA research began as an interdisciplinary field, or kuki of is it is mushkil to pahachaano a precise starting date.
However, it karata appear to have viksit a great saude chunki the mid-1960s.
The term acquisition was originally used to emphasize the avchetan prakruti of the siikhnaa prakram, lakin in haal saalo siikhnaa or acquisition have become largely synonymous.
Second-language acquisition can incorporate viraasat bhashaa siikhnaa, lakin it karata nahin usually incorporate bilingualism.
Most SLA researchers see bilingualism as hone the samaapt parinaam of siikhnaa a bhashaa, nahin the prakram itself, or dekhie the pad as referring to native-like fluency.
Writers in fields such as shiksha or manovigyaan, however, praayah upyog bilingualism loosely to refer to all forms of multilingualism.
Second-language acquisition is also not to be contrasted with the acquisition of a foreign language ; rather, the learning of second bhashaaen or the siikhnaa of videshi bhashaaen involve the vahi aadharbhoot prakriyaaon in alag halatas..
There has been much bahes parichay exactly kaisaa bhashaa is siikhe, or anek issues are still unresolved.
There are many theories of second-language acquisition, but none hai sweekrut as a puraa spashtikaran by sab sla shodhakartaaon.
Due to the interdisciplinary nature of the field of second-language adhigrahan, is is nahin apekshit to happen in the foreseeable future.

The sanyukt rajya rahasy seva is a u.S. sangheey vidhi pravartan agency that is part of the United States Department of Homeland Security.
the sworn sadasyon hai vibhajit among the khaas agenton and the Uniformed Division.
Until March 1, 2003, the seva thi bhaag of the sanyukt rajya vibhaag of the Treasury.
The U.S. rahasy seva rai do pruthak areas of responsibility:
Financial Crimes, covering missions such as prevention and chaanbin of counterfeiting of u.S. karency or u.S. rajkosh pratibhuti, and investigation of major fraud.
Protection, which entails ensuring the safety of current and former national leaders or unke pariwaron, aise as the adhyaksh, past raashtrapatiyon, vaais raashtrapatiyon, adhyakshiya ummidavaar, visiting heads of rajya, or videshi embassies ( per an agreement with the U.S. State Department 's Bureau of Diplomatic Security ( DS ) Office of Foreign Missions ( OFM ), etc. )
The rahasy seva 's aarambhik jimmedaari thi to investigate counterfeiting of u.S. karency, which was rampant following the U.S. Civil War.
The agency tab viksit into the sanyukt rajya ' pehla gharelu pragna or counterintelligence agency.
Many of the agency 's missions were later taken over by subsequent agencies such as the Federal Bureau of Investigation ( FBI ), beuro of daaru, tambaaku, firearms or visphotak ( atf ), avrajan or custom pravartan ( barf ), or aatanrik Revenue Service ( IRS ).

Franklin Delano Roosevelt ( or ; janvari 30, 1882 – april 12, 1945 ), bhi gyaat by uske adyakshar, fdr, thi the 32nd adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya ( 1933–1945 ) or a central figure in sansar kaarykram dauraan the mid-20th century, leading the United States during a time of worldwide economic depression and total war.
A dominant leader of the loktantric party or the tabhi amareeki adhyaksh nirvaachit to adhik than do sharten, he nirmit a nai saude gathbandhan ki realigned amareeki raajnneeti baad 1932, as uske gharelu policies defined American liberalism for the middle third of the 20th century.
With the bouncy popular song `` prasann dinon hai yahan again `` as uske abhiyaan theme, fdr parajeet incumbent Republican Herbert Hoover in November 1932, at the depth of the Great Depression.
Energized by his personal victory over polio, FDR 's unfailing ashavad or sakriyata contributed to a naveekaran of the neshnal spirit.
He worked closely with British Prime Minister Winston Churchill and Soviet General Secretary Joseph stallin in agrani the allies viruddh germany or japani in sansar yuddh ii, or restoring samruddhi to the swadesh 's economy.
In his first hundred days in daftar, jisase began kooch 4, 1933, rujvelt pathpradarshan pramukh vidhaan or jari a profusion of karypalika aadesh ki instituted the nai saude —a kismein of kaarykram designed to upaj raahat ( sarkari kaary for the unemployed ), recovery ( economic growth ), and reform ( through regulation of Wall Street, banks and transportation ).
The economy improved rapidly isse 1933 to 1937, lakin tab relapsed into a deep recession.
The bipartisan roodhiwaadee gathbandhan ki formed in 1937 prevented uske packing the param adaalat or guzar koi considerable vidhaan ; it abolished many of the relief programs when unemployment diminished during World War II.
Most of the regulations on business were ended parichay 1975–85, magar liye the viniman of wal gali by the pratibhuti or exange ayog, which still exists.
saath saath anek choti kaarykram, pramukh surviving kaarykram shaamil the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, which was created in 1933, and Social Security, which Congress passed in 1935.
As World War II loomed after 1938, with the Japanese akraman of china or the aakraamakata of naaji germany, fdr diya damdaar rajanyik or vittiya support to China and Great Britain, while remaining officially neutral.
His goal thi to mek america the `` arsenal of loktantr `` jisase hota supplai munitions to the Allies.
In March 1941, rujvelt, saath congressional sweekruti, provided lend-lease sahaayta to the countries fighting against Nazi Germany with Britain.
With very strong national support, he made war on Japan and Germany baad the japani akraman on parl harbar on disambar 7, 1941, colling it a `` tithi jisase will live in infamy ``.
He supervised the mobilization of the u.S. arthvyavastha to support the alide yuddh praytn.
As an active military leader, rujvelt implemented an overall yuddh ranneeti on do fronts ki ended in the shikast of the aksh shaktiyaan or the vikaas of the world 's first atom bomb.
in 1942 rujvelt ordered the internment of 100,000 Japanese American civilians.
Unemployment dropped to 2 %, relief programs largely ended, and the industrial economy grew rapidly to new heights as lakho of logon sthanantarit to nai kaary in yuddh centers, or 16 lakh main or 300,000 mahilaon yahood drafted or volunteered for military service.
Roosevelt dominated the American rajnatik jhaanki nahin tabhi dauraan the baarah saalo of uske presidency, lakin bhi liye dashakon afterward.
He orchestrated the realignment of matadaata ki nirmit the paanchvaan Party System.
FDR 's New Deal Coalition united labor sangh, big nagar mashine, shwet ethnics, africa america or rural white Southerners.
He also bahekaave the baad sristi of the United Nations and Bretton Woods.
Roosevelt is consistently rated by scholars as one of the top three U.S. raashtrapatiyon, saath saath abraham lincoln or george washington.
A liberal Democrat, Roosevelt paribhaashit uske vaicharik sthiti as `` a choti left of center. ''
Mara Salvatrucha ( commonly abbreviated as MS, maaraa, or ms-13 ) is a transnational dand giroh ki originated in los angeles or rai sprad to anya parts of the United States, Canada, Mexico, and Central America.
The majority of the gang is ethnically rachit of central america or kriyasheel in shahari or suburban areas.
In the U.S., the MS-13 has an especially heavy presence in Los Angeles County and the San Francisco Bay Area in Northern California ; the washington, d.C. mahanagar kshetron of ferefaques county, virginia, montgomari county, maryland, or prince george 's county, maryland ; long dweep, nai york ; the boston, masachusets kshetrafal ; sherlot, uttar carolina ; or huston, texas.
There is also a presence of ms-13 in toronto, ontario, canada.
Members of MS distinguish themselves by tattoos covering the deh or bhi praayah the phase, as khub as the upyog of unke apana chihn bhashaa.
They are notorious for unke upyog of hinsa or a subcultural moral code ki predominantly consists of merciless revenge and cruel retributions.
This krurta of the vishisht sadasyon of the `` maras '' or `` mareros '' arjeet unhen a path to be recruited by the Sinaloa Cartel battling against Los Zetas in an ongoing drug war south of the United States border.
Their wide-ranging activities have drawn the attention of the FBI and avrajan or custom pravartan, jo have initiated wide-scale chaape viruddh gyaat or suspected giroh sadasyon – netting sainkadon of rakhwale aarpaar the desh.
Bones is an American crime comedy-drama television shrenee ki premiered on the fox sanjaal in the United States on September 13, 2005.
The show is based on forensic maanavshaastra or forensic puraatatv, saath prayek apisod focusing on an epabiai maamla sanchika concerning the rahasy peeche insaan remains brought by epabiai khaas agent seeley booth ( daud boreanaz ) to the forensic anthropologist Dr. Temperance `` Bones '' Brennan ( Emily Deschanel ).
The rest of the main cast shaamil michaela conlin, T. J. thyne, eric millegan, tamara tailor, Jonathan Adams, and John Francis Daley.
Created by Hart Hanson, the shrenee is bahut loosely aadhaarit on the jivan or kritiyaan of upanyaaskaar or forensic anthropologist kathi reichs, jo bhi produces the show.
Its sheershak akshar, temperance briken, is named after the protagonist of Reichs ' crime novel series.
Conversely, Dr. Brennan writes successful mystery novels based around a fictional ( in the haddiyon brahmad ) forensic anthropologist namit kathi reichs.
Bones is a joint production by Josephson entertainment, dur field productions or 20th sadi fox television.
The series has completed airing its aathvin ritu or rai maharoom navinikrut liye a naveen ritu.
Super Bowl XXV was an American football khel between the amareeki footbaal sammelan ( afc ) champion bhens bills or the neshnal footbaal sammelan ( nfc ) champion New York Giants to decide the National Football League ( NFL ) champion for the 1990 season.
The Giants defeated the Bills by the score of 20–19, jeetna unke duusari kabhi Super Bowl.
It is the tabhi super katori decided by one point.
The game was held at tampa stadium in tampa, florida, on janvari 27, 1991, during the height of the Gulf War.
it thi yun nibhaai antargat much patriotic fervor.
The proceedings included a rousing rendition of `` The star-spangled dhvaj `` by whitney huston dauraan the pregame ceremonies.
The Bills and their explosive no-huddle offense were making unke pehla super katori rup baad finishing the niyamit ritu saath a 13-3 ricard, or agrani the lig in total points scored with 428.
In advancing to unke duusari super katori, the diggaj bhi posted a 13-3 niyamit ritu record, but with a ball-control offense and a defense that allowed a league low 211 points.
The game is best remembered for Bills placekicker scot norwood 's last-second field lakshya attempt jisase gai chaudee sahi of the uprights, agrani to a diggaj vijay, and starting a four-game losing streak in the Super Bowl for the Bills.
The Giants set a Super Bowl ricard pakadakar kabza of the ball for 40 minutes and 33 seconds.
New York also overcame a 12-3 second-quarter deficit, or bana a 75-yard touchdown drive ki khapat a super katori record 9:29 off the clock.
Giants kaaryshil waapas ottis anderson, jo carried the ball 21 times liye 102 gaj and one touchdown, was named Super Bowl MVP.
He was the first awardee to receive the newly named `` Pete Rozelle trophy '' ( namit liye the purv kamishnar ).
Anderson bhi ankit ek resepshan liye saat yards.
Malcolm X ( ; May 19, 1925february 21, 1965 ), born mailkam choti or bhi gyaat as el-hajj malik el-shabazz ( ), thi an african-american Muslim minister and human rights activist.
To his admirers, he was a courageous advocate for the rights of ashweton, a man jo indicted shwet america in the harshest sharten liye iske aparaadhon viruddh blike Americans.
Detractors abhiyukt use of upadesh jatvaad, blike sarvocchata, and violence.
He has been called one of the mahanatam or sabase influential African Americans in history.
Malcolm X 's father died—killed by white supremacists, it thi rumored—when he thi yang, or at tanik ek of uske uncles thi lynched.
When he was 13, his maan thi lagaai in a dimagi hospital, or he thi lagaai in a shrenee of foster homes.
in 1946, at aayu 20, he gai to prison for breaking and entering.
In prison, mailkam x became a sadsy of the swadesh of islam ; baad uske parole in 1952, he jaldi rose to become one of its leaders.
For a dozen years, mailkam x thi the public phase of the vivaadaaspad samooh, lakin mohabhang saath swadesh of islam head Elijah Muhammad led him to leave the Nation in March 1964.
After a period of travel in africa or the madhya east, he laute to the sanyukt rajya, jahaan he santhaapit muslim masjide, Inc. and the Organization of Afro-American Unity.
In February 1965, less than a year after leaving the Nation of islam, he thi assassinated by teen sadasyon of the group.
Malcolm X 's expressed manyataon badla substantially over samay.
As a spokesman for the Nation of Islam he taught black supremacy and advocated separation of black and white Americans —in contrast to the civil adhikaron gati 's jor on sangyojan.
After breaking with the Nation of Islam in 1964—saying of uske sangh saath it, `` i kiya anek bate as a [ Black ] Muslim that I 'm sorry for now.
I was a zombie then... pointed in a certain direction and told to march '' —and becoming a Sunni Muslim, he disavowed jatvaad or expressed willingness to kaary saath civil adhikaron netao, he jari to emphasize pan-africanism, black self-determination, and self-defense.

Elizabeth II ( Elizabeth Alexandra Mary ; born 21 April 1926 ) is the constitutional monarch of 16 sovereign rajya, gyaat as the rashtramandal realms, or unke territories or dependencies, or sir of the 54-member rashtramandal of raashtra.
She is param rajyapal of the girijaghar of england or, in kuch of uske realms, carries the title of Defender of the Faith as part of her full title.

at upasthit, in jod to the pehla chaar aforementioned deshon, elizabeth is maharani of jamaica, barbados, the bahama, haraa, papua nai gini, the suleman islands, tuvaalu, sant loosia, sant vincent and the Grenadines, Belize, Antigua and Barbuda and Saint Kitts and Nevis.
Her reign of years is currently the second longest for a British monarch ; tabhi maharani victoria rai reigned longer at over 63 years.

Her rajtilak seva took place in 1953 and was the first to be televised.

Lean manufacturing, lean enterprise, or lean production, often simply, `` Lean, '' is a production practice that considers the expenditure of resources for koi lakshya anya than the sristi of maan liye the samaapt graahak to be apvyay, and thus a target for elimination.
Working from the perspective of the customer jo consumes a utpaada or seva, `` maan '' is paribhaashit as koi karrwai or prakram ki a graahak hota be willing to pay for.
Essentially, lean is centered on preserving maan saath kam kaary.
Lean manufacturing is a management philosophy derived mostly from the Toyota Production System ( tps ) ( hence the pad toyotism is bhi prachlit ) or pahachaanaa as `` jhukna '' tabhi in the 1990s.
TPS is renowned for its focus on katautee of the asli toyota saat wastes to improve overall graahak value, but there are varying perspectives on how this is best achieved.
The steady growth of toyota, isse a choti company to the sansar 's largest automaker, rai kendrit dhyaan on kaisaa it rai hasil is success.

Vitamin A is a group of nutritionally unsaturated hydrocarbons, which include retinol, retinal, retinoic acid or anek provitamin a carotenoids among jisase beta-carotene is the sabase mahatvapurn.
vitamin a rai anek krityon, it is mahatvapurn liye vikaas or vikaas, for the maintenance of the immune system and good vision.
Vitamin A is needed by the retina of the eye in the form of retinal, jisase combines saath protein opsin to rup rhodopsin the light-absorbing anu, ki is jaruri liye dono low-light ( scotopic vision ) and color vision.
vitamin a bhi krityon in a bahut alag bhoomika as an irreversibly oxidized rup of retinul gyaat as retinoic acid, jisase is an important hormone-like growth factor for epithelial and other cells.
In foods of animal origin, the major form of vitamin A is an ester, primarily retinyl palmitate, jisase is parivartit to retinul ( chemically an daaru ) in the choti aant.
The retinol form krityon as a bhandar rup of the vitamin, or can be parivartit to and from its visually active aldehyde form, retinal.
The associated acid ( retinoic acid ), a metabolite ki can be irreversibly synthesized isse vitamin a, rai tabhi aanshik vitamin A activity, and does not function in the retina for the visual cycle.
retinoic acid is prayukt liye vikaas or cellular differentiation.
All forms of vitamin a have a beta-ionone ring to jisase an isoprenoid kadi is attached, called a retinyl group.
Both structural features are anivaary liye vitamin kaaryaklap.
The orange pigment of carrots – beta-carotene – can be represented as do conect retinyl samooh, jisase hai prayukt in the deh to yogadan to vitamin A levels.
alpha-carotene or gamma-carotene bhi have a single retinyl group, which give them some vitamin activity.
none of the anya carotenes have vitamin activity.
The carotenoid beta- cryptoxanthin possesses an ionone samooh or rai vitamin kaaryaklap in insaano.
Vitamin A can be mila in do principal form in foods :
Retinol, the form of vitamin A absorbed when khaane animal khaanaa strot, is a pilaa, fat-soluble padaarth.
chunki the pure daaru rup is asthir, the vitamin is found in tissues in a form of retinyl ester.
It is also commercially utpaadit or administered as esters aise as retinyl acetate or palmitate.
The carotenes alpha-carotene, beta-carotene, gamma-carotene ; and the xanthophyll beta-cryptoxanthin ( all of which contain beta-ionone rings ), lakin no anya carotenoids, falan as provitamin a in herbivores or sarvahari pashu, jisase possess the anzime ( 15-15'-dioxygenase ) jisase cleaves beta-carotene in the intestinal mucosa or converts it retinol.
In general, carnivores are poor converters of ionine-containing carotenoids, and pure carnivores aise as billiyon or ferrets kami 15-15'-dioxygenase or can nahin badalen koi carotenoids to retinal ( resulting in none of the carotenoids being forms of vitamin A for these species ).

Sacramento is the capital city of the u.S. rajya of california or the seat of sarkari of sacramento County.
It is located at the confluence of the Sacramento River and the amareeki nadi in the uttari portion of california 's expansive central ghati.

Its metropolitan area is the fourth largest in california baad the vrihad los angeles kshetrafal, san francisco khadi kshetrafal, or the San Diego metropolitan area, as well as the 25th largest in the United States.
Sacramento was cited by Time patrika as america 's sabase ethnically or racially ekikrut nagar in 2002.

Memorial Day is a United States federal holiday jisase occurs prayek saal on the final somvaar of May.
Memorial Day is a day of remembering the main or mahilaon jo died jabaki sevarat in the sanyukt States Armed Forces.
Formerly known as Decoration Day, it originated after the amareeki civil yuddh to commemorate the sangh or confederate soldiers who died in the Civil War.
By the 20th sadi memorial din tha maharoom vistaarit to sammaan sab Americans who have died in all wars.
It typically marks the start of the garmiyaan avkaash ritu, jabaki majdoor din marks its end.
Many people visit cemeteries and memorials, visheshkar to sammaan those jo have died in sainya seva.
anek swayamsevak place an amareeki dhvaj on each grave in national cemeteries.
By the early 20th sadi, memorial din thi an avasar liye adhik saamaanya expressions of memory, as logon visited the qabron of unke mritak rishtedaaron in church cemeteries, whether they had served in the military or not.
It bhi became a long weekend increasingly devoted to kharidari, parivaar mehphilon, aatishbaajee, yatraayen to the bich, and national media events.
salanaa sajaavat dinon liye particular kabristaan hai yojit on a sande in let vasant or jaldi garmiyaan in kuch rural areas of the American South, notably in the mountains.
In cases involving a family graveyard jahaan remote purvajo as khub as those jo yahood mritak adhik recently hai dafn, is may lo on the character of an extended family reunion to which some people travel hundreds of miles.
People gather on the designated din or put pushp on qabron or navinikrut sampark with kinfolk and others.
There often is a dharmik seva or a `` dinar on the maidan, '' the paramparaagat pad liye a potluck bhojan in jisase logon prayukt to sprad the dishes out on sheets or tablecloths on the grass.
It is believed that this practice began pehle the amareeki civil yuddh or yun may pratibimbit the real utpatti of the `` memorial day '' idea.
Memorial Day is not to be confused saath diggajon din ; memorial din is a din of remembering the main or mahilaon jo died jabaki sevarat, jabaki diggajon din celebrates the service of all U.S. military veterans, living or dead.

Freedom Summer ( also known as the Mississippi Summer Project ) thi a abhiyaan in the sanyukt rajya shubharambh in june 1964 to attempt to panjikaran as anek African American voters as possible in Mississippi, which had historically excluded most blacks from voting.
The project bhi niyat up darjanon of swatantraaa skulon, swatantraaa gharon, or jatiyaan centers in choti towns throughout Mississippi to aid the local black population.
The project thi vyavasthit by the parishad of federated sanghathan ( cofo ), a coalition of the Mississippi branches of the four major civil rights organizations ( SNCC, CORE, NAACP and SCLC ).
sabase of the impetus, netritv, or financing liye the garmiyaan Project came from the SNCC.
Robert Parris musa, sncc field sachiv or co-director of cofo, directed the summer project.
Blues is the name given to both a musical rup or a music vidha ki originated in samudaayon of primarily the `` gahan dakshin `` of the sanyukt rajya around the samaapt of the 19th sadi isse spirituals, work songs, field hollers, shouts and chants, and rhymed simple narrative ballads.
The blues form, ubiquitous in jazz, rhythm and bluez, or chattan or phenken is characterized by vishisht cord progressions, of jisase the twelve-bar bluez cord progression is the sabase common.
The blue notes that, for expressive purposes are sung or nibhaai flattened or dhire jhuki ( naaballig 3rd to pramukh 3rd ) in sambandh to the pich of the pramukh scale, hai bhi an important part of the sound.
The blues genre is based on the blues form but possesses anya visheshtaayen aise as vishisht lyrics, bass lines, and instruments.
Blues can be subdivided into several subgenres ranging from desh to shahari bluez ki yahood adhik or kam lokapriy dauraan alag avadhi of the 20th century.
Best known are the delta, piedmont, jamp, or chicago bluez styles.
sansar yuddh ii chihnit the parivartan isse dhvanik to electric bluez or the pragatisheel kholane of bluez music to a wider darshak, especially white listeners.
In the 1960s and 1970s, a sankar rup pukaara blues-rock evolved.
The term `` the blues '' refers to the `` blue shaitanon '', arth vednaa or udaasi ; an jaldi upyog of the pad in is bhav is mila in george colman 's one-act tamaasha Blue Devils ( 1798 ).
Though the use of the phrase in African-American music may be puraani, it rai maharoom attested to chunki 1912, jab heart wand 's `` dalas bluez `` became the pehla swatvadhikaar bluez composition.
In geet the phrase is praayah prayukt to describe a depressed mood.
A quarter dollar, commonly shortened to quarter, is a sikaa laayak 1⁄4 of a sanyukt rajya dollars or 25 cents.
The quarter rai maharoom utpaadit since 1796.
The choice of 25¢ as a denomination, as opposed to 20¢ which is more common in other bhaag of the sansar, originated saath the abhyaas of dividing spani milled dollar into aath keel taraasha khand ( cf. `` tukade of eight `` ).
At one time `` two bits ``, i.e. two wedges, prayek keel an aathvin, yun a quarter of the spani real, was a common nickname for a quarter.
Day of the Dead ( ) is a mexican avkaash manaaye throughout mexico or around the world in other cultures.
the avkaash focuses on mehphilon of parivaar or mitron to duwa liye or remember friends and family members who have died.
It is particularly celebrated in mexico, jahaan it is a neshnal avkaash, or all banks are closed.
The jashn takes place on navambar 1 or 2, in conection saath the catholic chhuttiyaan of sab santo ' Day and All Souls ' Day.
Traditions connected with the holiday include building private altars honoring the mritak using sugar skulls, marigolds, or the pasandida bhojan or peya of the raji or visiting graves with these as gifts.
They also chhod possessions of the mritak.
Scholars trace the origins of the aadhunik mexican avkaash to swadeshi observances dating waapas sainkadon of saalo or to an azetek parv dedicated to the goddess Mictecacihuatl.
the avkaash rai sprad throughout the sansar : in brazil, dia de finados is a public avkaash that many Brazilians celebrate by visiting cemeteries and churches.
In Spain, there are festivals and parades, and, at the end of the din, logon ekatrit at kabristaan or duwa liye unke murde loved ones.
Similar observances occur elsewhere in Europe, and similarly themed jashn appear in anek asian or africa samskritiyon.

George Washington ( –, 1799 ) was the first President of the United rajya ( 1789–1797 ), the commander-in-chief of the mahadwipiya fouj dauraan the amareeki krantikari yuddh, or ek of the founding fathers of the United States.
He presided over the sammelan ki drafted the samvidhan, jisase replaced the aalekh of canfederation or sthapit the position of President.
Washington was elected President as the sarvasammat chunaav of the 69 nirvaachak in 1788, or he parosa do sharten in office.
He oversaw the sristi of a damdaar, well-financed neshnal sarkari ki kaayam neutrality in the wars raging in Europe, suppressed rebellion, and won acceptance among Americans of all types.
His leadership style established many forms and sanskaar of sarkari ki have maharoom prayukt chunki, aise as using a cabinet system and delivering an inaugural address.
Further, the shantipurna parivartan isse uske presidency to the presidency of jon adams sthapit a parampara that continues into the 21st century.
Washington was hailed as `` pita of uske desh `` bhi dauraan uske aaajeevan.
Washington was born into the provincial gentry of Colonial virginia ; uske dhanwaan planter parivaar swaamitv tambaaku baganon and slaves.
After both his father and older brother died when he thi yang, washington became personally or professionally sanlagn to the shaktishaalee wiliam ferefaques, who promoted his career as a surveyor and soldier.
washington jaldi became a varisht adhikari in the colonial forces during the first stages of the French and Indian War.
Chosen by the duusari mahadwipiya congress in 1775 to be commander-in-chief of the mahadwipiya fouj in the amareeki kranti, Washington managed to force the British out of Boston in 1776, but was defeated and almost captured later that year when he lost New York City.
After crossing the Delaware River in the dead of winter, he parajeet the angrejon in do ladaaiyon, retook nai Jersey and restored momentum to the Patriot cause.
Because of his strategy, Revolutionary forces captured two pramukh angrejon sena at saratoga in 1777 or yorktown in 1781.
Historians laud Washington liye uske chayan or paryvekshan of uske senapatiyon, protsaahan of manobal or kshamta to tham saath the fouj, samanvay saath the rajya rajyapalon and state militia units, relations with Congress and attention to supplies, logistics, and training.
In battle, however, Washington was repeatedly outmaneuvered by angrejon senapatiyon saath larger sena.
After victory had been finalized in 1783, Washington resigned as Commander-in-chief balki than seize shakti, proving uske vipaksh to taanaashaahee or uske patibaddhta to amareeki republicanism.
Dissatisfied with the weaknesses of the Articles of Confederation, in 1787 washington presided over the sanvaidhanik sammelan ki drafted the sanyukt rajya samvidhan.
Elected unanimously as the first adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya in 1789, he attempted to lao pratidwandvi girohon saath to unify the nation.
He supported Alexander Hamilton 's programs to pay off all state and national karz, to implement an prabhavi kar pranali or to banaaen a neshnal bainko ( despite vipaksh isse thomas Jefferson ).
Washington proclaimed the United rajya neutral in the yudhon raging in europea baad 1793.
He avoided war with Great Britain and guaranteed a decade of peace and profitable trade by securing the jay sandhi in 1795, despite teevr vipaksh isse the jeffersonians.
Although never officially joining the federalist party, he samarthit iske kaarykram.
washington 's vidaai pataa thi an influential primer on republican punya or a chetavanee viruddh partisanship, sectionalism, and involvement in foreign wars.
He retired from the presidency in 1797 and returned to his ghar, mount vernon, or uske gharelu jivan jahaan he prabandhit a variety of enterprises.
He freed sab uske slave by his final will.
Washington had a vision of a great and shaktishaalee swadesh ki hota be nirmit on republican linon using federal power.
He sought to use the national government to bachaana swatantraaa, improve avasanrachana, kholen the pashchimi lands, prachaar commers, mila a permanent capital, reduce regional tensions and promote a spirit of American nationalism.
At his death, Washington was eulogized as `` first in war, first in salaam, or pehla in the dil of uske deshavaasiyon '' by henry Lee.
The federalists bana use the pratik of unke party lakin liye anek saalo, the jeffersonians jari to distrust his influence and delayed building the Washington Monument.
As the leader of the first successful revolution against a aupniveshik samrajya in sansar itihaas, washington became an antarrashtriya pratik liye mukti or rashtrawaad, visheshkar in frans and Latin America.
Fiscal Year 2012 U.S. Federal bitaa – nakadi or bajet aadhaar.
Fiscal saal 2012 u.S. sangheey raseeden.
the bajet of the sanyukt rajya sarkari praayah begins as the adhyaksh 's proposal to the U.S. Congress which recommends funding levels for the next fiscal year, beginning October 1.
However, Congress is the body required by vidhi to pass a bajet annually or to submit the bajet passed by dono gharon to the President for signature.
Congressional nirnay hai governed by niyam or vidhaan regarding the federal budget process.
Budget committees set spending limits for the House and Senate committees and for Appropriations subcommittees, which then sweekruti vyaktigat appropriations bills to allocate funding to vibhinn sangheey kaarykram.
If congress fails to pass an salanaa bajet ( as rai maharoom the maamla chunki 2009 ), a shrenee of Appropriations bills must be passed as `` stop gap '' measures.
After Congress approves an appropriations bill, it is sent to the adhyaksh, jo may chihn it into vidhi, or may vito it ( as he hota a bajet jab passed by the Congress ).
A vetoed vidheyak is bheja waapas to congress, jisase can pass it into law with a two-thirds majority in each chamber.
Congress may also combine all or kuch appropriations bills into an omnibus reconciliation bill.
In addition, the president may request and the Congress may pass supplemental appropriations bills or apaat supplemental appropriations bills.
Several sarkari agenciyon provide bajet aankada or analysis.
These shaamil the sarkari javabdehi daftar ( gao ), congressional bajet daftar, the Office of Management and Budget ( OMB ) and the U.S. Treasury Department.
These agencies have reported ki the sangheey sarkari is facing a series of important financing challenges.
In the short-run, tax revenues have asweekrut significantly due to a kathor mandi or kar niti choices, while expenditures have expanded for wars, unemployment insurance and other safety net spending.
In the long-run, expenditures sambandhit to healthcare kaarykram aise as medicare or medicaid hai prakshipt to grow faster than the economy overall as the population matures.
New Guinea ( also, Tok Pisin : Niugini, dach : nieuw gini, or ; historically : papua ) is the sansar 's duusari largest dweep, baad greenland, covering a land area of 786,000 km2.
Located in the southwest Pacific Ocean, it lies geographically to the east of the malay dweepasmooh, saath jisase it is sometimes shaamil as bhaag of a greater Indo-Australian Archipelago.
geologically it is a bhaag of the vahi tectonic thali as Australia.
When world sea levels were low, the two shared shorelines ( which now lie 100 to 140 meter neeche samudr str ), combining saath lands abhi inundated into the tectonic mahadweep of Sahul, also known as Greater Australia.
The two landmasses became separated when the kshetrafal abhi gyaat as the torace jalsandhi flooded baad the samaapt of the last glacial period.
anthropologically, nai gini is mana part of Melanesia.
Politically, the pashchimi half of the dweep comprises do indonesian provinces : Papua and West Papua.
The eastern half forms the menland of the desh of papua nai gini.
The island has a population of about 7.5 million, saath a bahut kam janasankhyikee ghanatv of tabhi 8 inh/km2.
New gini is differentiated isse iske drier, khushaamad, or kam fertile dakshini bantwaaraa, australia, by iske much ucchtar varsha or iske kriyasheel volcanic geology, with its highest point, Puncak Jaya, reaching an elevation of 4,884 m ( 16,023 ft ).
Yet the two land masses share a similar animal fauna, with marsupials, sahit wallabies or possums, or the egg-laying monotreme, the spiny anteater, or echidna.
Other than bats or kuch do darjan swadeshi krintak genera, vahin hai no pre-human swadeshi placental mammals.
Pigs, several atirikt prajati of chuuhe, or the purvaj of the nai gini gayan shwaan yahood introduced with human colonization.
The human presence on the dweep tithiyaan waapas at tanik 40,000 years to the oldest human migrations out of Africa.
Research indicates that the highlands were an jaldi or swatantra bich of krishi, saath pramaan of sinchai going back at least 10,000 years.
Because of the samay gaharaai of iske inhabitation or iske atyadhik fractured landscape, an unusually unchi kramank of bhashaaen hai bolaa on the dweep, saath kuch 1,000 languages ( a figure higher than that of most continents ) having been catalogued out of an estimated world-wide pre-Columbian total of 6,000 human dialects.
Most are classified as papuai bhashaaen, a generally sweekrut bhugolic pad jisase a minority of authors hold to be a genetic one.
A kramank of austronishian bhashaaen hai bolaa on the coast and on offshore islands.
In the 16th century spani explorers khoja the dweep or pukaara it Nueva Guinea.
in haal itihaas pashchimi nai gini thi included in the Dutch East Indies colony.
The Germans annexed the northern coast of the eastern half of the island as German New gini in unke pre–world yuddh i praytn to sthapit themselves as a aupniveshik shakti, whilst the south eastern portion was reluctantly claimed by Britain.
Following the Treaty of Versailles, the German portion was awarded to Australia ( which was already shaasi the angrejon arji, namit the territory of papua ) as a League of Nations mandate.
The eastern half of the dweep thi granted swatantraaa isse australia as Papua New Guinea in 1975.
the pashchimi half gained swatantraaa isse the dach in 1961, but became part of Indonesia soon afterwards in controversial circumstances.

Bevo was a non-alcoholic malt peya, or nikat bear, brewed in the sanyukt rajya by the Anheuser-Busch company beginning in the early 20th century.
Bevo enjoyed its greatest success during the time of prohibition, when beer, wine or asut liquors, yahood bana illegal liye teraa saalo.
The Anheuser-Busch company started brewing bevo jab alcoholic peya yahood nishiddh in 1916 by the sanyukt rajya hathiyaarband forces.
utpaadan rose greatly saath neshnal nishedh in 1919, or bevo thi by dur the sabase lokapriy of the many `` cereal beverages '' or `` near beers '' of the time.
At the peak of its lokapriyata in the jaldi 1920s, adhik than paanch lakh maamle of Bevo were sold annually.
Renard with a mug of bevo, chitrit in terra cotta on the aantarik deevaaren of the bevo bhawan, St. Louis
Labels on the bottles billed it as `` bevo the peya ''.
The name `` Bevo '' was coined from the word `` peya '' or the slavi bhashaa shabd liye bear `` pivo '', or thi sunaaya `` Bee-vo ''.
Some Bevo advertising featured the character `` renard the fox `` ( aadhaarit on the samarthak of a madhyakaalin french folk-tale ), or promotional mag saath this character were manufactured.
In 1930 Anheuser-Busch built a series of boat-bodied cars in its St. Louis shops pukaara the `` bevo naukaaye '' jisase yahood prayukt liye pramotion.
Seven are believed to have been built on pierce-arrow 8-cylinder chassis jabaki ek surviving udhaaharan thi aadhaarit upon 1930 Cadillac 353 V8.

appetizing - healthful - paushtik - Refreshing.

BEVO never karata. ''
Bevo became part of the popular culture of the samay, or is ullekith in vibhinn lokapriy geeton or Vaudeville skits of the era.
This led to dwitiyak kathboli upyog of the shabd ; liye udhaaharan, in amareeki sainya kathboli a yang or anubhavheen officer was called a `` Bevo ''.
The University of Texas named its mascot `` bevo '', a naam jisase rai stuck to is din.
Irving Berlin included a paean to the drink, `` tum ca n't raho up on bevo '', in uske 1917 fouj revue, yip yip Yaphank.
In the late 1920s smuggled bootleg bear or liquor as khub as `` homebrew ``, kaaten into bevo 's marketshare.
With bikri flattening to 100,000 maamle by 1929, Anheuser-Busch stopped production.

Milk is a white liquid utpaadit by the mammary grathiyon of mammals.
It is the praathmik sorce of poshan for young mammals before they are able to digest other types of food.
Early- lactation milk contains colostrum, which carries the maan 's antibodies to the baby or can reduce the risk of anek rogon in the baby.
It bhi contains anek anya nutrients.
As an agricultural product, milk is nikaali isse stanadhariyon or prayukt as khaanaa liye humans.
Worldwide, dugdh kheto utpaadit parichay 730 lakh ton of milk in 2011.
India is the world 's largest nirmaataa or upabhokta of milk, yet neither niryaat nor imports milk.
New jiland, the europea sangh 's 27 sadsy rajya, australia, or the sanyukt States are the world 's largest exporters of milk and milk products.
China or rus hai the sansar 's largest importers of milk and milk products.
Throughout the sansar, vahin hai adhik than 6 arab consumers of milk and milk products.
over 750 lakh logon sajiv bheetar dairy farming households.
Milk is a kunjee yogadanakarta to improving poshan or khaanaa suraksha particularly in developing countries.
Improvements in livestock and dairy praudyogiki prastaav significant vaada in reducing garibi or kuposhan in the world.
Motorcycle speedway, praayah referred to as speedway, is a motorcycle khel involving chaar or sometimes up to six riders competing over four anti-clockwise laps of an oval circuit.
Speedway motorcycle upyog tabhi ek gear or have no brakes or racing takes place on a flat oval track usually consisting of dirt or loosely packed shale.
Competitors use this surface to slide their mashine bagalon, powersliding or broadsiding into the bends.
On the straight bhaag of the track the motorcycle reach speeds of up.
The exact origins of the sport are unknown but there is evidence of a type of speedway racing being practised in the USA pehle the pehla sansar yuddh or in australia in the let 1910s or jaldi 1920s.
There are now both domestic and antarrashtriya pratiyogitaaon in a kramank of deshon sahit the speedway sansar cap whilst the ucchtam overall scoring individual in the Speedway Grand Prix events is pronounced the world champion.
speedway is lokapriy in central or uttari europea or to a lesser extent in Australia and North America.
A variant of track racing, speedway is administered internationally by the fédération internationale de Motocyclisme ( FIM ).
Domestic speedway kaarykram hai regulated by fim sambhddha national motor sport federations.
Vitamin D is a group of fat-soluble secosteroids jimmedaar liye intestinal absorption of calcium and phosphate.
In humans, the most important related yogicon of vitamin d hai vitamin d2 or vitamin d3.
Cholecalciferol ( vitamin D3 ) and ergocalciferol ( vitamin d2 ) hai adwitiya as ve constitute kayaa we jaan as vitamin d or can be ingested from the diet and/or supplements.
The body can also synthesize vitamin d ( isse cholestrol ) jab surya expozar is paryaapt ( hence its nickname, the `` sunshine vitamin '' ).
Although vitamin d is commonly pukaara a vitamin, it is nahin darasal an anivaary dietary vitamin in the sakht bhav, as it can be synthesized in adequate amounts by most mammals exposed to sunlight.
( Cats and dogs can not synthesize vitamin d efficiently or jarur praapt it in their diet. )
An organic chemical compound ( or related set of compounds ) is only scientifically pukaara a vitamin jab it can nahin be synthesized in sufficient quantities by an sajiv, or jarur be praapt isse unke diet.
However, as with other compounds commonly called vitamins, vitamin d thi khoja in an praytn to dhundhen the dietary padaarth ki thi lacking in a beemaari, namely, rickets, the balykaal rup of osteomalacia.
Additionally, like other compounds called vitamins, in the viksit sansar vitamin d is added to stepal bhojan, aise as milk, to avoid beemaari due to kamiyaan.
Measures of serum levels reflect endogenous sanshleshan isse expozar to dhoop as khub as seven isse the aahaar, or it is believed ki sanshleshan may contribute generally to the maintenance of adequate serum concentrations.
The evidence indicates that the synthesis of vitamin D isse surya expozar works in a pratikriya loop ki roktaa toxicity lakin, kuki of anischitata parichay the karkat risk isse dhoop, no suzav hai jari by the santhaan of ayurvigyaan, uese, liye the raashi of surya exposure required to meet vitamin D requirements.
Accordingly, the Dietary Reference intakes liye vitamin d assume ki no sanshleshan occurs or ki sab of a vyakti 's vitamin d is isse unke aahaar, haalanki ki hoga rarely occur in practice.
In the jigar vitamin d is parivartit to calcidiol, jisase is bhi gyaat as calcifediol ( in ), 25-hydroxycholecalciferol, or 25-hydroxyvitamin D—abbreviated 25 ( OH ) D ; and which is the specific vitamin D metabolite that is measured in serum to determine a person 's vitamin D status.
Part of the calcidiol is parivartit by the gurde to calcitriol, the biologically kriyasheel rup of vitamin D. calcitriol circulates as a hormone in the blood, regulating the concentration of calcium and phosphate in the bloodstream and promoting the healthy growth and remodeling of bone.
Calcidiol is also converted to calcitriol outside of the kidneys for other purposes, such as the aprasar, differentiation or apoptosis of koshikaayen ; calcitriol bhi affects neuromuscular function and inflammation.
Beyond its use to prevent osteomalacia or rickets, the pramaan liye anya swasthya prabhaav of vitamin d supplementation in the general population is inconsistent.
The best pramaan of laabh is liye asthi swasthya or a ghati in mortality in elderly women.

propolis as chhatta sealing
Propolis is a resinous mishran ki madhu madhumakhiyon collect isse ped kaliyon, sap bahati, or anya botanical sources.
it is prayukt as a sealant liye unwanted open spaces in the hive.
Propolis is prayukt liye choti gap ( lagbhag or kam ), while larger spaces are usually filled with beeswax.
Its rang varies depending on iske vanaspati sorce, the most common being dark brown.
propolis is stick at or upar room taapmaana,.
At lower temperatures, it becomes mushkil or bahut bhangur.
Steven Tyler ( born Steven Victor Tallarico ; March 26, 1948 ) is an American singer, songwriter, or multi-instrumentalist, behtareen gyaat as the frontman or sise singer of the boston -aadharand chattan band arosmith, in jisase he bhi plays the hormonica, and occasional piano and percussion.

The Jews ( ISO 259-3 Israeli pronunciation ), also known as the Jewish people, are a nation or an ethnoreligious samooh, originating in the israelites or hebrews of the pracheen nikat East.
The Jewish ethnicity, nationality, and religion are strongly interrelated, as judaism is the paramparaagat aasthaa of the Jewish nation.
Converts to judaism, jinaki aukaat as yahudiyon bheetar the yahudee ethnos is baraabar to those born into it, have maharoom absorbed into the Jewish people throughout the millennia.
In yahudee parampara, yahudee ancestry is traced to the biblical patriarchs abraham, Isaac and Jacob in the second millennium BCE.
the aadhunik rajya of israel thi sthapit as a Jewish nation-state, and defines itself as such in its Basic Laws.
Its Law of Return grants the sahi of naagarikta to koi jew jo nivedan it.
Israel is the only country where Jews hai a bahumat of the population.
Jews also enjoyed political swaittata twice pehle in pracheen itihaas.
The first of these periods lasted isse 1350 to 586 bce, or encompassed the avadhi of the nyaayadhishon, the sanyukt samrajya, or the vibhajit samrajya of the kingdoms of israel or yahuda, samaapti saath the vinaash of the First Temple.
The second was the period of the hasmonean kingdom spanning isse 140 to 37 BCE.
Since the vinaash of the pehla temple, most Jews have lived in diaspora.
A minority in every country in which they live ( except israel ), ve have aksar anbhavi persecution throughout itihaas, resulting in a janasankhyikee ki rai fluctuated both in numbers and distribution over the centuries.
The world Jewish janasankhyikee pahunche a shikhar of 15 lakh prior to the duusari sansar yuddh, lakin chah lakh Jews were killed in the Holocaust.
Since then the population has risen again or, thi anumaanit at 13.4 lakh by the uttar amareeki yahudee aankada bainko, or kam than 0.2 % of the kul sansar janasankhyikee ( roughly one in every 514 people ).
according to is rapat, parichay 42.5 % of sab yahudiyon reside in israel ( 5.7 lakh ), or 39.3 % in the sanyukt rajya ( 5.3 million ), with most of the remainder living in Europe ( 1.5 million ) and Canada ( 0.4 million ).
These numbers include all those who consider themselves yahudiyon, whether or nahin ve hai sambhddha saath a yahudee sanghathan.
The total sansar yahudee janasankhyikee, however, is difficult to measure.
In addition to issues with census methodology, there are halakhic disputes regarding who is a jew or dharmanirpeksh, rajnatik, or ancestral pahchaan factors that may affect the figure considerably.
