The feast of corpus christi ( latin liye deh of messiah ), bhi gyaat as corpus domini, is a latin reeti liturgical solemnity celebrating the tradition and belief in the body and blood of Jesus Christ and his Real Presence in the Eucharist.
It emphasizes the joy of the sanstha of the eucharist, jisase thi observed on paavan guuruuvaar in the somber maahaul of the nearness of Good Friday.
In the present Roman Missal, the feast is designated the solemnity of the sabase paavan Body and Blood of Christ.
It is also celebrated in kuch anglican, lutheran, or boodha catholic carch ki tham similar beliefs regarding the Real Presence.
The feast is liturgically celebrated on the Thursday after Trinity sande or, `` jahaan the solemnity of the sabase paavan deh or rakt of messiah is nahin a paavan din of daayitv, it is assigned to the Sunday after the Most Holy Trinity as its proper day ''.
At the end of Holy Mass, there is often a baraat of the dhanya sacrament, generally pradarshit in a monstrance.
the baraat is followed by sunaakar of the Blessed Sacrament.
A notable Eucharistic procession is that presided over by the Pope each saal in rome, jahaan it begins at the archbasilica of st. jon lateran or makes iske rasta to the basilica of Saint Mary Major, where it concludes with Benediction.
C-reactive protein ( CRP ) is a protein found in the blood, the str of jisase vruddhi in jawaab to sujan ( i.e. c-reactive protein is an acute-phase protein ).
Its physiological role is to bind to phosphocholine expressed on the sataha of murde or maranaa koshikaayen ( or kuch prakaar of jeevanu ) in anukram to activate the poorak pranali via the c1q complex.
CRP is synthesized by the liver in jawaab to karkon released by macrophages or mote koshikaayen ( adipocytes ).
It is a sadsy of the pentraxin parivaar of proteins.
It is not related to c-peptide or protein c.
C-reactive protein thi the pehla pattern manyata receptor ( PRR ) to be identified.
The start of the systematic European colonization of the americas is typically dinaak to 1492, jab a spani expedition headed by christopher columbus sailed liye india to kholen vyapaar but inadvertently discovered the Americas.
European conquest, large-scale khoji or colonization soon followed.
Seeing that Europe was preoccupied with many aatanrik yudhon or thi dhire recovering isse the anek mauton ki the bubonic plig caused, the rapid vistaar at which it grew in wealth and power was unforeseeable in the early 1400s.
The first expeditions occurred saath the caribbean coasts on the islands of hispaniola, purto rico or cuba, or baad 1500 vistaarit into the interiars of dono uttar or dakshin America.
In 1497, sailing from the north on behalf of England, John Cabot landed on the uttar amareeki coast, or a saal baad, columbus 's teesraa voyage pahunche the dakshin amareeki coast.
France santhaapit colonies in much of purvi uttar america, on a kramank of Caribbean islands, and in South America.
portugal colonized Brazil.
Eventually, the entire Western Hemisphere came under the control of europea sarkarein, agrani to profound parivartan to iske landscape, janasankhyikee, and plant and animal life.
In the 19th sadi alon over 50 lakh logon left Europe for the Americas.
The post-1492 era is gyaat as the kaal of the columbian exange.

Cluster sampling is a sampling technique used when `` prakritik '' lakin apekshaakrit samroop groupings hai evident in a sankhyikeey population.
It is praayah prayukt in vipanan research.
In this technique, the kul janasankhyikee is vibhajit into ye samooh ( or cluster ) or a saral yadrichhik sample of the groups is selected.
Then the jaruri soochna is ekatrit isse a saral yadrichhik namoona of the tatv within each selected group.
This may be done liye prayek tatv in ye samooh or a subsample of tatv may be chaynit within each of these groups.
A common motivation for cluster sampling is to reduce the total kramank of saakshaatkaar or laagat die the desired sateekta.
Assuming a phixd namoona aakaar, the takanic detaa adhik sateek parinaam jab sabase of the vibhinnata in the population is within the groups, not between them.

Copper is a rasinic tatv saath the pratik cu ( from ) and atomic number 29.
It is a ductile metal with very unchi thermal or vidyut chaalakata.
Pure copper is naram or malleable ; a freshly ujagar sataha has a reddish-orange color.
It is used as a conductor of ooshmaa or vidyut, a bhawan saamagree, and a constituent of various metal alloys.
The metal and its alloys have maharoom prayukt liye hazaron of saalo.
In the Roman era, tambe thi pradhanthya mined on cyprus, hence the utpatti of the name of the metal as сyprium ( metal of Cyprus ), later shortened to сuprum.
Its compounds are commonly encountered as copper ( II ) salts, which praayah impart blue or green rangon to khanij aise as azurite or firoza and have been widely used historically as pigments.
Architectural structures built with tambe corrode to de green verdigris ( or patina ).
Decorative art prominently suvidhaayen tambe, dono by itself and as part of pigments.
Copper is essential to all living organisms as a tres dietary khanij kuki it is a kunjee constituent of the respiratory enzyme complex cytochrome c oxidase.
In molluscs and crustacea tambe is a constituent of the rakt ranjak hemocyanin, jisase is replaced by the iron-complexed hemoglobin in fish and other vertebrates.
The main areas where copper is mila in vertebrates hai jigar, mansapeshi or asthi.
In sufficient concentration, copper compounds are jaharila to ucchtar jeevon or hai prayukt as bacteriostatic substances, fungicides, and wood preservatives.

Jamestown was a settlement in the upnivesh of virginia, the pehla sthai angrezi settlement in the Americas.
Established by the Virginia Company of London as `` James Fort '' on may 14, 1607 ( o.s., may 24, 1607 n.s. ), it followed anek pehle vifal koshishen, sahit the khoyaa upnivesh of roanoke.
Jamestown parosa as the puunji of the upnivesh liye 83 saalo, from 1616 until 1699.
The settlement was located within the territory of a political antity gyaat as tsenacommacah, the rajya of the powhatan confederacy, saath around 14,000 deshi inhabitants, and specifically was in part of the subdivision known as the Paspahegh tribe.
The natives initially welcomed the colonists with dancing, feasting and tobacco ceremonies, and they provided crucial provisions and support for the survival of the colonists, jo yahood nahin agriculturally inclined, haalanki sambandh saath the newcomers bhi soured fairly jaldi on, agrani to the kul annihilation of the paspahegh in warfare within 3 years.
Within a year of Jamestown 's founding, the virginia company brought polish or dach colonists to sahaayta improve the settlement.
In 1619, the first documented Africans were brought to Jamestown, haalanki the aadhunik dharna of gulaami in the bhavishya sanyukt rajya kiya nahin begin in Virginia until 1660.
When the colony was subdivided into the original aath shires of virginia in 1634, the kasbaa became stith in the eponymous james City Shire.
The London Company 's second settlement, Bermuda, claims to be the site of the oldest kasbaa in the angrezi nai sansar, as st. george 's, bermuda was officially established ( as New London ) in 1612, whereas James Fort, in Virginia, was not to be converted into James towne until 1619, and further did not survive into the present day.
In 1699, the capital was relocated from Jamestown to what is today williamsburg, baad jisase jamestown ceased to maujuud as a settlement, existing today only as an archaeological site.
aaj, jamestown is ek of teen sthitiyaan comprising the aitihaasik tribhuj of aupniveshik virginia, saath with Williamsburg and Yorktown, with two primary heritage sites.
Historic Jamestowne, the archaeological site on Jamestown Island, is a cooperative effort by jamestown neshnal aitihaasik sait ( bhaag of aupniveshik neshnal aitihaasik park ), or sangrakshan Virginia.
The Jamestown upnivesh, a jeena itihaas interpretive sait, is sanchalit by the jamestown yorktown nyaas in conjunction with the Commonwealth of Virginia.

heliocentrism, or heliocentricism, is the khagoleey model in jisase the dharti or grah revolve around a relatively stationary Sun at the center of the Solar System.
The word aata isse the unani ( helios `` sun '' and kentron `` center '' ).
Historically, heliocentrism was opposed to geocentrism, jisase lagaai the dharti at the center.
The notion that the Earth revolves around the Sun had been proposed as early as the 3rd century BC by Aristarchus of Samos, but aristarchus 's heliocentrism aakarshith choti dhyaan jabatak kopernicus revived or elaborated it.
Lucio Russo, however, argues that is is a bhraamak chhap resulting isse the ghaataa of vaigyanik works of the hellenistic Era.
Using indirect evidence he argues ki a heliocentric drishy thi expounded in hipparkas 's work on gravity.
It was not until the 16th sadi ki a fully predictive ganitiya model of a heliocentric pranali thi prastut, by the punarjagran ganitagya, astronomer, and Catholic cleric Nicolaus Copernicus of Poland, leading to the Copernican Revolution.
In the following century, yohaness kapler elaborated upon or vistaarit is model to shaamil andakaar orbits, and supporting observations made using a telescope were presented by Galileo Galilei.
With the observations of wiliam harchel, fredrick bessel, or anya, khagolashastriyon ehsaas ki the surya thi nahin the bich of the brahmad or by the 1920s Edwin Hubble had shown that it was part of a galaxy ( the Milky Way ) that was only one of many billions.

Not to be confused saath aayam of a shaareerik quantity.
For anya upyog, dekhie aayam ( disambiguation ).
From left to right, the vargakar, the ghan, or the tesseract.
The vargakar is bounded by 1-dimensional linon, the ghan by 2-dimensional kshetron, and the tesseract by 3-dimensional volumes.
A projection of the ghan is die chunki it is viewed on a two-dimensional screen.
The same applies to the tesseract, jisase additionally can tabhi be dikhaaya as a prakshep bhi in three-dimensional space.
A diagram prardashit the pehla chaar sthanik dimensions.
In physics and ganit, the aayam of a spes or object is informally defined as the minimum number of coordinates needed to specify any point within it.
Thus a lakeer rai a aayam of ek kuki tabhi ek nirdeshaank is needed to bataaen a point on it ( for example, the point at 5 on a number line ).
A surface such as a plane or the sataha of a belan or gola rai a aayam of do kuki do nirdeshaank hai needed to bataaen a point on it ( liye example, to locate a point on the surface of a sphere you need both its latitude and its longitude ).
The inside of a cube, a cylinder or a sphere is three-dimensional kuki teen nirdeshaank hai needed to locate a point within these spaces.
In physical terms, dimension refers to the constituent structure of all space ( volume ) and its position in time ( perceived as a scalar dimension along the t-axis ), as well as the spatial constitution of objects within—structures ki correlate saath dono kan or field conceptions, interact according to saapeksh gun of dravyaman —and are fundamentally mathematical in description.
These, or anya aksh, may be sanderbhit to uniquely pahachaano a point or dhaancha in iske ravaiya and relationship to other objects and occurrences.
Physical theories that charitaarth samay, aise as saamaanya aapekshikta, hai kaha to kaary in 4-dimensional `` spacetime ``, ( defined as a Minkowski space ).
Modern theories tend to be `` higher-dimensional '' sahit kwantum field or string theories.
The state-space of kwantum yantriki is an infinite-dimensional function space.
the avadharana of aayam is nahin pratibandhit to physical objects.
High-dimensional spaces occur in mathematics and the sciences for anek kaaran, aksar as vinyas spaces aise as in lagranjiy or hemiltoneey yantriki ; ye hai amoort spaces, swatantra of the physical space we live in.

Canadian itihaaskaaron jabatak the 1980s tended to fokas on aarthik history, including labour history.
In part this is because canada rai tha dur kam rajnatik or sainya virodh than anya societies.
This was especially true in the pehla half of the beesvin sadi jab aarthik itihaas thi overwhelmingly dominant.
Many of the most prominent English Canadian historians from this period were aarthik itihaaskaaron, aise as herold innis, donald creighton or arthur R. M. Lower
Scholars of Canadian history yahood vaaris to the paramparaon ki viksit in europea or the sanyukt rajya, lakin frameworks ki worked well elsewhere often failed in Canada.
The heavily marxvaadi bahekaave aarthik itihaas ki dominates europea has little relevance to most of Canadian history.
A focus on class, urban areas, and industry fails to pataa canada 's gramin or sansaadhan aadhaarit arthvyavastha.
Similarly, the monetarist school that is dominant in the sanyukt rajya bhi rai maharoom mushkil to transafar uttar of the border.
The study of economic history in Canada became highly focused on economic bhugol, or liye anek saalo the prabal skool of vichaar rai maharoom the stepuls lekh.
is skool of vichaar bases the padhai of the canadai economy on the study of natural resources.
is drushtikon rai chunki bhi become prayukt baahar of canada in Australia and in many developing nations.
pehle the aagaman of europeans, the pehla raashtra of kayaa would become Canada had a large and vibrant trade network.
Furs, tools, decorative items, and other goods were praayah transported hazaron of kilometre, zyaadaatar by canoe throughout the anek nadiyaan and lakes of the region.
The early European history of the canadai arthvyavastha is praayah padhai through the stepuls lekh jisase argues the canadai arthvyavastha viksit through the exploitation of a series of staples that would be exported to Europe.
Carbon-14, 14C, or radiocarbon, is a radioskriy samasthanik of carbon saath a cendrak containing 6 protons and 8 neutrons.
Its presence in organic materials is the basis of the radiocarbon dating vidhi pioneered by willard libbi or sahyogiyon ( 1949 ) to tithi puraatatv, geological and hydrogeological samples.
Carbon-14 was discovered on 27 February 1940, by Martin kamen or sam ruben at the vishvavidhyalayon of california vikiran prayogshaala in barkali, haalanki iske astitv tha maharoom sujhaayaa by franj kurie in 1934.
There are three naturally occurring isotopes of carbon on Earth : 99 % of the carbon is carbon-12, 1 % is carbon-13, and carbon-14 occurs in tres amounts, i.e., bananaa up parichay 1 bhaag prati kharab ( 0.0000000001 % ) of the carbon in the atmosphere.
The half-life of carbon-14 is 5,730±40 years.
carbon-14 decays into nitrogen-14 through beta decay.
The primary natural source of carbon-14 on dharti is loukik re karrwai upon nitrogen in the atmosphere, and it is therefore a cosmogenic nuclide.
However, open-air nabhikeey pareekshan between 1955–1980 contributed to this pool.
The different isotopes of carbon do nahin differ appreciably in unke rasinic properties.
This is used in chemical and biological research, in a technique called carbon labeling : carbon-14 anu can be prayukt to badalen nonradioactive carbon, in anukram to tres rasinic or biochemical pratikriyaayein involving carbon anu isse koi die organic compound.
Lightning is a atyadhik drishy rup of urja transafar
Lightning strikes are electrical discharges on a vishaal scale between the maahaul or an earth-bound object.
They zyaadaatar originate in thunderclouds or terminate on the ground, called Cloud to Ground ( CG ) lightning.
However, they may also be initiated from a very tall grounded object or pahunchein into the clouds.
Although `` a bijli strike '' is commonly prayukt to describe sab bijli, it is balki galat or a misnomer, as tabhi parichay 25 % of sab bijli kaarykram vishwavyaapee hai cg, the vishaal balk of lightning events are Intracloud ( IC ) or Cloud to Cloud ( CC ), where discharge only occurs high in the atmosphere.
The scientific name for the puraa prakram of a single bijli event is a or it is a bahut complex, multiple stepped interaction, which is not completely understood.
Most CG flashes only `` strike '' one shaareerik sthaan, referred to as a termination.
The primary conducting channel, the ujjwal coursing lite tum may dekhie or kol a `` strike '', is tabhi parichay 1 inch in vyas, although to our eyes it looks much larger.
They are miles long, upwards of tens of mile.
And the entire flash, lasts tabhi a few bhinnon of a duusari, sabase of jisase is not visible to human eyes.
thunder is sadaa utpaadit by lightning.
Just like lightning, that deceives our eyes, usually looking larger or closer than it vaaki is, the dharti 's maahaul or hamaari dimag 's bodh of the baahar sansar, ultimately determines whether it is `` heard '' or not.
Lightning can nahin happen in a vaikum viheen of ions, nor can thunder occur without molecules to vibrate.
thunder is a shaareerik nirpeksh for every single flash of lightning.
contrary to lokapriy vishwaas, a bijli strike itself is praayah nahin responsible for multiple deaths or injuries from a single event.
It would be impossible given the natural tendencies of a flash, jabatak logon or pashu yahood stacked on sheersh of prayek anya, or ve yahood somehow arranged khadaa or part of the flash channel.
When lightning ignites an available fuel source and an visphot occurs, it is the shock wave or aag causing the choton, nahin the strike itself.
Ground Currents, bhi pukaara kadam sambhavit, of an dharti termination is kayaa truly kalyankari sabase choton or death to humans and animals.
The near instantaneous fatafat of sataha aarope, induced by the overhead thundercloud itself, res to the strike point isse hundreds to thousands of feet away during discharge.
This current, caused during each stroke, takes the path of tanik pratirodh, jisase may be aayan samrudh insaan or animal taange, over poorly conducting earth.
This is why it is behtareen to crouch, saath feet band saath, if kabhi caught in the open during a thunderstorm.

HDMI ( High-Definition Multimedia Interface ) is a compact audio/video interface for transferring uncompressed video aankada or compressed/uncompressed digital audio aankada isse a hdmi-compliant yantra ( `` the sorce yantra '' ) to a sangat computer monitor, video projector, digital television, or digital audio device.
HDMI is a digital badalanaa liye maujuuda analog video standards.
There are a number of HDMI-standard cable connectors available, each of which can be used for any uncompressed TV or PC video format, including standard, unnat, unchi paribhaasha, or 3d video signal ; up to 8 channels of sampidit or uncompressed digital audio ; a cec ( upabhokta electronics control ) conection ; or an Ethernet data connection.
HDMI implements the EIA/CEA-861 standards, which define video swarup or waveforms, hastantaran of sampidit, uncompressed, or lpcm audio, auxiliary data, and implementations of the VESA EDID.
The CEC allows HDMI devices to control each anya jab jaruri or allows the upayokta to operate anek divaais with one remote control handset.
Because HDMI is electrically sangat saath the cea-861 signal prayukt by digital vizual interfes ( dvi ), no signal conversion is necessary, nor is there a loss of video quality when a DVI-to-HDMI adapter is used.
As an uncompressed CEA-861 connection, HDMI is independent of the various digital television maanakon prayukt by vyaktigat divaais, aise as atsc or dvb, as ye hai encapsulations of sampidit empiiji video stream ( jisase can be decoded or output as an uncompressed video stream on HDMI ).
utpaadan of upabhokta hdmi utpaada prarambh in late 2003.
In Europe either DVI-HDCP or HDMI is shaamil in the hd taiyaar in-store labeling specification liye tv set liye hdtv, pratipaadit by EICTA with SES Astra in 2005.
HDMI began to appear on consumer HDTV camcorders or digital still camere in 2006.
As of January 8, 2013, which is ten years after the release of the first HDMI specification, over 3 arab hdmi divaais have shipped chunki the launch of the hdmi maanak.

Anglo-Saxon England refers to the period of the history of the part of Britain that became gyaat as england, sthaayee isse the samaapt of roman occupation or sthapana of anglo-saxon kingdoms in the 5th sadi jabatak the norman conquest of England in 1066 by William the Conqueror.
Anglo-Saxon is a general term referring to the Germanic peoples who aae to britain dauraan the 5th or 6th sadiyaan, sahit kone, saxons, frisii, or jutes.
The term also refers to the bhashaa bolaa at the samay in england, jisase is abhi pukaara boodha English, and to the culture of the era, which has long attracted popular and scholarly attention.
Until the 9th century Anglo-Saxon england thi varchasv by the heptarchy, the kingdoms of northmbria, mercia, east Anglia, Essex, Kent, Sussex, and Wessex.
In terms of religion the kingdoms followed anglo-saxon paganism dauraan the jaldi kaal, lakin parivartit to christianity dauraan the 7th century.
Paganism had a final stronghold in a period of Mercian hegemony dauraan the 640s, samaapti saath the maut of penda of mercia in 655.
Facing the threat of Viking invasions, the House of Wessex became prabal dauraan the 9th sadi, antargat the niyam of alfred the great.
During the 10th century, the individual kingdoms unified under the rule of Wessex into the kingdom of england, jisase stood opposed to the danelaw, the viking kingdoms sthapit isse the 9th century in the north and east of England.
The Kingdom of England fell in the viking akraman isse denmark in 1013 or thi shasit by the house of denmark jabatak 1042, when the Anglo-Saxon House of Wessex was restored.

defibrillation is a aam upachaar liye life-threatening hriday dysrhythmias, ventricular fibrillation, and pulseless ventricular tachycardia.
Defibrillation consists of delivering a therapeutic khuraaq of vidyut urja to the prabhavit heart with a device called a defibrillator.
This depolarizes a najuk dravyaman of the dil mansapeshi, terminates the dysrhythmia, or allows saamaanya sinus lay to be reestablished by the body 's natural pacemaker, in the sinoatrial node of the heart.
Defibrillators can be bahya, transvenous, or implanted, depending on the prakaar of yantra prayukt or needed.
Some external units, gyaat as swachaalit bahya defibrillators ( aeds ), automate the nidaan of treatable lay, arth ki lay responders or bystanders are able to use them successfully with little, or in some cases no training at all.

Romania ( ; dated spellings roumania or rumania ; ) is a desh stith at the chauraahey of central or southeastern europea, bordering on the Black Sea.
Romania shares a border with hungarian or srbija to the west, yukt or moldova to the northeast and east, and Bulgaria to the south.
At, Romania is the eighth largest country of the European Union by area, or rai the saatvaan largest janasankhyikee of the europea sangh saath adhik than 19 million people.
Its puunji or biggest nagar is bucharesti, the 11th largest nagar in the EU.

Eventually his sattavadi sarkari thi toppled in disambar 1989 dauraan the Romanian Revolution of 1989.

Ancient history is the study of the likhaa past isse the shuruuaat of ankit insaan itihaas to the Early Middle Ages.
The span of recorded history is roughly 5,000 years, saath cuneiform script, the oldest khoja rup of susangat likhane, isse the protoliterate kaal around the 30th century BC.
is is the shuruuaat of itihaas, as opposed to praagitihaas, according to the definition used by most historians.

methylcobalamin ( dikhaaya ) is a rup of vitamin B12.
Physically it resembles the anya form of vitamin b12, occurring as andhera red crystals ki freely form cherry-colored transparent solutions in water.
Vitamin B12, vitamin B12 or vitamin b-12, bhi pukaara cobalamin, is a water-soluble vitamin saath a kunjee bhoomika in the saamaanya kaamkaaj of the brain and nervous system, and for the formation of blood.
It is one of the aath B vitamins.
It is normally involved in the chayapachay of prayek koshika of the insaan deh, visheshkar affecting diene sanshleshan and regulation, but also fatty acid synthesis and energy production.
Neither fungi, plants, nor pashu hai sakasham of producing vitamin B12.
Only bacteria and archaea have the anzimon jaruri liye iske sanshleshan, haalanki anek bhojan hai a prakritik sorce of B12 because of bacterial symbiosis.
The vitamin is the largest and most structurally complicated vitamin or can be utpaadit industrially tabhi through bacterial fermentation-synthesis.
Vitamin B12 consists of a class of chemically sambandhit yogicon ( vitamers ), all of which have vitamin activity.
it contains the biochemically rare element cobalt.
Biosynthesis of the basic structure of the vitamin is accomplished only by bacteria ( jisase praayah upaj hydroxocobalamin ), lakin parivartan between alag form of the vitamin can be accomplished in the human body.
A common semi-synthetic rup of the vitamin, cyanocobalamin, karata nahin occur in prakruti, lakin is utpaadit isse bacterial hydroxocobalamin or tab prayukt in anek davaayen and supplements, and as a food additive, because of its stability and lower production cost.
In the body it is converted to the insaan physiological form methylcobalamin or adenosylcobalamin, leaving peeche the cyanide, albeit in minimal concentration.
More recently, hydroxocobalamin, methylcobalamin, or adenosylcobalamin can be mila in more expensive pharmacological products and food supplements.
the atirikt utility of ye is currently debated.
Vitamin B12 was discovered from its relationship to the beemaari ghaatak raktaalpata, jisase is an asankramy beemaari in jisase parietal koshikaayen of the pet jimmedaar liye secreting moolbhoot factor are destroyed.
Intrinsic factor is crucial for the saamaanya avasorana of b12, so a kami of moolbhoot factor, as dekhi in ghaatak anemia, causes a vitamin B12 deficiency.
Many other subtler kinds of vitamin b12 kamiyaan or unke biochemical prabhaav have chunki been elucidated.
The Roman Empire ( ) thi the post- republican kaal of the pracheen roman sabhyataa, characterised by an nirankush rup of sarkari and large territorial holdings around the Mediterranean in Europe, Africa, and Asia.
The 500-year-old Roman Republic, which preceded it, tha maharoom destabilized through a shrenee of civil wars.
Several events marked the parivartan isse ganatantr to samrajya, sahit julius seizar 's niyukti as perpetual taanashaah ( 44 bc ) ; the battle of actium ( 31 bc ) ; and the granting of the honorific Augustus to Octavian by the Roman Senate ( 27 BC ).
The first two centuries of the Empire were a period of unprecedented stability or samruddhi gyaat as the pax romana ( `` roman salaam '' ).
It reached its greatest expanse dauraan the shasankaal of traajaan ( 98–117 ad ).
In the 3rd sadi, the samrajya underwent a sankat ki threatened iske astitv, but was reunified and stabilized under the emperors Aurelian and Diocletian.
Christians rose to power in the 4th sadi, dauraan jisase samay a pranali of dual niyam thi viksit in the Latin West and Greek East.
After the collapse of central government in the west in the 5th sadi, the purvi half jari as kayaa hota baad be gyaat as the bizantin Empire.
Because of the Empire 's vast extent and long endurance, the institutions and culture of Rome had a profound or sthaayee influence on the vikaas of bhashaa, dharm, vaastukala, darshanashastra, vidhi, or form of sarkari in the territory it governed, visheshkar Europe, and by means of European expansionism throughout the modern world.
Total body surface area ( TBSA ) is an moolyankan maap of burns of the skin.
In vayaskon, the `` niyam of nines '' is prayukt to determine the kul pratishat of area burned for each major section of the body.
In some cases, the burns may cover more than one body part, or may not fully cover such a part ; in these cases, burns hai measured by using the casualty 's tad as a sandarbh point liye 1 % of the deh.
For children and infants, the lund-browder chart is prayukt to assess the burned deh surface area.
Different percentages are used kuki the anupaat of the sanyukt sataha kshetrafal of the sir or gardan to the sataha kshetrafal of the limbs is typically larger in children than that of an adult.
theth maan liye aam samooh of insaano follow.
( due to rounding, values may not add to 100 %. )

This is a list of roots, suffixes, and prefixes used in chikitsa shabdaawalee, unke meanings, or unke etymology.
There are a few niyam jab using chikitsa roots.
Firstly, prefixes or pratyay, primarily in unani, lakin bhi in latin, have a droppable -o-.
As a general rule, this -o- almost sadaa adhiniyamon as a joint-stem to conect do consonantal jaden, e.g. arthr- + -o- + logy = arthrology.
But generally, the -o- is dropped when connecting to a vowel-stem ; e.g. arthr- + itis = gathiya, bajaay of arthr-o-itis.
Secondly, medical roots generally go saath according to bhashaa : unani prefixes go saath unani pratyay or latin prefixes with Latin suffixes.
Although international scientific vocabulary is not stringent about segregating combining form of alag bhashaaen, it is advisable jab coining nai shabd nahin to mixr alag lingual roots.

The Berlin nakebandi ( 24 june 1948 – 12 may 1949 ) thi ek of the pehla pramukh antarrashtriya crises of the Cold War.
During the multinational occupation of post–World War II Germany, the Soviet sangh avarodhit the pashchimi allies ' rail, sadak, or kanal abhigam to the sector of Berlin under Allied control.
Their aim was to force the pashchimi shaktiyaan to allow the soviet mandal to prarambh supplying berlin saath khaanaa or eendhan, thereby giving the Soviets practical control over the entire city.
In jawaab, the pashchimi allies vyavasthit the berlin airlift to carry supplies to the people in West Berlin.
Aircrews from the United States Air Force, the British Royal Air Force, the Royal Australian Air Force, the Royal Canadian Air Force, the Royal New Zealand Air Force, and the dakshin africa air force udaaya over 200,000 flite in ek saal, providing up to 4700 ton of rose necessities aise as eendhan or khaanaa to the berliners.
By the spring of 1949, the effort was clearly succeeding or, by april, the airlift thi delivering adhik cargo than tha previously maharoom transported into the city by rail.
The kamyaabi of the berlin airlift brought sharmindagi to the soviets jo had refused to believe it could make a difference.
The blockade was lifted in may 1949 or resulted in the sristi of do separate German states.
the sangheey ganatantr of germany ( west germany ) and the German Democratic Republic ( East Germany ) split up Berlin.
In remembrance of the airlift, three airport in the purv pashchimi zones of the nagar parosa as the praathmik gateways to Germany for another fifty years.

In kuch styleguides, lakin nahin anya, the european chihn is unspaced.
Mate (, ; sometimes bhi spelled maté ), bhi gyaat as chimarrão ( ) or cimarrón ( ), is a paramparaagat dakshin amareeki infused peya, visheshkar in argentina, urugve, paragway and the southern states of Brazil and to a lesser degree in south of Chile, the Bolivian Chaco, Syria and Lebanon.
It is prepared from steeping sukhi pattey of yerba mate ( llex paraguariensis, gyaat in portugali as erva-mate ) in hot water.
Mate is served with a metal straw isse a saajha khokhla calabash gourd.
The straw is called a bombilla in some latin amareeki deshon, a bomba in portugali, or a bombija or, adhik generally, a masassa ( prakaar of straw ) in Arabic.
the straw is traditionally made of silver.
Modern, commercially uplabdhiyaan lobhi hai typically bana of nikal silver, called Alpaca ; stainless steel, or hollow-stemmed cane.
The gourd is known as a mate or a guampa ; jabaki in brazil, it rai the vishisht naam of cuia, or bhi cabaça ( the naam liye indigenous-influenced calabash gourds in anya regions of Brazil, still used for general food and drink in remote regions ).
bhi if the jal is supplied isse a aadhunik thermos, the infusion is traditionally drunk from mates or cuias.
As with other brewed herbs, yerba mate pattey hai sukhi, kataa, or maidan into a powdery mixture called yerba.
The bombilla adhiniyamon as dono a straw or a sieve.
The submerged end is flared, with small holes or slot ki allow the brewed drav in, lakin blaak the chanki padaarth ki makes up much of the mixture.
A modern bombilla dizine upyog a sidhaa tub saath chhed, or vasant sleeve to act as a sieve.
`` Tea-bag '' type infusions of mate ( mate cocido ) have maharoom on the market in argentina, paragway or urugve liye anek saalo antargat aise vyapaar names as `` taragüí vitality '' in argentina, `` Pajarito '' and `` Kurupí '' in Paraguay, and in Brazil under the name `` Mate Leão ''.
This is considered a completely alag peya.
It is never drunk from cuias or called chimarrão, nor is it sambhddha saath the gaucho/gaúcho culture.

The term automotive thi nirmit isse unani autos ( swah ), or latin motivus ( of gati ) to represent any form of self-powered vehicle.
This pad thi prastaavit by sae sadsy Elmer Sperry.

In June 2007, Sampson was shaadishuda to laura howzell yang in st. thomas, u.S. virgin Islands.

Halloween or Hallowe'en ( a contraction of `` All Hallows ' sandhya `` ), bhi gyaat as sab hallows ' sandhya, is a vaarshik jashn observed in a kramank of deshon on aktubar 31, the sandhya of the pashchimi Christian feast of All Hallows ( or All Saints ) and the day initiating the triduum of Hallowmas.
According to many scholars, All Hallows ' Eve is a christianised feast originally bahekaave by pashchimi europea kataai tyohaar, or tyohaar of the dead with possible pagan roots, particularly the Celtic Samhain.
Other vidwaanon maintain ki it originated independently of samhain or rai solely Christian roots.
Typical festive Halloween activities include trick-or-treating ( also known as `` guising `` ), upasthit veshbhusha partiyon, nakkashi pumpkins into jack-o'-lanterns, lighting bonfires, tehraana bobbing, visiting haunted attractions, playing pranks, telling scary stories, and watching horror films.
Freedom of speech is the political right to communicate one 's raay or vichaar using ek 's deh or property to anyone jo is willing to receive them.
The term freedom of expression is sometimes used synonymously, but shaamil koi adhinium of seeking, receiving or imparting soochna or vichaar, regardless of the medium used.
In practice, the right to freedom of speech is nahin nirpeksh in koi desh or the sahi is commonly vishay to simaaen, as saath manahani, badanaami, obscenity, rajdroh ( sahit, liye udhaaharan inciting ethnic hatred ), copyright violation, revelation of information that is classified or otherwise.
The right to freedom of expression is pahachaanaa as a insaan sahi antargat aalekh 19 of the saarvbhaumik ghoshnaa of insaan adhikaron or pahachaanaa in antarrashtriya insaan adhikaron vidhi in the antarrashtriya vachan on civil and Political Rights ( ICCPR ).
Article 19 of the ICCPR rajya ki `` [ e ] veryone shall have the sahi to tham raay bagaiyr hastkshep '' or `` everyone shall have the sahi to swatantraaa of abhivyakti ; is sahi shall shaamil swatantraaa to talash, receive and impart information and ideas of all kinds, regardless of frontiers, either orally, in writing or in print, in the form of art, or through any other media of his choice ''.
Article 19 goes on to say that the exercise of these rights carries `` special duties and jimmedaariyon `` or may `` isliye be vishay to nishchit pratibandh '' jab jaruri `` [ f ] or aadar of the adhikaron or pratishtha of anya '' or `` [ f ] or the suraksha of neshnal suraksha or of public order ( order public ), or of public health or morals ''.
Freedom of vaak may be legally curtailed in kuch dharmik vidhik pranaaliyon or in dharmanirpeksh jurisdictions jahaan it is found to cause religious offense, such as the British Racial and Religious Hatred Act 2006.
Sydney Harbour from the air, showing the Opera House, the CBD, golakaar quay, the sethu, the parramatta nadi, uttar sidney or kirribilli in the foreground
The Sydney Harbour Bridge is a steel through arch bridge aarpaar sidney harbour ki carries rail, vehicular, cykil or paidal trekkic between the sidney central business district ( CBD ) and the North Shore.
The dramatic view of the bridge, the harbour, and the aasapaas sidney opera house is an iconic chitra of sidney, nai dakshin Wales, and Australia.
The bridge is nicknamed `` the coathanger '' kuki of iske arch-based design.
Under the directions of Dr j.j.c. bradfield of the nsw vibhaag of public works, the sethu thi designed or nirmit by angrejon firm Dorman Long and Co Ltd of Middlesbrough and opened in 1932.
The sethu 's dizine thi bahekaave by the narak phatak Bridge in New York.
It was the world 's widest long-span bridge, at 48.8 meter ( 160 feet ) chaudee, jabatak nirmaan of the new Port Mann Bridge in Vancouver.
It is also the fifth longest spanning-arch sethu in the sansar, or it is the tallest steel mehrab bridge, measuring from top to water level.
jabatak 1967 the harbour sethu thi sidney 's tallest structure.
The Hawaii hotspot is a volcanic hotspot stith nikat the namesake hawaii Islands, in the northern Pacific Ocean.
One of the most well-known and heavily studied hotspots in the world, the Hawaii plume is responsible for the creation of the Hawaiian – Emperor seamount kadi, an over 5,800 kilometre ( 3,600 mi ) long kadi of jwalamukhi, chaar of jisase hai kriyasheel, do of jisase hai dormant, or adhik than 123 of jisase hai vilupt, anek having chunki maharoom maidan beneath the lehren by erosion as seamounts and atolls.
The chain extends from south of the island of Hawaii to the kinare of the aleutian gart, nikat the purvi kinare of rus.
While sabase jwalamukhi hai nirmit by geological kaaryaklap at tectonic thali seemayen, the hawaii hotspot is stith dur isse aasapaas thali seemayen ; the clasik hotspot siddhanth, pehla prastaavit in 1963 by jon tuzo wilson, proposes ki a single, phixd mantle plume builds jwalamukhi ki tab, kaaten off from their source by the movement of the Pacific Plate, become increasingly inactive and eventually erode below sea level over millions of years.
According to this theory, the nearly 60° bend separating the Emperor and hawaii khand of the kadi thi caused by a achaanak shift in the gati of the prashanth Plate.
In 2003, bhais investigations of is irregularity led to the prastaav of a mobile hotspot siddhanth, suggesting ki hotspot hai mobile, nahin fixed, and that the 47 million year old bend was caused by a shift in the hotspot 's motion rather than the plate 's.
Ancient Hawaiians were the first to recognize the increasing aayu or weathered rajya of the jwalamukhi to the north as they progressed on fishing expeditions along the islands.
The volatile state of the Hawaiian volcanoes and their nirantar battle saath the samudr thi a pramukh tatv in hawaii mythology, embodied in Pele, the deity of volcanoes.
After the arrival of Europeans on the island, in 1880-1881 james dwite dana nirdeshit the pehla aupchaarik geological padhai of the hotspot 's volcanics, confirming the sambandh long observed by the natives.
1912 chihnit the founding of the hawaii jwalamukhi vedhashala by volcanologist thomas jaggar, initiating continuous scientific observation of the islands.
In the 1970s, a maanchitran project thi initiated to laabh adhik soochna about the complex geology of Hawaii 's seafloor.
The hotspot has since been tomographically imaged, showing it to be wide and up to gahan, or oliwine or garnet -aadharand adhyayan have dikhaaya iske megma kaksh is lagbhag.
In iske at tanik 85 lakh saalo of kaaryaklap the hotspot has produced an estimated of rock.
The chain 's rate of drift rai dhire increased over samay, causing the raashi of samay prayek vyaktigat jwalamukhi is kriyasheel to ghati, isse 18 lakh saalo liye the 76 lakh saal boodha detroit seamount, to bas antargat 900,000 liye the ek million year-old Kohala ; on the other hand, eruptive volume has increased from per year to about.
Overall, this has caused a trend towards more active but quickly-silenced, closely spaced volcanoes—whereas jwalamukhi on the nikat paksh of the hotspot overlap prayek anya ( forming aise superstructures as hawaii dweep or the pracheen maavi nui ), the oldest of the samraat seamounts are spaced as far as apart.

osteonecrosis of the jabadon ( onj ) is a kathor asthi beemaari ki affects the maxilla and the mandible.
Various forms of ONJ have maharoom varnit over the pichhlaa 160 saalo, or a kramank of kalyankari have maharoom sujhaayaa in the literature.
osteonecrosis of the jabade sambhddha saath bisphosphonate chikitsa, jaruri by kuch karkat upachaar regimens, rai been identified and defined as a pathological entity since 2003.
The possible risk isse nimnatar maukhik doses of bisphosphonates, liya by marijon to prevent or treat osteoporosis, remains uncertain.
Various treatment options have maharoom chaan, however kathor maamle of onj still aavashyaktaa surgical removal of the affected bone.
A thorough history and assessement of pre-existing pranaligat samasyaayein or sambhavit site of danta sankraman hai jaruri to help prevent the condition, especially if bisphosphonate therapy is considered.
The Boston Red Sox are a professional baseball team based in boston, masachusets, or a sadsy of pramukh lig besabaal 's amareeki lig purvi prabhag.
Founded in as one of the American lig 's aath charter franchises, the red sox 's ghar ballpark rai maharoom fenway park since.
the `` red sox '' naam thi chuni by the toli maalik, jon I. tailor, around, following previous Boston teams that had been known as the `` Red Stockings ``.
They have played in 11 sansar shrenee, jeetna 7.
Boston was a prabal toli in the nai lig, defeating the pittsburg Pirates in the first World Series in and winning four more championships by.
However, they then went into one of the longest championship droughts in baseball history, called by kuch the `` abhishaap of the bambino `` baad iske kathith shuruuaat saath the red sox 's bikri of beb ruth to the pratidwandvi yankis do saalo baad unke sansar championships in 1918, an 86-year wait before the team 's sixth World Championship in.
However, the toli 's itihaas dauraan ki kaal thi hardly ek of futility, lakin thi balki punctuated saath kuch of the sabase yaadgaar pal in sansar shrenee itihaas, sahit enos vadh 's `` mad dash `` in, the `` Impossible Dream `` of, Carlton Fisk 's home run in, and Bill Buckner 's error in.
Red Sox history has also been marked by the team 's intense rivalry with the nai york yankis, arguably the fiercest or sabase aitihaasik in uttar amareeki peshewar khel.
The Boston Red Sox are owned by Fenway khel samooh, jo bhi apana liverpool footbaal klbon of the Premier League in England.
The Red Sox are consistently one of the sheersh emelbi tiimon in ausat sadak upasthiti, jabaki the choti kshamta of fenway park roktaa unhen isse agrani in overall attendance.
From May 15, 2003 to April 10, 2013, the Red Sox sold out every home game-a total of 820 games ( 794 regular ritu ) liye a pramukh peshewar khel ricard ki lasted lagbhag a dashak.
mince pai bhar saath mincemeat
mincemeat is a mishran of kataa sukhi fal, asut atmaaon or masaale, and sometimes beef suet, beef, or venison.
Originally, mincemeat sadaa contained meat.
Many modern recipes contain bif suet, haalanki sabzi shortening is sometimes used in its place.

In some countries the term mincemeat refers to minced or maidan meat.

Argentina, officially the Argentine Republic ( ), is the duusari largest desh in dono dakshin america or the latin america region.
The country is a federation of 23 provinces or the autonomous nagar of buenos yrs, iske puunji or largest city.
It is the eighth -largest country in the world by jameen kshetrafal or the largest among spanish-speaking raashtra by bhugolic kshetrafal of 2,780,400 km2 or is the fourth by population, with over 41 million people.
argentina is a founding sadsy of the sanyukt raashtra, mercosur, the sangh of dakshin amareeki raashtra, the sanghathan of ibero-american rajya, the sansar bainko Group and the World Trade Organization, and is one of the G-15 and G-20 major economies.
Argentina is located in South America, bordered by chile to the west or dakshin, bolivia or paragway to the uttar or brazil and Uruguay to the northeast.
Argentina daawa prabhutaa over bhaag of antarctic, the fockland islands ( ) and South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands.
Argentina is the successor state of the viceroyalty of the río de la plata, an videshi upnivesh of the spani Empire.
Argentina declared independence during the argentine yuddh of swatantraaa, jisase thi followed by the argentine Civil Wars during most of the 19th century.
The country faced anek sainya coups or rajnatik asthirataa dauraan the 20th sadi, along with periodic economic crisis that continue to this day.
A recognized Southern Cone power, and middle power, Argentina is Latin america 's third-largest arthvyavastha, saath a `` bahut unchi '' darja on the Human development index.
Within Latin America, Argentina has the paanchvaan ucchtam nammaatr jidipi prati capita or the ucchtam in purchasing power terms.
The Legatum Institute have argued that the country has a `` foundation for future growth due to its market size, levels of foreign direct nivesh, or pratishat of high-tech niryaat as share of kul manufactured goods '', or it is classed by investors as middle emerging economy.

The country has three Nobel puraskaar in vigyaan or do of salaam.

The country also has the aachman pradarshnee bich of vigyaan, praudyogiki, udyog and art that are Latin America 's largest.

Polyethylene terephthalate ( sometimes written poly ( ethylene terephthalate ) ), commonly abbreviated PET, peet, or the obsolete petp or pet-p, is a thermoplastic polimur raal of the poliester parivaar or is prayukt in synthetic machhlee ; beverage, food and other liquid containers ; thermoforming applications ; and engineering resins often in combination with glass fiber.
The term polyethylene terephthalate is a sorce of bhram kuki is padaarth, paalatu, karata nahin contain polyethylene.
Thus, the alternate form, poly ( ethylene terephthalate ), is praayah prayukt in scholarly jarnals liye the khatir of accuracy and clarity.
Depending on its processing and thermal history, polyethylene terephthalate may maujuud dono as an amorphous ( paardarshee ) or as a semi-crystalline polymer.
The semicrystalline material might appear paardarshee ( kan aakaar < 500 nm ) or apaardarshee or shwet ( kan aakaar up to a few microne ) depending on its crystal structure and particle size.
Its monomer ( bis-β-hydroxyterephthalate ) can be synthesized by the esterification reaction between terephthalic acid or ethilin glykol saath jal as a byproduct, or by transesterification pratikriya between ethylene glycol and dimethyl terephthalate with methanol as a byproduct.
bahulkikaran is through a polycondensation pratikriya of the monomers ( done immediately after esterification/transesterification ) with water as the byproduct.
The majority of the world 's PET production is for synthetic machhlee ( in excess of 60 % ), saath bottle utpaadan hisaab liye around 30 % of vaishvik demand.
In the context of textile applications, PET is referred to by its aam naam, `` poliester, '' whereas the echronim `` paalatu '' is generally used in relation to packaging.
Polyester makes up about 18 % of world polymer production and is the third-most-produced polimur ; polyethylene ( pe ) or polypropylene ( pp ) hai pehla or duusari, respectively.
PET consists of polymerized ikai of the monomer ethilin terephthalate, with repeating C10H8O4 units.
PET is commonly recycled, or rai the number `` 1 '' as its recycling symbol.

In Europe and the Americas, theth fillers shaamil maance, mote, suet, bread, cornmeal, mithi aalu, onion, chestnuts, barley, and oatmeal.
in spain, portugal or Asia, potato is often replaced by rice.
shairdharak may refer to:
Stakeholder ( corporate ), a person, group, organization, sadsy or pranali jo affects or can be prabhavit by an sanghathan 's actions
Stakeholder, an entity ki can be prabhavit by the parinaam of ki in jisase ve hai kaha to be hitdharakon, i.e., ki in which they have a stake.
Project stakeholder, a vyakti, samooh or sanghathan saath an byaaj in a project
Stakeholder theory, a siddhanth ki identifies or model the samooh jisase hai hitdharakon of a corporation or project
shairdharak vishleshan, the prakram of identifying those affected by a project or event
shairdharak ( vidhi ), a teesraa party jo temporarily holds dhan or property while its owner is still being determined

swatantraaa din, commonly gyaat as the chauthi of july, is a sangheey avkaash in the sanyukt rajya commemorating the adoption of the Declaration of Independence on July 4, 1776, declaring independence from the Kingdom of Great Britain.
Independence Day is commonly associated with aatishbaajee, parades, barbecues, carnivals, melon, picnics, concert, besabaal khel, parivaar reunions, or rajnatik bhaashanon and ceremonies, in addition to various other public and private events celebrating the history, government, and traditions of the United States.

A gender symbol denotes the sex of an sajiv or characterizes an agent by gender.
The two standard gender pratikon denoting purush ♂ or maadaa ♀ hai niklaa isse astrological symbols, denoting the classical planets Mars and Venus, respectively.
These symbols have been in use since the Renaissance also denoting tatv in alchemy, specifically the dhaatuon aayran or tambe.
They were first used to denote the effective gender of plants ( i.e. sex of vyaktigat in a die crossbreed, chunki sabase paudhe hai hermaphroditic ) by Carolus Linnaeus in 1751.
A leasehold estate is an swaamitv of a asthai sahi to tham jameen or property in jisase a lessee or a kiraayedaar holds adhikaron of real property by kuch rup of title from a lessor or landlord.
Although a tenant does hold adhikaron to real property, a leasehold estate is typically considered personal property.
Leasehold is a form of land tenure or property kaarykaal jahaan ek party kharidta the sahi to occupy jameen or a building for a given length of time.
As lease is a vidhik estate, leasehold estate can be bought and sold on the open market.
A leasehold thus differs isse a freehold or shulk saral jahaan the swaamitv of a property is kharida outright or thereafter yojit liye an anirdharya lambaai of samay, or bhi differs isse a tenancy jahaan a property is let ( rented ) on a periodic basis such as weekly or monthly.
Until the end of the lease period ( often measured in dashakon or sadiyaan ; a 99 saal patte is kaaphi aam ) the leaseholder rai the sahi to remain in occupation as an assured tenant paying an agreed rent to the owner.
Terms of the agreement are contained in a patte, jisase rai tatv of anubandh or property vidhi intertwined.
The term estate liye saalo may occasionally be prayukt.
This refers to a leasehold estate liye koi vishisht kaal of samay ( the shabd `` years '' is misleading ).
An estate for saalo is nahin automatically navinikrut.
Colloquially, `` patte '' or `` patte `` hai praayah a formalization of a longer, specific period as compared with a `` rental '' that created a tenancy at will, terminable or renewable at the end of a short period.

Location of Panama between Pacific ( neeche ) or caribbean ( sheersh ), saath kanal at top center
The Panama Canal ( ) is a jalayaan kanal in panama ki connects the atlantic samandar ( via the Caribbean Sea ) to the Pacific Ocean.
the kanal katautee aarpaar the isthmus of panama or is a key conduit for international maritime trade.
There are locks at prayek samaapt to lift jahaajon up to gatun jhil ( upar sea-level ).
Gatun Lake was created to reduce the raashi of kaary jaruri liye the canal.
The vartmaan taale hai wide.
A third, wider len of taale is being built.
France began kaary on the kanal in 1881, lakin tha to roke kuki of engineering problems and high mortality due to disease.
The United States ( US ) baad took over the project or took a dashak to puraa the kanal in 1914, enabling jahaajon to avoid the lengthy kep sing root around the southernmost tip of South America ( via the Drake Passage ) or to navigate the Strait of Magellan.
One of the largest and most difficult abhiyantriki project kabhi undertaken, the panama kanal shortkat bana it sambhavit liye jahaajon to safar between the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans in half the time previously required.
the shorter, tej, safer root to the us west coast or to raashtra in or saath the prashanth Ocean allowed those places to become more integrated with the world economy.
During this time, ownership of the territory ki is abhi the panama kanal thi pehla columbian, tab french, or tab American ; the United States completed the construction.
The canal was taken over in 1999 by the panamanian sarkari, as long niojit.
Annual traffic has risen from about 1,000 ships when the canal opened in 1914, to 14,702 baratan in 2008, the latter measuring a kul of 309.6 lakh panama canal/universal maapan pranali ( pc/ums ) tons.
By 2008, more than 815,000 vessels had passed through the canal, anek of unhen much larger than the asli planners could have envisioned ; the largest jahaajon ki can pargaman the kanal aaj hai pukaara Panamax.
The American Society of Civil ejiniers rai namit the panama kanal ek of the saat chamatkaar of the aadhunik world.
Benjamin Franklin ( April 17, 1790 ) thi ek of the founding fathers of the United States.
A noted polymath, Franklin was a agrani lekhak, mudrak, rajnatik theorist, rajaneta, postmaster, vaigyanik, musician, inventor, satirist, civic activist, statesman, and diplomat.
As a scientist, he was a pramukh figure in the amareeki atmagyaan or the itihaas of bhautikee liye uske discoveries and theories regarding electricity.
He invented the lightning rod, bifocals, the franklin stove, a carriage odometer, and the glass 'armonica '.
he facilitated anek naagarik sanghathan, sahit a aag department and a university.
Franklin earned the sheershak of `` the pehla amareeki '' liye uske jaldi or indefatigable campaigning liye aupniveshik ekta ; as an lekhak or pravaktaa in landan liye anek colonies, tab as the first United States Ambassador to France, he exemplified the emerging American nation.
franklin thi foundational in dhamak the amareeki ethos as a vivaah of the vyaavhaarik maan of thrift, mushkil kaary, shiksha, jatiyaan spirit, self-governing institutions, and opposition to authoritarianism both political and religious, with the scientific and tolerant values of the Enlightenment.
In the shabd of itihaaskaar henry steel commager, `` in a franklin could be milaayaa the virtues of Puritanism without its defects, the illumination of the Enlightenment without its heat. ''
To Walter Isaacson, this makes Franklin `` the most sampannataa amareeki of uske aayu or the sabase influential in inventing the prakaar of samaaj america would become. ''
Franklin, always proud of his working class jaden, became a kaamyaab samachaarpatr editor or mudrak in Philadelphia, the leading city in the colonies.
He was also partners with William Goddard and Joseph Galloway the three of whom published the Pennsylvania vrittant, a samachaarpatr ki thi gyaat liye iske krantikari sentiments or aalochanaon of the angrejon samrajya in the amareeki colonies.
He became wealthy publishing garib richard 's almanack or the pencilvenia Gazette.
Franklin gained international renown as a vaigyanik liye uske prasiddh prayog in vidyut or for his many inventions, especially the lightning rod.
He played a pramukh bhoomika in establishing the vishvavidhyalayon of pencilvenia or was elected the first president of the American Philosophical Society.
Franklin became a national hero in america jab he pathpradarshan the praytn to have parliament repeal the unpopular Stamp Act.
An sampannataa rajanyik, he thi widely admired among the french as amareeki mantri to Paris and was a major figure in the development of positive Franco-American relations.
For many years he thi the angrejon postmaster liye the colonies, jisase sakriy use to niyat up the first national communications network.
He was active in community afares, aupniveshik or rajya raajnneeti, as khub as neshnal or international affairs.
isse 1785 to 1788, he parosa as governor of Pennsylvania.
Toward the end of his life, he freed uske slave or became ek of the sabase prominent abolitionists.
His colorful life and legacy of scientific and political achievement, and aukaat as ek of america 's sabase influential founding fathers, have dekhi franklin sammanit on coinage or dhan ; warships ; the names of anek kasbon, county, shaikshanik sansthaanon, namesakes, and companies ; and more than two centuries after his death, countless cultural references.

The orbital speed of a body, generally a planet, a natural upgrah, an kritrim upgrah, or a anek star, is the gati at jisase it orbits around the barycenter of a pranali, praayah around a more massive body.
It can be used to refer to either the mean orbital speed, the ausat gati as it completes an kaksha, or instantaneous kakshiya gati, the gati at a particular point in its orbit.
The orbital speed at any position in the orbit can be computed from the alahada to the central deh at ki sthiti, or the vishisht kakshiya urja, jisase is swatantra of sthiti : the gatij urja is the total energy minus the potential energy.

DVD-Video is a consumer video format prayukt to store digital video on dvd discs, or is philhal the prabal upabhokta video swaroop in Asia, North America, Europe, and Australia.
discs using the dvd-video specification aavashyaktaa a dvd drive or an h.262/mpeg-2 bhaag 2 decoder ( e.g., a DVD player, or a computer DVD drive with a software DVD player ).
vanijyik dvd filmon hai encoded using a sangyojan of h.262/mpeg-2 bhaag 2 sampidit video or audio of varying formats ( often multi-channel formats as described below ).
typically, the aankada rate liye dvd filmon seemayen isse 3 mbit/s to 9.5 mbit/s, or the bit rate is usually adaptive.
It was first uplabdhiyaan liye khudara around 1997.
The DVD-Video specification was created by dvd foram or can be praapt isse dvd format/logo licencing nigam liye a shulk of $ 5,000.
The specification is not publicly available, because prayek sadsy jarur chihn a non-disclosure anubandh.
Certain information in the DVD kitaab is malikana or gopneey.
The nautical mile ( symbol M, NM or nmi ) is a ikai of lambaai ki is parichay ek minute of chaap of akshansh measured along any meridian, or about one minute of arc of longitude at the equator.
By antarrashtriya anubandh it rai maharoom niyat at 1,852 meter exactly ( about 6,076 feet ).
It is a non- SI unit ( although accepted for upyog in the antarrashtriya pranali of ikai by the bipm ) prayukt visheshkar by navigators in the shipping and aviation industries, and also in polar exploration.
It is commonly used in international law and treaties, visheshkar regarding the had of territorial waters.
It developed from the samudr mile or the sambandhit bhugolic mile.
The nautical mile remains in use by sea and air navigators vishwavyaapee kuki of iske convenience jab working with charts.
Most nautical chart upyog the mercator prakshep jinaki scale varies by parichay a factor of chah isse the equator to 80° akshansh, so chart covering large areas can not use a single linear scale.
The nautical mile is nearly equal to a minute of akshansh on a chart, so a alahada measured saath a chart divider can be roughly parivartit to nautical miles using the chart 's latitude scale.
Shippensburg is a baro in kambarland or franklin county in the u.S. rajya of Pennsylvania.
Settled in 1730, shippensburg jhooth in the kambarland ghati, 41 mile ( 66 km ) west-southwest of Harrisburg, and is part of the Harrisburg– Carlisle Metropolitan Statistical Area.
In 1900, 3,228 logon jiya vahin ; in 1910, 3,457 ; and in 1940, 5,244 people lived there.
the janasankhyikee thi 5,492 at the 2010 census.

In the past, there were furniture kaarkaanon, ingine or pump works, or anya audyogic works stith bheetar the town.
Shippensburg is also the home of The Beistle Company, the oldest and largest nirmaataa of sajaavat or party goods, jisase bikta iske distinctive madhukosh paper sajaavat vishwavyaapee.
It is bhi the sthaan of pague or fegan, the oldest lagaataar operated hardware store in Pennsylvania.
In May 2012, Volvo Construction Equipment began a $ 100 lakh vistaar project to lao iske amareeki mukhyalay to Shippensburg.
shippensburg is bhi ghar to shippensburg vishvavidhyalayon of pencilvenia, ek of 14 vishvavidhyalayon of the pencilvenia State System of Higher Education.
Yearly the pichhlaa puraa saptaah of july, the shippensburg jatiyaan Fair is held.
Begun in 1958, the fair bills itself as pencilvenia 's largest bi-county mela.
The fair includes agricultural exhibits, a shilp dikhaaen, khaanaa vikreta, or carnival yatraayen amongst other things.
Every summer on the last Saturday of August, Shippensburg holds the Corn Festival, an event ki brings kshetreey shilpkaar or vikreta to operate stands downtown.
the shahar is band to trekkic liye at tanik 5 block for most of the day.

Black hairy tongue ( BHT, also termed lingua villosa nigra ) refers to a condishan of the jeebh jahaan the filiform papillae elongate saath blike or bhura discoloration, giving a black and hairy appearance.
The appearance may be alarming, lakin it is a hanirahit condishan.
Predisposing factors shaamil dhumrapaan, xerostomia ( shushk munh ), naram aahaar, garib maukhik hygiene or certain medications.
Management is by improving maukhik hygiene, visheshkar scraping or brushing the tongue.
The IEEE 1394 interfes is a serial bas interfes maanak liye high-speed sanchaar and isochronous real-time data transfer.
It was developed in the late 1980s or jaldi 1990s by tehraana, jo pukaara it FireWire.
The 1394 interfes is comparable to usb, or praayah those do technologies hai considered together, though USB has more market share.
Apple first shaamil firewire in kuch of iske 1999 model, or sabase tehraana computer chunki the saal 2000 have shaamil FireWire ports, though, as of 2013, nothing beyond the 800 version ( IEEE-1394b ).
The interfes is bhi gyaat by the brands i.link ( soni ), or Lynx ( Texas Instruments ).
IEEE 1394 replaced parallel SCSI in many anuprayog, kuki of nimnatar kriyanvayan laagat or a sarlikrut, adhik anukoolneey cabling system.
the 1394 maanak bhi defines a backplane interfes, though this is not as widely used.
IEEE 1394 is the High-Definition audio-video sanjaal gathbandhan ( haana ) maanak conection interfes liye a/v ( audio/visual ) ghatak communication and control.
FireWire is also uplabdhiyaan in betaar, resha optic, or samakshiya sanskaran using the isochronous protocols.
Stephen `` Stevie '' Ray Vaughan ( October 3, 1954 – agast 27, 1990 ) thi an amareeki guitarist, singer-songwriter, or ricard producer.
Often referred to by his initials SRV, Vaughan is behtareen gyaat as a founding sadsy or netaa of doguna Trouble.
Together with vadak kris layton or bassist tommy shainan, ve ignited the bluez revival of the 1980s.
With a career spanning saat saalo, vaughan or doguna trubal consistently bechi out concerts while their albums frequently went gold.
He was born or uthaaya in dalas, texas, or liye a choti period of time lived in Graham, Texas.
As the younger brother of Jimmie Vaughan, Vaughan prarambh playing the guitar at aayu saat or formed several bands that occasionally performed in local nightclubs.
At age 17, he dropped out of high school and sthanantarit to austin to further pursue uske musical kariyar, joining samooh aise as krackerjack, the nightcrawlers, and the Cobras.
In 1977, he formed Triple Threat Revue, a band that eventually evolved into doguna trubal or regularly performed around austin.
In 1982, Vaughan and Double Trouble performed at the montreux jaiz parv in switzaraland, catching the dhyaan of sangeetkaaron daud bovi or jackson Browne.
Bowie asked Vaughan to khel on uske aagaamee studio album let 's nrity, jabaki browne offered the band free upyog of uske nijee studio in Los Angeles to record an album.

After successful touring, the samooh released the album, could n't stand the mausam ( 1984 ) or aatma to aatma ( 1985 ), the latter of jisase pradarshit nai keyboardist Reese Wynans.
Although his career had progressed safaltaapurvak, vaughan checked into a punarvaas hospital in atlanta, georgia to de up a coca or alcohol habit and returned to touring with the band.
In June 1989, In Step was released and arjeet unhen a grami puraskaar liye behtareen Contemporary Blues Performance.
On August 27, 1990, vaughan thi maare in a helicopter krash following a pradarshan in East Troy, Wisconsin.
Vaughan 's uniquely eclectic yet teevr style thi niklaa isse a variety of musical genres.

In computer networking, gigabit Ethernet ( GbE or 1 gige ) is a pad describing vibhinn technologies liye transmitting ethernet frames at a rate of a gigabit prati duusari ( 1,000,000,000 bits per second ), as defined by the IEEE 802.3-2008 standard.
It came into upyog shuruuaat in 1999, dhire supplanting tej ethernet in taar local sanjaal, jahaan it performed considerably faster.
The cables and equipment are bahut samaan to pichhlaa maanakon or yahood bahut aam or kifayati by 2010.
Half-duplex gigabit links connected through hubs are allowed by the specification, lakin full-duplex upyog saath switches is much adhik common.

A postage stamp is a small piece of paper ki is kharida or pradarshit on an mad of mail as pramaan of bhugtan of postage.
Typically, stamps are made from khaas paper, saath a neshnal namakan or denomination ( daam ) on the phase, or a gam chipakane on the reverse paksh.
Postage stamps are purchased from a postal administration or other authorized vendor or hai prayukt to adaa liye the laagat shaamil in chalati mail as khub as anya kaarobaar necessities aise as insurance and registration.
The stamp’s aakaar is praayah ki of a choti ytaakar of varying proportions, though triangles or other shapes are occasionally used.
The stamp is affixed to an lipapha or anya dak cover ( i.e., packet, baksaa, mailing belan ) that the customer wishes to send.
The item is tab processed by the dak pranali, jahaan a postmark, sometimes gyaat as a raddikaran chihnit, is praayah applied over the stamp and cover ; this procedure marks the stamp as used, which prevents its reuse.
The postmark indicates the tithi or point of origin of the mailing.
The mailed item is then delivered to the address ki the graahak rai lagu to the lipapha or cover.
postage stamps have facilitated the delivery of mail since the 1840s.
Before this time, ink and hand-stamps ( hence the shabd 'stamp ' ), praayah bana isse lakdi or cork, yahood praayah prayukt to frank the mail or confirm the payment of postage.
The first adhesive postage stamp, commonly referred to as the paini blike, thi jari in the sanyukt kingdom in 1840.
The invention of the stamp was a part of the attempt to reform and improve the postal system in the United Kingdom of Great Britain or ireland, jisase in the jaldi 19th sadi thi in astavyastata or rife saath bhrashtachar.
There are varying khate of the avishkaarak or avishkaarak of the stamp.
Before the introduction of postage stamps, mail in the UK was paid for by the recipient, a system that was associated with an irresolvable problem : the laagat of delivering mail yahood nahin recoverable by the dak seva jab praptakarta yahood asamarth or unwilling to adaa liye vitarit vasteen, or preshkon tha no protsaahan to simit the kramank, aakaar, or weight of items sent, whether or not they would ultimately be paid for.
The postage stamp resolved this issue in a saral or suruchipurna manner, saath the atirikt laabh of room liye an tatv of saundarya to be introduced.
Later related inventions include postal stationery such as prepaid-postage envelopes, post cards, lettercards, aerogrammes and wrappers, postage meter, or, adhik recently, specialty baks or lipaphe provided free to the graahak by the u.S. dak seva liye pradhanta or express mailing.
The postage stamp afforded convenience for both the mailer or dak officials, adhik efficiently baraamad laagat liye the dak seva, or ultimately resulted in a better, faster postal system.
With the conveniences stamps offered, unke upyog resulted in greatly increased mailings dauraan the 19th and 20th centuries.
Postage stamps during this era were the most lokapriy rasta of paying liye mail, lakin by the samaapt of the 20th sadi yahood rapidly hone eclipsed by the use of metered postage and bulk mailing by businesses. )
The same result with respect to communications by private parties occurred over the pichhlaa dashak of the 20th sadi or the pehla dashak of the 21st due to ghatati laagat of long alahada telephone sanchaar or the vikaas or visphotak sprad of electronic mailing ( `` e-mail '' via the Internet ) and bill paying systems had.
As postage stamps with their engraved imagery began to appear on a faili aadhaar, itihaaskaaron or collectors began to take notice.
The padhai of postage stamps or unke upyog is referred to as philately.
Stamp collecting can be dono a shauk or a rup of aitihaasik padhai or sandarbh, as government-issued postage stamps or unke mailing systems have always been involved with the history of nations.

tofu, bhi pukaara saim dahi, is a khaanaa bana by coagulating soya ras and then pressing the resulting curds into soft white blocks.
it is a ghatak in anek east asian or southeast Asian cuisines.
There are many different varieties of tofu, sahit bhais tofu or tofu ki rai maharoom processed in some way.
Tofu rai a halkaa swaad or can be prayukt in savory and sweet dishes.
It is often seasoned or marinated to suut the dish.
tofu originated in pracheen china kuch 2,000 years ago.
Chinese legend ascribes iske avishkaar to prince liyu an ( chinis : 劉安 Liú Ān, 179–122 BC ).
Tofu and its utpaadan takanic yahood introduced into korian or tab japani dauraan the Nara period.
It sprad into anya bhaag of east asia as well.
is sprad sambhavit coincided saath the sprad of buddhism because it is an important source of protein in the vegetarian diet of East Asian Buddhism.
Li Shizhen in the Ming Dynasty varnit a vidhi of bananaa tofu in Bencao Gangmu.
Tofu has a low calorie count, apekshaakrit vishaal amounts of protein, or little fat.
It is high in iron and depending on the coagulant prayukt in nirmaan, may bhi be unchi in calcium and/or magnesium.

The meaning of life is a philosophical question concerning the significance of jivan or astitv in general.
It can bhi be expressed in alag form, aise as `` kyon hai we yahan ? ``, `` kayaa is jivan sab parichay ? ``, and `` What is the purpose of existence ? ''
It rai maharoom the vishay of much philosophical, vaigyanik, and theological speculation throughout history.
There have been a large kramank of prastaavit jawaab to ye sawaal isse anek alag cultural and ideological backgrounds.
The meaning of life is in the philosophical and religious conceptions of existence, social ties, consciousness, and happiness, and borders on many other issues, such as sankethik arth, sattamimasaa, maan, purpose, aachaar, shubh or dusht, free hoga, the astitv of ek or anek devataaon, conceptions of parameshwar, the soul, and the afterlife.
Scientific contributions focus primarily on describing related empirical facts about the brahmad, exploring the context or paramiters concerning the 'how ' of life.
Science also adhyayan or can provide suzav liye the pursuit of well-being and a related conception of morality.
an vaikalpik, humanistic drushtikon mudraayen the sawaal `` What is the meaning of my life ? ''
The value of the question pertaining to the purpose of life may coincide saath the uplabdhi of param vaastaviktaa, or a ahsaas of oneness, or bhi a ahsaas of sacredness.

`` The Princess and the Pea '' ( ; shabdic anuwaad : `` the rajkumaari on the matar '' ) is a saahitiyik pari tail by hans isai Andersen about a young woman whose royal identity is established by a test of her physical sensitivity.
The tale was first published with three anya by andersen in an inexpensive pustika on 8 may 1835 in copenhegan by C.A. Reitzel.
Andersen had heard the story as a child, and it likely has its source in lok saamagree, sambhawatah originating isse sweden as it is unknown in the Danish oral tradition.
Neither `` The Princess and the Pea '' nor Andersen 's other tales of 1835 were well praapt by danish aalochakon, jo disliked unke cazual, chatty style, and their lack of morals.
In 1959 `` The Princess and the Pea '' was adapted to the musical stage in a utpaadan pukaara ekbar upon a gadda abhinit carol burnett.
German Americans ( ) are citizens of the United rajya jo yahood either born in germany or hai of germany ancestry.
They comprise parichay 50 lakh logon, bananaa unhen the largest ancestry samooh ahead of Irish Americans, African Americans and English Americans.
They comprise parichay 1/3 of the germany diaspora sab over the world.
None of the germany rajya tha nai sansar colonies.
Not until the 1670s did the first significant groups of German apravasiyon arrive in the angrejon colonies, settling primarily in New York and Pennsylvania.
Immigration continued in very large numbers during the 19th sadi, saath kuch aath lakh aamad isse Germany.
They were pulled by the attractions of land and dharmik swatantraaa, or dhakel out of europea by shortages of jameen or dharmik or rajnatik oppression.
Many arrived seeking dharmik or rajnatik swatantraaa, anya liye aarthik avasar vrihad than those in Europe, and others simply for the chance to start fresh in the New World.
The arrivals before 1850 were mostly farmers who sought out the sabase utpaadak jameen, jahaan unke intensive kheti takneekon hota adaa off.
After 1840, many aae to shaharon, jahaan `` germania '' —german-speaking districts—soon emerged.
German Americans established the first kindergartens in the United rajya, introduced the christmas ped parampara, or originated lokapriy amareeki foods such as hot dogs and hamburgers.
German American celebrations are held throughout the desh, ek of the sabase well-known hone the german-american steuben parade in nai york nagar, yojit every third Saturday in September.
There are also major annual events in Chicago, sinsinati, milvowki, pittsburg, st. lui or anya cities.
Like many other immigrants ki aae to the sanyukt rajya, an overwhelming kramank of logon of germany or aanshik germany descent have essentially become Americanized.
The Preamble to the United rajya samvidhan is a bread parichayatmak bayaan of the samvidhan 's fundamental purposes and guiding principles.
It states in general terms, and courts have referred to it as vishwasaneey pramaan of, the founding fathers ' iraadon regarding the samvidhan 's meaning and what they hoped the Constitution would achieve as it pertains to all of the people of the United States.
As the phrase, `` we the logon '' suggests ki the nai sarkari originates isse the logon of the sanyukt rajya or it set into gati a sawaal as it pertains to ki vishaal janasankhyikee concerning the individual rights and equality among all people ; this can be seen most broadly in the divide between republicanism and social democracy.
The history of the Internet began saath the vikaas of electronic computer in the 1950s.
The public was first introduced to the avadharanaon ki hota sise to the antarjaal jab a sandesh thi bheja over the arpanet isse computer vigyaan praadhyaapak leonard kleinrock 's prayogshaala at vishvavidhyalayon of california, los angeles ( ucla ), baad the second piece of network equipment was installed at Stanford Research Institute ( SRI ).
Packet switched networks such as ARPANET, Mark I at NPL in the UK, CYCLADES, Merit Network, tymnet, or telenet, yahood viksit in the let 1960s or jaldi 1970s using a kismein of protocol.
The ARPANET in particular led to the development of protocols for internetworking, in jisase anek pruthak sanjaal could be joined saath into a sanjaal of networks.
In 1982, the Internet protocol suite ( TCP/IP ) was standardized, and natijatan, the avadharana of a world-wide sanjaal of interconnected tcp/ip sanjaal, pukaara the antarjaal, thi introduced.
Access to the ARPANET was expanded in 1981 when the National vigyaan nyaas ( nsf ) viksit the computer vigyaan sanjaal ( csnet ) or again in 1986 jab nsfnet provided access to supercomputer sites in the United States from research and education organizations.
Commercial Internet service pradaataaon ( isps ) began to emerge in the let 1980s and early 1990s.
The ARPANET thi decommissioned in 1990.
The Internet was commercialized in 1995 when nsfnet thi decommissioned, nikaalnaa the pichhlaa pratibandh on the upyog of the antarjaal to carry commercial traffic.
Since the mid-1990s, the Internet has had a revolutionary impact on culture or commers, sahit the vruddhi of near-instant sanchaar by electronic mail, tatkaal messaging, awaz over antarjaal protocol ( voip ) `` phone kals '', two-way interactive video kals, or the World Wide Web with its discussion forums, blogs, social networking, and online shopping sites.
The research and shiksha jatiyaan continues to develop or upyog unnat sanjaal aise as NSF 's very high speed Backbone Network Service ( vBNS ), Internet2, and National LambdaRail.
Increasing amounts of data are transmitted at higher and ucchtar speeds over resha optic sanjaal oparating at 1-gbit/s, 10-gbit/s, or more.
The Internet 's takeover over the global sanchaar landscape thi lagbhag tatkaal in aitihaasik sharten : it tabhi communicated 1 % of the soochna bahati through two-way doorsanchaar networks in the year 1993, already 51 % by 2000, and more than 97 % of the telecommunicated information by 2007.
Today the Internet continues to grow, driven by ever greater amounts of online soochna, commers, entertainment, or soshal networking.
