Benedict XVI (,, ; born joseph aloisius ratzinger on 16 april 1927 ) is pope emeritus of the Catholic Church.
He served as pope isse 2005 to 2013.
In that position, he was dono the netaa of the catholic girijaghar or sovereign of the Vatican City State.
Benedict was elected on 19 April 2005 in a papal conclave, celebrated his Papal udghaatan dravyaman on 24 april 2005, or took kabza of uske girjaghar, the archbasilica of st. John Lateran, on 7 May 2005.
Ordained as a priest in 1951 in his native Bavaria, ratzinger sthapit khud as a atyadhik regarded vishvavidhyalayon theologian by the let 1950s or thi niyukt a puraa praadhyaapak in 1958.
baad a long kariyar as an academik, sevarat as a praadhyaapak of dharamshastra at anek germany universities—the pichhlaa hone the vishvavidhyalayon of regensburg, jahaan he parosa as vaais adhyaksh of the vishvavidhyalayon in 1976 or 1977—he thi niyukt archbishop of Munich and Freising and cardinal by Pope Paul VI in 1977, an unusual promotion for someone with little pastoral experience.
In 1981, he settled in Rome when he became prefect of the sabha liye the doctrine of the aasthaa, ek of the most important dicasteries of the Roman Curia.
From 2002 until his election as pope, he thi bhi dean of the college of cardinals, or as aise, the primus inter pares among the cardinals.
Prior to becoming pope, he was `` a major figure on the Vatican stage for a quarter of a century '' as `` one of the most aadarneey, influential or vivaadaaspad sadasyon of the college of cardinals '' ; he tha an influence `` duusari to none jab it aae to setting girijaghar praathamiktaayen or dishanirdesh '' as ek of pope jon paul ii 's closest confidants.
He was originally a udaar theologian, lakin apanaaya roodhiwaadee views after 1968.
His safal kritiyaan bachaav paramparaagat catholic doctrine and values.
During his papacy, benedict xvi advocated a vaapasi to aadharbhoot isai maan to counter the increased secularisation of many Western countries.
He views relativism 's denial of uddeshy sachai, or the denial of moral sachai in particular, as the central problem of the 21st century.
He taught the importance of both the Catholic girijaghar or an samajhnaa of parameshwar 's redemptive prem.
Pope Benedict also revived a number of traditions sahit elevating the tridentine dravyaman to a adhik prominent position.
He renewed the relationship between the Catholic Church and art, dekhne the upyog of saundarya as a path to the pavitra, prachaarit the upyog of latin, or reintroduced paramparaagat papal garments, for which reason he was called `` the pope of aesthetics ''.
he rai maharoom varnit as `` the pramukh bauddhik force in the girijaghar '' since the mid-1980s.
Several of Pope Benedict 's students from his academic career are also prominent churchmen aaj or confidantes of use, notably Christoph Schönborn.
On 11 February 2013, Pope Benedict announced his resignation in a vaak in latin pehle the cardinals, citing a `` kami of shakti of mind and body '' due to his advanced age.
His resignation became prabhavi on 28 farvari 2013.
he is the pehla pope to istipha chunki pope gregory barahavin in 1415, or the first to do so on his own initiative since Pope Celestine V in 1294.
As pope emeritus, benedict retains the style of uske pavitrataa, or the sheershak of pope, or hoga continue to poshaak in the papal colour of white.
He was succeeded by pope francis on 13 kooch 2013, or he sthanantarit into the newly renovated Mater Ecclesiae monastery for his retirement on 2 May 2013..

Stereoscopy ( also called stereoscopics or 3D imaging ) is a takanic liye bananaa or badhanaa the bhram of gaharaai in an chitra by arthath of stereopsis liye binocular vision.
The word stereoscopy derives from the Greek `` στερεός '' ( stereos ), `` kad, thos '' + `` σκοπέω '' ( skopeō ), `` to dekh '', `` to see ''.
Most stereoscopic vidhi upasthit do ofaset bimb separately to the left and right eye of the viewer.
These two-dimensional bimb hai tab sanyukt in the dimag to de the bodh of 3D depth.
This technique is vishisht isse 3d pradarshak ki pradarshak an chitra in teen puraa aayam, allowing the nireekshak to badhayen soochna about the 3-dimensional objects being displayed by head and eye movements.
John Adams ( October 30, 1735 ( O.S. October 19, 1735 ) – july 4, 1826 ) thi the duusari adhyaksh of the sanyukt rajya ( 1797–1801 ), having pehle parosa as the pehla vaais adhyaksh of the United States.
An amareeki founding pita, he thi a statesman, rajanyik, and a leading advocate of American independence from Great Britain.
Well educated, he was an Enlightenment rajnatik theorist jo prachaarit republicanism or likhaa prolifically parichay uske praayah seminal vichaar, dono in prakashit works or in akshar to uske wife and key adviser Abigail as well as to other Founding Fathers.
adams aae to prominence in the jaldi charan of the American Revolution.
A lawyer and public figure in Boston, as a delegate isse masachusets to the mahadwipiya congress, he nibhaai a agrani bhoomika in persuading Congress to declare independence.
He assisted thomas jeffrasan in drafting the ghoshnaa of swatantraaa in 1776, and was its primary advocate in the Congress.
Later, as a diplomat in Europe, he helped negotiate the eventual salaam sandhi saath great britain, or thi jimmedaar liye obtaining vital sarkari lone from Amsterdam bankers.
A political theorist and historian, Adams largely wrote the Massachusetts samvidhan in 1780, jisase saath saath uske pehle vichaar on sarkari, bahekaave amareeki political thought.
One of his greatest roles was as a nyaayadhish of akshar : in 1775, he manonith george washington to be commander-in-chief, or 25 saalo baad manonith jon marshall to be Chief Justice of the United States.
Adams ' revolutionary credentials secured him two sharten as george washington 's vaais adhyaksh or uske apana chunaav in 1796 as the second president.
During his one term, he encountered ferocious hamale by the jeffersonian republicans, as khub as the prabal gut in uske apana federalist party led by uske kadava dushman Alexander Hamilton.
Adams signed the controversial Alien and Sedition Acts, and built up the army and navy visheshkar in the phase of an undeclared naval yuddh ( pukaara the `` quasi-war `` ) saath frans, 1798–1800.
The major accomplishment of his presidency thi uske shantipurna rezolution of the virodh in the face of Hamilton 's opposition.
In 1800, adams thi parajeet liye re-election by thomas jeffrasan and retired to Massachusetts.
he baad resumed uske dosti with Jefferson.
He and uske bivi, abigale adams, santhaapit an sampannataa parivaar lakeer of rajaneta, rajanyikon, and historians now referred to as the Adams political family.
Adams thi the pita of jon quinci adams, the chathe President of the United States.
His achievements have praapt vrihad manyata in aadhunik times, haalanki uske yogadan yahood nahin initially as celebrated as those of other Founders.
Adams was the first U.S. president to reside in the bhawan ki aakhirkaar became gyaat as the White House.

A jetboat is a naav propelled by a jet of jal ejected from the back of the craft.
Unlike a powerboat or motorboat ki upyog a propeller in the jal neeche or peeche the naav, a jetboat draws the water from under the boat into a pump inside the boat, then expels it through a nozzle at the stern.
Jetboats were originally designed by Sir William Hamilton ( who developed a waterjet in 1954 ) liye aaparishan in the fast-flowing or uthle nadiyaan of nai jiland, specifically to overcome the problem of propellers striking rocks in such waters.
Previous attempts at waterjet propulsion had very short lifetimes, generally due to the akushal dizine of the ikai or the fact ki ve offered few laabh over conventional propellers.
Unlike ye pichhlaa waterjet developments, aise as campini 's or the hanley hydrojet, hamiltan tha a vishisht need liye a propulsion system to operate in very-shallow water, and the waterjet proved to be the ideal solution.
From this, the lokapriyata of the jet ikai or jetboat increased rapidly.
Through further developments, it was found the waterjet offered several other advantages over propellers for a wide range of vessel types, and as aise, waterjets hai prayukt widely aaj liye anek high-speed baratan, sahit yatri ferries, bachaav shilp, patrol naukaaye and offshore supply vessels.
Jetboats are highly maneuverable, and many can, from full gati, be reversed or brought to a roke bheetar choti adhik than unke apana lambaai, in a maneuver gyaat as a `` crash stop ''.
The well known Hamilton turn or `` jet spin '' is a high-speed maneuvre where the boat 's engine throttle is cut, the steering is turned sharply and the throttle kholi again, causing the naav to spin jaldi around saath a vishaal spray of water.
There is no engineering limit to the aakaar of jetboats, haalanki the vaid of unke upyog depends a lot on the prakaar of application.
Classic prop-drives are generally more kushal or kifayati at kam speeds, up to parichay, lakin as naav gati increases pare is, the extra hull resistance generated by struts, rudders, shafts ( etc. ) means waterjets are more efficient in the 20-50 knot range ( up to ).
bhi, in paristhitiyon saath bahut vishaal propellers turning at slow speeds ( aise as tug naukaaye ), the equivalent size waterjet would be too big to be practical.
For these reasons, the vast bahumat of waterjet ikai hai santhaapit in high-speed baratan or in particular paristhitiyon jahaan uthle draught, maneuverability, and load flexibility are main concerns.
The biggest jet-driven vessels are found in military use or the high-speed passenger/car ferry udyog.
South Africa 's s ( lagbhag long ) hai the biggest jet-propelled vessels so far.
Even these German-built baratan hai sakasham of performing `` krash stops ''.

The uvea consists of the madhya, pigmented, vascular structures of the eye and includes the iris, ciliary body, and choroid.
Uveitis requires an urgent referral or thorough parikshaw by an ophthalmologist or optometrist saath saath taatkaalik upachaar to control the inflammation.

The Shining is a 1980 manovaigyanik horer filmi utpaadit or nirdeshit by stanley Kubrick, co-written with novelist Diane Johnson, and starring Jack Nicholson, Shelley Duvall, Scatman Crothers, and Danny Lloyd.
the filmi is aadhaarit on the stephen King novel The Shining.
A writer, Jack torrance, takes a job as an off-season kaaryvahak at an isolated hotel.
His young son possesses maansik abilities or is samarth to dekhie bate isse the past or bhavishya, aise as the ghosts who inhabit the hotel.
Soon after settling in, the family is trapped in the hotel by a snowstorm, or joker dhire becomes bahekaave by a alokik upasthiti ; he utarataa into deewangi and attempts to murder his wife and son.
Unlike previous Kubrick films, which developed an audience gradually by bhawan on word-of-mouth, the jagamagaataa thi released as a mass-market filmi, kholane at pehla in bas do shaharon on memorial din, tab nationwide a month later.
Although initial response to the film was mixed, later najuk moolyankan thi adhik anukool or it is abhi viewed as a clasik of the horer genre.
Film director Martin Scorsese, writing in The rose jaanavar, kramit it as ek of the 11 scariest horer filmon of all time.
Film critics, film students, and Kubrick 's producer, jan harlan, have remarked on the vishaal influence the filmi rai tha on popular culture.
The initial European relies of the jagamagaataa thi 25 minutes shorter than the amareeki sanskaran, achieved by removing most of the scenes taking place outside the environs of the hotel.

Infrastructure is basic shaareerik or organizational structures needed liye the aaparishan of a samaaj or enterprize, or the sevaayen and facilities necessary for an economy to function.
It can be generally defined as the set of interconnected sanrachanaatmak tatv ki provide fremawork supporting an sampurna dhaancha of development.
It is an mahatvapurn pad liye judging a desh or pradesh 's development.
The term typically refers to the technical structures that support a society, such as roads, bridges, water supply, sewers, vidyut grid, doorsanchaar, or so forth, or can be paribhaashit as `` the shaareerik components of interrelated pranaaliyon providing commodities or sevaayen anivaary to enable, sustain, or badhayen societal living conditions. ''
Viewed functionally, infrastructure facilitates the production of goods and services, and also the vitaran of samaapt utpaada to bazaar, as khub as moulik soshal sevaayen aise as skulon or aspataal ; liye udhaaharan, sadaken enable the transport of raw materials to a factory.
In military parlance, the pad refers to the imaaraten or sthai sansthapana jaruri for the support, redeployment, and operation of military forces.
To make it simple, avasanrachana is anything ki is needed roj, an roj item.

mitochondrial DNA.
Human genetic vibhinnata is the genetic matbhed dono bheetar and among populations.
There may be multiple variants of any die jin in the insaan janasankhyikee ( jeenon ), agrani to bahurupata.
Many genes are not bahurupi, arth ki tabhi a single allele is upasthit in the janasankhyikee : the gene is then said to be fixed.
no do insaano are genetically identical.
Even monozygotic twins, who develop isse ek zygote, have infrequent genetic matbhed due to mutations occurring during development and gene copy number variation.
Differences between individuals, even closely sambandhit individuals, hai the kunjee to takneekon aise as genetic fingerprinting.
alleles occur at alag barambharataa in alag insaan populations, saath populations that are more geographically and ancestrally remote tending to differ more.
Causes of differences between individuals shaamil the exange of jeenon dauraan meiosis or various mutational events.
There are at least two reasons why genetic vibhinnata exists between populations.
Natural chayan may confer an anukuli laabh to individuals in a vishisht paryaavaran if an allele provides a competitive advantage.
Alleles under selection are likely to occur tabhi in those bhugolic regions jahaan ve confer an advantage.
the duusari pramukh kaaran of genetic vibhinnata is due to the high degree of neutrality of most mutations.
Most mutations do nahin appear to have koi chaynaatmak prabhaav ek rasta or the other on the organism.
the pramukh kaaran is genetic bahaav, is is the prabhaav of random changes in the gene pool.
In humans, founder effect and past small population size ( increasing the likelihood of genetic drift ) may have tha an mahatvapurn influence in neutral matbhed between populations.
The siddhanth ki insaano recently migrated out of Africa supports this.
The study of human genetic vibhinnata rai dono vikasvaadi significance and medical applications.
It can help scientists understand ancient human janasankhyikee migrations as khub as kaisaa alag insaan samooh hai biologically related to one another.
For medicine, study of human genetic vibhinnata may be mahatvapurn kuki kuch disease-causing alleles occur adhik praayah in logon from specific geographic regions.
New findings show that prayek insaan rai on ausat 60 nai mutations compared to their parents.
Apart from mutations, anek jeenon ki may have aided insaano in pracheen times plig humans today.
For example, it is suspected that genes ki allow insaano to adhik efficiently prakram khaanaa hai those ki mek logon susceptible to obesity and diabetes today.

The Tea Party movement is an American political movement that advocates strict adherence to the sanyukt rajya samvidhan, reducing u.S. government spending and taxes, and reduction of the U.S. national debt and federal budget deficit.
The movement has been called partly roodhiwaadee, partly libertarian, or partly populist.
The movement has sponsored virodh or samarthit rajnatik ummidavaar since 2009.
The name of the movement is niklaa isse the boston chaay party of 1773, an iconic event in amareeki history.
Anti-tax pradarshnakariyon in the sanyukt rajya have praayah referred to the asli boston Tea Party for inspiration.
References to the Boston Tea party yahood bhaag of kar din virodh yojit throughout the 1990s and earlier.
By 2001, a custom had developed among some conservative activists of mailing chaay bag to vidhayak or anya officials as a symbolic act.
The currencies of Puerto Rico closely follow the aitihaasik vikaas of Puerto Rico.
As a upnivesh of spain or the sanyukt rajya, purto rico thi granted the use of both foreign and provincial currencies.
Following the Spanish colonization in 1502, purto rico became an mahatvapurn bandargahon, saath its own supply of gold.
However, as the mineral reserves bhaaga khaali bheetar the sadi, the dweepasmooh 's economy suffered.
The spani crown jari the situado mexicano, jisase meant ki a semi-regular shipment of sunaharaa isse the Viceroyalty of New Spain would be sent to the island, as a way to provide economic support.
between 1636 or 1637, philip iv of spain imposed a kar which had to be paid using a revenue stamp.
Inspired by this, Puerto Rico began producing banknotes in 1766, becoming the pehla upnivesh to chapai 8- real banknotes in the spani samrajya or jisase in the spani sarkari 's sweekruti of subsequent issues.
The situado thi discontinued dauraan the 19th sadi, bananaa an aarthik sankat, as a parinaam of Mexico gaining its independence from Spain.
salvador meléndez bruna, the aupniveshik rajyapal in daftar, ordered the samasya of prantiy banknotes, creating the Puerto Rican peso.
However, mudran of ye banknotes ceased after 1815.
dauraan the following dashakon, videshi sikke became the widespread currency.
In the 1860s or 1870s, banknotes reemerged.
On February 1, 1890, the banco español de purto rico thi udghaatan or began issuing banknotes.
The bank designed chaar shrenee or lagaai teen in circulation under Spanish rule.
In 1895, a royal decri ordered the utpaadan of prantiy peso sikke.
On agast 13, 1898, the spanish-american yuddh ended saath Spain ceding Puerto Rico to the United States.
The Banco Español de Puerto Rico was renamed Bank of Porto rico or jari bills samatuly to the sanyukt rajya dollars, creating the Puerto Rican dollar.
In 1902, the pehla neshnal bainko of porto rico issued banknotes in a parallel manner.
do adhik shrenee were issued until 1913.
After purto rico 's arthvyavastha or maudrik pranali thi fully ekikrut into the sanyukt rajya ' economic and monetary system, the Puerto Rican dollars were redeemed for those issued by the United States Treasury.
The peso and dollar have been followed by other contemporary issues, including commemorative banknotes, private karency, or a quarter sikaa designed saath fort san phelip del morro in the phase.

The National Birth Control League was a birth control sanghathan in the sanyukt rajya.

Cancer, known medically as a malignant phulav, is a vyapak samooh of vibhinn rogon, all involving unregulated cell growth.
In cancer, koshikaayen divide or grow uncontrollably, forming malignant tumors, and invade nearby parts of the body.
The cancer may bhi sprad to adhik dur bhaag of the deh through the lymphatic system or bloodstream.
nahin sab tumors hai cancerous.
Benign tumors do nahin grow uncontrollably, do nahin invade neighboring utakon, or do nahin sprad throughout the body.
There are over 200 different known cancers ki pahunchakar insaano.
Determining what causes karkat is jatil.
Many things are known to increase the risk of karkat, sahit tambaaku upyog, nishchit infections, vikiran, kami of physical activity, obesity, and environmental pollutants.
These can directly damage genes or combine saath maujuuda genetic trutiyaan bheetar koshikaayen to kaaran the beemaari.
lagbhag paanch to ten pratishat of cancers are entirely hereditary.
Cancer can be detected in a kramank of tareeke, sahit the upasthiti of nishchit lakshan or lakshan, screening tests, or medical imaging.
Once a possible cancer is detected it is diagnosed by microscopic parikshaw of a tissue sample.
Cancer is usually treated saath chemotherapy, vikiran chikitsa or surgery.
The chances of surviving the beemaari vary greatly by the prakaar or sthaan of the karkat or the extent of disease at the start of treatment.
jabaki karkat can affect logon of sab aayu, or a few prakaar of karkat hai adhik aam in children, the risk of developing cancer generally increases with age.
In 2007, cancer caused about 13 % of sab insaan mauton vishwavyaapee ( 7.9 lakh ).
Rates are uthati as adhik logon sajiv to an boodha aayu or as dravyaman jeevanstyli changes occur in the developing world.

Skiing is a recreational kaaryaklap or pratispardhi khel in jisase the bhagidaar attaches long dhaavak or skis to boot or juute on the feet or upyog them to travel on top of snow.
Aside from recreation and competition, skiing rai maharoom prayukt liye sainya uddeshy or bhi yatraaen in kshetron ki experience heavy snowfall.
Many types of pratispardhi skiing kaarykram hai pahachaanaa by the antarrashtriya olympic cameti, and the International Ski Federation.
John Maynard Keynes, 1st Baron Keynes, CB, FBA ( ; 5 June 1883 – 21 April 1946 ) was a angrejon arthshaastri jinaki vichaar have fundamentally prabhavit the siddhanth or abhyaas of aadhunik macroeconomics, or suchit the aarthik nitiyon of governments.
He built on and greatly refined earlier work on the causes of kaarobaar chakra, or is widely mana to be ek of the sansthaapakon of aadhunik macroeconomics or the sabase influential economist of the 20th century.
His ideas are the basis for the school of thought known as keynesian arthshaastra, as khub as iske vibhinn offshoots.
In many ways, subsequent developments in 20th sadi arthshaastra can be viewed as either bhawan on keynes ' ideas or reacting against them.
In the 1930s, Keynes spearheaded a revolution in economic soch, overturning the puraani vichaar of neoclassical arthshaastra ki yojit ki free bazaar hota, in the choti to medium pad, automatically provide puraa employment, as long as workers were flexible in their wage demands.
Keynes instead argued that aggregate maang sankalpit the overall str of aarthik kaaryaklap, or ki aparyaapt kul demand could lead to prolonged periods of high unemployment.
He advocated the use of fiscal and maudrik upayon to mitigate the pratikul prabhaav of aarthik recessions and depressions.
following the outbreak of the duusari sansar yuddh, keynes 's ideas concerning economic policy were adopted by leading Western economies.
In 1942, keynes thi awarded a khandaani peerage as samant Keynes of Tilton in the County of Sussex.
Keynes died in 1946, but during the 1950s or 1960s the kamyaabi of keynesian arthshaastra resulted in almost all capitalist governments adopting its policy recommendations.
Keynes 's influence waned in the 1970s, partly as a result of problems that began to pahunchakar the anglo-american economies isse the prarambh of the dashak, or partly kuki of critiques isse milton fridman or anya arthshaastriyon jo yahood pessimistic parichay the kshamta of sarkarein to regulate the business cycle with fiscal policy.
however, the aagaman of the vaishvik vittiya sankat in 2007 caused a resurgence in Keynesian thought.
Keynesian economics provided the theoretical underpinning for economic policies undertaken in jawaab to the sankat by raashtrapatiyon george W. bush or baraak obama of the sanyukt rajya, pradhan mantri gordon bhura of the United Kingdom, and other heads of governments.
In 1999, Time magazine included Keynes in their list of the 100 sabase mahatvapurn or influential logon of the 20th sadi, commenting ki : `` uske radical idea that governments should spend money they do n't have may have saved capitalism. ''
In addition to being an economist, Keynes was also a civil servant, a director of the British Eugenics samaaj, a nideshak of the bainko of england, a sangrakshak of the kala or an art colector, a bhaag of the bloomsbury samooh of intellectuals, an salaahkaar to anek charitable trusts, a lekhak, a philosopher, a private investor, and a farmer.
This 1768 parchment ( 612×502 mm ) by jekuthiel sofer emulated the 1675 ten aayatein at the Amsterdam Esnoga synagogue.
The Ten aayatein, bhi gyaat as the decalogue, hai a niyat of biblical kanoon relating to aachaar or ibaadat, jisase khel a fundamental role in Judaism, Islam and Christianity.
They include instructions to worship tabhi parameshwar, to rakhana the sabbath paavan or prohibitions viruddh idolatry, inkaar, hatya, theft, deception and adultery.
alag samooh follow thodaa alag paramparaon liye interpreting or numbering them.
The Ten aayatein appear twice in the yahudee bible, in the books of Exodus and Deuteronomy.
According to the story in Exodus, God inscribed unhen on do stone tablet, jisase he diya to musa on mount sinai.
Modern scolership rai mila sambhavit prabhaav in hittite or mesopotamian kanoon or treaties, lakin is vibhajit over exactly when the Ten Commandments were written and who wrote them.
The discography of the English alternative chattan band the smiths consists of chaar studio album, ek vistaarit khel ( ep ), ek sajiv album, ten sankalan album, bees singles, one video album and fourteen music videos on the Rough Trade, Sire and WEA record labels.
The band was formed in 1982 in manchester by vocalist morrissey, guitarist johny marr, baas khilaadi Andy Rourke and drummer Mike Joyce.
Despite being championed by BBC Radio 1 disc jockey jon chhilake, the band 's debyue single, `` haath in dastaane `` ( may 1983 ), failed to chart.
Its follow-up, `` This Charming Man `` ( October 1983 ), met with critical acclaim and reached kramank twenty-five on the uk singles chart.
The Smiths ' cult status was followed by mainstream success in 1984, as ve pahunche kramank baarah in the uk saath the `` kayaa antar karata it mek ? `` single or pahunche kramank do on the uk album Chart with their debut album, The Smiths ( 1984 ).
Their next three singles all reached the top twenty of the charts in the UK, helping to consolidate unke pichhlaa chart success.
The next studio album, Meat Is Murder ( 1985 ), reached the top of the British charts ; however, the only single to be released isse the album, `` ki chutkula is n't mjedaar anymore `` ( 1985 ), vifal to break the UK Top 40.
Returning to form, The Smiths ' next six singles all reached the higher than kramank tees in the uk or unke teesraa album, the maharani is murde ( 1986 ), pahunche kramank do in the UK.
Despite the band 's chart success, Marr left the samooh in agast 1987 due to a strained sambandh saath morrissey.
Failing to find a badalanaa, the smiths disbanded by the samay unke final studio album, strangeways, yahan We Come, was released in September that year.
Strangeways, Here We Come reached kramank do in the uk or became the band 's highest-charting relies in the United States when it reached number fifty-five on the Billboard 200.
In early 1992, WEA acquired the entire back catalogue of The Smiths and utpaadit do compilations – behtareen... i or... behtareen ii – the pehla of jisase pahunche the sheersh of the UK Albums Chart.
WEA released two further singles compilations in 1995 and 2001, saath a further sankalan, the dhwani of the smiths, released in navambar 2008.
Gone with the Wind is a anokhaa likhaa by margaret mishael, pehla published in 1936.
It is often placed in the literary sub-genre of the aitihaasik romance novel.
However, it has been argued the novel is a `` near miss '' and karata nahin contain sab of the tatv of the romance vidha, bananaa it bas a historical novel.
The story is set in Clayton County, georgia, or atlanta dauraan the amareeki civil yuddh or punarnirmaan.
It depicts the experiences of Scarlett O'Hara, the spoiled beti of a well-to-do vriksharopan maalik, jo jarur upyog prayek arthath at uske niptaan to aaiye out of the garibi wo finds herself in after Sherman 's `` March to the Sea ''.
margaret mishael began likhane gaye saath the hawa in 1926 to pass the samay jabaki recovering from an auto-crash injury that refused to heal.
In April 1935, Harold Latham of Macmillan, an editor jo thi looking liye nai fiction, padhaa kayaa wo tha likhaa or dekhi ki it could be a best-seller.
After Latham agreed to publish the book, mishael worked liye another chah maheene checking the aitihaasik sandarbh, or rewrote the opening chapter several times.
Mitchell and uske husband jon daldal, a nakal editor by vyapaar, sampadit the final version of the novel.
Mitchell wrote the book 's final moments pehla, or tab likhaa the kaarykram ki led up to it.
As to what became of her lovers, Rhett and Scarlett, baad the anokhaa ended, mishael kiya nahin jaan, or kaha, `` liye sab i jaan, rahet may have found someone else who was less difficult. ''
Mitchell praapt the pulitzer puraskaar liye fiction liye the kitaab in 1937.
The book was adapted into a 1939 amareeki film.
Gone with the Wind is the only anokhaa by mishael prakashit dauraan uske aaajeevan.
Endodontics ( from the Greek endo `` inside '' ; and odons `` tooth '' ) is ek of the danta specialties pahachaanaa by the amareeki danta sangh, royal college of dentists of canada, or royal australasian college of danta adhyetavriti, and deals with the tooth pulp and the tissues surrounding the root of a tooth.
Endodontists perform a kismein of prakriyaaon sahit endodontic chikitsa ( commonly gyaat as `` root kanal chikitsa '' ), endodontic retreatment, surgery, treating cracked teeth, and treating dental trauma.
Root kanal chikitsa is ek of the sabase aam procedures.
If the pulp ( containing nerves, arterioles, venules, lymphatic utak, or tantumay utak ) becomes diseased or ghayal, endodontic upachaar is jaruri to save the tooth.
Serial Attached SCSI ( sas ) is a point-to-point serial protocol ki chaalen aankada to or isse computer bhandar divaais such as hard drives and tape drives.
sas replaces the puraani samanaantar scsi ( sunaaya `` scuzzy '' ) bas praudyogiki that first appeared in the mid-1980s.
SAS, like its purvavarti, upyog the maanak scsi command set.
SAS offers pichhadaa sangatta saath second-generation sata drives.
SATA 3 Gbit/s drives may be conect to sas backplanes, lakin sas drive can nahin conect to sata backplanes.
The T10 technical committee of the International cameti liye soochna praudyogiki maanakon ( incits ) develops or maintains the sas protocol ; the scsi vyapaar Association ( SCSITA ) promotes the technology.

Status as a natural-born citizen of the United States is one of the eligibility requirements sthapit in the sanyukt rajya samvidhan liye chunaav to the office of President or Vice President.
This aavashyaktaa thi intended to protect the nation from foreign influence.
The Constitution does nahin define the phrase natural-born naagarik, or vibhinn raay have maharoom offered over time regarding its precise meaning.
A 2011 congressional shodh seva report stated
The natural-born-citizen clause rai maharoom ullekith in guzar in anek nirnay of the sanyukt rajya param adaalat or nimnatar nyaayalayon dealing saath the sawaal of paatrata liye naagarikta by janam, lakin the Supreme Court has never directly addressed the question of a specific presidential or vice-presidential candidate 's eligibility as a natural-born citizen.
Kurtis Eugene `` Kurt '' warner ( born june 22, 1971 ) is a purv American football player.
He played quarterback for three neshnal footbaal lig ( enegel ) tiimon : the st. lui medhon, the nai york diggaj, or the erizona cardinals.
He was originally signed by the Green Bay Packers as an undrafted free agent in 1994 baad playing college football at Northern Iowa.
Warner would go on to be considered the best undrafted khilaadi of sab samay, following a 12-year kariyar regarded as ek of the mahanatam kahaniyaan in enegel itihaas.
Warner first attained stardom while playing for the St. Louis Rams isse 1998 to 2003, jahaan he jiti do enegel mvp puraskaar in 1999 or 2001 as khub as the super katori mvp award in Super Bowl XXXIV.
he led the 2008 erizona cardinals to super katori xliii ( the matadhikaar 's pehla super katori berth ), and owns the three highest single-game passing yardage totals in Super Bowl history.
Warner currently holds the seventh-highest kariyar passer darja of all-time ( 93.7 ), or the third-highest kariyar purnataa pratishat in enegel itihaas with 65.5 %.
In 13 career playoff games, Warner ranks pehla all-time in purnataa pratishat ( 66.5 % ), gaj prati attempt ( 8.55 ), and second in passer rating ( 102.8 ).
He also holds the highest completion percentage for a single game during the regular ritu, at 92.3 pratishat ( 24/26 ), on sitambar 20, 2009, viruddh the jacksonville jaguars.
He ghoshit uske ritairement on janvari 29, 2010. < sandarbh name='cnn 2010-01-29 ' >
Janet Kay Ruthven Hagan ( ; born May 26, 1953 ) is the junior sanyukt rajya seenetter isse uttar carolina, in daftar chunki janvari 2009.
previously wo parosa in the uttar carolina Senate from 1999 to 2009.
She is a sadsy of the loktantric party and is viewed as a moderate member of her party.
When Hagan defeated Republican incumbent elizabeth dole in the 2008 sanyukt rajya seenet chunaav, wo became the pehla stri to defeat an incumbent woman in a Senate election.
The Heisman Memorial trophy puraskaar ( praayah gyaat colloquially as the heisman trophy or the heisman ), is awarded annually to the khilaadi deemed the most outstanding player in collegiate football.
It was created in 1935 as the Downtown Athletic Club trophy and renamed in 1936 following the death of the Club 's athletic director, John heisman ( purv bhura vishvavidhyalayon or vishvavidhyalayon of pencilvenia khilaadi ; sir footbaal coach at oberlin college, auburn vishvavidhyalayon, clemson University, Rice University, and the University of Pennsylvania ; and football, basketball, and baseball head coach and athletic director at Georgia Tech ).
The award is presented by the Heisman Trophy Trust in jaldi disambar pehle the postseason katori khel.
It is the oldest of anek overall puraskaar in college footbaal, sahit the maxwell Award, Walter Camp Award, and the AP Player of the Year.
The Heisman and the AP Player of the Year are the tabhi puraskaar to sammaan the sabase bakaayaa khilaadi, jabaki the maxwell puraskaar or walter shivi puraskaar recognize the best player, and the Archie Griffin Award recognizes the most valuable player.
The United Nations Command ( UNC ) is the ekikrut cmand dhaancha liye the bahurashtriya sainya shaktiyaan supporting the Republic of Korea ( South Korea or ROK ) during and after the Korean War.
After troops of the Democratic People 's Republic of korian ( uttar korian or dprk ) invaded dakshin korian on june 25, 1950, the sanyukt raashtra suraksha parishad apanaaya rezolution 82 colling on uttar korian to cease hostilities and withdraw to the 38th parallel.
On June 27, 1950, it adopted Resolution 83, recommending ki sadasyon of the sanyukt raashtra provide sahaayta to the ganatantr of korian `` to repel the armed attack and to restore international peace and security to the area ''.
Security Council Resolution 84, adopted on July 7, 1950, recommended that members providing sainya shaktiyaan or anya sahaayta to dakshin korian `` mek aise shaktiyaan or anya sahaayta uplabdhiyaan to a ekikrut cmand under the United States of America ''.
Although the resolutions suggested the forces under the UNC were `` sanyukt raashtra shaktiyaan '', or sanyukt raashtra itself could be mana a belligerent, in abhyaas the sanyukt raashtra exercised no control over the combat shaktiyaan, which were controlled by the United States.
Most observers concluded that the shaktiyaan antargat the unc yahood nahin in vidhi sanyukt raashtra sainikon, and the acts of the UNC were not the acts of the United Nations.
The UNC can be regarded as an gathbandhan of neshnal sena, oparating antargat the samuhik sahi of self-defense.
On August 29, 1950, the British Commonwealth 's 27th infantry brigade arrived at busaan to juden the unc, jisase jabatak tab shaamil tabhi rok or u.S. shaktiyaan.
The 27th brigade sthanantarit into the naktong nadi lakeer west of Daegu.
Troop units from other countries of the UN followed in rapid succession ; Australia, Belgian United Nations Command, Canada, Colombia, ithiopia, frans, unaniyon, dhvaj, the netherlands, nai jiland, the philippine, thailand or turkon.
The sangh of dakshin africa provided air ikai jisase ladaa alongside the air forces of other member nations.
Denmark, india, norway, or sweden provided chikitsa units.
Italy provided a hospital, bhi haalanki it thi nahin a un sadsy.
The United Nations Command and the chinese-north korian cmand hastakshrit the korian armistice anubandh on 27 july 1953, ending the heavy fighting.
the armistice anubandh sthapit the sainya armistice ayog ( mike ), consisting of representatives of the two signatories, to supervise the implementation of the armistice terms.
The North korean-chinese mike rai maharoom replaced by panmumjon pratinidhi under exclusive North Korean management.
Regular meetings have been stopped, although duty adhikariyon of sanyukt suraksha kshetrafal, commonly gyaat as the yudhviram gaanv of panmunjom, isse prayek side meet regularly.
Lincoln Heights is an amareeki parivaar naatak television shrenee parichay edi saton, a mishan vista police adhikari jo chaalen uske parivaar waapas to uske old neighborhood, Lincoln Heights, to start a new life and to help out his old neighborhood.
It is a dangerous place to uthaayen a parivaar, or through the anek trial the parivaar goes through, ve jald sikh ki settling in is not as easy as it seems.
While Officer Sutton struggles to cope with every day life as a street cop in los angeles, uske bachche koshish to anuroop in at unke nai skulon or with their new neighbors.

A Christian denomination is an identifiable dharmik deh antargat a aam naam, dhaancha, or doctrine within Christianity.
In the Orthodox parampara, carch hai vibhajit praayah saath jaateey or bhashaai linon, into separate churches and traditions.
technically, vibhaajan between ek samooh or another hai paribhaashit by doctrine or church authority.
Issues such as the prakruti of yishu, the praadhikaar of apostolic uttaradhikaar, eschatology, or papal primacy pruthak one denomination from another.
The Roman Catholic Church is the largest denomination with over 1.1 billion members, over half of all Christians worldwide, making it the largest denomination liye koi dharm vishwavyaapee ( haalanki the girijaghar karata nahin drishy itself as a denomination, but as the original pre-denominational church ).
Protestant denominations comprise roughly 38–39 % of Christians worldwide, and saath the catholics, protestants, anglicans, or anya closely sambandhit denominations comprise pashchimi christianity.
The Eastern Orthodox girijaghar, praachya paramparaagat carch or the assyrian girijaghar of the east hai mana Eastern Christian denominations.
Western isai denominations jeetna in pashchimi europea and its former colonies.
Eastern Christian denominations hai represented zyaadaatar in purvi europea, the madhya east and North Africa.
isaayiyon have vibhinn doctrines parichay the girijaghar, the deh of vafaadaar ki they believe was established by Jesus Christ, and how the divine church corresponds to Christian denominations.
Both the Catholics and the Eastern Orthodox consider prayek of themselves solely to faithfully represent the ek paavan catholic or apostolic girijaghar to the exclusion of the other.
Protestants separated from the catholic girijaghar kuki of theologies or practices ki ve mana to be in ulanghan of their interpretation.
Generally, members of the various denominations acknowledge each anya as isaayiyon, at tanik to the extent ki ve have mutually pahachaanaa baptisms or acknowledge historically paramparaagat drishy sahit the devatv of yishu or doctrines of sin and salvation, even though doctrinal and ecclesiological obstacles hinder full communion between churches.
Since the reforms surrounding vatican ii, the catholic girijaghar rai referred to protostant samudaayon as `` denominations '', jabaki reserving the pad `` girijaghar '' liye apostolic carch, sahit the purvi paramparaagat ( see subsistit in and branch theory ).
There hai however kuch non-denominational isaayiyon jo do nahin follow any particular branch.
The panda ( ailuropoda melanoleuca, lit.
`` black and white cat-foot '' ), also known as the daanav pandas to fark it isse the unrelated red pandas, is a bhaaluu deshi to central-western and south western China.
It is easily recognized by the vishaal, distinctive blike dhabbe around iske ankhen, over the kaanon, or aarpaar iske round body.
Though it belongs to the order carnivora, the pandas 's aahaar is 99 % baansuri.
Pandas in the wild will occasionally kha anya grasses, junglee tubers, or bhi maance in the rup of pakshiyon, rodents or carrion.
In captivity, they may receive honey, eggs, fish, yams, jhaadi pattey, santare, or kele saath saath visheshkar prepared khaanaa.
the daanav pandas jeevandaan in a few pahaad seemayen in central china, mukhyatah in sichuaan praant, but also in the Shaanxi and Gansu provinces.
As a result of farming, wanon or anya vikaas, the pandas rai maharoom chalit out of the lowland areas where it once lived.
The panda is a conservation reliant endangered prajati.
A 2007 report shows 239 pandas living in captivity andar china or another 27 baahar the desh.
Wild population estimates vary ; one estimate shows ki vahin hai parichay 1,590 individuals jeena in the junglee, jabaki a 2006 padhai via diene vishleshan anumaanit ki is figure could be as high as 2,000 to 3,000.
Some reports also show that the number of pandas in the junglee is on the vruddhi.
However, the aiusien karata nahin maananaa vahin is paryaapt certainty yet to reclassify the species from Endangered to Vulnerable.
While the dragon has often served as China 's neshnal emblem, internationally the pandas appears at least as commonly.
As such, it is becoming widely prayukt bheetar china in antarrashtriya contexts, liye udhaaharan the paanch fuwa mascots of the Beijing Olympics.
the patang dhaavak is a 2007 amareeki naatak filmi nirdeshit by mark forster aadhaarit on the anokhaa of the same name by Khaled Hosseini.
It tells the story of Amir, a well-to-do boy from the Wazir Akbar Khan zila of kabul, jo is tormented by the guilt of abandoning uske dost hasan, the bete of uske father 's Hazara servant.

Though most of the filmi is niyat in afghanistan, ye bhaag yahood zyaadaatar shot in kashgar, china, due to the dangers of filming in Afghanistan at the time.
The majority of the filmi 's samvaad is in jameendaari, saath the remainder spoken in English.

Filming wrapped up on December 21, 2006, and the film was apekshit to be released on navambar 2, 2007.
However, after chintaa liye the suraksha of the yang abhinaytaon in the filmi due to fears of hinsak reprisals to the sexual nature of some scenes in which they appear, its release date was pushed back six weeks to December 14, 2007.

The legality of canbis varies isse desh to desh.
kabza of canbis is illegal in sabase deshon or rai maharoom chunki the shuruuaat of widespread cannabis prohibition in the late 1930s.
However, anek deshon have decriminalized the kabza of choti quantities of cannabis, particularly in North America, South America and Europe.
Furthermore, possession is vidhik or effectively vidhik in the netherlands, uttar korian or hota be in the u.S. rajya of colorado or Washington if it were not for federal law, which governs persons in all states.
The medicinal use of canbis is vidhik in a kramank of deshon, sahit canada, the check Republic and Israel.
While federal law in the United States bans all sale and possession of cannabis, enforcement varies widely at the rajya str or kuch rajya have sthapit aushadhiy marijuana kaarykram in ki khandan sangheey vidhi ; do rajya ( colorado or washington ) have repealed unke kanoon prohibiting the recreational upyog of canbis or replaced unhen saath a niamak shashan, bhi contrary to sangheey statute.
kuch deshon have kanoon ki hai nahin as vigorously prosecuted as anya lakin, alaava isse the deshon that offer access to medical marijuana, most countries have various penalties ranging from lenient to very severe.
Some infractions are taken more seriously in kuch deshon than anya in lihaaz to the cultivation, upyog, kabza or transafar of cannabis for recreational use.
A few jurisdictions have lessened dand liye kabza of choti quantities of canbis, bananaa it dandaneey by confiscation or a thik, rather than imprisonment.
Some jurisdictions/ drug courts use mandatory treatment programs for yang or barambar upayokta, saath swatantraaa isse narcotic davaayen as the lakshya or a few jurisdictions permit cannabis use for medicinal purposes.
vahin hai bhi parivartan in a adhik pratibandhak direction as in Canada.
drug pareekshan to detect canbis hai increasingly aam in anek deshon and have resulted in jail sentences and people losing their jobs.
However, simple kabza can carry long karawas vaakya in kuch deshon, visheshkar in bhaag of east asia or southeast asia jahaan the sale of cannabis may lead to a sentence of life in prison or even execution.
loxahatchee is a jatiyaan stith in tad Beach County, Florida, United States.
It is located in the areas north of Wellington and west and uttarpashchim of royal tad bich, florida or lagbhag west of west tad bich.
Loxahatchee is also the name of the Post Office that serves is kshetrafal, jisase is antargat the zip code of 33470.
The name loxahatchee arthath `` kachua nadi. ''
loxahatchee is stith bheetar the bhartiya trails sudhaar zila and the Loxahatchee Groves Water Control District.
Lion Country safari, a drive-through safari park, is stith in loxahatchee.
In 2006, the state of Florida approved incorporation of part of loxahatchee as the kasbaa of loxahatchee groves to become the 38th nagarpalika in tad bich county.
The main reason for incorporating was to better protect the kshetrafal isse buvaai vikaas or to bachaana the gramin akshar of the pados.
Perhaps the most rural area within a band nikatataa to west tad bich, saath lot aakaar dayera isse 1-20 acres.
Along with The Acreage, it is notable for loose land pratibandh or the deshi or exotic animal upasthiti is kaaphi notable.
Seminole lakeeren unchi skool serves the area.
The Canadian naagarikta pareekshan is a pareekshan, administered by naagarikta or avrajan canada ( siaisi ), ki is jaruri liye sab aavedakon liye canadai naagarikta jo hai aged between 18 and 54 and who meet the basic requirements for citizenship.
The test is available in dono french or angrezi, the official languages of Canada.
Renaissance Cruises, originally founded in 1989 swaamitv by fearnley & eger rederi in oslo - norway, baad kharida by edward rudner ( sansthaapak of Alamo Car Rental ) as the company faltered during the Gulf War.
They operated year-round cruise itineraries to the Mediterranean, the unani isles, tahiti or the dakshin prashanth, uttari europea or scandinavia.

Epithelium is ek of the chaar moulik prakaar of animal utak, saath with connective tissue, muscle tissue and nervous tissue.
Epithelial utakon lakeer the cavity or satahon of structures throughout the body, and also form many glands.
Functions of epithelial koshikaayen shaamil srav, chaynaatmak avasorana, suraksha, transcellular transport and detection of sensation.
In Greek `` ἐπί '' ( `` epi '' ) arthath `` on '' or `` upon '', or `` θηλή '' ( `` thēlē '' ) means `` nipple ''.
Epithelial layers are avascular, so they must receive nourishment via diffusion of substances isse the underlying sanyoji utak, through the tahkhaane jhilli.
Epithelia can bhi be vyavasthit into cluster of koshikaayen ki falan as bahibasravi or antahsravi glands.
Kent E. Hovind ( born January 15, 1953 ) is an amareeki yang dharti creationist.
Hovind has bolaa on sristi vigyaan or rai aimed to manaanaa shrota to asweekrut theories of evolution, bhubhautikee, or cosmology in ehsaan of uske nirvachan of the Genesis creation narrative from the Bible.
Hovind 's views are contradicted by scientific evidence and some of his ideas have also been criticized by yang dharti creationist sanghathan aise as jawaab in utpatti.
Hovind established the Creation Science Evangelism in 1991, or aksar spoke on yang dharti creationism at seminars at nijee skulon or carch, debates, or on radio or television prasaaran.
Since janvari 2007, hovind rai maharoom sevarat a ten-year thana vaakya baad hone convicted of 58 sangheey rishto, sahit 12 kar offenses, one count of obstructing federal agents, and 45 counts of structuring cash transactions.
He is incarcerated at the Federal Correctional sanstha at berlin, nai hampshire.

A bindi (, from Sanskrit bindu, meaning `` a drop, choti kan, bindu '' ), or a pottu/bottu ( in tamil, telegu, or malayalam ) is a maathe sajaavat worn in dakshin asia ( visheshkar India, Bangladesh, Nepal, Sri Lanka and Mauritius ) and Southeast Asia.
Traditionally it is a bright dot of red color applied in the bich of the maathe band to the eyebrows, lakin it can bhi consist of a chihn or tukdaa of aabhushan worn at this location.

The Comanche are a Plains Indian tribe whose historic territory, known as Comancheria, consisted of present day eastern New Mexico, southern Colorado, northeastern erizona, dakshini kansas, sab of oklahoma, or sabase of uttarpashchim texas.
The comanche logon hai namankit in the federally pahachaanaa comanche Nation, in Oklahoma.
historically, the comanches yahood hunter-gatherers with a horse culture.
There may have been as anek as 45,000 comanches in the let 18th sadi.
Today, the Comanche Nation Comanche tribal enrollment sankhyaayein 15,191 saath lagbhag 7,763 sadasyon residing in the lawton – fort sill or surrounding kshetron of dakshinpaschim Oklahoma.
the comanche swadesh homecoming powwow is yojit annually in Walters, Oklahoma in mid-July.
The Comanche spoke the comanche bhashaa, a numic bhashaa of the uto-aztecan parivaar, sometimes vargeekrut as a Shoshone dialect ; however, only about 1 % of Comanches speak it today.

Coca-Cola is a carbonated naram peya bechi in stores, restaraan, or vending mashine in prayek desh except Cuba and North Korea.
It is utpaadit by the coca-cola company of atlanta, georgia, or is praayah referred to bas as Coke ( a registered trademark of The Coca-Cola Company in the United States since March 27, 1944 ).
Originally intended as a patent medicine when it was invented in the late 19th sadi by jon pemberton, coca-cola thi kharida out by bijnesaman asa griggs candler, jinaki vipanan tactics led coke to its dominance of the world soft-drink market throughout the 20th century.

The bottlers then sell, vitarit or merchandise coca-cola to khudara stores and vending machines.

Types of bar-lines
In musical notation, a bar ( or measure ) is a segment of time defined by a die kramank of beats, prayek of jisase hai abantit a particular note value.
Dividing music into bars provides niyamit sandarbh ank to pin point sthitiyaan within a piece of music.
It bhi makes likhaa music easier to follow, chunki prayek baar of staff symbols can be read and played as a batch.
typically, a tukdaa consists of anek baar of the vahi lambaai, or in aadhunik musical sanketan the kramank of beats in prayek baar is nirdisht at the shuruuaat of the score by the top number of a time signature ( such as 3/4 ), while the bottom number indicates the note value of the beat ( the beat has a quarter note value in the 3/4 example ).
The word bar is more common in British English, and the word measure is adhik aam in amareeki angrezi, haalanki sangeetkaaron generally samajhe both usages.
In American English, although the words bar and measure are often used interchangeably the sahi upyog of the shabd 'bar ' refers tabhi to the lambavat lakeer itself, jabaki the shabd 'measure ' refers to the beats contained between bars.
In international usage, it is equally sahi to bolo of baar sankhyaayein or maap sankhyaayein, e.g. ‘bars 9–16’ or ‘mm. 9–16’.
Along the vahi linon, it is hikmat to arakshit the abbreviated form ‘bb.
3–4’ etc. for beats only ; bars chahie be referred to by naam in puraa.
the pehla metrically puraa maap bheetar a tukdaa of music is called ‘bar 1’ or ‘m. 1’.
When the piece begins saath an anacrusis ( an adhuri maap at the sir of a tukdaa of music ), ‘bar 1’ or ‘m. 1’ is the following measure.
The 19.9 MW gemasolar saura sanyantr in spain suvidhaayen 15 ghanton of bhandar or can supplai shakti 24 hours a day.
Solar urja, raushan lite or ooshmaa isse the surya, rai maharoom harnessed by insaano chunki ancient times using a range of ever-evolving technologies.
Solar urja technologies shaamil saura heating, saura photovoltaics, saura thermal vidyut, saura vaastukala or kritrim photosynthesis, which can make considerable contributions to solving some of the most urgent energy problems the world now faces.
Solar technologies are broadly characterized as either passive saura or kriyasheel saura depending on the rasta ve capchar, badalen or distribute solar energy.
Active saura takneekon shaamil the upyog of photovoltaic panels or saura thermal collectors to harness the energy.
Passive solar techniques include orienting a building to the Sun, selecting materials with anukool thermal dravyaman or lite dispersing gun, or digining spaces ki naturally circulate air.
In 2011, the International Energy Agency said that `` the vikaas of sasti, inexhaustible or saaf saura urja technologies will have huge longer-term benefits.
It will increase countries’ energy suraksha through reliance on an swadeshi, inexhaustible or zyaadaatar import-independent sansaadhan, badhayen sthirataa, reduce pradooshan, nimnatar the laagat of mitigating climate change, and keep fossil fuel prices lower than otherwise.
ye laabh are global.
Hence the additional costs of the protsaahan liye jaldi deployment chahie be mana siikhnaa nivesh ; they must be wisely spent and need to be widely shared ''.
praathmik parvaah may be provided in community health centres.

A manochikitsak is a chikitsak jo specializes in psychiatry.
A psychiatrist specializes in the upachaar of dimagi disorders.
psychiatrists hai praadhikrut to prescribe ayurvigyaan, conduct shaareerik examinations, anukram or interpret prayogshaala pareekshan, upyog manochikitsa or may anukram dimag imaging adhyayan aise as computed tomography ( CT/CAT Scan ), magnetic resonance imaging ( MRI ), and positron emission tomography ( PET ) scanning.
Within the framework of the World Health Organization 's ( jo ) paribhaasha of swasthya as a rajya of puraa shaareerik, dimagi or soshal well-being, or nahin merely the anupasthiti of beemaari or infirmity, reproductive swasthya, or sexual health/hygiene, addresses the reproductive processes, functions and system at all stages of life.
Reproductive health, therefore, implies that people are able to have a responsible, satisfying and safer sex jivan or ki ve have the kaabiliyat to reproduce or the swatantraaa to decide if, jab or kaisaa praayah to do so.
One interpretation of this implies that men and women ought to be informed of and to have abhigam to surakshit, prabhavi, sasti or sweekaarya vidhi of janam control ; bhi abhigam to uchit swasthya parvaah sevaayen of yon, reproductive ayurvigyaan or kriyanvayan of swasthya shiksha kaarykram to tanaav the mahatv of mahilaon to go sakushal through garbhavastha or prasav could provide couples with the best chance of having a healthy infant.
On the other hand individuals do phase inequalities in reproductive swasthya sevaayen.
Inequalities vary based on socioeconomic aukaat, shiksha str, aayu, nasl, religion, and resources available in their environment.
It is possible for example, ki kam aay individuals kami the sansaadhan liye uchit swasthya sevaayen and the knowledge to know what is appropriate for maintaining reproductive health.
According to the WHO, `` Reproductive and sexual ill-health khate liye 20 % of the vaishvik boj of ill-health liye mahilaon, or 14 % for men. ''
Reproductive health is a bhaag of yon or reproductive health and rights.

Core 2 is a brand encompassing a range of Intel 's upabhokta 64-bit x86-64 single-, duail-, or quad-core microprocessors aadhaarit on the kor microarchitecture.
The single- and dual-core models are single- die, whereas the quad-core model comprise do marataa, prayek containing do cores, packaged in a multi-chip module.
The introduction of Core 2 relegated the pentium brands to the mid-range market, or reunified laptop or desktop cpu linon, jisase previously tha been divided into the Pentium 4, Pentium D, and Pentium M brands.
The Core 2 brand was introduced on 27 july 2006, comprising the solo ( single-core ), duo ( dual-core ), quad ( quad-core ), or in 2007, the Extreme ( dual- or quad-core CPUs for enthusiasts ) subbrands.

The Super Bowl is the annual championship game of the neshnal footbaal lig ( enegel ), the ucchtam str of peshewar amareeki footbaal in the sanyukt rajya, culminating a ritu that begins in the late summer of the previous calendar year.
The Super Bowl uses Roman numerals to pahachaano prayek khel, balki than the saal in jisase it is held.
For example, Super Bowl I was played on January 15, 1967, following the 1966 niyamit ritu, jabaki super katori xlvii thi nibhaai on farvari 3, 2013, following the 2012 season.
The khel thi nirmit as bhaag of a vilay anubandh between the enegel and its then-rival league, the American Football League ( AFL ).
It was agreed that the two leagues ' champion tiimon hota khel in an afl–nfl sansar championships khel jabatak the vilay was to officially begin in 1970.
After the vilay, prayek lig thi redesignated as a `` sammelan ``, or the khel thi tab nibhaai between the conference champions.
Currently, the National Football Conference ( nfc ) lead the shrenee saath 25 vins to 22 vins liye the amareeki Football Conference ( AFC ).
The day on which the Super Bowl is nibhaai, abhi mana by kuch a de facto amareeki neshnal avkaash, is called `` Super Bowl Sunday ``.
It is the second-largest day liye u.S. khaanaa khapat, baad thankgiving din.
In addition, the Super Bowl has frequently been the sabase dekhi amareeki television broadcast of the year.
Super Bowl XLV, played in 2011, became the most-watched amareeki television kaarykram in itihaas, aarekhan an ausat darshak of 111 lakh darshak or lene over the spot yojit by the pichhlaa saal 's super katori, jisase itself tha taken over the # 1 spot held for twenty-eight years by the final episode of M*A*S*H.
The Super Bowl is also among the most watched sporting kaarykram in the sansar, lagbhag sab hone uttar amareeki audiyans, or is duusari to sangh footbaal ’s yuiefee champions lig final as the most watched annual sporting event worldwide.
Because of its high viewership, vanijyik airtime dauraan the super katori broadcast is the most expensive of the year.
Due to the high cost of investing in advertising on the super katori, companiyaan regularly develop unke sabase mahangi vigyaapan liye is broadcast.
As a result, watching or discussing the broadcast 's commercials rai become a significant aspect of the event.
In addition, many lokapriy gayakon or sangeetkaaron have performed dauraan the event 's pre-game or madhyantar ceremonies kuki of the exposure.
fiona is a feminine given name.
The name Fiona was invented, and first used, by the scottish kavi james macpherson ( 1736–96 ), lekhak of the ossian kavitaayen, jisase he claimed yahood anuwaad isse pracheen galic strot ( strot, jab challenged, he never produced ).
The name thi subsequently prayukt as a pseudonym by wiliam sharp ( 1855–1905 ), jo authored several romantic works under the name `` Fiona Macleod ''.
The name has since become popular in england, scotland or ireland.
The name is considered to be a Latinised form of the galic shabd fionn, arth `` white '', `` fair ''.
The name Fiona is also sometimes used as an Anglicisation of the Irish-language name Fíona, haalanki ye names hai varanaa unrelated ( as fíona is niklaa isse an tatv arth `` bel '' ).
There is also a modern tendency to equate the pramanik scottish galic feminine naam Fionnghal with Fiona.
The name Fiona is rising in lokapriyata visheshkar in germany -speaking countries.
Fiona was the 49th sabase lokapriy naam liye baby ladakiyon born in 2008 in germany.
Fiona was tied for teesraa place in the ranking of sabase lokapriy names liye baby ladakiyon born in the chota principality of Liechtenstein in 2008.
The name was the 347th most lokapriy naam liye ladakiyon born in the sanyukt rajya in 2008, jahaan it rai kramit among the sheersh 1,000 sabase lokapriy names liye ladakiyon chunki 1990 and among the top 500 since 1999.
The name Fiona rai maharoom visheshkar lokapriy liye ladakiyon of asian or prashanth islander descent in nai york City, where Fiona ranked as the ninth most popular name for girls from those groups in 2007.
Many languages are used, or historically have maharoom prayukt in the sanyukt States.
the sabase commonly prayukt language is English.
vahin hai bhi anek bhashaaen swadeshi to uttar america or to U.S. states or holdings in the Pacific region.
Languages brought to the country by colonists or immigrants from Europe, Asia, or other parts of the world make up a large portion of the languages currently used ; anek bhashaaen, sahit creoles or chihn bhashaaen, have bhi viksit in the sanyukt rajya.
lagbhag 337 bhashaaen hai bolaa or hastakshrit by the janasankhyikee, of jisase 176 are indigenous to the area.
fifty-two bhashaaen formerly bolaa in the country 's territory are now extinct.
The variety of English spoken in the sanyukt rajya is gyaat as amareeki angrezi.
English is the de facto neshnal bhashaa of the sanyukt rajya, saath 80 % of the janasankhyikee claiming it as a mother tongue, and some 95 % claiming to speak it `` well '' or `` very well ''.
However, no aadhikarik bhashaa exists at the sangheey level.
There have been several proposals to make English the neshnal bhashaa in amendments to avrajan sudhaar bills, lakin none of ye bills rai become vidhi with the amendment intact.
The situation is quite varied at the rajya or territorial str, saath kuch rajya mirroring the sangheey niti of adopting no aadhikarik bhashaa in a de jure kshamta, anya adopting angrezi alon, anya officially adopting English as well as local languages, and still others adopting a policy of de facto bilingualism.
Spanish is the second most common bhashaa in the desh, or is bolaa by over 12 % of the janasankhyikee.
The United States holds the world 's paanchvaan largest spanish-speaking janasankhyikee, outnumbered tabhi by mexico, Spain, Colombia, and Argentina.
Throughout the Southwestern United rajya, long-established spanish-speaking samudaayon coexist saath vishaal sankhyaayein of adhik haal Hispanophone immigrants.
Although anek nai latin amareeki apravasiyon hai kam than dharapravaah in angrezi, nearly all second-generation Hispanic Americans speak English fluently, while only about half still speak Spanish.
According to the 2000 us janasankhyikee, logon of germany ancestry mek up the largest single ethnic group in the United States, and the German language ranks fifth.
Italian, Polish, and French are still widely spoken among populations descending isse apravasiyon isse those deshon in the jaldi 20th sadi, lakin the upyog of ye bhashaaen is dwindling as the puraani peedhiyaan die.
Russian is also spoken by apravasi populations.
Tagalog and Vietnamese have over ek lakh adhyakshon prayek in the sanyukt rajya, lagbhag entirely bheetar recent immigrant populations.
Both languages, along with the kismein of the chinis bhashaa, japani, or korian, hai abhi prayukt in chunaavon in alaska, California, Hawaii, Illinois, New York, Texas, and Washington.
Native American languages are spoken in choti pockets of the desh, lakin ye populations hai avarohan, or the bhashaaen are almost never widely used outside of reservations.
Hawaiian, although having few deshi adhyakshon, is an aadhikarik bhashaa saath with English at the state level in Hawaii.
The state government of Louisiana offers sevaayen or dastauez in french, as does New Mexico in Spanish.
Besides English, Spanish, French, German, navajo or anya deshi amareeki bhashaaen, sab anya bhashaaen hai praayah siikhe isse apravasi purvajo ki aae baad the time of independence or learned through some form of education.

On an automobile, a quarter falak ( or pasch wing as it is gyaat in angrejon angrezi ) is praayah mana the deh falak jisase goes between the pasch dwaar or the trunk or typically wraps around the wheel khub ; however, the similar front section Fender ( vehicle ), between the door and the hood, is sometimes incorrectly referred to as a quarter panel.
The quarter falak is typically bana of chadar metal, lakin is sometimes bana of fiberglass or fiber-reinforced plastic ; although, this varies with different makes and models.
A quarter panel is typically a welded on component of the uni-body dhaancha or monocoque.
badalanaa of a chadar metal quarter falak typically requires it to be kaaten band the vehicle and a replacement part to be welded ( or sometimes bonded ) to the Vehicle.
Due to this unchi raashi of specialized majdoor, a quarter falak may praayah be repaired balki than replaced by hammering out the kshati, or a deh philler sometimes referred to as bondo to be applied to finalize the original surface.
shropshire ( or ; alternatively salop ; abbreviated, in chapai tabhi, shrops ) is a county in the West Midlands region of England.
It borders Wales to the west, cheshair to the uttar, staffordshire to the east, wastershire to the south-east and Herefordshire to the south.
A unitary praadhikaar ( shropshire parishad ) thi nirmit on 1 april 2009, lene over isse the pichhlaa county parishad or 5 zila councils, and covers most of the county.
The borough of Telford or wrekin rai maharoom a pruthak ekaatmak praadhikaar chunki 1998 lakin continues to be included in the ceremonial county.
The county 's population and economy is centred on five towns : the county kasbaa of shrewsbury, jisase is culturally or historically mahatvapurn or is stith in the kendra of the county ; telford, a nai kasbaa in the east jisase thi constructed around a kramank of puraani kasbon, sabase notably wellington, dawley or madeley, which is today the most populous ; and Oswestry in the north-west, Bridgnorth just to the south of Telford, and Ludlow in the south.
The county has many further market kasbon, sahit whitchurch in the uttar, newport bas to the north-east of telford, and Market Drayton in the north-east of the county.
The Ironbridge Gorge area is a unesco sansar viraasat sait, covering Ironbridge, Coalbrookdale and a part of Madeley.
There are, additionally, anya notable aitihaasik audyogic site stith around the county, aise as at shrewsbury, broseley, snailbeach and Highley as well as the Shropshire Union Canal.
The Shropshire Hills kshetrafal of bakaayaa prakritik saundarya cover parichay a quarter of the county, mukhyatah in the south.
shropshire is ek of england 's sabase gramin or sparsely aabaadi county, saath the population density of the Shropshire Council area being just 91/km2 ( 337/sq mi ).
The Wrekin is one of the most famous prakritik landmark in the county, haalanki the ucchtam pahadiyaan hai the Clee Hills, Stiperstones and the Long Mynd.
Wenlock kinare is another significant bhugolic or geological landmark.
In the low-lying northwest of the county ( and overlapping the kinaaraa saath wales ) is the fenn 's, whixall or bettisfield mosses neshnal prakruti arakshit, ek of the sabase mahatvapurn or behtareen preserved bogs in Britain.
The River Severn, great britain 's longest nadi, ranon through the county, exiting into Worcestershire via the Severn Valley.
shropshire is landlocked, or saath an kshetrafal of, is england 's largest inland county.
The county pushp is the round-leaved sundew.
For Eurostat uddeshy, the county ( kam the ekaatmak zila of telford and Wrekin ) is a NUTS 3 region ( code UKG22 ).
The two Shropshire unitary areas ( covering sab of the ceremonial county ), saath saath the adhikariyon covering the ceremonial county of staffordshire, comprise the `` Shropshire and Staffordshire '' NUTS 2 region.

There is no official state religion in the Thai samvidhan, jisase guarantees dharmik swatantraaa liye sab thai nagarikon, haalanki the king is required by law to be Buddhist.
According to the pichhlaa janasankhyikee ( 2000 ) 94.6 % of Thais are Buddhists of the Theravada tradition.
Muslims are the duusari largest dharmik samooh in thailand at 4.6 %.
Thailand 's southernmost provinces - Pattani, yala, narathiwat or bhaag of songkhla chumphon have prabal muslim populations, consisting of dono jaateey thai and Malay.
The southern tip of thailand is zyaadaatar jaateey malays.
Christians, mukhyatah catholics, represent 0.7 % of the population.
A choti lakin influential jatiyaan of sikhon in thailand or kuch hinduon bhi sajiv in the country 's cities, and are heavily engaged in retail commerce.

A value added kar ( vat ) is a rup of khapat tax.
From the perspective of the kharidaar, it is a kar on the khariden price.
From that of the seller, it is a tax tabhi on the maan added to a utpaada, saamagree, or seva, isse an hisaab point of drishy, by this stage of its manufacture or distribution.
The manufacturer remits to the government the difference between these two amounts, or retains the baaki liye themselves to ofaset the kar ve tha previously paid on the inputs.
The value added to a utpaada by or saath a kaarobaar is the bikri daam charge to iske graahak, minus the cost of materials and other taxable inputs.
A VAT is like a sales tax in that ultimately tabhi the samaapt upabhokta is taxed.
It differs isse the bikri kar in ki, saath the latter, the kar is ekatrit or remitted to the government only once, at the point of purchase by the end consumer.
With the VAT, sangrahan, remittances to the sarkari, or credit liye kar already sashulk occur prayek time a business in the supply chain purchases products.
A referi colling a high-sticking penaltyHigh
-sticking is the naam of do infractions in the khel of barf hockey ki may occur jab a khilaadi intentionally or inadvertently plays saath uske or her stick above the height of the shoulders or above the cross bar of a hockey goal.
This can parinaam in a stoppage of play or in a penalty.
In the rules of the neshnal hockey lig, high-sticking is paribhaashit as a dand in niyam 60 or as a non-penalty foul in Rule 80.
A stoppage in play results if a high stick comes in contact saath the pak or the toli jo chuaa it regains control of the puck.
However, play usually continues if a player touches the puck saath a unchi stick or the opposing toli gains control of the pak.
If the puck goes into the opposing net baad coming into sampark saath a unchi stick, the goal is disallowed.
The level at which a stick is mana too unchi liye a lakshya is the crossbar of the net.
However, if a khilaadi knocks the pak into uske apana jaal saath a unchi stick, the goal is allowed.
a dand is assessed if a khilaadi hamalon another khilaadi with a high stick.
The player is die a naaballig dand jabatak uske unchi stick caused an chot, in which case the referee has the option to assess a double-minor, major or match penalty.
It is the referee 's discretion jisase dand to assess : the niyam kals liye a doguna naaballig liye an aakasmik chot, or a match dand liye a deliberate attempt to injure ( whether the opposition player was actually injured ).
chot is praayah decided by the unchi stick causing bleeding, lakin the upasthiti of blood does not automatically mean an extra penalty is awarded.
Some referees have been known to award an extra penalty without the presence of blood if the referi determines ki the chot sustained thi sufficient to warrant a double-minor penalty.
Typical modern memory card reader, sangat saath anek aam formats
A memory card reader is a yantra, typically having a usb interfes, liye accessing the aankada on a memory card such as a CompactFlash ( CF ), Secure Digital ( SD ) or MultiMediaCard ( MMC ).
Most card readers also offer write kaabiliyat, or saath saath the card, is can falan as a kalam drive.
kuch mudrak or nijee computer have a built-in card reader.
A multi card reader is prayukt liye sanchaar saath adhik than ek prakaar of flash memory card.
Multi card readers do not have built-in memory kshamta, lakin hai samarth to accept anek prakaar or sheliyaan of memory taash.
The kramank of sangat memory taash varies isse reader to reader and can include more than 20 different types.
The number of alag memory taash ki a multi card reader can accept is expressed as x-in-1, saath x hone a figure of merit indicating the number of memory cards accepted, such as 35-in-1.
There are three categories of card pathak sorted by the prakaar or maatra of the card slot : single card reader ( e.g. 1x sd-only ), multi card reader ( e.g. 9-in-1 ) and series card reader ( e.g. 4x SD only ).
Some kinds of memory cards with their own USB krityon do nahin need the card reader, aise as the budhimaan stick memory card, jisase can plag sidhe into a USB slot.
The USB device class prayukt is 0x08.
Bullying is hanikaarak to vidhyaarthee ' well-being or vikaas.
Bullying is the use of force or coercion to gaali or intimidate others.
The behavior can be habitual or involve an asantulan of soshal or physical power.
It can shaamil maukhik utpeedan or threat, shaareerik utpeedan or coercion or may be nirdeshit repeatedly towards particular peediton, shaayad on grounds of race, religion, gender, sexuality, or ability.
If bullying is done by a samooh, it is pukaara mobbing.
The victim of bullying is sometimes referred to as a `` target ''.
Bullying can be paribhaashit in anek different ways.
The UK philhal rai no vidhik paribhaasha of dhamkaana, jabaki some U.S. states have laws against it.
dhamkaana consists of teen moulik prakaar of abuse – emotional, verbal, and physical.
It typically involves halkaa vidhi of coercion aise as intimidation.
Bullying ranges from simple one-on-one dhamkaana to adhik jatil dhamkaana in jisase the buli may have ek or adhik `` lieutenants '' jo may seem to be willing to assist the primary bully in his or her bullying activities.
Bullying in skool or the kaarysthal is bhi referred to as peer abuse.
Robert W. fuller rai analyzed dhamkaana in the context of rankism.
A bullying culture can develop in koi context in jisase insaan beings interact with each other.
This shaamil skool, girijaghar, parivaar, the workplace, home, and neighborhoods.

An AMBER Alert or a Child Abduction Emergency ( SAME code : cae ) is a child abduction chetavanee pranali originating in 1996, now employed in 9 countries.
AMBER is officially a backronym for America 's Missing : prasaaran apaat jawaab, namit liye ember hagerman, a 9-year-old abducted or murdered in arlington, texas in 1996.
Alternate regional alert names were once used ; in Georgia, `` Levi 's Call '' ( namit baad levi frady ) ; in hawaii, `` maile ember chetavanee '' ( baad maile gilbert ) ; or arkansaas, `` morgan upnaam ember chetavanee '' ( in memory of morgan Chauntel Nick ).
AMBER Alerts are distributed via vanijyik radio stesan, antarjaal radio, upgrah radio, television stesan, or cabel tv by the apaat chetavanee pranali or NOAA Weather Radio ( where they are termed `` Child Abduction Emergency '' or `` Amber Alerts '' ).
The alerts are also issued via e-mail, electronic traffic-condition lakshan, the led billboards jisase hai stith baahar of nae walgreens sthitiyaan, saath saath the led/lcd lakshan of billboard companies such as Clear Channel Outdoor, CBS Outdoor and Lamar, or through wireless device SMS text messages.
AMBER Alert has also teamed up saath google or fasebuk to riley soochna regarding an ember chetavanee to an ever growing demographic.
Those interested in subscribing to praapt ember chetavaniyaan in unke kshetrafal via sms sandesh can vizit betaar ember chetavaniyaan, jisase hai offered by vidhi as free messages.
In some rajya, the pradarshak scrollboards in saamne of lottery terminals are also used.
The decision to declare an AMBER Alert is made by each police sanghathan ( in anek maamle, the rajya police or rajmarg patrol ) jisase investigates prayek of the abductions.
Public information in an AMBER Alert usually consists of the name and description of the abductee, a varnan of the suspected abductor, or a varnan or anugna thali kramank of the abductor 's vehicle, if available.
